UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You have proven your value to our efforts in Warsong Gulch. Continue to rage against the Silverwing Sentinels! Bring me more marks of honor!',objectives_loc4='You obtained a Warsong Mark of Honor for your last task, talk to me again, and you gain your reward.' WHERE entry=8293;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Kill 8 Mana Wyrms; they are located close to the Burning Crystals that are adjacent to the tower and gazebo.  Return to Magistrix Erona at the tower on Sunstrider Isle when you are done.',offerrewardtext_loc4='For your toubles you may choose your reward.' WHERE entry=8325;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The tower and surrounding areas should now be relatively secure, though only for the time being.  You have done well in providing us with a buffer of security, but we will need to reassert control over the entire isle if we are to survive here in the long run.  This will involve tackling much greater threats than errant mana wyrms and lynxes.$B$BTake this, $N - you will no doubt make good use of it for the tasks to come.' WHERE entry=8326;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Magistrix Erona told me you\'d be along quick enough, $N. The Falthrien Academy to our west - the huge floating building with the ornate spires - is in bad shape. You\'re going to be leading the effort to recapture it from one of the Wretched - a $R who has forever succumbed to their basest cravings.$B$BI hope you\'re ready to work. This is not only going to be a lesson about danger, but also of what happens when you forsake the realities of who you are.' WHERE entry=8327;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='As you advance within your class, you will want to take advantage of the training that your class trainer can provide you.  For young warriors here on Sunstrider Isle, your trainer is Jesthenis Sunstriker.  Speak with Jesthenis and see what training he has available for you.  The things he will teach do have a cost, so bring some coin with you.$B$BJesthenis - as with all the trainers on Sunstrider Isle - is inside the Sunspire on the lower level.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Jesthenis Sunstriker - the warrior class trainer - inside the Sunspire on Sunstrider Isle.' WHERE entry=8329;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done - I knew you\'d be perfect for the task.  Once it\'s safe to make use of our outdoor facilities on the isle, I\'ll be putting these things to good use.$B$BLike I mentioned, please feel free to keep the satchel.  Also, you may find this piece of armor to be useful.  Consider it ample compensation for a simple task performed dutifully!' WHERE entry=8330;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='While the deaths of the tenders give me no joy whatsoever, it does show me that you\'re ready for the most important task you\'ll do here on Sunstrider Isle. Take this and put it to good use; you\'ll need good items and sharp wits for the task ahead. Our reassertion of control over the island depends on it.' WHERE entry=8334;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Felendren\'s head... you are to be commended, $N.  You\'ve succeeded where others, like Felendren, have utterly failed.  Perhaps you are truly ready to be a contributing member of $R society.$B$BYour success here means that you are capable of surviving the greater threats that lurk in Eversong... and believe me, there are plenty to face.' WHERE entry=8335;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Splendid - these will do nicely.  I\'ve been doing quite a bit of thinking on the current malaise Sunstrider Isle suffers under.  One possible course of action I had pondered was to collect these arcane slivers from the beasts on the isle.  In doing so, they could be experimented on; this would provide a potential source of culpability.$B$BAnyway, I will tend to the research.  Allow me to place this incantation on you.  I believe you\'ll make good use of it!' WHERE entry=8336;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This is... most interesting.  And when I say interesting, I mean more disturbing than anything else.$B$BOur efforts to reassert control over the isle in the time following the destruction of the Sunwell have been a challenge.  I suspect that whatever foul source is corrupting the isle is at the heart of it all; this sliver may be of some aid in uncovering what\'s really going on.$B$BYou were wise to bring this to me, $N. Take this as compensation for your diligence.  Thank you.' WHERE entry=8338;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, $N - thank you for sharing your experience at the Shrine of Dath\'Remar. First off, you should be commended for your sense of duty and respect - it will serve you well not only here, but in all of Azeroth as well.$B$BAs for the odd sensation, it is no doubt a contributing part of the taint that has befallen Sunstrider Isle. We shall keep an eye on it; thank you for alerting us to it!' WHERE entry=8345;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well hello there, $C! I heard that a resourceful young $R formerly in the service of Magistrix Erona might be making their way down here to help us Outrunners out. We certainly welcome the help, especially from someone who\'s proven to be so competent.$B$BI hope you\'re interested in running an errand or two for us.' WHERE entry=8347;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, I do appreciate the prompt delivery.$B$BWhile you\'re here, please make yourself comfortable.  If you haven\'t done so already, feel free to get a hearthstone and bind yourself here.  Using a hearthstone will allow you to recall to an inn once every hour.  If you ever lose your hearthstone, simply return to any inn - an innkeeper will gladly get you a new one.' WHERE entry=8350;
UPDATE locales_quest SET EndText_loc4='Do the "train" for Talvash' WHERE entry=8355;
UPDATE locales_quest SET EndText_loc4='Flex for Innkeeper Allison' WHERE entry=8356;
UPDATE locales_quest SET EndText_loc4='Dance for Innkeeper Saelienne' WHERE entry=8357;
UPDATE locales_quest SET EndText_loc4='Do the "train" for Kali Remik' WHERE entry=8358;
UPDATE locales_quest SET EndText_loc4='Flex for Innkeeper Gryshka' WHERE entry=8359;
UPDATE locales_quest SET EndText_loc4='Dance for Innkeeper Pala' WHERE entry=8360;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The Battle in Alterac Valley rages on, $N! Have you done your part as of late, $N?' WHERE entry=8383;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The battle for Alterac rages on! You must return to Alterac Valley and once more drive the invaders out of Frostwolf territory, $N!' WHERE entry=8387;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='x',objectives_loc4='x' WHERE entry=8444;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='x',objectives_loc4='x' WHERE entry=8445;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work, $N.' WHERE entry=8463;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Some of the Deadwood furbolgs wear a distinctive headdress that may be used as a means of proof in thinning their numbers. Bring me a feather from any headdresses you acquire; for every set of five you bring me, you will earn recognition amongst the Timbermaw.' WHERE entry=8466;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Some of the Deadwood furbolgs wear a distinctive headdress that may be used as a means of proof in thinning their numbers. Bring me a feather from any headdresses you acquire; for every set of five you bring me, you will earn recognition amongst the Timbermaw.' WHERE entry=8467;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That scoundrel, Thaelis, finally met his fate.  Good job, $N.  Things should be quiet with the Wretched for a while.' WHERE entry=8468;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='The Winterfall are known to carry spirit beads to ward against foul spirits. These beads have clearly failed in their purpose, as the Winterfall themselves are the agents of corruption. Bring to me these spirit beads from fallen Winterfall furbolgs; for every set of five you bring me, you will earn recognition amongst the Timbermaw.' WHERE entry=8469;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done well, $N.  With our arcane sanctums not operating at full capacity, these power cores will go a long way in supplementing our needs.' WHERE entry=8472;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So, it is done. Curse these times that have driven us to desperate measures... and curse our enemy, the Scourge!$B$BLearn this, $N. Our lands must be protected, no matter what the cost. We shall prevail!' WHERE entry=8473;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This... this pendant.  I gave it to Old Whitebark after his people helped us rebuild our village.I guess this means he\'s...<clears her throat as she regains her composure.>I appreciate you bringing this to me, $N.  There is something I\'d like to ask of you.' WHERE entry=8474;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We don\'t anticipate the Scourge letting up on their attacks any time soon, but we still appreciate any help we get guarding the Scar.' WHERE entry=8475;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good work, $N. With more people like you we\'ll soon restore our lands to their former glory.' WHERE entry=8476;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='There\'s truth to the rumors! This hammer is light and strong at once; I shall manage to complete several of my unfinished projects.  And of course, I\'ll let you have first pick.' WHERE entry=8477;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ya, $Gdad:mon;.  Zul\'Marosh had this comin\'.  He burn down Ven\'jashi\'s village.  I kill many Amani before they put me in this cage.  I hide something in the sand, my gift for you now.$B$BAh... ah, the poison... it spread now, mon.  Time to rest...' WHERE entry=8479;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Great job, $N. Let\'s show the Wretched what we\'re made of!' WHERE entry=8480;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Are you sure you found these on a night elf? They\'re clearly written in Dwarven...$B$BFrom what I can understand of this letter, whoever wrote this did not cause the malfunction, but rather was sent here as a spy to observe the results of it. They call our endeavors reckless and dangerous... but who?$B$BOf course! That envoy from Ironforge! We were fools to trust anyone belonging to the Alliance!' WHERE entry=8482;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So, the deed is done. Excellent job.$B$BWord has been passed to the ranger general and believe me, the dwarves will pay dearly for their treason.$B$BYou\'ve been of great service to your people today, $N.' WHERE entry=8483;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $N. Now that we have the wraiths under control we can send someone in to assess the damage. Hopefully this wasn\'t anything permanent.' WHERE entry=8486;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent. I will cast an augmentation enchantment on the samples so I can more clearly analyze the taint on the soil.' WHERE entry=8487;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Protect Apprentice Mirveda from the Scourge ambush.',offerrewardtext_loc4='My endeavors are hopeless, $N. The very nature of the soil has been altered... the taint is irreversible. Thank you for your assistance. I\'ll need to ask one last task of you.' WHERE entry=8488;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent.  The defenses should hold off the Scourge a bit longer.  Thank you for lending us a hand, $N.' WHERE entry=8490;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These will do perfectly, $N. Take this piece of armor as a reward. I\'ll be able to make more with the pelts you brought me.' WHERE entry=8491;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='The Alliance Needs More Light Leather!' WHERE entry=8512;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='$C, I need your help. In the Molten Core there are these stones, singed Corestones to be precise, that we need to harvest for the Ahn\'Qiraj war effort. I\'m told that our blacksmiths and engineers can put them to good use, so that\'s where you come in. I need you to go into the Molten Core and gather up as many of these corestones as you can. Of course, you\'ll want to talk thirty-nine of your closest friends along with you.',objectives_loc4='Bring 50 singed corestones to Commander Stronghammer at the airfield in Dun Morogh.' WHERE entry=8530;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Welcome to the World of Warcraft!$B$BAs special thanks for purchasing the World of Warcraft Collector\'s Edition, turn in this gift voucher to Marsilla Dawnstar at the Sunspire on Sunstrider Isle.  You\'ll then be given a gift: a little companion to join you on your quest for adventure and glory.$B$BThanks again, and enjoy your stay in the World of Warcraft!',objectives_loc4='Bring the Sunstrider Isle Gift Voucher to Marsilla Dawnstar at the Sunspire on Sunstrider Isle.' WHERE entry=8547;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='The Horde Needs More Peacebloom!' WHERE entry=8550;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='$N - your name has passed my ears as one seeking out a master in the ways of the $C.  You look capable enough, but I seek more than just looks from my students.  You must be ready to delve where others fear to look to gain your power.  I will teach you, but I will not tolerate failure.$B$BThere will be monetary costs associated with your training, but you should be more concerned with the cost your mind is willing to make.  If you are ready, we shall begin.' WHERE entry=8563;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You returned? Interesting. As you can see I am still collecting for the Ahn\'Qiraj \'war effort\'. Which means that I need you to once again go out and collect a stack of mageweave bandages for me. I look forward to your return, $C.' WHERE entry=8608;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='A thousand years has passed and just as it was fated, one stands before me. One who shall lead their people to a new age.$BThe Old God trembles, $N. Oh yes, it fears your faith. Shatter the prophecy of C\'Thun.$BIt knows you come, champion - and with you comes the might of Kalimdor. You have only to let me know when you are prepared and I shall grant you The Scepter of the Shifting Sands.' WHERE entry=8742;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Ah, here for additional supplies for yourself, are you?  Well, I can certainly understand the need for additional materiel... just take a look around if you need any proof.$B$BI\'ll issue you some additional supplies, but you\'ll need to give me an appropriate number of commendation signets in exchange.  You won\'t receive any recognition for surrendering the signets in this manner, but you might find something useful that will help keep you alive when battle is finally upon us.' WHERE entry=8846;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Thank goodness for you, $C! Those slimy Grimscale murlocs have pirated away my cargo! It\'s bad enough that the Wretched have stolen what little magical goods I had, but the murlocs took the rest! What has this land come to?$B$BCould you retrieve my cargo? I can\'t expect that you\'d be able to get all of it back, but I\'ll be grateful for any of it at this point. It was the Grimscale murlocs in the huts, just to the west and south of the anchorage on the Golden Strand, I\'m sure of it!$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='You did it! You\'ve saved me from ruin and delivered my revenge upon those disgusting creatures!$B$BNow if I can just get these pretty rangers here to help me with this cargo, I\'ll finally get out of here! I\'ll have to come back when Velendris has retaken the shipyard.$B$BHere, take this coin. It\'s what little I can afford, and the least that I can do to reward your efforts.' WHERE entry=8886;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh you sweet, sweet $C! I had no idea that those disgusting Grimscale murlocs had also pirated away with my navigation rudders! Without them, I would have no chance of navigating the seas again once we retake the anchorage and repair the ship.$B$BThank you very much! Here, take this coin as a sign of my appreciation.' WHERE entry=8887;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The magister was concerned for my wellbeing? How sweet; I wish that he had shown such an interest before, when we were at the Spire.$B$BThat doesn\'t matter now. Please listen carefully, $C, as I have a favor to ask of you.' WHERE entry=8888;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I am grateful to you for your assistance, but saddened to hear that some of my fellow apprentices have fallen to their addiction.$B$BWith the power to the Spire cut off, I think I\'ll stay here a while and see if things calm down long enough for me to sneak in and retrieve their remains.' WHERE entry=8889;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='No! I was too late. It is all my fault.$B$BMy investigation into purifying alternative magical sources got out of hand before I could put a stop to it. If only I had gone myself... or that they had listened to me, and heeded my warnings!$B$BI have blood on my hands, $C. I thank you, though, for putting to rest the tortured souls of my former apprentices. It is some small consolation that they will not linger in that state where a Blood Elf is better off dead.' WHERE entry=8890;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Here it is, $N, the proof of my crime. This journal contains all of my ill-conceived studies.$B$BHeedless of the warnings, I continued my research, until it was almost too late. Then, when I grasped my error, I did what I could. But by then, some of my pupils had already gone too far. I evacuated the Spire to get them away from the corruption, but in my haste, forgot to shutdown the power sources.$B$BI will burn this tome so that no one else falls prey to its contents. I only wanted to help the sin\'dorei.' WHERE entry=8891;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'ll teach them not to mess with us.  Good work, $N.' WHERE entry=8892;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, I suppose that will have to do, now won\'t it? Thanks for the help, $C. I can only hope to get this mess completely cleaned up before the Magister returns to Duskwither Spire.$B$BTake this pocket change; it\'s not much but it\'s all that I have at the moment. Feel free to dispatch a few more of the beasties on your way out, if you\'d be so kind.' WHERE entry=8894;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $N.  I\'ve been expecting this letter.' WHERE entry=8895;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Are you sure you found these notes on a Night Elf, then?  Most of them are written in the Dwarven...$B$BProspector Anvilward!  He was sent here from Ironforge on a diplomatic mission.  I should\'ve known his interest in our Arcane Sanctums was a bit excessive.  $N, find the dwarf in the North Sanctum and take care of him.  Oh, and be discrete about it.',objectives_loc4='Find and kill Prospector Anvilward in the North Sanctum and report back to Aeldon Sunbrand in Eversong Woods.' WHERE entry=8896;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Valthalak\'s soul was stored in this amulet.  In our greed we foolishly split it into three parts, not knowing the curse that would await us.$B$BThe only way to stop Valthalak\'s spell is to put the medallion back together.  Return to Deliana and tell her that Bodley is her only hope for finding the remaining pieces.$B$BI, for once, shall rest in peace.  I wish you the best of luck, and you shall need it!',objectives_loc4='Speak to Deliana in Ironforge.' WHERE entry=9030;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='They\'re gone now. Scared the breeches out of them with a well-placed fireball! Unfortunately for me, they threw our precious cargo into the river.' WHERE entry=9035;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The book is completely soaked. Instructor Antheol\'s not going to like this at all.$B$BHere, take this money. I have an idea.' WHERE entry=9062;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You say those two incompetent fools bribed you to lie to me? You\'ve done very well in coming to me, $N.' WHERE entry=9064;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent job, $N. Don\'t worry, they\'re not stuck in that form permanently.  Their apprenticeship, however, won\'t be restored until they earn it back.' WHERE entry=9066;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re quite the energetic young woman, aren\'t you?$B$BThis all looks very adequate.  You certainly deserve compensation for gathering up all of this for me, and something a little extra I think.$B$BOh, I almost forgot, here\'s an invitation to the party.  And, $C, next time that you drop in make sure to dress up in something a little more... festive.' WHERE entry=9067;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You defeated him after all!  Undoubtedly my men softened him up for you.$B$BI jest, $C.  You\'ve done well.  You\'ll make a name for yourself if you keep your nose clean.' WHERE entry=9076;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Look around you. Things aren\'t exactly in order.$B$BWe have a severe malfunction at the West Sanctum. Let us do our best to prevent matters from getting worse.' WHERE entry=9119;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Welcome volunteer!  We\'re running low on supplies here, but the blood elves have promised us materiel assistance.  That\'s where you come in.$B$BTake this bill of lading over to Skymaster Sunwing. He\'ll have further instructions for you on how best to get up to Silvermoon City.',objectives_loc4='Deliver Quartermaster Lymel\'s Bill of Lading to Skymaster Sunwing in Tranquillien.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Lymel wants you to head up to Silvermoon City and bring back her goods. huh? Sure. I can get you there quickly... for a small fee, of course.' WHERE entry=9130;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Purchase a flight to Silvermoon City and deliver Quartermaster Lymel\'s Bill of Lading to Sathren Azuredawn in Silvermoon City.',offerrewardtext_loc4='What\'s this? Has Lymel\'s rotting brain finally slid out of her head? She wants all of this!?$B$BDid you bring anyone with you to help take it back?' WHERE entry=9133;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='It doesn\'t look as if you have a cart or a beast of burden with you, so I\'d better send you back only with what you can carry.  If you\'ve spoken with Skymaster Sunwing at Tranquillien, then you should get this to Quartermaster Lymel as soon as possible by flying back.$B$BTake these goods for final inspection to Skymistress Gloaming just outside Silvermoon City\'s Shepherd\'s Gate.',objectives_loc4='Bring Quartermaster Lymel\'s Goods to Skymistress Gloaming just outside Silvermoon City\'s Shepherd\'s Gate.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Back down to Tranquillien in the Ghostlands, then? Sure, I can get you there fast!' WHERE entry=9134;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='It all checks out as far as I can tell.  Seems to me that the Forsaken have put their backs to the wall for us and we owe them, even if they are all ugly and rotting.$B$BSo, the question is, have you already spoken to Skymaster Sunwing in Tranquillien?  If so, then this can be as simple as you paying the small fare and quickly flying back.$B$BLet me know when you\'re ready.',objectives_loc4='Purchase a flight back to Tranquillien in the Ghostlands and deliver Quartermaster Lymel\'s Goods to Quartermaster Lymel at Tranquillien in the Ghostlands.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, I guess if he said that the rest of it will be coming quickly overland, then I\'ll take him at his word.  He\'s certainly never failed to provide the goods in the short time that we\'ve been working together.$B$BThank you, $N, you\'re a credit to the sin\'dorei!  Here take this coin... it\'s done nothing but jingle around in my pocket all day.' WHERE entry=9135;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We\'re surrounded here, $C.  The outlying villages have all been overrun by the Scourge!$B$BYou must head northeast to Suncrown Village immediately and deal with the nerubian Scourge menace.  You can\'t miss them - they\'re spider-like creatures.$B$BThere\'s no time to waste.... Quel\'Thalas must be reclaimed!',offerrewardtext_loc4='Outstanding! But, there\'s much to be done before the Scourge menace is completely driven from mighty Quel\'Thalas!$B$BHere, take this coin... it\'s not much, but you\'ve earned it.' WHERE entry=9138;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Your success at Goldenmist Village takes us another step closer to taking our land back. Don\'t fool yourself though, $C; this fight is far from over.$B$BHere, you\'ve more than earned this. You may need it when you go up against Windrunner Village.' WHERE entry=9139;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done it, $N. You\'ve broken the Scourge hold on the three villages! Now we can focus our forces with greater ease against the Scourge on the Dead Scar and south at Deatholme.$B$BHere, take your choice of any one of these. I trust that you\'re not going anywhere? We can really use your continued assistance!' WHERE entry=9140;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You know the drill, kid. One valor token gets you a craftsman\'s writ.' WHERE entry=9142;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Help me, stranger. I must... reach Tranquillien... I cannot fail.$B$B<The blood elf falls back into unconsciousness as his eyes go blank.>' WHERE entry=9144;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good to hear that Lethvalin made it to safety. and that he was smart enough to ask you for help instead of just waiting there.$B$BI hope that Ranger Salissa made it safely to Farstrider Enclave.' WHERE entry=9145;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Just in time, $N! I was about ready to start digging a hole for our friend here.$B$BMy potion seems to be working; he\'s coming to.$B$BHey, I think he\'s trying to get your attention. Why don	 you talk to him?' WHERE entry=9147;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Finally!  We\'ve waited for a response from the regent lord for weeks! Let me see here...$B$B<Vandril begins to read the letter.>$B$BWhat\'s this? A dark presence? He senses a dark presence in the Ghostlands?! No kidding; I could have told him that!$B$BThis is what we\'ve been waiting for?' WHERE entry=9148;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent!  These spines will be invaluable to my research!  When I find a cure for the plague and word of my name spreads I\'ll make sure to make mention of you!$B$BIn the meantime, take these as a reward.  You might need them if you decide to go back to the coast.' WHERE entry=9149;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These are remarkably powerful, $N.  I\'m very pleased with your work.' WHERE entry=9150;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Darenis sent you? Very well, I suppose we can use your aid in fighting Dar\'Khan\'s forces.' WHERE entry=9151;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='With the rest of my supplies here. I can finally open shop. I\'m sure that the high executor will be most pleased to hear that the war on Dar\'Khan and the Scourge can commence.$B$BAnd, of course, there\'s the small matter of your recompense. Very well, $C, here is the coin that I alluded to. Do be sure to drop by should you find yourself in need of any trade goods.' WHERE entry=9152;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Not bad, $N. Keep it up, we could use a few more people like you around here.' WHERE entry=9155;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah... Luzran and Knucklerot! Not looking so tough anymore, are you? I can see you\'re still looking ugly as ever.$B$BTake one of these rewards, $N. You\'ve earned it.' WHERE entry=9156;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='With these necklaces we shall once again summon Aquantion.  The rebellious elemental will pay and our deaths will be avenged!' WHERE entry=9157;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done well, $N. It\'s important that the plague doesn\'t spread to the healthy wildlife in Eversong. I have more work for you if you\'re looking for something to do.' WHERE entry=9158;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve taken your task seriously and thus I\'d like to present you with suitable rewards. We need more allies with your courage and determination, $N.' WHERE entry=9159;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Disappointing that the night elves\' plans were not readily apparent at An\'daroth. However, those objects that looked like small magically-grown trees with powered orbs atop them sound interesting. It would appear that we\'ll need to be more direct in our information gathering efforts.$B$BHere, take this coin and these potions. I believe that you\'ll have use for them before we\'re done dealing with these night elves.' WHERE entry=9160;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc4='$C. what word do you bring concerning An\'daroth and what the night elves were up to there?' WHERE entry=9160;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='After browsing through the first few pages of this old book, you come to the conclusion that it once belonged to the one known as Dar\'Khan Drathir.' WHERE entry=9161;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This information is very valuable, $N.  We all knew about Dar\'Khan\'s plans to steal the power of the Sunwell for the Scourge, but much of the information found here is completely new to us.  Magister Kaendris at the Sanctum of the Sun will want to look at this.' WHERE entry=9162;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Troubling! These plans show the night elf forces at An\'daroth, which we already knew, but also at An\'owyn, a more remote ley-line nexus to the southeast.$B$BThere is a third nexus to the east, which is not mentioned, named An\'telas. I have a very bad feeling about all of this, $C.' WHERE entry=9163;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Ah, yes.  One of my finest creations.  This draught will break most forms of alchemically induced stupor.$B$BSide effects include confusion, nausea and - in rare cases - temporary blindness.  All much preferable to whatever the Scourge plans to do to those prisoners in Deatholme, if you ask me.$B$BBest of luck, brave $C.  You are going to need it.',objectives_loc4='Take Renzithen\'s Restorative Draught to Deatholme and rescue Apprentice Varnis,  Apothecary Enith and Ranger Vedoran.  Return to Arcanist Janeda at the Sanctum of the Sun for a reward.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent job, $N. Without your help those prisoners would\'ve lost their minds and souls to the Scourge.' WHERE entry=9164;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText4_loc4='Ranger Vedoran Rescued' WHERE entry=9164;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It was just horrible! Night elves! They conjured their moon crystal here for some nefarious plot, but I snuck away and gathered a larger group of our scouts and casters from the nearby Sanctum of the Sun. We killed most of them and the rest of the group is hunting down the remnants!I\'m glad that you\'re here now; I was only left a couple of scouts for protection! It\'s not safe out here!Give me a moment and I\'ll read through these plans to see what the night elves are up to.' WHERE entry=9166;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Today you\'ve dealt a deadly blow to the Scourge\'s grasp in the region.$B$BWith the vile traitor gone, it shall not be long before we\'ve reclaimed our lands and our greatness is restored once again.' WHERE entry=9167;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Deep inside Deatholme our enemies are striving to create stronger, deadlier spectral soldiers.  These abhorrent creatures are perfect killing machines, handcrafted by Dar\'Khan himself and hardened by the dark magic of Deatholme.$B$BTravel to the Tower of the Damned inside Deatholme and destroy them, $N.  We cannot let our enemy\'s army grow in power while we struggle to maintain our foothold in the Ghostlands.',objectives_loc4='Destroy 8 Eyes of Dar\'Khan and report back to Magister Idonis at the Sanctum of the Sun in the Ghostlands.' WHERE entry=9168;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'s a relief, $C! I can assure you that if you hadn\'t deactivated those scrying orbs we would be in a more tenuous position than the one we\'re already in! To think, surrounded by enemies, and one of them able to spy upon our every move!$B$BBut now we don\'t need to worry about that thanks to you! Here, take this, I want you to be rewarded for your efforts and I just happen to have a few things here that I no longer have any use for.$B$BThank you again, $N!' WHERE entry=9169;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Dar\'Khan\'s armies will soon fall. The Scourge shall not stand a chance against the combined might of the sin\'dorei and the Forsaken.' WHERE entry=9170;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Very well. these will have to do. No, don\'t describe them crawling around, I don\'t want to know! I\'ll work my magic upon these legs and they\'ll turn out quite tasty. A little spice here, a pinch of herb there, and then of course some arcane ingredients, and voila, a meal fit for a queen... or in this case, a dame.$B$BYour service has been adequate, $C. Here, take this recipe and some samples.' WHERE entry=9171;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This book... it can\'t be!  It\'s Dar\'Khan\'s very own handwriting.  There must be information here that will reveal a weakness in our opponent.$B$BYou\'ve done well in coming to us, $N.  The Farstriders have shown great wisdom in leaving this matter in our hands.  This armor should help you further our cause.' WHERE entry=9172;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m certain that Lady Sylvanas will be pleased to hear that we\'ve made progress in the matter.$B$BHere, take this coin as payment for your efforts.' WHERE entry=9173;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve avenged our deaths and broken Aquantion\'s grasp on our souls. We may finally rest.' WHERE entry=9174;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You say that you found it on one of the Scourge at Windrunner Spire and that there\'s an inscription on it? Let me see!Here, take this coin for a job well done.' WHERE entry=9175;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The rumors were true!  The stone of light and the stone of flame do exist!  We shall use their power to create weapons against Dar\'Khan.$B$BUse them when the time is right and the energies of the Sunwell, trapped within these objects, will vanquish him with the very power he sought to steal from us!' WHERE entry=9176;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Sylvanas takes the necklace from your grasp.>$B$BIt can\'t be! After all this time, I thought it was lost forever.$B$B<After a lingering moment the Lady seems to become aware once again of her surroundings, composing herself.>$B$BYou thought this would amuse me? Do you think I long for a time before I was the queen of the Forsaken? Like you, it means nothing to me, and Alleria Windrunner is a long dead memory!$B$B<She drops the amulet to the ground.>$B$BYou may now remove yourself from my presence, $C.' WHERE entry=9180;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'s a fair job of butchery you managed there, $C. We\'ll get the miners back to work now. I\'m sure they\'ll be disappointed that their break is over, but there\'s armor and weaponry to be made, and that requires ore to be mined.$B$BHere, take this as payment for doing your duty. Go get your armor and weapons repaired, and have a drink on me.' WHERE entry=9192;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='$C, our sources tell us that the trolls buried in the Amani Catacombs inside Sungraze Peak have been rising from the dead. Dame Auriferous would have you investigate these catacombs and put to the torch any of the unanimated remains you come across so as to prevent any more of these creatures from rising.$B$BThe fastest way there is to head north out of town and then take the first fork to the right. This will put you on the north side of the peak, so look to the south for the entrance.',objectives_loc4='Investigate the Amani Catacombs and burn 10 Mummified Troll Remains, then return to Advisor Valwyn at Tranquillien in the Ghostlands.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Disgusting, but necessary I can assure you. You have done us good service by investigating this matter, Please, take this as a token of our generosity and appreciation.' WHERE entry=9193;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc4='This is a most grim and undignified business, I trust that you will complete this task to milady\'s complete satisfaction?',ObjectiveText1_loc4='Mummified Troll Remains Burned' WHERE entry=9193;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Collect 8 Troll Juju and return them to Deathstalker Maltendis at Tranquillien in the Ghostlands.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Mummies being raised by troll priests... clever! The Shadowpine trolls must be trying to bolster their numbers through necromantic means. I\'d wager that these oracles were using the juju in their reanimation ritual.$B$BOnce again you perform your duty as befits a $C of your growing reputation. Take this with our gratitude.' WHERE entry=9199;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The bearer of this writ is entitled to payment in the form of an insignia of their choice upon completion of the contracted work order.$B$BWork Order AL-90:$B$B1 Potion of Petrification.$B$BAll filled orders should be delivered to Packmaster Stonebruiser at Light\'s Hope Chapel in the Eastern Plaguelands.$B$BContract is null and void if tampered with or damaged.$B$B-Dispatch Commander Metz, The Argent Dawn',objectives_loc4='Deliver 1 Potion of Petrification and the Craftsman\'s Writ - Potion of Petrification - to Packmaster Stonebruiser at Light\'s Hope Chapel in the Eastern Plaguelands.' WHERE entry=9203;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='My apprentice was unable to take care of this herself?  I shall have a word with her when she returns then, gnolls or not.  Speaking of which, why didn\'t she return with you?<The magister sighs.>That one is a handful, and is going to be quite a challenge to properly train.  Thank you, for bringing these samples to me.  We are hoping that we can uncover some special property from them that will help in the fight against the Scourge.Please take this coin as a token of my appreciation.' WHERE entry=9207;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='oh my! thank you! we will send a couple scouts and warriors out there quickly to deal with those trolls, and rescue Ranger Lilatha, you are so kind to help!' WHERE entry=9212;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'ll immediately send a few rangers out to survey the damage that you wreaked upon the Shadowpine trolls. I\'ve no doubt that we\'ll be able to mop up after your offensive and launch an attack on the Scourge soon if these weapons are any indication of your success.$B$BHere, I want you to take this coin in payment. It\'s burning a hole in my pouch anyway.' WHERE entry=9214;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah. Kel\'gash\'s head is what smelled so bad. That\'s a nice piece of work there, $C!$B$BWith their chieftain dead, the Shadowpine trolls should be in total disarray. Combined with your recent efforts to decimate their numbers, this should be the perfect opportunity to launch our counter-offensive against them and wipe them out for good.$B$BYou have my thanks, Might I interest you in one of these?' WHERE entry=9215;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Take this draught, $N.  After you drink it, your physical strength against the Scourge will receive a boost. If you need more than this sample bring me more hearts.' WHERE entry=9216;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This will provide you with greater power against the Scourge. Bring more hearts if you find them, $N.' WHERE entry=9217;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Take this, $N.  You\'ll feel the difference immediately!$B$BFeel free to bring more spinal dust; I can use as much of it as you can provide.  Side effects?  You might start feeling your joints acting up a bit.  Nothing permanent, I assure you!' WHERE entry=9218;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This dust is as potent as ever, $N. Keep bringing it to me if you\'re in need to boost your magical powers against the Scourge.' WHERE entry=9219;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Scourge has felt our wrath, $N. It won\'t be long before their cursed citadel lies in ruins.$B$BWith their numbers weakened, it is time to launch an attack on more strategic targets.' WHERE entry=9220;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Here you go, here you go!  A prize fit for a king!  Congratulations to you, my friend!$B$BIf you have more tickets you\'d like to turn in, then please let me know!  For as long as the Darkmoon Faire is here, I\'ll redeem your tickets.' WHERE entry=9249;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Many thanks, $N. Our job is a thankless one, but today you helped make it a bit easier.' WHERE entry=9252;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You must\'ve been sent by someone at Fairbreeze Village. I knew it would just be a matter of time until help arrived.' WHERE entry=9253;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s so nice of my old mentor to check on me. It\'s too bad she lost faith in my research long ago.$B$BDon\'t waste your time trying to get me to return to her; you can either help me with my research or leave.' WHERE entry=9254;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These notes... are shocking. If they\'re correct it means the damage to the land on the Dead Scar is irreversible.$B$BI\'ll notify the grand magister right away. More reason for our race to escape this world and find our true fate in Outland.' WHERE entry=9255;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thanks for coming, $N. Things are worse than we had anticipated. The Wretched have taken over Sunsail Anchorage in its entirety.' WHERE entry=9256;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, my brother sent you. I do have a task I could use assistance with.' WHERE entry=9258;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I appreciate your help, $N. It pains me to see the spirits of my ancestors in their pitiful state. May they finally get the rest they deserve.' WHERE entry=9274;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, excellent! I knew that a $R-delivery system would make for the most efficient application of the poison. With any luck the Shadowpine trolls will get fat on it before keeling over. That should get them off of the backs of the Farstriders, and me back to Tranquillien.$B$BIt has been a pleasure working with you, $C!' WHERE entry=9275;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good, good! You handled that very well! Let\'s see if you\'re up to something a little more difficult now.' WHERE entry=9276;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Unbelievable! You really should talk to the captain about joining up as a Farstrider.$B$BAlright, $N, you\'ve given us the breathing room that we need to continue building up our forces here. Actually, by your account there aren\'t many of those trolls left at all! Maybe now we can join with Tranquillien and attack Deatholme?$B$BI think you\'ve earned a little something. Take your pick.' WHERE entry=9277;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Welcome to the World of Warcraft!$B$BAs special thanks for purchasing the World of Warcraft Collector\'s Edition, turn in this gift voucher to Jaeleil at the Crash Site in Ammen Vale.  You\'ll then be given a gift: a little companion to join you on your quest for adventure and glory.$B$BThanks again, and enjoy your stay in the World of Warcraft!$B',objectives_loc4='Bring the Ammen Vale Gift Voucher to Jaeleil inside the ship at the Crash Site in Ammen Vale.' WHERE entry=9278;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='$N. by my eternal soul, it is good to see you! I don\'t know why the Exodar crashed. Only those of us that were in this part of the ship remain.$B$BThere\'s not much time if we\'re to save everyone that we can!' WHERE entry=9279;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Acquire 8 Vials of Moth Blood from the nearby Vale Moths and give them to Proenitus at the Crash Site in Ammen Vale.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Regrettable that those creatures had to die so that we might live - indiscriminate killing is not the $R way.  However, the blood you gathered will replenish our healing crystals, so their deaths will not be in vain.' WHERE entry=9280;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thanks for giving me a hand, $N. I was dreading the thought of venturing into the woods this close to Deatholme.' WHERE entry=9281;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Kaendris sent you? I might have a task for you, $C.' WHERE entry=9282;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Light be praised! You\'ve done what only a true heroine could have done, $N! The draenei you saved owes their continued life to your selflessness!$B$BPlease, take this supply pouch. You look like you can use it more than I.' WHERE entry=9283;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I am heartened by your initiative to speak with me. In the past I was responsible for the training of young paladins as they entered our order. This is a duty and privilege that I humbly take up once more. Your name has been mentioned as one who seeks to do good in the name of the Light. It would be my honor to guide you in your first steps as a $C.$B$BShall we begin?' WHERE entry=9287;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m glad that you have come to me. For quite some time now I have been responsible for the training of our young $Cs, a responsibility that I intend to continue on this new world. I\'ve had my eye upon you for a while now and it would be my honor to help train you in the ways of the $C.$BShall we begin?' WHERE entry=9288;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It is good that you seek my guidance. For centuries I have taught young $R warriors, so I may know a thing or two on how you should begin. I see in you the makings of a great $C, but only if you listen carefully to what I have to teach.$B$BAre you ready to learn, young $C?' WHERE entry=9289;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These will do. Thank you, $C!$B$BWhile you were out, I managed to gather some equipment together to make an analysis of the samples.  This should only take a moment.' WHERE entry=9293;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='From what you describe, the neutralizing agent worked! I just wish that I knew how long it will last; we really need to remove that power crystal from the lake entirely.$B$BThank you, $N! I will tell Tedon to try the neutralizing agent on one of the captured beasts at once.' WHERE entry=9294;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='This stone radiates a dark energy. You should deliver it to SOMEONE.',objectives_loc4='Deliver the Dim Necrotic Stone to SOMEONE.' WHERE entry=9296;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='This stone radiates a dark energy. You should deliver it to SOMEONE.',objectives_loc4='Deliver the Dim Necrotic Stone to SOMEONE.' WHERE entry=9297;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='This stone radiates a dark energy. You should deliver it to SOMEONE.',objectives_loc4='Deliver the Dim Necrotic Stone to SOMEONE.' WHERE entry=9298;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='With many of the owlkin now inoculated. we can focus on getting out of here and not have to worry about wiping out the owlkin population in the area.$B$BHere. choose from these. You\'ve done good work. and you deserve to be rewarded!' WHERE entry=9303;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Let me take a look at those.$B$BYes, I think that these will do nicely; good job, $N. The emitter is rather complex so it may take some time to finish the repairs. I\'ll let you know when it\'s ready.$B$BIn the meantime, you might see if Vindicator Aldar has anything he could use you for.' WHERE entry=9305;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='<DEPRECATED>Speak with Vindicator Aldar',details_loc4='$N, Vindicator Aldar has been looking for someone to take care of a problem that we\'re having with the mutated owlkin at Nestlewood Thicket.  We must deal with an unfortunate side effect of our unintended arrival here.$B$BYou\'ll find him outside to the south in the crash site. Please, speak with him as soon as you can.' WHERE entry=9306;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='<DEPRECATED>Blood Elf Remains?',objectives_loc4='Take the Blood Elf Amulet to Vindicator Aldar at the Crash Site in Ammen Vale.' WHERE entry=9308;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Help... blood elves! They... ambushed... me. Don\'t have... long.' WHERE entry=9309;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I thank you for dealing with the blood elf surveyor. Surely she was their leader. Rest assured, we will deal with whatever remnant of them is still nearby.$B$BPlease, take one of these weapons as a sign of my gratitude.' WHERE entry=9311;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I got it. I got it! I think I managed to fix the emitter! Here, I\'ll just activate this last crystal and that should do it.$B$BTake a look at the emitter, $N. It looks like it\'s beginning to work... someone is appearing!' WHERE entry=9312;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, good to see you again! I\'m glad that we were both able to get our emitters fixed or we might never have found one another. And don\'t worry, we\'ll see to it that Ammen Vale gets help and supplies.$B$BSpeaking of assistance, now that you\'re here, go around and introduce yourself to the others. I know that there\'s plenty to do.' WHERE entry=9313;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh, you must be one of the survivors we\'ve been hearing about!$B$BI\'m glad that you came. Don\'t worry, we will send someone to see to Aeun\'s injured leg.$B$BI\'m most interested in hearing all about your harrowing story of survival. You\'re a brave one to have made it all the way here.' WHERE entry=9314;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Come closer, I am ... dying.$B$BI was sent here ... to slay these nerubians, but Vandril didn\'t ... know that they have a leader.$B$B<The dying blood elf coughs up a good amount of blood.>$B$BYou must find and ... slay Anok\'suten.  Get help.  She wanders around ... Suncrown Village.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I apologize for the shoddy intelligence. $C. Had I known of this Anok\'suten ahead of time, I surely would have told you.$B$BWe\'re spread too thin and things are slipping through the cracks!' WHERE entry=9315;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We Forsaken are here because of a common enemy with the blood elves: Dar\'Khan! He has returned and now commands the Scourge that are invading this land from his steadfast, Deatholme, to the south.$B$BLady Sylvanas Windrunner, who originally hails from these lands, and used to be an elf, has a history with Dar\'Khan and wants him dead!$B$BWe will defeat him, $C, and you will help us do it!' WHERE entry=9327;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Now that\'s one face I was not expecting to see so soon.$B$BThis is quite the good news, $N, in more ways than you can imagine.' WHERE entry=9328;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I know it seems strange, but the Forsaken are here to help. You should speak with their leader, High Executor Mavren. He\'s in the tower on the west side of town.$B$BAnd, $C, when you\'re done talking with him return to me; I have something dire that needs to be dealt with immediately!',offerrewardtext_loc4='We Forsaken are here because of a common enemy with the blood elves: Dar\'Khan! He has returned and now commands the Scourge that are invading this land from his steadfast, Deatholme, to the south.$B$BLady Sylvanas Windrunner, who originally hails from these lands, and used to be an elf, has a history with Dar\'Khan and wants him dead!$B$BWe will defeat him, $C, and you will help us do it!' WHERE entry=9329;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good job, $N. That should teach the rock flayers to stay far away from us.' WHERE entry=9340;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These should do the job. I\'m going to prepare the salve and finish my splint before making my way back to Thrallmar. Why do I have the feeling that I know what Far Seer Regulkut will say when she sees me?$B$B<Grelag sighs half-heartedly.>$B$BThank you for your help, $N. I have some of the spineleaf left over. You\'re welcome to take it with you. Who can tell when it will prove useful?' WHERE entry=9345;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Examining the essence reveals violent swirls of energy sealed within a vessel made of unidentifiable material. As you consider it, you can feel it beginning to tug at your mind, inviting you to come closer and to look deeper.$B$BFeeling your will begin to slip away, you break your gaze immediately. Its presence remains at the edge of your consciousness as you determine what to do with it.',objectives_loc4='Bring the Pulsating Voidwalker Essence to Mahuram Stouthoof in Thrallmar.' WHERE entry=9347;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='In order to have great cuisine, you need to have great ingredients.  And these eggs look great!$B$BI\'ve just finished cleaning off my frying pan, so you\'re more than welcome to join me for a meal!' WHERE entry=9349;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This is perfect! In fact, I think it\'s going to work so well, I might just have to redesign the engine to take advantage of all this extra power. If, I mean, when we get out of here, I\'ll have to show my design to everyone back at Area 52!' WHERE entry=9351;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Night elves? Here? Those rats!$B$BDo you suppose they had anything to do with the malfunction in my sanctum? If you have any information, you\'d better take it to Captain Sunbrand at once!' WHERE entry=9352;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. We shouldn\'t be too quick to congratulate ourselves, though. I\'m certain we haven\'t seen the last of those worms. If they show their hideous heads around these parts again, the Sons\'ll be ready for them!' WHERE entry=9355;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ravager Eggs.  Bam!$B$BHellboar Bacon. Bam!$B$BBuzzard Wings. Bam!  Bam!$B$BWhat a great meal.  You\'ve really got to try it.' WHERE entry=9356;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re here to help us? Why didn\'t you say so earlier? We can always use a hand!' WHERE entry=9358;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re here to help? Excellent!$B$BThe battle against the Amani trolls has taken its toll on us and capable fighters such as yourself are always welcome.' WHERE entry=9359;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The trolls have been keeping us pinned here while planning an attack on Fairbreeze Village. We were not expecting this at all.' WHERE entry=9360;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hmm...$B$BThis looks edible, if spiced properly. Just don\'t tell Screed where his breakfast came from, ok?' WHERE entry=9361;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The information you\'ve brought is of vital importance, $N.  Now that we know of the trolls\' plans we can prepare for an attack.$B$BWe won\'t be caught with our guard down.' WHERE entry=9363;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The energy contained in these samples is tremendous, $N.  Now we just need to ensure that our access to this felblood continues uninterrupted.' WHERE entry=9366;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Acquire 8 Vials of Moth Blood from the nearby Vale Moths and bring them to Proenitus at the Crash Site in Ammen Vale.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Regrettable that those creatures had to die so that we might live - indiscriminate killing is not the draenei way. However, the blood you gathered will replenish our healing crystals, so their deaths will not be in vain.' WHERE entry=9369;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'ll show those holy fanatics to mind their own business.' WHERE entry=9370;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh, thank goodness you\'ve come. We have much to do.' WHERE entry=9371;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. These blood samples will prove helpful in my research and in the Expedition\'s wider studies of Outland\'s creatures.$B$BIf I could isolate what causes these creatures to change continuously, perhaps I could concoct an antidote.' WHERE entry=9372;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you for bringing this to me, $C. I was wondering why I hadn\'t heard from the Expedition in so long. I wonder how long ago this message was dispatched and what befell its carrier.$B$BHere\'s a bit of coin for your trouble.' WHERE entry=9373;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='My husband\'s journal... it\'s not about research at all!$B$BHow could I\'ve been such a fool?  "Magical properties of fel-infused slime forms," he really had me going there.' WHERE entry=9374;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Taleris shouts to several of the blood elves at the outpost.>$B$BGet her inside and see to her wounds!$B$B<Taleris turns back to you.>$B$BShe\'s fortunate that you found her when you did, $C. I don\'t think she\'d have lasted much longer out there.$B$BCan you make out what she was saying?' WHERE entry=9375;
UPDATE locales_quest SET EndText_loc4='Escort Wounded Blood Elf Pilgrim to Falcon Watch' WHERE entry=9375;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you for returning this, $N. I\'m not sure what significance it holds for the wounded pilgrim, but she refuses to let anyone get near her until it\'s in her hands again.' WHERE entry=9376;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I swear, if I get one more letter from Ironforge...$B$BHave you ever tried to explain something to someone who just wouldn\'t listen, $C? I sent the boys in Ironforge the warp hound they asked for, and they had the gall to write back saying they wanted a "pack" of the things! A pack!$B$BSo, I tried to tell \'em that warp hounds are solitary creatures, but they\'d have none of it. I\'ve given up on setting \'em straight. Grab 6 of the best ones from the area east of the hold, and brimg \'em back here?',objectives_loc4='Collect 6 Undamaged Warp Hound Corpses and bring them to Prospector Murantus in Honor Hold.' WHERE entry=9380;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These should do the job. I was concerned that the rangers might be short on arrows for a while, but that\'s one less thing I have to worry about. Thank you for your help, $C.' WHERE entry=9381;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done well, $N. It seems the containment crystal is holding for now, but how long it will last remains a mystery. We\'ll keep an eye on it and prepare more of the crystals in the meantime.' WHERE entry=9383;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. That should teach those beasts who\'s boss!' WHERE entry=9385;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve been most helpful, $N.  Now let\'s see what we can learn from our blue friend.' WHERE entry=9387;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve found the body of a young draenei $C. He appears to have been slain by a blow to his back.' WHERE entry=9390;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Great Fissure, though still dangerous, will prove to be a useful path for our pilgrims.$B$BWith the Alliance watching all the roads in and out of Falcon Watch this is the manner of desperate act that is required of us.' WHERE entry=9391;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'ve heard your name whispered from the shadows, $N. It\'s said that you\'re looking for someone experienced to show you the ropes - someone like me. I can do that, but it\'ll cost you a small cut of your take every time I\'ve got something to teach you. So yes, I will train you in what it means to be a rogue.$B$BBut remember, if you ever get caught stealing something, this conversation never took place. Now get out there and show me what you\'re made of!' WHERE entry=9392;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='$N, are your eyes keen as a hawk\'s, your motions as fluid as a monkey\'s, or your speed that of a cheetah? Mine are, and yours can be too with the proper training. The way of the hunter is one of mastery over the beasts of the world, an unparalleled precision in marksmanship, and the knowledge of how to survive in situations where others would perish.$B$BIf these are the things that you seek to learn, then I will train you - for a small fee, of course. Shall we begin?' WHERE entry=9393;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Who are you? You\'re not one of the magister\'s apprentices, that\'s for certain!$B$BSent here to help me clean up this mess, no doubt!' WHERE entry=9394;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, good of Magistrix Dawnstrider to finally respond to my simple requests.  I should take up the matter of her attitude with the regent lord in Silvermoon. She\'s quite rude!$B$BNothing for you to concern yourself with though. Now that you\'re here, maybe I\'ll finally be able to get those party supplies that I\'ve been waiting for?' WHERE entry=9395;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good work, $N.  Outland\'s secrets will not stay hidden from us for very long.$B$BIt\'s our destiny to become the masters of this world.' WHERE entry=9396;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You did it!  You caught a female hatchling!$B$BShe\'s precious.  You have my thanks, $N.' WHERE entry=9397;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done well, $N.  It is always unfortunate to have to resort to taking a life, even when it\'s that of a dangerous beast such as the rock flayer.$B$BYou have my thanks for carrying out this grim task.' WHERE entry=9398;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You did it!  I\'m in your debt, $N.  Look at all the Dreghoods that are showing up.$B$BUnder my guidance they\'ll learn all about the old ways, you\'ll see.' WHERE entry=9399;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The corpse matches the description of Krun Spinebreaker, Hellfire Citadel\'s assassin. As you turn the body over, you notice a stone axe protruding from his back.' WHERE entry=9400;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='He was killed by this weapon?  It can\'t be!$B$BHave we... found them?' WHERE entry=9401;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='So... $N is it?  Don\'t be flattered I know your name, one of my students has been fawning over you and won\'t shut up.$B$BHmm... if you\'d like to impress $Gher:him;, why don\'t you do something for me?  There\'s an azure phial at the bottom of the pond behind me.  Dive in, retrieve it, and bring it here.',objectives_loc4='Dive to the bottom of Stillwhisper Pond and retrieve the Azure Phial for Instructor Antheol.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh, well done...  I told you to jump in a pond, and you did.  I can only imagine what you\'d do if one of your good friends asked it of you.$B$BIf you want a reward for your efforts, it is this: never lift a finger without first knowing what\'s in it for you.  The $C\'s mind is his greatest weapon.  Remember that and try to use yours a bit more.' WHERE entry=9402;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I understand Nazgrel\'s request, $C. Say no more.' WHERE entry=9405;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='This news you bring from beyond the Dark Portal...  you want us to believe the son of Durotan now rules over the lands beyond it... free from any demonic taint?  And that now his people have returned to this world?$B$BI hope for your sake that this isn\'t some manner of joke, $C.  What this means to my people... cannot be described.  I must send word to Nagrand at once!  Hellscream must hear about this.$B$BTake this letter back to your leader in Thrallmar.  Tell him the Mag\'har welcome them!',offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re certain of this?  True orcs... here in Hellfire!  This is big news, $N.$B$BWe must inform the warchief at once.' WHERE entry=9406;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='For years the Dark Portal loomed silent... forgotten.  But it is silent no longer.$B$BAfter stopping the demonic assault here, our forces breached the portal and met the demons on their own ground!$B$BNow, we are locked in a savage war, and there are some who think we might not win.  So it is our duty, our grim pleasure, to battle the fiends of Outland and ensure our victory, $N.$B$BIf you would help us, then report to Lieutenant General Orion at once. He awaits you in the Outland...$B',objectives_loc4='Travel through the Dark Portal and find Lieutenant General Orion. He awaits your arrival on the other side, in Outland.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Our Expedition made it safely through the Portal and set up a new base called Thrallmar. Yet as you can see. the Burning Legion moved in and cut us off from our brothers. Clearly, the demons hope to retake the Dark Portal and prevent us from gathering reinforcements from Azeroth.' WHERE entry=9407;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='While it pains me to know that we have lost so many soldiers in our efforts to breach the portal, my heart swells with pride to know that the original expeditionary force is still alive.$B$BI can hardly believe it; but here they stand - a testament to the resolve of the Alliance.$B$BInside that keep stands one of our greatest heroes: Danath Trollbane! Seek him out, $C. He has already met and addressed all of our soldiers. He will surely want to meet you.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Force Commander Danath Trollbane at Honor Hold.' WHERE entry=9408;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good work!  This will do nicely to replenish our depleted healing crystals.$B$BBut now that you\'re here, I think I have another use for you, if you\'re willing?' WHERE entry=9409;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Who are you to walk in here unannounced?  I ordered my men to stay their hand only because Ryga sensed that the spirits were with you.$B$BSpeak freely, but choose your words wisely.  We rarely trust strangers this close to the Citadel.' WHERE entry=9410;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The arakkoa are smart creatures... smart as any gnome you ever met.  They have this way with magic and a violent temper, however. $B$BLately they\'ve taken to attacking Honor Hold patrols, which is why we were sent here.  See, Mirren and I are world-famous marksmen, we are!  But fowl and game are what we specialize in... not these... lightning-invoking birdmen.$B$BSo what do you say you give us a hand in this one assignment?  You\'ll find the Den of Haal\'esh to the southwest.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Great job, $N! I hereby proclaim you an honorary Longbeard.$B$BStick around and have a drink with us, won\'t you?' WHERE entry=9417;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='With this orb I regain my liberty.  Take your reward, mortal, so that our debt may be settled.' WHERE entry=9418;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You did your part. I guess a deal is a deal! $B$BHere you go. friend. Treat it well.' WHERE entry=9420;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I am Firmanvaar and you are wise to seek me out. It is my calling to provide instruction to $C, especially those who are just beginning to learn.$B$BShamanism is only now being relearned amongst the $R, $N. You are brave to follow its path as it is not popular amongst your kind.$B$BI will be here when you feel you are ready for further training.' WHERE entry=9421;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Sedai, dear brother...$B$BThose cowardly orcs! He was unarmed, how could they?$B$BLeave me be, $N. I thank you for your assistance but I wish to be alone with my thoughts now.' WHERE entry=9423;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes... revenge! You did good.$B$BYou take this now. It was a gift from Sedai. It only makes Makuru sad to see it.' WHERE entry=9424;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes. I feel the fel presence in the pools weakening.$B$BYou\'ve done well, $N.' WHERE entry=9426;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The essence of Aggonar lived on in the form of his foul offspring Aggonis.  With your success in defeating the demon, we can begin to work towards restoring the pools to their former purity.$B$BYou have our thanks, $N.  Your work will have a deep impact in this world.' WHERE entry=9427;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re very fortunate.  Just as I had hoped, you\'ve found a special relic among these other ones.' WHERE entry=9430;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='What\'s a sin\'dorei doing standing on the top of a windswept butte in Thousand Needles instead of the halls of Silvermoon?$B$BIt\'s simple. My brethren will no longer have me. Every copy of my treatise on natural cures for our magical addiction was burned.$B$BI can safely pursue my research here, but I am without my reagents. If you\'d be willing to gather purifying earth from the thundering boulderkin near the western end of the Needles and deliver it to my associate at Whitereach Post, I\'d appreciate it.',objectives_loc4='Gather 2 handfuls of Purifying Earth from Thundering Boulderkin and take them to Wizlo Bearingshiner at Whitereach Post.',offerrewardtext_loc4='What? She didn\'t mention the moonwell? That\'s what she had in mind all along. I admit the whole thing\'s a bit wacky, but who am I to turn away a client, especially when she\'s the only one I\'ve got?$B$BMaybe trying to sneak into a night elf settlement and steal water from their moonwell isn\'t the most prudent thing I\'ve ever helped a customer do, but her money is as gold as anyone else\'s!' WHERE entry=9431;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='If there\'s one great truth about Hillsbrad, it\'s that this region is destined to live under the shadow of war. Even something as innocuous as a cartload of stone is a target.$B$BNormally the loss of building materials is no great setback, but the most recent shipment from the Azurelode mine contained a crate of rare crystals I was eager to study. Forsaken raiders intercepted the cart and drove it northeast to a tower they\'re attempting to rebuild. It\'s imperative that we retrieve those crystals, $C!',objectives_loc4='Retrieve the Shipment of Rare Crystals from the Forsaken and return it to Huraan in Southshore.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank the Light! From the tone of the foreman\'s letter, it sounded as if that box of crystals contained the only known samples from the mine. If we had lost them, $N, we may never have seen another like them.$B$BI can\'t thank you enough for your help.' WHERE entry=9435;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done. Now, this is curious...$B$BThe inscription on this totem is in a language no troll could ever hope to learn, but one that is known to us. It names the bearer as an ally of a water elemental named Naias and marks him as one worthy to channel his power.$B$BThis is most unexpected, but not entirely bad, $N. With your help, I\'d like to pursue this further.' WHERE entry=9436;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N! As soon as Ithania has had time to rest and my preparations are complete, we\'ll depart this sodden wasteland and head back to civilization.' WHERE entry=9437;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='That blood elf witch, Cersei Dusksinger, has been cursing the Lost Ones, I just know it!  I don\'t know why or how, but the results are tragic.  Several of the Lost Ones have now been further corrupted - cursed with even more fel energies!$B$B$C, can you find it in you to take pity on these poor creatures?  They should not have to live out the rest of their lives in such a horrible condition.$B$BYou\'ll find these cursed Lost Ones at the Fallow Sanctuary, east down the path.',objectives_loc4='Slay 3 Cursed Lost Ones and then return to Anchorite Avuun at the Harborage in the Swamp of Sorrows.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It is done then.  I thank you for showing your compassion.  Once corrupted by whatever Cersei was feeding them, there is nothing else that could be done.$B$BThey are now at peace and hopefully my studies of the others will bear fruit so that they can be rehabilitated.' WHERE entry=9448;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The time has come, $N.  You have grown to the point where you are ready to commune directly with the elemental spirits of this world.$B$BBut be warned.  I can sense that the manner of our entry into this world, and its unfortunate side effects, have angered the earth spirits and caused an imbalance of the elements.$B$BIf you are to create your earth totem, you must first speak with the Spirit of the Vale.  You will find it in the Sacred Grove, nestled in the hills to the northwest.',objectives_loc4='Speak with the Spirit of the Vale at the Sacred Grove in Ammen Vale.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You are bold to seek my wisdom after what your people have done to these islands, stranger! Still, there is much to be said for your bravery, so I will impart to you some knowledge.$B$BThe earth beneath your feet forms the foundation for all things. The sky, the waters, even great fire - all rest upon its shoulders. While those others often form chaotic tempests, the earth abides. It grants strength and fortitude to the core of your being.' WHERE entry=9449;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The balance of the elements has been disrupted by the violent intrusion of the draenei to the Vale.  Your crash has caused the spirits of earth to be enraged and turn upon the other elements who have come to quell them.  You will learn that an understanding of the elements can only come when all are in harmony.$B$BThus, it falls to you to seek a balance.  Behind me in the grove you will find the restless spirits of earth warring upon the other three elements.  Help restore the balance.',objectives_loc4='Slay 4 Restless Elements of Earth and then return to the Spirit of the Vale at the Sacred Grove in Ammen Vale.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well. By thinning out the restless spirits you have helped to heal the imbalance between the elements, which your people inadvertently caused.$B$BThroughout your journey as a $C you must keep this in mind when calling upon our power. The balance must be preserved.' WHERE entry=9450;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I will now give you a piece of my physical being that you may create your earth totem.  Return it to he who sent you here.$B$BYou and I will be bound together for all time.  Throughout your life the forces of earth will be at your disposal.  The balance will come when your bones return to us at the end of your days.$B$BUse our power wisely.',objectives_loc4='Deliver the Earth Crystal to Firmanvaar at the Crash Site in Ammen Vale.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well, $N.  In helping to restore the balance of the elements at the grove, you have also created a balance between the earth element of this world and the $R.  Perhaps this will help to bring understanding to those amongst us who do not approve of our ways?$B$BI will create for you a totem through which you will be able to call on the power of earth to do your bidding.  And with time, more of the mysteries of earth will be revealed to you.$B$BNow, take your totem, $C.' WHERE entry=9451;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I\'ve found that these waters are bustling with red snapper, a very tasty fish. With a fishing net, I can catch enough to feed dozens of draenei! Unfortunately, I was recently attacked by a creature known as a murloc while netting in the river and have suffered some injuries that prevent me from doing my job. I need help!$B$BUse this fishing net near schools of red snapper, found in the Crystalbrook river to the east to catch the fish.$B$BWhat do you say? Remember to return the net when you are finished.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I hope the murlocs didn\'t cause too much trouble, $N. I owe you a great debt of gratitude for all that you\'ve done.$B$BPerhaps I could teach you how to fish? I\'ll even supply the fishing pole and a bauble.' WHERE entry=9452;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Poor Diktynna... That murloc gave her quite a scare.$B$B<Acteon sighs.>$B$BHopefully she will recover from the injuries soon...$B$BSo I presume you\'re looking for work. Well there\'s plenty of that to be found at Azure Watch!' WHERE entry=9453;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N, well done!$B$BHere, I cooked up some tenderloins while you were gone. Maybe you\'d like the recipe, too?' WHERE entry=9454;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='How did such a thing end up in the stomach of a nightstalker? Could the debris from the crash have contaminated more beasts?' WHERE entry=9455;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I just hope it\'s not too late...' WHERE entry=9456;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I can feel the raw power contained in this gem, $N. I\'ll send it to Silvermoon for our magisters to study further, but I am sure it will prove useful in our struggle against the Amani.$B$BYour help has been invaluable in procuring this gem, and I will see to it that the Farstriders know the name of the $R who made this find possible.' WHERE entry=9457;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You should know that The Prophet has been asking for you, having heard of your success in your trial. The creation of your fire totem will have to wait until you have spoken with him.$B$BThis is a rare honor; you must hurry to the Exodar to see him at once!',objectives_loc4='Seek out Prophet Velen at the Vault of Lights in the Exodar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Hello, $N, I have been expecting you. I trust this day finds you well?' WHERE entry=9461;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='$N! It is time for you to receive further training in the ways of the spirits. You should seek out Tuluun, the shaman at Azure Watch. He can begin your introduction to understanding and harnessing the power of flame.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Tuluun at Azure Watch on Azuremyst Isle.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Just in time, $N. I hope you are ready to continue your training. This next task will be a difficult one.' WHERE entry=9462;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Let us hope that this ointment will strengthen her spirit!' WHERE entry=9463;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Once again you are to be tested, and this time the chaotic element of fire must be understood if you\'re to create a totem to harness its energies.$B$BTo the northeast on the coast is a sacred place of fire known as Emberglade. Amidst its burned trees stands Temper, a fire elemental of great power, and the one that you must speak with.$B$BGo to him now and may the elemental spirits of Azeroth go with you.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Temper at Emberglade on Azuremyst Isle.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I trust that the burning I see behind your eyes is from a desire to grow and understand?  Good!$B$BTuluun has sent you here because he sees your potential to both learn and help with a problem that the crash of your Exodar has caused.$B$BWe shall see.' WHERE entry=9464;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='One of my brethren, Hauteur, has gone insane, no doubt because of the crash of your ship.  He\'s begun demanding that the local owlbeasts worship him.$B$BThis will not continue!  None of us would ever impersonate a god!  It falls to you to restore the balance.$B$BFirst, you must retrieve their ritual torch, which has been taken by the crazed wildkin inside Stillpine Hold to the west.$B$BReturn the torch to me.',objectives_loc4='Retrieve the Ritual Torch and return it to Temper at Emberglade on Azuremyst Isle.',offerrewardtext_loc4='See how its fire never goes out?  That is the work of Hauteur.  It is a symbol of his arrogance.  Flame is meant to consume that which it burns and then itself die, to be reborn anew another time.$B$BI would help you douse the torch, but it must stay lit for you to deal with Hauteur.  We will let it burn a little while longer.' WHERE entry=9465;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re a brave $C, $N. That savage beast took many of my best hunters\' lives.$B$BTake this reward, you\'ve earned it.' WHERE entry=9466;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The owlbeasts of Moonwing Den on Silvermyst Isle, far to the southwest, have been deluded into thinking that Hauteur is a god to be worshipped.  What he truly is, is a fallen elemental who needs to be put out of his misery.  That torch is the key to his downfall.$B$BHauteur regularly demands that these owlbeasts burn an effigy in his honor.  So, when you light it, he will come.  Slay him and bring me the ashes.  Then use the orb in the satchel that I will give you to return to me here.',objectives_loc4='Retrieve Hauteur\'s Ashes and then return them and the Ritual Torch to Temper at Emberglade on Azuremyst Isle.  Remember that you can use the Orb of Returning to teleport back to Temper once you have the ashes.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It is a valuable lesson that you learn here today.  It is the story of endings and new beginnings.$B$BWhen first we spoke I told you that fire was not just destruction, but also a renewing force of the elements.  Through your actions you have both destroyed and saved Hauteur, for he shall be reborn from his ashes.' WHERE entry=9467;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You have done a great thing here today in your pursuit of understanding your relationship to the flame.  Remember to always treat it with the utmost respect lest you get burned.$B$BI saved a portion of Hauteur\'s ashes for you.  Use them in the creation of your fire totem and remember all that you have learned in their attainment.$B$BNow, return to Tuluun.',objectives_loc4='Deliver Hauteur\'s Ashes to Tuluun at Azure Watch on Azuremyst Isle.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have passed through the cleansing fire of destruction and been renewed, $N.  This is not unlike the tribulation the $R people are currently undergoing.  And through saving Hauteur from himself, you have secured your connection to the elemental fire of this world.' WHERE entry=9468;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Featherbeard\'s journal appears to have a large number of recent entries. Leafing back to the beginning of the latest ones, you begin searching for clues about where he might have gone.' WHERE entry=9469;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. The Wildhammers will be heartened to know that they don\'t stand against the Witherbark trolls alone. Showing them that the Alliance can prove a reliable partner in protecting the gryphons should lend more weight to our proposition.' WHERE entry=9470;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Ambassador Rualeth nods as you give your report.>$B$BYou have done well. The culling of the silvermane will not go unnoticed by the Wildhammer. When I meet with their leaders, I am certain that your deeds will reflect well upon the Alliance. Please accept this coin as a small token of my thanks, $N.' WHERE entry=9471;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent!  That little backstabber won\'t be running off with anyone\'s husband any time soon.$B$BHere\'s a little something for your troubles.  I trust we can keep this incident between us, $N.' WHERE entry=9472;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Watch as the plant works its magic.' WHERE entry=9473;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $C!  The recovery of this holy symbol means a great deal to myself and others that honor the memory of Uther Lightbringer.' WHERE entry=9474;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You know, maybe we can become friends after all.  Follow me; we don\'t want to have to share this with the others now, do we?' WHERE entry=9483;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You have undoubtedly hunted and slain beasts for both your defense and sustenance, yet to befriend them and harness their strengths is only now within your grasp.  This I can teach you.$B$BTake this magical taming rod that allows a wild animal to temporarily bond and fight beside you.  Begin with the crazed dragonhawk, a nearly docile bird found just outside of Farstrider Retreat.  Return to me when this is done.',objectives_loc4='Use the Taming Rod to tame a Crazed Dragonhawk, and then return to Lieutenant Dawnrunner.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Withstanding the numerous claws and bites from the dragonhawk is a sign of your tenacity. Do you have the strength to learn more?' WHERE entry=9484;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You have done well, $N.  Your understanding of the wild grows quickly.$B$BThe mistbat is a clever hunter, combining the swiftness of the dragonhawk and the ferocity of the springpaw.  Mistbats are found just across the Elrendar River to the south, preying on hapless travelers who wander into the Ghostlands.$B$BUse this final taming rod to befriend a mistbat and return to me when you have finished.',objectives_loc4='Use the Taming Rod to tame a Mistbat, and then return to Lieutenant Dawnrunner.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So you see $N, there is nothing left for me to teach you at this time. You already understand what it is to befriend those you once hunted. You need only to choose one of nature\'s allies with traits that match your own.' WHERE entry=9485;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The elder springpaw is an efficient and swift hunter.  In attempting to befriend one, it sees you as prey.  Do not be dissuaded.$B$BUse the taming rod to bring the great cat to your side and hunt beside it.  They are found throughout Eversong Woods, some very close to the lodge.  When you have learned enough, return to me.',objectives_loc4='Use the Taming Rod to tame an Elder Springpaw, then return to Lieutenant Dawnrunner.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have shown both strength and tenacity. There remains the final test until you can tame without the use of magic.' WHERE entry=9486;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Such a waste, using magic to construct beings of physical strength. I always thought that\'s why we allied with the lesser races, after all.$B$BYou were good to destroy them so we can use what remains for a more suitable purpose.' WHERE entry=9487;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Rock flayers are mean, nasty, violent creatures.  But the plain ones are like tame beasts when compared to their matriarch, Blacktalon the Savage.$B$BMy cousin got eaten by her and it wasn\'t pretty.  I swore that one day Blacktalon would pay for that.  You bring back proof of that monster\'s death and I will give you my life\'s savings.  Deal?$B$BYou\'re going to need some friends to kill Blacktalon.  Big tough friends with sharp swords.  You\'ll find her inside a cave in the Great Fissure.  Good luck!',offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes, I remember these sharp claws!$B$BTake this reward, $N.  That was a dangerous task you just did.  You deserve every bit of this reward.' WHERE entry=9490;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='A rich, and I mean filthy rich, merchant came through here yesterday talking about some ring of "immense archeological importance" locked in one of the countless burial chests found in the Amani Catacombs.  When he wasn\'t talking about the ring, he was talking about how much he\'d pay for it.$B$BTell you what, I\'ll front the thieves\' tools, and if you manage to bring the ring back, I\'ll pay you enough to buy ten rings of your own!',objectives_loc4='Eralan in Tranquillien wants you to retrieve the Pitted Gold Band from the Amani Catacombs.',offerrewardtext_loc4='This is the ring, is it? Not much to look at, but you know what they say about one elves\' trash...$B$BAnd let\'s not forget your payment. Don\'t feel shy about spending it right here sister!' WHERE entry=9491;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. With your victory in Hellfire Citadel, we have struck a major blow against the orcs.$B$BI must speak with Field Commander Romus about following up and ensuring that the orcs stay on the defensive. Now that we\'ve been reinforced, we can do far more than simply defend Honor Hold.' WHERE entry=9492;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That is excellent news, indeed, $N. With progress to report from Hellfire Citadel, perhaps we can afford to turn our attention to the Fel Horde presence other parts of the peninsula and Outland as a whole.' WHERE entry=9493;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done! I can\'t hope to replicate the feats of Grand Warlock Nethekurse, nor should I aspire to, but we would be fools to ignore the power of the fel embers.$B$BHowever, there are those who would forbid the type of research I\'m about to embark upon, and for that reason, I must keep my efforts secret. Please do not speak of this to anyone, $N.' WHERE entry=9494;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The struggle to free the orcish people from our tainted blood has not been easy, $N. Warchief Thrall has seen too many orcish heroes laid low by fate\'s hand. Now, it seems Kargath Bladefist numbers among them.$B$BIn the Shattered Halls of Hellfire Citadel, Kargath has claimed the title of \'Warchief\' of the Fel Horde. With an army of crazed, bloodthirsty fel orcs at his back, he won\'t rest until Thrallmar is destroyed. Warchief Thrall has commanded us to defeat Kargath and his forces at all costs.',objectives_loc4='Bring Warchief Kargath\'s Fist to Nazgrel in Thrallmar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well, $N. In his prime, Kargath Bladefist was a fine warrior, a hero and example to his people.$B$BHis death is a blow to us all, but especially to Warchief Thrall. Whatever happened to him in his final days, we should not forget the orc Kargath once was, nor the lessons to be learned from his downfall.$B$BFor your service to the Horde, $N, you are to be rewarded with your choice from among these weapons.' WHERE entry=9495;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Overlord Maimfist\'s insults aside, $N, this Fel Horde is nothing to be trifled with.$B$BFrom what we know, Fel Horde troops under the command of Kargath Bladefist are a brutal, battle-hardened lot fortified by foul magics. The elite of this force, the Shattered Hand legionnaires, champions, and centurions are feared by the Fel Horde regulars and serve as an officer corps.$B$BTargeting and eliminating them is a necessary first step in any successful assault on the Fel Horde\'s leadership.$B',objectives_loc4='Shadow Hunter Ty\'jin at Thrallmar wants you to kill 8 Shattered Hand Legionnaires, 4 Shattered Hand Centurions, and 4 Shattered Hand Champions.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent job, $N. With the legionnaires broken, it will be easier to face the Fel Horde on the battlefield, though they remain a formidable enemy.' WHERE entry=9496;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Welcome to Falcon Watch, $R. All our Horde allies are welcome here, especially those recommended by Martik.' WHERE entry=9498;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Welcome to Falcon Watch, $Gbrother:sister;. Many other blood elves haven\'t been fortunate enough to make it this far.$B$BIt\'s a terrible shame; our work in Outland has just begun.' WHERE entry=9499;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='It\'s been a while since last you were tested.  Farseer Nobundo has been asking for you.  You must have grown greatly in wisdom because you are being called to learn the mysteries of the element of water.$B$BYou remember where to find him at the Crystal Hall inside of the Exodar, right?',objectives_loc4='Speak with Farseer Nobundo at the Crystal Hall inside the Exodar on Azuremyst Isle.',offerrewardtext_loc4='We meet again. I have been watching your progress from afar, $C, and I am pleased.$B$BThe time has come for you to commune with the element of water, to learn its mysteries and give yourself over to the water so that you might in turn learn to master it.' WHERE entry=9500;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='A powerful water elemental named Aqueous has requested your presence.  It would seem that there is a great imbalance occurring in the water element on Bloodmyst Isle.  Not surprising given the unnatural predilections of the blood elves.$B$BYou will find Aqueous in a hidden reef under the waves off the northern shore of Bloodmyst Isle.$B$BTake this potion; it can help you to get to her once you get into the water near the reef.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Aqueous in the Hidden Reef at Bloodmyst Isle.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Do not fear, $N. While you are here we will speak using our minds.$B$BI am grateful to Farseer Nobundo for sending you to me. There is a great disturbance that is polluting the waters on and around Bloodmyst Isle. Not even the blind would fail to notice the effect this is having on its creatures and the environment.$B$BYou and I will work together to stop this corruption before it spreads further.' WHERE entry=9501;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='It\'s been a while since last you were tested.  Farseer Nobundo has been asking for you.  You must have grown greatly in wisdom because you are being called to learn the mysteries of the element of water.$B$BYou remember where to find him at the Crystal Hall inside of the Exodar, right?',objectives_loc4='Speak with Farseer Nobundo at the Crystal Hall inside the Exodar on Azuremyst Isle.',offerrewardtext_loc4='We meet again. I have been watching your progress from afar, $C, and I am pleased.$B$BThe time has come for you to commune with the element of water, to learn its mysteries and give yourself over to the water so that you might in turn learn to master it.' WHERE entry=9502;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='In balance with the other elements, water is the source and sustenance of all living things.  It gives and nurtures life, and all rely upon it for their existence.  Yet, when polluted, it also brings life to an end.$B$BWe must determine the extent of the damage that has been done.  To the southwest is one such contaminated body of water that has come to be known as the Foul Pool.  Travel there and extract the foul essence from the water spirits that inhabit the pool.',objectives_loc4='Collect 6 Foul Essences and return them to Aqueous in the Hidden Reef at Bloodmyst Isle.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $C. These should be enough so that I can examine this corruption. Then we will have a better idea of how to proceed.' WHERE entry=9503;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='It is worse than I feared. The corruption is very potent and if unchecked it could spread to the ocean currents and be carried throughout all of Azeroth!$B$BWe are going to need a sample of the purest water to counter this malignancy. There is a forest on the nearby continent of Kalimdor named Ashenvale. Near its southwestern border is a place called the Ruins of Stardust.$B$BTake this bota bag and fill it with the water from the fountain on the small island at the center of the ruins. Hurry, $N!',objectives_loc4='Fill the Empty Bota Bag and then return to Aqueous in the Hidden Reef at Bloodmyst Isle.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Water parts easily, yet put enough of it together and it will create an unstoppable force. It washes away earth and fire, and easily pushes air out of the way.$B$BWe are that unstoppable force, $N, not those that have poisoned Bloodmyst Isle!' WHERE entry=9504;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You say that you\'ve found one of our crew and that she is injured? I will send one of my crewmen to your village immediately!' WHERE entry=9505;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re a resourceful one! With our navigation gear, we can figure out just how far we\'ve veered off course.$B$BBut wait, what\'s this? There\'s something rolled up in the map. Let me see...$B$BThese are orders from Mogul Razdunk of the Venture Company. According to these plans, they\'re here to strip-mine the island of the crystal wreckage, then hijack our ships once they\'re finished.$B$BBy Bronzebeard\'s bushy brow! This is why they forced us to land? How could they know of our plans?$B$BI smell a traitor...' WHERE entry=9506;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I have determined where the corruption is coming from.  It is the by-product of some demented research and you\'re going to put an end to it!$B$BJust to the southwest of the Foul Pool is a small camp.  There you will find the \'research\' of Tel\'athion the Impure.  This is where he produces the filth that has been seeping into the island\'s water.$B$BUse the pure water you obtained from Ashenvale to destroy his cache of barrels.  That will be sure to bring him out.$B$BWe will have an end to this!',objectives_loc4='Bring the Head of Tel\'athion to Aqueous in the Hidden Reef at Bloodmyst Isle.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It is done then!  The crisis is averted and you have put in motion the restoration of the water on Bloodmyst Isle.  Over time, the water, in conjunction with the other elements, will heal itself.$B$BIt is unfortunate that the blood elves cannot see that by contaminating their surroundings they\'re killing themselves off as well!' WHERE entry=9508;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I held back a little of the water from Ashenvale, not because I doubted your ability to deal with the situation.  Rather, I knew that you would succeed, and I wanted to make sure that you had something special to take back to Nobundo.$B$BHere, $N, take this flask of pure water.  It will ensure that you receive a very powerful water totem.$B$BFarseer Nobundo awaits your return at the Exodar.',objectives_loc4='Take the Flask of Purest Water to Farseer Nobundo inside the Exodar on Azuremyst Isle.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have comported yourself with wisdom beyond your years, $N.  I can sense that the water element is pleased with your actions.  It will be my great honor to take the pure water that you bear and combine its essence into your new water totem.$B$BRemember well the lessons of water as you go forward and you will gain an even greater understanding and mastery of the element.' WHERE entry=9509;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='"Cookie" McWeaksauce at the Odesyus\' Landing wants you to bring him 6 Skittering Crawler Meat.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Bless yer heart. stranger. This\'ll go a long ways in liftin\' the morale o\' the crew.' WHERE entry=9512;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Elune be praised! The restless spirits may find tranquility after all.' WHERE entry=9513;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Take the Rune Covered Tablet to Priestess Kyleen Il\'dinare at Odesyus\' Landing on Azuremyst Isle.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='I can\'t read these runes but I know someone who can...' WHERE entry=9514;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='With Warlord Sriss\'tiz dead, the possibility of a naga invasion is now only a distant memory. We are safe, for the time being...$N$NI must admit, I was wrong to think badly of you, $N. You have shown that you are nothing like the filth that was Archimonde. Accept this as a gift from the night elves.' WHERE entry=9515;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I will not tolerate their existence on this world!  The Burning Legion all but destroyed our race and we fell back to settle a new home on a new world.  Then they came again.  And we retreated, over and over.$B$BNo more!$B$BThere is a remnant of the Legion to the south in the regions known as Felfire Hill, Demon Fall Canyon and Demon Fall Ridge.  They are what is leftover from a force that once long ago invaded this world.$B$BGo and destroy as many as you can before it is too late!',objectives_loc4='Slay 6 Mannoroc Lashers, 6 Felguards and 6 Searing Infernals, and then return to Vindicator Vedaar at Forest Song in Ashenvale.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have my respect and thanks, $C. Perhaps we\'ll be able to create a new home here without having to worry about the Burning Legion yet again.' WHERE entry=9516;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Welcome to Forest Song, $C. Where you see tents, there will one day be buildings, but such ambitions require a steady stream of building materials. I cannot bring myself to order our workers to fell any of the ancient trees of this grove, but our neighbors to the south and west have no such reverence for the forest.$B$BWe shall relieve the Warsong loggers of their excess, and reclaim some of the tainted wood from the satyr stronghold to the west. Bring the wood to Gnarl, who will purify it for our use.',objectives_loc4='Bring 15 pieces of Warsong Lumber and 5 Satyrnaar Fel Wood to Gnarl at Forest Song.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Wood cut with orcs\' crude blades is warped as surely as that exposed to elemental extremes. Nothing sound can be built with it, but I shall purify it and return it to Architect Nemos and his men for their use. Some good will come from this tragedy, after all.' WHERE entry=9517;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Sentinel Luciel Starwhisper at Forest Song wants you to kill Overseer Gorthak, 2 Warsong Shredders, 5 Horde Deforesters, and 10 Horde Scouts.',offerrewardtext_loc4='At last we have sent a message that the orcs won\'t dare ignore. Any overseer or foreman who sets foot within the camp to replace Gorthak will feel my wrath!$B$BWe must press our advantage, $N, and never rest until the Warsong Lumber Camp is a distant memory and a glade of trees stands upon that ground.' WHERE entry=9518;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring the Chalice of Elune to Kayneth Stillwind at Forest Song.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work, $N. There is certainly a latent power here, one that not even constant exposure to the corruption of the satyr can dim. Do you see how it still shines, after all these years?' WHERE entry=9519;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The demon dropped this parchment, which is amazingly written in the Common tongue!  The ones mentioned in it, Diathorus and Gorgannon, are the two infamous dreadlords that control the demons hereabouts.$B$BThe plans detail preparations for a demonic attack on Forest Song to the north; the location where a new draenei settlement is being established.$B$BPerhaps Vindicator Vedaar at Forest Song would be interested in these?',objectives_loc4='Deliver the Diabolical Plans to Vindicator Vedaar at Forest Song in Ashenvale.',offerrewardtext_loc4='By the Seven Crystals of Ata\'mal, this cannot be!  They plan to attack us here at Forest Song?!$B$BNot on my watch!$B$B<Vindicator Vedaar crumples the demon-scrawled plans in his fist.>$B$BNo.  We will not allow this to happen!' WHERE entry=9520;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The battle against the Warsong Lumber Camp isn\'t being waged from Forest Song alone, $N. There\'s a more substantial Silverwing Sentinel presence at Silverwing Grove to the southwest, near the border with the Barrens. From the grove, Sentinel Farsong directs our efforts against those who would destroy our lands.$B$BI\'m a bit late in sending my latest report to Sentinel Farsong, but also hesitant to leave Forest Song unattended. If your travels take you near Silverwing Grove, would you deliver my report?',objectives_loc4='Deliver Sentinel Luciel\'s report to Sentinel Farsong at Silverwing Grove.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you for delivering this report, $C. From what Sentinel Luciel writes, it seems our worst fears have come to pass. With each advance we make, the Horde appears more determined to do as much damage as possible.$B$BWe can\'t afford to back down; the fate of our ancestral lands hangs in the balance. With more people like you on the frontlines, I\'m certain we could triumph. Will you join our fight?' WHERE entry=9521;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='$N, it falls to you to see that this attack by the Burning Legion never comes to pass.  You must go and slay their leaders.  Without them the rest of the demons are essentially mindless.$B$BYou will find Gorgannon in Demon Fall Canyon south beyond Felfire Hill, near Mannoroth\'s floating, broken spear.$B$BDiathorus the Seeker resides somewhere in the barrow den atop Demon Fall Ridge.  To find the ridge, look for a ramp up from Demon Fall Canyon near the Horde\'s monument to Grom Hellscream.',objectives_loc4='Kill Gorgannon and Diathorus the Seeker, and then return to Vindicator Vedaar at Forest Song in Ashenvale.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Never again will the Burning Legion threaten us here! You have delivered us from a fight we very likely would have lost, $C.$B$BI give you thanks and the deepest gratitude of the Hand of Argus. It honors me to have you at our side.' WHERE entry=9522;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='My pappy would be proud! His boy strikes it big at the first set of night elf ruins he comes across... With your help, of course. Yes, don\'t worry, I won\'t leave you out of the discovery. You\'re a $R, right? Right, sure... $R. They\'ll learn all about you in Ironforge.' WHERE entry=9523;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I thank you, $N. I must admit I didn\'t expect a rescue party to be on its way.$B$BI will round up the remaining prisoners and lead them back to Honor Hold.' WHERE entry=9524;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I was fortunate to escape Kargath\'s prison today, $N.  Several prisoners are scheduled to be executed, an important officer among them.$B$BIt would be a huge blow against our forces if Captain Boneshatter was slain.  You must do what you can to rescue him.  I\'m too weak to go on...',objectives_loc4='Rescue Captain Boneshatter inside Hellfire Citadel before he is executed.$B$BThis quest must be completed in Heroic dungeon difficulty.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve brightened my day, $C. When I die, I will make sure it\'s in the battlefield... covered in the blood of my opponents and taking them down with me.' WHERE entry=9525;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Little one, to the south is an area of Nightsong Woods that has in recent times come to be called Felfire Hill.  It is very sad to see the demons crawling over it, spreading their corruption.$B$BWould you do something to help take back the land?$B$BI have a number of seeds that I have been saving for such a purpose.  Take them to Felfire Hill and plant them in the fertile dirt mounds.',objectives_loc4='Plant 8 Tree Seedlings in the Fertile Dirt Mounds and then return to Gnarl at Forest Song in Ashenvale.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Good. Though it may take a great deal of your years for the seedlings to grow into ancients, in the fullness of time they will aid us in our fight against the demons at Felfire Hill.$B$BGo in peace, little $Gbrother:sister;.' WHERE entry=9526;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $N. Their spirits will be at peace now.' WHERE entry=9527;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Tears of joy stream down Cowlen\'s face.>$B$BHow can I ever repay you for this, $N? Please, take this heirloom. It symbolizes a sacred bond of friendship, trust and love amongst night elves. You are a $Gbrother:sister; to me - from this day until the end of time...' WHERE entry=9528;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I must warn you, what I ask of you next will be dangerous. I won\'t think less of you if you decide not to help me out, $N.' WHERE entry=9530;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='My people have undertaken an important endeavor in the eastern part of Ashenvale, with support and cooperation from the kaldorei.$B$BUnder the supervision of Architect Nemos and Vindicator Vedaar, they are revitalizing an old night elf outpost. The task of building won\'t be easy, $N, for the challenges and enemies they face are many. I know Architect Nemos and his compatriots at Forest Song would appreciate any help they can get, and he has asked me to send any interested $G men:women; his way.',objectives_loc4='Make your way to Forest Song and speak with Architect Nemos.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s good to see another new arrival here at Forest Song.$B$BVindicator Palanaar is sending as much help as she can muster and each set of hands is appreciated.$B$BTake a look around, $C. It may not be much now, but with time and help from our night elf allies, we\'ll build a settlement worthy of calling home. There is much to be done here and any help you can provide would be welcome.' WHERE entry=9533;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The remains of the demonic Burning Legion have been making raids against our Warsong Lumber Camp!$B$BNo more!$B$BThe demons are attacking from the areas known as Felfire Hill, Demon Fall Canyon and Demon Fall Ridge to the east.$B$BGo and destroy as many as you can to bring glory to both yourself and the Horde!',objectives_loc4='Slay 6 Mannoroc Lashers, 6 Felguards and 6 Searing Infernals, and then return to Valusha at Splintertree Post in Ashenvale.',offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'s better!  There\'s nothing quite like ridding our world of a demon.  And they make for worthy opponents as well, unlike the weak races of the Alliance.' WHERE entry=9534;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Dreadlords!  They plan to attack us here at Splintertree Post?!$B$BNot while I still draw breath!$B$B<Valusha crumples the demon-scrawled plans in her fist.>$B$BNo.  We will not allow this to happen!  They are a blight upon our world!' WHERE entry=9535;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='$N, you will see to it that this attack by the Burning Legion never comes to pass!  Go and slay these dreadlords!  Without them the rest of the demons are essentially mindless.$B$BYou will find Gorgannon in Demon Fall Canyon south beyond Felfire Hill, near Mannoroth\'s floating, broken spear.$B$BDiathorus the Seeker resides somewhere in the barrow den atop Demon Fall Ridge.  To find the ridge, look for a ramp up from Demon Fall Canyon near the monument to Grom Hellscream.',objectives_loc4='Kill Gorgannon and Diathorus the Seeker, and then return to Velusha at Splintertree Post in Ashenvale.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Never again will the Burning Legion make slaves of the orcs, or any other race of the Horde!$B$BBravely fought, $C! You have the true heart of the Horde beating inside of you! You give us much honor!' WHERE entry=9536;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Spark must be brought to justice!$B$BI need you to go down to the beach and find that deceitful gnome. Once you find him, get whatever information you can out of him!$B$BIf a high ranking official of the Alliance has committed treasonous acts, who knows how many others are corrupt?$B$BAnd $N, use force if you have to...$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Incredible! This was all part of their master plan!$B$BThis information must reach the king and your own leaders. The implications are staggering.' WHERE entry=9537;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The totem has various primal markings. You see owls, bears, wolves and stags carved into the surface.$B$BYou note a strange collection of symbols that makes your mouth form the word A-K-I-D-A.' WHERE entry=9538;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The totem has various primal markings. You see owls, bears, wolves and stags carved into the surface of the totem.$B$BYou note a strange collection of symbols that makes your mouth form the word C-O-O.' WHERE entry=9539;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The totem has various primal markings. You see owls, bears, wolves and stags carved into the surface of the totem.$B$BYou note a strange collection of symbols that makes your mouth form the word T-I-K-T-I.' WHERE entry=9540;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The totem has various primal markings. You see owls, bears, wolves and stags carved into the surface of the totem.$B$BYou note a strange collection of symbols that makes your mouth form the word Y-O-R.' WHERE entry=9541;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='As you read the totem, your mouth forms the word V-A-R-K. You understand this to mean justice.' WHERE entry=9542;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Can I offer you any assistance, $N? You sound troubled.' WHERE entry=9543;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The images on this totem depict a war between the Stillpine and the Bristlelimb furbolg tribes. The etchings show that the Bristlelimb have done unconscionable things to the furbolgs of Stillpine.$B$BAmidst the chaos, a prophecy has begun to unfold: A hero will rise - not of furbolg blood - and save the Stillpine tribe.$B$BSlay Bristlelimb furbolgs at Bristlelimb Village for their keys. Use the keys to free the Stillpine captives. Return to Arugoo of the Stillpine when you have freed them all!$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='The prophecy spoke of one that would rise and deliver us from the oppressive grasp of Bristlelimb -- that the spirits themselves would herald the arrival of this hero.$B$BAnd now, you have come.$B$BI humble myself before you, great one.' WHERE entry=9544;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I hope the vision you witnessed helped you gain some perspective on Sedai\'s death.  The relic showed you a likely series of events leading up to the present.  The truth may have been different, we\'ll never know for sure.$B$BWould you act differently knowing what you know now?$B$BWho can say whether our conflict with the orcs will continue?  What\'s important is to remain open to the possibilities.' WHERE entry=9545;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='$N, Farseer Nobundo has been asking for you.  It must be time for you to learn the secrets of air, the last of the elements!$B$BI want you to know that I\'m very proud of all that you have accomplished thus far.  I know that you have great things ahead of you.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Farseer Nobundo at the Crystal Hall inside the Exodar on Azuremyst Isle.',offerrewardtext_loc4='And finally we come to it, the last of the four great elements: air. Do you think yourself wise enough to continue, $N?' WHERE entry=9547;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This is fantastic! The theft of my equipment has given me more insight into the nature of these murlocs than I could have possibly gained in weeks of observations!$B$BI know what I\'m going to say in my report already.$B$B\'When faced with the products of a technologically superior culture, the Blacksilt displayed none of the curiosity characteristic of emerging cultures in humanoid species.\'$B$BIt\'s brilliant! The gentlemen in Ironforge are going to love it! I can\'t thank you enough, $N.' WHERE entry=9548;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Astounding, simply astounding! These are perfect, $N. I can already see them under the glass in the museum in Ironforge. The text for the display is virtually writing itself in my head!$B$BYour help has been invaluable in getting my studies back on track. How do you spell your name? I\'ll make sure it appears in my report as co-author.$B$BOne of the chaps on the ship gave me this \'treasure map\' to cover a gambling debt, but mythology isn\'t my area of study. Superstitious lot, sailors.' WHERE entry=9549;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Examining the book carefully, you conclude that it must be a journal. Its pages are filled with an elegant script differing from that of the map. The text of many of the pages is obscured by drawings and writing in the mapmaker\'s hand.$B$BIt\'s nearly impossible to make out the text beneath the mapmaker\'s tales of drunken carousing during shore leave.' WHERE entry=9550;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='$N, Farseer Nobundo has been asking for you.  It must be time for you to learn the secrets of air, the last of the elements!$B$BI want you to know that I\'m very proud of all that you have accomplished thus far.  I know that you have great things ahead of you.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Farseer Nobundo at the Crystal Hall inside the Exodar on Azuremyst Isle.',offerrewardtext_loc4='And finally we come to it, the last of the four great elements: air. Do you think yourself wise enough to continue, $N?' WHERE entry=9551;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The great spirit of air calls out to you, $N, and it is time for you to take heed.$B$BI wish for you to travel up the Wildwind Path on the north facing of the mountain that the Exodar has crashed into.  At its peak you will find a cave and within will be one of my most accomplished pupils, Velaada.$B$BPlease, listen to her wisdom and do as she bids.  When you return you will have a greater understanding of the element of air.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Velaada at Wildwind Peak on Azuremyst Isle.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It was whispered to me on the winds that you would be coming, $C.$B$BFarseer Nobundo thinks very highly of you, and from what I have heard of your travels, so do I.' WHERE entry=9552;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='While air may seem ethereal, it is an all pervasive force, covering and permeating everything around us.$B$BThough you cannot see it, the rocks of this cave are composed mostly of air, the waters of the oceans are saturated in it and without it, fire cannot be sustained.  Just don\'t let those elements hear you repeat that!$B$BWho you really wish to speak with for such wisdom is nearby.  At the northern edge of the precipice, Susurrus awaits you.  It is from him that you will gain understanding.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Susurrus at Wildwind Peak on Azuremyst Isle.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I have been awaiting your arrival, $C. You come seeking wisdom, and something else I sense.$B$BVery well, let us begin.' WHERE entry=9553;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='While my brothers and sisters of the other elements have demanded that you perform various tasks, I will not ask anything further of you.  I think that you have done enough to \'atone\' for the accident of your ship falling to this place from my skies.  I can see that you have all the wisdom within you already to use the element of air wisely.$B$BTake this portion of my being back to Farseer Nobundo so that he might help you fashion your totem.  And when you\'re ready, I will fly you back down to the Exodar.',objectives_loc4='Return to Farseer Nobundo at the Exodar on Azuremyst Isle with the Whorl of Air.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I am proud of you, $N.  You have persevered where others falter, and in the process you\'ve gained a greater understanding of the elements and yourself.  Remember their lessons as you go through life and you will be the wiser for it.$B$BNow, hand me the whorl from Susurrus so that I may imbue it into your air totem.  As with the other totems, it will serve as both a focus and a reminder of the connection that you have forged with the elements.' WHERE entry=9554;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I am thankful that you have chosen the difficult path of the shaman. Few enough do, but I foresee it as critical to our future that we learn shamanism from the Broken.$B$BThey are called that, but once they were draenei. Fel magics transformed them, and that is why they cannot call upon the power of the Light. Some disapprove of them and the shamanism they teach, but they are not evil.$B$BI wish you to speak with Farseer Nobundo. He is the wisest shaman I know and you will learn much with his guidance.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Farseer Nobundo at the Crystal Hall in the Exodar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Greetings. It is always heartening to meet a $R who is open to the way of shamanism. There are so few.$B$BYou have learned not to judge the flame for its outward appearance, just as you should not judge mine.$B$BYou are here because you are ready to create your fire totem.' WHERE entry=9555;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hmm... this is most intriguing. Yes, I should be able to make out what the original author wrote in the pages of this book.$B$BI should have everything I need for the process. This should only take a moment.' WHERE entry=9557;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='How\'d you find us, $C?  No matter, I imagine you were sent here to give us a hand.  Let\'s get to work then!' WHERE entry=9558;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='For centuries, we lived in relative peace with the creatures of the land. Several months ago, Kurz began to see dark omens. The peace that we enjoyed for so long was to be lost. The extent of the catastrophe could not be known!$B$BSo it would be that the gods would shatter our land - turning both friend and foe against us. But there was something else... Amidst the chaos, a hero would rise: A hero not of Stillpine blood. The Promised One would deliver us from devastation.$B$BThat prophesied hero was you.' WHERE entry=9559;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Not only is the prophecy true, this armor is also amazing! Surely it is armor fit for a champion! And I will sell it to you at discounted prices, furless one.$B$BI jest... The first piece is complimentary.' WHERE entry=9560;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Grasses and shrubs cover an unnatural bulge in the earth.$B$BA few minutes spent digging reveals an old box, almost certainly the one mentioned in Nolkai\'s journal.' WHERE entry=9561;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Mmmmm... Delicious grain... Parkat will be delighted!' WHERE entry=9562;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Why. yes! You seem to be quite an OK $R. I suppose I can trust you.' WHERE entry=9563;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Gurf spits on the clump of fur and tries to affix it to the hairless patch on his backside.>$B$BThis will have to do for now! Hopefully one of the $C will be able to repair the damage.' WHERE entry=9564;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The blood crystal radiates a sickly aura that seeps into the water of the cave.' WHERE entry=9565;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='On the surface, the crystal appears to be a piece of the Exodar. Something has gone terribly wrong with this crystal, however, as it is blood red and rapidly dissolving into the water supply of the cave.$B$BThis may explain the unusually aggressive behavior of the creatures in Azuremyst. Return to High Chief Stillpine with this information.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='These blood crystals that you saw; my scouts have seen many more to the north.$B$BI thank you for aid but now ask that you leave me to confer with the elders. I will call for you once I have spoken with the other elders of the village.' WHERE entry=9566;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. Let me see what I can learn from this glyph, so we can plan our next move.' WHERE entry=9567;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Without their leader, and with the recovery of the corrupted crystals underway, we can safely keep the satyr in check. Light knows how many more of these wretched creatures are out there.$B$BHarbinger Mikolaas and I are grateful for the help you\'ve provided in dealing with the satyr before they could become a larger threat. Your work stands as a reminder that vigilance is the key to victory against the Legion and its minions.' WHERE entry=9569;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='After the crystal storm had subsided, a beast of myth appeared in our village. Brought here by the invading wildkin, this beast, the Kurken, laid waste to our village. Many Stillpine were slain in defense of our lands by this fiend and many have since lost their lives attempting to subdue the beast.$B$BIn my visions, I have seen one defeat the Kurken. The one must be you, $N. You are our only hope. Enter Stillpine Hold and slay the Kurken. Bring me his hide as proof of deed.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='The Promised One has emerged victorious!$B$BThe prophecy is nearly complete. Now about that hide...' WHERE entry=9570;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Take the Kurken\'s hide to Moordo, on the other side of the village. He will fashion the hide into an item of your choice.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='This is the strongest armor I\'ve ever made! Make good use of it, $N.' WHERE entry=9571;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Quick, there isn\'t much time.  Thrallmar\'s existence balances on the razor\'s edge!$B$BWe\'re caught between Hellfire Citadel in the west and the Burning Legion to the east.  With the Legion\'s attention turned toward the Dark Portal we must take this opportunity to strike at the fel orcs of Hellfire Citadel.  The key to this is to first break through their ramparts!$B$BGo there, slay their leaders, and then bring back proof to Caza\'rez across the room from me!',objectives_loc4='Slay Watchkeeper Gargolmar, Omor the Unscarred and the drake, Nazan.  Return Gargolmar\'s Hand, Omor\'s Hoof and Nazan\'s Head to Caza\'rez at Thrallmar in Hellfire Peninsula.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s a good start.  With those three dead their forces should be in disarray.  And with their artillery up there silenced we\'ll have an easier time getting close enough to take the citadel!$B$BBut there\'s more to this than meets the eye - I can feel it - so I\'m going to have something else for you to do.$B$BFor the time being, though, you\'ve done well.  Take your pick of any of these from the Thrallmar armory.' WHERE entry=9572;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Stillpine the Younger at Stillpine Hold on Azuremyst Isle wants you to slay Chieftain Oomooroo and 9 Crazed Wildkin.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='This may very well be the opportunity that we needed! I will send an attack at once! The Stillpine thank you for your service, $N!' WHERE entry=9573;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Bloodmyst Isle was forever changed by our arrival. The Exodar\'s crash scattered debris all over the islands and I think it\'s beginning to have an adverse effect on the wildlife.$B$BBefore I can be certain of my conclusion, I\'ll need to get a closer look. The crystals seem to have affected the trees the fastest, so it seems that the treants would be the most likely to show symptoms. If you bring me samples of bark from corrupted treants, I can begin my in-depth studies.',objectives_loc4='Bring 6 pieces of Crystallized Bark to Morae in Blood Watch.',offerrewardtext_loc4='There\'s more than enough here for my research. Thank you, $N. If you find any other evidence that the crystals are corrupting Bloodmyst\'s native creatures, let me know right away.' WHERE entry=9574;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Do you know what I hate worse than being wrong? Losing gold on a bet that you couldn\'t pull it off, sweetheart.$B$BOutstanding! With those three dead their forces should be in disarray. And with their artillery up there silenced we\'ll have an easier time getting close enough to take the citadel!$B$BI have a feeling there\'s more to this than meets the eye, though' WHERE entry=9575;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This is most curious, $C. I don\'t believe we\'ve ever seen the murlocs wearing any kind of adornment before.$B$BGiven the corrupting influence that the crystal shards are known to have, the murloc that wore this pendant must have believed it granted him power over his fellows. I wouldn\'t be surprised if he had rapidly outgrown his fellow murlocs and gained in strength.' WHERE entry=9576;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The corpse appears to be dressed in the manner of an Exodar technician, but the pendant described by Morae is absent.' WHERE entry=9578;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<You tell Morae of your findings in the wreckage of the Cryo-Core.>$B$BSo... he\'s...$B$BI guess I knew on some level, but just wouldn\'t let myself believe it. It\'s not the news I was hoping for, but you have my deepest thanks for finding Galaen.' WHERE entry=9579;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This will keep us supplied for quite a while, and preparing it for consumption will certainly keep me busy. Thank you for your help, $N.' WHERE entry=9580;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This crystal shard will give our researchers a baseline to compare against samples from other parts of the island, since it comes from one of Bloodmyst\'s less corrupted regions.$B$BI won\'t be able to send it off until we have a full set of samples, but this is a great start. If you\'re willing to help gather the other samples, I\'ll see to it that you\'re rewarded for your efforts.' WHERE entry=9581;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Ruada nods solemnly.>$B$BThen it is done.$B$BYou are ready for your next lesson, $N, but I will not be the one to teach it to you.' WHERE entry=9582;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Harbinger Mikolaas examines the crystal shard.>$B$BThis shard is much different from the initial sample.$B$B<Harbinger Mikolaas holds the crystal up to catch the light.>$B$BDo you see how it pulsates like that? That\'s worrisome. I\'ll make a note in my report of the alterations the blood elves appear to have made to this crystal. Thank you again for your help, $N.' WHERE entry=9584;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Harbinger Mikolaas accepts the last crystal from you.>$B$BThat rounds out the set. All that remains to be done is to box them and send them to the Exodar.$B$B<The harbinger seems glad to be done with the task.>$B$BDon\'t get me wrong, $N, I\'m sure the research is valuable, but we\'re faced with a number of other pressing problems out here.' WHERE entry=9585;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s signed by Illidan you say?! Let me have that.$B$B<The commander reads the letter, and then again a second time, thinking a moment before going on.>$B$BThis news that you bring is ominous indeed. Knowing this, we must accelerate our plans against Hellfire Citadel and this Blood Furnace. Because you have shown that you can get the job done, I want you to head up those plans.$B$BGunny will give you your next mission, though I suspect it will be far deadlier than your first.$B$BLight be with you, $N!' WHERE entry=9587;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Giving the lifeless form of Vazruden the Herald the once-over, you discover a rolled letter, its seal yet unbroken.  An elaborate "I" is pressed within the blood-red ink.  Cracking the note open, the message that you read is most disturbing.$B$BNazgrel back in Thrallmar will definitely want to take a look at this!',objectives_loc4='Take the Ominous Letter to Nazgrel at Thrallmar in Hellfire Peninsula.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s signed by Illidan you say?! Let me have that.$B$B<Nazgrel reads the letter, and then again a second time, thinking a moment before going on.>$B$BThis news that you bring is ominous indeed. Knowing this, we must accelerate our plans against Hellfire Citadel and this Blood Furnace. Because you have shown that you can get the job done, I want you to head up those plans!$B$BCenturion Caza\'rez will give you your next mission, though I suspect it will be far deadlier than your first.$B$BLok\'tar ogar, $N!' WHERE entry=9588;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Out-frikkin-standing!  As of right now Private $N, you are my favorite person on the sorry remains of this sorry planet!$B$BI\'m sure that the eggheads are going to wet themselves when I hand that blood over to them for study.  Who knows, maybe we\'ll find a new weapon in the fight against those damned fel orcs?' WHERE entry=9589;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='That letter is disturbing, and not just because it comes from the Betrayer.  We must know how they are creating these new fel orcs if we\'re to defeat them!  It\'s bad enough that we must fight the Burning Legion on our eastern flank, but now a new army of fel orcs to the west!$B$BYou must infiltrate this Blood Furnace inside Hellfire Citadel.  Bring back samples of blood from the fel orcs that you find in there.',objectives_loc4='Collect 10 Fel Orc Blood Vials and return them to Centurion Caza\'rez at Thrallmar in Hellfire Peninsula.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I am impressed with your abilities, $N.  Not once, but twice now you have infiltrated Hellfire Citadel for us and accomplished what was asked of you.$B$BI will see to it that this blood is delivered to those who can unlock its mysteries.  Who knows, perhaps we can find a way to reverse the process?' WHERE entry=9590;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='When the $C first begins $Ghis:her; path, $Ghe:she; learns only to kill.  Now it seems you are ready for more.$B$BThe Stillpine furbolgs have provided a means to master the skill of taming without months of study.  They are able to carve a totem into the likeness of an animal, which you can use to temporarily bond with a creature of that type.$B$BFor your first lesson, take this totem and use it on the barbed crawlers found along the western coast of the isle.',objectives_loc4='Use the Taming Totem to befriend a Barbed Crawler and return to Huntress Kella Nightbow when you have succeeded.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m sure the first thing you learned was how unsympathetic the crawler was during the bonding process.  It\'s all claws until they know you aren\'t there to throw them into a boiling pot.' WHERE entry=9591;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The crawler was undoubtedly mean, but the timberstrider will test your resolve.  More powerful allies require more tenacity from the hunter.$B$BTake this taming totem and befriend a greater timberstrider.  They are found in the northern reaches of Azuremyst Isle.',objectives_loc4='Use the Taming Totem to befriend a Greater Timberstrider and return to Huntress Kella Nightbow.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Looks like the timberstrider didn\'t peck your eyes out.$B$B<Kella looks away for a moment.>$B$BNot that I thought that would happen, of course!' WHERE entry=9592;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You probably noticed the big cats known as nightstalkers when you tamed the timberstrider.  They are efficient and deadly hunters... and allies.$B$BUse this taming totem to befriend a nightstalker.  Hunt with the vicious cat and keep it from harm.  When you are finished, return to me.',objectives_loc4='Use the Taming Totem to befriend a Nightstalker and return to Huntress Kella Nightbow.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I must say, $N, you have learned far more quickly than I first imagined.  Looks like we won\'t need to use this last taming totem.  And honestly, I\'m not even sure what it is.  It appears to be some sort of monstrous lizard with wings and a long tail.  Oh well, perhaps another time!$B$BYou\'ve experienced enough to try it on your own now, without the aid of a taming totem.  Good luck!' WHERE entry=9593;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done well in bringing this to me, $N. This is, without a doubt, an armor fragment from a felguard.$B$BThen, it is as I feared. The Nazzivus satyr are renewing their contacts with the Burning Legion. If we don\'t stop them, the satyrs and their demonic allies will overrun us. I will notify Harbinger Mikolaas right away.' WHERE entry=9594;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='<NYI>Hey little man, do something worthy and talk to Jonathan LeCraft.',objectives_loc4='<NYI>Log description.' WHERE entry=9597;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I am responsible for putting paladins on the path to greater virtue as they devote themselves to the Light and defend our people from threats.$B$BThe time has come for you to take your first step towards being truly virtuous. If you accept it, I will give you a tome of divinity. In studying it, you shall learn some about the Light, and what is expected of you. If you understand it, and are capable, then you will succeed in attaining greater abilities.',objectives_loc4='Study the Tome of Divinity and speak with Jol.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve spent time reading the book, I hope?$B$BThen you should be prepared to have yourself tested. There are always tasks to be done in the wake of the Exodar\'s crash throughout these new lands: acts of compassion and understanding...people who need help...creatures to slay...$B$BBy proving you have the patience to help others, especially those who are less fortunate, you prove that you are a servant of the Light and of sound mind.' WHERE entry=9598;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='In all things, paladins must reflect the Light, which supplements our strength. To strive to be divine for one of our kind does not mean we strive for godhood--we strive to be good in all actions.$B$BAlthough called upon to smite evil in these harsh times, you must always remember that it\'s aiding others that will truly set you apart from the other citizens. Compassion, patience, bravery--these things mean as much to a paladin as strength in battle.$B$BKnow this well, and never forget it.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Jol in the Exodar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you $N! I am glad that Young Furbolg Shaman is fine.$B$BYou truly are blessed with the Light! Therefore, you shall use it to brign back the light in everyone!' WHERE entry=9599;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Your task then, $N, is to aid our new allies, the Stillpine furbolgs.$B$BSeveral of the younger Stillpine shaman stumbled across a Bristlelimb camp and were slaughtered to the last.  Take this Symbol of Life and resurrect one of the shaman.$B$BBristlelimb Enclave is located to the east of the road just after you cross the bridge spanning Azuremyst and Bloodmyst Isle.  Speak with me when you have done this.$B',objectives_loc4='Jol wants you to resurrect a Young Furbolg Shaman with the Symbol of Life and return to her.',offerrewardtext_loc4='who.....who are you? .....Jol? Yes! Praise the Light! We are ok thanks to the forces Jol sent us to help in our battles. Yes I am fine...although I cannot say the same about my brothers....' WHERE entry=9600;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Exarch Menelaous takes the letter from you and begins to read it.>$B$BDamn them... Damn them all to the Nether. They\'ve had a spy watching everything that we\'ve done! And for how long?$B$BI will notify Velen at once!$B$BYou\'ve done us a great service, $N. Be on guard as I will be contacting you once the Prophet has given me instruction as to what to do.' WHERE entry=9602;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Welcome to Blood Watch, $C. Please excuse the disorder you see around you. It\'s easy to take simple things for granted, like a fully furnished and stocked inn, until you\'re forced to build one from nothing.$B$BWe\'ve managed to salvage this pod for a building, but without the proper furnishings and first aid supplies, the inn is little more than a glorified tent. Nurguni at the Exodar has offered to put together a package to help with our most immediate needs, but I need someone to deliver this list to him.',objectives_loc4='Take Topher\'s List to Laando, the Hippogryph Master at Blood Watch.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So you need to go to the Exodar?$B$BThat\'s going to be a long trip, but don\'t worry, I have a way to get you there very quickly.' WHERE entry=9603;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Purchase a hippogryph ride to the Exodar from Laando. When you land, take Topher\'s List to Nurguni in the Seat of the Naaru at the Exodar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So you\'ve brought Topher\'s list. Excellent! I was hoping to receive this today. Let\'s see what he needs.$B$B<Nurguni reads over the list and begins placing various items in a box.>$B$BThat\'s most of what he requested. The pieces for the beds are simply too large to be delivered by hippogryph, but I\'ll make arrangements to have them sent by wagon.' WHERE entry=9604;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Here\'s the box, $N. That should be enough for Topher to get the inn up and running. Let him know that he can keep sending in orders as the need arises. Blood Watch urgently needs a place to care for the wounded and put up any travelers they receive.$B$BWhen you\'re ready to return to Blood Watch, seek out Stephanos near the gates of the Exodar.',objectives_loc4='Find Stephanos outside the Exodar and purchase a hippogryph ride back to Blood Watch.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So you\'re headed back to Blood Watch with this package? No problem at all, $C. Just speak with me again and we\'ll get you on your way with those supplies.' WHERE entry=9605;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='If I remember correctly, Blood Watch\'s hippogryph master is Laando.  If you\'ve spoken to him before, then you can take one of my hippogryphs to him.$B$BThat\'s a good lesson to know: hippogryphs are always trained to fly to their capital city, but they\'ll only take you to a remote hippogryph master after you\'ve already been there.$B$BSince you arrived on one of Laando\'s hippogryphs, you can also use that route to return to Blood Watch with the caregiver\'s supplies.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Stephanos to purchase a hippogryph ride back to Blood Watch. Once you have arrived, deliver Nurguni\'s Supplies to Caregiver Topher Loaal.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Handing Topher the box, you tell him that Nurguni is making arrangements to have the larger items delivered by wagon.>$B$BSplendid! Now, I\'ll finally be able to set up some beds and a first aid station so that we can better treat the wounded and any survivors we encounter.$B$BI can\'t thank you enough for your help, $N. You have my thanks and that of the Blood Watch\'s vindicators.' WHERE entry=9606;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='THEY HAVE A PIT LORD?!$B$B<The force commander looks around at the stares of the others and then lowers his voice to a whisper.>$B$BThat seals it.  They must be using the blood from this pit lord to create new fel orcs that are somehow not aligned with the Burning Legion.  And if they can do this to the brown orcs, they can do it to the green ones too.  With all of the new Horde orcs streaming in through the Dark Portal, that\'s not good!$B$BWe must strike at the heart of their military might, and soon!' WHERE entry=9607;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='$C, you must gather a group to investigate the Blood Furnace inside Hellfire Citadel at once!$B$BThe magical scrying that we have at our disposal indicates that something unnatural is occurring in there.  But a powerful force inside is blocking any detailed arcane investigations, so it must be very important.$B$BYou should expect heavy resistance - no other mission that we\'ve sent in there has ever returned!$B$BScout it entirely and then report back to Nazgrel, advisor to Thrall, with what you witness.',objectives_loc4='Fully investigate the Blood Furnace and then report to Nazgrel at Thrallmar in Hellfire Peninsula.',offerrewardtext_loc4='THEY HAVE A PIT LORD?!$B$B<Nazgrel notices the glances of the others assembled and lowers his voice to a whisper.>$B$BThat seals it. They must be using the blood from this pit lord to create new fel orcs that are somehow not aligned with the Burning Legion. And if they can do this to the Mag\'har brown orcs, they can do it to us!$B$BWe\'ll have to strike at the heart of their military might, and soon!' WHERE entry=9608;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Magtoor has informed me that there\'s a stranded watcher nearby.  Apparently the caravan he was escorting from Darkshire was attacked by Lost Ones.  It sounds as if he\'s the sole survivor.$B$BHe\'s somewhere to the south.  Please, $C, lend him your aid.',objectives_loc4='Find Watcher Biggs in the Swamp of Sorrows.',offerrewardtext_loc4='What?  A draenei sent you here from the Harborage?  How odd.$B$BWell, I\'m not one to turn down assistance.  Thanks for coming, $C!' WHERE entry=9609;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I am interested in studying Azeroth\'s past and I\'m wondering if you\'d be willing to help?$B$BThere is a nearby place of historical significance within the swamp that I would like for you to venture to.  The Pool of Tears lies to the southeast.  It is said that upon its shores and within its depths are buried artifacts of the Atal\'ai troll civilization.$B$BBut beware, it is guarded by Somnus, an ancient green dragon, and his dragonkin, as well as carnivorous fish in the pool itself!',objectives_loc4='Obtain 10 Atal\'ai Artifacts and return them to Holaaru at the Harborage in the Swamp of Sorrows.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I thank you, $C.  The study of these artifacts should keep me occupied for some time.  How else are we Broken and draenei to fit in if we do not come to understand the history of your world?' WHERE entry=9610;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. Well done indeed! You are turning out to be a special $R - a cut above the others of your age. Take this as a reward!' WHERE entry=9612;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Deprecated: Keanna\'s Will',objectives_loc4='The Shattered Blade you found in Karazhan wants you to ask Koren to repair it.  You\'ll also need to attain Honored reputation with the Violet Eye to complete this quest.' WHERE entry=9613;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='By the beardless, geometric head of O\'ros! It is good you brought this to me, $N. These blood elves are out for... well, blood. Velen will be informed at once! Take this as a reward.' WHERE entry=9616;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The bodies of the $R survey team are scattered all over the ground here, pierced by naga weaponry. The area is littered with the remains of their supplies and survey equipment, but their data crystals are nowhere to be seen.' WHERE entry=9620;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It is done then.  The foul traitor got what he deserved.$B$BYou did this yourself?  An impressive feat that proves that your race remains worthy, $N.$B$BI see that Lor\'themar has additional news that will greatly improve his relations with Thrall.' WHERE entry=9621;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Visions you say? Interesting... And this prophecy has come to pass?$B$BBut you say they saw the power core of the Exodar? And O\'ros was also in the vision? What can it mean?' WHERE entry=9622;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Torallius sighs.>$B$BAlright, let me have a look at those orders.' WHERE entry=9623;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Did you have a difficult time finding enough? It\'s been taking me longer with each trip.$B$BSoon, I\'ll have to stop altogether since I won\'t be able to spare the time. Thank you for gathering the pears for me, $N. It gives me a chance to make a last pie or two before the season\'s out.' WHERE entry=9624;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well ya made it this far! Let\'s put ya to work before you get too bloodied up.' WHERE entry=9625;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I haven\'t lost any love for my homeland or its people, as you know.  I\'ve fought tooth and nail for Silvermoon to be allowed a place beside Undercity and Orgrimmar at the negotiating table.$B$BThis should silence any opposition. Take this letter to Thrall in Orgrimmar.  As leader of the Horde he will have the final say on accepting your race\'s pledge.$B$BI\'ve added my own seal to the letter as a personal endorsement.  Go northwest of the city and board the zeppelin bound for Durotar at the tower.',objectives_loc4='Lady Sylvanas Windrunner wants you to take the Letter Sealed by Sylvanas to Thrall in Orgrimmar, capital of Durotar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Thrall begins to read the letter.>$B$BSylvanas is a persistent one.  So she\'s sent one of Silvermoon\'s own champions... how does this change anything?' WHERE entry=9626;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Your people suffered a great betrayal by the Alliance.  You\'ve succeeded in fending off Darnassian attacks as well as spies from Ironforge.  Now you\'ve defeated a powerful Scourge leader at the footsteps of your home.  Your worthiness is no longer in question.$B$BIt is now apparent that you need us and we need you.  Return to Lor\'themar.  Tell him I received his message loud and clear.$B$B<The warchief crushes the letter inside his palm.>$B$BWelcome to the Horde, elf.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Your work has helped advance our race\'s cause a tremendous deal. Not only does Thrall believe we\'re capable of handling ourselves in the face of the enemy, he also believes he can use our link with Outland as a means to reach his people.$B$BNot exactly the truth, but not a lie either.$B$BBrace yourself for great changes, $N. We are now officially part of the Horde.' WHERE entry=9627;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<You tell Harbinger Mikolaas of the survey team\'s fate. He accepts the crystal from you, but remains silent for a long moment.>$B$BThey were good men, $N, and they knew their mission would be dangerous. I\'m grateful for your help in locating the team and recovering the crystal.$B$B<The harbinger\'s fists clench.>$B$BWe\'ve lost too many good men already, and our mission has only just begun.' WHERE entry=9628;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. I was worried that the marking device might malfunction, but it seems like everything went according to plan.' WHERE entry=9629;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Archmage Alturus at Deadwind Pass wants you go into Karazhan and speak to Wravien.',offerrewardtext_loc4='A vast wealth of information... I could spend years here!  I\'m sure Dalaran will understand...' WHERE entry=9630;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Alturus wants to raise a whole dragon back from the dead? Not an easy task by any stretch of the imagination.$B$BLet us discuss how we can be of mutual assistance, $N.' WHERE entry=9631;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Take the Letter of Introduction to Huntress Kella Nightbow.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I can help you get to Auberdine. Fortunately, it\'s only a short boat trip away!' WHERE entry=9632;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='The Way to Auberdine',objectives_loc4='Take the boat from the dock near Huntress Kella Nightbow to Auberdine. Once you have arrived in Auberdine, take the Letter of Introduction to Thundris Windweaver.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Thundris accepts the letter from you and reads it quickly, nodding.>$B$BThe isles the $R call Azuremyst and Bloodmyst were inhabited long ago by my people. Some of the threats faced by Anchorite Paetheus and his brethren are ancient enemies of the night elves.$B$BI am certain that the people of Auberdine are willing to provide what aid we can to our new allies. As soon as I have spoken with the townspeople and the sentinels, I will send word to Paetheus.' WHERE entry=9633;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. The ravager population will bear watching for some time to come, but we\'ve made a good start.' WHERE entry=9634;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='The Zapthrottle Mote Extractor!',details_loc4='Have you seen the swamp gas?  Isn\'t it just shiny?$B$BIt takes a Zapthrottle Mote Extractor to suck \'em dry though.  I could give you the plans to make one, but I really need some spare parts to fix stuff \'round here.$B$BLast time I checked, there were plenty of parts laying around near the steam pump at the Dead Mire to the northeast.  I think the withered giants broke the pump out there.$B$BShall we help each other out?',offerrewardtext_loc4='Shiny!  And really, what engineer ever has enough spare parts just hanging around?  Ooh, maybe I could sell off the extra and buy me some of that Tigule and Foror\'s Strawberry Ice Cream?!  I just love strawberries!  Do you think they have any around here?$B$BOk, ok, I guess you\'ve earned this, $N. Have fun!' WHERE entry=9636;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent, $N. I\'ve been trying to attempt these books for a very long time. It is fortunate that we were able to be of mutual assistance.' WHERE entry=9637;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Can\'t you see I\'m in the middle of something here? What do you want?' WHERE entry=9638;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The journal you speak of... I was sent here to look for it wasn\'t I?' WHERE entry=9639;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Did you find what you were looking for? You were looking for something, weren\'t you?' WHERE entry=9640;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done. These will provide the raw materials for another batch of enhancement crystals.$B$BYou\'re welcome to choose from among the three kinds of crystals I can make. I find each of them useful for stalking different kinds of prey.' WHERE entry=9641;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Very well, here are the crystals that I have, $N. Use them well.' WHERE entry=9642;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These seem sturdy enough to do the job. Thank you for your help, $N. Your contribution to Blood Watch\'s defense will not be forgotten.' WHERE entry=9643;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Our preparations are complete.  I have put the materials you gathered into this urn.  Take it to the Master\'s Terrace, where the fight took place, and set it on fire.$B$BThe energy released will bring life back to the charred remains of Arcanagos.  Defeat the creature and retrieve its essence immediately!  You will need to take it to Alturus.$B$BShould you fail, the stars predict you will have let a great terror loose upon the skies.$B$BA terror known as Nightbane!',objectives_loc4='Go to the Master\'s Terrace in Karazhan and use Kalynna\'s Urn to summon Nightbane.  Retrieve the Faint Arcane Essence from Nightbane\'s corpse and bring it to Archmage Alturus.',offerrewardtext_loc4='This is astounding! Not only have you brought back Medivh\'s Journal, but you\'ve also retrieved a fragment of his very essence.$B$BAs faint as this lingering essence is, it will reveal to us vital information about Medivh. We will not forget this, $C.' WHERE entry=9644;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Go to the Master\'s Terrace in Karazhan and read Medivh\'s Journal.  Return to Archmage Alturus with Medivh\'s Journal after completing this task.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It is a shame that the agents we sent succumbed to Karazhan\'s magic. At least you managed to obtain what they were after.' WHERE entry=9645;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done. From what I\'ve heard, it couldn\'t have been an easy fight. You\'ve more than earned your reward, $N.' WHERE entry=9646;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='In time, we\'ll have to devise a plan for returning the species to its native state, but for now, periodically culling their numbers is about the best we can hope for. Thank you for your help, $N.' WHERE entry=9647;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, I did warn you - did I not? Hopefully this payment more than makes up for the mild discomfort that you may have suffered. Return to me when you have gained strength and perhaps I will have another job for you - mushrooms of course!' WHERE entry=9648;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Good to see you again, $N! You were exceptionally efficient in completing the last task that I offered you. Perhaps you would be interested in another?$B$BTo the northeast lies Wyrmscar Island, home to a rare species of mushroom known as Ysera\'s tear - named after the green dragonlings that inhabit the island. I only require a small sampling of the mushroom, but I must warn you that the denizens of the island do not welcome visitors. Tread carefully.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='I hope this wasn\'t too strenuous a task, $N. Once again you have proven yourself a competent and considerate $R. I offer my gratitude and a small bit of monetary compensation.$B' WHERE entry=9649;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. This was a difficult test of your abilities, but you have passed with flying colors. To become a soldier of the Hand of Argus, you must pass many such tests.' WHERE entry=9663;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I am sorry that you had to do that, $N. Heavy-handed violence is not the $R way, but sometimes it is the only way.$B$BThis is one of life\'s truths that many do not understand until it is too late. So it was for our people, when we were slaughtered at the hands of the orcs.$B$BBecoming a Hand of Argus is a process of rebirth. And with birth comes pain...' WHERE entry=9666;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Once again you have proven yourself to be all that was prophesied. You have the eternal gratitude of the high chief $N -- and these Stillpine relics to choose from...' WHERE entry=9667;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I had a feeling that you would make it this far, $C. If you are willing to go further, I am willing to teach you...' WHERE entry=9668;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Incredible! Did you find any survivors?$B$B<Achelus lowers his voice to a whisper.>$B$BI\'ll be honest, $N; nobody else was willing to take on this mission. You are a brave $C...' WHERE entry=9669;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='It was a bloody mess, $N. We were ambushed by a large pack of these spiders. Their progenitor descended upon us with incredible speed and wrapped us up in cocoons.$B$BAfter we were webbed, she began to lay eggs near us. We were to be food for her young! FOOD!$B$BI managed to cut my way out and escape but I will not leave the others behind. So far I\'ve been unsuccessful in nearing the pass. Would you lend a hand?$B$BDestroy those cocoons! Hopefully some of our team is still alive!$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='You rescued over half the team! Word of your deed will definitely get back to Blood Watch and the exarch. Thanks again, $N.' WHERE entry=9670;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Expedition Researcher Freed' WHERE entry=9670;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Are you $N? It\'s about time! I\'d just about given up on finding you!$B$BThere\'s an urgent message waiting for you at the mailbox. The person that gave it to me was a human admiral from Azuremyst. Admiral Odesy-something... the name escapes me. He said you would know who he was.$B$B<Hermesius shrugs.>' WHERE entry=9671;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Dear friend,$B$BMy hand trembles as I ink this letter. I pray that it reaches you in time.$B$BLast night, Edward Hanes, captain of the ship \'Lost Hope\', appeared before me in my tent. The same Edward Hanes that died of scurvy 20 years ago.$B$BThis apparition told me a tale that made my heart tremble. A tale that I need you to hear and a mission that I need you to accomplish. Will you do it? Will you seek out Edward on Wyrmscar Island, northeast of your base?$B$BRegards,$B$BAdmiral Odesyus$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Have you heard of the bloodcurse, landlubber? No, of course you haven\'t. The bloodcurse is what sunk all these ships. The spoiled, desecrated part of the water here is known as Bloodcursed Reef - a part of the world you never want to visit. I\'ve been here myself for 20 years.$B$BScurvy my foot! I died on these wild shores as food for the dragons... Ah, but that\'s another story for another time. Right now, we have to help the poor souls that are trapped in that reef.' WHERE entry=9672;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Captain Edward Hanes on Wyrmscar Island wants you to kill 10 Bloodcursed Naga.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='A good start, but there\'s much more to be done!' WHERE entry=9674;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I am heartened by your initiative to speak with me. In the past I was responsible for the training of young paladins as they entered our order. This is a duty and privilege that I humbly take up once more. Your name has been mentioned as one who seeks to do good in the name of the Light. It would be my honor to guide you in your first steps as a $C.$B$BShall we begin?' WHERE entry=9676;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Undergo the First Trial' WHERE entry=9678;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent! Though small in size, this fragment is teeming with energy, I can feel it!' WHERE entry=9680;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done the hopeless ones a great service, $N. There is but one final task: Destroy the leader of the Bloodcursed.' WHERE entry=9682;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You did it! Hundreds of souls are grateful for all that you have done.$B$BAllow me to make an offering...' WHERE entry=9683;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A ritual? The owlkin had lived in harmony with the land for thousands of years. Such a thing is an aberration!$B$BSuch a pity...' WHERE entry=9687;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Prince Toreth at Wyrmscar Island has asked that you slay 5 Viridian Whelps and 5 Viridian Broodlings.',offerrewardtext_loc4='As reprehensible as your task was, it had to be done. Now you must look into the face of evil.' WHERE entry=9688;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='How long has it been? A thousand years? Ten-thousand perhaps? You have done me and the memory of my people a great service, $N. Please accept this item of power as a token of appreciation from Loreth\'Aran - in honor of your deeds.' WHERE entry=9689;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Return to Silvermoon City and report to Knight-Lord Bloodvalor promptly. Your arrival will tell him all he needs to know about the outcome of the trial.$B$BHe will tell you of your remaining tasks on the road to becoming an adept. Hold your head high, $N. Many undertake this trial, but very few return to tell of their success.',objectives_loc4='Return to Knight-Lord Bloodvalor in Silvermoon City.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I knew you had the potential to pass the trial, $N. Your remaining duties are mostly ceremonial, but they are no less dangerous than staring down one of our champions with his weapon drawn. Listen closely, and I will tell you what else you must do to claim your new rank.' WHERE entry=9691;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, $N... I\'ve heard about you. You\'re the one that made the Kessel Run in under 15 minutes, right? Bah, probably not.$B$BAre you ready to spill some blood in the name of the Light? For Velen? For Argus?$B$B<Boros laughs.>$B$BI\'ll slow down.' WHERE entry=9693;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have returned - and in one piece!$B$BI have some good news, $N. We have received some new information about the possible location of more survivors. A new crash site has been discovered! When I am done attending to those matters, I will call for you.' WHERE entry=9694;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Take the Sun King\'s Command to Vindicator Boros at Blood Watch.$B' WHERE entry=9695;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Elysia reads from the document.>$B$BIf what this document says is true, the blood elves have opened a portal to the Outland! It would certainly explain their seemingly endless numbers...' WHERE entry=9696;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh, good... help finally!  There\'s just so much to do, and I need to stay here to organize it all.$B$BI hope that you\'re ready to get your hands dirty.' WHERE entry=9697;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I need you to deliver the translated documents to Velen personally, $N. I don\'t trust that deranged messenger.$B$BExplain to the Prophet that the blood elves are receiving reinforcements from the Outland and that they have a spy amongst the draenei at the Exodar. Velen resides in the Vault of Lights inside the Exodar.$B$BMake haste!$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Velen begins to read the document.>$B$BInteresting... This does indeed explain much.' WHERE entry=9698;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s a good plan, but a dangerous one. I\'m sure you\'ll be fine.' WHERE entry=9699;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Velen states that if the blood elves have been opening rifts between this island and the Outland, there will be residue or anomalies left in the areas where the portals have been opened. You must search the island for locations that exhibit or display these anomalies.$B$BBe warned, $N; some of these anomalies will be creatures from the void itself. Should you find void anomalies, slay them! Report back to me with any new information that you may find. Begin your search to the north, near the Warp Piston.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='How many did you say you saw at the Warp Piston? Just how many times have they opened up this sun portal? This is very bad news...$B$BAlas, you have learned all that I am able to teach you, $N. Kuros will call for you when it is time.' WHERE entry=9700;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What?!  The bog lords of Quagg Ridge are EATING the sporelings\' pods?  This isn\'t good!' WHERE entry=9701;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This is what you found?  That\'s odd.  These husked mushroom remains are both unusual and somehow look familiar.$B$BI have to think on this a moment.  Don\'t go anywhere!' WHERE entry=9702;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We have others pursuing leads on the sun portals, $N. I need you to focus on the task at hand.$B$BBoros has received new reports of another crash site. What we\'ve since discovered is that the crash site is actually the Exodar\'s cryo-core. This is a pod holding area that houses pods exactly like the ones we draenei crawled out of in Ammen Vale.$B$BThis area also holds medical supplies. Head to the Cryo-Core, directly west of Blood Watch. Search for supplies and search for survivors.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Just blood elves? No survivors? This is troubling. I\'ll need some time to think this through, $N. Perhaps Aesom or Boros have an assignment for you to complete.' WHERE entry=9703;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The outrunner\'s belongings have all been stolen with the exception of one package. It seems to match Alarion\'s description of Erona\'s package.' WHERE entry=9704;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='By the Sunwell!  That\'s the third outrunner we\'ve lost this month.$B$BI appreciate your courage in venturing into Dawning Street.  The guards need to keep a closer eye on these blasted Wretched.' WHERE entry=9705;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Take Galaen\'s Journal to Vindicator Kuros at Blood Watch.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Kuros\' face turns pale as he reads the journal; tears stream down his face.>$B$BSaruan was my master... my teacher... my mentor... I took his place among the Triumvirate only recently - after we had given up searching for him.$B$B<Kuros\' face contorts in anger.>$B$BMatis...' WHERE entry=9706;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We definitely have a match here.  And the presence of the ogres and what they were doing there explains everything.  Now I get why it\'s called the Hewn Bog, duh!$B$BWe have to do something about this situation, but what?  We can\'t just wipe out all of those ogres; they have every bit as much a right to be here as any of the other creatures in the marsh!' WHERE entry=9708;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These are perfect!  Oh, thank you, $C!$B$BYou\'ve been ever so careful not to disturb the natural order of things, and we\'ve gathered so much information in such a short amount of time!$B$BNow, let\'s see if our little plan to grow a new food supply for the bog lords is going to work.' WHERE entry=9709;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Matis will be brought to justice, $N; and I want you to be the one to find him and bring him back to the Triumvirate.$B$BScour the island for this bastard. Should you find him, use this flare gun. When my trackers see the flare, they\'ll come and assist in capturing Matis. Return to me after he\'s been captured.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The Triumvirate has decided to try Matis immediately. You have brought an arch-criminal to justice on this day, young $R.$B$BYou have performed admirably for two of three; only Aesom remains.$B' WHERE entry=9711;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We can still use more of the sanguine hibiscus from the shamblers, bog giants and underbats of the Underbog at Coilfang Reservoir.  Bring them to me in bunches of five and I will be most grateful.' WHERE entry=9714;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These will do nicely, but we can always use more.  Perhaps you will find yourself in the Underbog again soon?' WHERE entry=9715;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The naga are behind this!  But why?  From what you describe, that steam pump must be part of the cause for the water levels dropping in the marsh!$B$BNo matter - this explains their open hostility towards us.  Let\'s not waste any time, I need you to perform another task for us.' WHERE entry=9716;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The sporeling makes a sound that is vaguely reminiscent of snorting laughter.>$B$BPerfect! No doubt the morale of the spore giants will be at an all time low once they realize what you\'ve done.$B$BEither that, or they\'ll be so incensed that they\'ll attack us again soon.$B$B<T\'shu makes a shrugging motion.>' WHERE entry=9717;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It is as I suspected.  The naga have set up pumping stations at all the major lakes in Zangarmarsh. $B$BThey must be stopped if the marsh is to have a future.' WHERE entry=9718;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Black Stalker is dead! Normally I would not revel in such butchery, but the pain that the great mother and her brood have put my people through over the centuries is unspeakable.$B$BIt is unfortunate that now another of her progeny will transform to replace her, but that will take time and give us some breathing room so that we will not have to worry about the marsh walkers for a while.' WHERE entry=9719;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It is done, then.  The marsh has been saved for now.$B$BDon\'t think for a second that this will be the last we hear of the naga.  We must remain vigilant of our enemy as we continue with our mission in Outland.' WHERE entry=9720;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Serpent Lake Controls Disabled',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Lagoon Controls Disabled' WHERE entry=9720;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The news you bring about the naga activity in Zangarmarsh is dire.  Ysiel was wise in sending word to us.  She hasn\'t forgotten that the Expedition cannot exist without the Circle\'s support.' WHERE entry=9724;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Gzhun\'tt nods to you.>$B$BWe are pleased that you have affirmed our friendship, $N. Perhaps the naga heathens will think twice about harassing us in the future now that we have such a powerful ally?' WHERE entry=9726;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Gzhun\'tt nods to you.>$B$BWe are pleased that you have reaffirmed our friendship, $N. Surely now that you have made our point clear multiple times, their senseless attacks upon our people will cease?' WHERE entry=9727;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good job, $N.  You\'d do well to shed any feelings of remorse you might harbor.  These naga are vicious creatures - even more so than the Azerothian ones.' WHERE entry=9728;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Little naga make Fhwoor angry!  Sporelings good friend to Fhwoor, so Fhwoor get naga ark.$B$BWe go into nearby naga village.  You help?  Bring friends!',offerrewardtext_loc4='Fhwoor\'s a good giant. We saved him from the naga a while ago and he\'s stayed here helping us with things ever since.$B$BWe can only hope that the naga will take the hint and realize that if we can infiltrate their village and steal their most prized possession, we can do much worse. Perhaps now they will return to their reservoir and leave us in peace?' WHERE entry=9729;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Slay Rajah Haghazed at the Lagoon and return to Warden Hamoot at the Cenarion Expedition in Zangarmarsh for a reward.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I didn\'t like the naga in Azeroth and I like them less here.  It\'s a real shame our mission could not remain a peaceful one, but you won\'t see me shedding tears for dead naga.$B$BHere\'s your reward for taking care of the Darkcrest leader, $N.' WHERE entry=9730;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Search Serpent Lake for signs of a drain.  Return to Ysiel Windsinger at Cenarion Refuge with news of your discovery.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The naga have turned Serpent Lake into a giant water sink for the rest of Zangarmarsh.  What could they possibly be doing?$B$BYou\'ve done well in bringing this news to us, $N.  We will send a team to investigate this drain you\'ve discovered.  I have a different task for you in the meanwhile.' WHERE entry=9731;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are a welcome sight, $N.  Matters at the Cenarion Refuge have only gotten worse since you left.' WHERE entry=9732;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Speak to Mahuram Stouthoof at Thrallmar in Hellfire Peninsula.' WHERE entry=9733;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='A Blood Knight master possesses incredible skill at wielding and weaving the Light in a way that other so-called \'paladins\' can never comprehend. It doesn\'t stop them from despising us for unleashing the Light\'s true potential.$B$BWe must send them a message and show them that we are not to be trifled with. What I have in mind will be neither brief nor easy, but if you are committed, the first step will be to infiltrate the library wing of the Tyr\'s Hand Abbey and procure a vial of Tyr\'s Hand holy water.',objectives_loc4='Lord Solanar Bloodwrath in Silvermoon City wants you to bring him a vial of Tyr\'s Hand Holy Water.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Hmm... this is a rather small amount. but if we\'re careful. it should be sufficient. You see. the Scarlet Crusade believes itself dedicated to the Light. I suppose they still are, in a twisted sort of way, and that\'s exactly what I\'m hoping to capitalize on.$B$BTheir misguided zeal has even tainted the blessing spoken over this water, making it ideal for my purpose.' WHERE entry=9735;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Now that we have the water, we\'re going to need a number of reagents in precise quantities. Some of these substances are rare and expensive, $N, but I have located sources for two.$B$BYou should be able to purchase some arcane catalyst from Zalle, the reagent vendor in one of the shops on the plaza near the Dead Scar. Darlia, the poison merchant near the rogue trainers on Murder Row, stocks crepuscular powder.$B$BTo complete my mixture, I\'ll also need an azerothian diamond and a pristine black diamond.',objectives_loc4='Lord Solanar Bloodwrath in Silvermoon City wants you to bring him 1 Arcane Catalyst, 1 Crepuscular Powder, 1 Azerothian Diamond, and 1 Pristine Black Diamond.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Now that we have all the reagents, I can prepare the mixture.$B$B<A slow smile spreads across Lady Liadrin\'s face.>$B$BIt\'s all coming together perfectly, $N. When this is finished, I\'ll give you the details about what remains to be done.' WHERE entry=9736;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Ours is the true way of utilizing the Light, $N. To show others that would call themselves \'paladins\' the folly of their ways, I intend to send an unmistakable message.$B$BThe Alonsus Chapel, where the Order of the Silver Hand was founded, seems immune to the destruction of Stratholme. The chapel\'s eternal flame affords it the Light\'s protection, but when you use this mixture to extinguish the flame, that protection will be no more. It will burn, and our dominion over the Light will be proven to the world.',objectives_loc4='Use the Extinguishing Mixture near the eternal flame in the Alonsus Chapel to remove the Light\'s protection. Be prepared to fight anyone who may attempt to defend the chapel.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. All who would oppose us would do well to heed the warning you delivered. Our foes should know that they are in peril, from the lowest foot soldier to the mightiest $Ghero:heroine;.$B$BYou have earned your place in the ranks of the masters. Your dedication and prowess serve as an example for all Blood Knights. As a symbol of your new status, I grant you the ability to summon and command the thalassian charger.' WHERE entry=9737;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m glad that some of my friends yet live, but it breaks my heart to hear of the fate of others. <sigh>$B$BAt least they died doing what they loved most in life. You have my eternal gratitude for helping me with this, $N.$B$BPlease, take one of these as a sign of gratitude.' WHERE entry=9738;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Weeder Greenthumb Discovered',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Windcaller Claw Discovered' WHERE entry=9738;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done it!  You have my people\'s thanks.$B$BI hope you understand... this is where our young ones come from.  We can\'t let these beasts devour the sacs!' WHERE entry=9739;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Smashing! We\'ve cut off their supply line. Now all that we need to do is finish them off!' WHERE entry=9740;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Kill 12 Void Critters and report to Vindicator Aesom at Blood Watch.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s a real mess up there, eh? You\'ve done well, $N. I\'ll send some anchorites out to help Loryi and Jorli.$B' WHERE entry=9741;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes! You\'ve saved more spore sacs.$B$BYou\'re different than the other outsiders. I\'ll let my people know about your deeds!$B$B<This quest is repeatable up to friendly reputation.>' WHERE entry=9742;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You made it back alive!  I\'ll let the other sporelings know about you!  $N, the giant slayer!' WHERE entry=9743;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Unbelievable!  It would take hundreds of sporelings to slay as many giants as you have.  I will make sure to let everyone know of your feats!$B$B<This quest is repeatable up to friendly reputation.>' WHERE entry=9744;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Vindicator Aesom at Blood Watch wants you to slay 10 Sunhawk Pyromancers and 10 Sunhawk Defenders.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='This will surely soften up their defenses and make them think twice before rushing foolishly into our ranks!' WHERE entry=9746;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $N.  I will finally sleep comfortably at night.  Were I not so old and weakened I would deal with my own enemies.$B$BTake this gold.  It is not much, but your kindness cannot go unpaid.' WHERE entry=9747;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='As I suspected, the water has turned red due to contamination from leaking core fluid.$B$BI hope you didn\'t swim in any of that contaminated water.$B' WHERE entry=9748;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='It was a bloody mess, $N. We were ambushed by a large pack of these spiders. Their progenitor descended upon us with incredible speed and wrapped us up in cocoons.$B$BAfter we were webbed, she began to lay eggs near us. We were to be food for her young! FOOD!$B$BI managed to cut my way out and escape but I will not leave the others behind. So far I\'ve been unsuccessful in nearing the pass. Would you lend a hand?$B$BDestroy those cocoons! Hopefully some of our team is still alive!$B' WHERE entry=9749;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Last night, Edward Hanes, captain of the ship \'Lost Hope\', appeared before me in my tent. The same Edward Hanes that died of scurvy 20 years ago.$B$BThis apparition told me a tale that made my heart tremble. A tale that I need you to hear and a mission that I need you to accomplish. Will you do it? Will you seek out Edward on Wyrmscar Island, northeast of Blood Watch?$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Have you heard of the bloodcurse, landlubber? No, of course you haven\'t. The bloodcurse is what sunk all these ships. The spoiled, desecrated part of the water here is known as Bloodcursed Reef - a part of the world you never want to visit. I\'ve been here myself for 20 years.$B$BScurvy my foot! I died on these wild shores as food for the dragons... Ah, but that\'s another story for another time. Right now, we have to help the poor souls that are trapped in that reef.' WHERE entry=9751;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You rescued one of my druids.  We could never repay you, $N.$B$BYou have my thanks as well as that of the expedition.' WHERE entry=9752;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I am in need of your services, $N. I have a plan to topple the entire Sunhawk army, but before we can progress, we need to gather some vital information.$B$BWe need to identify the weaknesses in their primary defense. Unfortunately, we have been unable to get close enough to the Vector Coil to gauge their defenses. If we could get the prisoner to talk, we could get the information that we needed to break through the line and destroy the Vector Coil.$B$BYou heard me, I want to blow the damned thing up.' WHERE entry=9753;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Our attempts at interrogation have failed miserably, $N. Torture is - of course - out of the question. What we need is a draenei on the inside.$B$BI can cast a spell upon you that would make you appear blood elf and adjust your language. Through subterfuge, we may be able to get the information we need out of the captured agent.$B$BUnder this guise, I want you to get whatever information you can out of the prisoner.$B$BAnd $N, do not leave Blood Watch while disguised as the spell will fail.',offerrewardtext_loc4='A-ha! Well done, $N. Well done, indeed. Are you ready to eradicate the blood elf menace from our island forever?' WHERE entry=9756;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh good, there you are! And just in time... there is much to be done!' WHERE entry=9758;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have saved the whole of Bloodmyst and Azuremyst, securing the $R way of life on Azeroth, $N! For this, there can be no amount of thanks, no reward, nothing large enough in scope to truly express our appreciation.$B$BYet, there are still so many that were left behind on Draenor who cannot be here for this historic event. You must find your way back. Find your way back to the Outland, Hero of Argus. Bring our people home. Home to the land that you saved. Home to Azeroth...' WHERE entry=9759;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Speak with Vindicator Corin at Vindicator\'s Rest on Bloodmyst Isle.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Perhaps you will be the one to deliver our people into a new age of prosperity and peace.' WHERE entry=9760;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Only the most battle hardened, noble and positively fearless of draenei will submit to Legoso\'s mission. The exarch will not order any agent of the Hand to take on the task of destroying the Vector Coil and dispatching Sironas. He refuses to send any draenei to their death - which is what the mission is: suicide...$B$B<Corin sighs.>$B$BMy job is to soften up the Sunhawk defenses. You are to slay Sunhawks near the Vector Coil and keep the path clear for our champion - whoever that may be.',objectives_loc4='Vindicator Corin at Vindicator\'s Rest wants you to slay 8 Sunhawk Saboteurs and 8 Sunhawk Agents.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Hopefully a hero arrives before they are able to call forth reinforcements to guard the area you just secured.' WHERE entry=9761;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These islands will serve as the home to thousands. Most of these people will remain here their entire lives. If you so desired, you could do the same. But that\'s not what you want, is it, $N?$B$B<Velen nods.>$B$BYou will do many more great things before you pass. You must embrace your destiny and meet it head on!$B$BBefore you leave, I present you with two gifts: This tabard is worn by only the most revered of the Hand of Argus and this signet ring worn by our wisest sages. Wear them both with pride, $N.' WHERE entry=9762;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Our biggest enemy in the region is finally dead. You\'ve done the expedition a great favor, $N.$B$BWe shall be forever in your debt.' WHERE entry=9763;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Vashj!$B$BThis is much more than we bargained for. Our small victories here and there against the naga mean nothing.$B$BIf Lady Vashj is involved in this, then forces much greater than us are at work.$B$BYou\'ve done well in bringing this to us, $N. Now, we must prepare for war.' WHERE entry=9764;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These will do perfectly, $N. Bring any more armaments you find. Our need is great and our resources are scarce.' WHERE entry=9765;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work, $N. The naga will learn not to underestimate us.' WHERE entry=9766;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Defeating an enemy requires more than superior power or numbers.  Victory often hinges on knowledge of an opponent\'s weaknesses, the anticipation of their plans or the recognition of a behavior pattern.$B$BWe know much about the naga, yet much of their magical practices remain foreign to us.$B$BI seek to learn of the Hydromancy used by the naga of Coilfang Reservoir.  Bring me one of their spellbooks so I may learn more about it.',objectives_loc4='Obtain a Coilfang Spellbook from the naga inside of Coilfang Reservoir and bring it to Ashyen at the Cenarion Refuge in Zangarmarsh.' WHERE entry=9767;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These be fine ones, $N. Here\'s your payment.$B$B<Magasha bends one of the wings and holds it up to her head.>$B$BNope, not my thing, but who\'m I to complain?$B$B<Magasha shrugs.>$B$BCoin speaks.' WHERE entry=9769;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Had your fill already?$B$B<Reavij laughs.>$B$BThere\'s a reason why our visitors don\'t stay long.$B$BIf I had a choice, I\'d find a more agreeable spot for the post, but I\'ll take marshfangs over Denjai\'s temper any day.' WHERE entry=9770;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Search for Scout Jyoba.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The battered corpse matches Zurai\'s description perfectly. Whatever killed the scout appears to have taken him by surprise, as his weapon is sheathed and the contents of a small inkwell stain the nearby ground.' WHERE entry=9771;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Zurai accepts the report from you and glances over it.>$B$BMuch of this is information we already know. Everything in the area seems to be dried or wilting, but here\'s something new.$B$BHe says the fungal giants seem to have gone berserk from the lack of moisture. From your description, that must be what killed him.$B$BI\'ll instruct my men to avoid the area. We can\'t afford any more casualties.' WHERE entry=9772;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Finally, a break from the monotony of mushrooms! If you didn\'t smell like fish, I\'d hug you.$B$BLet\'s see how jealous the others get when they smell the meat cooking over the fire.' WHERE entry=9773;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $N. Every little bit helps.$B$BI\'ve still got a long way to go, but let\'s face it, what else am I going to do between patrols?' WHERE entry=9774;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring Zurai\'s Report to Shadow Hunter Denjai in Zabra\'jin',offerrewardtext_loc4='Why didn\'t you say you had a report from Zurai? I\'ve been waiting to hear from him.$B$BI sent him out there to give us a presence on the eastern border, not sit on his hands. Let\'s see what he has to say.' WHERE entry=9775;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Speak to Ikuti at the Orebor Harborage.',offerrewardtext_loc4='If Anchorite Ahuurn counts you a friend, then you may prove trustworthy. Please forgive my wariness, $R, but it is often all that stands between my people and death. You are welcome to shelter among us, and perhaps our mutual trust will grow.' WHERE entry=9776;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These are good spores and they should keep us going for quite some time. Thank you for helping us to replenish our supplies, $N.' WHERE entry=9777;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ysiel sent you? Of course I can use someone like you! We\'re always in need of a little muscle.' WHERE entry=9778;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Vindicator Boros eyes the document.>$B$BThis is in Thalassian. Fortunately, I know just the person that can translate it...' WHERE entry=9779;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you for your help, $N. Your generosity will not be forgotten. As a token of my gratitude, I\'ve prepared a hot drink for you.' WHERE entry=9780;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done. That should ease the demand on the food supply around here for the immediate future, although we\'re going to need to find new sources of food. Fish and mushrooms suffice, but variety can never be underestimated.' WHERE entry=9781;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hmm... The soil seems to be depleted, so it can\'t be the cause of the problem, as I\'d thought. What\'s the common link here? Why is everything suddenly dying?' WHERE entry=9782;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you for helping with this difficult task, $N. Our work in the Dead Mire is not yet done, but now our efforts will focus on doing what we can to restore balance to the area.' WHERE entry=9783;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent.  Keep bringing me more plant parts if you find any.$B$B<This quest is repeatable up to Honored reputation.>' WHERE entry=9784;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve returned.  Did you receive the ancients\' blessings?' WHERE entry=9785;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So, the Feralfen Lost Ones have taken over the ruins? Most intriguing. They must remember something of their heritage and the significance of the site. We must learn more, $N. This temple could hold the key to redeeming the Lost Ones and reuniting the many threads of draenei.' WHERE entry=9786;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These should be more than sufficient, $N. They seem to be fixated on birds, which is odd, because there aren\'t any bird species native to Zangarmarsh. What could this mean?$B$BCould they have encountered the arakkoa? To a shamanistic people, they might seem like the embodiment of a powerful bird spirit.' WHERE entry=9787;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='My things!  They\'re all here!$B$BI thank you, $N.  As promised, I\'ll let you pick one of the items for yourself.  I don\'t have much to offer, but my people have always shared what little we have.' WHERE entry=9788;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Hunt down 30 Clefthoof and return to Hemet Nesingwary at Nesingwary\'s Safari in Nagrand to prove yourself.',offerrewardtext_loc4='A fair start. But that\'s just the beginning.$B$BThe lesser clefthoof prove nothing. Let\'s move you up to a bigger challenge' WHERE entry=9789;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $N.$B$B<Haalrun smiles sympathetically.>$B$BAt least you don\'t have to clean them. That\'s the worst job of the lot, but once it\'s done, you\'d never know they were attached to a giant insect.' WHERE entry=9790;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you for your help in clearing out some of the marshfang rippers, $N. If they had any intelligence, perhaps they\'d learn that it\'s best to live and let live.$B$B<Noraani shrugs.>$B$BGiant, overgrown bugs with intelligence. I wonder what that would be like...' WHERE entry=9791;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You\'ve been honorable in our dealings, $N, at a time when trust is hard to win among my people.$B$BA large group of my brethren have made their home in the old draenei city of Telaar in Nagrand, to the south. To reach Telaar, take the road south into Nagrand, then continue southeast until you find yourself in the cliffs east of Oshu\'gun.$B$BAnyone who has aided us, as you have, would be welcome among the people of Telaar.$B$BSeek out Nahuud and tell him you have earned my trust.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Nahuud at Telaar in Nagrand.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m flattered that your Broken friend considers me a scholar of his people\'s relics, but to be honest, I haven\'t had much chance to study them since my arrival here. It was certainly my intent, but when I arrived, I found that there were other matters that required my attention.' WHERE entry=9792;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hmm... I remember hearing our scouts speak of the ruins of a draenei settlement in the forest\'s northern reaches. I don\'t know much about the ruins, personally, but you\'re welcome to talk to some of the scouts.' WHERE entry=9793;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So you\'ve brought Timothy\'s response?$B$B<Kialon pauses a moment to read the letter, then laughs.>$B$BHe\'s got everything under control, he says. Doesn\'t need help, he says. I could\'ve predicted that!$B$BSome people never change. Look, he even took the time to correct my spelling.$B$B<Kialon lets out a half-hearted sigh.>$B$BI shouldn\'t have sent the letter. I forgot. The specialist always has the situation under control. Always.' WHERE entry=9794;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Denjai seeks help? I\'d send him reinforcements, but we\'re spread thin here as it is. We\'ve got trouble of our own with the ogres up here.$B$BWhen I can, I\'ll give him what information we have on the local ogre tribes and their tactics. Perhaps if he can survive long enough, we\'ll be able to launch a two-pronged assault on the vile scum.' WHERE entry=9795;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s about time he got that outpost up and running. We\'ve lost far too many runners to Alliance outriders.' WHERE entry=9796;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Even though he endeavors to hide it, a look of relief spreads over Kroghan\'s face.>$B$BIt\'s about time you got here! Granted, you\'re not an army, but any able-bodied $R than can wield a weapon or chant a spell is welcome here. The people of Garadar are kin to all the Horde and we are proud to shed our blood in their defense.' WHERE entry=9797;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Here, let me read those plans.$B$BThe blood elves have followed us here?  They are evil to the core and should be wiped from existence!$B$B<The vindicator takes a moment to regain his composure.>$B$BI apologize, that was uncalled for.  We are indebted to you for uncovering this information, $N.' WHERE entry=9798;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These look like fine specimens. Thank you for performing the field work. Once I can find the time to analyze these, I should be able to tell what it will take to restore the fields.' WHERE entry=9799;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Elementalist Lo\'ap at the Throne of the Elements in Nagrand wants you to bring him 15 Digested Caracoli.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Please do not wash yourself in the sacred waters of the Throne.$B$B<Elementalist Lo\'ap holds a prepared caracoli tablet up.>$B$BYou place this under your tongue and allow it ample time to dissolve. Once it has dissolved, you will be able to breathe water as if it were air.' WHERE entry=9800;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Anchorite Ahuurn at Telredor wants you to bring him 4 Spore Bat Eyes and 4 Fen Strider Tentacles.',offerrewardtext_loc4='These will do quite nicely. Allow me a moment to mix up the potion.' WHERE entry=9801;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The decrease in native species is certainly a cause for concern.  The increase in invasive species could be related to the recent disturbance in the ecosystem.  I don\'t have enough information to make a conclusion, yet.$B$B<Lauranna jots down some notes on a journal as she goes through the plant parts.>$B$BTake these, $N.  They might be of some use to you.$B$BBring me any other plant parts you find.  I\'ll incorporate them into my statistics.' WHERE entry=9802;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='They refused? They are welcome to choose their own path, of course, but their choice surprises me. I would think that all the draenei, including the Broken and Lost Ones, would still remember that we\'re all a part of the same people.$B$BI suppose he is right about the folly of deceiving them, but still, could he not see that our intentions were friendly?' WHERE entry=9803;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Elementalist Lo\'ap at the Throne of the Elements in Nagrand wants you to destroy 12 Lake Spirits.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Elementalist Lo\'ap kneels in the water and says a prayer.>$B$BThe Earthen Ring takes no pride in what was done. We do what we must to heal the land.' WHERE entry=9804;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Your efforts have stifled the spread of pollution but other troubles have surfaced.' WHERE entry=9805;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Southern Hut Destroyed',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Eastern Hut Destroyed' WHERE entry=9805;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Gshaff wants you to gather 6 Fertile Spores from the various Zangarmarsh Spore Bats and Marsh Walkers.  Return to Ghsaff at Sporeggar when you\'ve completed this task.',offerrewardtext_loc4='These are great spores, $N!  Tallstalks are vital to rebuilding our town.  And after all the bog lord attacks we\'ve suffered, we\'re in quite the short supply.' WHERE entry=9806;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Your help is appreciated, $N. You will keep it up, yes?' WHERE entry=9807;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This will help us trade with other sporelings for food and supplies. Sporeggar thanks you, $N!' WHERE entry=9808;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Elementalist Lo\'ap at the Throne of the Elements in Nagrand wants you to destroy Watoosun\'s Polluted Essence and 10 Lake Surgers.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The elements sang of your victory the moment the disturbed essence was destroyed! The Earthen Ring thanks you and wishes for you to choose a reward.' WHERE entry=9810;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Friend of the Sin\'dorei',details_loc4='This is the beginning of a new chapter in blood elf history, $N.  You\'ve helped cement the bond between my race and yours, $R.$B$BTake the traitor\'s head to Regent Lord Lor\'themar Theron in Silvermoon City.  He\'ll be eager to hear the news.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So you killed Dar\'Khan, $R?  Impressive.  I\'ve a feeling my people and yours will soon get to be very good friends.' WHERE entry=9811;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I haven\'t lost any love for my homeland or its people, as you know.  I\'ve fought tooth and nail for Silvermoon to be allowed a place beside Undercity and Orgrimmar at the negotiating table.$B$BThis should silence any opposition. Take this letter to Thrall in Orgrimmar.  As leader of the Horde he will have the final say on accepting the sin\'dorei\'s pledge.$B$BI\'ve added my own seal to the letter as a personal endorsement.  Go northwest of the city and board the zeppelin bound for Durotar at the tower.',objectives_loc4='Lady Sylvanas Windrunner wants you to take the Letter Sealed by Sylvanas to Thrall in Orgrimmar, capital of Durotar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Thrall begins to read the letter.>So the blood elves finally took care of their little problem.  Never mind that it took your help as well as that of an entire Forsaken regiment to get the job done.<Thrall breaks into laughter.>I suppose there\'s no stopping this.  In the end we need them just as much as they need us. Welcome to the horde Blood Elf.' WHERE entry=9813;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These be excellent, mon!$B$BI\'ll tell you what. Since you been a good sport and helped with the mushrooms, I\'ll let you in on the fun!' WHERE entry=9814;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Earthen Ring thanks you, $N. The elements also give their thanks. Your continued efforts in cleansing our world are appreciated and noted.$B' WHERE entry=9815;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work, mon! I do hope they had a good time!' WHERE entry=9816;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'ll bet the Bloodscale will think twice about attacking expedition scouts again.  Take this as a reward, $N.  You\'ve earned it.' WHERE entry=9817;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Gordawg appears to be nodding at you.>$B$BSit.$B$B' WHERE entry=9818;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Bring up the usurper. You will find him. Follow earthen path. First you put to rest tortured earth spirits. Must sleep once more.$B$B<Gordawg smashes his fist into the ground and brings up very foul smelling soil.>$B$BMust sleep!$B$B<Gordawg points southeast.>$B$BFind spirits near mountains. Near hills. Near rocks. Near earth.$B$BPut to sleep.$B$BTelaari Basin... Southeast.$B',objectives_loc4='Gordawg at the Throne of the Elements in Nagrand has asked that you destroy 15 Tortured Earth Spirits.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Gordawg nods in approval.>$B$BGood. Spirits sleep now.' WHERE entry=9819;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. The presence of these ogres so close to our outpost does have me worried, though. It seems like they\'ve been filtering down from the northern mountains for some time.' WHERE entry=9820;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Gordawg at the Throne of the Elements in Nagrand has asked that you bring him 15 Enraged Crusher Cores.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Gordawg spits out the chewed up rock, pelting you with a hail of rubble.>$B$BPoison. These rocks are not Nagrand. These rocks are from poison. You destroy poison rock. You find usurper.' WHERE entry=9821;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Shadow Hunter Denjai examines the plans.>$B$BI knew it! The stench of ogres always carries an implicit threat. Now that we have proof of their intentions, we must act before they do.' WHERE entry=9822;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Your victory over the Ango\'rosh is to be celebrated, $N. I wonder how long it will be before those ogre brutes find themselves another bloodthirsty chieftain.$B$BNo matter, we\'ll be ready for them.' WHERE entry=9823;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These readings do not bode well, $N. Karazhan should be emanating all manner of arcane currents... instead it has become a huge energy vacuum. No signals. Nothing. Except for a very faint demonic echo.$B$BThis is bad news, $N.' WHERE entry=9824;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Fascinating. I will study these essences, $N. I thank you for your help.' WHERE entry=9825;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='These signs do not bode well for us, $N.  I\'ve never been one for secrecy so I will tell you a bit about my organization, the Violet Eye.$B$BWe are agents of the Kirin Tor, the Magus Senate of Dalaran.  We were assigned to keep an eye on Karazhan and Medivh, in case things got out of hand.$B$BWhich they did... very quickly, after Medivh disappeared.$B$BThis report details my findings.  Take it to Archmage Cedric, also from the Violet Eye; you will find him in the outskirts of Dalaran.',objectives_loc4='Bring Alturus\'s Report to Archmage Cedric in the outskirts of Dalaran.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You know of the Violet Eye? You do not look familiar.' WHERE entry=9826;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Take the Withered Basidium to Ruam in Telredor.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It looks like the basidium of a bog giant. but I haven\'t seen one in this condition before. I\'d heard that the giants in the Dead Mire had begun to wither. but it\'s far more advanced than I expected.$B$BThe Dead Mire was once a lake like the others in the marsh, and it served as the spawning ground for the giants. With the waters receding, it seems the changes are preventing the giants from sporing. If this continues, the giants may disappear entirely.' WHERE entry=9827;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring the Withered Basidium to Reavij at Swamprat Post.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It looks like the basidium of a boglord, but I haven\'t seen one in this condition before. I\'d heard that the giants in the Dead Mire had begun to wither, but it\'s far more advanced than I expected.$B$BThe Dead Mire was once a lake like the others in the marsh, and it served as the spawning ground for the giants. With the waters receding, it seems the changes are preventing the giants from sporing. If this continues, the giants may disappear entirely.' WHERE entry=9828;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Violet Eye? You don\'t say.$B$BShow me this report you speak of.' WHERE entry=9829;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you for bringing this venom, $N. It will go a long way toward making my demonstration possible without depleting my personal stores.' WHERE entry=9830;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done well, $N.  I wasn\'t sure you would succeed.$B$BThe containers are enchanted with a potent spell that masks their presence from unworthy eyes.  I\'m glad to see they did not elude you.' WHERE entry=9831;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have the fragments. This is most impressive, $N. You\'re certainly worthy of holding the key to Karazhan.$B A small problem remains.' WHERE entry=9832;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'s excellent news. The way is still far from perfectly safe, but the messengers are clever and resourceful.' WHERE entry=9833;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These are good hides, Maktu thinks. They will make very good armor.$B$BWho knows? There might even be enough left over for Maktu to make some armor for the draenei.' WHERE entry=9834;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Ango\'rosh threat is contained for the moment, but I\'m certain they won\'t give up that easily. I\'ve forgotten many things since the end of my life as a draenei, but the stubbornness of the ogres is an enduring memory.' WHERE entry=9835;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That key, I recognize it. That is Kadghar\'s key... of course I haven\'t given it to him yet.' WHERE entry=9836;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='His own key? That\'s incredible!$B$BI do not sense any disturbances in our timeline, so I suppose it was meant to occur all along. There\'s no turning back now, $N. The key is yours and only yours.' WHERE entry=9837;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I sent you to deliver a report and you come back with a key to this place? There must be more to you than meets the eye, $N.' WHERE entry=9838;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='At last! You have our thanks for your help in securing our position at the Orebor Harborage. I will send word of your deeds to the Kurenai city of Telaar in Nagrand. There will be many more opportunities for our peoples to work together.' WHERE entry=9839;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Koren looks at you with an uncertain look.>$B$BI know nothing of this Violet Eye you speak of. A blacksmith is all I am.' WHERE entry=9840;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I thought so. I can hear the difference already. I\'ll finally be able to get back to work, thanks to you. If you ever find yourself in need of tradeskill supplies, don\'t forget ol\' Gambarinka!' WHERE entry=9841;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You found the log. I sure hope the information we need is in here, $N.' WHERE entry=9843;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You did it! Yes, the readings are becoming normal once again!$B$BWe must give this news to Cedric. He\'s going to be very impressed with your achievement.' WHERE entry=9844;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I can\'t wait to return to fishing! Now I\'ll be able to return to town with some real fish in my bucket and Gambarinka won\'t be able to make fun of me anymore!' WHERE entry=9845;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hmm... They seem to be divided between images of a serpent spirit and a bird spirit. No self-respecting Darkspear troll engages in bird worship. Their spirits are weak, capricious, and best left to the Amani.$B$BBut the serpent, $N, the serpent wields considerable power and this is the spirit I shall study.' WHERE entry=9846;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Timothy leafs through the manual.>$B$BThey\'re using ragveil as a base for the poison? No, that can\'t be right. Ragveil has no toxic properties.$B$BIncluding ragveil in a poison is like a rogue wielding two maces. Sure, you can do it, but it isn\'t true to the essence of your calling! I just can\'t understand...$B$B<Timothy clears his throat.>$B$BI mean, thank you for fetching these for me. I\'ll try out the poison as soon as time permits.' WHERE entry=9848;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='GUROK! Gurok betrayed the elements!' WHERE entry=9849;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You\'ve proved to me that you can find and take down a regular clefthoof, but far more dangerous are the clefthoof bulls.$B$BBag yourself thirty of those.  Then you can talk to me of your hunting prowess.$B$BLook for them all along the middle region of Nagrand to the west and south.',objectives_loc4='Kill 30 Clefthoof Bulls and then speak to Hemet Nesingwary at Nesingwary\'s Safari in Nagrand about your prowess.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Impressive. Most impressive.$B$BYou\'ve got potential, kid. Now I\'m going to give you the chance to have some real fun!' WHERE entry=9850;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Banthar is the fiercest and most elusive of all the clefthoof in Outland.  She\'s also the hairiest.$B$BIt is said that she roams with her clefthoof herd in the Field of Spirits near Oshu\'gun.$B$BYou want to truly prove your hunting mastery?  Bring me her horn!',offerrewardtext_loc4='You did it! You took down Banthar! I never had a doubt, $N.$B$BHere, I think you\'ve more than earned this.' WHERE entry=9851;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='$N! You bring joy to this old dwarf\'s heart.$B$BYou have now proven yourself; you\'ve joined the ranks of the elite! Others ran away in fear, or died, trampled under the foot of the beast. You used your mind, your cunning, your determination to prove your mastery of the hunt.$B$BTake this and know that you are always welcome to hunt at my side!' WHERE entry=9852;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Gordawg chomps down hard on Gurok\'s earthen head, nearly disintegrating the stone formation.>$B$BGurok\'s reign has come to an end. The earthen elements are free. All sleep now. Champion gets reward!' WHERE entry=9853;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Kill 30 Windrocs and then return to Fitz at the Nesingwary Safari in Nagrand.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Every day is a gift.  Make the most of it.  For tomorrow we shall stride swifter over the plains than today.  We will spread our arms further and strain to achieve that which tonight we can only dream of, though it may ever elude us.' WHERE entry=9854;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Hunt down 30 Ravenous Windrocs and then return to Fitz at the Nesingwary Safari in Nagrand.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have proven your skill once more, $C. Now you must go on to stalk the fiercest of the windrocs.' WHERE entry=9855;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Her eye looks as if it is still alive. Do you think that she can still see into your soul?$B$B$N, you can now count yourself as one of the elite safari hunters. And you are another step closer to stalking the ultimate prey of this land, Tusker!$B$BYou\'ve earned the right to have this. May it serve you well.' WHERE entry=9856;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Kill 30 Talbuk Stags and then return to Harold Lane at the Nesingwary Safari in Nagrand.',offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'s a good tale... <cough>...of how you bagged all of those stags, $C. But I think that you can do better. I\'ve got something else in mind for you.' WHERE entry=9857;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Hunt down 30 Talbuk Thorngrazers and then return to Harold Lane at the Nesingwary Safari in Nagrand.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<cough>, <cough>... $N! You did it. There\'s only...<cough>... one thing left to...<cough>... do then.' WHERE entry=9858;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='<Wracking cough.>$B$BDon\'t worry about...<cough>... me.  I\'ll be fine.  It\'s just a...<cough>... scratch.$B$BJust the same, I think you\'ll... <cough>... have to fill in for me one more... <cough>... time.$B$BYou must seek out the great Bach\'lor, king of...<cough>... the stags.  It\'s ok if you... <cough>... take friends along.$B$BBring me one of his hooves...<cough>, <cough>... as confirmation.$B$BLook for him...<cough>... leading his herd in the far west of Nagrand.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Wow! You did it! That\'s really Bach\'lor\'s hoof!$B$BUm, I\'m starting to feel much better it would seem. Here, let me give you something in celebration of your proven hunting prowess!' WHERE entry=9859;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Speak to Archmage Cedric in the Outskirts of Dalaran.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Alturus told me all about what happened, $N. This is not the end of it, however. With Karazhan remaining sealed to outsiders, it\'s only a matter of time until the Legion renews its attacks while we stand powerless in the sidelines.$B$BUnless you accept the responsibility that fate has bestowed upon you, that is.$B$B<Cedric extends an open palm towards you, holding a badge with the Violet Eye\'s symbol on it.>$B$BWhat do you say, $N?' WHERE entry=9860;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It is a distress call, $R. An outside force is attempting to subvert the elements.' WHERE entry=9861;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Elementalist Morgh at the Throne of the Elements in Nagrand wants you to slay 8 Murkblood Putrifiers.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You saw them controlling the elements? The wind bent to their will?$B$B<Morgh is lost in thought for a moment.>$B$BThis is troubling, $N. I must consult with the others.$B$BWe thank you for your efforts, $N. Perhaps you should return to your village and see if they have any other information about the Murkbloods and their nefarious goals.' WHERE entry=9862;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Murkblood Leaders...',details_loc4='We have lost many friends in recent weeks.$B$BFor decades we have dealt with the ogres of Nagrand but now a new threat has arisen. The Broken tribe of Murkblood attacked our fishing village to the southwest, Sunspring Post, and managed to kill or evict all of the orcs that inhabited the town.$B$BWhile the others feel that the best course of action is to kill indiscriminately, I know that we must destroy their leadership. I do not know who their leader is but I suspect that you will know when you find him.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So, this is the face of our enemy? I will have this put upon a pike and placed outside of Garadar, near the gates. Should they think to attack us again, they will see the consequences for their actions looking down upon them...' WHERE entry=9867;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What does it matter? The Greatmother is dying. Life is not worth living...' WHERE entry=9868;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, thank you for the message. Perhaps you would not mind helping out the Earthen Ring? The elements are in flux. We can use all of the assistance that we can get.' WHERE entry=9869;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, thank you for the message. Perhaps you would not mind helping out the Earthen Ring? The elements are in flux. We can use all of the assistance that we can get.' WHERE entry=9870;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The parchment holds a crudely painted map of Nagrand. There is a big red \'X\' where Telaar would be on the map. It would seem that these savages are planning an attack on the city. Take the Murkblood invasion plans to Arechron in Telaar.$B',objectives_loc4='Take the Murkblood Invasion Plans to Arechron.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Arechron slams his fist into his hand.>Ortor... Treacherous bastard!' WHERE entry=9871;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Garrosh crumples up the map and throws it into the fire.>$B$BWhat\'s the use? They\'ve been attacking us for weeks. This is nothing new.$B$BDon\'t you understand? We\'re done for... Greatmother Geyah is dying.' WHERE entry=9872;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A thousand dead orcs you say? What could have triggered such an audacious advance into orc lands? It is good that he is dead but there is more to this than what meets the tentacle.' WHERE entry=9873;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Otonbu the Sage at Telaar in Nagrand wants you to use the Torch of Liquid Fire to destroy 10 Sunspring Villager corpses. Return the Torch of Liquid Fire when the task is complete.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Otonbu sighs.>$B$BThis will set back any chance of peace with the orcs another 10 years. At least we will be around to see those years as opposed to what could have happened had those corpses been allowed to rot.' WHERE entry=9874;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A new species! Are you sure?$B$B<Lauranna flips through pages of notes and diagrams.>$B$BNice job, $N. We\'ll have to add this one to our list. How does "Purple Leafed Ororarium" sound to you? It does have a ring to it.' WHERE entry=9875;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Ysiel Windsinger wants you to look for signs of Cenarion Expedition Druids near the entrance to Coilfang Reservoir.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank Cenarius you showed up.  My injuries prevented me from going back to the outside for help.' WHERE entry=9876;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Janeda\'s sending you to rescue the Deatholme prisoners? She must think very highly of you, $N.' WHERE entry=9877;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Poli\'lukluk the Wiser at Telaar in Nagrand wants you to kill 20 Murkblood Scavengers and 10 Murkblood Raiders.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It is doubtful that the orcs will understand or appreciate what you just did but Nagrand is better off for the deed. Thank you, problem solver...' WHERE entry=9878;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes, I know of the totem... but there is much more to this story. Alas, I lack the authority to reveal this information to you. Only the chosen may be privy to such knowledge.' WHERE entry=9879;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Color me impressed.  These are in excellent condition, for the most part.$B$BI will make sure to put in a good word for you with our people.' WHERE entry=9882;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Consortium is well known for taking good care of its friends. At the beginning of each month I\'ll have some gems ready for you as payment for your services.$B$BThe quality of the gems you get will depend on how loyal you\'ve been to us. Here\'s to hoping you do the smart thing and stay with us.' WHERE entry=9884;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Consortium is well known for taking good care of its friends. At the beginning of each month I\'ll have some gems ready for you as payment for your services.$B$BThe quality of the gems you get will depend on how loyal you\'ve been to us. Here\'s to hoping you do the smart thing and stay with us.' WHERE entry=9885;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Consortium is well known for taking good care of its friends. At the beginning of each month I\'ll have some gems ready for you as payment for your services.$B$BThe quality of the gems you get will depend on how loyal you\'ve been to us. Here\'s to hoping you do the smart thing and stay with us.' WHERE entry=9886;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Consortium is well known for taking good care of its friends. At the beginning of each month I\'ll have some gems ready for you as payment for your services.$B$BThe quality of the gems you get will depend on how loyal you\'ve been to us. Here\'s to hoping you do the smart thing and stay with us.' WHERE entry=9887;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Kilrath speaks in a hushed tone.>$B$BThese ogres are extremely peculiar. They are also extremely stupid. Look how the fat one makes the, um, lesser fat ones dance. It\'s mesmerizing.' WHERE entry=9888;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Let me live and I\'ll tell you whatever you want to know!' WHERE entry=9889;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='For many years, Boulderfist ruled all ogres in the Outland. The ogres were united under Krol and content with the lands that they were given. In the past few months, we have lost many ogres to a new clan known as Warmaul. Warmaul has taken most of our land in Nagrand and killed many of our people.$B$BWe had no choice but to take this town. We are being exterminated...$B$BKrol has gone missing and Boulderfist is in turmoil. Lantresor of the Blade rules in his absence.$B',objectives_loc4='Take the information that you beat out of Unkor back to Kilrath in Terokkar Forest.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Slow down, $N. I am but a lowly rogue. I have no idea what to do with such information.' WHERE entry=9890;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We\'ll make a good profit on these, $N. I\'ll make sure Khoraazi hears about your work here.' WHERE entry=9892;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent. This will keep us in business while we wait for the Sha\'tar to finish whatever housekeeping it is they need to do inside Oshu\'gun.' WHERE entry=9893;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have my gratitude, $N, and that of the watchers. They will be heartened to hear that they can continue their work to the south without fear of attack.' WHERE entry=9894;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Now that you\'ve seen the symptoms of imbalance with your own eyes, be mindful of them in your travels.' WHERE entry=9895;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I can\'t thank you enough. I\'m going to enjoy this...' WHERE entry=9896;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, I couldn\'t see if you helped out with saving Kristen, or not. But if she handed you one of her bundles of skins then you\'re alright in my book.Here\'s your reward.' WHERE entry=9897;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Fantastic! I\'ll never forget how you helped me to win her heart. In fact, you can be a guest of honor at our wedding.' WHERE entry=9898;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='At least someone is pulling $G his:her; weight around here. Thank you for taking care of that matter, $N. I need to have a word with Zurai about Reavij. His scheming and daydreaming have gone on long enough.' WHERE entry=9899;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We won\'t have to worry about Gava\'xi anymore, thanks to you.  Let us arrange for your reward now.' WHERE entry=9900;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. I think you and I have managed to outshine a whole team of prospectors. When I get back to Ironforge, I\'m sure I\'ll get my choice of assignments.' WHERE entry=9901;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $N. Perhaps with the help of the draenei, this marsh will one day be free of naga. I can\'t imagine what it must be like to be forced to serve them.$B$BHe doesn\'t talk about it often, but Maktu was once a slave.' WHERE entry=9902;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m sure the old boy must\'ve seen his days coming to an end. With all these new arrivals, the old order couldn\'t stand. It\'s just as well his spirit is at rest now.' WHERE entry=9903;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='At last! They say every great fisherman has a story of "the one that got away," but I haven\'t yet met a creature I couldn\'t beat one way or another.' WHERE entry=9904;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Maktu nods approvingly.>$B$BMaktu is thankful for your help. Maktu\'s pride is satisfied. He will not be caught off guard again.' WHERE entry=9905;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring "Count" Ungula\'s Mandible to Watcher Leesa\'oh.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Are you sure that\'s real? I mean, I knew there was large wildlife in the marsh, but there are giant creatures and then there are GIANT bugs.$B$BCome to think of it, the sporelings did mention a story about a fearsome nether ray that used to terrorize them before the boglord incursion.$B$BWhat if the stories are true? Oh, dear. I\'d better take that for safekeeping. The expedition will want to know about this.' WHERE entry=9911;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Welcome to Cenarion Refuge, $N.  I hope you\'ve come to aid us in our mission.  We\'ve much work ahead of us.' WHERE entry=9912;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Are you ready to get to work, $R? I think I\'ve got the perfect task for you.' WHERE entry=9913;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Never doubted you for a second, friend.  Most of those look like fine specimens, if a bit dirty and scratched up.  Still, I think they\'re worth the value we agreed upon previously.$B$BI hope that we can continue to do business in the future.' WHERE entry=9914;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Bintook reads the plans.>BY THE LIGHT! Their penmanship is atrocious. From what I can gather, they\'re either planning to "eat the blue skins and take their village" or bake a blueberry pie. It really could go either way. We must get to the bottom of this!' WHERE entry=9917;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh my! This is a small scouting and hunting party? You must tell Mo\'mor what you have discovered.' WHERE entry=9918;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Go to Sporeggar, north of the Spawning Glen, and deliver the Salvaged Spore Sacs to Msshi\'fn.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve helped protect the next generation of sporelings, $R. We can only repay you by welcoming you into our homes. Stay for a bit and meet the other sporelings. They will have many questions, I hope you don\'t mind.' WHERE entry=9919;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So, a new tribe of ogres is forcing the Boulderfist further and further south. This is quite troubling. We must first deal with the situation closest to home...' WHERE entry=9920;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Mo\'mor the Breaker at Telaar in Nagrand wants you to kill 15 Boulderfist Crushers and 15 Boulderfist Mystics.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent. Did you happen to locate this Lantresor creature that the stupid one\'s letter mentioned?$B$BRegardless, we must press on. I have gotten reports of more ogre activity that must be dealt with at once!' WHERE entry=9921;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Mo\'mor the Breaker at Telaar in Nagrand has asked that you slay 25 Boulderfist Warriors and 25 Boulderfist Mages.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work! I am currently researching the Warmaul tribe that the Boulderfist lieutenant mentioned. Now the tasks you have performed must be tested.' WHERE entry=9922;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='HELP! They\'re gonna eat me! I just know it!$B$BFind the key, I know it has to be on one of these ogres.$B$BIf you get me out of here, my father will reward you handsomely! He\'s the leader of Telaar, Arechron.$B',objectives_loc4='Find the Boulderfist Key and Free Corki. Speak with Arechron in Telaar should you succeed.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m really sorry about this, $R. He\'s always getting himself into trouble. I just wish I could put a leash on him...' WHERE entry=9923;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='<Arechron sighs.>$B$BThis is so embarrassing. Do you remember my boy, Corki? You rescued him from the Burning Blade Ruins recently. Well, his curiosity has gotten the best of him once more. He told me that he was going to investigate the Boulderfist menace for \'uncle\' Mo\'mor and ran off to the ogre mounds in the Halaani Basin, north of here.$B$BDo you think you could track him down? I would be eternally grateful.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you so much, $N. His mother will deal with him from now on.' WHERE entry=9924;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Zerid at Aeris Landing in Nagrand wants you to kill 12 Voidspawn near Oshu\'gun.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You bring a smile to my face, $N.  Or you would, rather, if I had a face.$B$BKeep it up and you and I are going to be the best of friends.' WHERE entry=9925;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Lantresor of the Blade at the Burning Blade Ruins in Nagrand wants you to drive 20 Warmaul Ogre Banners through the bodies of Kil\'sorrow members at Kil\'sorrow Fortress.$B$BReturn any unused Warmaul Ogre Banners.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Can you imagine their puzzlement over what is happening, $R? This will be glorious.' WHERE entry=9927;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Lantresor of the Blade at the Burning Blade Ruins in Nagrand wants you to collect 20 Kil\'sorrow Armaments.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent! Our next target will be the Laughing Skull Ruins.' WHERE entry=9928;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Lantresor of the Blade at the Burning Blade Ruins in Nagrand wants you to drive 20 Kil\'sorrow Banners through the bodies of Warmaul ogres at the Laughing Skull Ruins.$B$BReturn any unused Kil\'sorrow Banners.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The plan is perfect, $N. I am already seeing the fruits of your labor.' WHERE entry=9931;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I must admit, I have not felt this alive in decades. You have performed well, $N.' WHERE entry=9932;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='<Lantresor points to an unmarked crate.>$B$BTake it. It is my offering to your people. You have single-handedly saved my clan from extermination.$B$BYou may tell your leader that Lantresor of the Burning Blade and his Boulderfist ogres accept the offering of peace.$B$B<Lantresor bows.>',objectives_loc4='Take the Burning Blade Peace Offering to Arechron at Telaar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Please, $N, take from the peace offering whatever it is that you may desire. After all, without your efforts, this would not have been possible.' WHERE entry=9933;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Slay Giselda the Crone and any combination of 15 Kil\'sorrow Agents. Return to Warden Bullrok at Garadar should you complete this task.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The crone has been slain! This is wonderful news, $N. Here is your reward.' WHERE entry=9935;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Slay Giselda the Crone and any combination of 15 Kil\'sorrow Agents. Return to Warden Moi\'bff Jill at Telaar should you complete this task.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The crone has been slain! This is wonderful news, $N. Here is your reward.' WHERE entry=9936;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You have destroyed two of the biggest threats in Nagrand, $N. Are you ready to take on the scourge of the Spirit Fields?$B$BDurn the Hungerer lords over the area surrounding Oshu\'gun, decimating all in his path. Thus far, none have been able to rid Nagrand of this ferocious gronn. Gather your allies and venture to the Spirit Fields, far southwest of here, near Oshu\'gun, and track down Durn. Slay him and I assure you rewards commensurate with the difficulty of the task at hand.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Durn\'s murderous grip has been loosed! Nagrand has a brighter tomorrow because of you, hero. Well done!' WHERE entry=9937;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You have destroyed two of the biggest threats in Nagrand, $N. Are you ready to take on the scourge of the Spirit Fields?$B$BDurn the Hungerer lords over the area surrounding Oshu\'gun, decimating all in his path. Thus far, none have been able to rid Nagrand of this ferocious gronn. Gather your allies and venture to the Spirit Fields, west of here, and track down Durn. Slay him and I assure you rewards commensurate with the difficulty of the task at hand.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Durn\'s murderous grip has been loosed! Nagrand has a brighter tomorrow because of you, hero. Well done!' WHERE entry=9938;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Slay Zorbo the Advisor, 10 Warmaul Shaman and 10 Warmaul Reavers. Return to Warden Bullrok if you manage to complete this task.',offerrewardtext_loc4='This is a great victory for the people of Garadar! Well done, $N!' WHERE entry=9939;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Slay Zorbo the Advisor, 10 Warmaul Shaman and 10 Warmaul Reavers. Return to Warden Moi\'bff Jill if you manage to complete this task.',offerrewardtext_loc4='This is a great victory for the people of Telaar! Well done, $N!' WHERE entry=9940;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thirty orcs, $R! Of those original thirty, only Ungriz and I remain. We found the young orc, Saurfang, nearly dead near Sunspring. Apparently he was here for another reason...$B' WHERE entry=9944;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Elder Yorley at the Mag\'hari Procession in Nagrand has asked that you slay 15 Warmaul Brutes and 15 Warmaul Warlocks.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It is a good start, but their leader must be dealt with for your actions to have any lasting impact.' WHERE entry=9945;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Have you ever seen an ogre king, $R? Few have and lived to tell the tale. Unfortunately, that is exactly what we are dealing with here.$B$BThe leader of these barbarians is an ogre named Cho\'war. Rumor has it that Cho\'war was the ogre responsible for forcing the gronn out of the cave. Cho\'war then declared himself king and dissolved the ogre clans that served under the gronn. Thus, Warmaul was born.$B$BFind Cho\'war deep in the caves of Warmaul Hill. Slay him and bring me his head.',objectives_loc4='Elder Yorley at the Mag\'hari Procession in Nagrand has asked that you slay Cho\'war the Pillager and retrieve the Head of Cho\'war.',offerrewardtext_loc4='This head will be posted at the gates of Garadar for all to see. The ogres will think twice before interrupting sacred Mag\'hari rituals.' WHERE entry=9946;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Elder Ungriz at the Mag\'hari Procession in Nagrand has asked that you free 15 Mag\'har Prisoners.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done what none thought was possible and brought back our missing brothers and sisters. You are a hero to the Mag\'har, $N. All will know your name and the deeds that you have performed for us.$B' WHERE entry=9948;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s for the best, really.  If it cannot civilly accept an invitation then it has no business attending.$B$B<Warden Treelos looks momentarily confused.>$B$BWho are you and what are you doing here?  You must get out of here quickly before it is too late!' WHERE entry=9951;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='So Andarl is certain Deirom is being held in Veil Shalas? That\'s the largest of the arakkoa settlements that we know of.$B$BVeil Shalas is in the far south of the forest, close to the eastern rim of the Bone Wastes. Unfortunately, I don\'t have much information on it, but there is an Explorers\' League member camped down there who may be able to help you. Prospector Balmoral\'s camp is perched on the very edge of the land to the southwest of Veil Shalas. Consult him before making any move against the arakkoa.',objectives_loc4='Locate and speak with Prospector Balmoral.' WHERE entry=9952;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='So Kurgatok is certain Dugar is being held in Veil Shalas? That\'s the largest of the arakkoa settlements that we know of.$B$BVeil Shalas is in the far south of the forest, close to the eastern rim of the Bone Wastes. Unfortunately, I don\'t have much information on it, but we have a scout camped down there who may be able to help you. Lookout Nodak\'s camp is perched on the very edge of the land to the southwest of Veil Shalas. Consult him before making any move against the arakkoa.',objectives_loc4='Locate and speak with Lookout Nodak.' WHERE entry=9953;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='They\'ve got me locked up good this time, $N. The Warmaul king, Cho\'war, has the key.' WHERE entry=9954;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='They call him Cho\'war the pillager, $N. He\'s the ogre that forced out the gronn that used to rule over these ogres. You better believe he\'s powerful!$B$BThe chef said that Cho\'war lives in the big cave - wherever that may be... Get that key and get me out of here! If we live through this, my father will no doubt give you the big reward! As soon as I\'m free, seek him out.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $N. Corki\'s been sent away to live among the night elves in Blade\'s Edge. Hopefully they\'ll be able to keep him out of trouble.$B$BAbout that reward...' WHERE entry=9955;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Huntress Kima at Telaar in Nagrand wants you to recover 20 Telaar Supply Crates.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Amazing! How did you manage to carry all of that back by yourself?' WHERE entry=9956;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m glad that the refuge sent you.  The druids of the thicket have been slain!  Only myself and one other have survived, and he\'s insane.$B$BI don\'t know what happened, but I intend to get to the bottom of it.  Whatever it was, it happened quickly and feels unnatural.$B$BWill you help me?' WHERE entry=9957;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Hey there, $C.  We haven\'t heard from the druids of the Cenarion Thicket in quite some time.$B$BI want you to go over there and check to see what\'s happening.  You can find it by heading northwest through the forest.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m glad that Stonebreaker Hold sent you. The druids of the thicket have been slain! Only myself and one other have survived, and he\'s insane.$B$BI don\'t know what happened, but I intend to get to the bottom of it. Whatever it was, it happened quickly and feels unnatural.$B$BWill you help me?' WHERE entry=9960;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m glad that Stonebreaker Hold sent you. The druids of the thicket have been slain! Only myself and one other have survived. and he\'s insane.$B$BI don\'t know what happened, but I intend to get to the bottom of it. Whatever it was, it happened quickly and feels unnatural.$B$BWill you help me?' WHERE entry=9961;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='So are you ready for your first battle? If you are, let me know and I\'ll get things started. All you have to do is go wait in the Ring of Blood for your opponent to arrive.$B$BThis fight is against Brokentoe, a ferocious clefthoof.$B$BGood luck! I hope you brought friends.$B$BAnd remember, the fight\'s over when either you or your opponent are lying face down on the arena floor.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Hrm, not bad. Not bad at all... You\'ve got potential, kid. Here\'s a little gold to line your pockets with...' WHERE entry=9962;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'ll admit that I didn\'t think you had a prayer, $N! That was amazing! So how \'bout another fight? Gurgthock\'s got the perfect match lined up.' WHERE entry=9967;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Collect 4 Teromoth Samples and 4 Vicious Teromoth Samples.  Then return to Earthbinder Tavgren just outside the Cenarion Thicket in Terokkar Forest.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Odd.  The samples from the vicious teromoths are infused with what feels to me to be pure mana.$B$BIt would seem that whatever caused all of this death also left behind that strong field of residual energy.  But for some reason the teromoths were not killed by it; instead being driven into an agitated state.$B$BIt seems apparent that this strange energy is the by-product of whatever attacked the thicket.' WHERE entry=9968;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve got the ogres sweatin\', kid! Here\'s a little something extra this time - don\'t use \'em all in one place.$B$BAre you ready for another fight? Gurgthock\'s bettin\' the bank on you!' WHERE entry=9970;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So, I was right.  That was the corpse of one of the Broken?  And you can confirm that there was a strange object on the ground next to him?$B$BThis doesn\'t make any sense.  What would one of the Broken be doing here?  And what is that thing it had with him?$B$BIs it was caused all of this death?' WHERE entry=9971;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='KID! KID THIS IS IT! The next fight is the big one! The championship!$B$BOk, keep it cool. We don\'t want the ogres to know that we got anything going on. I get a cut of all this, after all.' WHERE entry=9972;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh boy. Mogor has invoked his right of battle as hero of the Warmaul. You have to fight him!$B$BNobody ever said the Warmaul were good sports... erm... ogres.' WHERE entry=9973;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Gurgthock told you he\'d make it worth your while, kid. Take your pick!' WHERE entry=9977;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Find and convince Empoor to tell you what he knows.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Fine, fine... I\'ll tell you what I know, but it\'s not much!' WHERE entry=9978;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes? How may I help you today, $R?' WHERE entry=9979;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Does my appearance startle you? Do you know what I am?' WHERE entry=9982;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Does my appearance startle you? Do you know what I am?' WHERE entry=9983;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Although you cannot read the strange script on the scroll, the ornate seal at the bottom of the document implies that it was drafted by an arakkoa of high standing. Luanga may have masterminded the capture and interrogation of Deirom, but it seems he was taking orders from someone else.$B$BYou remember Thander mentioning that Andarl has studied the arakkoa. Perhaps he can decipher the scroll\'s contents.',objectives_loc4='Take Luanga\'s Orders to Andarl at the Allerian Stronghold in Terokkar Forest.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I can read most of this, enough to get a general idea. Whoever wrote this is praising the \'progress\' made by Luanga and encouraging him to continue interrogating his \'guests.\'$B$BMeanwhile, it says, \'the preparations in Skettis are proceeding as planned\' and that they will \'soon be ready to reclaim their ancestral lands.\'$B$BI\'m not familiar with this \'Skettis\' mentioned by the writer, but wherever it is, it sounds like the arakkoa are assembling an army there! Thander must be told about this immediately.' WHERE entry=9984;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Although you cannot read the strange script on the scroll, the ornate seal at the bottom of the document implies that it was drafted by an arakkoa of high standing. Luanga may have masterminded the capture and interrogation of Dugar, but it seems he was taking orders from someone else.$B$BYou remember Rokag mentioning that Kurgatok has studied the arakkoa. Perhaps he can decipher the scroll\'s contents.',objectives_loc4='Bring Luanga\'s Orders to Kurgatok at Stonebreaker Hold in Terokkar Forest.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I can read most of this, enough to get a general idea. Whoever wrote this is praising the \'progress\' made by Luanga and encouraging him to continue interrogating his \'guests.\'$B$BMeanwhile, it says, \'the preparations in Skettis are proceeding as planned\' and that they will \'soon be ready to reclaim their ancestral lands.\'$B$BI\'m not familiar with this \'Skettis\' mentioned by the writer, but wherever it is, it sounds like the arakkoa are assembling an army there! Rokag must be told about this immediately.' WHERE entry=9985;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. We have enough to worry about without wondering when the arakkoa will accost our merchants and messengers again.' WHERE entry=9986;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Kill Ashkaz in Veil Reskk, Ayit in Veil Shienor, and Urdak in Veil Skith and return to Rokag at Stonebreaker Hold.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. We have enough to worry about without wondering when the arakkoa will accost our merchants and messengers again.' WHERE entry=9987;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Don\'t let Thander and company fool you. They may look like a band of fearsome warriors, but underneath all that steel, they\'re nothing more than a troop of dandies!$B$BAnd they won\'t be seen in public without their hats. They\'re extravagant affairs made from felt and fur, complete with the gaudiest feathers you\'ve ever seen.$B$BThe most desirable feathers come from any of the arakkoa, of course, and my supply is running low. I\'ll gladly pay you if you\'ll collect them for me.',objectives_loc4='Bring 30 Arakkoa Feathers to Ros\'eleth in the Allerian Stronghold.' WHERE entry=9988;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ethereals?  Goods delivered to Tuurem?  Exotic engineering parts?  And a blood elf getting ready to deliver this last box to Firewing Point?$B$BWhat does all of this mean?!  How does it relate to what happened to the druids in the Cenarion Thicket?$B$BI think we should have a look inside that box.' WHERE entry=9990;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='To be my eyes will require some diligence on your part. Nethrandamus will take you through the Legion camps, but you must catalog everything that you see. Even the smallest detail that you may think to be inconsequential could be useful for our purposes.$B$BPrimarily, I want you to note what structures are in the camps and what comprises the camps\' defenses.$B$BNethrandamus is ready when you are, $N. Do not be afraid, he will keep you safe from harm.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work, $N! We now have a point from which we can plan our counter-attack.' WHERE entry=9991;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you for bringing these seeds. I\'ve almost got enough to send back the first batch!' WHERE entry=9992;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh no! That\'s horrible news! I can\'t believe that all but two of our Cenarion friends are dead.$B$BAlright, let me have a look at those parts. I\'m just hoping they aren\'t what I suspect that they might be.$B$BYes, as I feared, I believe these are bomb parts. Our eyes and ears in Shattrath City have been feeding us information about some of the ethereals importing proscribed goods from other dimensions that they\'re in contact with.' WHERE entry=9994;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I don\'t know about you, but I have no idea what all of those things are.  I do know one thing though - they look dangerous!$B$B$N, I think you should take this box of parts to Tooki at Stonebreaker Hold to the southeast.  He may have some idea of what these are.',objectives_loc4='Deliver the Box of Parts to Tooki at Stonebreaker Hold in Terokkar Forest.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh no!  That\'s horrible news!  I can\'t believe that all but two of our Cenarion friends are dead.$B$BAlright, let me have a look at those parts.  I\'m just hoping they aren\'t what I suspect that they might be.' WHERE entry=9995;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'s a good start, but based on what you witnessed there in the courtyard, as well as intelligence that I\'ve received, we have a far more pressing matter at hand!' WHERE entry=9996;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We know that the blood elves of Firewing Point are working for Kael\'thas and Illidan.  And from what you\'ve told me, clearly they are using the Broken of Tuurem as smuggling go-betweens for the creation of some horrible weapon.$B$BWhatever they\'re up to out there, the most efficient thing that we can do right now is to thin out their numbers.$B$BThe Firewing blood elves need to be taken out!  Head over to Firewing Point to the northeast and see to it.',objectives_loc4='Kill 10 Firewing Defenders, 10 Firewing Bloodwarders, and 10 Firewing Warlocks.  Then report back to Sergeant Chawni at Stonebreaker Camp in Terokkar Forest.',offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'s a good start, but based on what you witnessed there in the courtyard, as well as intelligence that I\'ve received, we have a far more pressing matter at hand!' WHERE entry=9997;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Kill 12 Warped Peons and then report to Theloria Shadecloak at Allerian Post.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<The high elf nods.>$B$BIt\'s a good start, but Bertelm was right to send you to me. I\'ve made a discovery that may help explain the fel orc presence here.' WHERE entry=9998;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='As long as the transporters stand, nothing we do to the forge camps will have any permanence. We must find a way to destroy the Legion structures.$B$BI need time to devise a plan of attack. If you can keep their engineers and tinkerers busy, it would greatly slow down their progress, buying me the time I need.$B$BStay as far away as possible from the overseers, $N. They are extremely dangerous beings.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It is as I suspected. There are no conventional means of destroying fel steel. All is not lost, however...' WHERE entry=9999;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='My acquaintance will hopefully know of a way to destroy the camps. He was a Legion engineer, after all...' WHERE entry=10001;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Over the past couple of days, I\'ve observed a blood elf woman traveling to and from the fel orc stronghold and conversing with the fel orc leader. From her body language, she\'s clearly issuing orders. But why? Whose orders is she conveying?$B$BMy curiosity got the better of my judgment and I shadowed her when she left the fel orc encampment. She headed north, to Firewing Point. I stopped before reaching the perimeter of the blood elf outpost.$B$BKill her before she leaves the fel orc camp again.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Theloria nods at you.>$B$BWell done. We have bought ourselves a little time. The blood elves will grow curious about what happened to their friend. Hopefully, by that time, we will have a better understanding of their intentions.' WHERE entry=10002;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Over the past couple of days, I\'ve observed a blood elf woman traveling to and from the fel orc stronghold and conversing with the fel orc leader. From her body language, she\'s clearly issuing orders. But why? Whose orders is she conveying?$B$BMy curiosity got the better of my judgment and I shadowed her when she left the fel orc encampment. She headed north, to Firewing Point. I stopped before reaching the perimeter of the blood elf outpost.$B$BKill her before she leaves the fel orc camp again.',objectives_loc4='Locate and slay Lisaile Fireweaver, then return to Shadowstalker Kaide.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Kaide nods at you.>$B$BWell done. We have bought ourselves a little time. The blood elves will grow curious about what happened to their friend. Hopefully, by that time, we will have a better understanding of their intentions.$B$BWhen the time is right, I will inform Rogak of our progress.' WHERE entry=10003;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Take the blueprints and travel to Shattrath City in the Terokkar forest. Once at Shattrath, go to the Lower City and look for a mo\'arg by the name Sal\'salabim. He\'ll probably be at the bar, drinking away his sorrows.$B$BBy the way, you may need to convince him to lend his assistance. Try to approach him with patience and understanding. If that does not work, use your fists.',objectives_loc4='Altruis the Sufferer in western Nagrand wants you to take the Master Planner\'s Blueprints to Sal\'salabim in Shattrath City and convince him to help you.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Calm down, bright eyes! Sal\'salabim will help.' WHERE entry=10004;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A bomb utilizing pure mana that can take out whole towns! But why? Why would the blood elves create such a thing and use it on us? The Cenarion Thicket was a place of peace and repose.$B$BWhatever the reason, it must be locked inside the head of Warden Treelos, and I have no idea how to cure him. Perhaps his mind will heal in time?$B$BRegardless, I want to thank you for helping me to figure out what happened. I can only hope that this tragedy will never befall anyone else ever again!' WHERE entry=10005;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='$N, I think that after you\'re done celebrating here, you should go back to the Cenarion Thicket and speak with Earthbinder Tavgren.$B$BI\'m certain that he\'ll want to know what really happened out there.',offerrewardtext_loc4='A bomb utilizing pure mana that can take out whole towns! But why? Why would the blood elves create such a thing and use it on us? The Cenarion Thicket was a place of peace and repose.$B$BWhatever the reason, it must be locked inside the head of Warden Treelos, and I have no idea how to cure him. Perhaps his mind will heal in time?$B$BRegardless, I want to thank you for helping me to figure out what happened. I can only hope that this tragedy will never befall anyone else ever again!' WHERE entry=10006;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Things are starting to look up. I think if we can prevent the fel orcs from reinforcing their fellows here, we can keep this post under control.' WHERE entry=10007;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Now, deal is deal but when Sal\'salabim tell you, you not be mad, yes?' WHERE entry=10009;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='<Sal\'salabim points to the blueprint.>$B$BYou see where fel cannons are?$B$B<Sal\'salabim draws an arrow denoting a change of direction.>$B$BYou turn fel cannon around and use on structures.$B$BWait! Don\'t be mad! One thing you not know. Overseers have key to turn cannons. You need key first! One from each overseer!$B$BNot so easy, eh?$B$BTake information back to Altruis.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Of course! We will use their own weapons against them!' WHERE entry=10010;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Gather your allies, $N. You will need them if you are to face an overseer.$B$BOnce you have a suitable group, find and kill the overseers at each camp. Take their keys and use them to turn and fire the fel cannons upon the camps. Return to me once the camps are destroyed.',offerrewardtext_loc4='We are victorious! The Legion\'s advances have been halted!$B$BI offer you a choice of rewards for your heroic deeds!' WHERE entry=10011;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Forge Camp: Hate Destroyed',ObjectiveText2_loc4='Forge Camp: Fear Destroyed' WHERE entry=10011;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring the Fel Orc Plans to Bertelm at the Allerian Stronghold.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Bertelm takes the plans from you and looks them over.>$B$BIf you hadn\'t brought this map, I\'d say you were out of your mind, but here it is, plain as day. Not only are the fel orcs here to serve the blood elves, but it appears, they\'ve been ordered to keep us occupied.$B$BThis map raises more questions than it answers, but it gives us a better idea of what we\'re facing here.' WHERE entry=10012;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='As I was saying, we\'ve just received some further intel and there\'s a much larger problem at hand.$B$BThe blood elves are hard at work on the construction of a second bomb at Firewing Point.  I cannot stress strongly enough the implications of them completing and using such a device on the Allerian Stronghold!$B$BMy scouts tell me that they are guarding the codes to the device in the four smaller buildings ringing the central courtyard.  Get in there and retrieve those codes before it\'s too late!',objectives_loc4='Steal the four Mana Bomb Code Sheets and deliver them to Lieutenant Meridian at the Allerian Post in Terokkar Forest.' WHERE entry=10014;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='As I was saying, we\'ve just received some further intel and there\'s a much larger problem at hand.$B$BThe blood elves are hard at work on the construction of a second bomb at Firewing Point.  I cannot stress strongly enough the implications of them completing and using such a device on Stonebreaker Hold!$B$BMy scouts tell me that they are guarding the codes to the device in the four smaller buildings ringing the central courtyard.  Get in there and retrieve those codes before it\'s too late!',objectives_loc4='Steal the four Mana Bomb Code Sheets and deliver them to Sergeant Chawni at Stonebreaker Camp in Terokkar Forest.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Good work!$B$BLet me have a look at those code sheets.  I\'ve got an idea and it might just be crazy enough to work!' WHERE entry=10015;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, well done, friend. These are finer than I thought they\'d be. They\'ll make a fine cloak.$B$B<Bertelm glances toward the inn.>$B$BYes, a fine cloak it shall be.' WHERE entry=10016;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have my thanks, $N. The Aldor will hear of your actions.' WHERE entry=10017;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Vestments of the Wolf Spirit',details_loc4='Generations ago, when orc clans still called Terokkar Forest home, the wolf spirit played an important role in their lives. When the orcs departed, they had no longer had any need for the spirit and they left it behind.$B$BIn time, the spirit grew lonely and it too left the forest.$B$BI believe I can bring the wolf spirit back to his ancestral home, just as we orcs have returned. The ritual will require me to create vestments from the pelts of the wolves of the forest to guide the spirit back to its home.',offerrewardtext_loc4='These are perfect, $N! I could not have asked for better.' WHERE entry=10018;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $N. Caring for those in need is a difficult task, but in time I\'ve discovered that it is its own reward.' WHERE entry=10020;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have my thanks, $N. We are keepers of the light and cannot forsake our responsibilities, even in the most difficult of times.' WHERE entry=10021;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I bow to your skills, $N. You have proven yourself the superior hunter.$B$BI won\'t forget your help in making this cloak. It will truly be a one-of-a-kind piece and I\'ll wear it proudly.' WHERE entry=10022;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These are all in excellent state, $N. Carry on and you will soon count the Scryers as your friends.' WHERE entry=10024;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Andarl dabs at his forehead with the sleeve of his robe.>$B$BThank goodness. I was beginning to wonder if the things had displaced the rest of the forest\'s creatures.' WHERE entry=10026;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='There\'s nothing more annoying than preparing to cast a spell, only to have it interrupted by some unseen force. After the fourth time, I knew it couldn\'t be coincidence and I sent Keb\'ezil out to investigate.$B$BI guarantee you\'ll never encounter an imp that talks back more than Keb.$B$BAnyway, he managed to find the source of the problem, a pesky creature known as a warp stalker. They have a habit of disturbing the magical energy wherever they blink into existence. I\'ve had enough of their interference.',objectives_loc4='Kill 10 Warp Stalkers and return to Kurgatok at Stonebreaker Hold.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Keb\'ezil is relieved that you\'ve taken care of that little problem, aren\'t you, Keb?$B$B<The imp ignores its master, presumably out of indignation.>$B$BYou\'ll have to forgive his bad manners. You know how demons can be...' WHERE entry=10027;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I hope these aren\'t the only intact vessels in the city. This is a good start, but I suspect we\'ll need many more than this.' WHERE entry=10028;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Collect 10 Restless Bones.  Deliver them to Ramdor the Mad, just off the western side of the Ring of Observance in Auchindoun, which is in the middle of the Bone Wastes of Terokkar Forest.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Great, just what I needed... more bones.$B$B<Ramdor sighs.>$B$BYes, yes, I will see to it that these remains of our honored ancestors are given a proper burial, have no fear.$B$BThere is something else that you can do if you\'re truly interested in aiding the dead.' WHERE entry=10030;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Destroy 10 Lost Spirits and 10 Broken Skeletons, and then speak with Soolaveen at the Refugee Caravan in the Bone Wastes of Terokkar Forest.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done that which needed doing and there is nothing to forgive. Though it saddens me to hear that they were corrupted into a horrible undeath, through your actions you have put them to rest.$B$BThank you for setting them free, $N. You must accept a humble token of my regard for you and your selflessness.' WHERE entry=10031;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yeah, I\'m sure that you killed all of those bonelashers. It\'s obvious since the captain asked for you to turn in proof on that wanted poster.$B$B<Taela gives you a sarcastic look.>$B$BI\'ll take your word for it. I\'m not certain who I angered to pull this duty, but thanks for your efforts on behalf of the Alliance. Here\'s a little something for all of your trouble.' WHERE entry=10033;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The bonelashers of the Bone Wastes bit Mawg and made him sick.  Now he wants all of them destroyed!$B$BWhile they can be found throughout the wastes, they are known to congregate at Carrion Hill in the north.$B$BReturn to Mawg Grimshot after you\'ve done the deed and he\'ll give you a good reward.',objectives_loc4='Kill 20 Bonelashers and then report to Mawg Grimshot at Stonebreaker Hold in Terokkar Forest.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You must have killed a lot of those bonelashers! Good, I hate them! Ever since I was bit by one of them, I keep having fainting spells.$B$BDo you realize how embarrassing that is? Here, take this as thanks for exacting some revenge for me.' WHERE entry=10034;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Color me impressed, $C. Torgos was one of the toughest creatures I know of this side of Nagrand.$B$BWell, I suppose that\'s good enough for something from the Allerian Stronghold treasury. Take your pick.' WHERE entry=10035;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I thank you, $N! You have exacted my revenge, and as promised you will be rewarded!$B$BTake your pick of one of these and use it well!' WHERE entry=10036;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring 8 Pristine Shimmerscale Eels to Seth in Shattrath.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Thanks! I can\'t remember the last time I had eel!$B$BHow should I cook \'em?' WHERE entry=10037;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Locate and speak with Private Weeks near the north entrance to Grangol\'var Village in Terokkar Forest.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s about time someone came out here. I sent that report to the Allerian Stronghold over a week ago!$B$BBureaucracy!' WHERE entry=10038;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good, you finally made it back! Okay, what did you figure out? Who are they?' WHERE entry=10040;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='While in disguise, speak with the Shadowy Initiate, the Shadowy Laborer and the Shadowy Advisor.  Then return to Scout Neftis at Grangol\'var Village in Terokkar Forest.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Good, you finally made it back! Okay, what did you figure out? Who are they?' WHERE entry=10041;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'s dire news indeed! Well, it would seem I made the right choice in sending you out there to help Weeks. The last thing that we want is the Shadow Council establishing themselves right on our doorstep!$B$B$N, in recognition of your efforts at Grangol\'var Village, I hereby grant you the right to your pick of any of these fine rewards.' WHERE entry=10042;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='What!  Those guys are Shadow Council?!$B$B$N, you have to go back in there and waste them!  I want you to take out their leader and as many of their executioners and summoners as you can.$B$BAfter you\'re done with that, report back to Advisor Faila at Stonebreaker Hold.$B$BGood luck, $C!',objectives_loc4='Kill 10 Shadowy Executioners, 10 Shadowy Summoners and Shadowmaster Grieve, and then return to Advisor Faila at Stonebreaker Hold in Terokkar Forest.',offerrewardtext_loc4='That is unfortunate news! But, of course, I made the right choice in sending you out there to help Neftis. The last thing that we need is the Shadow Council establishing a strong point right on our doorstep!$B$B$N, you\'ve earned yourself something nice. Go ahead, take your pick.' WHERE entry=10043;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Two weeks ago, our scouts reported a heavily armed Alliance force under the command of Field Commander Romus departing Nethergarde Keep. With so many soldiers and supplies, along with such a distinguished commander, they can only have one goal: Outland.$B$BThe warchief sent an advance force through the portal, but if the Alliance believes there is a need for that many troops, perhaps we\'d be wise to send our own reinforcements.$B$BJourney through the Dark Portal and report to Nazgrel at Thrallmar.',objectives_loc4='Travel through the Dark Portal and speak with Nazgrel at Thrallmar.' WHERE entry=10046;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have my sincere thanks for your efforts, $N. Though much remains to be done, it gladdens me to know we have helped some find their long-deserved rest.' WHERE entry=10047;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Sons appreciate your efforts, even if few are willing to speak of the armory.' WHERE entry=10050;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Thank goodness for you!$B$B$C, I need you to help me escape.  I have information vital to the security of the Allerian Stronghold and probably all of Outland!$B$BI came here from the Cenarion Expedition on a diplomatic mission, but as you can see, they weren\'t very friendly.  If you help me get to safety, I can assure you that you will be handsomely rewarded!$B$BWe won\'t be able to do this on our own - you do have a group with you, right?',offerrewardtext_loc4='Isla Starmane just left, but she gave me a full rundown on what\'s going on out at Firewing Point. It\'s understandable that she\'s quite distraught over what happened to the Cenarion Thicket. Nasty blood elves!$B$BShe told me how you were instrumental in saving her so that we could get that information. Allerian Stronghold is indebted to you for your service.$B$BPlease, accept this gift on behalf of us all.' WHERE entry=10051;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Thank goodness for you!$B$B$C, I need you to help me escape.  I have information vital to the security of Stonebreaker Hold and probably all of Outland!$B$BI came here from the Cenarion Expedition on a diplomatic mission, but as you can see, they weren\'t very friendly.  If you help me get to safety, I can assure you that you will be handsomely rewarded!$B$BWe won\'t be able to do this on our own - you do have a group with you, right?',offerrewardtext_loc4='Isla Starmane just left, but she gave me a full rundown on what\'s going on out at Firewing Point. It\'s understandable that she\'s quite distraught over what happened to the Cenarion Thicket.$B$BShe told me how you were instrumental in saving her so that we could get that information. Stonebreaker Hold is indebted to you for your service.$B$BPlease, accept this gift on behalf of us all.' WHERE entry=10052;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This is in better condition than I thought it\'d be. Sure. it\'s going to take some time to work off all the rust. the char. and the like, but I\'ll not complain.' WHERE entry=10055;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The orcish ruins of Zeth\'Gor to the southeast serve as a base for an ever-growing tide of orcs emerging from Hellfire Citadel.$B$BThe Sons of Lothar have been fighting them for some time, and the stories they tell would be nigh unbelievable if I hadn\'t seen these \'fel\' orcs with my own eyes.$B$BSomething has changed them, augmented them in a way we\'ve never seen before. We have to do anything we can to keep them from strengthening. Go to Zeth\'Gor and destroy any supplies you find there.',objectives_loc4='Destroy 6 piles of Bleeding Hollow Supplies and report to Lieutenant Amadi at Honor Hold.' WHERE entry=10056;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We can only hope that with the quieting of the ghosts of the officers, the spirits of the foot soldiers will follow. Thank you once again for your help, $N.' WHERE entry=10057;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Is that really it? It\'s hard to believe it survived the battle. Conditions in the ruins haven\'t been kind to the book, but still, I\'m glad to have it.$B$BIt\'s the only token I have of Turalyon.$B$B<Father Devidicus seems to be fighting back tears.>$B$BWhen you fight beside someone for so many years, they become closer than even family.' WHERE entry=10058;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='When the Bonechewer fel orcs attacked the Expedition Armory, the garrison there fell quickly.  The battle was bloody and fierce, and there were no survivors.$B$BAlthough the dead were buried, their spirits continue to haunt those ruins.  Of late, I have been receiving visions that these spirits may soon become a threat to Thrallmar.$B$BThere is only one course of action to take.  We must grant these spirits rest.  You must overcome them in battle.',objectives_loc4='Grelag wants you to defeat 12 Unyielding Footmen, 10 Unyielding Sorcerers, and 5 Unyielding Knights at the Expedition Armory to the south of Honor Hold.' WHERE entry=10061;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The disturbances at the Expedition Armory continue, despite your best efforts. No one truly knows everything that happened there, nor exactly what binds the spirits of the fallen soldiers to the ruins.$B$BWe may be approaching this the wrong way. My visions suggested that each of the ghosts had a tie to the ruins, but what if their ties were to their leaders?$B$BArch Mage Xintor and Lieutenant Commander Thalvos were particularly close to their men, so perhaps overcoming their ghosts will calm the rest.',objectives_loc4='Overcome the ghosts of Arch Mage Xintor and Lieutenant Commander Thalvos and return to Grelag at Spinebreaker Ridge.' WHERE entry=10062;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I thought so! That grumpy old dwarf was supposed to help me carry my equipment and gather data, but all he does is sit in that strange draenei town, drinking himself into a stupor.' WHERE entry=10063;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I was hoping Blood Watch would send reinforcements once they learned what we\'re up against.' WHERE entry=10064;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It looks a bit better out there, but I still wonder if I wouldn\'t be better off waiting for a medic here.' WHERE entry=10065;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. It\'s going to be much easier to get reinforcements from Blood Watch, or launch strikes against the Sunhawks without having to worry about what the tanglers are up to.' WHERE entry=10066;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. It\'s important not to overlook any opportunity to deny the Sunhawks sustenance.' WHERE entry=10067;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='And now, I need for you to do something.$B$BWell Watcher Solanian is in need of your services.  You would do well to ingratiate yourself with him.$B$BHe awaits you on the exterior platform that the ramp in this chamber leads up to.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Well Watcher Solanian at the Sunspire on Sunstrider Isle.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah good, a $C. I\'ve been expecting you.$BThere are a few tasks that I have which you are particularly suited to.' WHERE entry=10068;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='And now, I need for you to do something.$B$BWell Watcher Solanian is in need of your services.  You would do well to ingratiate yourself with him.$B$BHe awaits you on the exterior platform that the ramp in this chamber leads up to.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Well Watcher Solanian at the Sunspire on Sunstrider Isle.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah good, a $C. I\'ve been expecting you.$B$BThere are a few tasks that I have to which you are particularly suited to.' WHERE entry=10069;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='And now, I need for you to do something.$B$BWell Watcher Solanian is in need of your services.  You would do well to ingratiate yourself with him.$B$BHe awaits you on the exterior platform that the ramp in this chamber leads up to.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Well Watcher Solanian at the Sunspire on Sunstrider Isle.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah good, a $C. I\'ve been expecting you.$B$BThere are a few tasks that I have to which you are particularly suited to.' WHERE entry=10070;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='And now, I need for you to do something.$B$BWell Watcher Solanian is in need of your services.  You would do well to ingratiate yourself with him.$B$BHe awaits you on the exterior platform that the ramp in this chamber leads up to.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Well Watcher Solanian at the Sunspire on Sunstrider Isle.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah good, a $C. I\'ve been expecting you.$B$BThere are a few tasks that I have to which you are particularly suited to.' WHERE entry=10071;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='And now, I need for you to do something.$B$BWell Watcher Solanian is in need of your services.  You would do well to ingratiate yourself with him.$B$BHe awaits you on the exterior platform that the ramp in this chamber leads up to.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Well Watcher Solanian at the Sunspire on Sunstrider Isle.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah good, a $C. I\'ve been expecting you.$B$BThere are a few tasks that I have to which you are particularly suited to.' WHERE entry=10072;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='And now, I need for you to do something.$B$BWell Watcher Solanian is in need of your services.  You would do well to ingratiate yourself with him.$B$BHe awaits you on the exterior platform that the ramp in this chamber leads up to.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Well Watcher Solanian at the Sunspire on Sunstrider Isle.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah good, a $C. I\'ve been expecting you.$B$BThere are a few tasks that I have to which you are particularly suited to.' WHERE entry=10073;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Chief Researcher Amereldine at Halaa wants 20 Oshu\'gun Crystal Powder Samples.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Wonderful, $N. This will help us in our battle against the Alliance filth that have surfaced in the Outland.' WHERE entry=10074;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I am always accepting crystal powder contributions, $N. You will be compensated for each set of samples that you recover.' WHERE entry=10075;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Chief Researcher Kartos at Halaa wants 20 Oshu\'gun Crystal Powder Samples.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Wonderful, $N. This will help us in our battle against the Horde filth that have surfaced in the Outland.' WHERE entry=10076;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I thank you for your contribution, $N. Should you find more, you know where to bring them!' WHERE entry=10077;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'s the spirit!$B$BI\'m glad we finally got some reinforcements, but I\'m not so sure about their attitude toward the Horde. Where I come from, anyone with a weapon pointed at you is an enemy and needs to be dealt with like one!' WHERE entry=10078;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Central Western Thrower Burned',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Western Thrower Burned' WHERE entry=10078;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='By Bronzebeard\'s bronze... beard, you\'ve done it! You\'re a hero, $N.' WHERE entry=10079;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Visit Garadar',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Visit Bleeding Hollow Clan Ruins' WHERE entry=10085;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This stuff is great! A little bent and a little burnt, but I\'ve never let low grade materials stop me from making precision high explosives.$B$BThanks, $N. You really have an eye for quality trash!' WHERE entry=10086;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I thought so! I couldn\'t quite make out the destruction from here, but I can imagine how it must have looked. Splendid!$B$BWell done, $N. Thrallmar command will be happy to hear of your success!' WHERE entry=10087;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The mine\'s been overrun by a plague of gan\'arg misfits, and on top of that, the peons have decided that this is a fine time for a nap! I don\'t know how they can sleep through all the disturbances coming from the mine, but that\'s the least of my problems.$B$BIf we don\'t get rid of those gan\'arg pests soon, Thrallmar\'s supply of ore and other minerals will be cut off. I\'ve already asked Watch Commander Krunk for help, but he says he can\'t spare the men with the town under constant attack. Will you help?',objectives_loc4='Kill 12 Gan\'arg Sappers and return to Foreman Razelcraz.',offerrewardtext_loc4='At last! Now, I don\'t suppose you\'re willing to bop a few peons on the head, or will that cost extra?' WHERE entry=10088;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='To\'gun was here earlier giving me his report. He should have stayed with you to help!$B$BI sent him back out there to assist Grik\'tha. I think they make a cute couple.$B$BSo, these are the soul devices that the Shadow Council were using to enhance their summoning power? They look dangerous to me' WHERE entry=10091;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, so you\'ve met Seer Kryv. He is a wise and gifted man and any $R he would name a friend is also a friend of mine.$B$BMake yourself comfortable and introduce yourself to the others who call the temple home.' WHERE entry=10093;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Opening the magically suspended tome, a sense of dread overwhelms you.$B$BSomething is most definitely wrong here!$B$BYou read on, but what you read seems unbelievable!' WHERE entry=10094;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Murmur almost broke free?! They\'ve had that thing contained in there for two years... I wonder what they did wrong to lose control over it after all this time?$B$B$N, by putting that beast down you\'ve likely saved all of us! I cringe to think what would have happened to all of us here, and the rest of Outland, if that thing had somehow managed to break free!$B$BI\'m glad you helped us to take matters into our own hands and deal with the Shadow Council threat at Auchindoun. How can we ever reward you?' WHERE entry=10095;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good!  Those marsh beasts have no right to invade the home of the sporeloks!$B$BIt would be better if these creatures would learn to live in harmony, but when that\'s not possible, we\'ll be here to take care of the situation!$B$BHere, please take one of these as thanks for your help.' WHERE entry=10096;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I can\'t thank you enough, $N. Knowing that Lakka is free means I can cut the rest of my ties to the Sethekk.$B$BPart of me will never forgive myself for Syth\'s death, but it had to be done. When I reach Skettis, I will perform the death rites for him. Perhaps his spirit will find rest once it has atoned for leading our people astray.' WHERE entry=10097;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I may never truly be forgiven for my role in the crimes of the Sethekk, but perhaps by restoring the relics of Terokk to my people, I can begin to redeem myself.$B$BThank you for helping me in this, $N. You have no idea of the magnitude of what you\'ve done this day.' WHERE entry=10098;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m glad you managed to take care of, of... what did you say he called himself? Z\'kral?$B$BFrom your description, it sounds more like an \'it\' than a \'him\' but all that matters is it\'s dead.' WHERE entry=10099;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Don\'t get me wrong, $N, I\'m glad that you agreed to help with the mines, but for every sapper you killed, I swear two more appeared.$B$BI\'ve been giving Watch Commander Krunk an earful, but he\'s still refusing to send me any help. He keeps muttering something under his breath about helboars. If I wasn\'t so sure he\'d hit me, I\'d tell him this is no time to be thinking about ribs!$B$BAnyway, it looks like there\'s someone down there deep in the mines directing this whole thing. Find him and kill him!',objectives_loc4='Locate and kill Urga\'zz within the mines beneath Thrallmar, then return to Foreman Razelcraz.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Hopefully, getting rid of their overseer will cause the leftovers to panic and break. Should be easy cleanup for my boys, once I\'ve found a way to keep them awake, that is.' WHERE entry=10100;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='A Secret Revealed',details_loc4='As my energies bled away over the centuries, a void slowly grew in my place - devouring the souls of those nearby. Helplessly, I watched as generations of orc souls were drawn into the vortex. Recently, my enemies harnessed the vortex and used it to draw countless void minions into their Burning Legion.$B$BNow, the key to ending this cycle and freeing the orc spirits lies with another naaru - A\'dal. I have sensed his essence within the ancient city of Shattrath in the Terokkar Forest.',offerrewardtext_loc4='K\'ure was wise to send you here. While we cannot assist you with the suffering of the orc ancestors, there is one that can.$B$BOne that is soon to be reborn of Light...' WHERE entry=10102;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='To be honest, I had expected more, but you\'ll have to do. Welcome to Swamprat Post.' WHERE entry=10103;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m flattered that your Broken friend considers me a scholar of his people\'s relics, but to be honest, I haven\'t had much chance to study them since my arrival here. It was certainly my intent, but when I arrived, I found that there were other matters that required my attention.' WHERE entry=10104;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. Your actions in the field are instrumental in our battle for Hellfire Peninsula.' WHERE entry=10106;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Kilrath sends news of the Boulderfist leader: He is an orc! An ancient orc that passed through the Dark Portal in the time of our fathers and has since returned to his homeland. I wish for you to track down this orc and try to convince him to pull back the Boulderfist ogres. He resides on an upper platform in the Burning Blade Ruins to the southeast near the border of Terokkar. Good luck, $N!$B$BBe warned, he is a blademaster...',objectives_loc4='Jorin Deadeye at Garadar in Nagrand has asked that you find and speak with Lantresor of the Blade in the Burning Blade Ruins.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So what is your decision? Will it be war or will you lend your assistance?' WHERE entry=10107;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So what is your decision? Will it be war or will you lend your assistance?' WHERE entry=10108;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent! Now just a few adjustments and this thing will be as good as new. Oh yes, your key! Here you go.$B$BBy the way, the Jump-a-tron still has a few kinks that I need to work out. Um, just be careful.$B' WHERE entry=10109;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Nice work, $N.  I could almost hear the battles waged at those forts.  I wish I was there to see them!' WHERE entry=10110;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, it\'s no egg... Hey! I love chicken too! I\'ll just chomp right through this ginourmous talon! Thanks!' WHERE entry=10111;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes, indeed, I do believe that it\'s all getting clearer now.$B$BAnd I think that your diligence in this matter deserves more than just the information that you seek.' WHERE entry=10112;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='"Go out and find us some supplies," he said. I was nearly killed about 15 times before I found this place! These Broken might not be the most hospitable bunch but at least they\'re not trying to tear my skin from my bones.$B$BAnyway, I\'m not going back. My days of huntin\' big game are over. If you end up heading northeast towards Zangarmarsh and run into the Nesingwary Safari, let them know that "Shotgun" quit. $B$BHey, maybe you can take my place! Good luck, stranger.$B',objectives_loc4='"Shotgun" Jones wants you to speak with Hemet Nesingwary at the Nesingwary Safari on the outskirts of northeast Nagrand.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='I suppose we\'ll have to find a replacement water boy. Say, you look like a powerful $C. Interested in a job? Or did you come for the hunt?' WHERE entry=10113;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='These orcs have never seen a tauren before - if you can believe such a thing. If it weren\'t for Captain Kroghan, they would have probably been serving me for their next meal right about now.$B$BBut where are my manners? I am Ohlorn Farstrider, hunter extraordinaire! I am part of the Nesingwary expedition that came up here from Azeroth in search of big game. If you are interested in the hunt, perhaps you should visit my crew at the Nesingwary Safari, due east of here near the border of Zangarmarsh.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='I am relieved to hear that he is safe. Have you come to join the hunt?$B' WHERE entry=10114;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well, $N. The Daggerfen are beyond redemption by anyone\'s standards, but I\'m not certain that the draenei would\'ve acted with the proper speed in this situation.' WHERE entry=10115;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Wanted: Chieftain Mummaki - leader of the foul and degenerate Lost One tribe of the Daggerfen, for his brutal attacks against the Orebor Harborage.$B$BThe chieftain and his band of assassins are responsible for the deaths of numerous Kurenai and draenei and should only be approached by seasoned combatants.$B$BTravelers are advised to avoid the Daggerfen Village area to the west of the Orebor Harborage.$B$BTo claim the bounty, present proof of the chietain\'s demise to Ikuti.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Remarkable! There have been others who tried to claim the bounty, but they never returned. It\'s not hard to figure out what happened to them.$B$BI\'m relieved that we\'ll no longer be troubled by Mummaki and his degenerates.' WHERE entry=10116;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Wanted: Chieftain Mummaki - leader of the foul and degenerate Lost One tribe of the Daggerfen, for his brutal attacks against Zabra\'jin and its inhabitants.$B$BThe chieftain and his band of assassins are responsible for the deaths of numerous scouts and messengers and should only be approached by seasoned combatants.$B$BTravelers are advised to avoid the Daggerfen Village area to the northwest of Zabra\'jin.$B$BTo claim the bounty, present proof of the chietain\'s demise to Shadow Hunter Denjai.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have my thanks, $N. I was beginning to think that I was going to have to take a substantial part of the garrison up there and deal with Mummaki myself. Of course, there\'s no telling what might have happened to Zabra\'jin then.' WHERE entry=10117;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I think you\'ve managed to send a fairly strong message to them. Perhaps now, the rest of my men won\'t be so afraid to take the fight to the Daggerfen. Or, if they are, they\'ll find themselves ashamed by their lack of bravery.' WHERE entry=10118;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Travel through the Dark Portal and find Commander Duron. He awaits your arrival on the other side - in the Outland.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Welcome to Outland, $N -- welcome to the nightmare! Though the initial Expeditionary Force made it through unscathed, the Legion is attempting to retake the Dark Portal and prevent any of our reinforcements from coming though.$B$BAs much as I\'d like your aid here, our troops and the Horde soldiers are able to fend off the Legion platoons that are attempting to take control of this platform.$B$BWe need you where your talents can best be utilized.' WHERE entry=10119;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So you\'re Orion\'s new messenger? I pray you fare better than the last one he sent, $C. With the Legion pressing in, you\'d never make it to Thrallmar on foot. Say the word, and my faithful wyvern will deliver you there safely.' WHERE entry=10120;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='No doubt you saw the Legion\'s warriors dotting the landscape on your flight from the Dark Portal. Though we defeated them at the Battle of Mount Hyjal some five years past, the cursed demons just keep coming back for more. If it\'s a challenge they crave, then the Horde will answer in kind!$B$BWe orcs have more than just a score to settle with the Legion. What about you, $N? Shall I tell you of our enemy?' WHERE entry=10121;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Each day, Hellfire Citadel opens its gates, and more fel orcs pour out and into the camps they\'ve established along the ramparts south of the fortress.$B$BI dispatched one of my most capable scouts, Private Imarion, to track their movements, preparations and numbers, but he hasn\'t returned to report his findings.$B$BImarion was to focus his efforts on the northernmost camp along the Southern Rampart, near where it joined the Citadel. Find him, $N. Without his information, we\'re sitting ducks.',objectives_loc4='Search the northernmost camp along the Southern Rampart for any trace of Private Imarion.' WHERE entry=10122;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Outstanding work, soldier. The frequency of the attacks is sure to lessen - at least until they bring forth more dreadlords.$B$BNow for the bad news: I\'ve got your new orders...' WHERE entry=10123;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Your battle prowess has been noted by high command, $C. They want to send you to the front lines to meet up with Maimfist\'s crew. They\'re radicals, devoted to the complete extermination of the Burning Legion, so you may fit right in...$B$BHead east about 200 paces and veer south at the jutting mass of land. You\'ll see Reaver\'s Fall where an old farm used to stand. Once there, you are to report to Foward Commander To\'arch.$B$BNow move out!',offerrewardtext_loc4='So you\'re the one responsible for clearing out Felspark, eh? That\'s good to hear - we need soldiers like you who can take these fiends head on!' WHERE entry=10124;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Legion Antenna: Hate Destroyed',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Legion Antenna: Fear Destroyed' WHERE entry=10125;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The orders, signed by \'Warboss Nekrogg,\' order the fel orc patrols stationed at this camp to bring their human prisoner south for interrogation.$B$BLieutenant Amadi mentioned that the Southern Rampart is dotted with fel orc camps. Perhaps the next large section of the wall to the south is where they took Private Imarion.$B$BJudging by the note\'s mention of interrogation, it seems the private\'s fel orc captors see some value in keeping him alive. Pick up the trail before they decide to change their minds.',objectives_loc4='Travel south along the west side of the South Rampart and search the next camp for signs of Private Imarion.' WHERE entry=10126;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That will set them back weeks! Fantastic work, $N. The Legion never expected such heavy resistance.' WHERE entry=10129;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='In addition to other instructions, the orders tell the remaining fel orcs to prepare their equipment and rations for a coming attack.$B$BAccording to the plans, Warboss Nekrogg\'s forces are to form the western flank of a pincer attack on Honor Hold.$B$BWith the hold\'s garrison concentrating on its eastern walls, an attack from the west would be devastating. Honor Hold can only hope to hold out if the western forces are kept out of the battle.',objectives_loc4='Kill 10 Shattered Hand Guards, 10 Shattered Hand Berserkers, and 5 Shattered Hand Acolytes, then report to Lieutenant Amadi at Honor Hold\'s western guard tower.' WHERE entry=10130;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You see that huge red crystal to the north?  It fell from the sky not long ago, causing a massive earthquake.$B$BWhen we came out here to investigate the disturbance, we found all of these colossi wandering about that weren\'t previously here.$B$BThere\'s definitely something strange about that crystal and the energies that it\'s emanating, but I don\'t have time for that.  Those mountain giants are my immediate concern.$B$BI want you to head up to Fallen Sky Ridge with some friends and deal with them.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Good work.$B$BIf you ask me, all that we have to do is kill enough of those colossi, and then we won\'t have to worry any longer about the ridge or that strange crystal in the middle of it.$B$BHere, take one of these as a gift from the Cenarion Expedition.' WHERE entry=10132;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hmph.  Just looks like a big lump of unrefined crystal to me.$B$BAdmittedly, I can feel a sickly, evil aura emanating off of it, but that\'s not exactly in my line of work.  I\'m just here to put an end to the mountain giant menace.' WHERE entry=10134;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='For generations to come, they will sing songs of this day, $N - songs of your valor. I wish Thrall had been here to celebrate this victory with us. The Legion is undone - and Hellfire now belongs to the Horde once again! There may yet be hope for this ravaged world - and our peoples\' place within it. $B$BLok\'tar ogar!$B$B' WHERE entry=10136;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Our expedition to this forsaken, wreck of a world has almost ground to a halt, $N. We encountered more resistance than we bargained for.$B$BAs if facing the Burning Legion again wasn\'t bad enough - there are horrors in this land unlike anything we\'ve ever encountered.' WHERE entry=10140;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Force Commander Danath may have misunderstood my request for reinforcements. You look capable, but... I asked for a full sized battalion!$B$BYou see, we have a bit of a demon problem...' WHERE entry=10141;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Outstanding work, soldier. The frequency of the attacks is sure to lessen - at least until they bring forth new dreadlords.$B$BNow for the bad news: I\'ve got your new orders...' WHERE entry=10142;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Glad to meet you, soldier.$B$BEnough chatting... now listen up -- I have a vital mission for you and I want you to succeed... and survive!' WHERE entry=10143;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. Disabling those portals will stem the flow of Legion reinforcements for a long time!$B$BBut we can\'t rest yet...' WHERE entry=10144;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That will slow them down, there\'s no denying it! I think you just put me in an uncharacteristically good mood, $N!' WHERE entry=10146;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Each day, Hellfire Citadel opens its gates, and more fel orcs pour out and into the camps they\'ve established along the ramparts south of the fortress.$B$BI dispatched one of my most capable trackers, Scout Makha, to track their movements, preparations and numbers, but she hasn\'t returned to report her findings.$B$BMakha was to focus her efforts on the northernmost camp along the Northern Rampart, near where it ends in the rocks. Find her, $N. Without her information, we\'re sitting ducks.',objectives_loc4='Search the northernmost camp along the Northern Rampart for any trace of Scout Makha.' WHERE entry=10150;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The orders, signed by \'Warboss Nekrogg,\' order the fel orc patrols stationed at this camp to bring their orcish prisoner south for interrogation.$B$BShadow Hunter Ty\'jin mentioned that the Northern Rampart is dotted with fel orc camps. Perhaps the next large section of the wall to the south is where they took Scout Makha.$B$BJudging by the note\'s mention of interrogation, it seems the scout\'s fel orc captors see some value in keeping her alive. Pick up the trail before they decide to change their minds.',objectives_loc4='Travel south along the west side of the Northern Rampart and search the next camp for signs of Scout Makha' WHERE entry=10151;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='In addition to other instructions, the orders tell the remaining fel orcs to prepare their equipment and rations for a coming attack.$B$BAccording to the plans, Warboss Nekrogg\'s forces are to form the western flank of a pincer attack on Thrallmar.$B$BWith the town\'s garrison concentrating on its eastern walls, an attack from the west would be devastating. Thrallmar can only hope to hold out if the western forces are kept out of the battle.',objectives_loc4='Kill 10 Shattered Hand Guards, 10 Shattered Hand Berserkers, and 5 Shattered Hand Acolytes, then report to Stone Guard Ambelan at Spinebreaker Post near Zeth\'Gor.' WHERE entry=10152;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The orcish ruins of Zeth\'Gor to serve as a base for an ever-growing tide of orcs emerging from Hellfire Citadel.$B$BShadow Hunter Ty\'jin sent me here to keep an eye on the outpost and its strange inhabitants.$B$BSomething has changed these orcs, augmented them in a way we\'ve never seen before. We have to do anything we can to keep them from strengthening. Fight your way into Zeth\'Gor and destroy any supplies you find there.',objectives_loc4='Destroy 6 piles of Bleeding Hollow Supplies and report to Stone Guard Ambelan at Spinebreaker Post.' WHERE entry=10158;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='With the ravagers cleared, travelers to and from the Cenarion Refuge in Zangarmarsh should have an easier time of it.$B$BThe Cenarion Expedition is indebted to you.' WHERE entry=10159;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Lieutenant Amadi nods.>$B$BGood, we need all the help we can get. The increasing fel orc presence around the Southern Rampart concerns me. I sent out a scout to investigate, but he hasn\'t yet returned.' WHERE entry=10160;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Some of this is in pretty bad shape, but there should be enough to work with here. With some creative engineering, I\'m confident I can make it work!' WHERE entry=10161;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You fly as if you\'ve been doing this your entire life, $N. Outstanding performance out there! Not even a scratch on the wyvern destroyers!' WHERE entry=10162;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Now that you\'ve got your wings, perhaps you\'d be interested in running another bombing mission?$B$BThis time we\'ve isolated the Legion\'s main production area, behind the forge camps to the north. I need you to get on a gryphon and destroy the whole damned thing!$B$BHere are your bombs - now, talk to Gryphoneer Windbellow when you\'re ready for takeoff.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='You fly as if you\'ve been doing this your entire life, $N. Outstanding performance out there! Not even a scratch on the wyvern destroyers!' WHERE entry=10163;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done it, $N! The spirits are freed!$B$BAlthough I am without a material manifestation, I am still able to reward you with items from the spirit world. Use them with caution as such items are often volatile and can cause great harm to their user.' WHERE entry=10164;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Another competitor goes under... You do good work for a flesh beast, $R. If you are ever in Netherstorm, look me up. I make my home at the Stormspire.' WHERE entry=10165;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I no longer belong to this world and must admit defeat.  The land has forever changed and nothing will ever be the same.Leave the pendant here with me, maybe one day, long after the elves are gone, a new tree will grow on this very spot - amongst a burnt forest and the husks of dead treants.' WHERE entry=10166;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Travel to the Auchenai Crypts in the Bone Wastes of Terokkar Forest and slay Exarch Maladaar to free the spirit of D\'ore.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='The memory is vivid, $N. My energies were wholly drained from the crash. I was only a dim speck of void energies when the Prophet Velen and his draenei compatriots lifted my remains and brought them here. After much ceremony, my diminished form was laid to rest within this sarcophagus. I have been regenerating for nearly a thousand years. The cycle is almost complete...' WHERE entry=10167;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Aldor marksmen appear distracted with their drill, allowing you ample time to place the contents of the vial into the stew.' WHERE entry=10169;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, so you managed to recover the staff. Impressive, $N. Perhaps you are the one I\'ve been looking for.$B$BOh yes, your reward...$B$B<Ravandwyr presses a few coins into your palm.>$B$BNo doubt you had higher expectations, but that too will come with time. For now, consider opportunity the true reward.' WHERE entry=10173;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Use Archmage Vargoth\'s Staff to make contact with Archmage Vargoth.$B$BIf you lose Archmage Vargoth\'s Staff, speak to Ravandwyr at Area 52 to receive a replacement.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Archmage Vargoth\'s image examines you as you convey Ravandwyr\'s message.>$B$BRavandwyr has everything a master can expect of his apprentice. When I gave him the staff and told him to flee. I hoped that he would use it to find help and free me once Kael\'thas\'s forces withdrew from the tower. Since then, I have learned a great deal about the nature of the curse.$B$BIt can be broken, $N, but it will require your help.' WHERE entry=10174;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well, $N. Destroying the dampening field will make it much easier for me to prepare the magic that will lift the tower\'s curse at last.' WHERE entry=10176;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s about time that you arrived.$B$BMehlisah said that she would be sending help days ago.  And we\'ve been fighting in here longer than that!' WHERE entry=10177;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What? Grik\'tha sent you in here after me?$B$BI don\'t know whether to be touched or call her a fool!$B$BDo you think you could help me get out of this cage? It\'s a bit cramped.' WHERE entry=10178;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='When it became clear that our expedition was trapped in Outland with no way to return to Azeroth, the Kirin Tor contingent traveled to the Plains of Farahlon and built Kirin\'Var village. I left the administration of the town in the hands of Custodian Dieworth, but when Kael\'thas and his forces sealed me in the Violet Tower, I lost contact with the custodian.$B$BSearch for him in Kirin\'Var Village and help him in any way you can, $N. I\'m certain he\'s got his hands full in the aftermath of the attack.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Custodian Dierworth at Kirin\'Var Village in Netherstorm.' WHERE entry=10179;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Speak with Isfar, who can be found near the entrance to the Sethekk Halls in Auchindoun.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I should\'ve suspected he would send you after me. He tried to talk me out of returning to the Sethekk Halls, but I couldn\'t live with myself if I allowed Lakka to die in there.' WHERE entry=10180;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done well, $N. I can no longer sense any restlessness in Dathric\'s spirit. I would give much for the opportunity to speak to him one more time, but it is enough that he is finally at rest.' WHERE entry=10182;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh, Coppernickels finally decided to report his findings, did he?  Lazy scientists!$B$BWhat\'s this?$B$B<The chief riffles through the notations a few times, clearly with a look of disbelief.>$B$BHe says here that the violent nether-energies flowing through the Netherstorm are going to rip everything to shreds in only a few months.$B$BThat\'s inconvenient - now we\'ll have to move up the time-table on building the rocket ship!' WHERE entry=10183;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It is not what they deserved, but it is the best we can do.' WHERE entry=10184;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The custodian looks dismayed.>$B$BI can already see the next wave coming over the horizon. Culling them will work for the time being, but more permanent measures are needed.' WHERE entry=10185;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Gah!  Those look rough.  Maybe we can use them in the tertiary engine manifold chamber?$B$BStill, a good job Junior Technician 3rd Grade!  You\'ll make 2nd Grade in no time.' WHERE entry=10186;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Although things are grim here, it heartened us quite a bit to hear from you that the archmage has not forgotten the village\'s plight.$B$B<The custodian glances up at the tower.>$B$BIt\'s ridiculous, isn\'t it? Sometimes it seems all that separates us is a wall of mere stone. The wall of magic is easy enough to forget.$B$BIf you would be so kind, ascend the tower and let Archmage Vargoth know that we are making progress with the village and will soon have a plan to ward off the mana creatures.',objectives_loc4='Speak to Archmage Vargoth at the top of the Violet Tower in Netherstorm.' WHERE entry=10187;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Retrieve the Sigil of Krasus from Spellbinder Maryana at Manaforge Coruu, northwest of the Violet Tower. When you have gained the sigil, use Archmage Vargoth\'s Staff to project an Image of Archmage Vargoth and inform him of your progress.$B$BIf you lose Archmage Vargoth\'s Staff, speak to Ravandwyr at Area 52 to receive a replacement.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, it is as magnificent as I remembered. Can you not feel the power radiating from it?$B$BOf course, there is much more to be done, but you have my deepest thanks for restoring the sigil to me.' WHERE entry=10188;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent! With this roster we can make more educated decisions when targeting Kael\'s followers at the manaforges.$B$BIt\'s too bad, I was beginning to take a liking to killing his lackeys indiscriminately.' WHERE entry=10189;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hey, watch where you\'re pointing that thing! You\'ve got it set to \'Kill\'!!!$B$BIt looks like you\'ve recharged the battery, and then some. This\'ll help immensely to keep these guys going.' WHERE entry=10190;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You did it! You did it! I could just kiss you!$B$BOh, darn... the Maxx A. Million Mk. V is out of juice again. Ah well, he had enough to get the job done, and that\'s what counts!$B$BRocket-Chief Fuselage will be pleased to get these draenei machines hooked up inside the X-52 Nether-Rocket! That means a promotion for me! I\'m so happy, I just have to give you a reward!$B$BHere, take your pick from one of these.' WHERE entry=10191;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Reclaim Krasus\'s Compendium - Chapter 1, Krasus\'s Compendium - Chapter 2, and Krasus\'s Compendium - Chapter 3 from Kirin\'Var Village\'s Town Square. Use Archmage Vargoth\'s Staff to contact the archmage once you have the chapters.$B$BIf you lose Archmage Vargoth\'s Staff, speak to Ravandwyr at Area 52 to receive a replacement.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Archmage Vargoth\'s image seems to inspect the compendium.>$B$BIt\'s a little worse for the wear, but considering the treatment it\'s been through, it\'s a miracle all of it survived. Safeguard it, $N. Without it, we stand little chance of being able to break the tower\'s ward.' WHERE entry=10192;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re one reliable fellow, $N. If there\'s one thing I like more than killing Kael\'s lapdogs, it is having someone else do it for me.$B$BLess blood on my clothes that way.' WHERE entry=10193;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Arranging for your flight wasn\'t cheap. Let\'s hope you have what it takes to get the job done.' WHERE entry=10194;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent! When I\'m through with you, you will be able to slip among the Sunfury ranks unnoticed.' WHERE entry=10197;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Use the Sunfury Disguise, go into Manaforge Coruu and listen to the conversation between Commander Dawnforge and Arcanist Ardonis.  Report back to Caledis Brightdawn after completing this task.$B$BCompleting tasks for the Scryers will cause your Aldor reputation level to decrease.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Manaforge Duro is in trouble? I\'m sure Thalodien will love to hear the news. Let\'s wrap up the job here first.' WHERE entry=10198;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc4='How goes the eavesdropping, $N? You\'d best hurry. I\'m getting antsy here.' WHERE entry=10198;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Wow! Alright, now we\'re talking!$B$BLet me just take those little beauties and squeeze the badness right out of them. This should make a rocket fuel brew that\'ll blow everyone\'s socks off!$B$BHere, just let me mix the shale oil and this stinger venom together, and we\'ll see what happens....' WHERE entry=10199;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You do not cease to amaze me, $N. That was quite the feat of stealth you pulled off at Manaforge Coruu.' WHERE entry=10200;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s about time you showed up. I was beginning to wonder if the Scryers were interested at all.' WHERE entry=10202;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You must be the one that zapped all of that sapping equipment back to us here from the ruins! Hooray for you!$B$BI\'ve already reallocated the equipment out to our other locations. Now we\'ll be able to expedite our fissure operations on this whole island by an order of magnitude! The nether-rocket will be completed in no time!$B$BHmmm, that\'s odd.  Wait a minute, did you say that you sent four things back to us?  I only got three...' WHERE entry=10203;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Multi-Spectrum Terrain Analyzer retrieved',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Big Wagon Full of Explosives retrieved' WHERE entry=10203;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hmmm... just as I suspected.$B$BExposure to this level of raw energy greatly magnifies our innate addiction to magic.$B$BI\'m not surprised Kael gets away with what he does; all his subordinates are basically drunk on this.' WHERE entry=10204;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s a relief to hear that scum is finally dealt with. You do good work, $N... may I be so forward as to call you by your name?$B$BIf you\'re willing, I have another task that needs doing. One that is very important and someone of your obvious skill should be able to handle with ease.' WHERE entry=10205;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hehe, ethereal suckers!$B$BThanks for getting us these parts, $C.  I bet we can just hook these babies right up inside the rocket.  I wonder what they do?  Should be fun finding out!$B$BHmm, let me see if I can dig up some pocket change to throw your way.' WHERE entry=10206;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Forward Base: Reaver\'s Fall REUSE',details_loc4='Your battle prowess has been noted by high command, $C. They want to send you to the front lines to meet up with Maimfist\'s crew. They\'re radicals, devoted to the complete extermination of the Burning Legion, so you may fit right in...$B$BHead east about 200 paces and veer south at the jutting mass of land. You\'ll see Reaver\'s Fall where an old farm used to stand. Once there, you are to report to Foward Commander To\'arch.$B$BNow move out!' WHERE entry=10207;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done! I could almost feel the tremors of the explosions from here!$B$BNow, we have one more bombing mission for you...' WHERE entry=10208;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Defeat Summoner Kanthin at Manaforge Duro, on the island to the north of Sunfury Hold, and reclaim the Stone of Glacius from him. When you have obtained the stone, use Archmage Vargoth\'s Staff to contact the archmage.$B$BIf you lose Archmage Vargoth\'s Staff, speak to Ravandwyr at Area 52 to receive a replacement.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<You\'re not sure whether it\'s just distortion. or the archmage really is smiling.>$B$BWith the last of my possessions restored, I have everything I need to break through Kael\'thas\'s magic. I\'ll begin working the spell right away.' WHERE entry=10209;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The light that filled your senses as you approached A\'dal intensifies as you address him. Melodic chimes continue to ring within your head.>$B$B<You are safe here.>' WHERE entry=10210;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I hope you learned a thing or two about Shattrath, $N. It might take some time for things to sink in.' WHERE entry=10211;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc4='The stories of men are ephemeral, $N. The stories of cities last well into the years.' WHERE entry=10211;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Hero of the Mag\'har',objectives_loc4='Return to Greatmother Geyah at Garadar in Nagrand.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='You are truly the hero of the Mag\'har, $N. If not for you, we would have surely been overrun by the ogres and Broken.$B$BWe are a poor people but we do have some artifacts of power. Please, I insist that you take from our coffer.' WHERE entry=10212;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We were shot down by the Burning Legion, even though we waved a flag of truce.  Who knew the Burning Legion was so mean? $B$BWe cannot come with you to Spinebreaker Post.  We need to repair our zeppelin and be on our way.' WHERE entry=10213;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The mine\'s been overrun by a plague of gan\'arg misfits, and on top of that, the peons have decided that this is a fine time for a nap! I don\'t know how they can sleep through all the disurbances coming from the mine, but that\'s the least of my problems.$B$BIf we don\'t get rid of those gan\'arg pests soon, Thrallmar\'s supply of ore and other minerals will be cut off. I\'ve already asked Watch Commander Krunk for help, but he says he can\'t spare the men with the town under constant attack. Will you help?',objectives_loc4='Kill 15 Gan\'arg Sappers and return to Foreman Razelcraz.' WHERE entry=10214;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<You close your eyes and press a button.>' WHERE entry=10216;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Fossil Fuel',details_loc4='My Shredder is out of fuel!' WHERE entry=10217;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Seeing as how this was Morphalius\'s idea, I decided to give him his old job back. Well done little flesh beast. Well done, indeed!$B$BRemember, if you\'re ever looking for work and happen to be in Netherstorm, come find me at the Stormspire.' WHERE entry=10218;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Unyielding have felt the strength of the Horde.  No doubt they will soon be in the mood to listen to my proposed alliance.' WHERE entry=10220;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'ll always miss Sparky. <sniff> But we\'ll all sleep better now knowing that as Dr. Boom he is no longer around to terrorize us!$B$BJust let this be a lesson to you. Don\'t come down here without a nether helmet!$B$BNow, how can I repay you?' WHERE entry=10221;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What you\'ve done this day can never bring back the fallen, but perhaps it can help soothe their spirits. Although, truth be told, no amount of blood can quench my anger over the actions of Kael\'thas.' WHERE entry=10222;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<You\'re not certain, but it seems as though Custodian Dieworth is on the verge of tears.>$B$BAt last, it is through. If I could will myself out of existence, I would, but the truth is I don\'t know how to let go. For the ones in the village, it is difficult but straightforward. I suppose this is the price we pay for retaining such strong ties to this place.' WHERE entry=10223;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Wow, that\'s a lot of essence!$B$BOk, let\'s see what happens when I mix it with the etherlithium matrix crystals.' WHERE entry=10224;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ooh, etherlithium matrix crystals. Yeah, those sound important!$B$BLet\'s just put them over here and I\'ll get to figuring them out in a moment.' WHERE entry=10225;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'s more like it! Alright, now I think we\'re in business.$B$BJust let me dump this stuff into the thing' WHERE entry=10226;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The child is correct. I was once a "death priest."$B$B<Ramdor winces.>$B$BSuch an unsavory title.$B$BThrough that corridor lies the Auchenai Crypts. Inside you will find the remnants of my priory. They are all mad now, of course. Insane to the last! I suppose I stood out, being the last one among them with any common sense. Of course, I was excommunicated for my beliefs.$B$BWhat are my beliefs, you say?' WHERE entry=10227;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I believe that the dead, which we have been caring for these last 500 odd years, should be left alone. Maladaar has other plans. He has retreated to the Crypt of Remembrance to start his experiments... Necromancy.$B$BI hope you weren\'t thinking about going in there... Not before helping me out so that these damned spirits will finally leave me alone. I know where they keep their treasures, $R. Got your attention, eh?$B$BBring me the book of the dead, held by the Aldor, Ezekiel of Shattrath.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Book of the dead? Never heard of it... What\'s this about anyway? Who sent you?' WHERE entry=10228;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I have studied ancient history my entire un-life.  I have never seen anything like this book.  It tells the entire history of the Armory, including events that happened after its destruction.  $B$BThe Unyielding have kept their history, even after they had fallen in battle.  With this book we will be able to understand the Unyielding and convince them to join us.' WHERE entry=10229;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well $N.  This ancient horn will allow us to summon the Unyielding. $B$BThat is, if they are willing.' WHERE entry=10230;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Ezekiel said the book has been stolen. Your best bet is to find the Ruffians and see if they have any information.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ok, ok! Don\'t hurt us. We had the book but we sold it...' WHERE entry=10231;
UPDATE locales_quest SET EndText_loc4='Beat Down "Dirty" Larry and Get Information' WHERE entry=10231;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, that\'s good and bad news, now isn\'t it? We\'ve dealt them a blow, but with the Burning Legion running free all over the Netherstorm' WHERE entry=10232;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Kirin Tor hardly relish destruction for its own sake, but we have no qualms about acting against our enemies, even in death.' WHERE entry=10233;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These will have to do for now, I suppose. If only we could scare them off.$B$BHey, that gives me an idea!' WHERE entry=10234;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='He, uh... he said what? THEY\'RE GONNA GO AFTER AREA 52?!$B$BOh, this is not good... not good!' WHERE entry=10235;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hurray, you found some parts!  Now maybe I can get my shredder working.  If I earn enough money I might be able to get back to Booty Bay.$B$BI sure hope my cousin, Screed Luckheed, crashes that stupid zeppelin of his.  I can\'t believe he tricked me into coming to Outland.' WHERE entry=10236;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Heh, you\'re kidding, right? The Burning Legion is blaming us for all of that?$B$BBut YOU\'RE the one that did it!$B$BOy, I have a headache and it\'s as big as this rocket. Okay, okay, this calls for a change of plans.$B$BIf the Burning Legion thinks that it\'s going to come here, destroy our town and ruin my dream of cruising through the Twisted Nether, they are sadly mistaken.$B$BAnd I know just the goblin to help us out.' WHERE entry=10237;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you for saving my peons.  Now maybe I can get them to fix my shredder with those parts you found. earn some money and get out of Outland.  I can\'t wait to be back in Booty Bay.' WHERE entry=10238;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I don\'t believe I\'ve seen anything like this before. There\'s certainly a lot of energy suspended in here, but it\'s in a raw form. We\'ll have to be careful with it, but I think we can find a way to adapt this to help ward off the mana creatures.' WHERE entry=10239;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work. Keep your fingers crossed, $N. I\'m going to activate the shield.' WHERE entry=10240;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work, $N. The Scryers have uncovered valuable information thanks to your distraction. Maybe they\'ll actually share it with us this time.' WHERE entry=10241;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A blood test, is it?  It will be my pleasure.  I always enjoy working with blood...' WHERE entry=10242;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You unwrap the scroll and ready yourself to copy down the strange symbols.' WHERE entry=10243;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done well, $N. Allow me a few moments to go over your transcription.$B$BYou have the priesthood\'s thanks, $C.' WHERE entry=10245;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent job, $N. With your dedication we\'re sure to defeat our enemy.' WHERE entry=10246;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well. well, it would appear that we are in luck, young man.$B$BI was just recently able to finish the construction of my latest invention, the Scrap Reaver X6000!$B$BAnd you\'re going to have the honor of helping me test it so that it can be used in defense of Area 52!' WHERE entry=10247;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, my boy that certainly was exciting! And for my money, I\'d say that the Scrap Reaver X6000 performed admirably, despite its rookie pilot.$B$BHehe, no, don\'t take offense, I was just kidding. After all, you just saved Area 52 and the X' WHERE entry=10248;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='$N! Or, should I say Junior Technician 1st Grade $N?! Oh hell, who am I kidding? Skipping a grade isn\'t a good enough reward for what you\'ve done. I\'m going to make you my first officer!$B$BYou\'ve saved all of us, and more importantly the X-52 Nether-Rocket! I could just kiss you... but I won\'t.$B$BInstead, please let me present you with the gratitude of Area 52. Take your pick!' WHERE entry=10249;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I am glad to hear that the Unyielding joined you in your battle.  I thought they might come to the sound of their own battle horn, but I could not be sure.  Perhaps we have given some of them the vengeance they so desperately crave.  $B$BYou have slain Urtrak and we must report your victory to Commander Hogarth in the Expedition Armory.  He will understand the risks you have taken on his behalf.' WHERE entry=10250;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The signs were all there but I turned a blind eye.$B$BThe Legion\'s grasp grows stronger every day. Even in these parts...$B$BHad I known... Had I known that my boy was communing with demons... They offered him power and then gave him a taste of that power. That was all that it took...$B$BThe book is gone. Taken by Levixus... His plans are known only to me and his dark master.$B$BStranger, I don\'t know if you\'ve ever done right in your life, but know this: the boy must be stopped.' WHERE entry=10251;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Stranger... I was not forthright with you. Once you drink this potion, you will forever see into the world of the dead. This recipe that you drink of is a rite of initiation for all death priests of Auchindoun. Many go mad after its effects have taken hold. Seeing the dead is ... shocking.$B$B<Nitrin puts the potion up to your lips.>$B$BDo you wish to continue?' WHERE entry=10252;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='If the old draenei said to destroy the book, why didn\'t you?$B$B<Ramdor glares at you.>$B$BBah, what\'s the difference. You might be greedy but at least you\'re honest.$B$BMe on the other hand... I lied to get this book. I have no idea where these poor lost souls kept their treasure nor would I tell you if I did - however - I do have something for you. You did a good thing on this day. Perhaps a great thing... You should be rewarded.$B$BBy the way, welcome to the fold.$B$B<Ramdor points to the spirits.>' WHERE entry=10253;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well met, my $Gbrother:sister;. I\'m glad you\'ve come. I am Danath - leader of the Sons of Lothar, and force commander of this hold.' WHERE entry=10254;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Thiah Redmane\'s eyes widen as you describe the results of the experiment.>$B$BBut, how could that happen? I\'m certain I prepared the antidote correctly!$B$BI\'ve seen it work with spider and snake venoms, so why would it backfire here? Perhaps that\'s one of Outland\'s many peculiarities, $N. I\'d best pass this information along to my comrades.' WHERE entry=10255;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Commander Sarannis, you say? Hmm...$B$BShe\'s one of Kael\'thas\'s advisors, but certainly not a mage. I remember her from the attack on Kirin\'Var Village. I think your impressions are correct, $N. She\'s not maintaining the curse personally, but she holds the key to it.' WHERE entry=10256;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Amazing! From what little I\'ve seen of the fate of Farahlon, I\'m not certain I want to go outside, but it\'s much better than being trapped here for the rest of my days.' WHERE entry=10257;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We lost our battle against the fel orcs so very long ago. You have restored some of our lost honor by killing Urtrak. $B$BTake one of our weapons with you.  When you are fighting our most hated foes, use this weapon, and those who are free of our curse will come to your aid.  $B$BBefore you leave, those who died at the siege tower wish to honor you for destroying our enemies.' WHERE entry=10258;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $N. Among the chaos of battle, heroes burn bright against the darkness. Your light shines true!' WHERE entry=10259;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Woo hoo! Do you know how hard these things are to come by? It\'s not like I\'m getting a regular shipment of parts out here.$B$BTell you what, as payment I want you to take something out of my box of junk. I\'m sure there\'ll be something in there you can use. And if not, sell it.$B$BAlright, let me just take that off of your hands and get it into my Long Neck Spectrum Analyzer before the failing servo in it explodes!' WHERE entry=10261;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These insignia are a good start.$B$BUnfortunately while you were at the Heap, one of my other agents amongst the Zaxxis sent word to me that Warp-Raider Nesaad still lives!' WHERE entry=10262;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hello, $R.$B$BYou don\'t happen to be available for a recovery mission of some importance?' WHERE entry=10263;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hello, $R.$B$BYou don\'t happen to be available for a recovery mission of some importance?' WHERE entry=10264;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Let me have a look at that.$B$BHmm, there doesn\'t appear to be anything special about it. I doubt this is it, though the manner in which you describe the Burning Legion\'s activities at the ruins, it sounds as if they\'re searching for something in particular as well.$B$BLet us hope that it\'s not the crystal that the nexus-prince wants so badly.' WHERE entry=10265;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes, it\'s true. The blood elves have reneged on yet another purchase of goods that has already been delivered.$B$BAs Nether-Stalker Khay\'ji has vouched for you, I am hopeful that you will be able to assist me in this matter.' WHERE entry=10266;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, I for one am glad that this petty little business is behind us. I cannot remember a time when the Consortium has had dealings with such boorish and untrustworthy beings.$B$BYou, however, seem to be very trustworthy, $N. Perhaps you wouldn\'t mind doing me one more favor?' WHERE entry=10267;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I welcome you to the Stormspire, $C. Please enjoy the hospitality of the Consortium.$B$BYou may place that equipment anywhere. I suspect that you\'ll be picking it back up rather soon.' WHERE entry=10268;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Dealer Hazzin lowers his voice to a whisper.>$B$BAh, I know of your mission. It is one of great importance to Nexus-Prince Haramad!$B$BNow that we know the location of this first triangulation point, you must move swiftly to find the second!' WHERE entry=10269;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This power cell should hold for our purposes. Once the money starts rolling in, we\'ll improve it even more.$B$BEnough with such things. Every moment spent in discussion translates to lost profit.' WHERE entry=10270;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Gather 8 Nether Dragon Essence, then return to the Ethereal Teleport Pad area. Nether Dragon Essence may be obtained from Nether Drakes or Nether Dragons.',offerrewardtext_loc4='And to think, that wretched ethereal was going to sell these essences to the blood elves like so much candy...' WHERE entry=10271;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These will work quite nicely, $N. Thank you for agreeing to help us.$B$BBefore we can continue, however, there is something else we\'ll need to address.' WHERE entry=10272;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Your former employer, Wind Trader Marid, must\'ve gotten wind that you\'re helping us now. Through my projection, I\'ve seen his nether-stalkers entering the area, hoping to track us down.$B$BWe\'ve been able evade them so far, but Marid must be dealt with before the problem grows more severe.$B$BIf your impressions of Marid are correct, he\'ll do just about anything to secure the supply of his product. Return to him and tell him you\'re prepared to offer a deal. Lure him away and slay him.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Now that that troublesome ethereal has been dealt with, we can focus our efforts on understanding these nether dragons. I\'ve had a chance to examine the eggs and I\'ve made a few discoveries.' WHERE entry=10273;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. Well done indeed. The nether dragonkin will not accept a blue dragon among them at first, but with time and the firm demonstration of my authority, they will come around. Scattered, isolated, and without a definitive leader, we must be vigilant in preventing them from falling under the sway of a malevolent power, keeping them in check all the while.' WHERE entry=10274;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Very good indeed. The nexus-prince shall be pleased!$B$BWe now have the second point, which will now tell us where the third is, and the general vicinity of the crystal!' WHERE entry=10275;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Beyond my wildest dreams, I never thought that you would be able to retrieve the crystal!$B$BAnd then to actually give it to me! Do you have any idea how powerful it is?$B$BYour selflessness is inspirational and beyond reproach, $N! You have given me much to think about.' WHERE entry=10276;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hopefully you now have a better understanding of what is expected of you.$B$B' WHERE entry=10277;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Unbelievable.  You have touched the void itself!  $N, you have saved my life\'s work.  But there is more that must be done, and you can help me.' WHERE entry=10278;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We must prepare you for the battles that lie ahead...' WHERE entry=10279;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have recovered Spirit\'s Song!  It is the ata\'mal crystal that Prophet Velen left behind with his people for safekeeping before he went upon his ill-fated mission to the Exodar.$B$BOdd that he did not foresee it falling into the hands of the Burning Legion, if even for a short time.$B$BOr, perhaps he did?  It may be that he foresaw all of this, and left it there so that you would retrieve the crystal and deliver it to me here?$B$BI sense that is the truth of it.  You are a great hero of your people, $N!' WHERE entry=10280;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='My name is Tyrygosa, of the brood of Malygos, but most call me \'Tyri.\' My companion is the $C Jorad Mace.$B$BWord of these strange dragonkin has already traveled far and I fear that too many will rush to exploit them for profit without realizing the true nature of what they\'re dealing with. With your help, we\'re hoping to gain insight into these creatures before others discover their presence.' WHERE entry=10281;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Our worst fears might soon be realized. The forces at work behind this temporal disturbance are a new flight of dragons known as the Infinite. We do not know where they came from or why they are destroying timeways.$B$BIn this pocket of time, they have kidnapped Taretha Foxton, daughter of Tammis Foxton, the secretary of Aedelas Blackmoore, ruler of Durnholde and overseer of all internment camps on Azeroth.' WHERE entry=10282;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are friends of Taretha? So this is her new plan? Very well then...' WHERE entry=10283;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Internment Lodges Set Ablaze' WHERE entry=10283;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done a great thing, $N. Alas, the young warchief\'s memory of these events must be as they originally were... Andormu awaits you in the master\'s lair.' WHERE entry=10284;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'ll talk, $C.  Put your weapon down, I don\'t want any more trouble.' WHERE entry=10286;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Return to Magistrix Carinda at Falcon Watch.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Viera Sunwhisper?  That lousy little brat.$B$BI will show her I\'m not one to be trifled with!' WHERE entry=10287;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I want you to speak with Amish Wildhammer, standing about 30 paces south of us, and catch the first flight to Honor Hold. When you arrive at Honor Hold, you\'ll be greeted by Marshal Isildor. I have prepared a report detailing our situation here.  Give him the report, and tell him you\'re ready for duty.$B$BYou have your orders, soldier, now move out!  And though your blood must be burning to help us against the fiends below, waste no time here.  Honor Hold needs you even more.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Reports for Honor Hold?  No problem -- we\'ll get you there fast and safe on one of my gryphons!' WHERE entry=10288;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'ll rally what troops I can and send them to aid Orion\'s forces at the Dark Portal. The Legion will not soon forget the battle cry of the Horde! As for you $N, you\'ve done a great service for Thrallmar this day. I expect you\'ll be a great help to us here... if you have the wits to survive, that is.' WHERE entry=10289;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, yes. This is precisely the grade I was hoping for. We may give up mining the crystal formations altogether if we can secure a supply from the giants.' WHERE entry=10290;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We\'ve already lost many brave warriors to this cursed wasteland. I have little interest in sending more untested recruits to the slaughter.$B$B<Nazgrel glares at you sternly through his ragged wolf-mask>$B$BStill, if General Krakork sent you to me, he must have seen something in you. What say you then, $N? Will you serve your warchief with honor?' WHERE entry=10291;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Gathering a precious commodity in small batches has a quaint, cottage-industry feel to it, but it\'s just not competitive in today\'s market.$B$BNo, what we need is a method of mass producing farahlite! Then, the quantity on the market will be completely within our control.$B$BI have an idea, but it\'s going to require a powerful, focused energy source. There\'s only one possible place to find an energy source powerful enough. Go to the Legion\'s camps to our north and \'procure\' some of their cannon.',objectives_loc4='Zuben Elgenubi wants you to capture 8 Legion Cannon and bring them back to the Stormspire.' WHERE entry=10292;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done! I can\'t wait to put this to the test.' WHERE entry=10293;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='$BExcellent. the warp rift generator is almost complete. There is only one final ingredient we require. Soon we shall be able to open up a warp rift to the deepest parts of the abyss. $B$BWho knows what strange creature may come through? Think of it $N. the power such knowledge will bring is limitless.' WHERE entry=10294;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have saved my life\'s work $N.$B$BThey called me insane. they laughed at me. they thought I was mad for my obsession with the Void Ridge and Warp Fields. Now with this soul shard I can unlock the secrets of the voidwalkers. I will command the power of the abyss.' WHERE entry=10295;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Indeed, if the orcs never make it to Azeroth, the Alliance will never form. Eventually civil war will break out, further weakening the human kingdoms.$B$BUltimately the Burning Legion will invade Azeroth, destroying it in the absence of any defenders.' WHERE entry=10296;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Beyond this timeway, in the heart of the Black Morass, the Guardian, Medivh, feverishly works to open the Dark Portal, heralding in the age of orcs upon Azeroth.$B$BThe Infinite have sent their rift lords to stop this from happening.$B$BScattered across the morass, rifts will materialize. Infinite will pour out of the rifts and attempt to destroy Medivh\'s shields and, ultimately, Medivh.$B$BKill their rift lords and leaders! Do this until Medivh succeeds. Use this chrono-beacon should you require aid.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well, $N. The child, Andormu, wishes to speak to you once more.' WHERE entry=10297;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Once more you have secured the present and the future of this world, $N. Please accept these items as reward for your accomplishments.' WHERE entry=10298;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Light smiles upon you, $N. We were all praying for your success.' WHERE entry=10299;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Ravandwyr carefully examines the crystals. then selects one.>$B$BThis crystal should work. I\'ll reshape the stave\'s socket to secure the new headpiece.$B$BWhen Archmage Vargoth sees it, he will be disappointed, but I can bear my master\'s disappointment if it means we\'ve freed him.' WHERE entry=10300;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Obtain the Heliotrope Oculus from Spellreaver Marathelle at Sunfury Hold. Use Archmage Vargoth\'s Staff to contact the archmage once you have achieved your goal.$B$BIf you lose Archmage Vargoth\'s Staff, speak to Ravandwyr at Area 52 to receive a replacement.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent, $N. Now, we have most of what we\'ll need to attempt to break Kael\'thas\'s magic.$B$BAnd if the blood elves suffer from the loss of their local commander, so much the better.' WHERE entry=10301;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re finished? That\'s good news. Hopefully, we can find a way to avoid the killing of these mutated beasts in the future.$B$BI believe I have formed a plan that might give us an alternative solution to this problem, but I will need your help.' WHERE entry=10302;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These blood elves mean to kill us all. How are we to divert them from this course?' WHERE entry=10303;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='$N, is it? I\'ve heard good things about you and the work you\'ve been doing in the short time since you came to.$B$BWe\'ll definitely need your help getting things back to normal. Zhanaa, over there, could also use your help, I\'m sure.' WHERE entry=10304;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, yes. I\'d heard that Abjurist Belmara had an old book of stories, but I had no idea that she brought it with her to Outland. I\'m certain her spirit will rest easier knowing that you\'ve found it and returned it to her dwelling.' WHERE entry=10305;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We used to always comment that Luminrath would wear that cloak with just about anything. To him, red went equally well with white, black, purple, blue, yellow, orange, and green. He would never wear the same robe two days in a row, but the cloak was always there...' WHERE entry=10306;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The custodian smiles at the mention of Cohlien\'s name.>$B$BYou\'re absolutely right about the hat. He wore it all the time and wouldn\'t let it out of his sight.$B$BThere were a couple of times when a fellow mage, who shall remain nameless, \'borrowed\' the hat and hid it as a prank. Needless to say the threat of one of Cohlien\'s frostbolts changed his mind.$B$BI\'m going to miss little Cohlien. He had quite a way with the elven women.' WHERE entry=10307;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Traitors, all of them!$B$BGood work, $C! If you find your way back down there again, I\'m always looking to add to my collection of their insignia!' WHERE entry=10308;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Wow, look at that... a beating fel reaver heart! Well, it\'s not really \'beating\', but you know what I mean.$B$BI can\'t wait to put this thing to good use. Or, maybe sell it. I know a few suck... er, clients that might be interested.$B$BHere, you\'ve earned your pay and then some!' WHERE entry=10309;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That is most excellent news, my friend!$B$BYou and Drijya have done us a great service. With that warp' WHERE entry=10310;
UPDATE locales_quest SET EndText_loc4='Burning Legion warp-gate sabotaged' WHERE entry=10310;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I hope that Gahruj has sent you to help me with my mission.' WHERE entry=10311;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hmm...$B$BIt seems I was right. There is a pattern here.$B$BThe most aggressive and dangerous ghosts coincide with the most powerful and highest ranking Kirin Tor who resided in the village. The townspeople and tradesmen seem overlooked by comparison. What could this mean?' WHERE entry=10312;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This is grave news, $N.  The warp energies emanating from the pipelines are dangerously high.$B$BWe must find a way to shut down the manaforges or what little remains of Outland will be shattered into pieces.' WHERE entry=10313;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Southern Pipeline Measured',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Western Pipeline Measured' WHERE entry=10313;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Custodian Dieworth examines the remnants.>$B$BThe device you described sounds like a necromantic focus... I should\'ve known that no-good apprentice would stoop to this. I thought his training would keep him from going this far. but I guess he\'s proven me wrong.' WHERE entry=10314;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Anything that we can do to encourage them to stop what they\'re doing at these manaforges is a good thing.$B$BThey certainly do not seem to be able to be reasoned with. And it seems clear to me that whatever their leaders have in mind, they are insane.$B$BAs remuneration for your faithful service to the goals of the Consortium, I would like to offer you the coin of your realm if it does not offend you.' WHERE entry=10315;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A glowing orb sits atop a square-shaped pedestal. At first glance, it seems to be a repository for magical energy, but what kind of energy, and for whose use?' WHERE entry=10316;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The foreman speaks in hushed tones.>$B$BYou came in here to kill me? Hmph. Well I guess the ethereal don\'t know everything, do they?$B$BI\'m not the one that you want, trust me.' WHERE entry=10317;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A doomguard overmaster? That\'s odd! What\'s the Burning Legion doing in there?$B$BSo, some of the blood elves are defecting. We\'ll keep that in mind if we ever attempt to take the place by force. At least there\'s some good news that has come from all of this, no?$B$BPlease, $N, take this with my deepest gratitude.' WHERE entry=10318;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work, $N. Possession of the phylactery will be the key to our victory. When you enter battle with Naberius, I will smash it, exposing him to your attacks.' WHERE entry=10319;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The defeat of Naberius is a great achievement, $N. I can\'t help thinking that we might have had a chance against Kael\'thas\'s forces if the apprentice\'s loyalties had been in the right place that day.' WHERE entry=10320;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work. Only two manaforges remain active.$B$BSoon Kael\'thas will be cut off from his main source of power.' WHERE entry=10321;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We\'ve received news from one of the two manaforges that remain operational.  The Sunfury army is losing control of Manaforge Duro.$B$BDroves of errant mana creatures have been attracted to it by its increased energy production - the manaforge is in chaos.$B$BAn explosion at Duro has the potential to cause a chain reaction that would endanger all of Outland.  Overseer Athanel is in possesion of the access crystal you need to safely disable the manaforge.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You are blessed by the naaru, $N. Your dedication to the cause will not go unnoticed or unrewarded.' WHERE entry=10322;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Burning Legion? Allied with Kael\'thas Sunstrider?$B$BThis is dire news. It explains much about what we\'ve seen here and in Shadowmoon.$B$BWe must send word back to Shattrath City immediately.' WHERE entry=10323;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Wonderful! You\'re turning into quite the hunter, $N.$B$BHow would you like to look more like me? Well here is your chance! While you were out hunting, I fashioned these items out of some buck hides I had laying around. Take your pick!' WHERE entry=10324;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Facing the demons of the Burning Legion and the mad cultists that worship them is no small feat, $N.  You\'ve shown great dedication and courage.  Keep it up and your renown among the Aldor will continue to grow.' WHERE entry=10325;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You continue to prove your worth, $N.  Fight the enemies of the Light wherever you may find them; your actions will be well-rewarded.' WHERE entry=10326;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You continue to prove your worth, $N.  Fight the enemies of the Light wherever you may find them; your actions will be well-rewarded.' WHERE entry=10327;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent job, $N! Let us see what can be learned from these briefings.' WHERE entry=10328;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Of course it worked! I\'m a spymaster; my information is always accurate.$B$BAnyhow, I have a whole new exciting job lined up for you. You want to hear about it? Of course you do.' WHERE entry=10329;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We heard all the commotion and were just about to leave. Glad to see you didn\'t take too bad of a beating.' WHERE entry=10330;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank goodness! Now I can get back to work. I know you think I\'m crazy, working on the piece that will earn me journeyman status away from the forge proper, but I can\'t run the risk of one of the other apprentices copying my design.' WHERE entry=10331;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Master Rhonsus taught me everything I know about my trade. I will honor his memory by using my skills to serve the people of Kirin\'Var.' WHERE entry=10332;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What?! He called me his \'partner\'? I\'m his wife!$B$BAnd he said I had a sharp tongue! Ooh, when I get back to Area 52, I\'m going to box his big, green ears!$B$BBut I\'m glad that you\'re here. He was right about one thing; I can definitely use your help!' WHERE entry=10333;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Find Bessy in the fields near Kirin\'Var Village\'s Chapel Hill.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Removing the bell from your pack, you ring it a couple of times and show it to Bessy, who seems to recognize it. The cow allows the bell\'s cord to be fastened around her neck and looks at you expectantly.>' WHERE entry=10334;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re not just pulling my bandage, right? That\'s most excellent news!$B$BNow that you\'ve done the surveying grunt' WHERE entry=10335;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Slay 10 Hounds of Culuthas and 5 Eyes of Culuthas.  Then return to Nether-Stalker Nauthis at the Stormspire in the Netherstorm.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Truly an exceptional job.$B$BWith the demons of Culuthas slain, Zephyrion will be able to safely take his excavation team into the Ruins of Farahlon.$B$BAccept this coin as a token of my gratitude.' WHERE entry=10336;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Bessy, is that you?$B$BThank you for bringing back my Bessy, $N. I couldn\'t live without her!' WHERE entry=10337;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That makes three manaforges you\'ve shut down, $N. Kael\'thas must be having a real fit right about now.' WHERE entry=10338;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We must gather whatever data that they\'ve stored in this area.' WHERE entry=10339;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hah hah! A fresh $R from the mainland! Well don\'t worry - Shatter Point might make you queasy but she doesn\'t stray far!$B$BAnd I\'ve only seen her flip upside down once... or twice.' WHERE entry=10340;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done well, $N. Kael\'s army will not easily recover from the blow you\'ve dealt today.' WHERE entry=10341;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='OK! Ingredient number one is down.$B$BNow, if you\'re up to it, we\'ll move on to something that\'ll give the shale oil that little extra kick that it\'ll need to blast the nether rocket into the Twisting Nether... or oblivion, whichever comes first.' WHERE entry=10342;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A mana bomb?$B$B<Morran turns the fragment over in his hands.>$B$BIt\'s nigh unthinkable! Even the best minds in Dalaran couldn\'t have conceived of a weapon like this. The sheer magnitude of the disturbance must\'ve torn a rift in the nether, giving these creatures access to our lands.' WHERE entry=10343;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You spoke with Runetog? A fine dwarf he is. Keeps his gryphons in good shape and battle ready.$B$BI\'m Gryphongar, commander here at Shatter Point. I know it\'s not pretty, but this hunk of rock is a vital staging point for sorties into Hellfire. You\'ll see gryphons flying out and in non-stop!$B$BAdvice? Here\'s some: keep your gear stowed, your stomach empty, and your eye on the horizon... if Shatter Point starts to teeter, then grab onto something that won\'t float away!' WHERE entry=10344;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Use the Protectorate Igniter on 12 Withered Corpses. Return the Protectorate Igniter to Agent Araxes outside of Access Shaft Zeon when the task is complete.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='You saved my wrappings, $N. The Protectorate will know of what you\'ve done on this day, friend.' WHERE entry=10345;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='How\'d it go out there this time? You\'re in pretty good shape... maybe even good enough for another run!' WHERE entry=10346;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='$N, are you ready for another sortie over the Abyssal Shelf?  I fear that, if we do not maintain pressure on the legion forces there and allow them to strengthen their hold, then we may suffer a large demon attack from the north.$B$BWhat say you, $C?  Do you want to take another windrider and hammer the Abyssal Shelf one more time?',offerrewardtext_loc4='The other windrider pilots speak highly of you, $N.  You\'ve scored quite a lot of kills on the Abyssal Shelf.  Keep up the good works!' WHERE entry=10347;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Interesting choice, isn\'t it? The healing properties had better be miraculous. I\'m charging a lot of money for a rather plain looking flower.' WHERE entry=10348;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh, excellent!  I\'ve been waiting to get my hands on a piece of that thing, but Tola\'thion\'s been dragging his feet.$B$BHe\'s supposed to be out here helping me to investigate what\'s going on up on Fallen Sky Ridge.  Instead he\'s just been sending poor dupes like you - no offense - up there into the slaughter mill.$B$BIf you give me the crystal maybe I can find a link between it and the colossi.' WHERE entry=10349;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, so you\'ve finally come. I am Behomat, and I will instruct you in the ways of the $C arts. Ruada told me of your trial against the ravager, and I am impressed. And I have a gift for you.$B$BWhat we have scavenged from the wreckage of the Exodar is little, and must be given to those most able. Please take a weapon suited to your fighting style and carry it with the knowledge you have earned it.$B$BAnd speaking of fighting styles, it\'s time you learned something new.' WHERE entry=10350;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Goliathon?  Pathaleon the Calculator?$B$BKAEL\'THAS!?$B$BPrince Kael\'thas has a hand in this?$B$B<The earthbinder fumes.>$B$BIt is insanity what he has done!  Dropping giant crystals from the sky and decimating the land can only be the work of a madman!$B$BI can assure you, the Cenarion Expedition will counter any further attempts by their forces to do this ever again.$B$BWe owe you a great debt, $N.' WHERE entry=10351;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='And Ya-six? Did he make it?$B$BLet\'s damn well hope so. I was unable to get reinforcements back to them... Ethereum have the entire area covered now.$B$BMy apologies, I nearly forgot about your reward.' WHERE entry=10353;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s exactly as I\'d feared, $N. The drying environment is taking a heavy toll on creatures never meant to live outside swampy environments. We\'ll have to continue to monitor the area and consult with the Cenarion Expedition to see if anything can be done.' WHERE entry=10355;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You have come far in a short time, $N. Faster than I had expected or hoped. It is time that you continued your training under the tutelage of Caedmos.$B$BI have sent word to him at the Exodar to expect you. You\'ll find him in the Anchorites\' Sanctum near the entrance of the Vault of Lights.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Caedmos in the Vault of Lights of the Exodar.' WHERE entry=10364;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Burning Legion is in cahoots with Kael? Hah! Voren\'thal is going to have a field day with this information.$B$BDo you think the thousands of pilgrims that have come from Azeroth want to be allied with the Burning Legion? I think not!' WHERE entry=10365;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The path of the Light and purity is not an easy one to walk, $N. Even I, at times, struggle with following its course.$B$BYou should seek out my master, Jol, at the Exodar. She trained me when I was beginning my journey, and I believe she will find in you a new star pupil.$B$BYou will find Jol in the Vault of Lights of the Exodar at the Vindicators\' Sanctum, a room surrounded by a vibrant glow of light.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Jol in the Vindicators\' Sanctum of the Exodar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='$N, I have been expecting you.$B$BTullas has sung your praises and I am eager to continue your training on the path of Light. When you are ready to unlock greater understanding of your abilities and power, I will guide you.' WHERE entry=10366;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I thank you, $N. My people will soon be free thanks to you.' WHERE entry=10367;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I can feel it, $N! The spirits are returning to us.' WHERE entry=10368;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It is true, $N. I was once Naladu the Keeper of Earth.$B$BIt was I who betrayed the other Dreghood elders in exchange for empty promises of power.  You can despise me now if you wish to.  What matters is that my tribe is free once again and that the spirits have returned to us.$B$BI will not be joining the rest of the tribe, but I can die in peace now.  May the spirit of earth find a new servant among my brothers.' WHERE entry=10369;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It is done then. We come here, hunt them down and slay them at the bidding of our masters. No quarter is given or expected.$B$BMakes you wonder sometimes.' WHERE entry=10380;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The bad news you bring fills my heart with sorrow. Two of our deadliest foes join forces and one of the dearest sons of Shattrath has lost his way.' WHERE entry=10381;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Well, $N, I hope you\'re prepared for the next phase of our operation. The Legion never rests - and neither shall we! Take a gryphon and fly over to Honor Point - it\'s a small post near the Legion Front. $B$BSpeak with Field Marshal Brock. He\'ll have instructions for you when you arrive. Oh, and tell that pasty-faced shield-kisser I said \'hello\'.  $B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well met, $C. I\'m glad that crusty old dwarf finally saw fit to send us some help!' WHERE entry=10382;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<You hold the data cell out so Ameer can read the plans.>$B$BNothing... Damn them! They\'re clever but not as clever as Ameer!$B$BWhat I\'m about to ask you to do is quite dangerous. I\'ll understand if you don\'t want to continue, fleshling.' WHERE entry=10384;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Protectorate\'s reason for existence is now fully realized.$B$BThe Ethereum are not here to hunt Dimensius! They are here to become void!$B$BThey are manipulating the void energy at this manaforge to bond their own energy into a creature known as a nexus-stalker.$B$BThey are undoubtedly using a proto-accelerator to complete the transformation.' WHERE entry=10385;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Hope you enjoyed your flight, friend. A messenger arrived while you were away - seems Nazgrel\'s got a new use for you. You\'d best head back to Thrallmar and check in with him. I have a feeling the Legion\'s just getting warmed up. $B',objectives_loc4='Return to Thrallmar and speak with Nazgrel.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, $N, you\'ve come just in time. Our scouts have discovered that the Legion positions on the ridge behind us are actually \'forge camps\'. It\'s there that the demons are constructing their infernal fel reavers. If we move against them quickly we can disrupt their production!' WHERE entry=10388;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Magister Bloodhawk wants you to kill 10 terrorfiends in the Pools of Aggonar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Bravo, $N. I knew you would be victorious! The Legion\'s defeat draws ever nearer!' WHERE entry=10389;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='$N, we have reason to believe that the easternmost forge camp is not yet complete. The Legion\'s gan\'arg servants are working \'round the clock to get the facility up and running. We can\'t allow that to happen. $B$BHead east to Forge Camp: Mageddon and slay 10 gan\'arg. Bring me the head of their master - Razorsaw - and the Legion\'s fel reaver production will grind to a halt!   $B$B',objectives_loc4='Nazgrel in Thrallmar wants you to attack Forge Camp: Mageddon and kill 10 gan\'arg servants and return with the head of Razorsaw.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $C, That\'s one less forge camp we\'ll need to worry about. It\'ll take the Legion a while to get that facility back up and running. You\'ve just bought us the one thing we\'d run out of' WHERE entry=10390;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='There is a second production facility, Forge Camp: Rage, that lies to the immediate northeast of Thrallmar. The demons have positioned a number of their fel cannons along the ridge - and they\'re aimed straight at us! You must enter the camp and destroy these fel cannons. $B$B$N, you must be sure to detonate them all - or nothing will stop the Legion from raining fiery hell down upon our heads!  $B',offerrewardtext_loc4='I knew you had spirit, $N, but you\'ve outdone yourself this time! We heard those wretched cannons exploding from here! That should teach the Legion not to underestimate the Sons of Durotar!' WHERE entry=10391;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Praise the ancients, you\'ve done it, $N! The Legion has suffered a terrible defeat - and Thrallmar is safe once again. Ah, if I had but a hundred warriors with your heart and cunning, this broken land would be tamed already! I salute you. $B$B<Nazgrel salutes you crisply>' WHERE entry=10392;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The text on the note is written in some dark, indecipherable scrawl. The more you stare at them, the more the symbols seem to twist and burn before your eyes. There is only one in Thrallmar that can transcribe such vile script - the blood elf Magister Bloodhawk. $B$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='You were right to bring this to my attention. This could be a production order for additional fel reavers - or new attack plans! This will take some time to decipher. Leave me. I will summon you when I know more. $B$B<Magister Bloodhawk nods to you as you turn to leave> $B$BYou are a sharp one, $N. I shall be watching your progress with interest.' WHERE entry=10393;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Pay close attention, $N. We\'ve been surveying the Legion camps that lie along the ridge ahead. We have reason to believe that these so-called \'Forge Camps\' are where the demons are constructing those blasted Fel Reavers. $B$BYou can see the closest target, Forge Camp: Mageddon, to the west. Our intelligence suggests that it\'s still under construction. If you can slay the Gan\'arg Servants and their master - Razorsaw - we can bring the Legion\'s Fel Reaver production to a grinding halt!   $B$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, I must say, I am impressed, $N. I didn\'t think you had the mettle for this mission. Well done. Well done, indeed.' WHERE entry=10394;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The text on the note is written in some dark, indecipherable scrawl. The more you stare at them, the more the symbols seem to twist and burn before your eyes. There is only one at Honor Hold who can decipher such archaic script - the draenei mystic, Kryv. $B$BTake the Burning Legion Missive to Warp-Scryer Kryv who resides within the War-Room at Honor Hold.$B',objectives_loc4='Take the Missive to Warp-Scryer Kryv in the main keep of Honor Hold.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It is fortuitous that you intercepted this missive when you did, $N. Though it will take me some time to decipher, I can already sense the hatred and urgency woven into this scroll. I fear the Legion\'s true motives in this land will soon be made evident...$B$BGive me a moment to decipher this script.$B$B<Warp-Scryer Kryv begins to read the demonic missive>' WHERE entry=10395;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I have to hand it to you, $N, you\'re a fighter born! Those Horde yokels may never know how close they came to the end. It takes real character to step in harm\'s way on behalf of your enemies. That\'s the kind of honor and commitment that holds the Alliance together!$B$B<Field Marshal Brock salutes you crisply>' WHERE entry=10396;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Well, we\'ve located the Legion\'s final base on the ridge - Invasion Point: Annihilator. It lies northwest of Forge Camp: Rage - and it houses a warp-portal through which the Legion has been drawing its reinforcements! $B$BYou\'ve got to close that portal to prevent any more demons from coming through. The Point\'s overlord, Warbringer Arix\'Amal, holds the portal\'s activation key. Take it from him and shut that blasted gateway down!  $B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Great job! That should drastically cut down on the number of demons trying to creep up our backsides. I can\'t thank you enough for your help out here, $N.' WHERE entry=10397;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='PH: Go to Honor Hold.',objectives_loc4='PH: Go to Honor Hold.' WHERE entry=10398;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='It is just as I feared. Arix\'Amal - the demon you killed earlier, was working for a secret Legionlord - Arazzius the Cruel. It appears this new villain has amassed a force of hellish terrorfiends near the Pools of Aggonar. $B$BYou must journey there and slay the terrorfiends before they strike against us. But be wary, friend - the Pools of Aggonar lie within a tortured, poisonous valley. You can find the cursed pools to the northwest of here, beyond Hellfire Citadel. $B$BLight be with you, $N.  $B',offerrewardtext_loc4='I foresaw this great victory, $N. The blessed naaru smile upon you this day.' WHERE entry=10399;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The honorable Warp-Scryer has told me of your perils, $N - and of the new foe you\'ve discovered. If Kryv is to be believed, this \'Arazzius the Cruel\' is as powerful and evil as any foe the Sons of Lothar have ever faced. $B$BWill you stand for us now, $N? Will you face this Legionlord and deliver the Light\'s justice upon him? If so, you will find him at the Pools of Aggonar. If not, his evil will most certainly find you. $B',objectives_loc4='Slay Arazzius the Cruel in the Pools of Aggonar and return to Force Commander Danath Trollbane in the keep of Honor Hold.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Light be praised, I knew you\'d do it! Arazzius and his minions are no more! Soon, we\'ll have the Legion running for home and this battered world will be safe once more. Then, when justice has been met, we can return home as well.$B$BThanks you, $N - the Alliance and the Sons of Lothar honor you this day!' WHERE entry=10400;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve come to help my tribe, $R? How unusual. There aren\'t many that care about the fate of the Broken in this land.' WHERE entry=10403;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent! Now to calibrate the device.' WHERE entry=10405;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I\'m sending one of my demolitionists out to place the disruption device. Just make sure no harm comes to him as he\'s placing the disruptor.$B$BKeep him protected! He will not fight back if enemies attack him as he is only a holographic image but the image can be destroyed!$B$BReturn to me once the job is done.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Thanks to you, their plans are in ruin! Now only one thing remains... Salhadaar.' WHERE entry=10406;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Your dedication to our cause is exemplary, $N. With Socrethar\'s teleportation stone in our possession only one thing remains to be done.' WHERE entry=10407;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It has been a thousand years, maybe more, since Salhadaar began his crusade to exterminate all that would stand in his way. I can hardly believe that this is the last we\'ll see of him... You have done all of us a great service, $N, and for that you will be rewarded.' WHERE entry=10408;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It is done, $N. Socrethar has been destroyed.$B$BI and the others will recover from our wounds, $N. The wrath of Socrethar\'s magic was far too much for young Kaylaan, however. Not even my strongest prayer could raise him.$B$BIt is an unbearable pity that one so young would fall in battle. However, in the end his will was strong enough to recover from the Legion\'s corruption and we may find solace in that.' WHERE entry=10409;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Socrethar... I remember that name.  He was once a renowned warrior of the Light and pride was his only flaw.' WHERE entry=10410;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Researcher Navuud at the Protectorate Watch Post in Netherstorm has asked that you destroy 30 Void Waste Globules and 30 Seeping Sludge Globules.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='I hope it\'s not too late. Did you notice any abnormally large slimes at or near the area where the void wastes drain into?' WHERE entry=10411;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. You might prove to be a useful ally after all.' WHERE entry=10412;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='WHAT!? You faced off against a void horror? And lived?! Incredible!$B$BThis sample is worth its weight in gold. A find like this deserves a reward.' WHERE entry=10413;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='As promised, $N. The entirety of the book\'s raw power, condensed into a single rune.' WHERE entry=10416;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This is worrisome. The damage is much more severe than I believed. I can send to the Stormspire for some tools to begin repairs, but that\'s useless unless we\'ve isolated what\'s damaging the equipment in the first place.' WHERE entry=10417;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The area\'s looking clearer already. The domes are quite useful, but the major drawback is the rampant growth they encourage in some places, accelerating the growth and proliferation of native species.' WHERE entry=10418;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The power contained in this tome is tremendous. Yet it is easily condensed into a single rune by one with a clear mind.' WHERE entry=10419;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Watch as foul materials disintegrate. Watch as metal turns to dust.$B$BThe Light cleanses all and only the purest residue remains.' WHERE entry=10420;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Flesh Handler Viridius at the Protectorate Watch Post in Netherstorm has asked that you find and free Captain Tyralius.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $N. Tyralius suffered massive injuries but we think he\'s going to make it.$B$BHe mentioned fields of prisons, much like the one you rescued him from. Prisons full of creatures from all across the universe!$B$BWe\'ll be in touch should a need arise to crack those open. The Consortium has already expressed some interest in sending some teams out and is working on some technology to break through the Ethereum\'s locks.' WHERE entry=10422;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Speak with Ghabar at the Stormspire.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<You introduce yourself and report the results of Mehrdad\'s diagnostics at EcoDome Midrealm.>$B$BMehrdad is little more than a technician, but he possesses a keen eye for detail. If his observations are correct, then we\'ll need to take diagnostics at the rest of our dome generators as soon as possible.' WHERE entry=10423;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These results match Mehrdad\'s exactly, but why? The only possible explanation I can think of is that some of the dome generation equipment has failed or gone missing. That would cause the domes to weaken significantly and fall out of balance as the diagnostics indicate.' WHERE entry=10424;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Thank K\'aresh! He would have torn me apart!$B$BI\'m a Protectorate soldier, fleshling. My platoon was sent on a recon mission about 10 days ago. As we were moving across the upper ledges of this island, a group of Ethereum jumped us. At least I think it was Ethereum. They had the same energy color but their wrappings looked void.$B$BOnly Tyralius was spared. I think they put him in a prison cell.$B$BI\'ve got to get back to the Protectorate Watch Post! Can you escort me back?$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Commander Ameer appears pleased.>$B$BWell done, fleshling! This soldier might be the key to taking down the Ethereum\'s entire operation.' WHERE entry=10425;
UPDATE locales_quest SET EndText_loc4='Captured Protectorate Vanguard Escorted' WHERE entry=10425;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh my! Focusing the dome\'s energy seems to continue accelerating growth to the point where it breeds extreme aggression. If we do get the ability to use this technology, we have to be sure to calibrate it correctly.' WHERE entry=10426;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work. I\'ll keep a close eye on the ones you tagged and see if they mature as quickly as the other lifeforms in the dome.$B$BWith the proper control, we could use this technology to regrow the ruined areas of Outland and Azeroth.' WHERE entry=10427;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='My family... What have I done... What could I have done?$B$BWhy must I be punished so?' WHERE entry=10428;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Even for a creature of that size, this heart is far too large. It struggled to keep up with the creature\'s gigantic body. I have little doubt it would\'ve died before reaching half its normal lifespan.$B$BEven with such risks, I\'m determined to convince the Consortium to share their technology. There\'s too much promise here to give up now.' WHERE entry=10429;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring the Repair Apparatus to Tashar at Eco-Dome Farfield.',offerrewardtext_loc4='This looks a little peculiar. Ghabar definitely didn\'t have Netherstorm in mind when he designed it.$B$BDon\'t look so surprised, $N. Netherstorm is tame compared to some of the environments I\'ve worked in. Nevertheless, a failing dome is always a concern.' WHERE entry=10430;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re all the help Orelis is sending? He must think very highly of you.$B$BLet\'s get this over with.' WHERE entry=10431;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This is big, $N. Very big!$B$BVoren\'thal is going to want to hear about this as soon as possible.' WHERE entry=10432;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These are magnificent, utterly magnificent! I\'ll pay you top coin for these! How much to retain your services?' WHERE entry=10433;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Speak with Audi the Needle at the Stormspire.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<You introduce yourself and tell Audi that Shauly sent you.>$B$BAh, yes, we\'ve been expecting someone to help us, err move some, uh, merchandise.' WHERE entry=10434;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work! The most difficult part of the project is done. Now, all we need is a way to get these back to Area 52 and attract the interest of the Cenarion Expedition as well. There should be enough here for our own needs and to earn a little profit on the side.' WHERE entry=10435;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Before we can begin the test, we have to make certain the area is clear of anything that might interfere. In our case, that means these overgrown lizards.$B$B<Tashar gestures toward the scythetooth raptors.>$B$BThere\'s no telling what might happen if one those decides to take a nice bite out of the generator while it\'s charging. I\'ve seen a lot of strange things in all my years as a technician, including more than a few abominations that had their beginnings as humble animals.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done. It looks like everything is in order. We\'re ready to begin.' WHERE entry=10436;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent. With these fragments, we can calibrate a bomb that will destroy the void conduit atop Ultris. With the void conduit destroyed, Dimensius\'s connection with the void will be severed and he will be left defenseless!' WHERE entry=10437;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Here it is, $N. Take this phase disruptor and mount up! The Protecotrate nether drake will fly you close enough to Ultris so that you can drop the disruptor on top of the void conduit.$B$BDrop as many disruptor charges as possible to ensure complete annihilation!$B$BWhen you are ready, speak with the nether drake and he\'ll take you up.$B$BIf you miss the mark you will have to get more bombs from me before you can go up again.',objectives_loc4='Professor Dabiri at the Protectorate Watch Post in Netherstorm wants you to use your Phase Disruptor when you get in range of the Void Conduit that rests atop Ultris. Drop as many charges of the Phase Disruptor as you can to ensure total annihilation. The Phase Disruptor charges will automatically home in on the Void Conduit so long as you are close enough to use it.$B$BReturn to Professor Dabiri should you succeed!$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='The time to strike has come! With the tear gone, Dimensius is vulnerable to physical and magical attacks!' WHERE entry=10438;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='For a thousand years, all we have known is conflict. We have defended our people from the attacks of both void creature and ethereal alike.$B$BNow, one of our most hated enemies lies dead - finally.$B$BI give you the thanks of a hundred million ethereals, fleshling.' WHERE entry=10439;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Return to the Stormspire and speak with Ghabar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'ll have my techs get to work on those repairs right away.$B$BTashar\'s suspicion of sabotage worries me, though. I can\'t think of anyone who would be bold enough to steal our technology. Not anyone who knows what we\'re capable of, anyway. It may be time to lock down the Stormspire.' WHERE entry=10440;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='<Audi lowers her voice again.>$B$BNow that we have the goods, I\'ll be sending most of the parts on to Area 52. There\'s enough here for more than one generator, presenting us with a perfect business opportunity.$B$BI\'ve seen the Cenarion Expdedition\'s representative trying to negotiate. I want you to let her know that we can provide what she seeks at a very reasonable price. There\'s no reason for her to continue dealing with those two-timing ethereals.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Aurine Moonblaze at the bottom of the Stormspire in Netherstorm.' WHERE entry=10441;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='$C, there\'s some tauren by the name of Thiah Redmane that keeps pestering us for assistance.  She\'s with the Cenarion Expedition, and they\'ve setup a little post just to the west on the south side of the the road leading to Zangarmarsh.$B$BIf you hit Thornfang Hill, you\'ve gone too far.$B$BDo you think you might head over there and see what she needs?  I don\'t want to have to bother Ranger Captain Venn\'ren with such trivialities.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh, goodness, you must be the help I requested weeks ago from Falcon Watch.$B$BWell, you\'re here now and there\'s a lot to be done.  I have just the thing to start you out.' WHERE entry=10442;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh, goodness, you must be the help that I requested from the Temple of Telhamat.$B$BI\'m glad that you\'re here; there\'s a lot to be done, and I have just the thing to start you out.' WHERE entry=10443;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Bomb parts. So my suspicions were true. That\'s not something that I wanted to be right about.$B$BOkay, you and I have some grim business ahead of us then.' WHERE entry=10444;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'ve asked the impossible of you, yet I expect you to succeed.  Much depends on it.' WHERE entry=10445;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='YOU DID IT! YOU SAVED US! YOU SAVED THE ALLERIAN STRONGHOLD!!$B$BWith their forces decimated, their leader dead and the mana bomb destroyed, we can all breathe much easier now.$B$B$N, I\'ve never seen such selflessness... such heroism! Please, accept this on behalf of all of us.' WHERE entry=10446;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='They\'re building a second mana bomb in the courtyard.  My intel suggests that the final code for the bomb is being held by Sharth Voldoun, the overseer of the project at Firewing Point.$B$B$N, you have to go back in there and retrieve the final code from him.  He keeps himself to the top of the highest spire.$B$BTake the final code to the mana bomb that they\'re working on in the central courtyard and set it off.$B$BOnly then will we be certain that Stonebreaker Hold is safe.',objectives_loc4='Sergeant Chawni wants you to use the Final Code Sheet to set off the Mana Bomb.  Then report back to Tooki at Stonebreaker Hold in Terokkar Forest.',offerrewardtext_loc4='YOU DID IT! YOU SAVED US! YOU SAVED STONEBREAKER HOLD!!$B$BWith their forces decimated, their leader dead and the mana bomb destroyed, we can all breathe much easier now.$B$B$N, I\'ve never seen such selflessness... such heroism! Please, accept this on behalf of all of us.' WHERE entry=10447;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Apethecary Zelana has been studying the beasts of Hellfire Peninsula in the field.  She wants a sample of the blood you gathered; with luck, she might discover what turned those Bonechewer bastards\' skins red!$B$BZelana is at Reaver\'s Fall, southeast of Thrallmar.  Follow the road east and when you see a destroyed, green-glowing hunk of metal, you\'re there.  She has a camp set up behind the wyverns.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, yes.  The blood of the Bonechewer clan.  I am very curious about these orcs... they are still the depraved fiends of the past, but their strength and power is greater than what I had heard...$B$BWell, let us begin, shall we?' WHERE entry=10449;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Bonechewers!  They should all die!  The sight of their red skin and depravity makes my blood boil!$B$BI have a mission for you, $N.  Kill bonechewer orcs and collect their vile blood.  There is an apothecary who needs the blood for her tests, so we can discover how these orcs fell to the demon taint, a taint from which we so recently freed ourselves.$B$BBonechewers scavenge near the ruined battlements along the Path of Glory, to the south.  Return to me when your mission is complete.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Hah!  So you did meet the bonechewers, our depraved cousins.  Well done, $N.  My only regret is that more of them could not lay down their lives and spill their blood, to cool my outrage!' WHERE entry=10450;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Thank the Earthmother! I parted ways with the others several days ago. I was intent on discovering the source of the disturbance that the spirits of water were feeling. My search led me to Coilskar where I discovered that the naga were befouling the water supply of Shadowmoon Valley.$B$BUnfortunately, I was discovered and taken prisoner. There\'s no telling what ghastly things they had in store for me.$B$BWe must leave this place! Help me escape and then seek out Torlok at the Altar of Damnation.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Praise the Earthmother. I am certain that Wilda will find her way home. Please accept this as a token of our appreciation.' WHERE entry=10451;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Rina Moonspring wishes you to slay 12 Grovestalker Lynxes with all due haste and then return to her at Sylvanaar in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='That was fast. Are you sure that you dealt with as many as was necessary?$B$BExcellent, there\'s something else that you can help us with if you are willing?' WHERE entry=10455;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Rina Moonspring has asked you to bring her 4 Thunderlord Dire Wolf Tails.  After doing so, return to her at Sylvanaar in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Good. I\'ll see if I can fashion something useful from these tails.$B$BNo doubt that the Horde will find a way to replenish the numbers of their wolf pack, but for now we can breathe a little easier.$B$B$N, if you are willing there\'s something else that I would ask of you in defense of Sylvanaar and the Living Grove.' WHERE entry=10456;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Use Rina\'s Bough on 5 of the Grove Seedlings to summon forth defenses for the Living Grove.  Then return to Rina Moonspring at Sylvanaar in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Now that you have strengthened the grove\'s defenses, I feel much safer.$B$BYou\'ve earned our thanks and appreciation, $N.$B$BOf course, it just occurred to me that there\'s something else that we need to take care of!' WHERE entry=10457;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='When all of the elemental souls of this region have been placed inside the totem, we will commune with them and find out if anything can be done for Shadowmoon Valley.' WHERE entry=10458;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve proved your worth, $R. Up to a certain point, at least.$B$BThe favor of Nozdormu\'s prime mate is not obtained easily.' WHERE entry=10464;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Restorer\'s Vow',offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve proved your worth, $R. Up to a certain point, at least.$B$BThe favor of Nozdormu\'s prime mate is not obtained easily.' WHERE entry=10465;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve proved your worth, $R. Up to a certain point, at least.$B$BThe favor of Nozdormu\'s prime mate is not obtained easily.' WHERE entry=10466;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Defender\'s Vow',offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve proved your worth. $R. Up to a certain point. at least.$B$BThe favor of Nozdormu\'s prime mate is not obtained quickly.' WHERE entry=10467;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are a worthy ally indeed. As you grow in power so does the band of eternity!' WHERE entry=10468;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Restorer\'s Oath',offerrewardtext_loc4='You are a worthy ally indeed. As you grow in power so does the band of eternity!' WHERE entry=10469;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are a worthy ally indeed. As you grow in power so does the band of eternity!' WHERE entry=10470;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are a worthy ally indeed. As you grow in power so does the band of eternity!' WHERE entry=10471;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are one with time, $N. You are one with us.$B$BBehold! Power beyond mortal understanding is unleashed from even that small remnant of the Well of Eternity.$B$BAccept this gift so that all may know of your covenant with the Scale of the Sands.... so that all may know of your covenant with time itself!' WHERE entry=10472;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Restorer\'s Covenant',offerrewardtext_loc4='You are one with time, $N. You are one with us.$B$BBehold! Power beyond mortal understanding is unleashed from even that small remnant of the Well of Eternity.$B$BAccept this gift so that all may know of your covenant with the Scale of the Sands.... so that all may know of your covenant with time itself!' WHERE entry=10473;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are one with time, $N. You are one with us.$B$BBehold! Power beyond mortal understanding is unleashed from even that small remnant of the Well of Eternity.$B$BAccept this gift so that all may know of your covenant with the Scale of the Sands.... so that all may know of your covenant with time itself!' WHERE entry=10474;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are one with time, $N. You are one with us.$B$BBehold! Power beyond mortal understanding is unleashed from even that small remnant of the Well of Eternity.$B$BAccept this gift so that all may know of your covenant with the Scale of the Sands.... so that all may know of your covenant with time itself!' WHERE entry=10475;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re starting to prove your worth as an ally and combatant. Keep up the good work.' WHERE entry=10476;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You continue to prove your worth to us, $N. May your strength never fail you.' WHERE entry=10477;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You continue to prove your strength and honor, $N.' WHERE entry=10478;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are a strong ally indeed, $N.  Going head to head against the ogres of Outland is not something that just anyone can do.' WHERE entry=10479;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The Illidari naga of the region have taken control of the only clean water supply that exists in Shadowmoon Valley.$B$BDirectly north of here you will find the lair of the naga: Coilskar. Around Coilskar are pockets of agitated water that howl to the land in anguish. It is at those pockets that the enraged spirits of water now wander.$B$BTravel to Coilskar and use the totem of spirits to capture watery souls. You will find the largest concentration of these spirits near Coilskar Cistern.$B',objectives_loc4='Earthmender Torlok at the Altar of Damnation in Shadowmoon Valley wants you to use the Totem of Spirits to capture 5 Watery Souls.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Only air remains, $N.' WHERE entry=10480;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Allow me to reward you for undertaking such an arduous task, hero.$B$BNow, we must get to work! Please stand back so that I may place the totem and unleash the souls.' WHERE entry=10481;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Very good. I\'m sure their loss will be felt in Hellfire Citadel. Although that dark bastion looms over us and seems nigh insurmountable, it is only with bold moves like you have made that we will find victory over the fel orcs!' WHERE entry=10482;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, you recovered an insignia from the Bleeding Hollow orcs?  Good -- it is outrageous that they use our own symbols against us, and mock our comrades who\'ve fallen to those red-skinned beasts!' WHERE entry=10483;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $N.  My heart is saddened to see these talismans -- they underline the great losses we of Honor Hold have suffered against the fel orcs.  But I am heartened to see you successful against them.  If we can kill enough, perhaps we might emerge from this war victorious.' WHERE entry=10484;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done it!  Morkh is slain!  Now, we have a fighting chance against the fel orc beasts!$B$BThank you, $N.  Your aid to the war effort here is beyond measure.' WHERE entry=10485;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The Thunderlord were once a proud orc clan before they were transformed into fel orcs through the blood of Mannoroth.$B$BRecently we recovered this orc stronghold from the ogres that infest the ravine below.  They had moved in when the Thunderlord clan abandoned it.$B$BWe will keep this place and I will have your help doing so.$B$BIn the Jagged Ridge to the south and the west, there are bloodletters that have become like a plague upon us.  They eat and breed incessantly.$B$BKill them and then return to me.',objectives_loc4='Gor\'drek has asked you to slay 12 Bladewing Bloodletters.  Return to him at Thunderlord Stronghold in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains once you have accomplished that.',offerrewardtext_loc4='That didn\'t take as long as I thought it would. Are you sure that you dealt with as many as was necessary?$B$BVery well, there\'s something else that I want you to help us with. Something far more important.' WHERE entry=10486;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='With the magical dust you recovered, I have fashioned a magic ointment that will aid in our own defenses.$B$BOur dire wolves are the perfect combination of mount, sentry and friend, but the Alliance scum have been poaching them in the Jagged Ridge.$B$B$N, I want you to take this ointment and apply it to our dire wolf friends.  The Alliance will get a rude surprise the next time that they send one of their hunting parties.$B$BBe aware though that some of the wolves may not like this, and will turn on you.',objectives_loc4='Use Gor\'drek\'s Ointment on 5 of the Thunderlord Dire Wolves to strengthen them and the defense of the Jagged Ridge.  Then return to Gor\'drek at Thunderlord Stronghold in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Now that you have strengthened the wolves, and the Jagged Ridge\'s defenses, perhaps we can refocus our attentions on more deadly matters, such as the ogres?$B$BYou have done a good job in aiding us here. We could use the help of someone capable, such as yourself, should you decide to stay.$B$BWhatever you do, you have earned my respect and appreciation.' WHERE entry=10488;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='WANTED!$B$BStronglimb Deeproot, ancient of war and chief defender of the Living Grove south of Sylvanaar.$B$BFind him by heading west across the bridge that traverses the Bloodmaul Ravine.$B$BReturn his hewn trunk to Tor\'chunk Twoclaws inside the Thunderlord Stronghold inn.',objectives_loc4='Acquire Stronglimb Deeproot\'s Trunk and deliver it to Tor\'chunk Twoclaws at Thunderlord Stronghold in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Stronglimb Deeproot\'s Trunk! Did you chop him down by yourself?$B$BI bet you did. You know, Rexxar and I are looking for a young, strong $C, such as yourself, to help out around here, especially with the problems we continually have with the ogres. Make sure that you follow-up with me on that possibility.$B$BWell that trunk\'s definitely proof, which means you\'re here to collect the bounty and not to listen to me talk. Go ahead, take your pick.' WHERE entry=10489;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I\'m sensing that it\'s been a while since last you were tested.  This is because Farseer Nobundo has been asking for you.$B$BYou must have grown greatly in wisdom because you are being called to learn the mysteries of the element of water.$B$BI trust that you remember how to take the boat from Auberdine in Darkshore on Kalimdor back to the Exodar?  And that you remember where to find the farseer at the Crystal Hall inside the Exodar, yes?',objectives_loc4='Speak with Farseer Nobundo at the Crystal Hall inside the Exodar on Azuremyst Isle.',offerrewardtext_loc4='We meet again. I have been watching your progress from afar, $C, and I am pleased.$B$BThe time has come for you to commune with the element of water, to learn its mysteries and give yourself over to the water so that you might in turn learn to master it.' WHERE entry=10490;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='$N, once again Farseer Nobundo has been asking for you.  It must be time for you to learn the secrets of air, the last of the elements!$B$BI want you to know that I\'m very proud of all that you have accomplished thus far.  I know that you have great things ahead of you.$B$BTake the boat from Auberdine in Darkshore on Kalimdor.  Cross the Veiled Sea and seek out the farseer inside the Crystal Hall of the Exodar on Azuremyst Isle.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Farseer Nobundo at the Crystal Hall inside the Exodar on Azuremyst Isle.',offerrewardtext_loc4='And finally we come to it, the last of the four great elements: air. Do you think yourself wise enough to continue, $N?' WHERE entry=10491;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Acquire 15 Winterspring Blood Samples and 20 gold and bring them along with a set of Bindings of Elements to Deliana in Ironforge.' WHERE entry=10492;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Acquire 15 Silithus Venom Samples and 20 gold and bring them along with a set of Lightforge Bracers to Mokvar in Orgrimmar.' WHERE entry=10493;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring a Cord of Elements and a set of Gauntlets of Elements to Deliana in Ironforge.' WHERE entry=10494;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring a Lightforge Belt and a set of Lightforge Gauntlets to Mokvar in Orgrimmar.' WHERE entry=10495;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Return to Deliana in Ironforge with a set of Boots of Elements, a Kilt of Elements and Pauldrons of Elements.' WHERE entry=10496;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Return to Mokvar in Orgimmar with a set of Lightforge Boots, Lightforge Legplates and Lightforge Spaulders.$B' WHERE entry=10497;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Give Deliana your Coif of Elements and Vest of Elements.' WHERE entry=10498;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Give Mokvar your Lightforge Helm and Lightforge Breastplate.' WHERE entry=10499;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Commander Skyshadow has tasked you with the destruction of any 30 Bloodmaul Ogres at Bloodmaul Outpost.  Return to him at Sylvanaar in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains once your gruesome task is completed.',offerrewardtext_loc4='This is a good first step toward securing Sylvanaar and the grove.$B$BWith their ogres not so numerous, the Bloodmaul will think twice about attacking us here.$B$BNow, if only they were the only clan of ogres that we have to worry about.' WHERE entry=10502;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Tor\'chunk Twoclaws has tasked you with the destruction of any 30 Bladespire Ogres and 10 Bladespire Raptors at Bladespire Hold and the Bladespire Grounds.  Return to him at Thunderlord Stronghold in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains once your task is completed.',offerrewardtext_loc4='This is a good first step toward securing our position here against the ogres.$B$BWith their numbers decimated, the Bladespire will think twice about attempting to retake Thunderlord Stronghold.$B$BNow, if they were the only clan of ogres that we have to worry about.' WHERE entry=10503;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='You have been asked by Commander Skyshadow to kill any 30 Bladespire Ogres in Bladespire Hold and the Bladespire Grounds.  Return to him at Sylvanaar in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains once you have done so.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Your actions against both the Bloodmaul and the Bladespire ogre clans have gone a long way to securing Sylvanaar\'s future. While we do not seek to expand past this patch of land, which we initially found empty, we will also not suffer those that would destroy us.$B$BAs you have done us good service, I would reward that service with the appreciation of the Alliance.' WHERE entry=10504;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='You have been asked by Tor\'chunk Twoclaws to kill any 30 Bloodmaul Ogres at Bloodmaul Outpost.  Return to him at Thunderlord Stronghold in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains once you have done so.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Your actions against both the Bladespire and the Bloodmaul ogre clans have gone a long way to securing Thunderlord Stronghold\'s future. We will not suffer those that would get in the way of our destiny here.$B$BAs you have done good work in destroying these ogres, I intend to reward you with the appreciation of the Horde.' WHERE entry=10505;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Rina Moonspring wants you to take her Diminution Powder and apply it to 5 of the Bloodmaul Dire Wolves, which can be found at Bloodmaul Outpost and in Bloodmaul Ravine.  After doing so, return to her at Sylvanaar in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m glad to hear that it worked. The fewer the number of Nature\'s creatures that have to die, the better.$B$BWith all that you\'ve done for us already, I must say that I\'m beginning to grow very fond of your company.$B$BTake care, $N.' WHERE entry=10506;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are an individual of formidable power, $N. The Scryers are fortunate to count you as an ally.$B$BAs word of Kael\'s new allegiance spreads, more people will see things our way. The fact that we can claim such a decisive victory against Kael\'thas\' new overlords puts us in a most favorable situation.$B$BI will not forget your deeds.' WHERE entry=10507;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You do not cease to amaze me, $N!  Good thing you\'re on our side.' WHERE entry=10508;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have no idea what this will mean for the Scryers, $N. You will have to excuse me while I catch my breath and assess the situation.' WHERE entry=10509;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bronwyn Stouthammer has asked you to collect 5 Draenethyst Mine Crystals and then return to her at Sylvanaar in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ooh, by the looks of those, they\'re fine specimens.  I can\'t wait to get my examination tools unpacked and have a real look at them!$B$BThank you!' WHERE entry=10510;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Borgrim Stouthammer wants you to procure 11 Bloodmaul Brutebane Brew for him.  Once you\'ve done that, return it to him at Sylvanaar in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='What is that smell?  Oh no, don\'t tell me that\'s the ogre brew?!$B$BI\'m almost afraid to try this stuff out.  Oh well, what the hell?  Bottoms up!' WHERE entry=10511;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Take the Bloodmaul Brutebane Keg and use it in an attempt to get 5 Bladespire Ogres drunk.  If you\'re successful, return to Borgrim at Sylvanaar in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, hahaha! That\'s what I thought. I guess ogre\'s will drink anything.$B$BStupid, the lot of \'em!$B$BWell, I must say even though I didn\'t get my brew, you have given me a great start to my vacation.$B$BTell you what... we have all sorts of stuff here we don\'t really need. Can I offer you something?' WHERE entry=10512;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Seek out Oronok Torn-heart on the Shattered Shelf - north of Coilskar Cistern.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Words of damnation? Never heard of \'em. Take my advice: Let the dead rest.$B$BBut since you\'ve already come all this way, I could use some help with a few other matters. What do you say?' WHERE entry=10513;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You say there were a lot more of those flayers than you expected? Looks like it\'s time to take out the trash.' WHERE entry=10514;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'ll teach those damned, filthy animals not to kill my boars! Well done, $N!' WHERE entry=10515;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Ravenous Flayer Egg Destroyed' WHERE entry=10515;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Retrieve Vindicator Vuuleen\'s Blade and Vindicator Vuuleen\'s Shield.  Then return them to Vindicator Vuuleen at Bladespire Hold in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='And now I owe you a great debt, for you have helped me to restore my honor.  But our work here is not yet over.' WHERE entry=10516;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Vindicator Vuuleen has asked you to kill Gorr\'Dim, leader of the Bladespire Hold ogres.  Once you have done so, return to her at Bladespire Hold in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Very well. You\'re a very resourceful $C, that\'s for certain.$B$BI wonder then if there\'s one more thing that you can do for myself and Sylvanaar?' WHERE entry=10517;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Use the Bladespire Banner atop the Northmaul Tower to lure Gurn Grubnosh.  Deliver the banner and the Helm of Gurn Grubnosh to Commander Skyshadow at Sylvanaar in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Gurn Grubnosh\'s helm and a Bladespire banner?$B$BQuite clever of you and the vindicator to come up with that plan.$B$BBy keeping the attention of the Bloodmaul clan on Bladespire Hold, you\'ve relieved the pressure that they were beginning to assert upon us here.$B$BPlease, $N, accept a humble gift from Sylvanaar.' WHERE entry=10518;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='<Oronok adjusts his posture and stands to his full height.>$B$BI had to be sure, $N. And to be sure, I had to test you. Please excuse the little masquerade. I am as much a farmer as you are $G female:male;. Which is to say, not at all.$B$BIf you are to recover the Cipher of Damnation, you will need to listen to what I have to tell you. When you are ready, let me know and I will tell you the story.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Do you understand what must be done? Find the sons of Oronok. Find my boys...' WHERE entry=10519;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Grom\'tor grunts.>$B$BIt\'s good you came. This maggot just spilled its guts. We\'ve got them now!' WHERE entry=10521;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This must be taken back to father at once.' WHERE entry=10522;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='When the Cipher of Damnation is reformed, we shall end this curse!' WHERE entry=10523;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Retrieve the Thunderlord Clan Drum, Thunderlord Clan Arrow and the Thunderlord Clan Tablet.  Return them, along with the Thunderlord Clan Artifact, to Rokgah Bloodgrip at Thunderlord Stronghold in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I do not believe my eyes! If this is some sort of trick, I will flay the flesh from your bones, $C!$B$BQuickly, let me examine these priceless artifacts before you break them with your clumsy hands.' WHERE entry=10524;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='If the vision that I granted you is true, then you must travel down into the ravine and to the south end of Bloodmaul Ravine.  There you will find the Draenethyst Mine.$B$BJourney to the back of the mine, and retrieve the Thunderspike.  Ignore everything else!  I have no interest in the crystals of the mine, nor the ogres therein.$B$BAs soon as you have the spear return it to me here!$B$BAnd, $N, be very careful with it... I would hate to think what would happen to you should you break it.',objectives_loc4='Rokgah Bloodgrip has tasked you with the retrieval of the Thunderspike.  Return it to her at Thunderlord Stronghold in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Now I am impressed! Do you have any idea how many others died attempting to retrieve all of these relics?$B$BWe are fortunate to have you working with us here, $N. Even if you are a bit slow.$B$BYou must allow me to reward your dedication to our cause. Choose, but choose wisely. When you are done, I will hand over the artifacts to appease the ghosts of Thunderlord Stronghold.' WHERE entry=10526;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ar\'tor\'s body lies limp, suspended in mid-air. You have no idea how long he has been dead but your heart aches for Oronok.$B$BPerhaps you should try and get him down and take his corpse back to his father.' WHERE entry=10527;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You slide the crystalline key into the slots at the base of each of the demonic crystals.' WHERE entry=10528;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Lieutenant Dawnrunner at Farstrider Retreat has requested an audience with all able hunters.  It would greatly benefit you to seek her out, $N.  She is a beacon of wisdom for those of our calling.$B$BFarstrider Retreat lies south of Silvermoon City.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Lieutenant Dawnrunner at Farstrider Retreat.',offerrewardtext_loc4='$N, it is good you have come. Our list of allies grows thin, and even those who share our cause are not completely trusted. It is because of this that we, the rangers, turn to nature for aid.$B$BIn the allies of the forest we find a deep bond that does not know deceit.' WHERE entry=10529;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Lieutenant Dawnrunner at Farstrider Retreat has requested an audience with all able hunters.  It would greatly benefit you to seek her out, $N.  She is a beacon of wisdom for those of our calling.$B$BFarstrider Retreat lies south of Silvermoon City.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Lieutenant Dawnrunner at Farstrider Retreat.',offerrewardtext_loc4='$N, it is good you have come. Our list of allies grows thin, and even those who share our cause are not completely trusted. It is because of this that we, the rangers, turn to nature for aid.$B$BIn the allies of the forest we find a deep bond that does not know deceit.' WHERE entry=10530;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='A $R $C...$B$BYes, there was a priest of your order here recently, $N.  He told me it was time you returned to the Exodar met with Caedmos.  There was a sense of urgency in his request, so I wouldn\'t take too long to see him.',objectives_loc4='Caedmos at the Exodar has requested you come see him.' WHERE entry=10534;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It means "hero\'s sojourn" in my native tongue. It rings true even now - in this era where our heroes have all died...$B$BIt seems as though one always rises.' WHERE entry=10537;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='That last experiment was not a complete loss -- I did save a small bit of the blood you brought me.  Now boiled down, it should be free of whatever curses the Bleeding Hollow witches placed on their people\'s blood.$B$BI need more for study.  Go gather bleeding hollow blood from the orcs in Zeth\'Gor.  When you\'ve gathered the blood, bring it to their cursed cauldron and boil it.  Bring me the boiled blood.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Very good. Now I can more easily perform my tests...$B$BThank you, $N. Your talents are considerable.' WHERE entry=10538;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='A $R $C...$B$BYes, there was a priest of your order here recently, $N.  He told me it was time you returned to the Exodar met with Caedmos.  There was a sense of urgency in his request, so I wouldn\'t take too long to see him.',objectives_loc4='Caedmos at the Exodar has requested you come see him.' WHERE entry=10539;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Ar\'tor fades in and out of existence.>$B$BIt would seem that my time is nearly at an end, hero.' WHERE entry=10540;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Take Ar\'tor\'s Lockbox to Oronok Torn-heart at Oronok\'s Farm in Shadowmoon Valley.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Oronok wipes the tear away and smiles at you.>$B$BThank you. I promise you, hero, a song of honor will be written in your name.' WHERE entry=10541;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Use the Wicked Strong Fetish to curse 5 buildings or towers in Bladespire Hold and 2 in Bloodmaul Outpost.  Return to T\'chali the Witch Doctor at Bloodmaul Ravine in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains after you have done so.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Hahaha, revenge is sweet!$B$BBut, T\'chali can see you be interested in moving on now that you help him get his revenge. I hear you, mon... life is for the living.$B$BTell you what, T\'chali got lots of goodies still left here in his grave. You pick the one you like best!' WHERE entry=10544;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Borak is silent for a moment.>$B$BI\'ve been watching these blood elves for weeks now, trying to get a lock on where they\'ve hidden the third part of the Cipher of Damnation.$B$BThus far, I\'ve been unsuccessful in gathering any clues. The only thing I do know is that Illidan sends an envoy from the Black Temple here once a day.$B$BThis envoy is untouchable. I\'ve shadowed him for a week, trying to figure out how to separate him from his bodyguard. Unfortunately, the bodyguard never leaves his side.' WHERE entry=10546;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve got a rotten arakkoa egg? Well why didn\'t you say so! I think we can do business.$B$B<Tobias smiles, exposing a mouthful of decay and filth.>' WHERE entry=10547;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Remember how I told you about the fat merchant who was looking for that ring?  As it turns out, he had his archeologist son looking for the thing and it didn\'t turn out so well.  By not so well I mean they killed him and shrunk his head.$B$BNow this might seem cold, calculating, and exceptionally callous, but he\'d pay a lot to get his son\'s head back.  Sounds like the perfect job for you!$B$BGo east until you find the troll ruins of Zeb\'Tela and Zeb\'Nowa.  You\'re bound to find it one of the chests there.',objectives_loc4='Eralan in Tranquillien wants you to retrieve the Archeologist\'s Shrunken Head from one of the chests in Zeb\'Tela or Zeb\'Nowa.' WHERE entry=10549;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Take the Bundle of Bloodthistle back to Borak, Son of Oronok at the bridge near Eclipse Point in Shadowmoon Valley.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Now to set the trap!' WHERE entry=10550;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Are you certain of your choice, $N? $BThe Aldor will welcome you as an ally, but the Scryers will not easily forgive your decision.' WHERE entry=10551;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Are you certain of your choice, $N? $BThe Scryers will welcome you as an ally, but the Aldor will not easily forgive your decision.' WHERE entry=10552;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Khadgar sends a new recruit? Let us put you to work, $C.' WHERE entry=10553;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Welcome, $N. I\'m glad to hear you\'ve decided to join us in our mission. May the Light always protect you.' WHERE entry=10554;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The magic practiced by the Lashh\'an arakkoa is unnatural. They rip out handfuls-clawfuls?-of their own feathers as reagents!$B$BThat doesn\'t sound like good magic to me. I\'ve come here to learn more about their spells. Unfortunately getting close is too much for me.$B$BYou could succeed: cast one of their spells on yourself, then return to me. You\'ll have to find one of their spellbooks, high up in the trees of Veil Lashh.$B$BAnd unless you\'ve grown feathers I can\'t see, you\'ll need to get some of those.$B',objectives_loc4='Collect 18 Plucked Lashh\'an Feathers, then read the Lashh\'an Tome in the treetops of Veil Lashh.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Flipping through the pages of the scratched notes and spindly script of the Lashh\'an arrakoa, you find a page with a pictogram of the circles of power you have seen in Veil Lashh.' WHERE entry=10555;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Use the Fistful of Feathers on the Lashh\'an Spell Circle, then return to Daranelle at Sylvanaar before the kaliri spirit fades.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I don\'t know what to say. This spell is very strange. It is not a simple conjuration or enchantment, but some sort of communion or communication spell.$B$BI\'m not sure what to make of it, $N. I\'ll have to think about it some more.$B$BBut thanks for your help, anyways! I\'m sure I\'ll think through this sooner or later.$BGains.' WHERE entry=10556;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Speak with Rally Zapnabber and use the Zephyrium Capacitorium.  Return to Tally Zapnabber at Toshley\'s Station.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Wow, you made it! And not a single bruise or compound fracture! See, I told you everything would work out!$B$BHere\'s your pay, $N, though I factored in medical expenses and you don\'t need those... so that\'s a bonus for you!' WHERE entry=10557;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<A\'dal appears to be extremely pleased with you.  With your help Tempest Keep will one day reclaimed from the clutches of evil.>' WHERE entry=10560;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you for relieving my men, $N. With your help, and that of others, we may yet hold out. Unfortunately, merely holding out is not enough. We must go on the offensive.' WHERE entry=10562;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The fortress of Legion Hold is nigh impregnable, and to be completely honest, I can\'t spare the forces for an assault. Our hopes are riding on you, $N.$B$BWhat little information we\'ve been able to gather indicates that the Legion stocks and prepares its infernals at the hold. With the help of a disguise I\'ll give you, you must sneak into Legion Hold and learn about the their plans. Your best hope is to intercept or overhear communication between their commanders. Good luck, $N.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Wing Commander Nuainn listens to your report, growing more alarmed with each sentence.>$B$BSo you\'re saying they have more than enough infernals to intensify the bombardment? If we don\'t stop them before they can put the next phase of their plan into motion, Wildhammer Stronghold is finished.' WHERE entry=10563;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N! I wish I could say that the Legion would give up after a setback like this, but you and I know better than that. The Deathforge that you learned about during your reconnaissance mission will be our next target.' WHERE entry=10564;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Collect and use a Vekh\'nir Crystal at the Vekh\'nir Spell Circle, then return the Charged Vekh\'nir Crystal to Dertrok at the Mok\'Nathal Village.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, look how it glows! I must try this at once.' WHERE entry=10565;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Try out each of Dertrok\'s wands on an Arakkoa Ogre Slave, then return to Dertrok. Each wand will require an Infused Vekh\'nir Crystal to use.',offerrewardtext_loc4='This information will be every helpful, $N. I will further refine that design and see if we can\'t expand its utility.' WHERE entry=10566;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Test the third wand',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Test the fourth wand' WHERE entry=10566;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Find 6 Ruuan\'ok Claws and use them at the Ruaan\'ok Oracle Circle to summon a Harbinger of the Raven. Kill it and return its Harbinger\'s Pendant to Timeon at Ruuan Weald.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have it!$B$BWith this pendant, I will be able to attune you to the arakkoa of Grishnath in such a way that will enable you to comprehend their speech.$B$BWith this, we may gain further understanding of the arakkoa, and the nature of the Raven. I will need your help to do this.' WHERE entry=10567;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Baa\'ri tablets! Yes, this might provide us with very useful information.' WHERE entry=10568;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Kieran leafs through the journal pages.>$B$BMuch of this is unintelligible. but I can make out bits here and there about preparations for a spell gone awry. casualties, and a deteriorating situation. There\'s also a curious note here about a \'deserter.\'' WHERE entry=10569;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Borak takes the missive from you and begins to read.>$B$BClever bastards! This is a directive from Illidan that dictates where the cipher is to be hidden next. Apparently, they keep it moving. It does not tell us where it currently rests... If only we could deliver the missive now that we know the next location.$B$BToo bad the seal on the missive is broken, rendering it unusable.$B$BHrm... Yet...' WHERE entry=10570;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Akama\'s very own handwriting. It is truly sad to think of what became of one as wise and beloved as he.' WHERE entry=10571;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The wing commander inserts the power core into the armor plates and seals the device shut, nodding.>$B$BThis should do the trick. Should make quite an explosion too, if I do say so m\'self.' WHERE entry=10572;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The dwarf nods.>$B$BIt\'ll be good to have the backup. We\'ve gathered some preliminary information on what the Shadow Council is up to in there, but I\'ll feel better once we\'re able to start taking action against them.' WHERE entry=10573;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes! The four fragments of the medallion. Now to put them together...' WHERE entry=10574;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We\'ve been expecting you, $N. Akama said you would arrive sooner or later.' WHERE entry=10575;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Borak, Son of Oronok at the bridge near Eclipse Point in Shadowmoon Valley wants you to recover 6 pieces of Eclipsion Armor.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. I hope you are a good actor. The next step in my grand plan is going to require some theatrics!' WHERE entry=10576;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Now all you need to do is go get the cipher. Easy, right?' WHERE entry=10577;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='That Cipher fragment will never reach Zuluhed. You\'re going to ambush Ruul the Darkener and his transport before it has a chance to make the delivery.$B$BThe Dragonmaw Fortress is directly east of here, across the Netherwing Fields. Somewhere between Dragonmaw Fortress and the Sanctum of the Stars is where you\'ll find Ruul. Strike hard and strike fast! And $N, from the sound of it, this Ruul is going to be tough. Keep your guard up.$B$BReturn the Cipher to me should you succeed.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Finally! The cipher fragment is ours!$B$B<Borak places the fragment into a box.>' WHERE entry=10578;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='As soon as all three of the fragments of the cipher are together, the ancient words will be known.$B$BRecovery of this fragment was no doubt challenging. You must be rewarded for such heroism.' WHERE entry=10579;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Commander Skyshadow has asked you to look in the southern area of the Jagged Ridge of the Blade\'s Edge Mountains for a clue as to the whereabouts of Toshley and the other gnomes.',offerrewardtext_loc4='SYLVANAAR? COMMANDER SKYSHADOW?$B$BTHIS DOES NOT COMPUTE!$B$BBACK AWAY BEFORE I AM FORCED TO PLAY LOUD SOUNDS AT YOU!' WHERE entry=10580;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='In a round-about way, R-3D0 has informed you that if you follow the trail of spare parts up the ramp here to the Razor Ridge, you will find the gnomes at a place named Toshley\'s Station.$B$BIf you find him, speak with Toshley.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Alright, you want to make yourself useful? Good, I have just the thing that you can prove yourself with.$B$BI think you\'ll like it.' WHERE entry=10581;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I wish I could\'ve been out there with you! I\'ve been itching to put my hammer to use, but my mission is to observe, not to kill.$B$BNow that you\'ve punched a hole in their defenses, let\'s get to work on shutting down production in the Deathforge.' WHERE entry=10582;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Ewan shakes his head as he accepts the pack from you>$B$BI don\'t think Flanis realized how heavily guarded the Deathforge would be. Now that we know what\'s really going on there, I don\'t blame them. I just wish Flanis had known that when he went in.$B$BI can only hope there\'s something here that will help us shut down the Deathforge once and for all.' WHERE entry=10583;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Toshley has asked you to take the Protovoltaic Magneto Collector and gather up 5 Electromentals.  Return to him at Toshley\'s Station in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains after you have done so.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent! With all of this power that you\'ve recovered we\'ll be able to keep the machinery running for a little while, anyway.$B$BThe Zephyrium Capacitorium is a real pig when it comes to power consumption!$B$BI hope dealing with those electromentals wasn\'t too difficult. I have something else in mind for you to do, and I have a feeling that it\'s going to be a little more dangerous.' WHERE entry=10584;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. Disrupting the Shadow Council\'s summoning puts us one step closer to shutting down the Deathforge.' WHERE entry=10585;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<You make your report to the wing commander and hand over the captured orders.>$B$BDefeating Warbringer Razuun should\'ve meant the end of our troubles with the Legion, but these orders outline a much larger plan that I had anticipated. I fear that more remains to be done.' WHERE entry=10586;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Let\'s take a closer look at these weapons, $N.  Hmmm... this is rather unsettling.' WHERE entry=10587;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='How many times has this spell has been used in the history of our worlds? Undoubtedly, its power for destruction is unparalleled.$B$BWhat you must do now is take the cipher, now made whole, and read from it at the Altar of Damnation - where the memory of Gul\'dan stands.$B$BWhat you will see once the words are uttered are the memories left imprinted upon the land. Stand your ground and await the coming of Cyrukh.$B$BYou must be victorious, $N. This land can not withstand another shattering.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Earthmender Torlok takes the Cipher of Damnation from you.>$B$BYou have done as the elements asked. For that, we are grateful. While you will be rewarded, trouble still looms. The spirits of fire are in turmoil. A claim has been made. The Cipher of Damnation is known by another.$B$BIt is cryptic, I know, but that is all that the spirits would have me know. That and this symbol...$B$B<Earthmender Torlok turns around and points to the sky.>$B$BWhat could it mean?' WHERE entry=10588;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Let me see if I can find out how this works...' WHERE entry=10589;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Nickwinkle the Metro-Gnome wants you to place the Oscillating Frequency Scanners in such a way that when you stand amongst them, you are hit by five overlapping Oscillation fields.$B$BReturn to him at Toshley\'s Station in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains after you have done so.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh, this is extraordinary! I had no idea... it\'s almost as if those crystals are alive.$B$BI wonder if there\'s some sort of symbiotic relationship between them and the nether drakes?$B$BThank you, thank you! You must accept a little something from my collection of odds and ends that I wouldn\'t be caught dead wearing.$B$BOne of them might look good on you, though.' WHERE entry=10594;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='<Gulmok looks to the sky.>$B$BOur scouts are putting up a good fight, but the infernals keep coming!$B$BFrom their base of Legion Hold to the southwest, the demons bombard us with impunity! Even the elite Kor\'kron guard cannot hold them off forever.$B$BI\'m drafting every able-bodied $R to do their part in defense of Shadowmoon Village. This is no game, $C. The survival of the village is at stake. Do your duty to the Horde, and join the fray!',objectives_loc4='Blood Guard Gulmok outside of Shadowmoon Village, wants you to kill 10 Infernal Attackers.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m impressed that you managed to survive the carnage. You just might be the person we need for a dangerous mission.' WHERE entry=10595;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Make your way to Legion Hold, locate the Legion Communication Device, and learn about the Legion\'s plans while in disguise. Return to Blood Guard Gulmok at Shadowmoon Village when you\'ve completed your mission.',offerrewardtext_loc4='What do you mean they\'re going to step up the bombardment? We can\'t allow that to happen. Get back out there and take care of it while there\'s something left of Shadowmoon Village!' WHERE entry=10596;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We can\'t allow the Legion to trample us on their march to Black Temple.$B$BFind a way to destroy the infernals they intend to use against us. That\'s not a request, $N; it\'s an order.$B$BThe Fetid Pool near Legion Hold holds an old fel reaver power core you could use as the basis for a kind of fel bomb. Search the other wreckage near the fel reaver for a section of armor plating. You should be able to make a bomb powerful enough to take out those infernals and give the hold a nice shake!',objectives_loc4='Obtain a Fel Reaver Power Core and a Fel Reaver Armor Plate, then bring them to Blood Guard Gulmok at Shadowmoon Village.',offerrewardtext_loc4='That should do the trick. I wouldn\'t want to be in the hold when that thing goes off.' WHERE entry=10597;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Use the Fel Bomb while standing on the green glyph in Legion Hold to destroy the infernals, then report to Blood Guard Gulmok at Shadowmoon Village.',offerrewardtext_loc4='This is no time for celebration, $N. We\'re not out of the fire yet. I\'ve got new orders for you.' WHERE entry=10598;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='While you were taking care of the infernals at Legion Hold, I\'ve been going over your reports. We\'ve got no reason to believe the Legion lied about what\'s going on at the Deathforge. They\'re really cranking out infernals down there, so I\'ve dispatched a scouting party to keep watch over it.$B$BIf we don\'t shut down the Deathforge, they\'ll rebuild the infernal stockpile that you destroyed at Legion Hold.$B$BReport to Scout Zagran atop Slag Watch, to the southeast of here and overlooking the Deathforge.',objectives_loc4='Report to Scout Zagran at Slag Watch.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<The orc nods.>$B$BIt\'ll be good to have the backup. We\'ve gathered some preliminary information on what the Shadow Council is up to in there, but it\'s time for the hammer to fall.' WHERE entry=10599;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='<Zagran listens to you recount the events at Legion Hold, nodding.>$B$BThat fills in the gaps we\'ve seen. We\'ve caught glimpses of them launching infernals in the direction of the hold, but haven\'t been able to find much more than that.$B$BThe Shadow Council has the forge pretty much locked down. Looks like you\'re going to need to fight your way in. Start eliminating the Shadow Council guarding the entrance to the Deathforge!',objectives_loc4='Scout Zagran at Slag Watch wants you to kill 10 Deathforge Guardians and 5 Deathforge Summoners.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'d\'ve been down there cracking skulls myself, but I\'m under strict orders not to engage the enemy.$B$BLet\'s get to work on shutting down production in there.' WHERE entry=10600;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Zagran shakes his head as he accepts the pack from you>$B$BI told you he was a fool. I hope there\'s something in here that justifies the time you spent searching for him.' WHERE entry=10601;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good, we\'re making progress. That puts us one step closer to shutting down this facility and returning safely to Shadowmoon Village.' WHERE entry=10602;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We\'ve made a lot of progress against the Shadow Council here at the Deathforge, but now it\'s time to finish the job.$B$BI found a key among the items in Kagrosh\'s pack. At least he accomplished something before they got to him.$B$BThe key should help you to track down this Warbringer Razuun you observed at Legion Hold.$B$BAfter you\'ve hunted down and dealt with Warbringer Razuun, report directly to Blood Guard Gulmok. We must not keep him waiting.',objectives_loc4='Defeat Warbringer Razuun, recover Razuun\'s Orders, and report to Blood Guard Gulmok at Shadowmoon Village.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<You make your report to the blood guard and hand over the captured orders.>$B$BGood work, $N, but don\'t go thinking you\'ll be getting any ribbons for it. Let the night elves decorate their pretty little uniforms if they wish. Real warriors share tales of battle over a mug of ale.' WHERE entry=10603;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='According to Razuun\'s orders, the massive infernal staging area is called Invasion Point: Cataclysm and it\'s located in the mountains behind our village! The only way to reach it is by using a teleporter at Legion Hold.$B$BCertain Legion minions carry a device allowing them to use the teleporter. You must capture one of these devices to win access to the teleporter. Slaughter all of the demons if you must, but you can\'t afford to return empty-handed. Do not delay; the enemy is perilously close.',objectives_loc4='Bring a Legion Teleporter Control to Blood Guard Gulmok at Shadowmoon Village. The Mo\'arg Weaponsmiths at Legion Hold are known to carry the devices.',offerrewardtext_loc4='At last, we have a means with which to drive the Legion from Shadowmoon!' WHERE entry=10604;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, this is exactly what we\'ll need. I\'d never accuse the Legion of producing anything resembling literature, but it gets the job done.' WHERE entry=10606;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Kill Grishna arakkoa to gain Understanding Ravenspeech for 2 minutes. While under the effects of the spell, you can find and receive the prophecy from the four shrines. Return when you have visited all four.',offerrewardtext_loc4='This is truly disturbing. The arakkoa were peaceful for a long time. This cult of the Raven was nothing more than a gathering of misfits and madmen.$B$BBut their power has grown, that we cannot discount. Perhaps there is more to this Raven than we know.' WHERE entry=10607;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Receive the Third Prophecy',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Receive the Fourth Prophecy' WHERE entry=10607;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Nickwinkle the Metro-Gnome wants you to slay 10 Crystal Flayers and then return to him at Toshley\'s Station in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Good riddance to them; that\'s what I say. Filthy creatures!$B$BSo, if you\'re certain that you eliminated those pests, then I have a little research project for you. I think you\'ll like it.' WHERE entry=10608;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Collect 3 Proto-Nether Drake Essences, 3 Adolescent Drake Essences and 3 Mature Drake Essences.  Return with them to Fizit "Doc" Clocktock at Toshley\'s Station in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve no idea how important this research could be. Thank you!$B$BIt\'ll be interesting to delve into these essences. I\'m particularly curious to see if the nether effect that changed the black dragon eggs into nether dragon eggs resulted in any potential extra blessings for my studies.$B$BI\'m thinking, in fact, that you should be the first person to test out the benefits of my little concoction. Here, take these preliminary samples and use them when you find the need.' WHERE entry=10609;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The best way to destroy the rest of the Legion\'s supplies is to use their own weapons against them. I\'ve been working on a rig that will let you take control of one of those Fel Reaver Sentinels below.$B$BThere are a couple things I need to work out, yet. For that, I\'ll need the manual that Doctor Maleficus keeps locked in a chest near the bottom of the ramp. He probably won\'t give up the key without a fight, so you\'ll need to capture it. Bring the fel reaver manual back to me and I\'ll do the rest.',objectives_loc4='Kill Doctor Maleficus and obtain the Doctor\'s Key. Use the key to open the Doctor\'s Strongbox to retrieve The Art of Fel Reaver Maintenance and deliver the book to Nakansi at Invasion Point Cataclysm.',offerrewardtext_loc4='This has the information I\'m looking for. Just a couple more tweaks, and we\'ll have you taking control of a fel reaver in no time.' WHERE entry=10611;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Amazing! You\'ve managed to do what all the gryphonriders in Wildhammer Stronghold couldn\'t! You\'ve broken the back of the Burning Legion\'s advance and spared us from annihilation at the hands of their infernals. You have our deepest gratitude for your service, $N.' WHERE entry=10612;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='<Nakansi leafs through the manual.>$B$BAll the information is here, but be warned. These things weren\'t built to be controlled remotely.$B$BWe can modify one for you to use for a short time, but you\'ll have to work fast, or there\'s no telling what might happen! I wouldn\'t be surprised if your little stunt with the fel reaver catches the attention of the Legion scum, either. Try to keep yourself safe, but remember, the mission and the safety of Shadowmoon Village come first!',objectives_loc4='Use a Fel Reaver Control Console to take control of a Fel Reaver Sentinel. Destroy 60 Deathforged Infernals before your fel reaver fails. When your mission is complete, report to Nakansi at Invasion Point: Cataclysm.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'ll admit it, $N. I\'m impressed by all you\'ve managed to accomplish. Destroying the Legion\'s ability to make war in Shadowmoon will give us the opportunity to turn the tide elsewhere.' WHERE entry=10613;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, yes, Dertrok. We spoke briefly about the arakkoa. I must say that our... interests in them vary quite significantly.' WHERE entry=10615;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Taerek at Mok\'Nathal Village wants you to collect 8 Silkwing Cocoons from Silkwing Larva.$B$BKill the Larva quickly or they will turn into Silkwings, ruining their cocoons.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Good quality cocoons, these. I can see you\'ve gotten the hang of harvesting them.$B$BWe have experimented with trying to raise our own silkwing larva, but unfortunately the small ones do not produce enough silk to be of use to us.' WHERE entry=10617;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Silmara at Mok\'Nathal Village wants you to collect 12 Iridescent Wings.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $N. We will use these sooner than you might think.' WHERE entry=10618;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Glory to the naaru, $N.  You\'ve done the Light\'s bidding by defeating those who follow Illidan.' WHERE entry=10619;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Dizzy Dina wants you to kill 10 Ridgespine Stalkers.  After you have done so, return to her at Toshley\'s Station in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Pretty good for a rookie. As it turns out, we\'ve got a small group of eggheads that want to go \'observe\' the ethereals and their technology up north. They\'ll be thrilled to know that you cleared the way for them.$B$BHere, take some of these. We don\'t have many, but maybe they\'ll help you out in the future.' WHERE entry=10620;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Ordinn accepts the weapon fragment from you.>$B$BI haven\'t seen something like this in a long time. Sure, it\'s made from a rare ore, but this is destined for no mundane weapon, $N. It\'s infused with a magic intended to destroy demons. If you obtained this from the Legion, it must be some kind of \'secret weapon\' they\'re planning to deploy against Illidan. What a find!' WHERE entry=10621;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Very well, $N. Your allegiance is no longer in question. You may see Akama now.' WHERE entry=10622;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Grokom accepts the weapon fragment from you.>$B$BI haven\'t seen this in years. Not only is it made from a rare ore. but it\'s not about to be used in an ordinary weapon, $N.$B$BThese runes imbue the blade with the power to obliterate demons. This shows how much the Legion hates Illidan, if they\'re willing to arm their own troops with demon-destroying weapons. We could use this to our advantage.' WHERE entry=10623;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Have you felt the cold chill? Perhaps what you thought was a hand on your shoulder? That was not your mind playing tricks on you, $R. The land is haunted. Ghosts litter the landscape, stuck here for all eternity.$B$BWould you like to see them? Are you sure about that? These types of things tend to change a person - and not for the better.$B$BVery well, I will need you to collect for me the ever-burning ash that is found near any of the fel lava pools of western Shadowmoon. Anywhere near green lava...$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Your world is about to change, $N.' WHERE entry=10624;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I call them "Spectrecles." Clever, no? When you equip these goggles, you will be able to see the spirits of Shadowmoon Valley.$B$BBefore I let you have them, though, you must promise me that you will help us clear out the ghosts at the village.$B$BTake the goggles and destroy any and all spirits that you see wandering about Shadowmoon Village. Hopefully, destroying these spirits will force any that remain to move elsewhere.',objectives_loc4='Chief Apothecary Hildagard at Shadowmoon Village in Shadowmoon Valley wants you to slay 12 Shadowmoon Zealots.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Gorefiend? T... Teron Gorefiend? But... How?$B$BHow could Gorefiend be here? This is impossible!$B$BThe legend of Teron Gorefiend is one that causes even the Forsaken to tremble in fear. By all accounts, Gorefiend was a warlock of Gul\'dan' WHERE entry=10625;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These should work nicely. Now, let\'s forge them into a more useful form.' WHERE entry=10626;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These should work nicely. Now, let\'s forge them into a more useful form.' WHERE entry=10627;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hail, $N. There is much we need to talk about.$B$BI hope your mind is an open one. The decisions I make are not understood by many. Only my closest collaborators have understanding of the portents I see and the signs I await.$B$BWhen I joined forces with Illidan it was based on visions foretelling that otherwise my race would have been destroyed. I\'ve waited patiently for other signs and visions to come to pass... Velen\'s exodus... the opening of the Dark Portal... and now... your arrival.' WHERE entry=10628;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You smell terrible.  But you found my keys!  Thank you so much.  Now I can get my shredder started and make some money.  Pretty soon I will have enough money to leave Outland.  I don\'t know why you stay, I hate this place.  Wouldn\'t you rather be back in Booty Bay?$B$BMaybe do some fishing?' WHERE entry=10629;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='All those gan\'arg are sure to clear out now.  I\'ll be back in Booty Bay within a week.  I can\'t wait to go fishing again.  Coming to Outland was a mistake.  If you\'ll take my advice, you\'ll head back the way you came.  Spend some time in Stranglethorn, or maybe, if you feel adventurous, head to Un\'Goro Crater.  Just don\'t stay here.' WHERE entry=10630;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Razak Ironsides has asked you to gather up 5 Extra Sharp Daggermaw Teeth.  Return them to him at Toshley\'s Station in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Good work, kid. All of the pain is worth it if even one of my soldiers\' lives is saved by your efforts.$B$BI think you should benefit from your sweat and tears, too. Since we\'re going to have a new batch of weapons soon, why don\'t you take one of mine?' WHERE entry=10632;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Chief Apothecary Hildagard at Shadowmoon Village in Shadowmoon Valley wants you to find the Ancient Shadowmoon Spirit.$B$BIf you lose your Spectrecles, Chief Apothecary Hildagard can make you a new pair.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Gorefiend? Why, I have not heard that name in ages!$B$BAfter the Second War, Gorefiend returned here, along with his death knights. Unable to cope with the terrible nature of his new form and without the support of his beloved leader, Gul\'dan, Gorefiend killed himself.$B$BIf he walks these lands now as a spirit, it is news to me. Yet, perhaps I can divine such knowledge with your assistance.' WHERE entry=10633;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='In life, Gorefiend was a bastard, but in death, Gorefiend was an unmitigated terror.$B$BTo the southeast you will find Netherwing Ledge. What was once part of the mainland of Shadowmoon is now a floating island in the sky.$B$BVhel\'kur, spawn of Deathwing, once called it his home, but now knows it as his grave. He flies an endless circle above the island, seething at his defeat to Gorefiend.$B$BIf you are to recover the Gorefiend\'s armor, it is Vhel\'kur that you must defeat.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I must have all of the pieces before I am able to divine the fate of Gorefiend.' WHERE entry=10634;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='When I have all three of the pieces in my possession, I will be able to divine the whereabouts of Gorefiend.' WHERE entry=10635;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Only with all three united may I divine the secrets you so desperately seek!' WHERE entry=10636;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Let us hope that distraction bought us the time we need to fully learn what we need of the training grounds at Karabor.' WHERE entry=10637;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='The Ancient Shadowmoon Spirit has used you as a pawn! Now that you have collected the items he required, he has revealed himself to be Teron Gorefiend. To break free of his possession, you must do his bidding and slay Karsius the Ancient Watcher.$B$BIf you succeed, return to Chief Apothecary Hildagard at Shadowmoon Village.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You did what? FOOL!$B$BYou must right this wrong. After all, it is your fault. Take one of these helmets. They are each infused with the ever-burning ash that you retrieved for me. More importantly, they will allow you to see the ghosts of Shadowmoon, including Teron Gorefiend.$B$BShould you ever find Teron Gorefiend, destroy him.' WHERE entry=10639;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve come a long way, stranger. I\'m surprised whoever sent you has heard of me.' WHERE entry=10640;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I fear that these dwarves do not understand what they have built upon. This area was once the ancestral grounds for the Shadowmoon orcs. I speak of spirits, $R.$B$BFor nearly twenty years they have laid dormant beneath the WIldhammer Stronghold, but recently, something has riled them up.$B$BVenture beyond the gates of Wildhammer and seek out the pools and rivers of fel lava found across this land. Near the lava will be ever-burning ash. Bring me this ash so that I may craft something that will help us.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Zorus begins to craft something out of the ash samples.>$B$BIt is done. Behold, Spectrecles!' WHERE entry=10642;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You claim to have heard the ghosts whisper to you? And they mentioned Teron Gorefiend?$B$B<Zorus shudders.>$B$BYes... I know Teron Gorefiend. Rather, I knew of him. He has long been thought dead. What could these ghosts be speaking of?' WHERE entry=10643;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Zorus the Judicator at Wildhammer Stronghold in Shadowmoon Valley wants you to find the Ancient Shadowmoon Spirit.$B$BIf you lose your Spectrecles, Zorus the Judicator can make you a new pair.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Gorefiend? Why, I have not heard that name in ages!$B$BAfter the Second War, Gorefiend returned here, along with his death knights. Unable to cope with the terrible nature of his new form and without the support of his beloved leader, Gul\'dan, Gorefiend killed himself.$B$BIf he walks these lands now as a spirit, it is news to me. Yet, perhaps I can divine such knowledge with your assistance.' WHERE entry=10644;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You did what? FOOL!$B$BYou must right this wrong. After all, it is your fault. Take one of these helmets. They are each infused with the ever-burning ash that you retrieved for me. More importantly, they will allow you to see the ghosts of Shadowmoon, including Teron Gorefiend.$B$BShould you ever find Teron Gorefiend, destroy him.' WHERE entry=10645;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You know the story now. Only one thing remains to be done.' WHERE entry=10646;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Quite da haul you got der, mon. Well done! An\' ya be getting\' yer reward. Don\'t ya worry!' WHERE entry=10647;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yep, here\'s your reward. Don\'t go spendin\' it all in once place.' WHERE entry=10648;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I was able to sense the book\'s power from yards away. The temptation to keep it is... very strong.' WHERE entry=10649;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You bring this abomination of a book to this holy site? You\'d better have a very good explanation, $N?' WHERE entry=10650;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work, $N! Your victory over Varedis will have a tremendous impact on our war against Illidan.$B$BYou\'ve proven yourself not just to the Aldor but to all of Outland. Allow me to destroy what remains of that horrible book.' WHERE entry=10651;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Welcome, $C. Try not to give our position away.$B$BWe wouldn\'t last long if Kael\'s cronies sniff us out.' WHERE entry=10652;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Facing the demons of the Burning Legion and the mad cultists that worship them is no small feat, $N.  You\'ve shown great dedication and courage.  Keep it up and your renown among the Aldor will continue to grow.' WHERE entry=10653;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You continue to prove your worth, $N.  Fight the enemies of the Light wherever you may find them; your actions will be well-rewarded.' WHERE entry=10654;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You continue to prove your worth, $N.  Fight the enemies of the Light wherever you may find them; your actions will be well-rewarded.' WHERE entry=10655;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Kael\'s Sunfury army is extremely well-trained.  Very impressive job, $N.' WHERE entry=10656;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Toshley wants you to use the Repolarized Magneto Sphere to absorb 25 lightning strikes from the Scalewing Serpents.  As well, collect 5 Scalewing Lightning Glands.  Then, deliver them back to him at Toshley\'s Station in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Woo hoo, it worked! To be honest I wasn\'t sure... I calculated a twenty-three point seven two chance that you\'d implode by the third strike.$B$B<Toshley grins innocently.>$B$BSo, now we know that the sphere works, we should have no problem meeting our energy needs for the Zephyrium Capacitorium. Well, that is if we can find more volunteers to go out there and get zapped.$B$BStill, you\'ve pioneered our efforts and deserve something in return!' WHERE entry=10657;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent! That\'ll show Kael\'thas not to underestimate our power.' WHERE entry=10658;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Kael\'s army will soon fall.' WHERE entry=10659;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I am interested in learning more about the strange reptiles that mill about the lava flows of Shadowmoon Valley. Never have I seen beasts able to withstand the searing heat of molten lava!$B$BOutside of Shadowmoon Village, where the ground has ruptured and lava flows through the cracks, you will find felfire diemetradons. Slay them and bring me their spleens. From their spleens I will be able to begin preliminary analysis of their resistance to heat.$B$BBegin your search to the southeast.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='This may take a while. Take these coins for your hard work.' WHERE entry=10660;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Gnomus hungrily grabs at the spleens.>$B$BHere\'s your coin as promised. I\'ll call for you if I need more spleens.$B$BSo delicious... I dare say that they are \'spleendid!\'' WHERE entry=10661;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ordinn sent you with these?$B$B<The smith examines the ingots.>$B$BHe was right. Most of the magic is gone, but I can still sense traces of it. With some work and a few \'exotic\' resources, I can forge you a powerful anti-demon sword from this metal.' WHERE entry=10662;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='<The orc shakes his head at his failure.>$B$BThis is beyond my ability, but that\'s not to say the weapon can\'t be recreated.$B$BIt pains me to suggest this, but your only hope may be a human smith by the name of David Wayne. It\'s true he was once a member of the Alliance\'s expedition, but that was a long time ago and he has since left the Sons of Lothar. These days, he lives in a small camp on a peninsula east of Firewing Point in Terokkar Forest. Take the ingots to him and see if he can help you.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<The smith frowns and examines the ingots.>$B$BI\'ll be frank with you, $C. I\'m a relic of an age when cooperation with the Horde was unthinkable.$B$BI am not so blind as to see that we do not have common enemies. I will help you to reforge the anti-demon weapon but it\'s going to take a lot of hard work and a few \'exotic\' resources.' WHERE entry=10663;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The smith accepts the materials, nodding approvingly.>$B$BThese will suffice. The remainder of the materials I\'ll need won\'t be quite so easy to come by.' WHERE entry=10664;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Working with the ingots you brought is going to require a lot of heat -- rather more than a conventional forge can supply.$B$BI\'m going to need a supplemental heat source for the forge and there are very few things in Outland that can supply that kind of power.$B$BThe Mechanar area of Tempest Keep turns out manacells containing an incredible amount of power. Find one of the overcharged manacells from the stacks around Mechano-Lord Capacitus and bring it back here.',objectives_loc4='David Wayne at Wayne\'s Retreat wants you to bring him an Overcharged Manacell.',offerrewardtext_loc4='This is even more potent than I expected! With this much power, I could forge a dozen blades!' WHERE entry=10665;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<David leafs through the book\'s pages, shuddering.>$B$BThis is not something to be trifled with, $N. After the weapon is created, I will destroy it. There is enough demonic power about in the world without this text out in the open.' WHERE entry=10666;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This should do the trick. I\'d hoped for a bit more, but to be honest, we were lucky to get our hands on any at all out here.' WHERE entry=10667;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So you\'re not with Illidan. You\'re one step closer to gaining my full trust.' WHERE entry=10668;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N.  He still remembered the day I drove this spear into him?  That was so long ago...' WHERE entry=10669;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<David Wayne holds the gem up, to the light, admiring it.>$B$BIt\'s aboslutely flawless, and that\'s exactly what we\'ll need. A flawed gem would endanger the weapon\'s wielder, twisting the magic against them.' WHERE entry=10670;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Dizzy Dina has asked you to acquire 5 Ether-Energized Flesh and return them to her at Toshley\'s Station in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='These ought to do nicely. Don\'t they stink, though?$B$BI hope that this is worth your troubles... I\'m just glad that it was you collecting this stuff instead of me!' WHERE entry=10671;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We must study these creatures further.$B$BFar to the east - near the huge lava flow beneath the ruins of Baa\'ri - you will find arcano control units. These controllers were crafted by a genius named Gnomus for the sole purpose of exploring lava via mechanical scorpion.$B$BHe has long since lost his mind and is now only interested in eating the hottest food known to gnome-kind.$B$B<Tiorus gives you a funny look.>$B$BI want you to use the control and tag the diemetradons of the lava flow for further study.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Listen, there is no time to spare. I\'ve been watching the tagged diemetradons and have discovered that they all report to a gigantic, nay, ENORMOUS, diemetradon named Felspine the Greater.' WHERE entry=10672;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Gnomus knows about the massive diemetradon and plans to eat it! He must have been able to see what I could see through the eyes of his arcano-scorp. Look, there\'s no time to explain. He\'s crazy and that craziness is going to cost us the closest thing we\'ve got to a fireproof jumpsuit.$B$BGet back to the lava flow near Baa\'ri and track down Felspine the Greater. Once you find it, kill it and bring me back its hide.$B$BDon\'t try and reason with me, $N. I\'m well past that point.',objectives_loc4='Researcher Tiorus at Shadowmoon Village in Shadowmoon Valley wants you to kill Felspine the Greater and recover Felspine\'s Hide.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='At last! Total protection against lava is mine! Of course you get a cut of this technology too, $N. You\'ve earned it!' WHERE entry=10673;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Toshley would like you to use the Light Trap to catch 15 Razaani Light Orbs.  Return to him at Toshley\'s Station in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains after you have done so.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Hey! Wait just one damned minute!!$B$BThis doesn\'t look good...' WHERE entry=10674;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Toshley wants you to retrieve the Collection of Souls and return it to him at Toshley\'s Station in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Good riddance to him! Thank you for putting an end to their macabre twisting of magic and technology.$B$BAs a true hero of gnomes everywhere, I hereby bequeath unto you our highest honor... some power converters and your pick of any of these.$B$BI know that you\'ll put them to good use!' WHERE entry=10675;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<David mops sweat from his brow.>$B$BThe bulk of the work is done, but to set the magics, the blade must now be quenched.' WHERE entry=10676;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This is fantastic but I just received some incredible news!' WHERE entry=10677;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'ll need some alone time now, $N. Thanks for all the help!' WHERE entry=10678;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done!$B$B<The smith examines the blade closely.>$B$BI\'d say it\'s a fair improvement over the crude Legion weapons you started with. Not only will this blade cut down Illidari demons, but it will work against the Legion\'s minions as well.' WHERE entry=10679;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It is good that you came, $R. We have much work to do.' WHERE entry=10680;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The elements need your help, $R! Shadowmoon Valley has been subject to unspeakable evils. The spirits remain tortured to this day. Many are enraged and unwilling to commune with the Earthen Ring.$B$BHelp this world heal, friend.$B$BSoutheast of Shadowmoon Village - in the heart of Shadowmoon Valley - you will find an area known as the Altar of Damnation. Make your way there and speak with Earthmender Torlok.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It is good that you came, $R. We have much work to do.' WHERE entry=10681;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Tree Warden Chawn has asked you to negotiate with Overseer Nuaar.  Return to the tree warden at Evergrove in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains afterward.',offerrewardtext_loc4='WHAT?!  They dismissed you and our proposals out of hand?$B$BThis is outrageous!  We go to them in good faith, and they turn you away without even trying to come to a compromise?$B$BWell, we\'ll see about that!' WHERE entry=10682;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Baa\'ri tablets! Yes, this might provide us with very useful information.' WHERE entry=10683;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It matches Akama\'s handwriting... let us see what we can learn.' WHERE entry=10684;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes! The four fragments of the medallion. Now to put them together...' WHERE entry=10685;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We\'ve been expecting you, $N. Akama said you would arrive sooner or later.' WHERE entry=10686;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Let\'s take a closer look at these weapons, $N.  Hmmm... this is rather unsettling.' WHERE entry=10687;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That should buy us some time... hopefully it will be enough for us to obtain more information.' WHERE entry=10688;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You don\'t see many demon hunters nowawdays.  They\'re viewed with suspicion by their own people and it\'s very rare to find one that doesn\'t have some sort of allegiance to Illidan.$B$BThere are rumors of one such demon hunter out in Nagrand.  His name is Altruis.  He hates all demons with a passion and will help us if you can convince him that you share his goals.$B$BGo to western Nagrand and find him.  He might be willing to shed some light on these new demon hunter training grounds.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve come a long way, stranger. I\'m surprised whoever sent you has heard of me.' WHERE entry=10689;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Kill Rema and then inform Commander Skyshadow at Sylvanaar in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Unbelievable. Did you slay Rema all by yourself?$B$BBy the looks of you, I\'d say that you could. You know, we\'re looking for a young, strong $C, such as yourself, to help out around here, especially with the problems we continually have with the ogres. Make sure that you follow-up with me on that possibility.$B$BWell, you\'ve definitely earned the bounty that I put on that wanted poster.$B$BPlease, take your pick.' WHERE entry=10690;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Many would pay a great price for the book you carry with you. It is a shame we\'ll have to destroy it.' WHERE entry=10691;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done well, $N. By slaying Varedis you\'ve put an end to one of Illidan\'s most dangerous projects.$B$BYour name will definitely get around after this.$B$BAllow me to take what remains of the Book of Fel Names. I will make sure it\'s properly... disposed of.' WHERE entry=10692;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh! Oh... you took care of Netherock. Good news that!$B$BWith that troublesome mountain giant out of the picture, we should have an easier time of exploi... er, husbanding the resources of the Crumbling Wastes.$B$BGlad to hear that those poor, innocent elementals down there won\'t be getting squished by him.$B$BHow ever can I repay you?' WHERE entry=10701;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Fantastic! Should I have any other grunt work that needs to be done, I\'ll find you.' WHERE entry=10702;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Aye, good work! Here\'s some coin for your efforts. If we be needin\' more garbage taken out, I\'ll know who to call.' WHERE entry=10703;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I am impressed, $N, though I should expect nothing less of the hero who returned the ata\'mal crystal to us.$B$BGive over the two shards and I will see to it that they are combined into their final form.  Then you will have access to the Arcatraz.' WHERE entry=10704;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Ashtongue Seer has been long dead.  As you turn over his body, you spot writing scrawled on the floor.' WHERE entry=10705;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes... of course! It all becomes clear now.' WHERE entry=10706;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='It has been known to us that the fel orcs, under Illidan\'s command, have guarded an Ata\'mal crystal known as the Heart of Fury at the Ata\'mal Terrace.  They cloud its presence with dark magic, to keep it from the Sha\'tar.$B$BFight your way to the Atam\'al Terrace outside the Black Temple and turn your eyes to the sky.  Shadowlord Deathwail will circle the terrace, beyond your reach.  You will have to slay him and his warlocks before you can obtain the crystal.$B$BIt won\'t be easy, $N.  I wish you luck.',objectives_loc4='Go to the top of the Atam\'al Terrace in Shadowmoon Valley and obtain the Heart of Fury.  Return to Akama at the Warden\'s Cage in Shadowmoon Valley when you\'ve completed this task.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The crystal! Its power... now in my hands!' WHERE entry=10707;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<As you give the medallion to A\'dal, it disappears into his being in a flash of light.>$B$B<You are briefly shown a glimpse of a moment... perhaps in the future. You see Akama and Maiev coming out of the Warden\'s Cage, fighting their way to the Dark Temple. A third figure shrouded in shadows is aiding them. Upon closer inspection you notice that the figure is you.>' WHERE entry=10708;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Return to Rexxar at Thunderlord Stronghold in Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So my father does live. I did not expect him to forgive - that was never his way. But I had hoped that the years had dulled the anger he must have felt at my departure.$B$BThirty years ago, I left the Mok\'Nathal to follow the Horde to Azeroth. Leoroxx was staunchly against it, but then, he never gave me any reason to stay. Still, a better welcome for this I had hoped for.$B$BHe wanted a Mok\'Nathal for a son and he has one now, even if he will not know it.$B$BI must open his eyes.' WHERE entry=10709;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Sign Tally\'s Waiver, then speak with Rally Zapnabber to use the Zephyrium Capacitorium.  Return to Tally Zapnabber at Toshley\'s Station.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Wow! Again, you survived! I\'m a much better engineer than I give myself credit for!$B$BHere\'s your pay! And check back with me later... I\'ll have more experiments that\'ll need more test subjects!' WHERE entry=10710;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Speak with Rally Zapnabber to use the Zephyrium Capacitorium.  Return to Tally Zapnabber at Toshley\'s Station.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh, gosh! You\'re back so soon! I saw you take off and you shot up like a rocket! I was sure it would take at least a month of convalescing to mend the broken legs from that flight! You\'re tough, and brave, and foolhardy! But mostly... you\'re brave!' WHERE entry=10711;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Speak with Rally Zapnabber to use the Zephyrium Capacitorium.  While flying to Ruuan Weald, spin the Nether-weather Vane.  Deliver the Spinning Nether-weather Vane to O\'Mally Zapnabber in Ruuan Weald.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh, you took readings from the nether-weather vane? Splendid! The data gained from this instrument -- coupled with my measurements of druid magic -- will bear much fruit!$B$BOh, the applications will boggle the mind, I assure you!' WHERE entry=10712;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Venture out into the Ruuan Weald and slay 10 Wyrmcult Hewers, then return to Tree Warden Chawn at Evergrove in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $N.$B$BWhile we\'ll see to it that the wildlife will replenish itself in quick order, regrowing the trees, especially in a natural fashion, is a much more time-intensive process.' WHERE entry=10713;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Find a Bloodmaul Taskmaster and a Bloodmaul Soothsayer engaged in conversation, then use Rexxar\'s Whistle to summon Spirit to spy on them. When this is complete, return to Rexxar at Thunderlord Village in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Spirit perches upon Rexxar\'s shoulder, while Rexxar listens intently.>$B$BSo it is the sons of Gruul that are behind the ogres\' actions. They command the Bloodmaul ogres to destroy the Mok\'Nathal to gain their favor.' WHERE entry=10714;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Baron Sablemane has told you that in order to make the poison that Rexxar needs, you must acquire 7 Crust Burster Venom Glands.  Return to him at the Circle of Blood in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains once you have done so.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Very well. A simple, if mundane, task has been completed. Now, hand me the glands and I will do the difficult part.' WHERE entry=10715;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Samia Inkling has asked you to acquire 5 Wyrmcult Nets and return them to her at Evergrove in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh, those look splendid.  These cultists certainly have an eye for craftsmanship.$B$BToo bad for them that it\'s misdirected.$B$BAnd now that we have the nets, would you be willing to help little old me with a thing or two?' WHERE entry=10717;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This is interesting, but disturbing.  I wonder if Samia knows who this Kolphis Darkscale is?' WHERE entry=10719;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Use the Kodohide Drum at the Marmot Den. While controlling the Marmot, poison the three kegs in the Bloodmaul Camp. When that is completed, return to Rexxar at Thunderlord Stronghold in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='For many long years I have concentrated my efforts on perfecting the ways of communicating with nature. This is but a small part of the untapped potential that beasts can bring to you.' WHERE entry=10720;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Poison the keg of Green Spot Grog',ObjectiveText2_loc4='Poison the keg of Ripe Moonshine' WHERE entry=10720;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Gather up enough Costume Scraps from the various wyrmcultists to create an Overseer Disguise.  Use the disguise to attend the meeting with Kolphis Darkscale, and report your findings back to Tree Warden Chawn at Evergrove in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Attack us? Wipe us out? I think not!$B$BThis Blackwing Coven has a great deal to learn if they think the Cenarion Expedition is so easily dealt with!$B$BWhat is it that they say? Turnabout is fair play!' WHERE entry=10722;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The gronn we seek is Gorgrom the Dragon-Eater. With Sablemane\'s trap, you will make short work of the gronn. You will find him accepting sacrifices from the ogres of Boulder\'mok.$B$BFollow the road north from the Circle of Blood, then west at Ruuan Weald. Go northwest through the tunnel.$B$BFirst, kill the ogres for their heads. We will send a message. Set the trap at his altar. When he is dead, plant the grisly totems near him - none can mistake that message.$B$BTake the bear.$B$B<Misha growls.>',objectives_loc4='Go to Boulder\'mok and collect 3 Grisly Totems from the Boulder\'mok ogres. Use Sablemane\'s Trap at Gorgrom\'s Altar to set the trap and summon and kill Gorgrom the Dragon-Eater.$B$BWhen Gorgrom is dead, place the 3 Grisly Totems near his corpse, then return to Rexxar at Thunderlord Stronghold in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The ogres of Bloodmaul and their master, Gorgrom, will trouble the Mok\'Nathal no longer.$B$BHowever, I worry about the effect our actions will have on the other gronn. I believe we must end this fight once and for all.' WHERE entry=10723;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The signet you now hold is as powerful as that of any Archmage of the Council. Wear it wherever you go so that the initiated may recognize your allegiance. Wear it wherever you go so its power may serve you as you\'ve served us!' WHERE entry=10725;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The signet you now hold is as powerful as that of any Archmage of the Council. Wear it wherever you go so that the initiated may recognize your allegiance. Wear it wherever you go so its power may serve you as you\'ve served us!' WHERE entry=10726;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The signet you now hold is as powerful as that of any Archmage of the Council. Wear it wherever you go so that the initiated may recognize your allegiance. Wear it wherever you go so its power may serve you as you\'ve served us!' WHERE entry=10727;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The signet you now hold is as powerful as that of any Archmage of the Council. Wear it wherever you go so that the initiated may recognize your allegiance. Wear it wherever you go so its power may serve you as you\'ve served us!' WHERE entry=10728;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Are you certain of your choice, $N? This is not a decision you ought to take lightly.$B$BThe Violet Signet will grow in power as you continue to prove yourself to the Violet Eye.' WHERE entry=10729;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Are you certain of your choice, $N? This is not a decision you ought to take lightly.$B$BThe Violet Signet will grow in power as you continue to prove yourself to the Violet Eye.' WHERE entry=10730;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Are you certain of your choice, $N? This is not a decision you ought to take lightly.$B$BThe Violet Signet will grow in power as you continue to prove yourself to the Violet Eye.' WHERE entry=10731;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Are you certain of your choice, $N? This is not a decision you ought to take lightly.$B$BThe Violet Signet will grow in power as you continue to prove yourself to the Violet Eye.' WHERE entry=10732;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You honor us with your service, $N. Behold as I unleash the power contained in your signet!' WHERE entry=10733;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You honor us with your service, $N. Behold as I unleash the power contained in your signet!' WHERE entry=10734;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You honor us with your service, $N. Behold as I unleash the power contained in your signet!' WHERE entry=10735;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You honor us with your service, $N. Behold as I unleash the power contained in your signet!' WHERE entry=10736;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Your services have not gone unnoticed, $N. Your signet may look the same, but its powers grow as you continue to prove your loyalty.' WHERE entry=10738;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Your services have not gone unnoticed, $N. Your signet may look the same, but its powers grow as you continue to prove your loyalty.' WHERE entry=10739;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Your services have not gone unnoticed, $N. Your signet may look the same, but its powers grow as you continue to prove your loyalty.' WHERE entry=10740;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Your services have not gone unnoticed, $N. Your signet may look the same, but its powers grow as you continue to prove your loyalty.' WHERE entry=10741;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Now it comes to this. We will bring Goc forth from his lair, and we will destroy him. With Goc dead, the Bladespire ogres will threaten the Mok\'Nathal no longer. Go to Goc\'s altar outside Gruul\'s Lair, then blow my horn. I will come, and we will face the son of Gruul together.',objectives_loc4='Use Rexxar\'s Battle Horn at the Altar of Goc, then kill Goc. Return to Rexxar at Thunderlord Village in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains when this is done.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The battle was hard and you fought well, $N. I am honored to have stood by your side in the battle against Goc. I am thankful beyond words.$B$BThe Mok\'Nathal should know of these great defeats, but I am not ready to face them yet. I know my father\'s mind, and I know my heart. There is still much I can learn and do to become stronger, to show to him that I am his true son.' WHERE entry=10742;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Kurdran listens to your report.>$B$BThat is good news, indeed! Mere days ago, I wouldn\'t have dreamt that we could break the Legion\'s siege on the stronghold.$B$BNot only have you halted their offensive, but you\'ve broken the back of their war machine as well! You have the gratitude of the Wildhammer clan for your valor, $N.' WHERE entry=10744;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You must bring word of our success to Overlord Or\'barokh immediately! Now that we\'ve crushed the Legion and obliterated their presence in Shadowmoon Valley, the overlord can turn his attention to our other foes.$B$BAlthough the Kor\'kron guard will never admit it, they\'ll be glad we\'re no longer fighting on two fronts.',objectives_loc4='Return to Shadowmoon Village and speak with Overlord Or\'barokh.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<The overlord listens to your report.>$B$BExcellent news! Holding the line against the Legion\'s infernals was taking too many resources. Not that I expected my men to break, but they were greatly strained.$B$BYou have proven your worth to the Horde this day. The Kor\'kron guard would be honored to fight by your side anytime.' WHERE entry=10745;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='DEPRECATED Karazhan: LAB - E - Exalted Ring - Caster' WHERE entry=10746;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Samia Inkling has asked you to use the Blackwhelp Net to capture 10 Wyrmcult Blackwhelps.  Return them to her at Evergrove in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh my goodness, these are more than I\'d hoped for! You are certainly to be lauded for your heroics!$B$BThis looks like a fine brood of blackwhelps to make a start with. Examining them, that is.$B$BPlease, accept this as payment. I insist!' WHERE entry=10747;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='On behalf of the Cenarion Expedition druids of Evergrove, and the indigenous life of the Ruuan Weald, Tree Warden Chawn has asked you to slay Maxnar the Ashmaw.  Return to him at Evergrove in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains after you have done so.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Now we can breathe more easily knowing that the leader of our enemy has been dealt with. Not only that, but you\'ve saved the entire mountain range from their depredations.$B$BWhatever their ultimate goals, you\'ve foiled them!$B$BYou have our gratitude, $N. Please accept this token of our esteem, as well as our unending hospitality.' WHERE entry=10748;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This is unsavory business, this use of poisons. But it will do what we want.' WHERE entry=10749;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Travel to the Path of Conquest in Shadowmoon Valley. Once you have done a preliminary assessment of the area, use the Kor\'kron Flare Gun to signal a Kor\'kron Wind Rider.$B$BSpeak with Overlord Or\'barokh should you lose your Kor\'kron Flare Gun and require a replacement.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Indeed, these troublesome whelps are up to something insidious. We must investigate further...' WHERE entry=10750;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Slay 20 Eclipsion Soldiers, 10 Eclipsion Cavaliers, and 10 Eclipsion Spellbinders and then use the Kor\'kron Flare Gun to signal another Kor\'kron Wind Rider to report your task complete.$B$BSpeak with Overlord Or\'barokh at Shadowmoon Village in Shadowmoon Valley should you lose your Kor\'kron Flare Gun and require a replacement.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You won\'t believe this, grunt.' WHERE entry=10751;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So Thundris Windweaver still thinks I need looking after? I\'ll need to remind him who saved whom; he seems to forget it was I that pulled him from harm\'s way.$B$BWell now that you\'re here, $R, perhaps I can find something for you to do.' WHERE entry=10752;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Kill 4 Felsworn Scalewing, 4 Felsworn Daggermaw, and 2 Fel Corrupters.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I do not pride myself knowing we destroyed what Elune has created, but the corruption needed to be stopped. You have done well $C.' WHERE entry=10753;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Could this be?  Let me take a closer look at that mold.' WHERE entry=10754;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A key mold? Could this be what grants us access to the Shattered Halls?' WHERE entry=10755;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring the Primed Key Mold to Rohok in Thrallmar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Nazgrel wants me to work on a key? Does he forget we\'re in a battlefield? There are blades and spears to forge!' WHERE entry=10756;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent. Let\'s give it a shot.' WHERE entry=10757;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve succeeded! Only thing left for you to do is try it out.' WHERE entry=10758;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The arakkoa cackles.>$B$BYes, I am the deserter mentioned in the commander\'s journal. I have been waiting for the day when others might recognize the threat posed by those I once called brothers.' WHERE entry=10759;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The Sketh\'lon Wreckage, just to the east, is an eerie place. The peons are convinced that it\'s cursed.$B$BThere are few trees here, so the peons have no choice but to venture into the arakkoa ruins to chop wood. The arakkoa spirits prey on the work groups, draining their life and using it to fuel their foul magics.$B$BWe must find out what is driving the dark conclave and stop them before their influence expands. Search the Sketh\'lon Wreckage for evidence of their plans.',objectives_loc4='Recover the Skethlon Commander\'s Journal Page 1, Skethlon Commander\'s Journal Page 2, and Skethlon Commander\'s Journal Page 3 from the Dark Conclave arakkoa at the Sketh\'lon Wreckage to Sergeant Kargrul at Shadowmoon Village.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I don\'t see much of use here, but there are a couple of entries that could prove useful. It looks as though these arakkoa were preparing some kind of elaborate magical ritual up until the time of their deaths, but why? There\'s also a curious note here about a \'deserter.\'' WHERE entry=10760;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='There\'s nothing here that would explain why the spirits of these arakkoa have remained in this world or how they came into thirst for the blood of orcs.$B$BI think our best lead is to try to find the deserter mentioned in the journal. If he left his comrades at the camp, there\'s a chance you might be able to persuade him to help us understand what the dark conclave arakkoa are planning.$B$BStart your search for him on the road through the Magma Fields to the southeast.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<The arakkoa cackles.>$B$BYes, I am the deserter mentioned in the commander\'s journal. I have been waiting for the day when others might recognize the threat posed by those I once called brothers.' WHERE entry=10761;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A key? Danath should have us working on siege engines!' WHERE entry=10762;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Let\'s try it then. Let\'s see what fel orc crafting is all about.' WHERE entry=10763;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='It\'s not working, $G lad : lass;.  I cannot give it enough heat... the materials will not be properly tempered.$B$BYou know, the Fel Reavers used by the Burning Legion are powered by a scalding core of fel fire - it burns much hotter than normal fire.$B$BIf you could find enough people to take one down, you could heat the mold in the insides of the fallen reaver.  Beware, $C, those fel reavers pack quite a punch.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done it, laddie!  Only thing left to do is for you to take it to Hellfire Citadel and kill yourself some orcs!' WHERE entry=10764;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Slay Chancellor Bloodleaf and Corok the Mighty and recover Illidan\'s Command. Use the Kor\'kron Flare Gun to signal another Kor\'kron Wind Rider once you have accomplished this task.$B$BSpeak with Overlord Or\'barokh at Shadowmoon Village in Shadowmoon Valley should you lose your Kor\'kron Flare Gun and require a replacement.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So they are attempting to gain the favor of the giants. eh? I have a plan that promises to sever this unholy union.' WHERE entry=10765;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Pleased to meet you, $N. Name\'s Plexi.$B$BI won\'t bore you with formalities. We both know why we\'re here. Now, let\'s get to work.' WHERE entry=10766;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Now that we have access to the Legion\'s base at Invasion Point: Cataclysm, we need to figure out a way to shut down their operations there. Shadowmoon Village won\'t be safe until the Legion\'s presence is erased from the valley.$B$BI\'ve sent an advance party up to the invasion point to help you formulate a plan to destroy the Legion\'s supplies. Go back to Legion Hold and step into the teleporter with the green crystals above it. Nakansi will meet you at your destination.',objectives_loc4='Report to Nakansi at Invasion Point: Cataclysm.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You must be the $R Blood Guard Gulmok told me to expect. I have a plan in mind, but I\'ll need your help to complete the preparations.' WHERE entry=10767;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Collect 10 Illidari Tabards and then use the Kor\'kron Flare Gun to signal another Kor\'kron Wind Rider.$B$BSpeak with Overlord Or\'barokh at Shadowmoon Village in Shadowmoon Valley should you lose your Kor\'kron Flare Gun and require a replacement.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah-ha! These will do quite nicely.' WHERE entry=10768;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, well, well... If it isn\'t the grunt I sent out into the field. You\'re back and in one piece.$B$B<Or\'barokh nods.>$B$BI knew you wouldn\'t let me down, soldier. You\'ve stopped a major Illidari advance and, in doing so, earned yourself a little reward.' WHERE entry=10769;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='There are so many that we can never kill them all, but you have given me hope.  Perhaps I shall try a little harder for another few centuries to revive my beloved wood.' WHERE entry=10770;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You destroyed many of those foul little creatures.  I can rest easier knowing that so many were destroyed.' WHERE entry=10771;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Travel to the Path of Conquest in Shadowmoon Valley. Once you have done a preliminary assessment of the area, use the Wildhammer Flare Gun to signal a Wildhammer Gryphon Rider.$B$BSpeak with Thane Yoregar at Wildhammer Stronghold in Shadowmoon Valley should you lose your Wildhammer Flare Gun and require a replacement.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Indeed, these troublesome whelps are up to something insidious. We must investigate further...' WHERE entry=10772;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Slay 20 Eclipsion Soldiers, 10 Eclipsion Cavaliers, and 5 Sons of Corok and then use the Wildhammer Flare Gun to signal another Wildhammer Gryphon Rider to report your task complete.$B$BSpeak with Thane Yoregar at Wildhammer Stronghold in Shadowmoon Valley should you lose your Wildhammer Flare Gun and require a replacement.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You won\'t believe this, soldier!' WHERE entry=10773;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Slay Chancellor Bloodleaf and Corok the Mighty and recover Illidan\'s Command. Use the Wildhammer Flare Gun to signal another Wildhammer Gryphon Rider once you have accomplished this task.$B$BSpeak with Thane Yoregar at Wildhammer Stronghold in Shadowmoon Valley should you lose your Wildhammer Flare Gun and require a replacement.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So they are attempting to gain the favor of the giants, eh? I have a plan that could serve to sever this unholy union.' WHERE entry=10774;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Collect 10 Illidari Tabards and then use the Wildhammer Flare Gun to signal another Wildhammer Gryphon Rider.$B$BSpeak with Thane Yoregar at Wildhammer Stronghold in Shadowmoon Valley should you lose your Wildhammer Flare Gun and require a replacement.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah-ha! These will do quite nicely.' WHERE entry=10775;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, well, well... If it isn\'t the soldier I sent out into the field. You\'re back and in one piece.$B$B<Yoregar nods.>$B$BI knew you wouldn\'t let me down, soldier. You\'ve stopped a major Illidari advance and, in doing so, earned yourself a little reward.' WHERE entry=10776;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Parshah examines the totem.>$B$BGood. This old totem hasn\'t lost its power over the years, but it alone is not enough to stop the dark conclave.' WHERE entry=10777;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done. Such a treasure deserves better than to be shut away in a dark chest. We shall see it used for a worthy purpose.' WHERE entry=10778;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Hello, young hunter. You look to me like you are skilled enough to handle a beast and train it as your companion.$B$BYou must see Huntress Kella Nightbow at LOCATION. She can put you on the path to earning a pet of your own.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Huntress Kella Nightbow at LOCATION.' WHERE entry=10779;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Parshah accepts the ash-dusted feathers, shaking his head.>$B$BIt would\'ve been better if they had died that day, but nothing is ever that simple. That Gul\'dan\'s magic would turn them into the kind of threat they tried to stop is a particularly cruel twist of fate.' WHERE entry=10780;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This Crimson Sigil will be investigated. They pose a threat to all life on Draenor. I foresee a day when their dark master has to answer for his crimes. Perhaps it will be you who brings him to justice, hero.' WHERE entry=10781;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Equip the Unfinished Headpiece, travel to the Altar of Damnation, and use it while standing near Gul\'dan. When the headpiece is energized, return to Parshah in the Magma Fields.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Parshah accepts the headpiece, handing it gingerly.>$B$BThis holds the power that we\'ll need to disrupt the dark conclave\'s efforts in the Sketh\'lon Base Camp.' WHERE entry=10782;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hello, $R. I am Baron Sablemane. A friend of Rexxar\'s is a friend of mine.' WHERE entry=10783;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Tor\'chunk Twoclaws has asked you to slay 10 Bloodmaul Maulers and 5 Bloodmaul Warlocks.  Afterward, return to him at Thunderlord Stronghold in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Tor\'chunk nods his head in obvious approval of your killing prowess.>$B$BYou continue to impress me, $N. Every time one of those stinking ogres is felled, we come one step closer to ridding ourselves of an unworthy foe.' WHERE entry=10784;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='There\'s is no cause of fury greater in this world than that of Gruul and his sons. They slaughtered my people - my children - and now I will have revenge.$B$BI have fashioned a trap from dragon fire, and if you\'re clever enough, you can use it to kill even a gronn.$B$BJust hurry, take the trap to Rexxar. My thirst for revenge must be quenched.',objectives_loc4='Deliver the Dragonfire Trap to Rexxar at Thunderlord Stronghold in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Hmm, a trap fashioned from the essence of dragon fire? I wonder how Sablemane comes by such rarified substances?$B$BIt does not matter. What does matter is that we are going to use it to slay a son of Gruul.' WHERE entry=10785;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I know that Rexxar has plans for you to head to Boulder\'mok.  I have something that I want you to do while you are there.$B$BWe must take any chance we can get to strike down the ogres of these mountains, or they will overrun us, and all that we have bled and died for will be for nothing!$B$BBoulder\'mok lies far to the northwest.  Travel north to Ruuan Weald, and from there head west through the tunnel and past the Raven\'s Wood.$B$B$N, I want you to kill the Bladespire ogres of Boulder\'mok.  Wipe them out!',objectives_loc4='Slaughter 5 Boulder\'mok Brutes and 3 Boulder\'mok Shaman, and then return to Tor\'chunk Twoclaws at Thunderlord Stronghold in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Tor\'chunk grins at the story that you tell him about your adventures at Boulder\'mok.>$B$BAh, I wish that I could have been there with you. Let me tell you something, $N: never accept any duty that keeps you from the glory of battle!$B$BHah! After all of the ogre killing that you\'ve done, are there any still left in these mountains for me?!' WHERE entry=10786;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Return to Gan\'rul Bloodeye',details_loc4='You are a long way from home, $R.  Perhaps it is time you returned to learn from your master, Gan\'rul Bloodeye.  His knowledge is known to all of our craft, even those of us here.$B$BGan\'rul dwells in the Cleft of Shadow in Orgrimmar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It is the forbidden knowledge you hunger for, is it? I can give you that...' WHERE entry=10790;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hah! I could see the smoke and flames of Zeth\'Gor from here! May the Bleeding Hollow fiends burn to ash and drift far from the sight of any true orc!$B$BThank you, $N. You helped burn away an afront to every orc\'s spirit.' WHERE entry=10792;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Western Hovel Burned',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Stable Burned' WHERE entry=10792;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You slew their conqueror? Then we haven\'t much time...$B$BThe Crimson Sigil is a group comprised of Illidan\'s elite minions. They are at the top of the chain of command for all Illidari forces outside of the Black Temple. These soldiers communicate directly with the Betrayer here, carrying out his orders without question.$B$BThey are the fiends that will undoubtedly lead an assault on this world, trampling under foot all that would stand in their way.' WHERE entry=10793;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So, you want to work for the Shattered Hand? Seems like we\'re getting someone new every day.$B$BPay close attention and I\'ll explain what you have to do.' WHERE entry=10794;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Commander Haephus Stonewall has asked you to kill Dorgok at Bloodmaul Camp.  Return to him at Evergrove in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains after you have done the deed.',offerrewardtext_loc4='With Dorgok dead, the Bloodmaul ogres are without leadership, and should be in disarray until another leader arises from within their ranks.$B$BThank you, $C, I think we can breathe a little easier now.' WHERE entry=10795;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Lieutenant Fairweather has tasked you with slaying 10 Bloodmaul Maulers and 5 Bloodmaul Warlocks.  Afterward, return to her at Evergrove in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<The lieutenant nods her head in obvious approval of your killing prowess.>$B$BI am impressed, $N. Your reputation seems to be well-deserved.$B$BEvery time one of the ogres is felled, we come one step closer to ridding ourselves of a danger that has no intention of leaving us in peace.' WHERE entry=10796;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh, now that\'s pretty. Looks a lot like those gronn that are always bossing the Bladespire ogres around.$B$BOdd that you should find it in the hands of one of the Bloodmaul leaders.' WHERE entry=10797;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Speak with Baron Sablemane about fashioning a trap.  He is located at the Circle of Blood in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, an envoy from the vaunted Alliance. Tell me, lackey, why is it that you are here, begging me for this thing, instead of your illustrious commander?$B$BCould it be that he is afraid of me? It says something about you that you are not, but I haven\'t quite decided yet what that is.' WHERE entry=10798;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Baron Sablemane has told you to bring him 7 Crust Burster Venom Glands.  Return to him at the Circle of Blood in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains once you have procured them.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Very well. A simple, if mundane, task has been completed. Now, hand me the glands and I will perform the difficult part.' WHERE entry=10799;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Baron Sablemane wants you to steal Grulloc\'s Sack, and then return it to him at the Circle of Blood in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Baron Sablemane peers inside the gronn\'s sack and seems satisfied.>$B$BVery well, you have upheld your end of the bargain. And now, I will gift your Commander Stonewall with the trap.' WHERE entry=10800;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hmm, a trap fashioned from the essence of dragon flame? I wonder how Sablemane comes by such rarified substances?$B$BIt does not matter. What does matter is that we are going to use it to slay a son of Gruul!' WHERE entry=10801;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Go to Boulder\'mok and collect 3 Grisly Totems from the Boulder\'mok ogres. Use Sablemane\'s Trap at Gorgrom\'s Altar to summon and kill Gorgrom the Dragon-Eater.$B$BWhen Gorgrom is dead, place the 3 Grisly Totems near his corpse, then return to Commander Haephus Stonewall at Evergrove in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. Well done!$B$BI suspect we will hear little more from the ogres and their master.' WHERE entry=10802;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Slaughter 5 Boulder\'mok Brutes and 3 Boulder\'mok Shaman, and then return to Lieutenant Fairweather at Evergrove in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Lieutenant Fairweather grins at the story that you tell her about your adventures at Boulder\'mok.>$B$BAh, I wish that I could have been there with you. Let me tell you something, $N: never accept any duty that keeps you from the glory of the battlefield!$B$BHah! After all of the ogre killing that you\'ve done, are there any still left in these mountains for me?!' WHERE entry=10803;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are a kind and compassionate $R, friend.' WHERE entry=10804;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Baron Sablemane has tasked you and your friends with the deaths of 10 Bladespire Enforcers, 5 Bladespire Battlemages, 5 Bladespire Ravagers and their leader, Fingrom.  When you have managed this feat, return to him at the Circle of Blood in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Very well, I chose wisely when I selected you to spearhead my fight. Time to ramp things up to a whole new level, I think.$B$BYou remember that little goodie that you stole for me out from underneath Grulloc\'s nose? You\'re going to get a chance to put it to good use.' WHERE entry=10805;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Use Sablemane\'s Signet at the Altar of Goc, then kill Goc. Return to Baron Sablemane at the Circle of Blood in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains when this is done.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You fought surprisingly well for a $R, and it was an honor to have you at my side. My transformation must have been quite a surprise for you. I trust it was not too startling?$B$BLet us keep my true identity between the two of us for now, shall we? In return, and for your adept service, I grant you your choice of any of these baubles.' WHERE entry=10806;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Glory to the Scryers, $N. You\'ve done the Seer\'s bidding by defeating those who follow Illidan.' WHERE entry=10807;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I have sought a way to stop the dark conclave for years, and you have succeeded where I failed. The conclave\'s dark rituals will threaten us no more.$B$BI often feel guilty for abandoning my fellows all those years ago, but now I finally know that I made the right decision. If not for my wavering conscience then, I might have ended up as a shade among them.' WHERE entry=10808;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, so you slew that villain, Kruush! Well done, $N! Well done! His death will defang those cursed worg riders. In fact, I hope you took a few of them out during your foray into Zeth\'Gor!$B$BHere\'s your reward. You earned every piece of it!' WHERE entry=10809;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring the Damaged Mask to O\'Mally Zapnabber in Ruuan Weald.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, what\'s that you have? Let me take a closer look, $C. Yes, yes... it\'s just what I thought it was. Here, let me fix this mask for you.' WHERE entry=10810;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='My children have told me of your heroic deeds, $R. There is more that you can do.' WHERE entry=10811;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring the Mystery Mask to Wildlord Antelarion in Ruuan Weald.',offerrewardtext_loc4='That mask you hold in your hands is a Felsworn gas mask and by the appearance, it\'s not damaged. The trouble we can cause Forge Camp: Anger is boundless. Are you interested in helping us out, $N?' WHERE entry=10812;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I am indebted to you, $N. You have again braved Zeth\'Gor and held its darkness close to your heart. I will study the eye and perhaps pierce the secrets of its master, Grillok.$B$BLet us hope that he can no longer use its magic!' WHERE entry=10813;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So you will help us?' WHERE entry=10814;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work, $C. May the Light continue to protect you.' WHERE entry=10816;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve gained my utmost respect today, $N.$B$BSlaying one fel orc is not an easy task. Massacring a score of them is, well... heroic.' WHERE entry=10817;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='You have received an invitation to speak again with Baron Sablemane on some matter of import.  Go to him at the Circle of Blood in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, I see that you decided to take your sweet time answering my summons.$B$BNo matter, I have plenty of time to exact my revenge, and I intend for you to be my proxy in the coming battle!' WHERE entry=10818;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I have a very special mission for you, $N. I need you to infiltrate Forge Camp: Anger east of here. When you enter the camp you will need to wear the Felsworn gas mask and locate the Legion communicator. Once you have located the communication device speak with whomever is on the other side of the device.$B$BIf all works out you can trick the demon into something devious! Try telling the demon that camp anger has revolted.$B$BGood luck to you $C.',objectives_loc4='Wear the Felsworn Gas Mask and use the Legion Communicator at Forge Camp: Anger.',offerrewardtext_loc4='What\'s the meaning of this! No one summons me! Speak, or I will silence you forever!' WHERE entry=10819;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Kill 4 Doomforge Attendants and 4 Doomforge Engineers.',offerrewardtext_loc4='That will surely teach those that don\'t do as I say...$B$BBy the way... where is Doomcryer? Why have you reported this revolt to me and not she?' WHERE entry=10820;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Kill Doomcryer and report back to Wildlord Antelarion in Evergrove.',offerrewardtext_loc4='That is great news, great news indeed $N. I could not have asked for a better outcome. Your service to our people is most greatly appreciated, choose one of the following heroic items.$B$BYour name will forever be remembered in our peoples heart.' WHERE entry=10821;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Kael\'s army will soon fall.' WHERE entry=10822;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent! That\'ll show Kael\'thas not to underestimate our power.' WHERE entry=10823;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Kael\'s elves are extremely well-trained. Excellent job.' WHERE entry=10824;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Deliver the Orb of the Grishna to Tree Warden Chawn at Ruuan Weald in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes, it\'s that orb you have there!  Odd, it appears to be of arakkoan design.  Were you recently at Grishnath?$B$BAll right, that explains that, but I wonder what diabolical purpose this object serves.  Though it radiates evil, it also somehow feels as if it were connected to the natural world as well.$B$BHere, allow me to try activate it.  The evil is so strong within it, there\'s some sort of residual memory here....' WHERE entry=10825;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Your courage is strong, friend. Let it be known to all that you are a true ally of the priesthood!' WHERE entry=10826;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You continue to prove your worth, $N.  Fight the enemies of the Light wherever you may find them; your actions will be well-rewarded.' WHERE entry=10827;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You continue to prove your worth, $N.  Fight the enemies of the Light wherever you may find them; your actions will be well-rewarded.' WHERE entry=10828;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Tree Warden Chawn has asked you to seek out and speak with Treebole, an ancient of lore who lives in the Raven\'s Wood of the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Greetings, tiny $R. The birds in my boughs whispered to me that you were to be expected.$B$BYou are here to help free the trees of the woods from their possession?' WHERE entry=10829;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Collect 5 Grishnath Orbs and 5 Dire Pinfeathers and then combine them into Exorcism Feathers.  Use these feathers to exorcise and slay 5 Koi-Koi Spirits from the Raven\'s Wood Leafbeards.  Once you\'ve done this, return to Treebole in the Raven\'s Wood of the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The evil is lifting from the Raven\'s Wood!  Can you feel it, $N?$B$BYou have saved us, and all of the surrounding wildlife, from certain destruction, little one!$B$BI keep stashed four magic rings amongst my boughs for such occasions as this, when a hero arises to do some great deed.$B$BYou are one such hero!  On behalf of all of the Raven\'s Wood, we give you thanks.' WHERE entry=10830;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Grillok Darkeye has wagered a piece of himself to dark powers, and gained great magic for it.  His lost eye burns deep in some hellish pit, now a demon\'s trinket... and the patch that covers his betrayal holds its own dark secrets.$B$BBring me Grillok\'s eyepatch, $N, and I will reward you greatly for your service...',objectives_loc4='Kill Grillok Darkeye and bring Grillok\'s Eyepatch to Zezzak in Spinebreaker Post.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, yes. Just as some who lost a hand or a leg in battle will oftentimes feel their severed limb, I wonder if Grillok still clutched at his lost eye in his dark, dark dreams...$B$BI too will dream on this, and if fortune is with us then perhaps I will learn what drew Grillok and the Bleeding Hollow orcs to succumb to demons.' WHERE entry=10834;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring Albreck\'s Findings to Apothecary Antonivich in Thrallmar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, a report from Albreck? Very good. The Royal Apothecary Society works feverishly to determine how the orcs of Hellfire Peninsula became fel orcs. Their betrayal is unforgivable... and we must ensure that our orc friends are forever safe from future corruption.' WHERE entry=10835;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. I have discovered a way in which we can free the enslaved drakes that are being held at Dragonmaw Fortress.' WHERE entry=10836;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Neltharaku, flying high above Netherwing Fields in Shadowmoon Valley, wants you to collect 12 Nethervine Crystals from Netherwing Ledge.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Neltharaku takes the crystals from you.>$B$BI will prepare the crystals for you now.' WHERE entry=10837;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You obtained the reading? Excellent -- I am sure this data will prove invaluable to our research. I will disseminate it to Apothecaries Zelana and Albreck.$B$BYou should be proud, $N. Your strength and bravery is unquestionable... as is your service to the Horde.' WHERE entry=10838;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Use the Rod of Purification on the Darkstone of Terokk in Veil Skith and return to Kirrik at the Refugee Caravan in Bone Wastes.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I heard the explosion from here. Not with my ears, but with my heart.$B$BIf the touch of the blessed Naaru, A\'dal, is not enough to bring the arakkoa to redemption, nothing will be. Those who have not given themselves over to the Light are mere servants of evil.$B$BThey must be destroyed.' WHERE entry=10839;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='High Priest Orglum wants you to journey to the Tomb of Lights and kill 10 Ethereal Nethermancers and 10 Ethereal Plunderers and then return to him by the Refugee Caravan.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Out here in the wilds of Outland we are weak with few heroes to defend our rights, but you have given them something to fear $C. I do not think the ethereals will soon forget the strong right arm of $N.' WHERE entry=10840;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The Tomb of Lights has become corrupted by the Shadow Council and the draenei dead have become cursed spirits, angry and confused with a burning hatred for the living.$B$BEnter the tomb and seek out these tragic victims. Give them the rest that they deserve.',objectives_loc4='High Priest Orglum wants you to journey into the Tomb of Lights and defeat 5 Vengeful Draenei.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You cannot know what you have done here $N. You have saved so many of us from an eternity of darkness. There is little that I can do for the living and nothing that I could give that would thank you enough. Take what seems useful to you.' WHERE entry=10842;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='In order to prove yourself to the Mok\'Nathal, Leoroxx has ordered you to slay Gnosh Brognat, leader of the ogres at the Bladespire Outpost.  Return to Leoroxx at Mok\'Nathal Village in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains after you have done so, or do not return at all.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Leoroxx appraises you with a keen eye, seemingly trying to take your measure.>$B$BThe death of Gnosh Brognat is a boon to all of the Mok\'Nathal.  This is a good thing for you.$B$BLet us see if we can push the boundaries of your prowess just a bit more.' WHERE entry=10843;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Leoroxx has challenged you to slay Dreadwing.  Return to him at Mok\'Nathal Village once you have managed to kill her.',offerrewardtext_loc4='No?  You slew Dreadwing?  Perhaps I was wrong about you, $C.$B$BPerhaps.$B$BStill, you have slain the chiefs of the three greatest threats that we face.  That is something to be proud of.$B$BI offer you a token of my appreciation, but don\'t let it go to your head.  You still do not fully understand what it is to be Mok\'Nathal, and we may still have need to call upon your skills.' WHERE entry=10845;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='To begin your understanding of the Mok\'Nathal, slay Vekh, leader of the Vekh\'nir arakkoa.  Then, return to Leoroxx at Mok\'Nathal Village in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The Vekh\'nir are the least of our adversaries.$B$BSo, you know how to slay an overgrown bird.  This does not make you a true warrior.  This does not give you a full understanding of our ways.$B$BBut it\'s a start.' WHERE entry=10846;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring the Eye of Reskk and the Eye of Shienor to Rilak the Redeemed in the Lower City district of Shattrath.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Your bravery should be commended. The guardians of Skettis do not part with their belongings willingly.$B$BBut heroics of the past are of little consequence now. We shall see if such bravery continues to persist in the future, for Terokk\'s gaze fixates on the south.$B$BThese Eyes are all seeing.' WHERE entry=10847;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Kill 4 Deathtalon Spirits, 4 Screeching Spirits and 2 Spirit Ravens and return to Kirrik at the Refugee Caravan.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Those foul spirits deserved to die. The death they would have wrought on others is reason enough.$B$BWe cannot hope to redeem those in Terokk\'s grasp. But we shall deliver them a devastating blow in the name of the Light.' WHERE entry=10848;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Take Rilak\'s Missive to Kirrik at the Refugee Caravan in the Bone Wastes.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Rilak\'s tale is grim, traveler. As you can see from the state of the caravan, there is much sorrow and darkness in the forest of Terokk these days.' WHERE entry=10849;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The fel reaver\'s engine begins to rumble and sputter as you supply it with the incorrect fuel.' WHERE entry=10850;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Collect 5 Bladespire Totems for Spiritcaller Dohgar at Mok\'Nathal Village in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='This looks like a good assortment.  We should be able to find a respectful use for one or two of them.$B$BIn fact, I have an idea for how to do just that!' WHERE entry=10851;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You found all my friends!  Now I have someone to play with.  Thank you, Mister $N.  $B$BSince I have kids to play with maybe you would like one of my toys?  That way you have something to play with too.' WHERE entry=10852;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Spiritcaller Dohgar has asked you to use the Spirit Calling Totems to collect 8 Lesser Nether Drake Spirits and return them to him at Mok\'Nathal Village in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done a good thing this day, $C.  The spirits of the drakes will truly sing again now that they have been freed.  And the residual part of their spirits that they leave behind are powerful medicine, too.$B$BI wonder, are you up for a journey to the north?  There is something that I am curious about concerning the activities of the ethereal.$B$BI sense a great deal of pain coming from their direction.' WHERE entry=10853;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Neltharaku laughs.>$B$BThe orcs must have been shocked to see the drakes turn on them in such a manner. Well done, $N. Perhaps you truly are the hero of our flight.' WHERE entry=10854;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That is excellent news, $N. Now that we know how to deal with these, I can have hirelings sabotage any remaining reavers.' WHERE entry=10855;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Nice work, $N. Keep it up and I\'ll put in a good word with the Nexus Prince.' WHERE entry=10856;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='As fun as killing demons might be, it does us little good when the Legion can keep using its teleporters to replace anything we kill.$B$BUnfortunately, I don\'t have any high-powered explosives handy... but the mo\'arg that maintain the teleporters do.$B$BTake this rod... I\'ve tuned its powers to interfere with mo\'arg brain frequencies.  Return to Forge Base: Gehenna and use it on any Mo\'arg you see.  You won\'t have long, but you\'ll be able to use their demolition charges on the nearby teleporters.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Thanks to you, $N, I\'ll breathe a little easier. Figure of speech, of course!$B$BI suppose you\'ll want some form of reward now.' WHERE entry=10857;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='It shames me to ask for your assistance once more, $N, but you are my flight\'s only hope. Without my mate, the netherwing brood may die out completely.$B$BMake your way to the top of Dragonmaw Fortress and find Karynaku.$B$BWe will be flying overhead. Should a break appear in their defenses, the might of the netherwing will swoop down to assist you.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='It is the chains. They sap my power. The only way is to get the key from Zuluhed and unbind me.' WHERE entry=10858;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The Razaani ethereals have strange devices that emit small, pink floating light orbs.  They remind me of souls.$B$BThey are not to be confused with the large yellow balls that break free of the ethereal when they die, these are something else entirely.$B$BI\'d like for you to head north to Razaan\'s Landing and drop some totems, which will attact the pink light orbs.$B$BBring them back to me so that I might determine exactly what they are.',objectives_loc4='Spiritcaller Dohgar has asked you to use the Orb Collecting Totem to collect 15 Razaani Light Orbs.  Return to him at Mok\'Nathal Village in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains after you have done so.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Something does not feel right.$B$BPlease, $N, hand me the totem. I must examine those orbs!' WHERE entry=10859;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Matron Varah has given you a list of ingredients for the making of her two favorite dishes, which includes the collection of 3 Raptor Ribs and 3 Serpent Flesh.  Bring them to her at Mok\'Nathal Village in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Mmm, I can taste them already.  Quickly, hand over those parts... I\'m going to get them diced up and onto the fire!$B$BLuckily for you, this stuff keeps, and I mean for a long time!  So, take these, and I suppose you can have the recipes as well for being so kind as to restock my larder.' WHERE entry=10860;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Break the cursed eggs in Veil Lithic. Redeem 3 Hatchlings and slay 3 Malevolent Hatchlings before returning to Kirrik at the Refugee Caravan.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It is grim work toiling with someone\'s hatchlings, yet ignoring the brewing evil would be a bleak proposition as well. You have done well. A\'dal\'s favor shines upon your heart.' WHERE entry=10861;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Rokag wants you to seek out Rilak the Redeemed in Shattrath and demand that he and his people surrender to the Horde.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Your people are angry but there is little I can do. Some of us have been touched by the power of the naaru and we are forever changed. Those of us who remain in the wild are as we have always been.' WHERE entry=10862;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Lady Dena Kennedy wants you to seek out Rilak the Redeemed in Shattrath and find out what secrets he will share of the Arakkoa.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You are wise to find me. There is much that I can show you.' WHERE entry=10863;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. Your soul is burdened with many deaths... and the Demonaic Scryer will now perform its duties for you.$B$BLet us hope you are ready for the coming trial...' WHERE entry=10864;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Spiritcaller Dohgar has implored you to inform Leoroxx about what the Razaani ethereal are up to.  He can be found at Mok\'Nathal Village in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='What you say, is it even possible? What am I saying? Of course it is, if the spiritcallers say so.$B$BRemember before when I said that we might need your further assistance? It would seem that I can tell the future.' WHERE entry=10865;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I am free! You have saved us, $N!' WHERE entry=10866;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Leoroxx has beseeched you to retrieve the Collection of Souls and return them to Spiritcaller Dohgar at Mok\'Nathal Village in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Good that the ethereal filth and their leader are dead. I wish a thousand plagues upon their brethren!$B$BYou are to be rewarded for you actions on behalf of all of the Mok\'Nathal, $N! You are truly one of our heroes.$B$BLet us now release the souls of our ancestors to the cleansing fire.' WHERE entry=10867;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done $C. The arakkoa have learned to fear the might of the Alliance.' WHERE entry=10869;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have proven yourself as an ally of the Netherwing. My mother is free and my brothers and sisters are saved! $B$BPerhaps someday, we will call for you again. When that day comes, know that you will be welcomed with open arms - a brother to the Netherwing Dragonflight.' WHERE entry=10870;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Our small outpost is under constant attack. Several nights ago, we were raided by the spiders of Netherweb Ridge, on the southeastern edge of the Bone Wastes. They poisoned many of our people, wrapped them in webs and carried them away. Some of our warriors took up arms and with little preparation pursued the spiders.$B$BWe have not seen the captives or our hunting parties since. We hope that some may still be alive, perhaps imprisoned by the spiders.  Our numbers are few. Will you search for our people?$B',objectives_loc4='Scout Navrin wants you to travel to the Netherweb Ridge and free 6 Webbed Sha\'tar Warriors and then return to him at Sha\'tar Outpost.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You saved so many.  I didn\'t think we would ever see them again.  We cannot thank you enough, $N.' WHERE entry=10873;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Terokk\'s perch, Skettis, looms above the Bone Wastes to the east. At the base of Skettis lies Veil Shalas, the most formidable of Terokk\'s colonies. It is through the stronghold of Veil Shalas that Terokk\'s forward Sages wage war against the Light.$B$BThe evil-doers of Shalas communicate with their master using a complex system of magical signal fires. Travel to the east, $R, and extinguish the fires. Once Veil Shalas is silenced, we can begin to plot the fall of Skettis.$B$BBut I get ahead of myself.',objectives_loc4='Kirrik at the Refugee Caravan wants you to extinguish the four signal fires of Veil Shalas.',offerrewardtext_loc4='We witnessed the cursed smoke rise from here. You are most brave. $C.' WHERE entry=10874;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Violet Fire Extinguished',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Bloodstone Fire Extinguished' WHERE entry=10874;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Speak with Nazgrel in Thrallmar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It is good to hear of all your moves against the fel orcs, $N. The apothecaries have spent much time and resources studying the cause of their corruption, and although such information in invaluable... my orc blood burns to strike a severe blow against these betrayers!$B$BListen close, and I will explain my task...' WHERE entry=10875;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Force Commander Gorax is training Shattered Hand captains at the base of Hellfire Citadel, honing them to a bloody razor\'s edge.  You must kill him, $N, for his loss would be a mighty blow to the fel orcs.$B$BHowever, that is not all you must do.$B$BTake this banner.  Place it atop Gorax\'s corpse.  Gorax\'s commander, the Hand of Kargath, must answer your challenge if he has even a drop of true orc blood within him!$B$BHis head, the head of the hand of Kargath, is what I seek.',objectives_loc4='Kill Force Commander Gorax, place the Challenge From the Horde upon his corpse, kill The Hand of Kargath, and then bring the Head of the Hand of Kargath to Nazgrel in Thrallmar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done a great deed, $N. The fel orcs are a shame to all true orcs. If we have one fear, it is the fear of succumbing to demonic corruption once again. So you see, our war against the fel orcs is more than merely a battle with fierce foes -- it is also a battle within ourselves.$B$BAnd with strength, strength you have shown time again, it is a battle we will win.' WHERE entry=10876;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It is incredible that you succeeded.  The Dread Relic is far more powerful than I feared. Only a mighty hero could have survived the long journey back carrying such blasphemous evil.' WHERE entry=10877;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Mekeda at the Refugee Caravan in Terokkar Forest wants you to kill 8 Cabal Skirmishers, 4 Cabal Spell-Weavers and 2 Cabal Initiates.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I can breath a sigh of relief for now, $N. The Shadow Council will be held off for the time being.$B$BThey are murderers and cowards and your display of courage will keep them at bay.' WHERE entry=10878;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Skettis has waged war on us! Have you gathered enough to help with Shattrath\'s defense?$B$BHold off the attackers!',objectives_loc4='Hold off the attackers and speak with Rilak.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I applaud your prowess in combat, $C. You have proven yourself to be a true defender of the Light. May A\'dal\'s blessing shine upon your darkest hours.$B$BBut look far into the horizon. Dark skies loom above Skettis. Terokk is undoubtedly plotting his next move. Shattrath is safe for now. But only tomorrow knows what terror will descend upon us.' WHERE entry=10879;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring the Cabal Orders to Mekeda at the Refugee Caravan in Terokkar Forest.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, yes... this was written in a basic form of the shadow cypher.  My knowledge of it is not perfect but it should suffice to translate this.$B$BYou learn much about unsavory subjects when you live among outcasts and refugees in the Lower City.' WHERE entry=10880;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Light might have forgotten me, but I have not forgotten the Light. These relics were once very sacred to my people.$B$BAllowing the Shadow Council to use their power for evil is... unthinkable!' WHERE entry=10881;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Once again you have proven your mettle. Had Harbinger Skyriss broken free, countless thousands would have perished in the ensuing conflict, just as happened with another servant of the Old Gods, Skeram, on your world of Azeroth.$B$B$N, what I have to offer in return may seem a pittance in comparison, but know that it comes with the everlasting gratitude of the Sha\'tar.' WHERE entry=10882;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You have proven yourself capable of great feats, $N. Your discovery of the Cipher of Damnation and Kael\'Thas\' involvement is most important to our cause. Should Kael use the cipher, what little is left of this world may collapse.$B$BA\'dal is convinced that Kael must be stopped and now seeks adventurers willing to undergo trials. Those that prove their strength will be granted favor by the naaru.$B$B<Khadgar nods.>$B$BA\'dal awaits...$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Tempest Keep is a naaru creation, mortal. Access to the vessel has always been within our power to grant. A return to Tempest Keep, though, had been deemed unnecessary. A point of pride for a mortal race, perhaps, but naaru invest little in such things.$B$BWe go now because we must. Kael\'thas cannot be allowed to utter the words of damnation.$B$BWhile the way is open, only a fool would enter unproven. Do not underestimate the purpose of the trials, mortal.' WHERE entry=10883;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Four trials you must pass before you are deemed worthy by the naaru.$B$BWithin the Shattered Halls of Hellfire Citadel are three of your people. They are held there by the merciless one, Kargath Bladefist. He seeks to execute them as a sign of his virility and power. You must save these prisoners before such an atrocity can come to pass. As proof of deed, bring me the unused axe of the executioner. It must not have a drop of blood on its blade!
',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. You have passed the trial of mercy.' WHERE entry=10884;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. You have passed the trial of strength.' WHERE entry=10885;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. You have passed the trial of tenacity.' WHERE entry=10886;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Help Akuno find his way to the Refugee Caravan in Terokkar Forest.  Speak to Mekeda after you\'ve completed this quest.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You rescued Akuno, a dear friend of mine. For this I am in your debt, $N.' WHERE entry=10887;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have proven yourself as a being of great power. The naaru grant you access to Tempest Keep.' WHERE entry=10888;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Travel to Shattrath City and speak with Rilak.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The guardians of Skettis grow restless from their perch. Shattrath is in trouble. We will surely feel the brunt of Terokk\'s revenge.$B$BMuster a defense party quickly! Speak with Defender Grashna and let him know you are ready to bear arms against our attackers!' WHERE entry=10889;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Eliminate Draaca Longtail, the leader of the wyrmcultists in Wyrmskull Tunnel.  Report back to Watcher Moonshade at the Wyrmskull Tunnel in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains once you have done so.',offerrewardtext_loc4='With Draaca out of the picture, we should be able to take advantage of the situation.  They\'ll be in-fighting over who should be in charge, and that will relieve some of the pressure.$B$BThat is, unless the overseer mentioned in that note you gave me comes to take her place.$B$BLet\'s see if you can do something to make sure that never happens!' WHERE entry=10893;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s as I thought, and that\'s not good!$B$BI\'ve got an idea for how to help you, but first, I was wondering if you might help us out first?$B$BYou scratch my back, I\'ll scratch yours.' WHERE entry=10894;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I could see the smoke and flames from here! Good job, $N! You received more than a few words of praise from our gryphon riders -- what you just did took a lot of guts...' WHERE entry=10895;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Forge Tower Marked',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Foothill Tower Marked' WHERE entry=10895;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The trees of this land are ravaged by the power that was unleashed from Auchindoun.  The foul magic that was unleashed blasted the land into the wastes you see all around.  The trees that survived are now infested with wretched wood mites that crawl under their bark and gnaw at their flesh.  $B$BRotting forest-rages and infested root-walkers are breeding grounds for the mites.  They are found along the edge of the wood to the east.  Destroy these creatures and then kill the mites that flee their husks.',objectives_loc4='Lakotae wants you to kill 25 wood mites and then return to him at the Refugee Caravan.  The mites can be found living inside the bodies of rotting forest-ragers and infested root-walkers.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done much to help Terokkar Forest, $N. With the worst of the mite colonies destroyed we may yet be able to reclaim this wasted land.' WHERE entry=10896;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Alas, poor Skywing was under the dreaded curse of Luanga the Imprisoner!$B$BSkywing traveled to Veil Shalas to attempt to sway others in seeing the way of the Light. They didn\'t take lightly to his actions, especially sitting on the doorstep of Skettis.$B$BLuanga was one of Terokk\'s most feared agents. You have done well by freeing Skywing! I thank you.' WHERE entry=10898;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Bring me the elemental signets that the cudgel requires!$B$BThe earthen signet is held by Gruul the Dragonkiller. Gruul can be found inside his lair in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.$B$BThe second signet is the blazing heart of a creature known as Nightbane. This mythical beast is said to reside in the hallowed halls of the prophet, Medivh.$B$BMake haste!$B',objectives_loc4='Skar\'this the Heretic in the heroic Slave Pens of Coilfang Reservoir wants you to bring him the Earthen Signet and the Blazing Signet.',offerrewardtext_loc4='At last!$B$BI have not forgotten our agreement, mortal. You too will now be able to enter the lair of Lady Vashj. Now leave me! I have much to plan.' WHERE entry=10901;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes, it is true. Colonel Jules\' situation has grown much worse these past days. Anchorite Barada is busy praying for him... let us hope he may be cured.' WHERE entry=10903;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='The Evergrove Druid has asked you to collect 5 Fel Cannonballs.  Once you have done so, use the Druid Signal to call to the Evergrove Druid inside of Death\'s Door at the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Those things stink more than I thought they would!$B$BQuickly, hand them over to me and I will imbue them with Nature\'s force such that they will prove extremely deadly to their fel masters and their unnatural creations.' WHERE entry=10904;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Kirrik the Awakened wants you to speak with Rilak the Redeemed in the Lower City district of Shattrath.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So we meet, $N. You must forgive the lack of formalities for time is of the essence.' WHERE entry=10908;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Shattered Hand orcs are foul and beyond hope, but my heart is saddened that the road to salvation for Colonel Jules holds such bloodshed.' WHERE entry=10909;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Wildlord Antelarion has implored you to travel to Death\'s Door.  Once you arrive there, use the Druid Signal to call down an Evergrove Druid so that you can speak with them.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It is a relief that Wildlord Antelarion has sent you to us. The problem is much worse than first we feared!' WHERE entry=10910;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Now that the ammunition can affect the Burning Legion, it\'s time for you to use it.$B$BThere are two warp-gates, which are used for teleportation and enhancement of the void terrors.  One is in the south and the other in the north, and each is within range of a fel cannon.$B$BUse the naturalized ammunition to take control of each fel cannon and destroy the warp-gates.$B$BAttack the gate with artillery to begin, and be prepared to kill its defenders to keep the cannon alive if necessary.',objectives_loc4='Use the Naturalized Ammunition to take control of the Death\'s Door Fel Cannons.  Use them to destroy both the South Warp-Gate and the North Warp-Gate.  Then, use the Druid Signal to call out to an Evergrove Druid to report your success.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Your prowess is staggering!$B$BVery well, with the warp-gates out of the picture, there\'s only one thing left to do.' WHERE entry=10911;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='The Evergrove Druid has told you that the final thing you must do is to slay Baelmon the Hound-Master.  Afterward, return to Evergrove in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains, and inform Wildlord Antelarion of your success.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You are truly an amazing $R! If I thought that we were indebted to you before, then now there is simply no way in which we could ever repay you.$B$BBut we\'ll give it a try. Thank you, $Ghero:heroine; of Evergrove!' WHERE entry=10912;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Commander Ra\'vaj at the Sha\'tari Outpost in the Bone Wastes of Terokkar Forest wants you to burn 8 Slain Auchenai Warriors and 8 Slain Sha\'tar Vindicators.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Commander Ra\'vaj holds his head in his hands.>$B$BIt\'s not enough... It\'s just not enough.' WHERE entry=10913;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Commander Ra\'vaj at the Sha\'tari Outpost in the Bone Wastes of Terokkar Forest wants you to slay 12 Auchenai Initiates and 5 Auchenai Doomsayers.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done it, $N! Because of you, we have made a new discovery...' WHERE entry=10914;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Commander Ra\'vaj at the Sha\'tari Outpost in the Bone Wastes of Terokkar Forest wants you to destroy the contents of the Auchenai Coffin.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Victory is ours! This defeat will set the Auchenai back several weeks.' WHERE entry=10915;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You found the prayer beads! Well done, $N. You are a wonder, indeed -- you slay the horrors of Hellfire Peninsula one moment and find lost treasures the next. Your people truly inspire!$B$BIt is good that you recovered these beads... for they will be invaluable in the exorcism ritual to come.' WHERE entry=10916;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='As an outcast, I am marked by death by arakkoa loyal to the city of Skettis.  I cannot leave these walls for fear of my life, but that doesn\'t mean I cannot strike at them in retaliation.$B$BI have a small cache of treasure that I\'m willing to part with, should you help me strike back at my would-be assassins.  Bring me feathers from the denizens of the various Veils of Terokkar as proof of their demise.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Vekax squawks in glee as you present him with proof of his enemies\' demise.>$B$BYes, that will show Skettis that we Outcasts will not take their punishment lying down. Here is the reward I promised you. I can arrange for more, should you provide me with additional feathers.' WHERE entry=10917;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Vekax squawks in glee as you present him with proof of his enemies\' demise.>$B$BYes, that will show Skettis that we Outcasts will not take their punishment lying down. Here is the reward I promised you. I can arrange for more, should you provide me with additional feathers.$B$B<This quest can be repeated up to Honored reputation.>' WHERE entry=10918;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Fei Fei barks happily and grabs the doggy treat. He looks left and right... deciding where he should hide this new treasure...>' WHERE entry=10919;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I heard the sounds of your battle from here, $C. The sounds of your victory filled my heart with hope. If you can win against such terrible odds, perhaps I can find the strength to drag my companions from this terrible place.' WHERE entry=10920;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The dreadfangs are beaten. You have killed many and even their foul mother has fallen before you. I am too poisoned to fight my way to freedom.$B$BPlease, take some of my equipment. It will lighten my load and give you the tools you need to make the journey back to Sha\'tar Outpost.' WHERE entry=10921;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Escort Letoll and his crew and protect them while they make their dig. Return to Dwarfowitz at the Sha\'tari Outpost if you succeed.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='A bone wurm! Fantastic! This may actually be the first time in recorded history that Letoll has actually made a discovery.' WHERE entry=10922;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A great evil has been cleansed from Terokkar. The Sha\'tar are in your debt.' WHERE entry=10923;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This should prove a large enough supply for my needs.$B$BI hope the imp didn\'t give you too much trouble. He has a bit of a nasty mouth on him.' WHERE entry=10924;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Vindicator Haylen wants you to return to Sha\'tari Base Camp and speak with Scout Navrin.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It is good to know that some of our warriors fought well against the dreadfang widows. We will send a rescue party immediately.' WHERE entry=10926;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Commander Skyshadow wants this tunnel cleared out so we can expedite trade with the Harborage. I must not leave my post here so I am leaving the task in your hands. Clear the tunnel and report to Commander Skyshadow at once!$B',objectives_loc4='Sentinel Moonwhisper at the tunnel between Zangarmarsh and Blade\'s Edge Mountains wants you to kill 6 Cavern Crawlers and report to Commander Skyshadow in Sylvanaar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Good work, $C. That tunnel is our lifeline to the swamp.' WHERE entry=10927;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Tor\'chunk Twoclaws wants this tunnel cleared out so we can expedite trade with Swamp Rat. I must not leave my post here so I am leaving the task in your hands. Clear the tunnel and report to Tor\'chunk Twoclaws at once!$B',objectives_loc4='Grunt Grahk at the tunnel between Zangarmarsh and Blade\'s Edge Mountains wants you to kill 6 Cavern Crawlers and report to Tor\'chunk Two-claws in Thunderlord Stronghold.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Good work, $C. That tunnel is our lifeline to the swamp.' WHERE entry=10928;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Sand gnomes? Yea, sure... The desert can do strange things to a person.$B$BI think we\'re about to make a breakthrough here with these worms!' WHERE entry=10929;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I was right! These carcasses you brought me belong to the baby bone worms. Do you know what that means? It means that somewhere out there is a big one! I think we can get it to come out if we can provide the right kind of food. Let\'s see... something big! Yes!$B$BI remember seeing clefthooves east of here on the other side of the Bone Wastes. Get out there and kill a clefthoof. Once it\'s dead, use the drums. Hopefully the big one will come up to feed. If you manage to kill it, bring me its organs!',objectives_loc4='Dwarfowitz at the Sha\'tari Base Camp in the Bone Wastes wants you to recover Enormous Bone Worm Organs.$B$BHe wants his Fumper back too.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Amazing! Look at this stuff! The thing-a-ma-whatever has some sort of dust inside its whatcha-ma-bobber. Bah! I won\'t bore you with all this scientific jargon. I did manage to pull a few teeth from the little ones to make these incredibly sharp knives. Want one?' WHERE entry=10930;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done it, $N.  You have saved Colonial Jules\' soul and cast the darkness within him back to where it came.  A great, noble deed this is!  A hero\'s day!' WHERE entry=10935;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s about time!  I heard all about what you\'ve been up to with that draenei priest. You totally freaked my messenger out!$B$BNow that you\'re done with that, I have a little mission planned for you to Hellfire Citadel.' WHERE entry=10936;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I wasn\'t going to believe it until I heard it from you, personally. Already our scouts are trickling in with information that the Shattered Hand are in disarray without their precious drillmaster to tell them what to do.$B$BYou\'ve traveled a long road, $N. I trust that you will accept this armor along with my thanks. Wear it proudly, you\'ve earned it!' WHERE entry=10937;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Now that you have gathered all of the Blessings cards together into a deck, a ninth card mysteriously appears with the same backing as the first eight.   On this card is inscribed, "Return these cards to the Darkmoon Faire and be rewarded."   You have heard that this faire alternately stops at Mulgore and Goldshire every few months, so you will have to wait until they are here next.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So you have put together a deck of Blessings. Your gesture of returning it to us will create a tie between you and the Darkmoon that will not soon be forgotten. Allow me to present you with one of the greater Darkmoon cards as a small token of our appreciation.' WHERE entry=10938;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Now that you have gathered all of the Storms cards together into a deck, a ninth card mysteriously appears with the same backing as the first eight.   On this card is inscribed, "Return these cards to the Darkmoon Faire and be rewarded."   You have heard that this faire alternately stops at Mulgore and Goldshire every few months, so you will have to wait until they are here next.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So you have put together a deck of Storms. Your gesture of returning it to us will create a tie between you and the Darkmoon that will not soon be forgotten. Allow me to present you with one of the greater Darkmoon cards as a small token of our appreciation.' WHERE entry=10939;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Now that you have gathered all of the Furies cards together into a deck, a ninth card mysteriously appears with the same backing as the first eight.   On this card is inscribed, "Return these cards to the Darkmoon Faire and be rewarded."   You have heard that this faire alternately stops at Mulgore and Goldshire every few months, so you will have to wait until they are here next.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So you have put together a deck of Furies. Your gesture of returning it to us will create a tie between you and the Darkmoon that will not soon be forgotten. Allow me to present you with one of the greater Darkmoon cards as a small token of our appreciation.' WHERE entry=10940;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Now that you have gathered all of the Lunacy cards together into a deck, a ninth card mysteriously appears with the same backing as the first eight.   On this card is inscribed, "Return these cards to the Darkmoon Faire and be rewarded."   You have heard that this faire alternately stops at Mulgore and Goldshire every few months, so you will have to wait until they are here next.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So you have put together a deck of Lunacy. Your gesture of returning it to us will create a tie between you and the Darkmoon that will not soon be forgotten. Allow me to present you with one of the greater Darkmoon cards as a small token of our appreciation.' WHERE entry=10941;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Use the Blood Elf Orphan Whistle to call for the ward that you will be looking after during Children\'s Week.' WHERE entry=10942;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Use the Draenei Orphan Whistle to call for the ward that you will be looking after during Children\'s Week.' WHERE entry=10943;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I thank you, $N.  Olum is one of my dearest friends and most trusted followers.  His contributions have been of vital importance to our plans.' WHERE entry=10944;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done well, $N. This will bring us a step closer to shifting Illidan\'s focus away from us and from...$B$B<Akama looks in Maiev Shadowsong\'s direction.>$B$BMore work remains to be done, $N.' WHERE entry=10946;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc4='Is the deed done, $N?  Illidan is not a patient master!' WHERE entry=10946;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='My vision... it all becomes clear now.  The powers this artifact has over a soul.... to contain it... to siphon it into itself... I will use those powers to reclaim what belongs to me!  The time has arrived for us to take the fight to Illidan!' WHERE entry=10947;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<A\'dal\'s light surrounds you as he welcomes you back.  You have a feeling he knows what you\'re about to ask of him.>' WHERE entry=10948;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Xi\'ri appears to acknowledge your presence.  He seems to be focused on the battle in the surrounding area.>' WHERE entry=10949;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='One of the priests that comes to visit told a story about a place nearby.  It\'s called Auchindoun, and it\'s supposed to be very important to the draenei.$B$BHe said it used to be the place where the bodies of the draenei were taken when they died.  But some time ago, something bad blew it up.$B$BI\'d like to see its Ring of Observance.  The orphan matron told me that it is in the middle of the Bone Wastes, on the south side of the Terokkar Forest.$B$BPlease, $G Mr. : Miss; $N, can we go?' WHERE entry=10950;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='How can we look at all of these interesting places and not see the Dark Portal?!$B$BThe grown-ups are always trying to tell us scary stories about it and how it\'s so dangerous, with lots of demons, and stuff.$B$B<Salandria rolls her eyes.>$B$BBut you\'re here, so it can\'t be too bad, right?$B$BI want to see for myself.  You remember where it is on the east edge of Hellfire Peninsula?',objectives_loc4='Take your orphan, Salandria, up the steps of the Stair of Destiny to stand before the Dark Portal in Hellfire Peninsula.  Make sure to call for her if she is not present when you arrive.' WHERE entry=10951;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Before all of the druidic orders coalesced into the Cenarion Circle, the Druids of the Talon were responsible for teaching promising young druids the mysteries of flight. With the dissolution of the order, former members teach the skill sparingly.$B$BEven now, Morthis Whisperwing continues his search for a suitable apprentice. Few druids have truly mastered all the forms available to them, but you show the promise Morthis requires of his students. Seek him out at the Cenarion Refuge in Zangarmarsh.',objectives_loc4='Seek out Morthis Whisperwing at the Cenarion Refuge in Zangarmarsh.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Have you brought the Ingredients for the draught? <Morthis considers you somewhat skeptically.>$B$BI have long searched for an apprentice to pass my knowledge to. Though the Druids of the Talon are no longer a formal group, I shall remain one to the last of my days.$B$BI accept you as my apprentice from this moment forward. For my part, I will teach you the secrets of the stormcrow. For your part, you must be prepared to do all I ask. Do you understand?' WHERE entry=10955;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Do you know anything about the naaru?  They\'re these angelic beings that have been helping the draenei for a really long time.  I\'ve seen a bunch around Shattrath.$B$BThey say that one naaru, O\'ros, was with the Exodar when it traveled to your homeworld.  I should like to see for myself.$B$BCan you take me there?  I bet we could get there fast by using one of the portals inside the Terrace of Light at Shattrath City!  When we get there, if you get lost, we could always just look at your map.' WHERE entry=10956;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It is done, $N.  The time to strike at Illidan has come.' WHERE entry=10957;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We\'ve been expecting you, $N.  Akama is in great need of your help.' WHERE entry=10958;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It is as it was foretold, $N.  One by one, Illidan\'s lieutenants have fallen... and now the Betrayer himself has met his demise!$B$BKnow this, $N: every decision Akama made and every moment of his life since Illidan arrived, Akama planned for this moment.  Illidan is finally dead and our people... are free!' WHERE entry=10959;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Neato! A dragon of my very own! One day I hope that I\'m lucky enough to have a dragon as a friend.$B$B<Dornaa bounces up and down with joy, fiercely hugging her new toy.>$B$BThis has been the best trip ever! I hope it never ends.' WHERE entry=10962;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='In the orphanage, the old stinky priest that comes by told us stories about the Caverns of Time.  He said that it sits in the middle of time, and is really important for keeping things straight.$B$BI don\'t know what that means, but he said that there were dragons there that were helping to save the world!  I want to see a dragon!$B$BI think we should go there.  He said that the entrance was on the eastern edge of a great desert named Tanaris.$B$BYou could buy me a souvenir while we\'re there!',objectives_loc4='Take your orphan, Salandria, to stand before Zaladormu, the dragon on the dais in the middle of the Caverns of Time.  Make sure to call for her if she is not present when you arrive.$B$BThen, purchase a Toy Dragon for her from the Keepers of Time Quartermaster, Alurmi, near the bottom of the entrance tunnel.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Awesome! A dragon of my very own! Someday I plan to own a real one.$B$B<Salandria slyly eyes her new toy, the gears within her mind turning.>$B$BThis has been the best trip ever! I hope it never ends.' WHERE entry=10963;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It is good for the soul to know that there are heroes such as yourself that are willing to give of their time so selflessly.$B$BI can tell already that your time together with Dornaa has made a huge impression. It\'s good for the children to have a chance to get out and see the world.$B$BHere, she told me that she wanted you to take care of one of her favorite pets, just like you took care of her. Something to remember her by.$B$BDon\'t be a stranger.' WHERE entry=10966;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It is good for the soul to know that there are heroes such as yourself that are willing to give of their time so selflessly.$B$BI can tell already that your time together with Salandria has made a huge impression. It\'s good for the children to have a chance to get out and see the world.$B$BHere, she told me that she wanted you to take care of one of her favorite pets, just like you took care of her. Something to remember her by.$B$BDon\'t be a stranger.' WHERE entry=10967;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='It would seem that an outside force has taken an interest in the business practices of the Consortium. Five Consortium dealers have gone missing in the past two days. We have reason to believe the Ethereum are involved. If you are interested in assisting, seek out Commander Ameer at the Protectorate Watch Post.$B$BYou will find the Protectorate Watch Post directly east of here on the next island. $B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Aye, it is true, but the Consortium are not the only group claiming losses.' WHERE entry=10969;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Stand back, $N. This could very well be an Ethereum trap.' WHERE entry=10970;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It seems to be more than just an identifier. There is some sort of code written on these tags. I\'m on the verge of breaking it wide open. Perhaps if I had a few more pieces.' WHERE entry=10971;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We are close to the truth, $N.' WHERE entry=10972;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Ameer deftly combines the keys and begins to read the markings on the newly formed key tablet.>$B$B"A thousand worlds shattered, a thousand worlds more to overcome... Such is the will of the Nexus-King."$B$B<Ameer turns the tablet over and begins to read from the back-side.>$B$BStasis chambers of Bash\'ir?' WHERE entry=10973;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The image of Commander Ameer rummages through the evidence.>$B$BIt is worse than I thought... These chambers hold ferocious beasts and creatures from many, many different worlds. They hope to one day command the beasts to do their bidding. We must destroy them all!' WHERE entry=10974;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='At last!$B$B<Commander Ameer reads from the Mark of the Nexus-King.>$B$BTwo final prisons? I shudder to think what horrors lie in wait...' WHERE entry=10976;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='From what you\'ve told me, Morthis\'s suspicions seem plausible, but we need confirmation.$B$BIn his research, Timeon has uncovered clues that a "book of the raven" served as an ancient scripture to the cult.$B$BThe arakkoa spirits will not reveal themselves to your eyes. Take this stone with you to the high peaks in the western part of Blade\'s Edge, to the south of Raven\'s Wood, obtain an aether ray eye, and combine them to augment your sight. Search for the ghost Timeon identified as Sai\'kkal the Elder.',objectives_loc4='Use an Aether Ray Eye with your Seer\'s Stone to reveal the raven cult ghosts. Search the Vortex Pinnacle for the spirit of Sai\'kkal the Elder and question him about the book of the raven, then return to Arthorn Windsong.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Isn\'t it amazing that even among arakkoa, the cultists were considered heretics? That the traditional priests hated them enough to destroy their holy text is incredible! We must get our hands on that book, $N.$B$BIt\'s the key to unraveling the mystery of the raven god and preventing him from taking over the Emerald Dream.$B$BPerhaps Morthis will finally agree to take me as a student if we succeed!' WHERE entry=10980;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done much for the Protectorate and the Consortium, $N. It is only fitting, then, that the first of our new keys goes to you. With this key you will be able to open Shaffar\'s personal stasis chamber at any time without having expended the key itself.$B$B<Ameer nods.>$B$BIt is permanent and will be with you forever.' WHERE entry=10982;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Grok said that I am wise?  I don\'t know about that.$B$BPerhaps it is because I am the only one in my clan that is truly trying to save us from annihilation by the Bladespire clan, and Gruul and his sons, who are backing them.$B$BI hope that you have come to deliver us from certain doom, $C.' WHERE entry=10983;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You help Grok?  Grok need help!  Bloodmaul clan need help!' WHERE entry=10984;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Xi\'ri pulses with energy as you feel an object materialize in your hands.  It is the medallion you gave to A\'dal on Akama\'s behalf, its power augmented by the naaru\'s magic.  The Sha\'tar have entrusted you with the Medallion of Karabor, and with it access to the Black Temple.>' WHERE entry=10985;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Locating the pieces of the Book of the Raven, if they survive at all, is going to be difficult. Our best hope is to use a keener pair of eyes than your own.$B$BDown in western Nagrand, on the eastern lip of the Twilight Ridge, Watcher Elaira studies the various bird species that make their home there. Visit her and see if she can help you harness avian sight to gather the pieces of the Book of the Raven.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Watcher Elaira at the Twilight Ridge in Nagrand.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Elaira listens as you describe your search for the Book of the Raven and Arthorn\'s suggestion to use birds to locate the missing pieces of the tablet.>$B$BIt\'s an excellent idea and Nagrand is teeming with candidates, but which one to use?' WHERE entry=10986;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Visit Mog\'dorg the Wizened atop the tower where Chort is standing, just outside the Circle of Blood in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Finally, Chort has sent me someone who looks like they might be able to help.  I am trying to save the Bloodmaul from annihilation by the Bladespire clan, and Gruul\'s sons, who are backing them.$B$BI trust that you will be the one to aid our secret society and deliver us into freedom.' WHERE entry=10989;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='To the east, at the terminus of Dragons\' End, is the Cursed Hollow.  Therein, Grulloc, son of Gruul, plots his dimwitted schemes.$B$BI heard that one of his possessions was stolen from him through trickery.  Was that you?  Unfortunate that he was not slain in the process.$B$BIf we are to regain our freedom, I would have you take his most prized possession, a dragon skull from when he rejoiced in his father\'s slaying of the Black Dragonflight.  The only way you\'ll get the skull is to vanquish him.',objectives_loc4='Retrieve Grulloc\'s Dragon Skull and deliver it to Mog\'dorg the Wizened atop the tower at the Circle of Blood in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Indeed, it must have been a difficult struggle, $C.  I feel greatly relieved now that he will not be breathing down our necks here.$B$BI will send this skull down to Chort for safekeeping.  I\'m beginning to think that with your help, we might just pull this off.' WHERE entry=10995;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Retrieve Maggoc\'s Treasure Chest and deliver it to Mog\'dorg the Wizened atop the tower at the Circle of Blood in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You say it was empty?  Unfortunate, but you can see the mindless brutality that we\'re up against.$B$BWith the fall of Maggoc, we are one step closer to realizing my dream of a home for the ogres where we can determine our own destiny.' WHERE entry=10996;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Retrieve Slaag\'s Standard and deliver it to Mog\'dorg the Wizened atop the tower at the Circle of Blood in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='What a relief that Slaag is gone.  No longer will we be threatened by the looming specter of his return!$B$BIf you do not mind, I will take the standard as a symbol of hope for all of the ogres of the mountains.$B$BThank you, $N.' WHERE entry=10997;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='There is one more gronn to be slain: Skulloc Soulgrinder.  He keeps himself hidden away, but there is a way to coax him forth.$B$BHe was trained by an ogre warlock known as Vim\'gol the Vile, whose grimoire you must retrieve!$B$BVim\'gol must be summoned by yourself, and four others, each standing within a different fire ring at his circle.  Find Vim\'gol\'s Circle in the mountains, to the northeast, near the Broken Wilds.$B$BAnd, $N, if you hear Vim\'gol talk about growing bigger, get back to the fire rings!',objectives_loc4='You must retrieve Vim\'gol\'s Vile Grimoire.  Deliver it to Mog\'dorg the Wizened atop the tower at the Circle of Blood in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I hesitate to even touch such a tainted thing of evil.  Yet read it we must if we are to glean what knowledge it contains and bring forth Skulloc from his hiding place.' WHERE entry=10998;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Retrieve Skulloc\'s Soul and deliver it to Mog\'dorg the Wizened atop the tower at the Circle of Blood in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It is over then.  You have freed us from the shackles of our enslavement to the Sons of Gruul.  You have given the Bloodmaul Clan a reprieve from certain extinction.$B$BWords cannot describe the extent of the debt that ALL of the ogres of the Blade\'s Edge Mountains, Bloodmaul and Bladespire alike, owe you, $N.$B$BLook down, even now the ogres gather to pay you tribute.  Let Gruul and his puppet, the old king, Maulgar, cower within their lair.  Go to the ogres below as our new king!' WHERE entry=11000;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We must waste no time in dealing with the raven god. You must take the essence-infused moonstone to a place of great power in order to lure the god from the relative safety of the Emerald Dream.$B$BDescend into the Sethekk Halls and set the moonstone in the clutches of the raven\'s claw. You\'ll find it in the chamber before the talon king\'s hall.$B$BAnzu must be made believe that his followers have gathered to welcome him back into the world. Once he has manifested, show him no mercy!',objectives_loc4='Slay the Raven God and return to Morthis Whisperwing at Cenarion Refuge.$B$BThis quest must be completed in Heroic dungeon difficulty.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s good to see you again, $N. Your triumph over the raven god counts for far more than any test or rite of passage that I might set for you.$B$BYou have truly proven yourself worthy of the knowledge guarded by the Druids of the Talon for countless generations.' WHERE entry=11001;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The source of Illidan Stormrage\'s fel orc army has been vanquished. The manufactory halts production of its grim product - at least for now. All that remains are a few trinkets and this severed head - a fitting trophy for a hero of the Alliance.$B$BReturn Magtheridon\'s head to Danath Trollbane at Honor Hold.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='This defeat is not only a blow to Illidan. The Legion too reels... A pit lord commander has been defeated. The siege of Hellfire Citadel now holds no purpose for the Burning Legion. All of their efforts will undoubtedly be turned upon the Black Temple.$B$BRedemption comes for Illidan... and soon.' WHERE entry=11002;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The source of Illidan Stormrage\'s fel orc army has been vanquished. The manufactory halts production of its grim product - at least for now. All that remains are a few trinkets and this severed head - a fitting trophy for a hero of the Horde.$B$BReturn Magtheridon\'s head to Nazgrel at Thrallmar.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='This defeat is not only a blow to Illidan. The Legion too reels... A pit lord commander has been defeated. The siege of Hellfire Citadel now holds no purpose for the Burning Legion. All of their efforts will undoubtedly be turned upon the Black Temple.$B$BRedemption comes for Illidan... and soon.' WHERE entry=11003;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I thank you, $N. I will administer a small amount to the commander... to humor him. You can keep the rest, perhaps you\'ll find a use for it.' WHERE entry=11004;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done well, $N. You\'ve dealt a tremendous blow to the enemy by slaying the talonpriests.' WHERE entry=11005;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Keep bringing the dust to me. I\'ll prepare as many elixirs as you need.$B$BCommander\'s orders.' WHERE entry=11006;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<A\'dal\'s thoughts intermingle with your own.>$B$BThe sphere... Strange. Did you know that he lived? Yes. It is here - in the sphere itself. Maimed for certain. He calls to a higher power now. No, not Illidan.$B$BHigher.$B$BKil\'jaeden the Deceiver comes...$B$BNot here...$B$B<A\'dal points your mind elsewhere.>$B$BAzeroth. Unknown.$B$BRest. Your brothers and sisters will retake Tempest Keep now.$B$B<A\'dal hums a song of battle.>$B$B' WHERE entry=11007;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent job, $N! That\'ll show those bird men the meaning of air superiority!' WHERE entry=11008;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Mog\'dorg sent a message ahead, saying that I should expect you. I am glad that you came.$B$BWith the Sons of Gruul destroyed, it is only a matter of time - a short amount at that - before the various inhabitants of this mountain terrace, and the one to the north, decide to prey upon our ogre brothers down below.$B$BI trust that you will help us to prevent that, $B.' WHERE entry=11009;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Sky Sergeant Vanderlip has tasked you with the bombing of 15 Fel Cannonball Stacks.  Return to her at the Skyguard Outpost atop the Blade\'s Edge Mountains once you have done so.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, well, well, I guess you had it in you after all. Good work. Maybe Old Man Keller was wrong about you after all.$B$B<Sky Sergeant Vanderlip smirks.>' WHERE entry=11010;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Our lands are lost. Our children stolen in the night, forced into slavery - or worse...$B$B<Mordenai\'s voice tenses.>$B$BThe time is now, my ally. The time to retake what was once ours has come! You have proven yourself a capable combatant and compassionate soul.$B$BWill you swear to assist the Netherwing Dragonflight in retaking our lands and rebuilding our homes? Will you swear to watch over the flight and allow the bloodline to be born anew? Swear this and let us battle for our home and our loved ones!' WHERE entry=11012;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Travel to Netherwing Ledge and deliver the Illidari Service Papers to Overlord Mor\'ghor at Dragonmaw Base Camp.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Mor\'ghor reads the letter and laughs.>$B$BA death knight? You couldn\'t shine the boots of a death knight, maggot.$B$B<Mor\'ghor looks you over.>$B$BBut yes... You might be able to work your way up to peon. At the worst, I\'ll toss you into the pit and leave you to die...' WHERE entry=11013;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Varkule gonna set you up right, grunt. You get your choice of one job best suited to your skills and Netherwing crystal collection. You\'ll be required to fill your work orders once per day.$B$BYeah, it\'s a bunch of crap jobs but even the ascendants started out as peons.' WHERE entry=11014;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='No good at nothin\'? That\'s fine. Even lunkheads like you can be used around here. Just find creatures on the ledge and kill \'em. Sometimes they\'ll have nether crystals on their carcasses. Gather those and bring \'em back to me and I\'ll consider your work order for the day complete.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re done for today, kid. Come back tomorrow if you\'re still alive.' WHERE entry=11015;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re done for today, kid. Come back tomorrow if you\'re still alive.' WHERE entry=11016;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re done for today, kid. Come back tomorrow if you\'re still alive.' WHERE entry=11017;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re done for today, kid. Come back tomorrow if you\'re still alive.' WHERE entry=11018;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Didn\'t think we\'d leave you to face the fel orc army by yourself, did you?$B$B<Yarzill\'s eyes flicker a translucent blue.>$B$BAye, we are here with you, $N. For every service you perform for the fel orcs in your quest to reclaim Netherwing lands, we\'ll be at your side to make sure that they suffer a sufficient setback.$B$BYou\'ll need to keep a low profile so as not to draw any unwanted attention to yourself during your sabotage missions.' WHERE entry=11019;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Yarzill the Merc at Dragonmaw Base Camp in Shadowmoon Valley wants you to use Yarzill\'s Mutton in conjunction with Fel Glands to poison 12 Dragonmaw Peon Camps.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Yarzill speaks in a low whisper.>$B$BExcellent work, $N. Lay low for now. Come back to me tomorrow and we can do it again.' WHERE entry=11020;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What have you brought to me? I can\'t make out the writing on this tome, $N... my loss of blood... must\'ve blurred my vision.' WHERE entry=11021;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='$G King : Queen; $N!  You speak with Mog\'dorg the Wizened before you leave and go to Ogri\'la!',offerrewardtext_loc4='My good man, I am glad that you have decided to speak to me again before leaving.' WHERE entry=11022;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Sky Sergeant Vanderlip has tasked you with the bombing of 15 Fel Cannonball Stacks.  Return to her at the Skyguard Outpost atop the Blade\'s Edge Mountains once you have done so.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Outstanding work, $N!  I\'d have you back up in the air and bombing them again, but policy around here is to make sure that our pilots get plenty of R&R.  Sorry, I don\'t make the rules, but I sure as hell enforce them!' WHERE entry=11023;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring Ishaal\'s Almanac to Rilak the Redeemed in Lower City inside Shattrath.',offerrewardtext_loc4='This cannot be... this belonged to a talonpriest once. How did you ever come across it?' WHERE entry=11024;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Chu\'a\'lor\'s left head begins to speak.>$B$BThese will do fine.$B$BRemember, $B, the value of the shard is not in what it can purchase for you. It is not even in what it can potentially do for you when properly forged, though there is some debate over that.$B$B<His right head finishes,...>$B$BThe true value is in the journey to attain the shard.' WHERE entry=11025;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Kronk has asked you to use the Banishing Crystal to banish 15 demons at Forge Camp: Wrath or Forge Camp: Terror atop the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.  Return it to him once you have done so.',offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'ll teach them! And, of course, now for your reward.$B$BThe demons of Forge Camp: Wrath, to the north, have created a special transporter on their southern border. This experimental gate is being used to expand the forge camp, and we don\'t think we need to tell you how that will effect us if they expand too far.$B$BHowever, if we were you, we\'d take this darkrune over to Gahk, and ask him how you can help. Just take it easy on him, $N. Like you, he\'s new here.' WHERE entry=11026;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Return to Sky Commander Adaris with the news about Terokk\'s return.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The arakkoa seek to bring Terokk back beyond the veil of time and Rilak... wants to find a way to accelerate the process? Is he out of his mind?$B$B<Adaris lays back down as his strength fades.>$B$BYou\'ve done your duty, $N. It is time you let my men take over from here. This has become a purely military matter.' WHERE entry=11028;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent! This book catalogs the descendants of Terokk\'s ancient enemies. It is prophesied that their demise will be followed by Terokk\'s return.' WHERE entry=11029;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Torkus has asked you to obtain an Unstable Flask of the Beast for him.  Return with it to him at Ogri\'la atop the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re a lifesaver, $N. Our boys are going to be so excited to hear the news!$B$BOK, so one down and one to go. We did tell you about the other magical flask that they\'re going to need, didn\'t we?' WHERE entry=11030;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Make this next decision carefully.  We do our best to accommodate our allies, but even Dalaran\'s resources have their limits.' WHERE entry=11032;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Yarzill whispers.>$B$BYou are doing the Netherwing a great service, $N. Slowly, we will topple the Dragonmaw. From the inside a disease now grows - a disease with no cure...$B$BReturn to me tomorrow if you are interested in more work at the Dragonmaw Skyway.' WHERE entry=11035;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring the Preserved Fruit to Rocket-Chief Fuselage at Area 52.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<The chief inspects the crate\'s contents.>$B$BEverything looks good here. That\'s one more thing to cross off the list. Now all we need to do is get the rocket off the ground!' WHERE entry=11036;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='A Strange Vision',details_loc4='I\'ve had a most unusual vision, $N, and I don\'t know quite what to make of it. I\'ve seen an arrow, an immense arrow, riding into the sky on a trail of fire. Such a feat is trivial for a skilled mage, but somehow I know the arrow I saw is not the product of magic.$B$BIt will be unlike anything the people of Azeroth have ever achieved. You must seek out the people working on this, $N. Lend them your help, for without it, their efforts may yet fail.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<The chief listens as you describe the seer\'s vision.>$B$BWell, I don\'t know about any of that, but we could certainly use your help around here. Behold the rocket behind me! That\'s the X-52...$B$BIsn\'t it the most beautiful thing you\'ve ever seen?' WHERE entry=11037;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So you\'re here to help us determine exactly what Kael\'thas is planning? Your help is most welcome. Netherstorm is crawling with blood elf agents whose activities threaten to tear the land asunder.' WHERE entry=11038;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<A brief look of disappointment crosses the spymaster\'s face.>$B$BI was hoping for at least a squad, but if Voren\'thal saw fit to send only you, then I will adjust my plans accordingly.' WHERE entry=11039;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring Bossi\'s Spare Parts to Rocket-Chief Fuselage at Area 52.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I don\'t even know what some of these parts do! I\'m certain I\'ll find a use for some of them, but I never suspected I\'d have to learn to think like a gnome!' WHERE entry=11040;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So from the remains of one of my own overseers you recovered the command and took matters into your own hands? You have managed to impress Mor\'ghor. Well done...' WHERE entry=11041;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The chief listens as you describe the seer\'s vision.>$B$BWell, I don\'t know about any of that, but we could certainly use your help around here. Look at the behemoth behind me. That\'s the X-52...$B$BIsn\'t it the most beautiful thing you\'ve ever seen?' WHERE entry=11042;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Speak with Brunn Flamebeard at Wildhammer Stronghold.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Brunn\'s face reddens until its color is indistinguishable from his beard.>$B$BHe wants to do WHAT to my gryphons?$B$BIf that little pipsqueak puts anything other than a saddle on them, I\'ll personally travel up to Blade\'s Edge and stuff that rocket o\' his down his throat!' WHERE entry=11043;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A vision, you say? I don\'t care if he saw it in a vision, read it in a letter, or heard it from the mouth of a pit lord. He was dead on! What matters is that you\'re here, friend, and we need all the help we can get.' WHERE entry=11044;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Fantei speaks the truth and I would welcome your help.' WHERE entry=11045;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Fantei has a good memory. It\'s been months since I was last in Shattrath to buy reagents. He\'s right, though. I could use the help.' WHERE entry=11046;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Speak with Dama Wildmane at Shadowmoon Village.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Dama listens to Agadai\'s request.>$B$BI can\'t guarantee that there will be any wind riders available, but I\'ll see what I can do. As it is, we\'re having trouble keeping up with the demands of other buyers and outposts.' WHERE entry=11047;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Neltharaku will be most pleased, $N. Well done.' WHERE entry=11049;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are a true hero, $N.' WHERE entry=11050;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Kronk has asked you to use the Banishing Crystal to banish 15 demons at Forge Camp: Wrath or Forge Camp: Terror atop the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.  Return it to him once you have done so.',offerrewardtext_loc4='We wish the process of creating a darkrune was foolproof, $N. Alas, it is not. Please, take this bag and look in it to see what we\'ve wrought today. We couldn\'t bear to look ourselves.$B$BRemember, if you get a darkrune, take it to Gahk to exchange for a crystalforged darkrune. Then you\'ll be able to once more bring down Shartuul\'s transporter.$B$BOh, and $N, don\'t forget to come by again tomorrow and pickup the banishing crystal. There are always more demons to be banished.' WHERE entry=11051;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I have been following your activities closely, $N. You have proven to be an invaluable asset to Dragonmaw. With that said, I am going to promote you to Overseer. With that rank comes new responsibilities that you must fulfill.$B$BRise, Overseer $N! Rise and seek out those that need your assistance at the base camp.' WHERE entry=11053;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Chief Overseer Mudlump at the Dragonmaw Base Camp in Shadowmoon Valley wants you to bring him 10 pieces of Knothide Leather and 1 Hardened Hide of Tyrantus.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='ARRR! You might make it as an overseer after all. That oversized lizard has been the bane of many an orc!$B$B<Chief Overseer Mudlump begins to fashion the weapon>.' WHERE entry=11054;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='This is your booterang. There are many like it but this one is yours.$B$BAs an overseer you will use this booterang to sow terror into the hearts of defiant peons. Proper use of the booterang will instill obedience and ensure subservience.$B$BVenture forth to the crystal fields and discipline any peons that you see slacking off. Show them the might of the booterang!$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='A hard day\'s work! It pays off, though, doesn\'t it? Warms your heart seeing those worthless runts slavering over those crystals... Anyhow, that\'s all for today. Come back tomorrow for another round of booterang discipline.' WHERE entry=11055;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent, $N. You will see that I\'m true to my word.' WHERE entry=11056;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Chu\'a\'lor has asked you to speak with Mog\'dorg the Wizened atop one of the towers just outside the Circle of Blood in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='You were sent from on high? Truly my mission is blessed! I am trying to save the Bloodmaul from annihilation by the Bladespire clan, and Gruul\'s sons, who are backing them.$B$BI trust that you will be the one to aid our secret society and deliver us into freedom.' WHERE entry=11057;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Chu\'a\'lor has asked you to return to him at Ogri\'la atop the Blade\'s Edge Mountains after you have gained Apexis Vibrations from an Apexis Relic.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Chu\'a\'lor nods his heads at you in satisfaction at your accomplishment.>$B$BYou have a quick mind, $N. It took us much longer to successfully make use of the relic.$B$BNow that you know how, you can do so as much as you care to. Just remember that they require an apexis shard to power them.' WHERE entry=11058;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You\'ve figured out how to use the single-person relics, but as you may have seen, there are bigger ones, which they surround.$B$BThese larger apexis monuments function in much the same way, but they take many more apexis shards to activate and require four persons to operate.$B$BOf greater concern to us are the guardians that are summoned through their use.  These crystal constructs turned on their arakkoan masters long ago, and now endanger Ogri\'la.$B$BWe would ask that you destroy one and bring us proof.',objectives_loc4='Chu\'a\'lor has asked you to obtain an Apexis Guardian\'s Head for him as proof.  Return with it to him at Ogri\'la atop the Blade\'s Edge Mountains once you have done so.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Chu\'a\'lor beams at you with obvious respect.>$B$BNot only are we impressed with the mental alacrity of you and your friends, but we are indebted to you, as is all of Ogri\'la and the Skyguard, for helping to protect our way of life here.$B$BAnd remember, $N, at any time you can gather others and return to any of those larger apexis monuments to make use of them; as long as you have enough apexis shards to power it that is.' WHERE entry=11059;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Torkus has asked you to obtain an Unstable Flask of the Sorcerer for him.  Return with it to him at Ogri\'la atop the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='We can\'t thank you enough, $N!$B$BNow with these two flasks, unstable though they may be, we\'ll be able to send one of our boys north to the Skyguard Outpost.$B$BHere, just wait a moment and we\'ll call for one of them.$B$B<Torkus\'s right head shouts out for his boy in a low growl.>' WHERE entry=11061;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Chu\'a\'lor has asked you to speak with Sky Commander Keller at the Skyguard Outpost atop the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Welcome ta the Skyguard Outpost! I built it with me own hands ya know.$B$BYeah, the whole thing!$B$B<The sky commander looks serious.>$B$BSo, ye must be lookin\' ta spoil for a fight if ye\'re here talkin\' ta me. It was kind of old Chu\'a\'lor ta send ye along. We can always use fresh meat for the grinder around here.$B$BIf ye don\'t mind, I\'d like ya ta start by having a talk with my sergeant across the way: Vanderlip. Don\'t mind her tongue, though it be sharper than the greatsword she be carrying.' WHERE entry=11062;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Wanna help the Skyguard and Ogri\'la?$B$BJust hear me out before you walk away, $G hot stuff : girly;.  We\'re in need of remounts!  The bombing runs and missions to Bash\'ir Landing have taken a toll on our mounts.$B$BThe aether rays that fly around Vortex Pinnacle, and the Crystal Spine to the northeast, look like they\'d do just fine.  You don\'t even have to bring them back here, though that would be nice.  Just break and rope them, and we\'ll track them down later.$B$BThink you can wrangle me up some?',objectives_loc4='Skyguard Khatie has asked you to wrangle 5 Aether Rays.  After you have done so, return them to her at the Skyguard Outpost atop the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Woo hoo!  Nice job, $N! Those rays are going to make excellent mounts!$B$BStick around kid... the Sha\'tari Skyguard can always use a man of your obvious talents!' WHERE entry=11065;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='So, I hope that you\'re up to helping us wrangle up even more aether rays!  From what I can see, you\'re a natural with the rope!  And it\'s for a good cause, because not only do we get fresh mounts, but it helps us to protect Ogri\'la, which the ogres appreciate.$B$BRemember, the aether rays fly around Vortex Pinnacle, and the Crystal Spine to the northeast.$B$BThink you can wrangle me up some more?',objectives_loc4='Skyguard Khatie has asked you to wrangle 5 Aether Rays.  After you have done so, return them to her at the Skyguard Outpost atop the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You continue to amaze me! Tell you what... why don\'t you come back tomorrow and we\'ll let the rope cool off for now?$B$B<Khatie laughs.>$B$BThank you so much, $N!' WHERE entry=11066;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The next two riders were the two top pilots that the dwarves and orcs of Azeroth had to offer. You stand no chance!' WHERE entry=11068;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Three years of blood, sweat and tears. Mostly tears... The amount of crying that a hardened soldier does when it comes down to all-out war is amazing!$B$B"They\'re jumping into our tower with their horses!" "Why is their base so well defended?" "They\'re taking our relief hut, I\'m going A.W.O.L.!"$B$BWimps...$B$BI took the first train out of "cry-town" the minute the Dark Portal opened. Now I\'m a top gun for the Dragonmaw. If you want to be top orc, you\'ll have to defeat me.$B$BWe go when you are ready.$B',objectives_loc4='Follow Wing Commander Mulverick while attempting to stay on your flying mount. Should you defeat Wing Commander Mulverick, report your victory to Ja\'y Nosliw at the Dragonmaw Base Camp in Shadowmoon Valley.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well it looks like it\'s just you and the captain now, grunt. Good luck! You\'re gonna need it!' WHERE entry=11070;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I never dreamed any would be skilled enough to defeat Skyshatter. You do know what this means, right? You are now the top orc! You must defend your title.' WHERE entry=11071;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The descendants held prisoner by the Skettis talonpriests are listed in this book: Gezzarak the Huntress, Karrog the crystal giant, the heretic known as Darkscreecher Akkarai and Vakkiz the Windrager.  They will all need to be slain before Terokk returns to this world.$B$BYou will need the scrolls carried by the time-lost arakkoa to call them forth at the summoning circles in Skettis.  Bring me a token from each one.  These are powerful beings you will be facing; you would do well to bring friends.',objectives_loc4='Find the Skull Piles in the middle of the summoning circles of Skettis. Summon and defeat each of the descendants by using 10 Time-Lost Scrolls at the Skull Pile.  Return to Hazzik at Blackwind Landing with a token from each.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent!  Take this.  I\'ve prepared this bundle with the items you obtained.  They will allow you to summon Terokk.$B$BBeware, $N.  He is the most powerful arakkoa to ever exist.  Do not underestimate him!' WHERE entry=11072;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve made us all very proud, $N. I\'ll send word of your deeds back to Shattrath. The Skyguard will be forever in your debt.' WHERE entry=11073;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The miners are working hard but none dare step foot further into the mines. They choose death rather than being forced to mine deeper! It is going to be your job to carry out the duties and tasks that they failed to complete.' WHERE entry=11075;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. Return tomorrow for another mission into the depths of the mine.' WHERE entry=11076;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'ll be enough for today, overseer. Come back tomorrow for another round of clean up.' WHERE entry=11077;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='As ye\'ve flown around, ye must have noticed the dragons above.  I trust ye haven\'t fallen victim ta their rage.  Help us put an end ta it, $N!$B$BRivendark and Obsidia lord over this terrace, while Insidion and Furywing rule the skies over yon terrace ta the northeast.  Each has a perch on their respective domains.  I be wondering if ye and yer friends will go ta one, $G lad : lass;, break open an egg and attract the dragon down.$B$BBring me some teeth as proof.  Ta rule the skies, it\'s either them or us.',objectives_loc4='Sky Commander Keller has asked you to acquire Dragon Teeth and return them to him at the Skyguard Outpost atop the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes! Those teeth look like they be sharp enough ta cut through just about anything!$B$BAnd let me encourage ye and yer friends ta keep up the good work! Those dragons be fierce predators that make the skies wholly unsafe.$B$BYe might have noticed, too, the dragon scales. I hear they be good fer making powerful cloaks if ye get one o\' each o\' their scales. And if yer not happy with the cloak ya get, I\'ll be willing ta trade ye an apexis crystal fer it.' WHERE entry=11078;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Gahk think being smart is dumb sometimes.  Gahk not want to think.  Me want little $R to smash big demons!$B$BDey have some chiefs, and da chiefs all have whips to hurt da little demons.  You bring Gahk a whip!$B$BYou challenge demon chief in forge camps at burning, green, fel crystal prism.  Use many apexis shards to get dem to come.  Dey called Galvanoth, Braxxus, Zarcsin and da Mo\'arg Incinerator.',objectives_loc4='Gahk has asked you to acquire a Fel Whip.  Bring it to him at Ogri\'la atop the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Gahk like whip. Maybe Gahk take whip and beat demons with it!$B$BMe say to $R that $R summon demon chiefs anytime $R have friends and many shards.' WHERE entry=11079;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Chu\'a\'lor has asked you to return to him at Ogri\'la atop the Blade\'s Edge Mountains after you have gained Apexis Emanations from an Apexis Relic.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You continue to amaze us with your acumen as concerns the relics. $B. May we suggest that you practice with the relics at least once a day to maintain such a sharp edge to your mental acuity?' WHERE entry=11080;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work, overseer. Mor\'ghor will hear of your outstanding service to the Dragonmaw.$B$BNow back to these Murkblood dogs. They plan an escape, eh? Dare they defy the one true lord of Outland? Their masters will pay for this!' WHERE entry=11081;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Nothing to say? Perhaps as he lies bleeding to death on the floor of this cursed mine he will remember... Remember what it means to cross the forces of Illidan!.' WHERE entry=11082;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yeah, I don\'t understand it... You would think that they wouldn\'t even be that hungry after 2 days. Murkblood...$B$B<Ronag shakes his head.>$B$BDamn they\'re stupid...' WHERE entry=11083;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Mor\'ghor nods.>$B$BThat\'s right, I said captain. You\'ve earned another promotion, $N.$B$BYou certainly don\'t work like any fel orc I\'ve ever seen. Keep this up and you might make overlord some day.$B$BNow get out there and take command. I would suggest you try and earn your Skybreaker wings.' WHERE entry=11084;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you for rescuing one of our scouts, $N. We lose good people every day and there aren\'t enough new recruits to replace them.' WHERE entry=11085;
UPDATE locales_quest SET EndText_loc4='Rescue the Skyguard Prisoner.' WHERE entry=11085;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work, captain! Lord Illidan will hear of your heroism!' WHERE entry=11086;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='HYJAL FLAG' WHERE entry=11087;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Reth\'hedron now lords over the Twilight Ridge of Nagrand. An eredar of such power being loosed upon this world does not bode well for the Illidari. Alas, we do not have the resources required to slay Reth\'hedron. Not with the war the bastards have brought to the Black Temple. No... I have a better plan.$B$BYou will subdue Reth\'hedron, banishing him back through the Twilight Portal. For this a soul cannon must be fashioned.$B$BReturn to me with the materials on this list.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Balthas deftly combines the components you brought him.>$B$BYou are now ready for the second phase of the plan, captain.' WHERE entry=11089;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='He will be back, but for now the Legion\'s war against Lord Illidan is weakened. He shall know of your deeds, captain.' WHERE entry=11090;
UPDATE locales_quest SET EndText_loc4='Subdue Reth\'hedron the Subduer' WHERE entry=11090;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Chu\'a\'lor suggested that you speak with Jho\'nass at Ogri\'la atop the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Hey. man. that\'s great. We hear you\'ve been doing good things. That\'s cool. We\'ve got a feeling that you\'re going to make things right for us here in Ogri\'la, and keep us safe, and everything nice and mellow.$B$BHere, take this. It\'s nothing much, just a care package that we whipped up as a thanks for your effort.$B$BFeel free to look around at our goods. We have a lot of really choice stuff that you\'re gonna want to get.' WHERE entry=11091;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Lord Illidan himself has asked that I promote you to the rank of commander! This is unprecedented. You will be the first Dragonmaw to reach such a rank outside of the Black Temple.' WHERE entry=11092;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thanks for taking care of the ray, $N. Goodness knows these guys fly much better when they\'re well-fed. We don\'t want our boys getting shot down because their ray was too weak to fly.' WHERE entry=11093;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Commander $N, stand at attention! You are to take a battalion of Skybreakers and sack the Scryers\' outpost located at the foot of the Netherwing Fields. With the Sanctum of the Stars destroyed, our lines of communication to our posts at Eclipse Point and Illidari Point will once more be open.$B$BGo now! Use this flare gun to signal the Skybreakers for the attack!',objectives_loc4='Deliver news of your mission along with the Dragonmaw Flare Gun to Arcanist Thelis at the Sanctum of the Stars in Shadowmoon Valley.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It is good that you came to us. Perhaps we can use this attack to our advantage and turn the tables on the Dragonmaw.' WHERE entry=11094;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The Dragonmaw only dare attack us when our guard is down. They would face certain defeat if they were to attack us while we were prepared.$B$BI want you to let them come, $N.$B$B<Thelis nods.>$B$BYes... a trap. Take this flare that their overlord gave you and deliver it to Commander Hobb. He is standing guard right outside this building.',objectives_loc4='Give the Dragonmaw Flare to Commander Hobb at the Sanctum of the Stars in Shadowmoon Valley.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Hobb grins.>$B$BThe deadliest trap ever laid...' WHERE entry=11095;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good job, ace.  I\'ve a feeling you\'re going to fit in well with us.' WHERE entry=11096;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc4='Have you completed your task, $N?' WHERE entry=11096;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Take these Scryer medals. Mor\'ghor will need proof of "victory" once this is over. He will recognize them as coming from the corpses of fallen Scryer soldiers.$B$BNow all that remains is to use the signal flare to alert the Dragonmaw raiders. We will crush them when you are ready. Just give me the word.',objectives_loc4='Assist Commander Hobb and the Scryers in defending the Sanctum of the Stars. Once all of the Dragonmaw forces have been defeated, return to Overlord Mor\'ghor at Dragonmaw Base Camp with the Scryer Medals.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Mor\'ghor laughs.>$B$BHAH! I knew you wouldn\'t let me down, commander! I want you to lead a raid on the Sanctum of the Stars at least once per day. They will have no choice but to leave Shadowmoon!' WHERE entry=11097;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thanks for the supplies; we\'ll put them to good use!  A new recruit?  Well, let\'s see what you\'re made of.' WHERE entry=11098;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Commander $N, stand at attention! You are to take a battalion of Skybreakers and sack the Aldor outpost located northwest of our beloved Black Temple. With the Altar of Sha\'tar destroyed, our lines of communication to our posts at Coilskar will once more be open.$B$BGo now! Use this flare gun to signal the Skybreakers for the attack!',objectives_loc4='Deliver news of your mission and the Dragonmaw Flare Gun to Anchorite Ceyla at the Altar of Sha\'tar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It is good that you came to us. Perhaps we can use this attack to our advantage and turn the tables on the Dragonmaw.' WHERE entry=11099;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The Dragonmaw only dare attack us when our guard is down. They would face certain defeat if they were to attack us while we were prepared.$B$BI want you to let them come, $N.$B$B<Ceyla nods.>$B$BYes... a trap. Take this flare that their overlord gave you and deliver it to Commander Arcus. He is standing guard right outside this building.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Arcus grins.>$B$BThe deadliest trap ever laid...' WHERE entry=11100;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Mor\'ghor laughs.>$B$BHAH! I knew you wouldn\'t let me down, commander! I want you to lead a raid on the Altar of Sha\'tar at least once per day. They will have no choice but to leave Shadowmoon!' WHERE entry=11101;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You can fly around as a crow... so what!  Ever annihilate something on the ground while you were flying?  Want to?$B$BForge Camp: Wrath and Forge Camp: Terror, to the north and south, are a major pain in my backside, as well as being a threat to peaceful Ogri\'la.  With all of those fel cannons shooting down the Skyguard left and right, we can\'t get through there to take care of business.$B$BWant to prove yourself?  Take these bombs and knock out their ammo stacks.  Just don\'t let them shoot you down, too!',objectives_loc4='Sky Sergeant Vanderlip has tasked you with the bombing of 15 Fel Cannonball Stacks.  Return to her at the Skyguard Outpost atop the Blade\'s Edge Mountains once you have done so.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, well, well, I guess you had it in you after all. Good work. Maybe Old Man Keller was wrong about you after all.$B$B<Sky Sergeant Vanderlip smirks.>' WHERE entry=11102;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Speak to Overlord Mor\'ghor at Dragonmaw Base Camp in Shadowmoon Valley.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='You are the first highlord of the Dragonmaw, $N. The master himself has chosen to come here to promote you.' WHERE entry=11107;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I was the first, you know. The abandoned child of a monster...$B$B<Barthamus shakes his head.>$B$BWe owe you everything, $N. You have single-handedly shattered the Dragonmaw empire and gathered enough information to keep my brethren occupied for ten lifetimes.$B$BIt is not much but there is something that we can offer... My kin have each offered to join you on your mission in Outland. Simply ask and they will bond with you.' WHERE entry=11108;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Here now. Ye hear that? There be sounds in them hills. Those\'re the wolpertingers! Wily beasts, they are, attracted by the smells o\' Brewfest. I\'ve a mind to catch me some, but I knocked me shin and can\'t outrun the buggers. Ye can help me, though!$B$BTake this net and cast it over the little blighters. Bring me a good five of \'em and I\'ll make it worth yer while! Oh, and one more thing - in order to even see these critters, ye need t\' be blitzed! Load up on the booze!',objectives_loc4='Goldark Snipehunter has asked you to capture 5 Stunned Wolpertingers using the Wolpertinger Net. He mentioned that you must be intoxicated to see them.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, lookee there! Ye\'ve got yerself a right bushel o\' wolpertingers, ye do!$B$B<He takes a deep drink from his tankard.>$B$BI\'ll tell ye what I\'m gonna do. Since ye\'re such a spot-on $C, I\'ll let ye keep one\'a these fer yer very own!' WHERE entry=11117;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Getting drunk is a time-honored tradition at Brewfest -- it\'s damn near required! Thing is, I\'m getting reports across Azeroth saying the celebration\'s plagued by hallucinations!  We can\'t have that!$B$BThese elekks can\'t be harmed by normal weapons -- they pass right through \'em -- so take this fabulous piece of gnomish machinery, visit the other beer gardens, and zap \'em to oblivion. Remember, you have to be drunk to see \'em!',objectives_loc4='Visit the beer gardens outside of Stormwind, Darnassus, and the Exodar, zap three elekks at each location, and return to Goldark Snipehunter. You must be drunk to see the pink elekks.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Good work! Pink elekks... what a preposterous notion!' WHERE entry=11118;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Sky Commander Keller has asked you to speak with the Aether-tech Apprentice at the Skyguard Outpost in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Despite how Keller cares to characterize it, I prefer to think of our missions as research-oriented.$B$BBut yes, we do resupply the Skyguard while we\'re there. That is if we can stay long enough to do so.$B$BYou look like you\'d be willing to keep the ethereals off of our backs. If you can manage to for long enough, we\'ll sell you surplus items that we create at the crystalforge, so bring your apexis shards and crystals!$B$BWe leave in 2 hours.' WHERE entry=11119;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Look. We\'re running a business here. People being drunk? It\'s good business. But I\'ll tell ya one thing that puts a cramp in the profits - hallucinations. Wouldn\'t ya know it, the boys are reporting that the sot- er, the loyal customers are seeing pink elekks everywhere.$B$BI don\'t need my customers unsettled. Look, take this ray and travel to the other beer gardens to take care of \'em for me, would ya? And be sure to get drunk!',objectives_loc4='Visit the beer gardens outside of Silvermoon, Thunder Bluff, and the Undercity, zap three elekks at each location, and return to Glodrak Huntsniper. You must be drunk to see the pink elekks.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ya did good, kid. Here, take this as payment for the job ya did.' WHERE entry=11120;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Get a keg from Flynn Firebrew in Kharanos and return it to Pol Amberstill.  Do this 3 times before your ram goes away.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Thanks a lot for your help! As long as Brewfest is going and the Dark Iron Dwarves are attacking, I\'ll need some help shipping kegs. So if you want to work for more tickets, talk to me every day.$B$BBut enough about that, I need to pay you for the job you just did. Here are your tickets, have fun at Brewfest!' WHERE entry=11122;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Poor James never recovered from the destruction of the Shady Rest and the murder of his family. The boys and I are doing what we can to find the bastards who did this.$B$BI\'ve sent our best investigator, Inspector Tarem, out to the ruins, but this is too big a job for any one man. If you\'d lend Tarem a hand, we\'d appreciate it. Light knows, we\'d all like to be out there helping.$B$BThe main road will lead you to the inn, but take care. Your journey will take you beyond the protection of my soldiers.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s good to see that Captain Vimes is finally assigning others to this investigation.$B$BI\'ve used a reflective powder to dust the area. It will reveal suspicious objects and markings, helping you to focus your efforts. Look over anything the dust illuminates.' WHERE entry=11123;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='If you follow the road south from the village, and then west toward the Barrens, you\'ll come across the ruins of the Shady Rest Inn.$B$BTheramore has sent an investigator to discover how the inn met its fate. Normally, I\'d advise you to steer clear, but we have orders from Orgrimmar to \'assist\' in the investigation.$B$BAccept any help the Theramore investigator offers, even feed him a tidbit or two of information if you\'d like, but save your real findings for me.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<The inspector regards you with what can only be distrust.>$B$BI\'ve been told that you\'re to... aid in this investigation. Very well, then.$B$BI\'ve been using this powder to search the ruins for clues that might help identify the attackers. It will illuminate anything that might have been involved in the attack. Don\'t hesitate to examine anything that looks suspicious.' WHERE entry=11124;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. I think we managed to catch them off guard. Their agents probably thought themselves safe within the city walls.$B$BGiven time, the agitators will return and spread their lies again. We\'ll use the time you\'ve bought to shut out the deserters further.' WHERE entry=11126;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='<NYI>Thunderbrew Secrets',objectives_loc4='Steal Grimbooze\'s Secret Recipe from Grimbooze\'s camp in Westfall and return to <NAME> Barleybrew in the Brewfest Grounds.' WHERE entry=11127;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring the Deserter Propaganda to Calia Hastings near the docks in Theramore.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<The SI:7 agent nods in approval.>$B$BExcellent. All that remains is to discredit the deserters so that they\'ll never gain a foothold in Theramore again, and I have just the plan to do it.' WHERE entry=11128;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Fantastic work, $N! Kyle came home as soon as he ate and went straight to bed. Thank you for your help.' WHERE entry=11129;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Come closer, $G man:sweetheart;! Let ol\' Griftah look at yer shiny things....$B$BHmm. Yeh, yeh, not bad, but ya can do better. Much, much better.$B$B<Griftah leans in and whispers.>$B$BThere be priceless shinies everywhere, $N, ya just gotta know where to look! It be yer lucky day; I know a fella who can help ya find more shinies than ya can ever carry.$B$BVisit my ol\' friend, Budd, near Zul\'Aman and show him this here. Ya be tellin\' him ol\' Griftah sent ya and he\'ll let ya in on his new project.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Budd reads the note.>$B$BAhh! A friend of Griftah? Welcome!$B$BYou have impeccable timing, friend. As fate would have it, I recently lost my latest partners. Tragic, truly, but great rewards often have a high price. Best not to dwell on the negative!$B$BYou\'ve doubtlessly heard of my countless exploits and discoveries. Well, all of that was nothing compared to this! Truth is, we\'re close to making history here at Zul\'Aman and, by fate\'s decree, you\'re in on the ground floor!' WHERE entry=11130;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh, thank you! May the Light bless your good works, kind $Glord:lady;. The shadow of the Dark Horseman yet looms, but at least, for now, the village is safe from his flames.' WHERE entry=11131;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Budd looks a bit shocked.>$B$BOh? You\'ve found it?$B$BAhem, I mean, of course you have! Well done, $C.$B$BLet me see if I can find you a little something nice... ahh yes, this should do.' WHERE entry=11132;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Calia Hastings wants you to distribute the Altered Leaflets to 6 Theramore Guards, then report back to her near the docks in Theramore.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Calia chuckles as you describe the guards\' reactions to the propaganda.>$B$BJust as I\'d hoped! I think it\'s safe to say any deserter agents who try to infiltrate Theramore will be laughed right out of town!' WHERE entry=11133;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Capture Gavis Greyshield, then report to Calia Hastings near the docks in Theramore.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Gavis\' request isn\'t as outlandish as it might sound. With the proper handling, Lady Jaina can return the deserters to the fold, but that is her decision, of course.$B$BIt\'s been a pleasure working with you, $N. Without your help, I doubt the operation would\'ve gone so smoothly. When I make my report in Stormwind, it will name you as the $C who ended the deserter threat.' WHERE entry=11134;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The Headless Horseman is driven away, but he will return as long as Hallow\'s End looms.  $N, end our misery, and the insane lament of the Horseman.  Face him when he is joined with his head, and destroy it!$B$BHe rests in the Forlorn Cloister of the Scarlet Monastery, in Tirisfal Glade.  Find his pumpkin shrine and say this:$B$B  Horseman, rise$B  Your time is nigh$B  You felt death once$B  Now, know demise!$B$BGo, $N.  And may the Light go with you.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The origin of this shrine is unknown, but there is no doubt to whom it pays homage...' WHERE entry=11135;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The captain makes no effort to hide that he\'s assessing your abilities.>$B$BSo you\'ve heard about the recent shipwreck off the coast? Good, I could use some help confirming my suspicions about the survivors. Welcome aboard, $N.' WHERE entry=11136;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='My scouts have reported a shipwreck just off the beach to the northeast. Shipwrecks aren\'t all that unusual out here, but the reports also indicated the survivors were all wearing red bandanas!$B$BThe Defias are craftsmen and guildsmen, not sailors. What are they doing at the site of a shipwreck on a continent they\'ve no interest in?$B$BTheir leader is rumored to reside on a large island just off the coast to the northeast of the tower. Kill him and retrieve any documents you find in his possession.',objectives_loc4='Obtain the Defias Orders from Garn Mathers and bring them to Captain Wymor at Sentry Point.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Captain Wymor accepts the orders from you and reads over them.>$B$BWhat in the world could \'precious cargo\' refer to? The Defias have done some small time smuggling back in lands of Stormwind, but this seems out of their league. The language of these orders suggests a wealthy or noble patron.' WHERE entry=11137;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Renn looks over the orders.>$B$BSo there was valuable cargo on board! We have to locate it before the Defias recover it. These guys are no divers, but we\'re going to need some of their gear if you\'re to help me find the cargo.' WHERE entry=11138;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Wow, this is in worse shape than I\'d thought, and these tools...$B$BWell, I said I\'d get this back into working condition for you, so I\'d better get to work.' WHERE entry=11139;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring 6 Salvaged Strongboxes to Renn McGill in Dustwallow Marsh.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Renn rifles through the contents of the strongboxes you recovered.>$B$BGood work. Now, let\'s see if our \'precious cargo\' is in here....' WHERE entry=11140;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You and Renn have done excellent work in bringing this information to light and reporting it immediately. There\'s no denying the Defias have hatched some sinister plan to strike at Stormwind and its allies. There\'s a level of complexity here that\'s beyond anything they\'ve ever attempted, which means they must have a wealthy sympathizer somewhere.' WHERE entry=11141;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='It looks like Renn\'s hunch about Alcaz Island was right. We need to survey that island, but it would take a whole brigade of troops to fight our way in there.$B$BTheramore\'s defenses can\'t weather such a hit, so I\'ve arranged with Cassa Crimsonwing, the apprentice to Theramore\'s gryphon master, to allow you to use one of her beasts to survey Alcaz from the air.$B$BAlcaz Island holds the key to the Defias\' plans for their prisoner and perhaps the prisoner\'s identity itself.',objectives_loc4='Speak to Cassa Crimsonwing and use one of her gryphons to survey Alcaz Island. When your survey is complete, speak with Lady Jaina Proudmoore in Theramore.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Lady Jaina listens intently as you report the results of your aerial survey.>$B$BA rune circle, dragonkin? The Defias certainly have hedge mages among their ranks, but no one powerful enough to make use of such a thing!$B$BAnd why would the black dragonkin be interested in an island full of naga? There are many unanswered questions, but I one thing is for certain: the Defias have a powerful ally in upper echelons of the Alliance.' WHERE entry=11142;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Captain Vimes thinks the Grimtotems are behind the destruction of the Shady Rest Inn? They wouldn\'t have been first on my list of suspects, but if Captain Vimes sent you here to follow up on a lead, he must have his reasons. Regardless, the Grimtotems have been a thorn in our side for some time and we\'re always glad to have the extra help.' WHERE entry=11143;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring the Grimtotem Battle Plan to Captain Darill at North Point Tower.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Captain Darill glances at the battle plan.>$B$BI\'d say it doesn\'t get any clearer than this. They\'ve taken it upon themselves to fight back against human settlements in the area and I have little doubt Theramore is next on their list.' WHERE entry=11144;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Sergeant Lukas at North Point Tower wants you to free 5 Theramore Prisoners.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The freed captives have already begun returning from Blackhoof Village. The information the captain is receiving from the prisoners will give us an advantage in our next battle against the Grimtotems.$B$BYou have my thanks and that of the men.' WHERE entry=11145;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The patch of swamp to the northeast is home to a particularly nasty breed of raptors. We\'ve lost more than one unwary soldier to them, but I think we can turn them against our Grimtotem neighbors.$B$BTake this rope and use it to capture bloodfen raptors or bloodfen screechers that you\'ve subdued. I wouldn\'t try to capture one of the beasts until you\'ve weakened them quite a bit in combat. It\'s going to be quite a struggle.',objectives_loc4='Sergeant Lukas at North Point Tower wants you to capture 6 raptors. You can capture either Bloodfen Raptors or Bloodfen Screechers.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You look a little scratched up, but nothing major. You\'re certainly in a lot better shape than the Grimtotems will be when our new raptor friends get done with them.' WHERE entry=11146;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Sergeant Lukas at North Point Tower wants you to place the Raptor Bait near the windmill in Blackhoof Village.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<The sergeant doesn\'t bother to hide his grin.>$B$BGood. That ought to forestall a raid or two.' WHERE entry=11147;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Captain Darill inspects the armaments you\'ve brought from Blackhoof Village.>$B$BThere\'s no doubt about it. These match the description exactly, but there\'s just one problem -- these have never been used in battle. Blackhoof Village must not be the only Grimtotem post in the marsh.' WHERE entry=11148;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So you want me to scry for Grimtotems, eh? And what will you say when I tell you there\'s no need?' WHERE entry=11149;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='There\'s no scrying necessary to see the trouble my new "neighbors" are creating. And if this is the band that burnt down the Shady Rest Inn, as you claim, there\'s no reason to tolerate their presence any longer.$B$BTake this torch and raze their camp to the ground! You\'ll find Direhorn just to the north of my farm. You can\'t miss it, really, as the Grimtotems have done a splendid job of announcing their presence with those totems they favor.',objectives_loc4='Burn the North Tent, East Tent, and the Northeast Tent at Direhorn Post, then return to Tabetha at her farm.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I hope the Grimtotems got the message. Any attempt to return will be met with far worse than a mere torch. My apprentices and I will see to that.' WHERE entry=11150;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The captain listens to your report intently.>$B$BWe have avenged James and his family, but not even that can restore what was destroyed.' WHERE entry=11151;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I wish we had a way of letting James Hyal\'s wife and son know that we have brought their murderers to justice.$B$B<Captain Vimes produces a small wreath decorated with flowers.>$B$BThere are some who say that their spirits will know, even if we cannot reach them. It\'s not much, but I\'d like you to lay this wreath at the Hyal family monument. It\'s one of the larger stones in the graveyard just north of Theramore\'s gates.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Captain Vimes smiles slightly as you relate the events you witnessed at the Hyal family grave.>$B$BIt\'s good to know that they understand. You didn\'t tell them about James, did you?$B$BI\'ll deliver his wife\'s message to him, but I doubt he\'ll understand.' WHERE entry=11152;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'s what I wanted to hear!  You\'ve got the stuff, $N, that\'s for sure!$B$BYou think maybe you could come back again tomorrow when we\'ve made more cluster bombs?  I\'d have you back out there right now, but my assistant, Feknut, isn\'t back from collecting more bat guano for them.$B$BI wonder what\'s taking him so long?' WHERE entry=11153;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ugh, what\'s that smell? Ack, it\'s you! Well, I guess I did send you on a smelly job!$B$BThank you, $C. Don\'t worry, I\'ll get this stuff back to Petrov as soon as we get out of here.$B$B<Feknut yells out loud to the explorers.>$B$BYou hear that guys? Lets get the hell out of here!!!' WHERE entry=11154;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This will make a fine meal for the men.$B$B<The chef leans in closer to whisper in your ear.>$B$BHere, deary, take some for yourself. You look like you could use some more meat on your bones!' WHERE entry=11155;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Kill 12 Direhorn Grimtotems and return to Apprentice Morlann at Tabetha\'s Farm.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Apprentice Morlann nods.>$B$BGood. Can\'t say I\'ll miss the company, if you can call it that. You\'d think at least in the middle of the swamp you\'d get some privacy, you know?' WHERE entry=11156;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good work! With any luck at all, the destruction of their egg clutches and whelps should drive off those fiery beasts and prevent that magical blaze from spreading.$B$BWait... what\'s that sound? It sounds like the beating of wings.' WHERE entry=11157;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring 5 Bloodfen Feathers to Brogg at Mudsprocket.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Brogg accepts the feathers.>$B$BBrogg pleased with these feathers. Very strong magic. Brogg not know what raptors do to give feathers power, but raptor feathers always best for ritual.' WHERE entry=11158;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Brogg, at Mudsprocket, wants you to put 10 Stonemaul Spirits to rest.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Brogg thanks you for your help, although he knows Overlord Mok\'Morokk never will. At least surviving Stonemaul can finally focus on problems with the living and leave dead where they belong. Only one thing remains for Brogg to do.' WHERE entry=11159;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Retrieve the Stonemaul Banner and bring it to Brogg at Mudsprocket.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have Brogg\'s thanks, $N. Brogg has big plans for clan banner.' WHERE entry=11160;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have Brogg\'s thanks, $N. Once Brogg adds their magic to the totem, it will be able to redeem the spirits of Brogg\'s fallen friends.' WHERE entry=11161;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Plant the Stonemaul Banner near the entrance to Onyxia\'s Lair, then return to Brogg at Mudsprocket.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Brogg listens as you recount your experience at the entrance to Onyxia\'s lair.>$B$BBrogg suspected Onyxia would be too much of a coward to confront you. Just like black dragonflight to attack when victory is guaranteed.$B$BBrogg is grateful for your help, $N, and he will never forget what you have done for him. Brogg will never give up his quest to bring Stonemaul back where they belong.' WHERE entry=11162;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ahh yeah, these be just what I be needin\'!$B$BHere be the payment I promised ya, $C.' WHERE entry=11164;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I be free!$B$BDey took most everyting when dey nabbed me, but here - take the last of my coin fer your troubles.$B$BAnd the least I can be doin\' is stickin\' around to offer my services....' WHERE entry=11165;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Budd struggles to maintain his composure.>$B$BErr - So, $N - it\'s, uhhh, about time you returned. Yes - in fact you\'re holding up the entire operation.$B$BNow then, let\'s get to filling in this map....' WHERE entry=11166;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s good that you\'re back in one piece. The danger of becoming infected from handling these containers is not non-existent. I suppose I should\'ve warned you about that earlier.' WHERE entry=11167;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Apprentice Garion at Tabetha\'s Farm wants you to test the Captured Totem on 10 Mottled Drywallow Crocolisks or Drywallow Daggermaws.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<The apprentice listens as you describe your experiment.>$B$BA haze and some lightning? That\'s it? There\'s got to be more to the totem than just that! The Grimtotems aren\'t likely to bring something like this to the battlefield unless it has some kind of utility.' WHERE entry=11169;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hmmphh.... the reports from the field are.... not encouraging!' WHERE entry=11170;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Excellent! Everything\'s nearly ready for my grand entrance into Zul\'Aman.$B$BYou\'ve done a fine job, $N. I\'ve spoken with my crew and they\'re warming up to you nicely. I\'d say you\'re very close to becoming a permanent member of the team. Only one thing remains for you to do - dispatch that \'Hex Lord\' fellow.$B$BNothing to it, really. You stand up to this wretch and he\'ll likely just turn and run. Weaker, older trolls just add intimidating titles to their name to make up for their deficiencies, you see?$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Finally! Now that the light work is done, I can at last make yet another mark on history. But first, there\'s one small matter to attend to - You....$B$BI\'m afraid, $N, that the time has come for me to let you go. I feel that your potential has been reached here, if not far exceeded.$B$BDon\'t feel bad, though. After all, it takes an exceptional type of individual to participate in such extraordinary events and not lose their wits. And look here, I have a little something for you to remember me by.' WHERE entry=11171;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Not long ago, a goblin zeppelin crashed to the east. A representative of the Steamwheedle Cartel passed through here a few days ago.$B$BShe was looking for information about the zeppelin\'s cargo and it\'s pilot, Beezil, but none of us really got a good look at the crash. I doubt she\'ll be able to clean up after the wreck by herself, much less recover whatever cargo the vessel might have carried.$B$BIf you have time, you may want to check up on her out at Beezil\'s Wreck, due east of here, near the mountains.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So those hermit mages sent you? How can I be sure that I can trust you?$B$BI suppose I can use the help. There\'s not much here a mage would be interested in, anyway.' WHERE entry=11172;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring 6 vials of Marsh Venom to Apprentice Garion at Tabetha\'s Farm.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Apprentice Garion inspects the venom.>$B$BThis is absolutely perfect! He\'ll never know the difference.' WHERE entry=11173;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, it does look a little cleaner out there...$B$BI suppose it\'s time to get down to the business of salvaging this wreckage.' WHERE entry=11174;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Grrr. I knew it! He\'s sooooo over-protective! This is just embarassing.$B$BNot that I\'m not happy to see you... I am! We all are. We can use your help!' WHERE entry=11175;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Irena sent you over, did she? Good, we\'ve got work for you then!' WHERE entry=11176;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Get off my lawn... unless, that is, you want to help old "Swamp Eye" with a little bit of cooking. Whad\'ya say?' WHERE entry=11177;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Th-the Blood of Zul\'jin himself you say?$B$B<Gathering himself, Budd continues>$B$BWell, I appreciate the gesture, $C, but I could\'ve taken him down with ease. There\'s no way he was as fearful as the legends say. These things have a way of being utterly overstated, as you\'ll learn in time. More likely, the pitiful old cretin was overcome with arthritis!$B$BAnyway, I suppose it was the least you could do as payment for the kindness I\'ve shown you here.$B$BNow off with you - I must dispose of this vile vial!' WHERE entry=11178;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='[Temporarily Deprecated Awaiting a New Mob]Finlay Is Gutless' WHERE entry=11179;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Mordant produces a small sheet of paper and a pen, beginning to scribble down notes on your findings.>$B$BFrom your findings, the spirits in this place must amount to everyone who ever lived on this land, not just the previous occupants.$B$BSomething has been corrupting and killing them. Those who follow don\'t learn the truth until it\'s too late. We have to put an end to this, $N!' WHERE entry=11180;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring 9 sprigs of Witchbane to Mordant Grimsby at Swamplight Manor.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Mordant accepts the bunch of herbs from you.>$B$BThese match the description exactly! I prepared the torch while you were out. All that remains is to fasten the herbs to the end here.' WHERE entry=11181;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Unfortunate that one predator must be used to put down another, but that is the natural order of things.$B$BPerhaps now the proto-drakes and their whelps can go back to living peacefully. Somehow I doubt it with the reawakening of the vrykul.' WHERE entry=11182;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Mordant Grimsby at Swamplight Manor wants you to plant the torch at the end of the dock and defeat anything that appears.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It worked?$B$B<Mordant clears his throat.>$B$BI mean... it worked! Jarl and I are in your debt, $N. Now the only remaining problem is my friend\'s taste in furniture, and I\'m afraid that won\'t be solved as easily.' WHERE entry=11183;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank goodness someone\'s finally taken me up on that offer. I was just thinking that I might need to triple the reward to get that stupid raptor killed, and our budget couldn\'t afford that!' WHERE entry=11184;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Recovered from the body of a Forsaken apothecary, this letter contains alarming evidence of a close alliance between the Grimtotems and the new masters of Lordaeron.$B$B"As a demonstration of good faith and a symbol of our newfound trust, we have dispatched Apothecary Cylla to aid you in battling our mutual enemy in the land of Kalimdor. None will stand before our combined might and determination."$B$BThis letter should be brought to the attention of the SI:7 agent at Tabetha\'s Farm, Andello Porter.',objectives_loc4='Bring the Sealed Letter to Andello Porter at Tabetha\'s Farm.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Andello reads the letter, shocked at its contents.>$B$BWe\'ve long had misgivings about the cooperation between the Horde and the Forsaken, and this only confirms those suspicions. With the backing for Forsaken magic and arms, the Grimtotems would become an even more fearsome enemy. The balance of power in Kalimdor could shift considerably.' WHERE entry=11185;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Malister beckons you closer and speaks in whispered tones.>$B$BI was worried that something like this might happen. I tried to dissuade the captain from this course of action, but he is a dwarf of action with a definite outlook on how things should proceed.$B$BLet us speak of the options left to us.' WHERE entry=11187;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The mage-lieutenant sighs.>$B$BUnfortunate business to be certain. Well, what\'s done is done. With any luck the new whelps that grow to be drakes at Ember Clutch will not retain a memory of our shameful actions therein.$B$BAnd with a bit more luck, the boundaries of that magical forest will not continue to spread.$B$BHere, $N, please take this pittance from the treasury for all of your troubles. It\'s the least that we can do.' WHERE entry=11188;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='One Last Time',objectives_loc4='Escort the Ghost of Explorer Jaren safely to Explorer Irena Stonemantle at Steel Gate in the Howling Fjord.' WHERE entry=11189;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='$G Lad : Lass;, who\'s the genius that made our cannons a non-standard size? Now we have ta make special cannonballs ta shoot out o\' the infernal contraptions!$B$BI would look kindly on ye if ye would go out and find the balls we\'ve already shot. No doubt with the way these louts shoot they be all o\'er the place ta the south and east.$B$B<The cannoneer spaces his hands apart to give you an idea of how big the cannonballs are.>$B$BThat would be faster than us making \'em from scratch fer a certainty.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh, bless ya, $N, bless ya!$B$BJust set \'em down right where yer standin\'. I\'ll have one o\' the boys come load \'em up soon enough and we can stop worryin\' \'bout runnin\' out o\' balls ta shoot at Skorn.' WHERE entry=11190;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good. I can use all the help you can offer. My first priority is to get that lamp re-lit.' WHERE entry=11191;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring 4 containers of Thresher Oil to Babs Fizzletorque at the lighthouse near Theramore.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, I have my doubts, but this is the only solution available right now. Once we have it up and running, I\'m sure there will be time to look at other ways to fuel the lamp.' WHERE entry=11192;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, now, that was thoughtful o\' Babs to send that over. I don\'t know if you\'ve leafed through it or not, but there\'s a lot of truth to the tales in that book. Sailors didn\'t just make it all up, you know.' WHERE entry=11193;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Talk to Nat Pagle at Nat\'s Landing in Tidefury Cove.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So you want to know about sea monsters? Hmm... well, I\'ll make you a deal, but it\'s going to involve a lot of alcohol and some embarrassment on your part.' WHERE entry=11194;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hey now, where ya be gettin\' this?$B$BNo, no, don\'t tell me - this be comin\' from the Hex-Lord himself! It all be clear now. Strong mojo! The bearer of this relic, no matter how many disgraces he be sufferin\', be always honored by his peers. Incredible!$B$B<As Griftah holds the doll in the air, a small, rusty charm falls from around its neck. The troll begins to discard it, but then turns toward you with a gleam in his eye.>$B$BI gots no coins right now, mon, but ya be welcome to this here...' WHERE entry=11195;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Lissen mon, there be sumthin\' else needs doin fer ol\' Prigmon.$B$BZungam, my good-fer-nuthin\' cousin, be stuck inside Zul\'aman. He still be alive too mon - I seen his signal flare just last night!$B$BI should be lettin\' him rot fer gettin\' me tied up in this mess, but he be owin\' me big money.$B$BDo what ya can to help him out, then leave the collectin\' to me!$B$B$B' WHERE entry=11196;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Major Mills at the Theramore docks wants you to defeat Tethyr.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N! I\'ll admit, when I caught my first glimpse of that beast, I had doubts about our ability to defend the docks, but you held together the defenders brilliantly!' WHERE entry=11198;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh good, help, and just in time!' WHERE entry=11199;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Nice!$B$BBut what\'s this about the stuff you found inside those tanks? Are you saying that the Forsaken are spraying a plague upon the vrykul down there?' WHERE entry=11202;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Northeast Plague Tank Destroyed',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Southeast Plague Tank Destroyed' WHERE entry=11202;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Seek Out Tabetha',details_loc4='The arms you captured in Blackhoof Village have not seen any combat beyond mere training exercises, which means the Grimtotems who destroyed the Shady Rest are still at large.$B$BTo the south, in the heart of the Quagmire, lives the witch Tabetha. Though she is a human, she has dealt honorably with us and trained some of our mages.$B$BAsk her for assistance in tracking down the band of Grimtotem responsible for burning the inn. The Alliance must not be allowed to think we were complicit in the attack.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Tabetha smiles slightly.>$B$BKrog wishes me to scry for the Grimtotems, eh? Well, I have no need of magic in this case.$B$BIt seems we have a mutual enemy. The Grimtotems have built an outpost nearby and are a constant thorn in the side of me and my students.' WHERE entry=11203;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='There\'s no scrying necessary to see the trouble my new "neighbors" are creating. And if this is the band that burnt down the Shady Rest Inn, as you claim, there\'s no reason to tolerate their presence any longer.$B$BTake this torch and raze their camp to the ground! You\'ll find Direhorn just to the north of my farm. You can\'t miss it, really, as the Grimtotems have done a splendid job of announcing their presence with those totems they favor.',objectives_loc4='Burn the North Tent, East Tent, and the Northeast Tent at Direhorn Post, then return to Tabetha at her farm.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The Grimtotems should have no trouble understanding our latest message.$B$BAs for you, your contact at Brackenwall Village will want to know of your success. I know the destruction of the Shady Rest Inn could be a source of tensions between the Horde and Alliance. If I encounter any investigators from Theramore, I will gladly tell them the Grimtotems acted on their own.' WHERE entry=11205;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Wow! You certainly found a lot more than I expected would be out there. I\'m not sure how much Drazzit thought we were going to find out here, but he\'s going to have to be happy with this for now.' WHERE entry=11207;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='So you found a copy of Dastardly Denizens of the Deep, did you? Well, I can tell you from experience, it\'s all true. I\'ve even seen a few of \'em with my own eyes.$B$BBut you want to know about Tethyr.  I said I\'d make you a deal, so here\'s what I want you to do. I\'m working on a new line of baits, but I haven\'t tested this one yet.$B$BJust take this paste -- yeah, it smells a little foul -- smear it on yourself, and swim over to that wrecked ship to the southwest. If you survive, let me know how it works!',objectives_loc4='Nat Pagle at Nat\'s Landing wants you to test his new fish bait.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Not bad at all, but you know, I think I\'d get a bath in as soon as possible, if I was you.$B$BNow, about your sea monster...$B$BHelp yourself to a brew or two in the meantime.' WHERE entry=11209;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<You recount your experiences with Nat Pagle, carefully omitting the portion about the \'bait test.\'>$B$BWell, it sounds like we\'ve got our work cut out for us. I\'ll make the preparations.' WHERE entry=11210;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s good of Tabetha to send you down here. I\'d prevail upon her for some food until the wreckage from the zeppelin is taken care of, but I know she\'s got none to spare at the moment. If you\'re feeling adventurous, I\'ve posted a bounty for the death of a particularly nasty raptor.' WHERE entry=11211;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s good of Theramore to send someone. Your guard friend\'s suspicions were correct. We\'ve got some new neighbors, and they aren\'t the kind you\'d bring a casserole.' WHERE entry=11212;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s fortunate Nazeer thought to send someone. We\'ve got some new neighbors and they\'ve been nothing but pests since they set up camp.' WHERE entry=11213;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So Theramore is interested in doing business? Well, that\'s not an offer I\'d turn down. Supplies are pretty scarce here right now, so we need all the business contacts we can get!' WHERE entry=11214;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Help Mudsprocket',details_loc4='The Steamwheedle Cartel\'s new outpost in the southern part of the marsh isn\'t faring so well. The zeppelin carrying supplies to Mudsprocket crashed, leaving them without vital tools, food, and medical supplies.$B$BFollow the road down south and into the marsh\'s interior. You\'ll pass by Tabetha\'s Farm and the Stonemaul Ruins before the road brings you to Mudsprocket. Offer any help you can provide to the town\'s leadership.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I won\'t turn down any help! We\'re in the process of setting up here and trying to make the most of what we\'ve got, until those supplies from the zeppelin arrive.' WHERE entry=11215;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I was sent here by my mentor to look for assistance, but unfortunately I\'m not allowed outside of Lower City and the individuals that frequent this establishment tend to be less than helpful.$B$BYou do seem different, more like the adventurous type.  If you\'re interested in aiding our cause, speak to Archmagae Alturus outside of Medivh\'s old dwelling, Karazhan.$B$BIn the meantime, I\'m going to see about gaining access to the rest of the city.  One of our old associates is rumored to be here.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I thank you for taking the time to come to our aid.  We\'ve important work ahead of us.' WHERE entry=11216;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Gizzix Grimegurgle at Mudsprocket wants you to bring him 8 Wyrmtail stalks.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you! This will help keep our guys going out in the field until Moxie returns with the rest of the supplies from the zeppelin crash.' WHERE entry=11217;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The ore gave you a strange feeling? Maybe we wnon\'t use that stuff after all.$B$B<Steelring looks at the stuff and takes a step back, changing the subject.>$B$BThose gems look really nice! I wonder what I can get for them? Of course, there are always repairs, and new stuff to be made.$B$BYou know, I\'ve really found working with you to be profitable. Take this... it\'s the least that I can do!' WHERE entry=11218;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The fires are out! You and your fire brigade were victorious! Hah!$B$BThe Headless Horseman\'s attack has failed, but until he and his head are destroyed together, He will return.$B$BUntil then, however, let\'s take comfort in the safety you brought our children. I am honored to have watched your brave work today.' WHERE entry=11219;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Until the head of the Headless Horseman is destroyed, his rampage will not end.$B$BThe Horseman rests within the Forlorn Cloister of the Scarlet Monastery, in Tirisfal Glade.  Go to his pumpkin shrine and speak these words:$B$B  Horseman, rise$B  Your time is nigh$B  You felt death once$B  Now, know demise!$B$BThis will rouse the fiend.  Destroy the head of the Horseman\'s and he will plague us no longer.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The origin of this shrine is unknown, but there is no doubt to whom it pays homage...' WHERE entry=11220;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Do not let Lady Prestor\'s protestations distract you, $N. That she is blind to this problem does not surprise me, but that is a separate matter.$B$BAs I was saying, you and Lady Jaina have my thanks for bringing your findings to me in such haste. Let her know that no good citizen of Stormwind will rest until our king walks among us again.$B$BGo to the Mage Quarter at the western end of the city and speak with Archmage Malin at the foot of the tower there. He will speed your return to Theramore.',objectives_loc4='Speak to Lady Jaina Proudmoore in Theramore.',offerrewardtext_loc4='That is excellent news, $N! I was worried the highlord might question the veracity of our information, but I see now my concern was misplaced.$B$BYou are to be well rewarded for your efforts on behalf of Theramore and the Alliance.' WHERE entry=11223;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m indebted to you, $C. At least with most of the mules and equipment recovered, we can hope to rebuild our numbers soon.$B$BPlease, take this.' WHERE entry=11224;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Have you come here to spy on me? No?$B$BPerhaps you have an appreciation for fine cuisine, then? Good, you can help!' WHERE entry=11225;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Did you hunt down some crows, $Gboy:girl;? Good $Gboy:girl;, good $Gboy:girl;!$B$BAh, these hounds remind me of my days raising purebreds in Tirisfal... those were good times!' WHERE entry=11227;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The dwarf speaks the truth. We can\'t afford to lose this port. It\'s one of two safe harbors that the Alliance has on this chunk of frozen hell - the other being a few hundred miles west of here on the coast of the Borean Tundra.' WHERE entry=11228;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='This should have been a walk in the park.  Their forces are hungry, injured and ill equipped.  Yet somehow, we walked right into their trap.$B$BWe approached these reefs from the south to gain cover and were immediately boarded by the Alliance dogs.$B$BI\'m sorry to say, if you want our cannons to fire at anything, you\'re going to have to help us take our ships back.',objectives_loc4='Captain Harker aboard the Windrunner wants you to kill 15 North Fleet Marines.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Nice work paring those mongrels down to size. My men will be able to clean up the rest.' WHERE entry=11230;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Bless you child! With your help, the Light shines even in the darkest of places.$B$BPlease, take this as just compensation for your good deeds. I shall see to the salvation of those you freed; at least, those truly within the Light, and the Alliance, who returned here to the keep.' WHERE entry=11231;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent. I will signal our ground troops to make their move.' WHERE entry=11232;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good work, $N, and good riddance.$B$BBut, what you say about that place troubles me still, and I think our culling is not quite at an end!' WHERE entry=11235;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The captain breathes a sigh of relief.>$B$BWell, that should take some of the pressure off of us.$B$B$N, time and again you have proven yourself invaluable to Westguard Keep and the Alliance at large. Pick something from the treasury, $G boy : girl;! It\'s the least we can do!' WHERE entry=11236;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='$N, we can\'t let this come to pass!' WHERE entry=11237;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You were right to bring this to me, $N. You must take help back north with you to Gjalerbron and slay that wyrm and its master, Wyrmcaller Vile!$B$BEven now, as we speak here, the frost wyrm may be on its way.$B$BHowever, if I\'m reading these plans correctly, blowing the wyrmcaller\'s horn on his platform, outside in the rear left area of Gjalerbron, will call Glacion back. When the creature lands, destroy it!$B$BAnd $N, please bring me the horn. We wouldn\'t want it falling back into the wrong hands.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Wow, that horn is cold!$B$BOnce again you\'ve saved Westguard Keep from certain doom. What a curious $G man : woman; you are, $N. If only there were more of you.$B$BWell, this certainly calls for a reward. Which do you prefer?' WHERE entry=11238;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The priest quietly mouths a benediction for you.>$B$BBless you, $N, you have answered my prayers. Stand proudly in the Light, chin held high with the knowledge that your actions were most holy!$B$BI\'m certain that the church\'s coffers can yield up something of use to you.' WHERE entry=11239;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The sapper grumbles as if he wishes that you hadn\'t succeeded.>$B$BThe captain will be pleased to hear of your success.$B$BYou know, since you\'ve been such a good sport in dealing with this Whisper Gulch business, why don\'t you take your pick of one of these?' WHERE entry=11240;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Rage was my prison, $N, and you have freed me.  Though I thought I did right, my soul now weeps for the terror and the death I have caused the good people of Azeroth.$B$BThank you for leading me back to the Light.  May I never again lose my way.$B$BTake this torn prayer book to an orphan matron, so the children may know that I will haunt them no more.',objectives_loc4='Take the Tome of Thomas Thomson to the Costumed Orphan Matron in Goldshire, Kharanos or Azure Watch.',offerrewardtext_loc4='What is this? The tome of Thomas Thomson? But that is the name of the Horseman before he was cursed! Does this mean that he is finally free? Does this mean he will no longer torment the good people of Azeroth?$B$BWhat a joyous day! $N, your feat will live long with us. The children, and their children, will sing your name!' WHERE entry=11242;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Vice Admiral Keller at Valgarde Port in the Howling Fjord wants you to slay 12 Dragonflayer Invaders or Dragonflayer Worgs.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='You gave our defenders the extra support they needed, $N. Morale is higher than ever now, thanks to you. I think they\'ll be able to handle the remaining onslaught on their own. I\'ve got bigger plans for you...' WHERE entry=11243;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We\'d been here for a month when those malformed giants appeared out of thin air. We were ill-prepared for any sort of attack and paid dearly for our complacency. An entire archaeology team was lost and several townsfolk were abducted and taken to the ruins. We\'ve been on the defensive ever since.$B$BTo make matters worse, the scouts we sent to rescue our people have been harpooned by the vrykul and left for dead in the forest directly north of Valgarde. Dislodge those harpoons and free our scouts!$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='What the vrykul did to our scouts was a gruesome display of savagery. It was a scare tactic, meant to weaken our resolve... to send us running in fear for our lives.$B$BIt failed.$B$BWe are going to show those monsters what it means to wage war against the Alliance!' WHERE entry=11244;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='$G Sir : Ma\'am;, as we move through Skorn, we have to bring down those towers!$B$BIf you have a look at them, you\'ll notice that their tops are lined with casters. Getting too close to them would mean certain doom for us!$B$BHowever, we do have it within our means to call in cannon volleys from Westguard Keep. To do so, we need to get close enough so that you can lob a smoke flare atop of them.$B$BJust don\'t get too close!',offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent targeting, $G sir : ma\'am;! I\'ll have to remember to buy a round for the cannoneers back at the keep.' WHERE entry=11245;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Southwest Tower Targeted',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Southeast Tower Targeted' WHERE entry=11245;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, $G sir : ma\'am;, I have to say that you went about that particular business with a bit of zeal.$B$B<The sergeant looks at you warily.>$B$BAnyway, if you don\'t mind, I\'ll be taking my machete back now. It looks dull and we wouldn\'t want you to accidentally slip and carve me up, too.' WHERE entry=11246;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Very good, $G sir : ma\'am;. That couldn\'t have been done without your help.$B$BI\'m sure that the captain will be pleased with my report on the matter once we\'re done here.' WHERE entry=11247;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Captain Adams has asked you to use the Westguard Command Insignia at Skorn, and then to speak with the Westguard Sergeant.',offerrewardtext_loc4='A pleasure to meet you, $G sir : ma\'am;! I look forward to working with you.$B$BSpeaking of which, we have a great deal to do.' WHERE entry=11248;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes, $G my son : my daughter;, that is ominous-looking, and you obviously had the right of it.$B$BThank you for bringing this scroll to me. I am very keen to study its implications. If I were to hazard a guess, I would say that these vrykul have a way to transcend death; at least those that are worthy.$B$BBy defeating the Winterskorn thane, you proved him unworthy. The Light only knows what he would have become, and what terror he might have rained down upon us, had you not slain him.' WHERE entry=11249;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'s unbelievably good news! I knew that you could pull it off, $N!$B$BAt least someone around here can produce results!$B$BWell, this calls for a reward. Go ahead, take your pick; the treasury is open to you.' WHERE entry=11250;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Late though ye may be, it\'s good to see a friendly face.$B$BNow stop standin\' around with yer thumb up yer nose. there\'s work to be done!' WHERE entry=11251;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Outstanding!$B$BThis could be the turn of luck we\'ve all been hoping for.$B$BWell done, $N!' WHERE entry=11252;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Those soldiers you rescued had a good bit of information for us. These monsters call themselves \'vrykul.\' The tribe that\'s taken up residence in Wyrmskull Village is led by a mystic named Yanis who himself is an underling of another vrykul known as Ingvar the Plunderer.' WHERE entry=11255;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Our elders say that these vrykul may be able to rise from the dead; not unlike the walking dead you call the Scourge, but a different kind of undeath.$B$BWe should not take any chances.$B$BHere, take my machete. As we move through this place, carve up the remains of the vrykul that we slay.$B$BI spent the morning sharpening it, so it should cleave even through their thick bones.',objectives_loc4='The Winterhoof Brave has asked you to use The Brave\'s Machete to dismember 20 Vrykul of the Winterskorn tribe at Skorn.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Have you done that before? Your skill with my machete seemed practiced.$B$B<The brave looks at you warily.>$B$BI\'ll take it back from you now, $C.' WHERE entry=11257;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Chieftain Ashtotem ordered me to destroy many buildings here.$B$BHowever, you are in charge, so it falls to your hands, $N.$B$BI suggest that we burn down the two longhouses and the barracks that are in the lower area of Skorn. All we have to do is get inside each and set them ablaze with this torch.',objectives_loc4='The Winterhoof Brave suggests that you use the Brave\'s Torch to set fire to the Northeast and Northwest Longhouses and the Barracks at Skorn.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<The brave nods at you in clear approval of your handling of the torch>$B$BLet these vrykul feel the heat of the land. Let them know the fear they would instill in others!' WHERE entry=11258;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='As we move through Skorn, we must destroy the towers.$B$BIf you have a look at them, you\'ll notice that their tops are lined with casters. Getting too close to them would mean certain doom.$B$BHowever, we can call in wind rider air strikes from Camp Winterhoof. To do so, we need to get close enough so that you can lob a smoke flare atop of them.$B$BJust don\'t get too close.',objectives_loc4='The Winterhoof Brave has informed you that using the Brave\'s Flare to target all four of the towers at Skorn for air strikes would be advisable.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have a strong arm, $N.$B$BIt looks as if those wind riders finally made themselves useful instead of just standing around and drinking all day.' WHERE entry=11259;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Southwest Tower Targeted',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Southeast Tower Targeted' WHERE entry=11259;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Present the Vrykul Scroll of Ascension near the Thane\'s Pyre to call him out and slay him. Afterward, due to the nature of the ritual, you\'re sure that Greatmother Ankha at Camp Winterhoof will be interested in seeing the scroll.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes, that is ominous-looking, and you obviously had the right of it.$B$BThank you for bringing this scroll to me. I will study its implications. If I were to hazard a guess, I would say that these vrykul have a way to transcend death; at least those that are worthy.$B$BBy defeating the Winterskorn thane, you proved him unworthy. Who knows what he would have become, and what terror he might have rained down upon us, had you not slain him?' WHERE entry=11260;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have my thanks, $N. I know that you do not have any duty to me or my people.$B$BWhat you say about that place troubles me still, and I sense that our culling is not quite at an end.' WHERE entry=11263;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The dead ones are at Gjalerbron and they have necromancers with them?$B$BWe must eliminate the leader of these necrolords.$B$BDo whatever it takes, $N, but see to it that Necro Overlord Mezhen, and whatever he\'s attempting to accomplish, is neutralized.$B$BWe cannot afford to see the vrykul successful in whatever they are doing with these undead creatures!$B$BLook for Mezhen on the platform in the rear right section of Gjalerbron.',objectives_loc4='Kill Necro Overlord Mezhen. Then, return to Chieftain Ashtotem at Camp Winterhoof.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Chieftain Ashtotem breathes a sigh of relief.>$B$BThat should take some of the pressure off.$B$B$N, time and again you have proven your value to the taunka of Camp Winterhoof. Please, choose something from our bounty. I insist.' WHERE entry=11264;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A great stone is lifted from my shoulders to hear of your success. And I smile to know that some you freed were taunka.$B$BPlease, take this as a gift for what you have done. I shall see to the health of those you freed.' WHERE entry=11265;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='These plans detail an imminent attack upon Camp Winterhoof. It would appear that the frost wyrm, Glacion, who circles overhead, is to be used for the offensive.$B$BSurely Celea Frozenmane would be of some assistance in this matter. Deliver the plans to her at the camp to the east.',objectives_loc4='Deliver the Gjalerbron Attack Plans to Celea Frozenmane at Camp Winterhoof.',offerrewardtext_loc4='$N, we cannot let this come to pass!' WHERE entry=11266;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Your instincts were right to bring this to me, but my wind riders cannot fight a dragon. You must take help back west with you to Gjalerbron and slay the frost wyrm and its master, Wyrmcaller Vile!$B$BEven now it may be on its way!$B$BIf I\'m reading these plans correctly, blowing the wyrmcaller\'s horn on his platform, outside in the rear left area of Gjalerbron, will  call Glacion back. When the creature lands, destroy it!$B$BAnd $N, bring me the horn. We wouldn\'t want it falling back into the wrong hands!',objectives_loc4='Slay Wyrmcaller Vile and use the Wyrmcaller\'s Horn to call down and slay Glacion. Then, return with the horn to Celea Frozenmane at Camp Winterhoof.',offerrewardtext_loc4='This horn is as cold as the land... perhaps even colder!$B$BYou have saved Camp Winterhoof from certain doom, not that we\'ll be staying here much longer. What a curious $Gman:woman; you are, $N. Perhaps you $R-types from over the ocean are not so bad after all.$B$BThis calls for a reward. Which do you prefer?' WHERE entry=11267;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank goodness! This should be enough to finish the order in time. Of course, I won\'t sleep until the troops arrive, but that\'s far better than risking Captain Adams\' wrath.$B$BI\'ve heard the stories they tell about him!' WHERE entry=11269;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m glad you\'ve proven you can follow orders. If I had a copper piece for every arrogant fool in shiny armor to come here and think they\'re above the chain of command... well, I\'d have a few gold.$B$BNow that you\'ve demonstrated a measure of discipline, I have other tasks more suitable for someone of your caliber.' WHERE entry=11270;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='This elf prince thinks he can come to my town, insult my queen, kill my men and get away with it?  He thinks we\'re going to stand by while the hordes of Utgarde build up to launch an attack?$B$BNot in a million years.$B$BYou\'re going to walk right into Utgarde and kill him in front of any of these vrykul gorillas that might be watching.  I want Arthas to know that we\'ve arrived and we\'re playing for keeps.',objectives_loc4='High Executor Anselm wants you to to go into Utgarde and slay Prince Keleseth.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Revenge feels good. To think that this is but a taste of what\'s to come.$B$BArthas will get what he deserves soon enough. Then and only then will I die a happy man.' WHERE entry=11272;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve found Pulroy. A bit too late it seems.$B$BWhile looking over the corpse you see a journal clenched tightly in Pulroy\'s death grip. Upon examining the journal you read what appears to be the scribbling of a dying dwarf.' WHERE entry=11273;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve found Zedd. You\'re no doctor but the prognosis for Zedd is most assuredly negative.$B$BIt looks as if they were preparing to feed him to the worgs. Gruesome...' WHERE entry=11274;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='About bloody time! Pulroy and Zedd are dead.$B$BAnd Daegarn...$B$B<Glorenfeld shakes his head.>$B$BTaken by the Dragonflayer chieftain into the depths of these catacombs. I overheard that oversized mongrel mention something \'bout a sacrifice to the "Dread King."$B$BThe cipher is hidden away in Daegarn\'s grimy beard.$B$BWhat? Dwarves hide things in their beards all the time!' WHERE entry=11276;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done well, mate. Now that we\'ve secured the tablets we can try and save Daegarn\'s life and recover the cipher that will help us decode the meaning behind these ancient relics!$B$BI\'ll hold on to these tablets, you rescue Daegarn.' WHERE entry=11277;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Sorting these tablets out is going to take some time. All I can gather from a precursory study is that whatever used to be here was an ancestor of the humans. Those vrykul things probably killed \'em all off. Anyhow, we\'ll know more once I get these relics set up.' WHERE entry=11278;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What?! No, this can\'t be right.$B$BCURSES!$B$BThis batch of the plague doesn\'t seem to have had any real effect on the proto-whelps at all other than to make them glow green!$B$BMy dream of using the plague upon anything we come into contact with seems to have gone up in smoke!' WHERE entry=11279;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Mimicking Nature\'s Call',objectives_loc4='Test the Carved Horn and then return to Nokoma Snowseer at Camp Winterhoof with the results.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Nokoma listens to your report from the test.>$B$BI\'m relieved that the horn worked so well... maybe too well if what you\'re saying was true. You\'re sure the beast spoke? I don\'t know if I can go on with the hunt if that\'s true. I\'ll have to speak with Chief Ashtotem about it.$B$BThis horn may end up being merely decorative, but that won\'t diminish its worth. Thank you for all your help, $N.' WHERE entry=11281;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done it? By the Light, you\'re a walking miracle! I was beginning to think I\'d personally have to explain to Captain Adams why his men\'s weapons weren\'t ready in time!' WHERE entry=11284;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I guess you burned everything. I see couple of spots not burning... but is close enough for Gorth.' WHERE entry=11285;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Winterskorn Bridge Burned',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Winterskorn Barracks Burned' WHERE entry=11285;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='My mother should not concern herself with my safety. But, I thank you for coming, stranger.$B$BSince you are here, perhaps you will help me with a few things?' WHERE entry=11287;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='<Ares gasps for air as he tries to speak.>$B$BI am an envoy of the Argent Crusade, charged with a sacred duty.$B$BOur forces were decimated in the Plaguelands. By the light of dawn, the artifact was cleansed and made pure once more. So many perished in the wake of its redemption.$B$BThere is still a chance... still time.$B$BThe artifact was hurled into the den of the fallen, far below us. Guarded by the unmerciful dead.$B$B<Ares\' body glows with blinding light.>$B$BLight. Will. Protect. You.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='You feel compelled to place the sacred blade next to the body of Ares.$B$BUpon doing this you are once again blinded by light.' WHERE entry=11288;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Many men and women died to recover this blade. $N, I fear valiant Ares will not be the last.$B$BBut you do the Light\'s work, hero. This sacred blade will be wielded by Lord Tirion Fordring himself. Even now the Argent Crusade works toward Icecrown. Lord Fordring has vowed that he will tear down the walls of the cursed place himself! And with the blade, he just might stand a chance against the Lich King.$B$BLord Fordring remains our greatest hope.' WHERE entry=11289;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Vice Admiral Keller at Valgarde Port in the Howling Fjord has asked that you bring him the Dragonflayer Battle Plans.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Vice Admiral Keller glances over the plans.>$B$BOutstanding! By the looks of things, there are many more vrykul villages in the fjord. A different tribe of vrykul is preparing an assault on Westguard Keep. Hell, for all I know it may already be too late. We haven\'t heard from Westguard in days. Either way, we must alert Westguard!' WHERE entry=11290;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Take the Dragonflayer Battle Plans to Captain Adams at Westguard Keep in the Howling Fjord.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Captain Adams takes the plans from you.>$B$BI\'m glad you decided to come over. My advisors and I will need some time to study these plans. In the meantime, we can use all the help we can get!' WHERE entry=11291;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Trapper Jethan inspects the creatures you\'ve brought him.>$B$BNicely done. Some of these will fetch a better price than others, but I should have plenty to trade with the locals.' WHERE entry=11292;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We need to get the word out about the Barleybrews at Brewfest.  You need to shout at the flags outside the bank, in the Military Ward, in the Hall of Explorers and in the Mystic Ward.  I\'ll make things easy though, I\'ll lend you some racing ram reins and a racing ram for 4 minutes.  Use the reins to let him go, but try not to tire him out.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done! That kinda shouting is sure to bring business our way.$B$BAnd we promised you a reward, here it is. The Barleybrew\'s keep their word.$B$BOh, and come back any other day if you want to help spread the good name of Barleybrew.' WHERE entry=11293;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Bark in the Hall of Explorers',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Bark in the Mystic Ward' WHERE entry=11293;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Bark for the Thunderbrews!',details_loc4='It\'s time to let people know that the Thunderbrew have heard their cries for good brew.  You need to shout at the flags outside the bank, in the Military Ward, in the Hall of Explorers and in the Mystic Ward.$B$BWe\'ll make it easy though.  We\'ll lend you a ram AND some reins for 4 minutes.$B$BBe careful with going too fast though since you won\'t find any apple crates in Ironforge...  We can\'t take the chance of helping out the Barleybrew messengers.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Good job! That\'ll show those arrogant Barleybrews.$B$BWell we promised you a reward and here it is. We Thunderbrew reward you with prizes, the Barleybrew reward you with foul odors and false promises.$B$BYou chose wisely.$B$BIf you want to keep making the right choice, stop by another day and help us spread the word.' WHERE entry=11294;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Bark in the Hall of Explorers',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Bark in the Mystic Ward' WHERE entry=11294;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, yes, the reclusive bison-men of the north. I\'ve seen them skulking about, believing themselves unseen. I suppose they fancy this land theirs? Well, that\'s but one of many things that will change shortly.$B$BI wasn\'t expecting any company, but while you\'re here on that fool\'s errand, you might as well make yourself useful.' WHERE entry=11297;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You might have already seen the room where Daegarn is being held while you were gatherin\' the tablets. It\'s through this corridor and then down a set of steps. Daegarn will be in the room at the bottom of the steps - locked up tight!$B$BGet down there and find him. At the very least you might be able to get the cipher from him.',objectives_loc4='Find Daegarn in the Ring of Judgement located inside the Utgarde Catacombs.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Yep. You found me. Woopedy-do!$B$BAnd no, I don\'t have the cipher. My beard was the first thing those beasts checked! Oluf\'s the one that\'s got it now. He\'s the chieftain of the gladiators.' WHERE entry=11299;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Oluf will come out if you defeat the other gladiators. That\'s \'bout the only way we\'re getting\' that cipher back. Put on your whompin\' boots and get busy in the Ring of Judgement. If you do manage to get the cipher back, return it to Glorenfeld o\'er near the entrance to these catacombs.$B$BMe? Don\'t worry about me! We\'re on the brink of discovering the missing link to human-kind!',objectives_loc4='Defeat the gladiators at the Ring of Judgement and face Oluf the Violent. Defeat Oluf and recover the Ancient Cipher.$B$BReturn the Ancient Cipher to Glorenfeld at the entrance to the Utgarde Catacombs.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Fascinating tale! Something is actually judgin\' these things? To what end?! For what purpose?$B$BWell, never mind that nonsense. Someone else can figure out that stuff. We got the cipher and the tablets back - and only two fatalities in the whole ordeal.' WHERE entry=11300;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Lurielle listens as you introduce yourself.>$B$BIt is good to finally meet you, $N. We have long hoped that you and the other newcomers might send representatives. We don\'t often venture beyond the borders of our glades, especially amid the changes the land is going through.' WHERE entry=11302;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I\'m afraid our equipment isn\'t exactly the best here at Vengeance Landing.  After all it\'s a military controlled outpost.$B$BI will need you to take a sample of this strain to Chief Plaguebringer Harris in New Agamand, follow the road beyond Baleheim south and then west.  They have better equipment there - he will know what to do.$B$BYou must hurry, $N.  Our enemies are stronger and more numerous than us.  We need to develop a viable weapon against them!',objectives_loc4='Bring Lysander\'s Strain to Chief Plaguebringer Harris in New Agamand in western Howling Fjord.',offerrewardtext_loc4='This strain is far from worthless, my friend! Those fools at Vengeance Landing have had all the answers right under their own noses!' WHERE entry=11304;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='For generations, my people have told tales of frost nymphs cavorting in glades hidden away in the wilderness. I used to search for them as a child, against the advice of my parents, until I nearly froze to death.$B$BThese days, it isn\'t necessary to comb the forests for them. They\'ve decided to reveal themselves for reasons I can only guess, but I don\'t think the change can be ignored. Venture southeast to the Frozen Glade and seek out the nymphs, but beware; you will pass the Twisted Glade on your way.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Lurielle listens as you introduce yourself.>$B$BIt is good to meet you, $C. My sisters have often watched the taunka search the forests for us, but we are forbidden by our queen from interacting with outsiders. You only see us now because the land has become unsettled and many of my sisters are in danger.' WHERE entry=11312;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Lurielle accepts the cores from you quietly.>$B$BThank you, $N.$B$B<Lurielle glances at the icy cores sadly.>$B$BI promise, my friends, I will do all I can to restore you.' WHERE entry=11313;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So there is hope for my sisters?$B$B<Lurielle looks away from you, then down at the ground.>$B$BI feel guilty for not thinking of the pendant sooner. We might have saved even more of the sisters.' WHERE entry=11314;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you for your help, $N. The Vibrant Glade was once a beautiful place, and when we return to it, we shall make it so again.' WHERE entry=11315;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well, $N. If we\'d had allies like you when the land first began to change, perhaps we might have been able to preserve some of what we\'ve lost.' WHERE entry=11316;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We braved the Rivenwood because of my troubled dreams concerning my worg life-friend, Ulfang. He has called out for help, and you must go to him.$B$BBut, you do not have the means to speak with him, or walk amongst the other worgs. I know a way.$B$BFirst, you must cleanse your inner turmoil.$B$BThere is a shrine that sits at the top of Frostblade Peak, northeast of Camp Winterhoof. A single path leads up to it from the western base of the mountain.$B$BMeditate there and then return to me.',objectives_loc4='Sage Mistwalker at Steel Gate has advised you to cleanse yourself of Your Inner Turmoil through meditation at the Frostblade Shrine.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Already I can sense the change within you.$B$BAre you ready for what comes next?' WHERE entry=11317;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Nice work there! It takes time to get the hang of controlling your ram. But once you do, you\'ll wish every ram was a racing ram.$B$BWhat\'s that? "Where\'s my reward?" Ha Ha Ha... you got to ride the fastest ram around! You want more? Well how about this...$B$BYou\'ve been rewarded with the chance to help other people around Brewfest. There\'s plenty of work, and rewards, for an eager, young, ram racer.' WHERE entry=11318;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The ice core worked well for you? I\'ll have to remember that. I\'m certain the keepers will not stop just because we\'ve destroyed their work once.' WHERE entry=11319;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Did Someone Say "Souvenir?"',details_loc4='Brewfest isn\'t just about racing rams, it\'s also about drinking!  When you have a moment, take this voucher to Belbi Quikswitch.  She\'s near the back of the Brewfest camp.  If you can\'t see her, don\'t worry, she\'ll be sure to see you.$B$BIn any case, take this voucher to her to get your free Brewfest stein.  She\'ll also be more than happy to handle any and all other Brewfest transactions.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Aww, it\'s just a stein voucher... Maybe you\'re just playing hard to get. So here\'s this years stein for you.$B$BBut I suspect I\'ll be seeing a lot more of you. After all, if you want any Brewfest tickets redeemed, I\'m your girl...$B$Bor maybe I\'m his girl...$B$Booohhh.... or his...' WHERE entry=11321;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Already I can sense the change within you.$B$BAre you ready for what comes next?' WHERE entry=11322;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='From my dreams, I know that Ulfang is in a cave on the snowy northwestern edge of the Rivenwood.$B$BHe is in great danger.$B$BI have devised a magical disguise that will make you appear as a worg while you are within the Rivenwood. The disguise is weak, relying upon the strange magics of that haunted wood. While it will only convince the worgs, it will allow you to get close to Ulfang.$B$BPlease, $C, find and help him.',objectives_loc4='Sage Mistwalker has asked you to seek out and help Ulfang in the Rivenwood.$B$BIf you somehow lose the Worg Disguise, return to Sage Mistwalker for a replacement.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You look and smell different... you are not one of my pack. Tell me your story; I have nothing but time while I am trapped in here.' WHERE entry=11323;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Watcher Moonleaf has asked you to seek out and help Ulfang in the Rivenwood.$B$BIf you somehow lose the Worg Disguise, return to Watcher Moonleaf for a replacement.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You look and smell different... you are not one of my pack. Tell me your story; I have nothing but time while I am trapped in here.' WHERE entry=11325;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Alpha Worg',details_loc4='When you\'ve eaten Talonshrike\'s eyes, you should be able see Garwal and rip out his throat!$B$B$R-thing, seek out and slay Garwal in the western Rivenwood. After you have killed him, go and tell Moonleaf that I am once more the alpha worg!',offerrewardtext_loc4='Garwal was not a worg at all! The thing you describe him turning into sounds a lot like a worgen!$B$BBut, Ulfang said that it came south from the Grizzly Hills? Odd. There aren\'t any worgen there.$B$BI thank you for helping to restore Ulfang to his proper place amongst his pack. Now we both will be able to sleep peacefully.$B$BPlease, you must accept this as a sign of gratitude.' WHERE entry=11326;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Holy... what the hell?! Look at this stuff!$B$BWe need to get this back to the keep a.s.a.p.!' WHERE entry=11327;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh... hey, that\'sh different!$B$BOkay, let me shee that shtuff. I jusht love tinkering with alchemy!$B$BInteresting, interesting... here, I think I know jusht what to do. A little mixing of that with the jusht the right amount of thish.$B$BYou know, I think a little dash of this rotgut will help, too ...hic!' WHERE entry=11328;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, these certainly are ugly enough, but I suppose I don\'t care if it actually works. I\'ll be relieved once the expedition has passed through and I can go back to simply fishing for my dinner.' WHERE entry=11329;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Huh? Well that sucks! Darn, I made thingsh worsh. In fact, I think I perfected their plague for them ...hic!$B$B<Peppy grimaces and takes a huge gulp of whatever noxious brew she\'s been drinking.>$B$BWell, I wash hoping that it wouldn\'t come down to thish, but it looks like there\'sh no alternative ...hic.' WHERE entry=11330;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes, $N, what is it now?$B$BWHAT?!! A Forsaken super plague that melts you in no time?$B$BYou oozed my vrykul prisoner?$B$B<The captain looks almost sad and spits in disgust.>$B$BAlright, I know what we need to do. Or rather, what YOU need to do!' WHERE entry=11331;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Nicely done, $N, nicely done!$B$B<The captain seems beside himself with glee.>$B$BThat\'ll show those good-for-nothing Forsaken to think about messing with us!$B$BI\'d say you\'ve earned yourself something from the treasury!' WHERE entry=11332;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A bit worse for the wear but still functional.$B$B<Thoralius reaches into the pouch and removes some odd looking roots.>$B$BNow to place them in the fire and inhale!$B$B<Thoralius throws the roots into the smoldering incense burner.>$B$B<Thoralius inhales deeply. His body begins to quiver.>$B$BWha... What... It cannot be... I cannot...' WHERE entry=11333;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='[PH] Shoot a marked target.',objectives_loc4='[PH] Rinling wants you to shoot a marked target and then return the Target Rifle to him.' WHERE entry=11334;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Win an Arathi Basin battleground match and return to an Alliance Brigadier General at any Alliance capital city or Shattrath.' WHERE entry=11335;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Win an Alterac Valley battleground match and return to an Alliance Brigadier General at any Alliance capital city or Shattrath.$B' WHERE entry=11336;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Win an Eye of the Storm battleground match and return to an Alliance Brigadier General at any Alliance capital city or Shattrath.' WHERE entry=11337;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Win a Warsong Gulch battleground match and return to an Alliance Brigadier General at any Alliance capital city or Shattrath.' WHERE entry=11338;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Win an Arathi Basin battleground match and return to a Horde Warbringer at any Horde capital city or Shattrath.' WHERE entry=11339;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We\'ve recently come extremely close to driving the Stormpike invaders from Alterac Valley.  As a result we\'re redirecting all our reinforcements to aid the Frostwolf Clan.$B$BA decisive victory there would free up the resources we need to crush the Alliance scum on all the other battlefronts.$B$BGo, $N.  Earn great honor by heeding the call of the brave Frostwolf warriors.',objectives_loc4='Win an Alterac Valley battleground match and return to a Horde Warbringer at any Horde capital city or Shattrath.' WHERE entry=11340;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We will fight and crush the enemy wherever we find them.  Azeroth, Outland, the place makes no difference.$B$BWe cannot allow the Alliance to establish superiority in the Eye of the Storm.  Take the battle to them today... tomorrow it might be too late!',objectives_loc4='Win an Eye of the Storm battleground match and return to a Horde Warbringer at any Horde capital city or Shattrath.' WHERE entry=11341;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The Alliance is an insidious enemy, $N.  They claim to defend the Ashenvale forests to justify their acts of aggression against our territories in the Barrens.$B$BToday we have an opportunity to drive the enemy from our lands once and for all.  Go to Warsong Gulch and take back what is rightfully ours!',objectives_loc4='Win a Warsong Gulch battleground match and return to a Horde Warbringer at any Horde capital city or Shattrath.' WHERE entry=11342;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I do not understand. The creatures that you saw looked like the vrykul that are attacking Valgarde?' WHERE entry=11343;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Human children born of vrykul? And Ymiron ordered the deaths of all human born offspring?$B$B<Thoralius goes silent for a moment.>$B$BAs much as I wish to deny what is so plainly presented to me, I cannot. There is no extinct "missing link" to humans as the Explorers\' League proposed. The vrykul are the missing link. They are the progenitors of humanity.' WHERE entry=11344;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Prospector Belvar browses the book of runes.>$B$BHmm... there\'s so much here. I\'m going to need some time to study it, and if we hope to understand these runes, we\'ll need to try to make our own.' WHERE entry=11346;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done well in defeating Binder Murdis, but the Iron Dwarves won\'t give up easily.$B$BWe\'ve made a lot of progress in understanding how they manipulate runes. Perhaps next time we encounter them, our knowledge will give us an advantage.' WHERE entry=11348;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Belvar handles the tools carefully.>$B$BI\'m going to try these out. If we\'re to understand the Iron Dwarves\' motives and defeat them, I need to know exactly what the runes are doing.' WHERE entry=11349;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The longrunner browses the book of runes.>$B$BI\'m no loremaster, but I have some familiarity with the language of the Iron Dwarves. I think the runes they\'re carving on the giants are derived from their spoken language, but there are some differences.' WHERE entry=11350;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I think I\'ve figured out what the Iron Dwarves are doing. The tools they use are imbued with magic during their forging.$B$BWhen they\'re used to carve runes, the symbols form much more than mere words. These runes have the power to bind, compel, and twist.$B$BIf I had a set of those tools, I could mimic the runes in the book. I captured one of these boxes from one of the pavilions at Giants\' Run, but it was empty. Look for similar boxes and recover a set of tools from them.',objectives_loc4='Bring a set of Iron Rune Carving Tools to Longrunner Pembe at Camp Winterhoof.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Pembe examines the tools.>$B$BThese are more delicate than I\'d thought. Allow me a moment to try them out.' WHERE entry=11351;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done well in defeating Binder Murdis, but the Iron Dwarves won\'t give up easily.$B$BAs my people move north, I\'m certain we will encounter the Iron Dwarves again. Next time, we will be prepared to thwart them before they can dig in.' WHERE entry=11352;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Researcher Aderan listens to your findings.>$B$BThe runes for "north" and "west" appeared multiple times? There\'s a highly reinforced command to move in that direction, but the runes are more than propulsion. Something is attracting them, but what?' WHERE entry=11355;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re here to visit the children!  Wonderful!  They have known such heartache in their short lives.  It is good that they see real heroes like you.  It really lifts their spirits!' WHERE entry=11356;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='For Hallow\'s End, orc orphans were taken on a trip to many Horde villages.  The orphan matrons thought it would be good for them to see real heroes adventuring in the field.$B$BWhy don\'t you visit them?  A brave $C like yourself could strengthen their spirits with tales of your valor!  Go to either Razor Hill in Durotar, Brill in Tirisfal Glades or Falconwing Square in Eversong Woods.  Speak with the masked orphan matron and she\'ll introduce you to the children.',objectives_loc4='Speak with a Masked Orphan Matron in either Razor Hill, Brill or Falconwing Square.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The children love to watch heroes at their work.  It is my hope that, one day, each of these orphans will grow into a strong member of the Horde, and ultimately die in glorious battle!$B$BAh, thoughts of such a fine fate brings mist to my eyes...' WHERE entry=11357;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Aderan listens as you describe your findings.>$B$BOf course! This Megalith must be the key to the Iron Dwarves\' plans. We must destroy it before their plan comes to fruition!' WHERE entry=11358;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done well in felling Megalith, but I wonder about his final words.$B$BYou\'re sure he said the Stoneforge?$B$BI know of no place with that name, but it sounds like a word with origins in the titans. What plans do the Iron Dwarves have for such a thing? This bears watching, $N, for we must find it before the Iron Dwarves\' plan comes to fruition.' WHERE entry=11359;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Throw water buckets onto 5 fires, and then speak with the Costumed Orphan Matron.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re wet and smudged with soot!  You must have been extinguishing fires!$B$BWell done!  As an honorary member of the Goldshire Fire Brigade, I beg you to return here if ever the village needs you!' WHERE entry=11360;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Toss buckets on 5 fires, then speak with the Masked Orphan Matron in Razor Hill.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N! Children, take a good look at this $C. Grow strong and brave like him and one day you too will fight for the Horde.' WHERE entry=11361;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Very well, you have earned your bounty.$B$BReturn again tomorrow and the winds will have whispered once more to Mah\'duun.' WHERE entry=11364;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='To the east, at Giants\' Run, rune-inscribed stone giants have started to migrate north toward Frostblade Peak. I know nothing of their goals, nor of their destination.$B$BThe glowing runes inscribed in the stone flesh of the giants guide them on their journey. Fell some of these giants.$B$BTake this pick with you and use it on the corpses of the runed stone giants. It will deactivate the runes. Once you\'ve tested enough giants, return to me with your findings.',objectives_loc4='Sage Edan and Camp Winterhoof wants you to use the Runeseeking Pick on the corpses of 4 Runed Stone Giants.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<The sage listens to your findings.>$B$BThe runes for "north" and "west" appeared over and over? I\'m not an expert in these runes, but the repetition of them suggests a strong command.$B$BThese carvings are more than passive directions, though. They seem to pull the giants toward something, but what?' WHERE entry=11365;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We must find what\'s luring the giants northwest, so we can stop them before they reach their destination.$B$BWhile the rune samples gave us some clues, the unknown runes worry me.$B$BWhen I visited Giants\' Run, I noticed a large broken tablet jutting from the ground where the northeastern part of the area met the snow at the foot of Frostblade Peak. Take this sample, compare the runes with the tablet, and see what you can learn about the identity of this lodestone.',objectives_loc4='Sage Edan at Camp Winterhoof wants you to compare the Rune Sample with the Broken Tablet.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Edan listens as you describe your findings.>$B$BMegalith? A literal transcription from the tablet! This Megalith must be the centerpiece of the iron ones\' mysterious plans.' WHERE entry=11366;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done well in felling Megalith, but I wonder about his final words.$B$BYou\'re sure he said the Stoneforge?$B$BIt is not a name our people know, but it sounds like it might be a creation of the "titans" the ousiders speak of. The Iron Dwarves have ever been a cunning and dangerous foe, $N. We must watch these giants and find this Stoneforge before they can carry out their plans.' WHERE entry=11367;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I trust that it was a fight worthy of your time? Certainly this bounty will be.$B$BReturn again tomorrow and the winds will have whispered once more to Mah\'duun.' WHERE entry=11371;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re quite the heroine, $N. I am certain that my customer will find a way to free the spirit of their loved one from within the gem. For a job well done, your payment awaits.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE entry=11374;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh, I do smell something tasty! I hope you gave that bird quite a good beating.$B$BPlease, help yourself to some of my extra stock. I\'m sure someone of your talent could put it to good use.' WHERE entry=11377;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Now look at that...$B$B<The Rokk takes a sip of the concoction and his face twists into a bizarre mask of pain and delight.>$B$BSweet A\'dal that\'s good! A cook with your potential shouldn\'t be without his proper materials. Take some of my extra stock and make me proud.' WHERE entry=11379;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Those are the juiciest mana berries I\'ve ever seen. I think I\'m getting smarter just by looking at them.$B$BSince I no longer need most of my meat and fish stock, why don\'t you take some? I\'m certain you could make something delicious.' WHERE entry=11380;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That is a fine batch of spiritual soup if I ever did smell one. Just a pinch of pepper and it\'s done.$B$BAs promised, here\'s your cut. And because you did such a fine job, I\'m going to throw in some of my extra stock.' WHERE entry=11381;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You found your way back in time, and then back again. You must be a great $C, $R. The bounty is earned.$B$BReturn again tomorrow and the winds will have whispered once more to Mah\'duun.' WHERE entry=11383;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Mah\'duun enjoys fighting constructs; they are less messy than organic beings.$B$BThe bounty is yours.$B$BReturn again tomorrow and the winds will have whispered once more to Mah\'duun.' WHERE entry=11387;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good job, though I think ye might be wanting a refresher course in basic piloting.$B$BWell, no matter, one warm body\'s as good as another. Here\'s yer haul for the day.' WHERE entry=11390;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Nice shooting, ace.$B$BHere\'s your wages. Come back tomorrow for another round, ya hear?' WHERE entry=11391;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Many dreary candles adorn this pumpkin shrine.' WHERE entry=11392;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The explorer beams a smile as you tell him who sent you. He continues in hushed tones.>$B$BIrena was concerned about me? She gets that from her father you know.' WHERE entry=11393;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Jaren seems very excited about your success, but motions you to keep your conversation to a whisper.>$B$BGreat job, $N! That\'s a lot of Scourge goo all over your stuff though. You might want to think about a quick dip in the strait. It\'s cold, but it\'ll get you cleaned up right quick.' WHERE entry=11394;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I know what this is! $N, it\'s a controlling device for those scourging crystals!$B$BI bet anything that it can be used to shut down their force fields. Hmmm.$B$B<The explorer looks thoughtful as he ponders the implications of you having the device.>' WHERE entry=11395;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Nice!$B$B<Jaren looks around quickly to make sure that nothing noticed his outburst.>$B$BAlright, you certainly earned your pick of one of these things I found while I was down here.$B$BAnd, $N, if you happen to find yourself back at Steel Gate, give Irena my love and let her know that I\'m okay.' WHERE entry=11396;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I came here to investigate a rumor about a Scourge presence nearby. I expected murlocs along the coast down below, but I never thought I\'d see this!$B$BThe Scourge are down there, and they\'re changing murlocs, and anything else they can get their hands on, into the walking dead!$B$B$C, we will not suffer them to create more of their kind, especially not from murlocs! There is a ramp down to the beach just northwest of the camp. See to it that you deal with the Scourge in a timely fashion!',objectives_loc4='Apothecary Anastasia has asked you to destroy 15 Scourge of any type along the Chillmere Coast. Return to her at the Apothecary Camp once you have done so.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Anastasia ponders your success for a moment.>$B$BA satisfactory job to be certain, yet somehow I sense that there\'s something else we should be doing to stop the efforts of the Scourge on that beach.' WHERE entry=11397;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The Scourge creature you just destroyed had this device held in its clutches. It has a jewel set into it which looks similar to the one that tops the scourging crystals.$B$BSurely, Apothecary Anastasia would like to have a look at this.',objectives_loc4='Deliver the Scourge Device to Apothecary Anastasia at the Apothecary Camp.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I can tell you what this is, $N. It\'s a controlling device for those scourging crystals down there!$B$BI bet anything that it can be used to shut down their force fields. Hmmm.$B$B<The apothecary looks thoughtful as she ponders the implications of you having the device.>' WHERE entry=11398;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Look at the button on the side of the controller here. I bet if you got close enough to one of those scourging crystals, you could use the controller to bring its shield down. Then it would simply be a matter of destroying the thing before its shield goes back up.$B$BBrave enough to hazard another trip down there, $N? I can guarantee a nice reward for you if you can bring down those shields and destroy the crystals.$B$BHow can you refuse if it means less Scourge, especially ones made from murlocs?',objectives_loc4='Apothecary Anastasia at the Apothecary Camp has asked you to destroy 3 Scourging Crystals.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Anastasia turns and smiles at her succubus.>$B$BVery well, $N, I concede that you have certainly earned a choice of one of these.' WHERE entry=11399;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good job, $N... you\'ve won the trust of the festival\'s brewers, earning the right to purchase a Brewfest riding ram.' WHERE entry=11400;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Rage was my prison, $N, and you have freed me.  Though I thought I did right, my soul now weeps for the terror and the death I have caused the good people of Azeroth.$B$BThank you for leading me back to the Light.  May I never again lose my way.$B$BTake this torn prayer book to an orphan matron, so the children will know that I will haunt them no more.',objectives_loc4='Take the Tome of Thomas Thomson to a Masked Orphan Matron in Durotar, Brill or Falconwing Square.',offerrewardtext_loc4='What? This holy tome once belonged to an infamous paladin of the Alliance. Was he the Headless Horseman? Does this mean that the Horseman is defeated?$B$BThis is a glorious day, $N! Your legend will shine bright, and may it last for twice the years of the Horseman\'s reign of fear.' WHERE entry=11403;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Will you lay the candle down and call the Headless Horseman from his doomed rest?' WHERE entry=11404;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So the quartermaster sent you?$B$B<Gil seems relieved.>$B$BTo be honest, we\'re running a bit behind here and we\'re going to need some help making our goals.$B$B<Gil shudders.>$B$BNone of the men want to brave the wrath of Captain Adams.' WHERE entry=11406;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Bark in the Valley of Wisdom',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Bark in the Valley of Spirits' WHERE entry=11407;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Bark in the Valley of Wisdom',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Bark in the Valley of Spirits' WHERE entry=11408;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='So you want to check out the racing rams?  The dwarves think they have got a handle on it, but let\'s be honest, they are drunk most of the time, so how hard can it really be?$B$BNow before I let you strut your stuff, you\'ll need to show me that you can handle these fine, legally obtained creatures.$B$BSo here\'s the deal:  I\'ll lend you some racing reins and the use of a ram. You need to prove to me that you can handle using these rams.$B$BKeep the ram at a trot, canter and gallop for 8 seconds each.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Hey, that wasn\'t too bad... are you sure you\'re not a dwarf?$B$BSo there\'s plenty more racing to be had and it\'s not just from me. All over the Brewfest grounds you\'ll find people in need of a decent ram racer. So go and make yourself useful.$B$BOh and don\'t forget, these rams were legally obtained. I just want to make sure we\'re clear.' WHERE entry=11409;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='At last, we can finally fish in peace! \'Course, by the time we catch anything, the expedition\'ll arrive and claim it all for themselves.$B$BYou have our thanks, $N. Don\'t be a stranger \'round here.' WHERE entry=11410;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='In my travels as a courier, I\'ve seen a number of strange denizens of the Howling Fjord, but one group stands out. From a distance, they look like tauren, but upon closer inspection, they\'re quite different -- sturdier and shaggier.$B$BI found one of their settlements far to the north, beyond Halgrind, Skorn, and the northern forests. Camp Winterhoof, it\'s called, and it sits in the foothills of Gjalerhorn near the border with Grizzly Hills. Make contact with them, and see if they might be of use to us.',objectives_loc4='Speak to Chieftain Ashtotem at Camp Winterhoof.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<The chieftain listens as you introduce yourself.>$B$BI am Chieftain Ashtotem, and my people are the taunka, and I will speak truly, outsider. Among my people, trust is earned, not given. You have my leave to walk among them and offer your assistance. Time grows short and some of them may welcome even an outsider\'s help with their preparations.' WHERE entry=11411;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Am I glad you\'re here.  We are in big trouble!  The goblin that was supposed to be bringing us more brew had an accident on his way from Razor Hill.  You gotta get us that brew!$B$BI\'ll put you on one of my racing rams and you follow the road to Razor Hill.$B$BOnce you get near him he\'ll toss you a keg, then you run the keg back here and toss the keg to my more capable assistant.  For now, all we want are 3 kegs.  Do a good job and maybe we\'ll have another job for you.',objectives_loc4='Get a keg from the Goblin stranded on the road to Razor Hill and return it to Ram Master Ray\'s assistant.  Do this 3 times before your ram goes away.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Thanks for your help! As long as Brewfest is going and the Dark Iron Dwarves are attacking and our supplier is stuck in that canyon, I\'ll need some help shipping kegs. So if you want to work for more tickets, talk to me every day.$B$BHere are the tickets we promised you. Have fun!' WHERE entry=11412;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The smell of their blood upon your muzzle pleases me. Brothers should not turn on each other.' WHERE entry=11414;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Mistwalker is from my dreams! If you are his friend, you are mine.$B$BI was alpha male until the last full moon. Then the strange white worg, Garwal, came from the north, and with the help of my once-brothers, he quickly became alpha. There is something unnatural about him.$B$BTo help, you must first kill those who betrayed me.$B$BBjomolf hunts to the northwest of a place the two-legs call Steel Gate. And look for Varg to the southeast, near the West Spear Tower.$B$BThey will not be fooled by your form.',objectives_loc4='Ulfang has asked you to kill the traitorous worgs, Bjomolf and Varg. Return to him in disguise in the Rivenwood after you have done so.$B$BIf you somehow lose the Worg Disguise, return to Sage Mistwalker for a replacement.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The smell of their blood upon your muzzle pleases me. Brothers should not turn on each other.' WHERE entry=11415;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Ulfang howls loudly at your defeat of his great eagle enemy.>$B$BThe honor of the kill is yours. I wish that it had been my maw to finally close upon her neck.$B$BLet us not waste the sacrifice that she has made for us. Here, eat them!' WHERE entry=11416;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Ulfang howls loudly at your defeat of his great eagle enemy.>$B$BThe honor of the kill is yours. I wish that it had been my maw to finally close upon her neck.$B$BLet us not waste the sacrifice that she has made for us. Here, eat them!' WHERE entry=11417;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You saw a nest, with hatchlings? Hmm... so our "he" is actually a "she," eh?$B$BI guess that settles it. I suppose I wouldn\'t want to move a nest full of hatchlings just because of a new neighbor, either.$B$B<Gil favors Trapper Jethan with a mock glare.>$B$BI\'m sure we\'d get along just fine if ol\' Jethan would stop trying to make a trophy of her.' WHERE entry=11418;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='If you show this hand stamp to Driz Tumblequick, the Ram Racing Apprentice, he\'ll allow you to purchase Brewfest riding rams.',objectives_loc4='Bring the "Honorary Brewer" Hand Stamp to Driz Tumblequick near the entrance to the Brewfest Grounds in Durotar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Good job, $N... you\'ve won the trust of the festival\'s brewers, earning the right to purchase a Brewfest riding ram.' WHERE entry=11419;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Zorek flips through the manual.>$B$BHrm, interesting...$B$BAccording to the manual, the vrykul have a special tool that allows them to control the harpoon guns with deadly accuracy. It looks a bit like the wheel of one of our ships. Furthermore, it\'s portable and seems to plug into the harpoon guns like a key. We need to get our hands on one of those!' WHERE entry=11420;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work, $N! You took out a good chunk of their dragon riders and really pissed off their leadership.$B$BAre you ready to head back to Valgarde and report the good news to Zorek? If so, I\'ve got a crazy idea!
' WHERE entry=11421;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Dragonflayer Dockhouse Destroyed',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Dragonflayer Storage Facility Destroyed' WHERE entry=11421;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Reaching out to take his son\'s trident from you, Old Icefin\'s hand shakes a little. Could it be that the aged murloc is grieving?>$B$B<Is that just extra moisture pooling at the base of his eye?>' WHERE entry=11422;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This is of tremendous value, $N. I must renew my efforts in salvaging and translating vrykul texts.$B$BDon\'t get me wrong. Our enemies need to be destroyed... their ancient knowledge doesn\'t.' WHERE entry=11423;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hmmmmph... these will do for now. There seems to be some oddness to them.$B$BI tell ya - I\'ve handled body parts for years now and never have I had such a weird feeling in my stomach. Anyway, a deal is a deal. Here\'s your payment.' WHERE entry=11424;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Outstanding! Those overgrown apes will soon know what it means to mess with the Alliance!' WHERE entry=11426;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Do you see those vrykul buildings on the bluffs to the northeast? The vrykul call that place Nifflevar. It\'s where most of their harpoon attacks on our frigates originate.$B$BWell guess what? The time for payback has come, $N. I need you to take this harpoon control mechanism and meet up with Lieutenant Icehammer, who is hiding out in a vrykul building northwest of Nifflevar.$B$BWhen you\'re ready I\'ll place you on the back of one of our gryphons and zip you right to him! $B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Lieutenant Icehammer takes the harpoon control mechanism from you.>$B$BAh, you come bearing gifts!' WHERE entry=11427;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='My heart broke when I learned the keepers had turned against us. Once, we considered them our brothers and our closest friends.$B$BI grieve for the brothers and sisters we have lost, but without your help, there would be no hope for our future. You will always be welcome among us, $N.' WHERE entry=11428;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I\'m not about to put the fate of this mission into the hands of some untested scrub.$B$BNow, if you want to prove to me that you\'ve got what it takes to carry out this mission, you\'ll need to do what I tell you.$B$BTake this battle standard and head over to Baleheim, directly north of here. Once you\'re at Baleheim, find the center of town and drop our flag. Fight off any vrykul dirt bags that attempt to take down our beloved flag and return to me once you\'ve established Alliance dominance!',objectives_loc4='Lieutenant Icehammer in the Howling Fjord wants you to place the Alliance Banner in Baleheim and then defend the banner against attackers.$B$BReturn to Lieutenant Icehammer with the Alliance Banner should you survive.',offerrewardtext_loc4='For the Alliance! You\'re a strong one, $N. Strong enough to crack some vrykul skull at Nifflevar.
' WHERE entry=11429;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='That was a fairly strong showing at Baleheim, $N. Before you go off patting yourself on the back there\'s work to be done at Nifflevar.$B$BWe\'ve located the vrykul responsible for the majority of the harpoon attacks on our frigates - goes by the name of Yavus. You\'ll find him in the main harpoon structure on the bluffs of Nifflevar, southeast of here.$B$BTrack him down and execute him for crimes against the Alliance!$B$BDo me proud, $N!$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'ll take them a while to find a replacement for Yavus. Now is the perfect time to unleash Zorek\'s plan! While they\'re scurrying to regain control of Nifflevar, you\'re going to use their own harpoon guns against them!' WHERE entry=11430;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Hey there!  I\'m a crazy dwarf!  We dwarves believe when you get enough brew together, invisible creatures show up.  In fact they are probably wandering around the Brewfest grounds right now! But you can only see them if you are really drunk.$B$BWe dwarves will come up with any excuse to drink.$B$BI bet you want a reason to drink too...  So here it is, bring me 5 of those wolpertingers with this net I got from a really drunk dwarf.$B$BIf you can\'t see them, you\'re probably not drunk enough.',objectives_loc4='The "dwarf," Glodrak Huntsniper, has asked you to capture 5 Stunned Wolpertingers using the Wolpertinger Net. He mentioned that you must be intoxicated to see them.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, lookee there! Ye\'ve got yerself a right bushel o\' wolpertingers, ye do!$B$B<He takes a deep drink from his tankard.>$B$BI\'ll tell ye what I\'m gonna do. Since ye\'re such a spot-on $C, I\'ll let ye keep one\'a these fer yer very own!' WHERE entry=11431;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You did what had to be done. Though some might consider it dishonorable to slay the helpless, in this case you would have been a fool to have done otherwise.$B$BAnd we certainly couldn\'t have just left them standing there to be ritually wakened, now could we?$B$BIt was a brave thing you did for all of us down in those catacombs, $N.' WHERE entry=11432;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I\'ve overheard what you\'ve had to say with Greatmother Ankha. With all due respect, she\'s not having you go far enough.$B$BYou must also deal with the vrykul that lie dormant in the Waking Halls beneath Gjalerbron!$B$BI have no doubt that the rituals involved with awakening them are the key to their downfall. Most likely the necrolords have some device that you can use to bring the vrykul out of their dormant state prematurely.$B$BSurely such a disruption will prove fatal to the vrykul.',objectives_loc4='Ahota Whitefrost has tasked you with slaying 5 Dormant Vrykul. Return to him at Camp Winterhoof when you have done so.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You did what had to be done. The unwise might consider it dishonorable to slay the helpless while they awaken, but in this case you would have been a fool to have done otherwise.$B$BAnd we certainly couldn\'t have just left them standing there to be ritually wakened, now could we?$B$BIt was a brave thing you did for all of us down in those catacombs, $R.' WHERE entry=11433;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We\'re going to go places together, $N.  With my good looks and your... can-do attitude, we\'re sure to make a killing.' WHERE entry=11434;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are insane, $N! What kind of degenerate would actually launch themselves from a harpoon gun as a method of travel?$B$BBut I guess you need to be a little crazy to pull off what you did up there on the bluffs! Fantastic work! We\'ve gotten word that the Dragonflayer leader, Ingvar, is furious! Maybe one day you\'ll be ready to stomp his face into the dirt - in the name of our beloved Alliance.' WHERE entry=11436;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Throw water buckets onto 5 fires, and then speak with the Costumed Orphan Matron.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re smudged with soot!  You must have been extinguishing fires!$B$BWell done!  As an honorary member of the Kharanos Fire Brigade, I beg you to return here if ever the village needs you!' WHERE entry=11439;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Throw water buckets onto 5 fires, and then speak with the Costumed Orphan Matron.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re wet and smudged with soot!  You must have been extinguishing fires!$B$BWell done!  As an honorary member of the Azuremyst Fire Brigade, I beg you to return here if ever the village needs you!' WHERE entry=11440;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ho ho! Come for your free beer?' WHERE entry=11441;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ho ho! Come for your free beer?' WHERE entry=11442;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Wow! You sure are efficient. Yep, well, just give me those crates. I\'ll need to document them and take inventory and some other stuff that you haven\'t been trained to deal with or understand. Don\'t worry; I\'ll be sure to let Keller know what a great job you did down here! Yep. Yea, you can leave now. Skedaddle!' WHERE entry=11443;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What?! A free beer? Yeah, yeah. I guess we said we\'d do that this year.' WHERE entry=11446;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What?! A free beer? Yeah, yeah. I guess we said we\'d do that this year.' WHERE entry=11447;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Stanwad takes the bundle from you and begins sorting the data.>$B$BWow. How many people did you say died to get this information?$B$B<Stanwad shakes his head.>$B$BYou\'ll be happy to know that what McSorf and his crew of bumbling imbeciles discovered is an ancient recipe for tundra stew. Did he not notice the icons of common vegetables and the pictograph of a humanoid mouth chompin\' down on said veggies? You don\'t need a damned cipher to break this code!' WHERE entry=11448;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Toss buckets on 5 fires, then speak with the Masked Orphan Matron in Brill.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. Children, take a good look at this $C. Let her be a strong example to you.' WHERE entry=11449;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Toss buckets on 5 fires, then speak with the Masked Orphan Matron in Falconwing Square.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N.  Children, take a good look at this $C.  Let $Ghim:her; be a fine example for you to follow.' WHERE entry=11450;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What a touching poem, thank you!' WHERE entry=11451;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m not sure that I like the sound of that one bit! The Lich King absconding with Ymiron can only mean trouble. Unfortunate that you weren\'t able to kill him along with his queen.$B$BStill, you\'ve put a huge dent in their plans and bought us the valuable time that we need.$B$BAnd who knows, with the way you get around, you\'ll likely run into King Ymiron again. I\'m sure that he won\'t fare so well the next time you meet.' WHERE entry=11452;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Defeat Queen Angerboda and stop the ritual to awaken King Ymiron. Should you manage to do so, return to Camp Winterhoof and report your success to Chieftain Ashtotem.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m not sure that I like the sound of that one bit! The Lich King absconding with Ymiron can only mean trouble. Unfortunate that you weren\'t able to kill him along with his queen.$B$BStill, you\'ve put a huge dent in their plans and bought us the valuable time that we need.$B$BAnd who knows, with the way you get around, you\'ll likely run into King Ymiron again. I\'m sure that he won\'t fare so well the next time you meet.' WHERE entry=11453;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s a damn shame, it is, you lot cavorting up there without drinking the finest of the fine brews - ours! Did we get an invite to the competition? Of course not. Ya fight in some war and suddenly yer beer\'s not good enough! So aye, we smashed up yer kegs a bit, and rightly so!$B$BEr... seeing as you\'ve smashed through our defenses and all, though, maybe ya can do something fer me...' WHERE entry=11454;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work!  It might not be quite as daring as plundering the high seas, but I\'d be a darned son of a deckswabber if I passed on this opportunity.' WHERE entry=11455;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I thank you, $N.  My people are in a time of great need.' WHERE entry=11456;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Elder Atuik wants you to obain 3 Chimaera Horns.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You continue to prove your worth as an ally, $N.  Your actions will not be forgotten.' WHERE entry=11457;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are a formidable ally, $N.  My people will forever be in your debt.' WHERE entry=11458;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You didn\'t understand a thing Zeh\'gehn said?  Well, of course not.$B$BLet\'s see then.' WHERE entry=11459;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes, $N. I can see the bond of companionship forming. She has accepted you as master.' WHERE entry=11460;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Don the Pirate Disguise and speak to Handsome Terry inside Scalawag point.' WHERE entry=11462;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Pirates of the North Seas',objectives_loc4='Find Grezzix Spindlesnap on the northern end of Garvan\'s Reef off of the Southwestern coast of Howling Fjord.' WHERE entry=11463;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A job well done.  Here\'s your cut, $N.  There\'s more where this came from.$B$BThere\'s no shortage of deadbeat pirates on this island.' WHERE entry=11464;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Clever fiends. And patient too! We need to stop underestimating our enemy. Those vrykul are deadly hunters!$B$BRegardless, mission accomplished. Perhaps it is time for you to hunt something a bit more elusive than a fat turkey, eh?' WHERE entry=11465;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m impressed, $N.  And I\'m not the type who\'s easily impressed.' WHERE entry=11466;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'ll take the gold, as it is what Conrad owed me.  The rest is for you to keep.$B$BIf you\'re ever in need of something more permanent, I\'m sure I could arrange for something.  In the meantime, may the wind blow strong in your sail, friend.' WHERE entry=11467;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Hidalgo at the Explorers\' League Outpost in the Howling Fjord wants you to use your Trained Rock Falcon to capture 10 Fjord Hawks.$B$BReturn to Hidalgo with the cage when you have completed this task.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Aye, the hawks are very territorial and often travel in packs. I suppose I could have told you that before I sent you out into the field.
' WHERE entry=11468;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ew, that\'s a stink if I ever smelled one!$B$BGo on now, put it down right here. I\'ll cast my spell and she\'ll be swabbin\' soap for sure!' WHERE entry=11469;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Bravo, $N! Bravo! The bond of kinship between you and your falcon is strong! Perhaps you can run some reconnaissance missions against the vrykul in the not-too-distant future?' WHERE entry=11470;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I know why you\'re here, $N.  You\'ve been sent to kill our leader, Jonah Sterling.$B$BI\'d like to offer my help.  Jonah\'s leadership threatens our operation.$B$BAttacking the Horde and the Alliance fleets simultaneously?  Suicidal.  Trying to sell the tuskarr as slaves when they die days after leaving this climate?  Disastrous.$B$BJonah\'s hideout is located inside a cave west of here.  Bring me his spyglass as proof of the deed  and my first action as lead will be to end all attacks against your allies.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Jonah Sterling\'s days are finally over!  He never thought this "wench" would make it.$B$BAs word of Jonah\'s death spreads among the pirates I will consolidate my leadership.  Your allies won\'t get any more trouble from my crew, $N.' WHERE entry=11471;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This is good news! Now more bulls will swim across the strait to mate with the cows. Soon there will be plenty of new reef pups on the isles.$B$BThank you, $R. Whatever you might have done in the past, know that you have helped with Kamagua\'s future!$B$BWe\'ll have to keep up the good work if we\'re going to see to it that their numbers are replenished. Please come back again tomorrow so that we can help another couple find each other.' WHERE entry=11472;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ku here, mate.  Ye come fe see I an\' I, aye?' WHERE entry=11473;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Over half our team is dead or missing, junior. This is our last stand up here on the high bluffs. Those damned iron dwarves pushed us out of both Ivald\'s Ruin and Baelgun\'s. Now I\'ve got a plan to get us back inside before they bury up all our goodies and we lose that data forever.' WHERE entry=11474;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Now that I\'ve got my tools, the building can begin. Well, as soon as I have some materials. You\'ll be getting those for me next.' WHERE entry=11475;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Much obliged, bucko.  Croaker\'s lookin\' real cris!' WHERE entry=11476;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good job, $N. That\'ll slow down the burial process a little.' WHERE entry=11477;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yea, this isn\'t anything we don\'t already know. At least Donny\'s still alive.' WHERE entry=11478;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Croaker\'s spoken, matey. "Crowleg" Dan\'s on da ship yonder.$B$BBest go trace that blaggard, mon.  Show\'im dis set\'s not fe be crossed.  Gaan back fe Terry when ye keelhaul \'is behind.',objectives_loc4='Confront "Crowleg" Dan, who is in one of the ships at Scalawag Point. Speak to Handsome Terry when you\'ve completed this task.',offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'s some sad news.  Dan was me old friend... AND he owed me money.  Either way, if he was working with the Southsea mongrels he got what he deserved.$B$BAs for you, my friend.  You\'re on your way up.  Literally.' WHERE entry=11479;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, well, well.  If it isn\'t $N.  You show up at Scalawag point, no one\'s heard of you except some goblin friend of that half-wit Terry.$B$BLet\'s just say I\'m a bit... skeptical... of your intentions here.' WHERE entry=11480;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Another soldier from Shattrath? A welcome sight!$B$BWish there were more of you, but we\'ll make due with what we have. Whatever\'s going on out here won\'t wait for us to make ready.$B$BHave a look around, $C. There\'s much that needs doing. Pitch in and do your share.$B$BOh, yeah, and don\'t go tauntin\' the cryers - err, Scryers. Looks like we\'re in this thing together....' WHERE entry=11481;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Welcome to Sunwell Plateau, cryer - What\'s that? Oh Scryer, yes of course. Isn\'t that what I said?$B$BWell, now, let\'s get a few things straight. There\'s some serious business going on behind those walls and it\'s in the interest of both of our people to address it. And since neither of us have the forces to go it alone, we\'re going to work - TOGETHER. Got that?$B$BNow let\'s get started, shall we?' WHERE entry=11482;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent. These combined with the skin will make for a flawless clone of the constructs the iron dwarves use.' WHERE entry=11483;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'ll have the construct all ready to go as soon as the infrastructure is complete.' WHERE entry=11484;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Alright, $N; the time has come for you to climb inside this thing and learn how to use its basic abilities. When you\'re ready, get on the work bench and I\'ll get you situated inside the construct.$B$BYour first lesson is going to be using the construct\'s transportation system. You\'ll notice that the iron dwarves have set up special rune carvings around the dig site. Their constructs use those rune carvings to power up and fly from point to point. Try it with the rune carving I built here.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re almost ready to take this work of art into the field, $N!
' WHERE entry=11485;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='...Come closer, $R... Listen carefully to my words....' WHERE entry=11488;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Perfect! Works like a charm!' WHERE entry=11489;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I consider it to be no coincidence that our paths cross this day.$B$BI sense the tendrils of destiny....' WHERE entry=11490;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Walt at the Explorers\' League Outpost in the Howling Fjord wants you to use the Iron Rune Construct\'s Bluff ability on Lebronski after you\'ve walked on his rug.$B$BDismiss your construct by dismissing it from the pet window once you have completed the quest.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='You showed him! Now it\'s time to put you in the field.$B$BFeeling confident, I hope...' WHERE entry=11491;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Larethor listens intently as you explain your deeds in Magisters\' Terrace.>$B$BTyrith will be missed - good man, that one. Thanks to you though, his death wasn\'t in vain.$B$BI\'ve underestimated you, $R. Please, accept this on behalf of the Sunwell Offensive - a gift worthy of a hero such as yourself.' WHERE entry=11492;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='And once again Walt proves that he is indeed the top dwarf! What do you think of my construct now, Lebronski!$B$BThank you, $N. This data will undoubtedly prove to be invaluable - as soon as I figure out how to get it out of the construct.' WHERE entry=11494;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Incredible! What could those iron menaces be up to? What are they doing in the Storm Peaks? And what is this Loken!? I\'ll forward this information to our central base of operations in the Dragonblight, $N. I\'ll also let \'em know that you were invaluable in the acquisition of said info.' WHERE entry=11495;
UPDATE locales_quest SET EndText_loc4='Thundering Cave investigated' WHERE entry=11495;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So, me boyo, Nutral, sent ya along did he?  Good man... I\'ll need ta remember ta send him along a pint fer all o\' the business he\'s sendin\' me way.$B$BIf it\'s the learnin\' o\' how ta fly right and proper yer after, ye\'ve come ta the right place. No one flies finer than us Wildhammer and those we train. Fer a fee, and not a small one mind ya, I\'ll teach ya how ta soar through the skies!$B$BAnd when yer done, don\'t forget ta talk ta Brunn over there about buying one o\' these gryphon beauties!' WHERE entry=11497;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Though it may end up hurting my business in the long run, you look the sort that dreams of flying $G his : her; own mount through the skies, rather than being flown from place to place.$B$BI understand the feeling completely.$B$BYou, my friend, need to head to Shadowmoon Village in the northwest corner of Shadowmoon Valley. When you get there, speak with Olrokk about some flight instruction. Mind you, his training\'s not cheap. But, I think that you\'ll find it worth your while.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Olrokk at Shadowmoon Village in Shadowmoon Valley.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Blood and thunder, Nutral sent me another ground grunt! Good man... for a draenei.$B$B<Olrokk spits on the ground near your feet.>$B$BYou\'ve come to the right place if you want to learn how to ride your own mount through the skies. In return for a big sack of gold, I\'ll teach you what you need to know and not fall dishonorably to your death.$B$BAnd when you\'re done, don\'t forget to talk to Dama Wildmane over there about buying one of the windriders from our stable!' WHERE entry=11498;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So, the blood elf prince is truly dead this time? A pity, I always thought he had class. To think that one so lofty could be brought down for such a paltry sum.$B$BBut as they say, business is business. Your reward is earned, adventurer.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE entry=11499;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Wonderful... As if having the Scourge all up our you-know-whats wasn\'t enough, now we got some angry ancient titan construct to deal with!$B$BI\'ll need some time to chew on this information, $R. In the meantime there\'s plenty of work that needs doing here.' WHERE entry=11501;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I thank you, $N. Your efforts will not be ignored.' WHERE entry=11502;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You bring great honor to our people. You have our thanks.' WHERE entry=11503;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Orfus\'s whiskers bristle.>$B$BPirates... Is there no end to the depths of their depravity?$B$BWe must recover the stolen artifacts and return them to this cursed place so that my people may once more know peace.' WHERE entry=11504;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Orfus is a good tuskarr - one of our strongest warriors. I knew he would not let us down.$B$BAllow me to see what it is that you have brought.
' WHERE entry=11507;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yarr, matey. Grezzix never did like to get his hands dirty! A pirate\'s life for Grezzix is a good one, so long as Grezzix doesn\'t have to do any of the work.$B$BI\'ve seen those artifacts. It\'s the reason I\'m here and not at Scalawag myself! Bad, bad things those are...$B$BHey, it\'s your life though, right? You wanna get inside Scalawag and Grezzix can help.' WHERE entry=11508;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The Northsea Freebooters all fear and respect Grezzix. I\'m thinking they recognize my special talents and envy my amazing ship. All you need to do is tag along with my cabin boy, Lou, and you\'ll be in like... In like tin. Pirates love tin.$B$BJust talk to Lou when you\'re ready to go and he\'ll take you to Scalawag.$B$BOh yea, you\'ll want to talk to "Silvermoon" Harry first. He\'ll have more information on the stuff they pilfered. Just watch what you say around him. He\'s a freak... crazy for blood elves.',objectives_loc4='Speak with "Silvermoon" Harry at Scalawag Point about the missing Vrykul artifacts.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Harry raises an eyebrow at you.>$B$BSo you\'re like me, eh? A little eccentric.$B$B<Harry whispers.>$B$BNobody dresses like that around here.$B$BAbout those artifacts... Everyone that came into contact with that stuff has ended up dead, missing or both.$B$BIf you\'re still interested in learning more, I can help - but it\'ll cost you.$B$B<Harry winks.>$B$BYou scratch my back and I\'ll try to not stick a dagger in yours.' WHERE entry=11509;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='One of the first things Jonah Sterling did after he went crazy was to take my prized sin\'dorei scrying crystal and feed it to the bane of my existence, "Scoodles" the orca.$B$BNo I didn\'t name the damned thing. I just know that she swims out past the ships directly southeast of Scalawag. Kill that overinflated goldfish and rip out my beautiful sin\'dorei crystal from its stomach.$B$BDo this and we can get down to business.',objectives_loc4='"Silvermoon" Harry at Scalawag Point wants you to recover his Sin\'dorei Scrying Crystal from the orca, "Scoodles."',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Harry takes the crystal from you and gently pets it.>$B$BOh my precious! Did the big, mean whale hurt you? It\'ll be ok. I\'ll never let you out of my sight again!$B$B<Harry looks up at you.>$B$BSo, where were we?' WHERE entry=11510;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Recover the Staff of Storm\'s Fury and deliver it to Orfus of Kamagua in the Howling Fjord.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='We must return all of the artifacts, $N. When all four are gathered, you will put them back in their graves.' WHERE entry=11511;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We must return all of the artifacts, $N. When all four are gathered, you will put them back in their graves.' WHERE entry=11512;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Intercepting the Mana Cells',details_loc4='I have devised a plan to acquire a power source strong enough for the creation of our portal.$B$BThe ethereal forces at Bash\'ir Landing, atop the northwestern Blade\'s Edge Mountains, have been smuggling mana cells out of Tempest Keep and transporting them to the Sunwell for Kael\'thas.$B$BThey have hidden the cells, but there is a way for you to find them; the ethereal carry phase devices that you can use to see the smuggled goods.$B$BJust beware the mana cells\' phase wyrm guardians.',offerrewardtext_loc4='These mana cells are vital to our efforts. We will have the portal to the Sunwell Isle created in no time!$B$BReturn tomorrow and I will send you out to acquire more of them from our Bash\'ir \'friends\'.' WHERE entry=11513;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These mana cells will continue to power the portal.$B$BReturn tomorrow and I will send you out to obtain more.' WHERE entry=11514;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Fools.  They learned to drain fel energy but did not learn how to retain it.$B$BWe were lucky, $N.  An experienced felblood would\'ve surely been a formidable opponent.' WHERE entry=11515;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work, $N.  The demons might repair the gateway in due time.  I suppose we\'ll just have to blow it up again.' WHERE entry=11516;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Portanuus sent you? Good, we haven\'t any time to spare!' WHERE entry=11517;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Arrr, me\'n\'me crew pilfered that thar shield! We be tryin\' to get her back from that no good, landlubbin\' scallywag, Sorlof! Ye come to help, arrr?$B$BWell, as ye can see we be runnin\' a skeleton crew!$B$B<Captain Ellis laughs.>$B$BSister Mercy be needin\' another powder monkey to man the big\'uns o\'er on the poop deck. Think ye be up to the job, me hearty?$B$BHelp me crew take Sorlof down and we\'ll split the booty! Ye can have the shield, me\'n\'me crew gets the rest!' WHERE entry=11519;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Discovering Your Roots',details_loc4='Greetings, $R.$B$BI\'m afraid I have little to offer here until my reagents are stocked.$B$BOf the supplies I require, there is a special reagent, razorthorn root, that is particularly difficult to harvest.$B$BFortunately, I know a secret....$B$BUsing the glands of the Razorthorn flayers, one can control a ravager there and use it to expose a root.$B$BTo find the roots, travel to Outlands and fly northeast from Shattrath until you reach Razorthorn Rise.',offerrewardtext_loc4='These should do nicely, $C.$B$BI thank you for your assistance.' WHERE entry=11520;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work, $N.$B$BThank you again for your help!' WHERE entry=11521;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good work, $N. The wards are slowly regaining their power. Sun\'s Reach will be ours in no time!' WHERE entry=11523;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent.  The converted sentries will help to secure our perimeter.' WHERE entry=11525;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s very sweet of Theris to worry about my hide, but we\'ve got bigger problems here.  Much bigger.' WHERE entry=11526;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Captain Ellis aboard the Sister Mercy in the Howling Fjord has asked that you recover 5 Barrels of Blasting Powder from the ship\'s hold.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Here\'s to hopin\' those treacherous bilge rats learned their lessons! Now it be time to man the big\'un, matey!' WHERE entry=11527;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A small tag on this present reads:$B$BHappy holidays, $N!' WHERE entry=11528;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A deal\'s a deal, me hearty!' WHERE entry=11529;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We must return all of the artifacts, $N. When all four are gathered, you will put them back in their graves.' WHERE entry=11530;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<K. Lee looks at the engine part and then stares off into the distance for a moment.>$B$BThis is somethin\' real special.  Difficulty to say where it\'s from--like it just fell out of the sky. I\'m gonna hold on to this and pay you for your troubles.$B$BBetween you and me though, I think it\'s best if we didn\'t mention this to anyone.$B$B<K. Lee puts on her most charming smile.>' WHERE entry=11531;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Distraction at the Dead Scar',details_loc4='The Legion will move against us as soon as their forces to the south are freed up.  The Scourge at the Dead Scar are keeping their forces occupied at the moment.  It won\'t last long, however.$B$BI want you to fly a dragonhawk over to the scar and put a dent in the demons\' numbers with these arcane charges.$B$BIf all goes well, they won\'t even notice us taking the armory from Kael\'s lackeys.  Talk to Ayren, the dragonhawk master in the west part of the harbor, when you\'re ready to fly there.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve got some real talent, kid.  Did you ever think of joining the Skyguard?$B$BI jest, $N.  We need you here if we want to take the docks any time soon.' WHERE entry=11532;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Any demons we kill today are demons that we do not have to fight tomorrow.  Keep it up.' WHERE entry=11533;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Portanuus sent you? Good, we haven\'t any time to spare!' WHERE entry=11534;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Making Ready',details_loc4='Supplies are inbound, or so I\'m told.$B$BRegardless, we can ill afford to wait around hoping that help arrives before our offensive stalls. We must make the best of what we have.$B$BAs for me, I need ore to fashion an anvil so I can begin to upgrade our armor and weapons.$B$BThere are a group of naga on the coast to the east of here collecting ore and placing it in chests for shipment to the Legion.$B$BRelieving them of their ore will help our efforts in more ways than one....',offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent! We\'re getting closer....$B$BSoon I\'ll be able to craft an anvil, then the real work can begin.' WHERE entry=11535;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent! This will help me keep our soldiers in weapons and armor.$B$BYour help is truly making a difference!' WHERE entry=11536;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Your dedication is exemplary, $N.  We will show the forces of the Burning Legion what we\'re capable of.' WHERE entry=11537;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Taking the Harbor',details_loc4='One of Kael\'s most elite forces, the Dawnblade army, has been stationed at the Sun\'s Reach Harbor and Dawnstar Village.$B$BThe harbor is of critical importance to our plans, so any Dawnblade casualties you inflict will be of tremendous help.  Kael\'thas will rue the day that he turned his back on his people and sided with the Burning Legion.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work, $C. Kael\'s armies will falter and once we take the harbor we shall deliver the killing blow!' WHERE entry=11539;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What thoughts go through Prince Kael\'thas Sunstrider\'s head when he hears of his armies\' defeats?$B$BDoes he feel despair? Helplessness? Fear?$B$BI sure hope so.' WHERE entry=11540;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'s enough for today. Slow and steady is the key here. Too much disruption and they\'d turn their attention directly upon us; something that we don\'t want.$B$BCome back again tomorrow and we\'ll work on it some more.' WHERE entry=11541;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Intercept the Reinforcements',details_loc4='We\'re making a push to solidify our control of Sun\'s Reach by capturing the harbor next.  Unfortunately a fleet of Dawnblade reservists is on its way to reinforce Kael\'s forces there.$B$BTake this oil and secure a dragonhawk from Ayren Cloudbreaker.    You should be able to fly within reach of the ships\' sails; once you\'re close enough, set them on fire.$B$BLand in one of the ships and attack the reservists.  With their ship sails on fire they won\'t be able to mount much of a defense.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N.  It should be a long time before the harbor receives any reinforcements.' WHERE entry=11542;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N.  It should be a long time before the harbor receives any reinforcements.' WHERE entry=11543;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, my friend. Now I will be able to fashion more of the special alloy that is going into the creation of our forces\' weapons and armor.$B$BAnd, I have some leftover extract from the process, which you\'ll likely find handy for use on your weapons. Please, take your pick of whichever will serve your purposes.$B$BReturn to me again on the morrow. No doubt I will need more armaments.' WHERE entry=11544;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='A Charitable Donation',details_loc4='We\'ve taken Sun\'s Reach from the enemy and our final victory is at hand.  The cost was high and many brave combatants gave their lives so we could achieve this.$B$BIt is my goal to ensure that those who perished in combat are not forgotten.  I ask that you take a moment to consider making a donation towards a memorial fund.  Any leftover gold will go to the widows and orphans of the fallen.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You are a virtuous soul, $N.  It is easy to forget the fallen amidst the turmoil of war and the euphoria of victory.  The friends and families of the dead thank you.' WHERE entry=11545;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent, $N.$B$BI hope this will aid you in your efforts here.' WHERE entry=11546;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes, yes. Let\'s have a look now, shall we?$B$BThings seem to be in order. Very well. Here is your translocator.$B$BIf any of your readings are faulty, there\'s no telling where you\'ll end up, and mind you, you\'ll only have yourself to blame.' WHERE entry=11547;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are a virtuous soul, $N.  It is easy to forget the fallen amidst the turmoil of war and the euphoria of victory.  The friends and families of the dead thank you.' WHERE entry=11548;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You truly are a generous person and a worthy ally. From now on you shall be known as $N of the Shattered Sun and all who fought here will know of your deeds!' WHERE entry=11549;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Kil\'jaeden bears down upon this world with the full force of the Burning Legion. Should the summoning complete, our world will once more be flung into the throes of chaos. Your assistance on the Isle of Quel\'Danas is critical to our success against the Burning Legion.$B$BOur mages are working on bringing down the barriers blocking access to the Sunwell. Do your part in battling the forces of the Legion by helping the Shattered Sun Offensive.' WHERE entry=11550;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Your aid in the offensive has not gone unnoticed, $N. The combined forces of the Aldor and Scryers offer you their thanks.' WHERE entry=11554;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You continue to prove yourself in this most important battle, $N. Please accept this as a token of our continued gratitude.' WHERE entry=11555;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We couldn\'t have gotten where we are without you, $N. The combined might of the Aldor and Scryers is not enough to crush the Legion and Kael. We are thankful to have allies of your caliber among us.' WHERE entry=11556;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are one of our very best, $N. Your name will be known throughout our ranks for a long time to come. Please accept this small gift on behalf of our forces.' WHERE entry=11557;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These are for me? Is this some sort of $R trick? No?$B$BWell then, thank you! Come back any time that you have more clams, and we\'ll do business!' WHERE entry=11559;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Now no matter what happens, the Winterfin murlocs have a secure future.$B$BYou are to be commended, and rewarded, for your selflessness, $N!' WHERE entry=11560;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I am pleased. I can smell the coppery tang of their blood on your hands.$B$BThis is a good start for you, $R.' WHERE entry=11561;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Aw, so you must be the so-called King Mrgl-Mrgl\'s lackey. I suppose that $R has sent you to appease me?$B$BGood, I have just the thing that needs doing for someone as powerful as you!' WHERE entry=11562;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Not bad. This will make a nice feast!$B$BWith the king of the orcas dead the attacks upon us should diminish while the whales fight amongst themselves for dominance.' WHERE entry=11563;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Aw yes, these will do nicely.$B$BJust plop them down anywhere. You can have some of my leftover stew from last night. And since you\'ve been helping us with our other problems, you can have my recipe, too.' WHERE entry=11564;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Upon seeing the spare murloc suit, the king rubs his costumed appendages together.>$B$BNicely done. Now, back to the pressing matter at hand. I\'ve got something of great importance for you to do.' WHERE entry=11565;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Regrettable, but necessary. I\'ll take the claw, $N.$B$BThank you for all of the help you\'ve given us. With Claximus defeated, maybe we\'ll be able to reunite the remaining murlocs and seal off those caverns.$B$BPlease, my friend, take this... it\'s the least I can do for all of the help you have rendered us!' WHERE entry=11566;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We must return all of the artifacts, $N. When all four are gathered, you will put them back in their graves.' WHERE entry=11567;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Grim tidings, $N. My people are in danger and must be warned. These sea faring aberrations will take no mercy upon the Kalu\'ak.' WHERE entry=11568;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Frozen Heart of Isuldof Returned',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Ancient Armor of the Kvaldir Returned' WHERE entry=11568;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Quickly, hand it here!' WHERE entry=11569;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This is wonderful news! And you say that Lurgglbr discovered that the emanations from the caverns are what caused this insanity?$B$BIt must be that the magic from Coldarra is growing stronger. The Nexus War... the battle between the blue dragonflight and all of the other dragons, is spilling over.$B$BSoon, we will all be embroiled in it!' WHERE entry=11570;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Now I will be able to use Scalder\'s essence to impart my understanding of the Winterfin murloc tongue to you.' WHERE entry=11571;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Kalu\'ak thank you for all that you have done, $N. We must now prepare for battle and warn our brothers and sisters across the sea of what is to come.$B$BI hope it is not too late...' WHERE entry=11572;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Lunk-tusk lives? At least there is some good news to be had on this day...' WHERE entry=11573;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You can tell your friend that her rescue was our pleasure, as well as our duty.$B$BHer encounter was but a small piece in what I believe to be a large puzzle.$B$BDalaran is sparing no effort in solving this mystery and to be honest, we could use a bit of assistance....' WHERE entry=11574;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You can tell your friend that her rescue was our pleasure, as well as our duty.$B$BHer encounter was but a small piece in what I believe to be a large puzzle.$B$BDalaran is sparing no effort in solving this mystery and to be honest, we could use a bit of assistance....' WHERE entry=11575;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Fascinating! This is the largest disruption yet.$B$BThough the worst is yet to come, I fear.' WHERE entry=11576;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It was how big?$B$BThat\'s impossible! I need to report to Dalaran at once!' WHERE entry=11582;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Honor the Silverpine Forest flame.' WHERE entry=11584;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A hero of the Horde, eh?$B$B<Garrosh sniffs at the air around you.>$B$BFear...$B$B<Garrosh spits.>$B$BYou won\'t last long.' WHERE entry=11585;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Do not think that I have forgotten what you did for my people in Nagrand, $N. Hellscream never forgets.$B$BFor that I am indebted to you and it is why I give you this chance now: run. Leave this place and never look back.$B$BReturn to your home and say a prayer for the dying.' WHERE entry=11586;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well, $N.$B$BThe Kirin Tor graciously accept the assistance you have rendered. Know that any service you provide us will not go unrewarded.$B$BPlease, accept this humble offering as a token of Dalaran\'s appreciation.' WHERE entry=11587;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Stop Ahune from coming to Azeroth and inciting an elemental war!',objectives_loc4='Destroy the elemental Ahune within Blackfathom Deeps.' WHERE entry=11588;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Stop Ahune from coming to Azeroth and inciting an elemental war!',objectives_loc4='Destroy the elemental Ahune within Blackfathom Deeps.' WHERE entry=11589;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work, $N.$B$BWe\'ll have him prepared for his interrogation at once.' WHERE entry=11590;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc4='Have you captured a Beryl sorcerer yet, $N?' WHERE entry=11590;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This isn\'t good, $C.$B$BLongrunner Proudhoof says that these are the burial grounds of his honored ancestors.' WHERE entry=11591;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Blood and thunder! You\'ve salvaged our newborn relations with the taunka.$B$BThank you for putting the situation to rights. Aka\'Magosh, $N!' WHERE entry=11592;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $C. We are the Horde, we do not leave our dead behind!$B$BIt should never have been necessary in the first place. Steeljaw was a fool!' WHERE entry=11593;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $C! You must have a great deal of experience fighting the undead. And, if you didn\'t before, you have some now.$B$BYou\'ll need it if you\'re going to survive in Northrend.' WHERE entry=11594;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Hellscream has the weight of the Horde upon his shoulders. Do not be dissuaded from your duties because of his temperament, $N.$B$B<Saurfang nods.>$B$BDid you think that I would forget the name of a hero of Orgrimmar? It is not every day that I have the pleasure of putting the head of Nefarian on a pike!$B$BThe Scourge have begun their assault upon this fortress. Our soldiers steady the line, but are in desperate need of backup. Report to Razgor. He is stationed directly outside of Warsong Hold.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Overlord Razgor salutes.>$B$BYour reputation precedes you, $N.' WHERE entry=11595;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Just in time... The Nerubians have seemingly doubled in number in just a week\'s time. We could use all the help we can get out here.' WHERE entry=11596;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='It seems that we always meet in the direst of circumstances, Scarab Lord. Were you not saving the world from certain destruction the last time we met?$B$B<Saurfang chuckles.>$B$BYour assistance is most welcome in Northrend, despite what the young chieftain might say.$B$BIf we had even a dozen more soldiers with your power, we would be sitting in Orgrimmar right now, hunched over a warm fire.$B$BReport to Overlord Razgor, right outside the main entry to Warsong Hold, to the south.' WHERE entry=11597;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve slowed them down, but more are sure to join the fight. Were you able to locate any of their egg sacs while in the quarry?' WHERE entry=11598;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The corpse matches the description that Leryssa gave you of William Allerton.  Oddly enough, there are no bite or claw marks on him.' WHERE entry=11599;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Do you think William\'s death was a random killing by the Scourge?  Things sure seem fishy.$B$BSomething\'s up.  We must find Thassarian.' WHERE entry=11600;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Can\'t say I can help you friend.  But I might know someone who can.' WHERE entry=11601;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Aerial reconnaissance of the quarry reports that the Nerubians are storing their eggs on the scaffolding surrounding the base. Smart beasts these are... They\'re keeping the eggs high and dry, away from the epicenter of conflict.$B$BYou\'re going to have to go back out there and track down their eggs. Find \'em, smash \'em, and trash \'em.$B$BEach egg destroyed means twenty less Nerubians feeding on our corpses.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='They just keep on coming, despite our best efforts. Something\'s gotta give, $N.' WHERE entry=11602;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText4_loc4='Nerub\'ar Egg Sac Destroyed' WHERE entry=11602;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Mmmmm... not too bitter... not too dry... it\'s just like the old days, with the lads at the barracks.' WHERE entry=11603;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Whad\'ya want?  I have enough problems as it is!' WHERE entry=11604;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Elder Atkanok\'s voice greets you as you approach his statue.>$B$BWell done, $N. With the names of the wandering elders, we can continue the ceremonies disrupted during the attack. However, before the elders\' spirits can be led to their stones, we must calm the spirits of the murdered craftsmen and shaman. Otherwise, the ancestor spirits may never hear the ceremony\'s call.' WHERE entry=11605;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='If my calculations are correct - and they\'re often not - you\'re gonna need about 10-20 seaforium depth charges.$B$BOh yea, you\'ll be planting these mothers into their sinkholes.' WHERE entry=11606;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I can sense the upheaval in the spirit world beginning to calm. You have done well, $N. The spirits of the ancestors are fortunate to have your help in this time of need.' WHERE entry=11607;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'ll stop \'em - at least I think it\'ll stop \'em. Either way, you\'ve done your part. That\'s all an $R can ask for, no?' WHERE entry=11608;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='West Nerub\'ar Sinkhole Destroyed',ObjectiveText4_loc4='North Nerub\'ar Sinkhole Destroyed' WHERE entry=11608;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<You hold the objects before the statue of Elder Atkanok.>$B$BThose will suffice, although they are in a sad state. Some of them have survived centuries of use, only to be battered and stolen by barbarians.' WHERE entry=11609;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The ancestors have found their statues, and they have you to thank, $N. The craftsmen of Kaskala will return to the quarry and ensure that the line of ancestors continues unbroken. For our part, the ancestors will continue to observe you with interest, as it seems your path is just beginning.' WHERE entry=11610;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='<Mortuus sighs.>$B$BPeons... We may as well post up a sign offering the Nerub\'ar a free meal.$B$BSee, the problem with a peon is that: (1) they\'re dumber than dirt; and (2) they\'re weaker than a leper gnome. Of course they\'re the first to be taken by the Scourge!$B$BThis puts me in a bit of a predicament, you see. Without peons, manual labor comes to a halt. No peons, no construction.$B$BFind and release my peons, $R. If they\'re alive, you\'ll find \'em spun up in webbing throughout Mightstone Quarry.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Most of them made it back. The ones smart enough to know that we\'re inside the gigantic metal and stone building, anyway...$B$BRegardless, a job well done. I hear you sprung more than a couple peons loose.$B$BOh yes, you\'re the talk of the... um... fortress.' WHERE entry=11611;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Now that these strange mages know that the people of Kaskala and their allies will not give up the quarry so easily, we must maintain our efforts and defeat them completely.$B$BMy brothers in Kaskala have also come under attack and will not be able to support us, but with your help, $N, we can overcome these pillagers.' WHERE entry=11612;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done my people a great favor, $N.  I must ask one more thing of you, however.' WHERE entry=11613;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It doesn\'t get much deader than this... Strangely, the Nerubians did not devour the corpse.$B$BAfter careful examination you see that Luther\'s death was self inflicted - deadly poison. Smart. Nerubians won\'t come near this toxic corpse.$B$BYou notice that Luther is holding a journal.' WHERE entry=11614;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Barthus flips to the last page of the journal and begins reading.>$B$BThis is very bad news. Hellscream must be notified at once.' WHERE entry=11615;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Hellscream reads the journal entry.>$B$BIs that all?' WHERE entry=11616;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The mage hunters won\'t find it as easy to plunder our quarry and steal our artifacts as they\'d imagined. With your help, we\'ll win back the quarry and set things right again.' WHERE entry=11617;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This is it? Hellscream sent a single $R $Gboy:girl;?$B$BIf I still had a jaw it would be on the floor right now.' WHERE entry=11618;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You did it, $N!  The spirits of the slain tuskarr can now rest in peace - their deaths have been avenged!' WHERE entry=11619;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hsssssssssssss!  Have you come to mock me, $R?' WHERE entry=11620;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The curator and his men must\'ve thought the quarry an easy target for their looting, but you\'ve shown them otherwise, $N. I am deeply grateful for your help and I\'m certain the ancestors will continue to watch over you.' WHERE entry=11623;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are foolish to come here, little $R.$B$BWhat is it that you seek?' WHERE entry=11624;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yesssssss!  We will slay the Kvaldir\'s beast!  I will show these brutes to never cross a priestess of the scale!' WHERE entry=11625;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='My people\'s spirits can rest in peace.  You\'ve helped me honor my father... perhaps I will one day be as strong as you are.' WHERE entry=11626;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I am pleased, though no doubt they will still continue to quarrel a bit longer.$B$BHowever, there is something else that you will need to accomplish before you can return to your spirit talker.' WHERE entry=11627;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='As much as I dislike bringing such disease-ridden things into the village, they may give us an advantage over our foes.$B$B<The chieftain gestures to Sage Aeire and waves dismissively at the pelts.>$B$BWhile she is preparing the pelts, there is one other element we need to create the cloak.' WHERE entry=11628;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Imperean gave you a primal essence of herself? I can hear its howling winds!$B$BI know a ritual we can make use of it in. We must hurry before her primal rips itself apart!' WHERE entry=11629;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Chieftain Wintergale gingerly accepts the clods of soil you gathered.>$B$BWe should get these into Sage Aeire\'s hands as soon as possible.$B$B<The chieftain grunts, pretending not to be disturbed by the tainted dirt.>$B$BWe can never know when the Scourge commander will launch the final assault on the village.' WHERE entry=11630;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='They\'ve shackled his spirit. $N, we have to put an end to his torture!$B$BYou must descend into the bowels of Magmoth and find a way to free him!' WHERE entry=11631;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Saurfang grins.>$B$BIt looks familiar... The Might of Kalimdor trampled a thousand bugs like this one in the desert of Silithus.$B$BThis is a different place - a different environment - but the result will be the same.$B$B<Saurfang looks you over.>$B$BYou will bring pride and honor to the Horde in Northrend, $N.$B$B<Saurfang nods.>' WHERE entry=11632;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Chieftain Wintergale listens as your describe your observations.>$B$BThe information you\'ve gathered will help us to plan our assault on the Temple City. We\'ll need to find a way to defeat the officers you identified and get into that necropolis.' WHERE entry=11633;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ay, mon. I been exceptin\' you.$B$B<To\'bor points west.>$B$BTake a peek. Across dat tundra be death, mon... death.' WHERE entry=11634;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you for the reprieve, $C. If only my true freedom were so easy to attain.' WHERE entry=11635;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='NO MERCY FOR THE DEAD!$B$BNone of \'em had the guts to stay behind to defend our glorious tanks after Hellscream deemed the coast \'condemned.\' It\'s mostly quiet here, seein\' as how the Scourge are formin\' up ranks to assault Warsong Hold. Sometimes I get a stray zombie or ghoul, but they don\'t last very long.$B$B<Gorge strokes his axe.>$B$B\'Course, there\'s the mist...$B$B<Gorge shudders.>' WHERE entry=11636;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='After my small force of grunts were killed, I was dragged down here and ritually murdered. The snobold who did this is known as Kaganishu.$B$BThough you have vanquished his shaman helpers, my spirit is still tethered to this place. After he slew me, he created a fetish from my body, which anchors me here. Kaganishu is using it to learn all that I know of shamanism.$B$BYou must retrieve the fetish from him and use it upon my spirit. Kaganishu is nearby in the caves.$B$BOnly then will I truly be free.',objectives_loc4='Retrieve Kaganishu\'s Fetish and use it upon Farseer Grimwalker\'s Remains.$B$BYou will need to give the fetish to Farseer Grimwalker\'s Spirit inside of Magmoth.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I am freed. Thank you, $N.$B$BAnd now, I have one final request of you.' WHERE entry=11637;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Chieftain Wintergale reads the words written on the scrolls.>$B$B\'Shabtir bakh sokhen.\'$B$BWords of the ancient, harsh language used by the Nerubians, and apt ones at that.$B$B\'The servant bows to the master\'s authority.\' These are the words that will gain you entry into the necropolis.' WHERE entry=11640;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have proven your fearlessness and demonstrated your prowess in combat. I believe you would make a fine taunka warrior. I only wish the chieftain had the same understanding.$B$BWe are fortunate to count you as an ally in our struggle to evacuate the village before it is overrun by the Scourge.' WHERE entry=11641;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re the new tank driver, $Gbuddy:lassy;? Fine by me! We just need to get these things up and running again. Yea, you try to go out into the Plains of Nasam without a tank and you\'re as good as dead.' WHERE entry=11642;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='These wrenches are useless, buddy. I need my pneumatic tank transjigamarig to get these things up and running! Unfortunately, I left it at my old digs, on the other side of this landing. It\'s the beat down hut next to the stables. You\'re gonna have to go and get it for me, because I sure as hellfire am not going to go anywhere near the mist.$B$BOh yea, buddy, watch out for the mist. The mist is what tore up these shores.$B',objectives_loc4='Mobu at the Coast of Echoes in the Borean Tundra wants you to recover his Pneumatic Tank Transjigamarig.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Great work, $Gbuddy:lassy;! Now where\'d I put those spare parts...' WHERE entry=11643;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Great work, $Gbuddy:lassy;! Now where\'d I put that pneumatic tank transjigamarig.' WHERE entry=11644;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh, $N, you\'re just the best!$B$BHere\'s your coin as promised.' WHERE entry=11645;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It was wise of Donathan to send you, $C.$B$BAs it turns out, I am in need of someone outside the Kirin Tor.' WHERE entry=11646;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Sage Aeire accepts the totem from you.>$B$BDid the totem work? Its preparation required ancient magics the sages haven\'t used in generations. Of all the knowledge passed down, only a fraction of it remains in use today.' WHERE entry=11647;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent! It was crucial that we collect that intelligence.$B$BWell done, friend.' WHERE entry=11648;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I regret the loss of those tempests, but my word is my bond... even to a mortal such as yourself.$B$BNow, let us see if we can fashion something of use to you.' WHERE entry=11649;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Alright, that\'s more like it! Now all we gots to do is put all this together.$B$BYeah, as if you\'re going to help me with that.$B$BHold your horses, this\'ll just take a second now that I\'ve got my tools back!' WHERE entry=11650;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Thanks for all your help, buddy. You can let Gorge know the tanks are ready for action. Hopefully you can clean up this place once and for all!$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='With the current state of our transports and shipping lanes, we haven\'t been able to get a damned siege engine to Warsong. These tanks are all that we have left from the original expedition. Now that they\'re operational, you\'re gonna use \'em to stomp the Scourge offensive at the Plains of Nasam.' WHERE entry=11651;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Kel\'Thuzad? So it\'s true - Naxxramas returns...$B$BPerhaps I underestimated you, $N. You\'ve done the Horde a great service. The Warchief would be proud!$B$B<Garrosh pauses to think.>$B$BIf Kel\'Thuzad is controlling these Scourge, there\'s no telling what else the Lich King has in store for us... I\'ll need time to think through this new information, $N. You are dismissed.' WHERE entry=11652;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Whadya mean it didn\'t work?!$B$BBut... but...$B$B<Crafty begins to sob.>$B$BOkay, we can deal with this. I\'m a big girl. Time to think outside the box!' WHERE entry=11653;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Sadness overcomes Waltor.>$B$BRuin... That is all they leave in their wake. They must be taught a lesson.' WHERE entry=11655;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Waltor of Pal\'ea at the Coast of Echoes in the Borean Tundra wants you to use the Tuskarr Torch to burn the Kvaldir ships at Pal\'ea and Garrosh\'s Landing. You must destroy the following ships: The Serpent\'s Maw, The Kur Drakkar, Bor\'s Hammer and Bor\'s Anvil.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='A show of resistance to the Kvaldir savages might be what is needed to save my people at the other encampments. Perhaps the Kvaldir will rethink their actions should they believe that retribution will come.' WHERE entry=11656;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Bor\'s Hammer destroyed',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Bor\'s Anvil destroyed' WHERE entry=11656;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Nice, but those clothes reek!$B$BPersonally, you\'d never catch me dead in such rags. But we\'re going to have to sort through them and find some that fit your, um... figure.' WHERE entry=11658;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You must call for Orabus using the Horn of the Ancient Mariner.' WHERE entry=11660;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It seems that the loss of their lieutenant has only stirred the nest. They are more angry and aggressive than before!$B$B<Waltor sighs.>$B$BYou\'ve done what you can here, friend. At the very least you deserve some form of compensation for thinning their numbers.' WHERE entry=11661;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Waltor was wise in sending you to me, $R. The gods smile down upon those that mete justice. You will be he that doles out punishment to the wicked!' WHERE entry=11662;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Forgive me, $N. I know that was unpleasant work.$B$BWere it not for the desperation of our circumstance I\'d never have asked you to assist us in such a manner.$B$BSo... what have you discovered?' WHERE entry=11663;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It is whispered in the winds, friend. Your name is known to the elements. You have done a great service to Mootoo on this day and you shall be rewarded.' WHERE entry=11664;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What a mean little creature!  I\'m sure the Rokk will make something tasty with him.$B$BI\'m just kidding, of course.$B$B<Old Man Barlo winks slyly.>' WHERE entry=11665;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well look at that... you caught a big one!  This old man is eating in style tonight.' WHERE entry=11666;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='There he is!  I\'d know that scar anywhere.$B$BTo be completely honest, I thought he\'d be... bigger.  Well, I suppose I\'ll let him go and try again another day.' WHERE entry=11667;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are skilled with both the hook and knife.  Hand those sweet tidbits over, and I\'ll let you have a taste.' WHERE entry=11668;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That is the biggest, ugliest fish I\'ve seen.  I can\'t even imagine what you used for bait.$B$BJust set the beast on the ground, and I\'ll deal with it once I\'m sure it\'s dead.' WHERE entry=11669;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Holey moley, you did it!$B$BAlright, now those pesky magnataur and their snobold flunkies should turn their attentions on the Horde.$B$BHow can I ever repay you, $N?' WHERE entry=11670;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Broken? $B$BLet me have a look....' WHERE entry=11671;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We\'ve been expecting your arrival, $N.  Welcome to Northrend.' WHERE entry=11672;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Huh? What?$B$BBonker who?$B$BI\'ve no idea who you\'re talking about, but I\'ll take your word for it. If you rescued him or her from the pit of Magmoth then I suppose you deserve a reward.$B$BLet me see what I\'ve got lying around in here....' WHERE entry=11673;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The greatmother sent you. She must be disappointed in me.$B$BBut when I saw the great object fall from the sky, I could not wait for a full group of longrunners and snow trackers to accompany me. Knowledge waits for no one.' WHERE entry=11674;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The magnataur at the Dens of Dying have contracted a plague. We must find the cause, but first we must put them out of their misery.$B$B$R, you must go north onto the slopes in front of us and destroy as many of the poor creatures as you can.',offerrewardtext_loc4='What else can we do but ease their suffering? In any case, they came here to die, so do not mourn them. At least you have given them some dignity.$B$BNow we must put an end to that which is causing the plague.' WHERE entry=11675;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Each prisoner saved is one less undead aberration that we have to deal with, $N. You\'ve done a great service for the Horde.' WHERE entry=11676;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The sage hangs her head and sighs in relief.>$B$BThis is a good start. If only that were our only problem.' WHERE entry=11677;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I am... not... long for this... world, little $R.' WHERE entry=11678;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The frivolous games you play here are of no consequence....$B$BYou and your Dalaran allies pick at loose threads while the fabric of this world\'s future is being shredded.$B$BStill, this may provide my drakes some needed amusement.$B$BShow me this key....' WHERE entry=11679;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Give Salrand\'s Key to Warmage Anzim when you are ready to free Evanor.',offerrewardtext_loc4='This is it, the key is ours!' WHERE entry=11680;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Your heroic efforts shall not be forgotten, $C.$B$BPlease, accept this with my sincere gratitude.' WHERE entry=11681;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So, $R, we speak again.$B$BWhen you\'ve heard my words you may wish we had not.' WHERE entry=11682;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $N.$B$BThe Lich King and his Scourge are a blight upon Northrend. We must not stop until they are all truly dead, and his existence is put to an end!' WHERE entry=11683;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Greatfather Mahan accepts the map, but makes no move to examine it..>$B$BWe\'ll be able to use your information later, once we\'re prepared to carry out the plan.' WHERE entry=11684;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These should be enough to form the core of a mighty elemental, but stone alone will not give my elemental life.' WHERE entry=11685;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This is far worse than what was noted in Luther\'s journal. They\'ve got this place covered in Scourge and are infecting everything they touch.$B$B<Ickoris nods.>$B$BIt gets worse - if you can imagine such a thing...' WHERE entry=11686;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Bristlehorn is dead?!$B$BI should never have let him go there by himself.' WHERE entry=11687;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I think I\'ve got it, $R!' WHERE entry=11688;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What word do you bring from Highmesa?$B$B<You explain what you know and give the greatmother the bad news concerning Longrunner Bristlehorn.>$B$BMy... my grandson!$B$B<The greatmother fights to keep control of her emotions.>$B$BHe died an honorable death like a true taunka!$B$BYou were the last to be with him, $N, so he shall always be a part of you. I give you my thanks for completing his last wishes.' WHERE entry=11689;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re a true hero, $N. My kodos would have died out there without you. You have my thanks and the thanks of all the soldiers and journeymen that will use these kodos to strengthen our presence in Northrend!' WHERE entry=11690;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Nice work, but I\'d grab a shower the next chance you get.$B$BNow, let\'s really deal with the problem out here.' WHERE entry=11693;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I knew you had it in you. Now there\'s something else that I need to ask you to take care of.' WHERE entry=11694;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Barah accepts the pieces of the horn from you and begins trying to fit them together.>$B$BStormhoof would be proud of you, $N. Perhaps when we\'ve dealt with the Scourge, I will take the horn with me on a pilgrimage to Stormhoof\'s tomb.' WHERE entry=11695;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hey there! Who are you?$B$BBixie sent you? Excellent, let\'s get me out of here!' WHERE entry=11697;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thanks, $N.$B$BThe Lich King and his Scourge are really scary, but we can\'t stop until they are all lying still in new graves!' WHERE entry=11698;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Outstanding! Now just a little modification here, and a tweak there....' WHERE entry=11699;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Tinky\'s got an evil twin?!$B$BWell, if she says she\'s okay, and that she\'ll be able to get herself back to the airstrip soon, that\'s good enough for me.' WHERE entry=11700;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'s quite a tale, $N. With all of the problems out here, it\'s a wonder that the airstrip hasn\'t been wiped out already.$B$BBut, thanks to you, there\'s one less adversary to worry about.$B$BI put aside some special things for just such an occasion as this. Why don\'t you take your pick?' WHERE entry=11701;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Finally, help! And by the looks of you, Horde.$B$BThat\'s alright... your people are very skilled in the art of combat. We\'re going to need a lot of that.' WHERE entry=11702;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Getry looks you over.>%B%BThis is all Ickoris could send?' WHERE entry=11703;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Finally, help! And by the looks of you, Alliance.$B$BThat\'s good... your people are very skilled in the art of combat. We\'re going to need a lot of that.' WHERE entry=11704;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Help Getry defeat Varidus the Flenser at Warsong Farms.$B$BReport to Garrosh Hellscream should you succeed.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='And you returned victorious, just as I thought! I told Saurfang you\'d be fine.$B$B<Hellscream grunts knowingly.>$B$BPerhaps this will show that old dog that he doesn\'t have all the answers, eh?' WHERE entry=11705;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Your efforts against the Nerubians have given us a reprieve from the overwhelming Scourge assault. Thanks to your accomplishments, we can strike at the the Scourge fortress to the northeast without fear of attack from the west.$B$BAs for the horn, I will safeguard it until next we need its power. Stormhoof gave his life to secure the horn and we cannot suffer its loss again.' WHERE entry=11706;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I see that Skyhopper finally got around to sending help. And none too soon I might add!$B$BWelcome, $Gbrother:sister;, we need your help badly!' WHERE entry=11707;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The old man sent you to me, huh? He tell you everything that\'s going on out here?$B$BGood... let\'s take care of business then!' WHERE entry=11708;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Nork scoffs.>$B$BPrisoners? These aren\'t prisoners. They\'re cowardly dogs! Just look at \'em. Did you know that without exception, every single one of these yellow-bellied "soldiers" came to our gates and surrendered their arms and armor?$B$BFrom what we\'ve been able to gather, these men and women are discharged and sent back to their homes if captured by us.$B$B<Nork spits.>$B$BPathetic...' WHERE entry=11709;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'s great, $C! These parts look like they\'re in serviceable condition.$B$BNow if I could only figure out how to fix this blasted thing....' WHERE entry=11710;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We\'re seeing more deserters show up at our gates with each passing day. We simply do not have enough room to keep all of these maggots caged up. Especially not if we want to keep the pigs happy.$B$B<Nork snorts as he laughs.>$B$BI want you to escort one of these cowards to the crossroads east of here and fire this flare gun. One of their captains will show up when they see the flare and take the coward off your hands.$B$BReport to Scout Tungok on the east road once the delivery has been made.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Good job, $N. That\'s one less filthy, useless, Alliance scum-bag that we\'ll have to provide for...$B$BIf you\'re lookin\' for more work, the tauren and blood elf nearby need some help.$B$B\'Course we\'ve got our own set of problems to deal with out here as well...' WHERE entry=11711;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You did it... it worked!$B$BI can\'t believe you were able to save so many. We\'re fortunate to have you around here!' WHERE entry=11712;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Abner accepts the map from you, then examines it closely.>$B$BGreat! This is all the information we need to begin the operation.' WHERE entry=11713;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Perhaps you\'d be interested in helping me clean up these fields? They\'re littered with dirty little rat men! Kobolds, snobolds, whatever you wanna call \'em, they\'re all over the damned place. The stink alone is making my life hell!$B$BTake care of the vermin for me and I\'ll make it worth your while, $N.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='A job well done, $N! Thank you!' WHERE entry=11714;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Abner sets about draining the fuel tank of the collector.>$B$BDistilling this by hand is going to be messy, but I\'ll have it taken care of soon. In the meantime, we\'ll need one more material to complete the machine.' WHERE entry=11715;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Lovely! Just lovely!$B$B<Laurith applies a sprinkling of pollen to one of the bloodspore carpels and then utters an incantation.>$B$BHrmph... I don\'t understand. Unless... Why of course!' WHERE entry=11716;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bloodmage Laurith at the Bloodspore Plains in the Borean Tundra wants you to recover 5 Bloodspore Moth Pollen.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='A-ha!$B$B<Laurith sprinkles the moth pollen onto the bloodspore carpels.>$B$BLook at that!' WHERE entry=11717;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Abner inspects the hides, coughing at all the dust rising from them.>$B$BDon\'t these animals even try to keep clean? Some of these are absolutely filthy. Well, I guess I\'d better get started cleaning them. It\'s not like anyone\'s got spare time around here.' WHERE entry=11718;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Primal Mighthorn will be delighted! This is better than even I expected!$B$BPerhaps it\'s time that I told you the truth.' WHERE entry=11719;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Speak to Primal Mighthorn at the Bloodspore Plains in the Borean Tundra.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='The bloodspore that you collected might just be enough to give us an edge against the magnataurs of Gammoth - with your help, of course.' WHERE entry=11720;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A job well done, $N! Would you honor Laurith and I by taking the head of the beast and presenting it to Hellscream? He will be extremely pleased.' WHERE entry=11721;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Hellscream picks up the head of Gammothra with one arm and spits in its face.>$B$BThey will learn, $N... They will all learn. The Horde is not to be trifled with...' WHERE entry=11722;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Abner listens eagerly as you report your success and the success of the Shake-n-Quake 5000.>$B$BFizzcrank will be delighted to hear the news! And who knows, perhaps we\'ll make a mechanic of you yet!' WHERE entry=11723;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Alkor is no more, eh? A pity... As for the egg, we have no real use for it anymore. We\'ve got much bigger problems to deal with now.' WHERE entry=11724;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank goodness. It was terrible.$B$BThere was a bright flash on the ground, and then, the next thing I know, the squadron\'s going down! I\'m hurt pretty badly, so I haven\'t had a chance to comb the site for other survivors, but something tells me I don\'t think there will be many.$B$B<Iggy grimaces in pain.>$B$BWill you help me complete my mission?' WHERE entry=11725;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Iggy holds his nose as he empties the spice pouches and addresses you in a nasal voice.>$B$BNow that we have what we need, I\'ll combine it with my emergency rations to create a bait for the wolves.' WHERE entry=11726;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='By Magni\'s beard!  Looks like the heavy artillery\'s arriving.' WHERE entry=11727;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Iggy holds his nose as he accepts the microfilm from you.>$B$BYuck, well, we\'ve complied with section 8.2, paragraph B of the emergency protocol here and recovered the film. Nothing in the protocol says I\'m responsible for cleaning it, though.' WHERE entry=11728;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='My screwdriver... you found my screwdriver! I\'d been wondering where that thing got lost.$B$BHmm, you found it inside one of their robots, you say? That gives me an idea....' WHERE entry=11729;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Woo hoo! And you brought back the screwdriver intact, too!$B$BReprogramming those robots is going to turn out to be a huge advantage in our favor in the fight against Gearmaster Mechazod. I think you\'ve earned a little something for that.' WHERE entry=11730;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='So you want to be a fire juggler?  Do you have what it takes?  The dexterity?  The reflexes?  ...the courage?  If you think so, then let\'s give you a little practice!$B$BTake these torches and run near the bonfire.  You\'ll see  braziers with markers flashing above them.  Toss a torch at a marked brazier.  Be quick! Do it before the mark fades if you want credit for the toss!$B$BHit enough marked braziers before the time limit, then come back here... for your next lession.' WHERE entry=11731;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Welcome to Coldarra, $C.$B$BUnder the Transitus Shield we lie hidden just a stone\'s throw from the Nexus, fortress of the great aspect Malygos and his blue dragonflight.$B$BDo make yourself comfortable.' WHERE entry=11733;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Desecrate the Alliance\'s Feralas bonfire!' WHERE entry=11746;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Desecrate the Alliance\'s Silithus bonfire!' WHERE entry=11760;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Desecrate the Alliance\'s Stranglethorn Vale bonfire!' WHERE entry=11761;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Desecrate the Alliance\'s Tanaris bonfire!' WHERE entry=11762;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Desecrate the Alliance\'s Winterspring bonfire!' WHERE entry=11763;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Wow, you survived!$B$BI guess all that\'s left to do now is to deal with Gearmaster Mechazod.' WHERE entry=11788;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I thank you, $N.  This man\'s recovery will be slow, but we won\'t lose him.$B$BWhat do you say?  You found cultists inside the Stormbreaker?  You\'d best notify someone... and bring some evidence.' WHERE entry=11789;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Cultists? Below deck? I ought to have my whole crew flogged!$B$BListen... why don\'t we have Admiral Cantlebree take care of this... situation?' WHERE entry=11790;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you for your concern, $N.  We were made aware of the situation not too long ago.$B$BCounselor Talbot assures me that this was an isolated incident and not a cause for military concern.$B$BOur civilian authorities will make sure everyone involved is properly prosecuted.' WHERE entry=11791;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Be discreet, $N.  We cannot look at this evidence in front of prying eyes.' WHERE entry=11792;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Speak quickly, $C.  What information do you have on the cult?' WHERE entry=11793;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done well, $N.  However, I can\'t shake the feeling that this is not the last we\'ve seen of these death cultists.$B$BDarkness has a way of hiding even in plain sight.' WHERE entry=11794;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you once again, $N. With your help, I may yet be able to complete this mission, disastrous as it\'s been, and return to Fizzcrank to make my report and properly honor the dead.' WHERE entry=11795;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Once again, you have my thanks, $N. Without you, I would not have been able to recover anything useful from this disaster.' WHERE entry=11796;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Nice job, $N.  Show the lads how it\'s done.  The only good creeper\'s a dead creeper!' WHERE entry=11797;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The old gnome breathes a heavy sigh of relief.>$B$BIt is done then... you have saved us! If you hadn\'t stopped him here, then who knows how far his madness would have spread?$B$BWith the threats from the blue dragons and the Nexus War, not to mention the Lich King, the last thing we need is a mad creation of the Titans running loose!$B$BThank you, $N!' WHERE entry=11798;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Honor the Silithus flame.' WHERE entry=11836;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Honor the Stranglethorn Vale flame.' WHERE entry=11837;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Honor the Winterspring flame.' WHERE entry=11839;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Honor the Arathi Highlands flame.' WHERE entry=11840;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Honor the Ashenvale flame.' WHERE entry=11841;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Honor the Badlands flame.' WHERE entry=11842;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Honor the Burning Steppes flame.' WHERE entry=11844;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Honor the Desolace flame.' WHERE entry=11845;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Honor the Dustwallow Marsh flame.' WHERE entry=11847;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Honor the Feralas flame.' WHERE entry=11849;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Honor the Hellfire Peninsula flame.' WHERE entry=11851;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Honor the Hillsbrad Foothills flame.' WHERE entry=11853;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Honor the Nagrand flame.' WHERE entry=11854;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Honor the Stonetalon Mountains flame.' WHERE entry=11856;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Honor the Swamp of Sorrows flame.' WHERE entry=11857;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Honor the Terokkar Forest flame.' WHERE entry=11858;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Honor the Barrens flame.' WHERE entry=11859;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Honor the Hinterlands flame.' WHERE entry=11860;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Honor the Thousand Needles flame.' WHERE entry=11861;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Honor the Zangarmarsh flame.' WHERE entry=11863;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The demon has many names and each name has held special meaning at one time or another. While the details were sometimes insignificant, the end result was always the same: death.$B$BBut it is now, nearly fifty years after it all began, that the details will find the devil and lead to his downfall.$B$BThis time, we have him... There will be no escape for Nesingwary.$B$BNorthrend will be the battleground for our war. The hunter will become the hunted!' WHERE entry=11864;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Zaza at the D.E.H.T.A. Encampment in the Borean Tundra wants you to use the Pile of Fake Furs to trap 8 Nesingwary Trappers.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='You do the Earth Mother\'s work, $N, but do not revel in this victory for too long. We have discovered the hiding place of the trapper leader.' WHERE entry=11865;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Whether they be treasure seekers or bloodthirsty hunters of the wastes, any being that supports Nesingwary and dares to strike at our beloved wildlife shall be considered an enemy of D.E.H.T.A.$B$BShould you slay these filthy Nesingwary sympathizers, bring me proof of their demise and you shall be rewarded with a blessing from the druids of D.E.H.T.A.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='These will hang around my neck. Let them hear our message and let these ears be the vessels that carry our truths!' WHERE entry=11866;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Whether they be treasure seekers or bloodthirsty hunters of the wastes, any being that supports Nessingwary and does dare strike at our beloved wildlife shall be considered an enemy of D.E.H.T.A. Should you slay these filthy Nesingwary sympathizers, bring me proof of their demise and you shall be rewarded with a blessing from the druids of D.E.H.T.A.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='These will hang around my neck. Let them hear our message and let these ears be the vessels that carry our truths!' WHERE entry=11867;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Near the southern end of this bluff is where you will find the treacherous leader of the caribou trappers. She is a savage like no other, making a mockery out of the carcasses of the slain animals: drinking from their blood and howling to the moons!$B$BFind this murderer, Karen, and end her worthless existence.$B$BPrepare yourself properly, $N. Karen the Culler has indulged in the riches that Nesingwary has lavished upon her! She will be well armed and guarded by lackeys.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Perhaps her death will serve as an example to others that dare slay animals for sport and riches.' WHERE entry=11868;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Now let us see how their nerve holds up when they see what became of their companions!' WHERE entry=11869;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We have just gotten word from Liandra that mercenaries hired by Nesingwary are moving goods off the beach and onto the main Nesingwary shipping vessel. No doubt they plan on making a fortune from their murderous trade!$B$BShe has asked that we send assistance to the Abandoned Reach, directly south of here on the beachfront of the Borean Tundra.$B$BMake haste, Liandra awaits you there!$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Cenius sent you? Well you\'re not a moment too soon!' WHERE entry=11870;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A job well done, $N. Now we strike at the pirate leader!' WHERE entry=11871;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Slay Clam Master K and return to Hierophant Cenius at the D.E.H.T.A. Encampment.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work, $N. We are closing in on Nesingwary!' WHERE entry=11872;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Fizzcrank listens to your report, looking somewhat relieved.>$B$BI should\'ve gone with them. We might\'ve been able to complete the mission without losing any pilots.$B$BTailspin is right, though, we have you to thank for what you\'ve been able to salvage. Your efforts may just make the difference in the fight against the Nerubians.' WHERE entry=11873;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The troops of the Shattered Sun Offensive will need every advantage they can get to beat back the allies of Kil\'Jaeden. My colleagues in Stormwind have created oils which will strengthen the blades and armor of our troops.$B$BThe key ingredient, nether residue, pervades Outland  -- if you know where to look. Any master herbalist, skinner, or miner who knows the signs can gather it while plying $G his:her; trade. Those herbs, ores, and beasts unique to Outland may all bear the residue.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you for your help, $N. No contribution to the war effort is too small. Our men are going to need every advantage they can get in this battle.' WHERE entry=11875;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Arch Druid Lathorius wipes away his tears.>$B$BThey never stood a chance. Now orphaned, they will surely die on their own.' WHERE entry=11876;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Lord Torvos accepts the plans and looks over them.>$B$BYou\'ve done the offensive a great service, $N, but we should not rest. I wouldn\'t put it beyond our foes to plan more mischief in the future.' WHERE entry=11877;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<You hear a voice in your head. It is Khu\'nok.>$B$BYour name has been heard in the whistling winds, $N. You have done a great thing for my kin. For this we will consider you an ally. Alas, our torment cannot end without bloodshed and violence.$B$BThe price of peace for the mammoths will be the death of Kaw...' WHERE entry=11878;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Lathorius takes the halberd from you.>$B$BIs this what I think it is?$B$B<Lathorius grins.>$B$BSmashing! Outstanding! Another of Nesingwary\'s lackeys brought to justice!' WHERE entry=11879;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thanks for your help. You don\'t know what it\'s like to have to deal with "Doctor" Wafflefry over there. In between his "checkups" on my progress, he\'s busy hawking some gadget or another derived from his military inventions.' WHERE entry=11880;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Fezzix looks over the salvage.>$B$BJenny\'s a little roughed up, but she\'ll be fine. As for the salvage, it\'s a bit more... piecemeal than I had hoped, but I should be able to find a use for it. You\'re not off the hook yet, though. We\'re going to rebuild this baby.' WHERE entry=11881;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='West of here, on the high bluffs above Lake Kum\'uya, roams a despicable being known as Nedar. The self proclaimed "Lord of Rhinos" hunts the wastes for the injured or young - rhinos unable to defend themselves against Ned\'s cowardly attacks. To add insult to injury, Ned has raised a rhino of his own to become his mount and bodyguard.$B$BIt is a rare thing that D.E.H.T.A. would ever call for the death of an animal, but Ned\'s tainted rhino must be disposed of... Kill them both and return to me.',objectives_loc4='Killinger the Den Watcher at the D.E.H.T.A. Encampment in the Borean Tundra wants you to kill Nedar, Lord of Rhinos and his companion, "Lunchbox."',offerrewardtext_loc4='At least for now the rhinos will know peace. Thank you, $N.' WHERE entry=11884;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent! Take this. I\'ve prepared this bundle with items symbolizing the foes you\'ve defeated. They will allow you to summon Terokk.$B$BBeware, $N. He is the most powerful arakkoa to ever exist. Do not underestimate him!' WHERE entry=11885;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Gnomish tools? For me? These should make rebuilding that flying machine even easier than I expected.' WHERE entry=11887;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='$R, the chieftain is making me wait... time that Taunka\'le does not have!$B$BThere has been talk of your prowess. Rather than wait for Garrosh to send help, I ask you to go and help my people.$B$BTaunka\'le village lies far to the northeast. Follow the road east out of the hold, turning north at the intersection. Not long after, you will come to another intersection. Follow the path east, passing south and then east of the great pools along the flood plains.$B$BSpeak with Sage Earth and Sky when you arrive.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It does not surprise me that the $R chieftain does not have time to hear of our troubles. The ambassador\'s efforts will likely be like so much mist blowing in the wind.$B$BBut you are here now. We shall see if he chose well in sending you.' WHERE entry=11888;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We\'ll beat them if they come by land and we\'ll beat them if they come by air.  If these motherless undead come by sea we\'re going to give them the beating of their lives.' WHERE entry=11889;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Troubling news indeed.$B$BMy people are leaving this place soon. We are going to break through the Scourge lines to get to our capital, Icemist, in the Dragonblight.$B$BBut, before we do that, we must deal with what the gnomes in their insanity have wrought.' WHERE entry=11890;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You have done much for the animals of the Borean Tundra, $N. Nesingwary\'s lackeys have been beaten back and taught a lesson that they will not soon forget.$B$BHarold Lane, the primary agent responsible for the mass slaughters in Nagrand, has been identified as the man in charge of Nesingwary operations in the tundra. He is stationed at Lake Kum\'uya, west of here.$B$B<Lathorius hands you an intricately carved oak horn.>$B$BFind Lane and kill him. Use this horn should you require our aid.$B',objectives_loc4='Arch Druid Lathorius at the D.E.H.T.A. Outpost in the Borean Tundra wants you to kill Harold Lane.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Alas, Nesingwary is gone. Perhaps he was never here to begin with...$B$B<Lathorius sighs.>$B$BThe demon is a slippery one, but his days are numbered. We will find him and when we do...' WHERE entry=11892;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Dorain nods.>$B$BGood. This should be sufficient to show Fezzix exactly what I\'ve been trying to tell him.' WHERE entry=11893;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Fantastic! A few more tweaks and I\'ll be an airborne goblin!' WHERE entry=11894;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I feel the power of the storm coursing through you!$B$BYou are ready, $N. Let us begin.' WHERE entry=11895;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='With their robotic minions dealt with, it is time for us to move on to bigger prey. Unfortunately, even now I feel the power of the storm waning from within you.$B$BNevertheless, it served its purpose, and I think that you\'re more than capable of taking the next step without it.' WHERE entry=11896;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work, $N.  Without you, Valiance Keep might\'ve not held against the attackers.  Thanks to your help we\'ll live to fight another day.' WHERE entry=11897;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='With the prince defeated, the Scourge presence in Borean Tundra is broken. I have no illusions that they will stay away for long, which is why I must focus on preparing Durm to lead the villagers on their way to Icemist.$B$B<The chieftain shakes his head slowly.>$B$BFor all the disagreements I\'ve had with Durm, I trust his judgment and his abilities. I cannot bring myself to abandon Taunka\'le, so I will defend it until I am slain.' WHERE entry=11898;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Now we must free the souls that you have captured.' WHERE entry=11899;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This is worse than I expected.$B$BMalygos is channeling too much power to this place. If he\'s not stopped, Azeroth will be the next Outlands!$B$BFortunately, I believe that I\'ve engineered a temporary solution....' WHERE entry=11900;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Northern Coldarra Reading',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Western Coldarra Reading' WHERE entry=11900;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='There\'s Scourge everywhere, $C.  We\'ve organized the farmers and miners into a militia, but this just won\'t cut it.$B$BThe one detachment of troops that Valiance Keep sent is defending the mine.  We haven\'t heard from them in days!$B$BIf you really wish to help us, why don\'t you go to the mine and see what\'s going on?  Maybe we can get them to send us some reinforcements.',objectives_loc4='Gerald Green in Farshire wants you to go into the mine to the north and find out what happened to the military detachment that was sent there.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Your stomach feels uneasy as you approach the grain.  The smell is nearly unbearable.' WHERE entry=11901;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Those poor lads... they never had a chance!$B$BThis sure sounds like an inside job.  Probably a Cult of the Damned infiltrator.  Curse those madmen!' WHERE entry=11902;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve communicated with the Scourge in the only language they understand: violence and death.  Unfortunately they just keep coming!' WHERE entry=11903;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I thank you, $N.  This ore will be of vital importance to the Alliance in the times to come.  I\'d like to think we\'ve made a difference today.' WHERE entry=11904;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I\'ve determined the cause of the instability!$B$BAzeroth\'s ley lines are being redirected to the Nexus. It\'s fascinating! If only I could spend the remainder of my days studying this anomaly....$B$BSadly, I must focus on the immediate crisis. The influx of arcane energies is tearing a rift between dimensions.$B$BDeep inside the Nexus, the fabric of our universe is being weakened. I cannot stop it, but I\'ve discovered a way to slow it down.$B$BTake this into the Nexus and activate it near the forming rift.',objectives_loc4='Archmage Berinand in the Transitus Shield wants you to use the Interdimensional Refabricator near the rift in the Nexus.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work, $N. The tremors have already begun to subside.$B$BWith any luck, your efforts have granted us sufficient time to find a way to thwart Malygos\' efforts.' WHERE entry=11905;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It is the taunka way to leave the land pristine before we move on.$B$BWe will be traveling to our capital, Icemist, very soon. You have helped by allowing us to depart that much more quickly.$B$BThank you.' WHERE entry=11906;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $N.$B$BWith these odd creatures destroyed, dealing with the rest of the pools should now be a simple matter.$B$BWe owe you a debt of gratitude.' WHERE entry=11907;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent!  The information I need should be in here.' WHERE entry=11908;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The greatmother breathes a heavy sigh of relief.>$B$BIt is done then... you have saved us! If you hadn\'t stopped him here, then who knows how far this mistake of the gnomes would have spread?$B$BWith the threats from the blue dragons and the Nexus War, not to mention the Lich King, the last thing we need is a mad creation of the Titans running loose!$B$BThank you, $N.' WHERE entry=11909;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes, yes. These shall do nicely.$B$BThank you, $R.' WHERE entry=11910;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Though we may be witnessing the end of our existence, I can\'t help but marvel. I\'ve learned more in my short time here than in decades of studies.$B$BThese Ancients are being exposed to incredible levels of arcane energy. It\'s literally transforming them into something... different.$B$BI\'m confident that there\'s another stage in their metamorphosis. I\'ll need you to actually enter the Nexus, $N, and find me some evidence of their final state.$B$BDo be careful....',objectives_loc4='Archmage Berinand in the Transitus Shield wants you to enter the Nexus and collect 5 Arcane Splinters from Crystalline Protectors.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Fascinating!$B$BAnd they\'re aggressive too, you say. That would suggest that some intelligence is behind this manipulation. It may not be natural at all....$B$BPlease, $N, accept this as a token of our gratitude for your efforts. Dalaran will hear of your service.' WHERE entry=11911;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, it\'s not much, but it should keep us alive for another day.$B$BI believe you\'ll find this to be a fair price for your efforts.' WHERE entry=11912;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I thank you, $N.  I would hate to see survivors of the attack on Farshire stumble upon plagued grain.' WHERE entry=11913;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Your service to Dalaran will not go unnoticed, $R.$B$BI hope you find this payment sufficient.' WHERE entry=11914;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Greetings. You\'ve come learn some new ways to handle fire?' WHERE entry=11915;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I fear that you may be too late, champion. Many of my brothers and sisters have already abandoned Taunka\'le, seeking shelter in the Dragonblight, far to the east.$B$BThere is much work left to be done here and few willing to lend us their strength...' WHERE entry=11916;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We must act to preserve the balance! Time is against us.$B$BReturn to the camp on the Zoram Strand with the large ice stones. They use them to communicate with the elementals, as they do in Silithus. Much as I am loath to do this, the spirits will understand - you must summon one of this Ahune\'s lieutenants and destroy it. Perhaps this forestalling action will be enough...',objectives_loc4='Slay the Frostwave Lieutenant summoned from the Ice Stone located on Zoram Strand in Ashenvale, then return to the Earthen Ring Elder in a capital city.' WHERE entry=11917;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Alright, $C, now that you\'ve become familiar with the enemy it\'s time for you to get to work.' WHERE entry=11918;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The fate of these young drakes need not burden your conscience, $R. Malygos alone is accountable for this.$B$BI am working ceaselessly to discover the secrets of these runes. We shall take no more lives than we must.' WHERE entry=11919;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Cultists? Below deck? I ought to have my whole crew flogged!$B$BListen... why don\'t we have Admiral Cantlebree take care of this... situation?' WHERE entry=11920;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='So you want to be a fire juggler?  Do you have what it takes?  The dexterity?  The reflexes?  ...the courage?  If you think so, then let\'s give you a little practice!$B$BTake these torches and run near the bonfire.  You\'ll see  braziers with markers flashing above them.  Toss a torch at a marked brazier.  Be quick! Do it before the mark fades if you want credit for the toss!$B$BHit enough marked braziers before the time limit, then come back here... for your next lession.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done!  You\'ll be a fire juggler faster than the fuse on a ground flower!  Now gird yourself!  The next test is when things really heat up...' WHERE entry=11922;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Hello, fire juggler!  Are you having fun and making fiery mayhem?  That\'s what I like to hear!  Now, do you think you\'re an expert at torch tossing?  Then I have a test for you...$B$BYou know the rules: toss torches at the marked braziers.  This time, however, you have a little more time and a LOT more braizers to hit.$B$BReady?' WHERE entry=11926;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Find Leryssa at the inn in Valiance Keep',offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you for coming to see me.  I didn\'t know who else to contact.' WHERE entry=11927;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re here to help?  You\'re just in time then!' WHERE entry=11928;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Mother Tauranook wipes her tears away.>$B$BThere was once a time when I could walk across this tundra and the snow would fill my view for as far as I could see.$B$BBut the snow has left us - signaling that our time here has come to an end. We leave behind Taunka\'le Village and the Borean Tundra with many happy memories...$B$B<Mother Tauranook whimpers.>$B$BPerhaps the future will welcome our return - along with the snow.' WHERE entry=11929;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Escort the Taunka\'le Evacuees across Transborea to Wartook Iceborn on the border of the Dragonblight.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Wartook looks upon you grimly.>$B$BIcemist is no more...' WHERE entry=11930;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well, $R.$B$BLet us hope for a clue that we can use against Malygos.' WHERE entry=11931;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I remember the man you speak of.  He bore the marks of Karkut.$B$BMay Karkut protect our fallen.' WHERE entry=11932;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It pains me to order the destruction of dragon eggs, enemy or no.$B$BMay the ends of this war justify the means....' WHERE entry=11936;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That should buy us some time.  Isidorus has been cooperative, but I really needed that alone time with the lich.' WHERE entry=11938;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='En\'kilah Casualty' WHERE entry=11938;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The fate of these young drakes need not burden your conscience, $R. Malygos alone is accountable for this.$B$BI am working ceaselessly to discover the secrets of these runes.$B$BRest assured, we shall take no more lives than we must.' WHERE entry=11940;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It was wise of you to bring this to me, $N.$B$B<Raelorasz eyes the fragment and slowly nods.>$B$BIf you truly desire to contribute to our efforts, no matter the risk, I shall share with you its meaning.' WHERE entry=11941;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work, $N.  Now for one last bit of information.' WHERE entry=11942;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The pieces you\'ve collected begin to glow brightly in Raelorasz\' hands.>$B$BIt is done.$B$BI sense a strong presence within this prison. Let us hope it proves to be an ally.' WHERE entry=11943;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That should buy us some time, $N.  We\'ll hope against hope for reinforcements from Valiance Keep.' WHERE entry=11944;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I thank you, $N.  These supplies will feed our cousins and children.  Even if Kaskala falls, our tribes must carry on.' WHERE entry=11945;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Keristrasza wants you to speak to her when you are ready to prepare for a confrontation with Malygos.$B$BIf you lose your Augmented Arcane Prison, speak to Raelorasz at the Transitus Shield.',offerrewardtext_loc4='We cannot wait for me to regain my strength.$B$BI must rely on you to make our preparations....' WHERE entry=11946;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We must act to preserve the balance! Time is against us.$B$BThere is a camp located in the shadow of Ethel Rethor within northwestern Desolace. There, they use ice stones to communicate with the elementals, as they do in Silithus. Much as I am loath to do this, the spirits will understand - you must summon one of this Ahune\'s lieutenants and destroy it. Perhaps this forestalling action will be enough...',objectives_loc4='Slay the Hailstone Lieutenant summoned from the Ice Stone located at Ethel Rethor in Desolace, then return to the Earthen Ring Elder in a capital city.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well. It may seem a small act, but even this can aid the fight as a whole. Take this with my blessing, and return later, as I may have more for you to do.' WHERE entry=11947;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We must act to preserve the balance! Time is against us.$B$BNeptulon has long had a base of operations on an island in western Stranglethorn. There, the Twilight Cult has set up ice stones to communicate with the Tidehunter\'s realm, much like they do in Silithus. Much as I am loath to do this, the spirits will understand - you must summon one of this Ahune\'s lieutenants and destroy it. Perhaps this forestalling action will be enough...',objectives_loc4='Slay the Chillwind Lieutenant summoned from the Ice Stone located on the water elemental\'s island in western Stranglethorn Vale, then return to the Earthen Ring Elder in a capital city.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well. It may seem a small act, but even this can aid the fight as a whole. Take this with my blessing, and return later, as I may have more for you to do.' WHERE entry=11948;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I thank you, $N.  I will be deeply in your debt if we ever make it out of here alive.' WHERE entry=11949;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ataika sent you, didn\'t he?  I am not to be swayed.$B$BAll is not lost.  The spirits are still with us.' WHERE entry=11950;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $N.$B$BI am drained from the effects of my confinement and my strength is returning ever so slowly.$B$BI shall use the power from these crystals wisely. They are a byproduct of Malygos\' malevolent schemes. With luck, they will play a part in his undoing.' WHERE entry=11951;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We must act to preserve the balance! Time is against us.$B$BFirewatch Ridge in Searing Gorge is an established bastion of Twilight Cult activity. Recently, they have been using ice stones in the cave to communicate with the Tidehunter\'s realm, much like they do in Silithus. Much as I am loath to do this, the spirits will understand - you must summon one of this Ahune\'s lieutenants and destroy it. Perhaps this forestalling action will be enough...',objectives_loc4='Slay the Frigid Lieutenant summoned from the Ice Stone located in the cave underneath Firewatch Ridge in the northwest of Searing Gorge, then return to the Earthen Ring Elder in a capital city.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well. It may seem a small act, but even this can aid the fight as a whole. Take this with my blessing, and return later, as I may have more for you to do.' WHERE entry=11952;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We must act to preserve the balance! Time is against us.$B$BSilithus is the Azerothian base of the Twilight Cult. In the north, they have been using new ice stones to communicate with the Tidehunter\'s realm. Much as I am loath to do this, the spirits will understand - you must summon one of this Ahune\'s lieutenants and destroy it. Perhaps this forestalling action will be enough...',objectives_loc4='Slay the Glacial Lieutenant summoned from the Ice Stone located at Twilight\'s Run in northern Silithus, then return to the Earthen Ring Elder in a capital city.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well. It may seem a small act, but even this can aid the fight as a whole. Take this with my blessing, and return later, as I may have more for you to do.' WHERE entry=11953;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well. It may seem a small act, but even this can aid the fight as a whole. Take this with my blessing, and return later, as I may have more for you to do.' WHERE entry=11954;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Just in time, $N.  Pinning down a lich is not as easy as it looks.' WHERE entry=11956;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Using the mana crystals you provided, I have created this Power Focus.$B$BSaragosa is a glutton. She will be unable to resist its lure. Inside it lie magics that will greatly diminish her power. Let us hope she does not see through my ruse....$B$BPrepare yourself, $N, and speak to me again when you are ready to face Saragosa.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='This world is a better place now that Saragosa is no more, but our work is not yet finished.$B$BThe time has come to strike at Malygos himself!' WHERE entry=11957;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I will not say that I am pleased to ask you to do such things on our behalf. It is all we can do to prepare quickly for our departure, though we know not yet where we go.$B$BMy sorcerers tell me that you are here to save the land from He Who Walks in Shadow.$B$BI trust that you will save the peoples of the land as well.' WHERE entry=11958;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Loguhn\'s honorable sacrifice at your hands is exactly what my people need. Now we will make the most of the wolvar in-fighting for his place.$B$BIt will have to be enough.' WHERE entry=11959;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, I guess you saved plenty of them. Thank you, $R.$B$BNow the wolvar will have a chance of surviving along with us. If we survive at all, that is.$B$BDo you think that you could return tomorrow so that we can save more of the pups?' WHERE entry=11960;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Can you feel Issliruk\'s presence, $N?  He does not want his children to perish at the hand of the mist-walkers.' WHERE entry=11961;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ore from Farshire?  We weren\'t scheduled for a shipment just yet.  Is something wrong?' WHERE entry=11962;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hilda\'s sending us weapons?  That\'s excellent news, $N.  I was about ready to tell the lads to pack things up.' WHERE entry=11963;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thanks once again for aiding us, $N.  The people of Farshire will always remember you.' WHERE entry=11965;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, and what is this?  Such a delightful aroma!  I am sure it will burn with a flame pure and bright!$B$BTake this blossom, $N.  Take it, and leave me be... I must attend to this precious fuel...' WHERE entry=11966;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Word of Keristrasza\'s rescue has reached my ears. You are to be commended.$B$BI am eager to speak with her again.' WHERE entry=11967;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done us a great favor, $R.  The fight is not yet won, but my people now have a chance.' WHERE entry=11968;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We have dealt a blow to Malygos, but it has come at a high price.' WHERE entry=11969;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'ll be happy to tell you what I know.' WHERE entry=11971;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Malygos has taken Keristrasza to serve as his consort!? Unthinkable!$B$BShe\'ll never cooperate willingly, but Malygos is a powerful aspect, and will eventually bend her will.$B$BThis cannot come to pass, $N. I refuse to allow her to suffer this indignity.$B$BYou must enter the Nexus and do whatever is required to spare her this fate.',objectives_loc4='Raelorasz at the Transitus Shield wants you to enter the Nexus and release Keristrasza.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So, it is done then....$B$BOur kind shall never forget the sacrifice Keristrasza has made for this cause. Nor shall we forget the part you have played, $N.$B$BMay this tragic event serve to further steel our resolve against the threat we face.$B$BOn behalf of the Red Dragonflight, please accept this gift as a token of our gratitude.' WHERE entry=11973;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Now, When I Grow Up...',details_loc4='Maybe I already asked you this, but when you were my age did you know that you wanted to be a $C when you grew up?$B$BI\'m not sure what I want to be.  Maybe a mage or a warlock or a Blood Knight, like I said before?  Or maybe... A rock star!!  Like Sig Nicious, the blood elf, in the Elite Tauren Chieftain!$B$BI heard that when they aren\'t touring, they hang out in Silvermoon City!  They just sit on a balcony in the Walk of Elders waiting for people to stop by.$B$BPlease take me there.  Please!' WHERE entry=11975;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What you see here is all that remains of the taunka from the Borean Tundra and the Dragonblight. They are a broken people... battered and brought to the brink of extinction by the Scourge.$B$B<Brighthoof shakes her head.>$B$BOnly the Horde can save them now. Only the Horde can mend their broken spirits. We will nurse them back to full health and they will in turn strengthen the Horde in Northrend.' WHERE entry=11977;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This is exactly what we need, $N! Brandishing Horde arms will lift their spirits and give them the protection they need against the Scourge.$B$BAre you prepared for the ceremony of initiation?$B$B<Brighthoof nods.>$B$BYou will be the one to admit our new allies into the Horde.' WHERE entry=11978;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What you see here is all that remains of the taunka from the Borean Tundra and the Dragonblight. They are a broken people... battered and brought to the brink of extinction.$B$B<Brighthoof shakes her head.>$B$BOnly the Horde can save them now. Only the Horde can mend their broken spirits. We will nurse them back to full health and they will in turn strengthen the Horde in Northrend.
' WHERE entry=11979;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Blood Guard Roh\'kill at the Westwind Refugee Camp in the Dragonblight wants you to slay 15 Anub\'ar Ambushers.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Roh\'kill salutes you.>$B$BYou have preserved our honor, $N. Tor\'zin and I both thank you for this selfless act!' WHERE entry=11980;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<You tell Kurun about the message given to you by the fallen Earthen.>$B$BThey fight bravely, but he is right. We will not overcome the iron dwarves of Thor Modan without help. My giants and the Earthen have long struggled against iron\'s evil, but our forces are not numerous enough to win the battle for Thor Modan. Will you aid us?' WHERE entry=11981;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='As quickly as we\'re able to fill the trench, the iron dwarves keep clearing it. Our assault from above will not take the city alone. You must aid the earthen fighting in the plaza below.' WHERE entry=11982;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you for doing this, Commander $N. They had nothing left. You have given them purpose and with purpose comes hope... Hope for a new tomorrow... for a new life.' WHERE entry=11983;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Great work, $C. Looks like we\'ll be keepin\' Budd around a little longer.$B$BWe\'ll have your cage picked up right away. Here\'s your share of the bounty.$B$BOh, and welcome to the camp. Stick around and I\'m sure we\'ll find a use for ya....' WHERE entry=11984;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. The loss of the iron dwarf commander should be enough to break the remaining defenders. The Earthen should be able to deal with the survivors.' WHERE entry=11985;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You found Brann\'s journal? Incredible! The league hasn\'t gotten a report from him in some time, and we began to fear he may have been captured or killed. What did he discover inside Thor Modan?' WHERE entry=11986;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Torthen works quickly to assemble the fragments you retrieved.>$B$BThis is incomplete, but it should still allow us to get most of the information from the plate.' WHERE entry=11988;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='There!$B$BNow we be connected by blood, mon. A true bond we be havin\'.$B$BYou lissen carefully to Drakuru, $R. There be much to do.' WHERE entry=11989;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Drakuru at Granite Springs wants you to bring him an Imbued Vial, a Waterweed Frond, and 3 Haze Leaves.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Drakuru takes the ingredients and deftly combines them in the vial.>$B$BThis should do it, mon. Now it be time to get to work.' WHERE entry=11990;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='A legendary set of artifacts, lost for thousands of years, were created to make Drak\'Tharon Keep impervious.$B$BMost think they be myth, but Drakuru knows better, mon!$B$BI nearly discovered where one be, but got captured while interpreting hieroglyphs. Ya gotta summon my soul back dere so I can finish readin\' em!$B$BUse my elixir at da brazier on Drak\'Zin Ruins, southwest of here. You\'ll hafta mix in da frozen mojo my bruddas be holdin\'. I hate ta see my bruddas fall, but it be for the greater good.$B',objectives_loc4='Drakuru wants you to get 5 Frozen Mojo from the Drakkari Trolls at the Ruins of Drak\'Zin and then use the elixir at Drakuru\'s Brazier there.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ahh, yes. Ya done good, mon.$B$BI be readin\' the walls just fine from here....' WHERE entry=11991;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Torthen listens as you recount the contents of the runic plates.>$B$BBy Madoran\'s hammer, he\'s discovered a whole new titan city!$B$B\'The cradle of stone and iron.\'$B$B\'Ulduar nestled in the storm.\'$B$BWhat d\'you suppose that means? Could it be where we come from, after all these years?$B$BWe have to follow him! We have to find him!' WHERE entry=11993;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'ve been expecting you, $C. We have much work to do, you and I.' WHERE entry=11995;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What took you so long? Time waits only for Aspects, $R.$B$BWe have much work to do, you and I.' WHERE entry=11996;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The Westfall Brigade has been dispatched to the northeastern part of Grizzly Hills to secure passage for our troops. They have established a base camp to the northeast of Grizzlemaw, and to the southwest of Thor Modan.$B$BYou might recognize the brigade\'s leader, Captain Gryan Stoutmantle as an honored veteran of the war against the Scourge in Lordaeron. But the people of Westfall know him best for his decision to leave the battlefield and return home to take on the Defias.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Captain Gryan Stoutmantle at the Westfall Brigade Encampment.' WHERE entry=11997;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Let me get this straight -- a $R I don\'t know brings me a cask of the finest booze in this miserable forest. Ok, then, what are you after?' WHERE entry=11998;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Curious, they seek an accord with the Ethereum. The ethereals could prove a powerful ally for Malygos and his madness.$B$BThis will not do!' WHERE entry=11999;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Curious, they seek an accord with the Ethereum. The ethereals could prove a powerful ally for Malygos and his madness.$B$BThis will not do!' WHERE entry=12000;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Brugar listens to your report.>$B$BIt sounds like things may be calming down there a bit. We\'ll start looking for entrances to the iron dwarves\' tunnel system.' WHERE entry=12002;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Brugar utters a stream of foul dwarven words.>$B$BNo entrances? None?$B$BNo, of course it couldn\'t be that easy. Well, I suppose there\'s no avoiding a foray into the city proper. My boys\'ll never get back to their real work.' WHERE entry=12003;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Unfortunate that Goramosh indicated the accord had already been reached.$B$BNonetheless, that\'s two less worms we\'ll have to worry about. Let us get to more important business.' WHERE entry=12004;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'s alright, $C, just put them down on the ground there in front of Agmar\'s throne.$B$B<You can practically sense the smile hidden behind the archmage\'s helm.>$B$BUnfortunate that Goramosh indicated the accord had already been reached.$B$BNonetheless, that\'s two less worms we\'ll have to worry about. Let us get on to more important business.' WHERE entry=12005;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Very well, you have satisfied my request if nothing more.$B$BThank you, $R.' WHERE entry=12006;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Dis be it, mon!$B$BIt be even more precious than I hoped. Dis be sure to bring mah people hope in dese dark times.$B$BNo time to waste, now. Let\'s be seein\' where da next artifact be hidin\'.' WHERE entry=12007;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Directly east of this refugee camp stands Agmar\'s Hammer - testament to the Hordes\' power in the Dragonblight.$B$BWhile I have no doubt that our Horde brothers and sisters are already seeing the result of your efforts to bring the taunka into the Horde, I want you to deliver news of your success to Overlord Agmar in person.$B$BGo now, $N! Race the winds! East to Agmar\'s Hammer!$B',objectives_loc4='Travel to Agmar\'s Hammer in the Dragonblight and speak to Overlord Agmar.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='While you have undoubtedly championed the cause of the Horde elsewhere, many more have been working towards expanding our grasp deeper into Northrend. Even now we have forces establishing bases in the frozen reaches of this desolate wasteland.$B$BWe surround the Scourge on all sides. Victory nears as our armies amass at the foot of the Wrathgate, Angrathar. Soon we will tear down the gate and breach Icecrown.$B$BBut there is much work left to be done...$B$BFirst we stop the Nerubians!' WHERE entry=12008;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m a simple trapper. The world has turned upside-down all of a sudden. It doesn\'t make sense.$B$BI hope that you\'ll be able to set it right again.' WHERE entry=12009;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A quick examination of the body reveals that the surveyor has been dead for some time. Looking through his pack, you stumble upon Orlond\'s handwritten notes.' WHERE entry=12010;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'s not the news I wanted to hear, $R.$B$BNo, no... it\'s good that you told me, but I fear my old nemesis has returned to these waters.' WHERE entry=12011;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Travel to a capital city and return the Totemic Beacon to the Earthen Ring Elder.' WHERE entry=12012;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have my deepest gratitude, $N.$B$BIf you haven\'t already, you should alert your betters to the danger that the blue dragonflight has unleashed. By blowing apart the ley line anchor underneath the gardens, they threaten to destroy us all!' WHERE entry=12013;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Brugar looks over the report.>$B$BThis isn\'t good at all. Even if we could excavate the tunnels behind the blockage, there\'s no guarantee they wouldn\'t collapse again. It looks like some of these areas haven\'t been used in generations. We\'ll have to give Captain Gryan the bad news.' WHERE entry=12014;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You were able to slay Kili\'ua... perhaps you\'ll be able to do the same to Tu\'u\'gwar.$B$BPerhaps not.' WHERE entry=12016;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We shall rejoice at your success, my young friend! There\'s blood in the water and it is our enemy\'s!$B$BYou have the eternal gratitude of this old fisherman, and most certainly of all the Kalu\'ak once I spread the word!$B$BHere now, I insist, take something as a reward, please.' WHERE entry=12017;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Sweet Revenge',objectives_loc4='Obtain 2 Stone Hunks O\' Gargoyle from Carrion Gargoyles in the Eastern Carrion Fields.  Return to Lord Bevis when the task is complete.' WHERE entry=12018;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You did well, $N.  I was hoping to leave my sister out of all this.  Thanks to you she is alive and well.$B$BMy obligations to my king and my army have been fulfilled.  It is clear I\'m not welcome among my comrades anymore.  I will have to find my own way, fighting no wars but my own and following no orders but my heart\'s.$B$BPerhaps we shall meet again, $C.  Until then, take this as a token of my gratitude.' WHERE entry=12019;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc4='Hail, $N.' WHERE entry=12019;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So you managed to stop the Dark Irons... While drunk too? That, $C, is truly the spirit of Brewfest! I guess in keeping with the spirit of Brewfest you want your prize tokens.$B$BThanks for your help, $N. Enjoy the rest of Brewfest.' WHERE entry=12020;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='This letter appears to be addressed to a resident of Stormwind from one of the late Villagers in the Carrion Fields.  Perhaps one of the surviving residents in the Eastern camp would be interested in forwarding it to its intended recipient.',objectives_loc4='Bring the letter home to Lady Alustra in the Eastern Carrion Fields.' WHERE entry=12021;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Hey there!  You look like you can handle your brew.  But can you handle your brew mug? $B$BThe Dark Irons have come back with a vengeance to ruin our celebration.  Tossing mugs at them is the best way to stop them, but first, let\'s see if you can toss one at old S.T.O.U.T. here.$B$BIt\'s easy, pick up a complimentary sampler and take a drink.  Just make sure you\'re facing S.T.O.U.T.  Talk to me after you\'ve hit him 5 times.',objectives_loc4='Use the Complimentary Brewfest Sampler to hit S.T.O.U.T. 5 times, then talk to Boxey Boltspinner.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Do you know what that was? Gnomish engineering at its finest! S.T.O.U.T. took the abuse like a champ!$B$BI think you\'re ready now to take on the Dark Irons if they show up again.' WHERE entry=12022;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='A Scarlet Among Us' WHERE entry=12025;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='This battered, mud-stained journal has seen better days. Leafing through the pages, you discover dozens of notes, diagrams, and maps in the dwarven language.$B$BThe only text you\'re able to decipher is the name of Brann Bronzebeard scrawled at the end of one of the entries.$B$BThe back half of the book, containing the most recent entries, has been torn away. Someone thought the notes important enough to attempt to destroy them. Perhaps gathering the missing pages from the battlefield will yield some clues.',objectives_loc4='Recover 8 Missing Journal Pages, combine them with the Incomplete Journal, and return the completed journal to Sage Paluna at Camp Oneqwah.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Who is this Brann Bronzebeard? The iron dwarves found no reason to treat with him, but I have no idea why we\'d be interested in his writings.' WHERE entry=12026;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank goodness you found Emmy! When she left without me, I was worried she\'d get lost.$B$BI\'m glad to see Mr. Floppy\'s back safe and sound, too.' WHERE entry=12027;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='$R, we have not heard from our people at Indu\'le Village since the ground shook and was torn apart!$B$BHave you ever been upon a vision quest? You\'ve bested Loguhn, so you must be capable.$B$BI will give you a special incense to sprinkle into my brazier. Breathe deep from its vapors and your spirit will be sent aloft to view what has transpired at Indu\'le.$B$BAs your spirit soars, I will be able to look through your eyes.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ghosts and gibbering madness? This cannot be!$B$BWe must seek further guidance.' WHERE entry=12028;
UPDATE locales_quest SET EndText_loc4='Spiritual insight concerning Indu\'le Village attained.' WHERE entry=12028;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done!$B$B<Mack laughs hysterically for a moment.>$B$BAww, come on now. That was funny...<hic>.' WHERE entry=12029;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'ve been expecting you, $R. I saw your spirit fly by and sensed the mystic watching behind your eyes.$B$BYour fate and that of the Kalu\'ak are now tied together.' WHERE entry=12030;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Not the most pleasant task, but necessary and merciful.$B$BAnd now there is something else that you are destined to do for the Kalu\'ak.' WHERE entry=12031;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You spoke with Oacha\'noa?!$B$BIf it is her will that we stand with your people then so be it. Elder Ko\'nani will accept this as our destiny, for weal or woe.$B$BMy people believe that all souls are one with the magic of the world. We must oppose the blue dragon attempts to controI the magic or we are all doomed!$B$BI never thought that a $R would be the champion of the Kalu\'ak, but you have proven me wrong. On behalf of my people, I give you thanks, $N.$B$BMay the gods smile upon you and keep you safe.' WHERE entry=12032;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Torvus nods at you.>$B$BSo we are understood? I will return to my lord and tell him that you have accepted.' WHERE entry=12033;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='By land and by air, that\'s how we will end the Anub\'ar threat.' WHERE entry=12034;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Nice job!  I finally feel useful again... and that\'s sayin\' something.' WHERE entry=12035;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The undead Nerubians that attacked Icemist Village came from a gigantic sinkhole known as the Pit of Narjun. If left alone, those fiends will no doubt flank our forces at the Wrathgate and end our march to victory.$B$BI need eyes on the ground, $N. You are to head west and investigate the Pit of Narjun. We need to locate their primary exit point and seal it off! Find me that location.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='That damned sinkhole must be directly connected to Azjol-Nerub. This is worse than I thought.$B$B<Juktok pauses to think for a moment.>$B$BSeek and destroy... That\'ll be the next course of action.' WHERE entry=12036;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I knew it!$B$BEven my going missing wasn\'t enough to get those spineless weasels to come in here after me.$B$BWell, they sent you. I suppose that\'s something....$B$BHere, take this. I\'d rather it go to you than to those dimwits back at the camp.' WHERE entry=12037;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Whatcha waitin\' fer, $C? Them shcourged trolls ain\'t gunna kill themselves!$B$BYou know the drill. Git up ta Drak\'Tharon up north... Take some o thish here grog and hurl it at \'em from a distance...<hic>.  Then jusht sit back an\' watch \'em burn.',objectives_loc4='Mack at Granite Springs wants you to use his grog to burn 30 Famished Scourge Trolls.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done!$B$B<Mack laughs hysterically for a moment.>$B$BAww, come on now. That was funny...hic.' WHERE entry=12038;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s so light... As if it weighs nothing at all! I\'ll need time to analyze the metal and see if I can do anything with it! Tests! I need to run tests!$B$BI\'ll keep in contact, $N. If anything comes of this, you\'ll be the first to know.' WHERE entry=12039;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Kilix the Unraveler at the Pit of Narjun in the Dragonblight has asked that you slay 6 Anub\'ar Underlords.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='There are thousands more and they spill out from every dark crevice in Northrend. Alone you stand no chance, but together... Maybe...' WHERE entry=12040;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You have proven that you are willing to assist the Azjol Empire in its time of need and as such the Azjol Empire will assist the Horde.$B$BTake this scroll back to your leader. It documents the strengths and weaknesses of the Nerubians attacking Icemist Village. Consider it a gesture of good faith - a willingness to help your people. Use the knowledge on those pages to crush the Anub\'ar and you will have done a service for us all.$B$BFarewell, $R.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Overlord Agmar looks over the document.>$B$BIs this what I think it is? With the information contained within these pages we will CRUSH the Anub\'ar assault!$B$BYou have done well to bring this document to me, $N. Perhaps you will be allowed to watch or even participate in the final battle at Angrathar! LOK\'TAR!' WHERE entry=12041;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This unfortunate goblin must have unearthed the Heart of the Ancients during his excavations in the region.$B$BIt\'s doubtless that he had no clue as to its nature.$B$BYou determine that it must have been overlooked in the chaos sweeping through the area.' WHERE entry=12042;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh!  Yeah, the undead.  Here\'s your coin, bugger off.' WHERE entry=12043;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Hello hello!  The Scourge to the south are digging up some ancient dragon thing.  I could care less why they\'re doing it, but they\'re pulling cartloads of composite ore in the process.$B$BGo lift me a bunch of that ore.  That stuff should yield a pretty penny for all the weapons the Horde are crafting.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Hah!  That\'s quite a load!  Your back feeling alright?' WHERE entry=12044;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I\'ve never seen you before... are you new to the Vice?  Glad to have you.  I could always use some more hands.$B$BYou get the materials, I\'ll finish my machine, then we can sell it to those commander types and all go home rich.$B$BI actually have most of the primary components, so I just need some of the materials for the weapon itself.  Narf said that jagged ice shards from those elementals to the north would make perfect shrapnel for my bombs - go nab some, will ya?$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent!  They\'re even sharper than I expected them to be.  I\'ll pack them in the snow until the bomb is ready.$B$BLet\'s see... what next...
' WHERE entry=12045;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I need some new packaging for the shrapnel bombs.  All the stuff I have is too hard and the shrapnel doesn\'t spread when it bursts.  $B$BWhat we need is some really thin animal hide.  Those jormungar tunnelers to the west might work... or perhaps the condors sifting through the dragon bones.  Go get me whatever you can find.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Good... good... these should do fine.  The shrapnel bombs are almost finished. $B$BWait... what happened to my ice shards?  Narf told me shards from those elementals should be enchanted, but they\'re melting just like the one\'s hanging from Narf\'s grumpy chin!' WHERE entry=12046;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent!  That should be the last thing I need to test out the new bombs.  Just a moment and I\'ll try this out!' WHERE entry=12047;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These are in excellent condition, $N. I\'ll get to work right away. If anything comes of this, you will be the first to know!' WHERE entry=12048;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ha ha!  One of those meat slabs landed clear over here!  Nice work there!
' WHERE entry=12049;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Next up, we need to haul in some lumber for all the towers the Alliance are building.  There are some thin trees to the south, but the trees the Harpies are nesting in to the north look much more fit for structures.$B$BTake this.  When you get to the Harpy nesting area, use the control and one of my Shredders should come to you.  Gather as much lumber as it can carry.  The Harpies are sure to disagree with you chopping down their homes - just deal with them as necessary.$B$BHop to it!',offerrewardtext_loc4='If a tree falls in the forest, and you can\'t hear it through the saw blade, does it really make a sound?' WHERE entry=12050;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That should make those uglies think twice.  Here... take your reward and get away with ya.' WHERE entry=12052;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We have crushed them by land! Soon we will crush them by air!' WHERE entry=12053;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='$N, if I\'m not mistaken, you\'ve uncovered the key to allow us to discern exactly what the mage hunter forces are up to!' WHERE entry=12055;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I witnessed his treachery with my own eyes! The traitor led an Anub\'ar assault on this stronghold, taking out some of my best soldiers.$B$B<Gort shakes his head.>$B$BHe\'d been working with the Scourge the whole time and we didn\'t have a clue! How many more like Zangus are there? We\'ll find \'em all and when we do...$B$B<Gort makes a cutting motion across his neck.>$B$BFirst on the list is Zangus. Our scouts report that he is hiding in The Pit of Narjun, west of here. Find him, kill him, bring me his head.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Gort holds the head up and stares into its dead eyes.>$B$BI told you we\'d get you...$B$BHere\'s your reward, $C. That\'s one less headache for us to worry about.' WHERE entry=12056;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Gort takes the tome from you.>$B$BSavages... Bound in $R flesh... This language... Its existence has never been proven. It is the language of death... The tongue of the Scourge.' WHERE entry=12057;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Brann\'s journal also contained a guide to iron dwarf symbols. I\'ve inscribed these on a keystone which will help you to understand the words inscribed on the rune plates.$B$BFrom the journal entries, it seems Brann may be chasing after clues to the origins of his people. Keep your eyes open for any clues as to his destination.$B$BReturn to Thor Modan, northeast of here, stand before each of the plates, and use the stone to determine the contents of each. We can\'t allow the Alliance to find him first.',objectives_loc4='Sage Paluna at Camp Oneqwah wants you to decipher the three Rune Plates.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Sage Paluna listens as you recall the translations of the plates.>$B$BSo Brann thinks he\'s discovered a new titan city?$B$B\'The cradle of stone and iron.\'$B$B\'Ulduar nestled in the storm.\'$B$BI will ask the chieftain to dispatch longrunners to the Storm Peaks. My people know these lands well and have the best chance of tracking down this wayward dwarf.' WHERE entry=12058;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='$N, if I\'m not mistaken, you\'ve uncovered the key to allow us to discern exactly what the mage hunter forces are up to!' WHERE entry=12059;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What you\'re describing... that\'s a projection of the Arcanomicon!$B$B<The archmage\'s show of concern is quickly masked behind an impassive countenance.>$B$BThe Arcanomicon is a map of all of the magical ley line intersections in the world. The blue dragonflight has been using it to find and destroy ley line \'anchors\' to send the magical power back to the Nexus.$B$BThe question is, why is the path of destruction leading east when it should be heading west instead?' WHERE entry=12060;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Object on the Surge Needle observed' WHERE entry=12060;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What you\'re describing... that\'s a projection of the Arcanomicon!$B$B<The archmage\'s show of concern is quickly masked behind an impassive countenance.>$B$BThe Arcanomicon is a map of all of the magical ley line intersections in the world. The blue dragonflight has been using it to find and destroy ley line \'anchors\' to send the magical power back to the Nexus.$B$BThe question is, why is the path of destruction leading east when it should be heading west instead?' WHERE entry=12061;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Object on the Surge Needle observed' WHERE entry=12061;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What? What did you say? How dare you! My beer can stand up to any of that rot they serve at Brewfest!$B$BYou\'ll pay for this insult, $C!' WHERE entry=12062;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='My father still lives! We must save him! I cannot do it alone, $R. You must help me!' WHERE entry=12063;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Banthok Icemist at Icemist Village in the Dragonblight has asked that you bring him Anok\'ra\'s Key Fragment, Tivax\'s Key Fragment and Sinok\'s Key Fragment.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes, this will work.$B$B<Banthok expertly manipulates the key fragments.>$B$BHere it is, $C. With this key, my father will be freed of the Anub\'ar prison.' WHERE entry=12064;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='How very odd that it imprinted this information upon you magically.$B$BSo, not only do we know that they\'ve redirected the flow of the power coming out of the Moonrest Gardens, but we now know that the power is being purposefully changed in some way. Just what are they up to with all of that magic?$B$BI don\'t like where this is leading, $N, not one bit!' WHERE entry=12065;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='How very odd that it imprinted this information upon you magically.$B$BSo, not only do we know that they\'ve redirected the flow of the power coming out of the Moonrest Gardens, but we now know that the power is being purposefully changed in some way. Just what are they up to with all of that magic?$B$BI don\'t like where this is leading, $N.' WHERE entry=12066;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh no... and we sent you down there to kill her, didn\'t we?$B$B<The commander shakes her head and sighs.>$B$BI\'m sorry. I\'ll see to it that the letter is delivered to her father, Archmage Malin in Stormwind, right away. Don\'t worry, you won\'t be implicated... it wasn\'t your fault.$B$BTry to put it out of your mind. There was no way that you could have known, $N.' WHERE entry=12067;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We\'ve done it, $N!$B$BWe have all of the components we need to perform the cleansing ritual.' WHERE entry=12068;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are a brave $C, $N. You\'ve done the Horde a great service by rescuing the High Chief.' WHERE entry=12069;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have given our allies the strength to fight on, and for that you have my thanks. Even so, we must begin planning a way to end this battle before we are overrun.' WHERE entry=12070;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='They have seen the might of the Horde by land, now they must feel it from the air! I want you to report to Valnok Windrager at once! You will find him here, in Agmar\'s Hammer.$B$BValnok has already been briefed on your mission and is expecting you.$B',objectives_loc4='Speak with Valnok Windrager at Agmar\'s Hammer.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Valnok salutes.>$B$BSo you\'re the hot shot, eh?' WHERE entry=12071;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Valnok salutes.>$B$BAnd now they have been crushed by air! Perhaps soon you will be called to Angrathar, hero!' WHERE entry=12072;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<You introduce yourself to Kurun.>$B$BSo the sons of iron are your enemies as well?$B$BMy forces have the iron dwarves pinned inside their city, but we could use help in pressing the attack. Will you aid us?' WHERE entry=12074;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This is perfect.  Thank you, $C.' WHERE entry=12075;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Still fresh.  Just a moment and I will mix this with the rest of the elixir that I have prepared.' WHERE entry=12076;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I will be blunt little one - I do not trust this mixture, and I will not use it. Keep it... if you find more trust in the green runt than I do, perhaps it will be of use to you.' WHERE entry=12077;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These will do nicely. Perhaps after I grow these beasts to full size, I will bring them back and introduce them to the giants personally.$B$BBunch of useless rocks if you ask me.' WHERE entry=12078;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A satisfying display of slaughter.' WHERE entry=12079;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The jormungar have a spawnmother in the caverns below. We call her Rattlebore - a name that was gifted to her by an adventurer from the Plaguelands. I saw her only briefly as I was fighting off their initial onslaught - she is large enough to make even my icy bones shiver. This cavern will not be ours until she is removed from it.$B$BGather your friends and end this.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So she is dead. As it should be. Your intentions do indeed prove nobler than those of the runt.$B$BThrough the north canyon you will find Crystal Song Woods.  It is a cursed and dangerous place, $R. Should that be your next destination, proceed with caution. $B$BTake this for your efforts, little one, and leave this conflicted land with my blessing.' WHERE entry=12080;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I know Kurun is glad for your help. The defeat of Thor Modan will be a great achievement for us, but it will not free our brothers.' WHERE entry=12081;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So, yah survived a little adventure with our good friend, did yah?$B$BThat should be reward enough in itself, but here - I\'m feelin\' generous.' WHERE entry=12082;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='They\'re empowering their forces with it? That doesn\'t make any sense; the mage hunters aren\'t that powerful.$B$BThis must mean that they\'re only using the magic at the terminus of wherever they\'ve redirected the ley line to.$B$BWe\'re going to need more information if we\'re to have a chance at finding and stopping them!' WHERE entry=12083;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='They\'re empowering their forces with it? That doesn\'t make any sense at all; the mage hunters aren\'t that powerful!$B$BThis must mean that they\'re only using the magic at the terminus of wherever they\'ve redirected the ley line to.$B$BWe\'re going to need more information if I\'m to devise a plan to stop them!' WHERE entry=12084;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ahahahaha... boo hoo, how touching.$B$B<The condescension in the overlord\'s deep-throated laughter is palpable.>$B$BWhat did I say? Traitors! Still, I knew Deino once upon a time. She at least is a troll with honor!$B$BI\'ll see to it that she finds out what happened to her brother. I\'ll even forget to tell her that you\'re the one that killed him.$B$B<Agmar fixes you with a calculated stare.>$B$BBut I own you now, $C!' WHERE entry=12085;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thassarian?  Yeah he was here... what of it?  We have more pressing problems right now, my friend.' WHERE entry=12086;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Leryssa... is looking for me?  You must help me, $N.  We must finish this before she gets hurt.' WHERE entry=12088;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='By decree of Overlord Agmar:$B$BTarget: Magister Keldonus$B$BCrime: Treason$B$BStatus: Alive$B$BMagister Keldonus, once mage commander of Agmar\'s Hammer, is to be killed on sight in the name of the Horde.$B$BKeldonus was last seen traveling southwest towards Moonrest Gardens to join the Blue Dragonflight in their campaign against magic.$B$BApproach with caution as Keldonus is a powerful magus. Do not engage solo!$B$BAll bounties are paid out by Captain Gort at Agmar\'s Hammer.',offerrewardtext_loc4='He wasn\'t the first of those sissy spell casters to betray us, and he certainly won\'t be the last. Damned shame, too... He was one of our best mages. He\'d summon a buffet that would make your mouth water and your heart jump for joy...$B$BBAH!' WHERE entry=12089;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='By decree of Overlord Agmar:$B$BTarget: Gigantaur$B$BCrime: Attacks upon the Horde; "Bein\' ugly"$B$BStatus: Alive$B$BThe magnataur lord, Gigantaur, is wanted in relation to a number of attacks against Horde soldiers and installations in the Dragonblight.$B$BGigantaur was last seen wandering the woods and roads south by southeast of Agmar\'s Hammer.$B$BGigantaur should be considered armed and extremely dangerous. Do not engage solo!$B$BAll bounties are paid out by Captain Gort at Agmar\'s Hammer.',objectives_loc4='Slay Gigantaur and return to Captain Gort at Agmar\'s Hammer in the Dragonblight.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='You got that ugly son-of-a-horse, eh? Well that\'s one less nuisance our soldiers will have to deal with out in the frozen wastes.' WHERE entry=12090;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='By decree of Overlord Agmar:$B$BTarget: Dreadtalon$B$BCrime: Attacks upon the Horde$B$BStatus: Alive$B$BDreadtalon is wanted for numerous attacks upon Horde caravans traveling to and from Venomspite.$B$BDreadtalon makes his home on a bluff overlooking the Ruby Dragonshrine, east of Agmar\'s Hammer. He should be approached with extreme caution. Do not engage solo!$B$BAll bounties are paid out by Captain Gort at Agmar\'s Hammer.',offerrewardtext_loc4='About time someone put a stop to that filthy beast\'s killing spree! A job well done, $N.' WHERE entry=12091;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $R! We\'ve lost so much already. You\'ve ensured that we won\'t lose the most majestic of Northrend\'s children.$B$BI\'ll soon leave to speak with the ancients you saved and see if they will help us in our time of need.' WHERE entry=12092;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good. Now, we must act swiftly, before the sons of iron realize that their runes have been rendered harmless.' WHERE entry=12093;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I can detect the power you\'ve imbued in the shard and I hope it will be enough to break the runic magic.' WHERE entry=12094;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What make you tink dat you succeed where Rokhan fail?' WHERE entry=12095;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have my thanks, $C.$B$BAs soon as I am done observing what these disgusting apothecaries are up to, I\'ll head to the woods and see if I can convince these ancients to side with us.$B$BOr, if nothing else, I\'ll convince them not to attack those that saved them!' WHERE entry=12096;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Me hunters be dead or frozen, $N. Just you and whatever allies you bring wit ya is all da help you get. You still want to do dis? Just say da word and me call for da dragon once more.$B$BIf ya kill it, take da beast\'s frozen heart back to Agmar\'s Hammer and present it to Gort. He sure to reward you good, mon.',offerrewardtext_loc4='HA! You did it! The soldiers at the Wrathgate are indebted to you, $N! This\'ll surely buy a few of them another day above ground.' WHERE entry=12097;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You find the corpse of the mage hunter commander here.$B$BJudging by his appearance, and the condition of the forces around him, you would guess that they didn\'t drown. Rather, when they summoned the focus in, they didn\'t expect the elementals that arose from the rents in the lake bed to attack.$B$BIt would appear that the mage hunter forces were the architects of their own demise.' WHERE entry=12098;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So it\'s an uncertain thing? I wish it was not a matter of chance, but at least we\'re on the right path. Without your help, this wouldn\'t have ever been possible. Should you learn any more about the machinations of the iron dwarves and their plans toward the children of stone, seek us out and we will hear you, $N.' WHERE entry=12099;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It pains me to put animals down, but it is a service that must be performed. Now we must move on to the next step: Inoculation.' WHERE entry=12100;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Deliver the Rot Resistant Organ to Doctor Sintar Malefious at Agmar\'s Hammer.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='The oafish man-cow actually acquired a rot resistant organ? Curses... I was certain that task would keep his malformed mind occupied well into the next millennium.$B$BWell give it here, $Gboy:girl;. I have much to do without your feeble needs getting in the way.' WHERE entry=12101;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That wasn\'t so difficult, now was it?$B$BNow give me a moment to prepare the vaccine.' WHERE entry=12102;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I\'ve heard enough, $N.  We must make sure whatever\'s happening at Silverbrook doesn\'t spread to the rest of the continent.$B$BI don\'t care if it\'s the water, the altitude or an ancient troll curse that\'s driven these villagers murderously insane... return to Silverbrook and put an end to them.',objectives_loc4='Captain Derrick at Amberpine Lodge wants you to slay 8 Silverbrook Villagers and 8 Silverbrook Trappers.' WHERE entry=12103;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Soar holds the vial up to the sky and examines its contents.>$B$BOnly one thing left to do now.' WHERE entry=12104;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I imagined there would be more to this than just an isolated town of hostiles.$B$BWe have men near Hollowstone Mine, perhaps it would be in our interest to do a little research.' WHERE entry=12105;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You find the corpse of the mage hunter commander here.$B$BJudging by his appearance, and the condition of the forces around him, you would guess that they didn\'t drown. Rather, when they summoned the focus in, they didn\'t expect the elementals that arose from the rents in the lake bed to attack.$B$BIt would appear that the mage hunter forces were the architects of their own demise.' WHERE entry=12106;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='WHAT?!$B$B<The image before you distorts for a moment as the archmage attempts to regain her composure.>$B$BOf course, we should have guessed that this was what they were up to all along. Quickly, there\'s no time to waste.$B$BWyrmrest must be warned!' WHERE entry=12107;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The dirt mound is, indeed, a hastily dug grave.  The body beneath is unrecognizable but you find a note that identifies that man as Mikhail.$B$BThe note mentions Hollowstone Mine once again.  Perhaps someone back at Amberpine Lodge might be familiar with the area.',objectives_loc4='Bring Mikhail\'s Note to Cartographer Tobias at Amberpine Lodge.' WHERE entry=12108;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Dumont sent you?  Very well.  Let\'s see what you can do for us.' WHERE entry=12109;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='WHAT?!$B$B<The image before you distorts for a moment as the archmage attempts to regain his composure.>$B$BOf course, we should have guessed that this was what they were up to all along. Quickly, there\'s no time to waste.$B$BWyrmrest must be warned!' WHERE entry=12110;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Inside this pack are several vials containing the vaccine that Sintar created. I now want you to search the nearby woods for Snowfall elk and arctic grizzlies. When you locate the animals, find a safe distance and throw a vial in their general direction. The vial will shatter and release a fine gas that will act as the inoculating agent. The beasts merely have to step inside the gas and they will be vaccinated - ultimately saved.$B$BInoculate as many of the beasts as you can and return to me.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done an honorable thing, $N. Please, choose a reward.' WHERE entry=12111;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I can think of some uses for you, go ahead and stay for a bit.' WHERE entry=12112;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Outstanding!$B$BNuthin\' better with a pint than a hot morsel of meat.' WHERE entry=12113;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thankyeh, $C.$B$BWhen time allows I\'ll git up and have meself a look around.' WHERE entry=12114;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='There is one who recently joined our cause that might be able to decipher this tome. An unbound death knight known as Koltira Deathweaver has temporarily taken residence here at Agmar\'s Hammer. As he was once a death knight of Arthas and member of the Scourge, he might be able to translate the language of the dead.$B$BTake the flesh-bound tome to Koltira and ask him to translate the pages.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='There are only two things in life that interest me, peon, and neither of them involve translating a Scourge tome for you.$B$BHowever... perhaps we could work something out that would benefit the both of us.$B$B<Koltira unsheathes his weapon.>$B$BThis is my runeblade, Byfrost. Byfrost thirsts for the blood of the Lich King and his minions, but first I must etch upon it runes of power: symbols of frost, blood, and shadow. Bring me suitable sources of power and I will translate your tome.' WHERE entry=12115;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Entrails? An interesting choice, $R.$B$BKraz shall see what is to be learned from them. Thank you for braving the depths of that place.' WHERE entry=12116;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='$R, word just arrived from Moa\'ki Harbor. Something very bad happened over there this morning!$B$BYou\'ve been very helpful to us here. Would you consider using the boat from Unu\'pe to travel to the great Dragonblight?$B$BBy the sound of things, Elder Ko\'nani could certainly use your assistance.',offerrewardtext_loc4='What\'s that you say, $R? Hotawa sent you?$B$BGood, good... there\'s much to do. We can use all of the help that we can get!' WHERE entry=12117;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='$R, word just came in off the boat from Moa\'ki Harbor. Something very bad happened over there this morning!$B$BYou\'ve been very helpful to us here. Would you consider using the boat to travel to the great Dragonblight?$B$BBy the sound of things, Elder Ko\'nani could certainly use your assistance.',offerrewardtext_loc4='What\'s that you say, $R? Anuniaq sent you?$B$BGood, good... there\'s much to do. We can use all of the help that we can get!' WHERE entry=12118;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A letter of introduction to meet with the queen? Let me see that.$B$BWhatever your business is, I hope that it\'s important.  The skies are full of attacking blues today!' WHERE entry=12119;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well thus far, $N, but now comes the true test.' WHERE entry=12120;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Your coming has been foretold, friend. It was good of you to come.' WHERE entry=12121;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A letter of introduction to meet with the queen? Let me see that.$B$BWhatever your business is, I hope that it\'s important.  The skies are full of attacking blues today!' WHERE entry=12122;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are very courageous to bring us this information. I was beginning to wonder why the blue dragonflight had so boldly initiated an attack upon the temple itself. Now we know that they are using enormous amounts of the very magic they view as such a threat to Azeroth.$B$B<The queen shakes her head in seeming resignation.>$B$BHypocritical, but so be it. If Malygos will not come to his senses, we have no choice but to take action in response to their assault.' WHERE entry=12123;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are very courageous to bring us this information. I was beginning to wonder why the blue dragonflight had so boldly initiated an attack upon the temple itself. Now we know that they are using enormous amounts of the very magic they view as such a threat to Azeroth.$B$B<The queen shakes her head in seeming resignation.>$B$BHypocritical, but so be it. If Malygos will not come to his senses, we have no choice but to take action in response to their assault.' WHERE entry=12124;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A simple task for a simpleton. You have performed within my expectations.' WHERE entry=12125;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The power of the unholy is coveted among my kind. It makes up the very fiber of our existence, granting death to those that dare make a mockery of it! Thankfully there is a font from which I may draw from in my time of need.$B$BTake this unholy gem and make your way to the Ruby Dragonshrine, east of here. It is there that you will find Duke Vallenhal, death knight of Arthas. Weaken his resolve in battle and unleash the power of the gem upon him. It will finish him off and steal his unholy energy!$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Koltira\'s eyes widen.>$B$BImpressive. You bested a deathknight of Arthas... Clearly you were not alone... but still...' WHERE entry=12126;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I can already feel the cold coursing through me, $N.' WHERE entry=12127;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hmm... you don\'t look like a research assistant, which is just as well. The iron dwarves look to be preparing for war, and my research team hasn\'t returned. We could use some help around here.' WHERE entry=12128;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You got all of them? Brilliant! I can\'t wait to see the looks on their faces when the golem\'s done.' WHERE entry=12129;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Raegar wipes his forehead with the back of his hand.>$B$BOh, no. This is going to be harder than I thought. These things don\'t have serial numbers or anything, do they?$B$BNever a gnome around when you need one...' WHERE entry=12130;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Raegar takes the batteries from you.>$B$BExcellent! We should be all ready to go.' WHERE entry=12131;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The power I hold comes at a great cost, $N. Many knights, light and dark alike, lost their lives in the final battle at Light\'s Hope. The prospect of the future looks grim, but at least now I know what I face. The Lich King will never release his grasp and for that alone he must die!' WHERE entry=12132;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='This large jack-o\'-lantern rests in the middle of the village.  It eyes those who look upon it, betraying a dark menace within.$B$BSmashing the pumpking reveals an old, scorched holy symbol.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You found this inside the Headless Horseman\'s jack-o-lantern?  It is an old symbol of the Light.  If must have been the Horseman\'s, before he was cursed and turned into the monster he is today.  Thank you, $N.  This symbol deserves to be with paladins.  I will make sure they get it.$B$BOh, and I almost forgot!  You have a secret admirer...$B$BOne of the children wanted you to have this.  She was too shy to give it to you herself.' WHERE entry=12133;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Killing these monsters won\'t bring my father back... but that\'s not the point now, is it?' WHERE entry=12134;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You must help us!  The Headless Horseman will attack the village at any moment!  Fires will be everywhere!  The children aren\'t safe!$B$BPlease, $N, will you face the fires of the Headless Horseman?  When he comes, you must join the fire brigade.  Grab a bucket and toss it on the fires, or pass it to a friend who\'s closer to the blaze.  If you put out all the fires then we may yet be saved!',objectives_loc4='The Costumed Orphan Matron wants you to help put out all the village fires after the Headless Horseman lights them.  When they are out, speak again to the Costumed Orphan Matron.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh, thank you! May the Light bless your good works, kind $Gsir:lady;. The shadow of the Dark Horseman yet looms, but at least, for now, the village is safe from his flames.' WHERE entry=12135;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Gort takes the tome from you and begins reading.>$B$BWHAT! This can\'t be right. I\'ve known some of these $Rs for years!$B$BLeave me, $N. I have much work to do and many traitors to execute.$B$BTake one of these items for your trouble. You\'ve done a great service for the Horde this day.' WHERE entry=12136;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well.$B$BPlease, sit and listen. There are many things we must discuss.' WHERE entry=12137;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Finally, it\'s ready. I only hope it holds together long enough to get the job done. If we don\'t take out the thane leading Dun Argol, Captain Gryan\'ll be in for a nasty surprise.' WHERE entry=12138;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The Headless Horseman will attack the village at any moment!  Fires will be everywhere!$B$B$N, will you face the fires of the Headless Horseman?  When he comes, you must join the fire brigade.  Grab a bucket and toss it on the fires, or pass it to a friend who\'s closer to the blaze.  If you put out all the fires then we may yet be saved!',offerrewardtext_loc4='The fires are out! You and your fire brigade were victorious! Hah!$B$BThe Headless Horseman\'s attack has failed, but until he and his head are destroyed together, He will return.$B$BUntil then, however, let\'s take comfort in the safety you brought our children. I am honored to have watched your brave work today.' WHERE entry=12139;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Like the tauren, Forsaken, trolls and blood elves, so too do the taunka need a leader born of their own blood. The one you saved from Icemist, Roanauk, will be this leader.$B$B<Overlord Agmar hands you a parchment.>$B$BI give to you something familiar - the blood oath of the Horde.$B$BTake the oath to Roanauk Icemist and initiate him into the Horde as leader of the taunka.$B$BLet us not keep him waiting.$B$B<Agmar nods.>$B',objectives_loc4='Seek out Roanauk Icemist at Agmar\'s Hammer and initiate him as a member and leader of the Horde forces.$B$BReturn to Overlord Agmar with the Blood Oath of the Horde when you complete this task.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='With the aid of such a powerful shaman, we are sure to be victorious at the Wrathgate!' WHERE entry=12140;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve come to my aid?  I thank you, $N.' WHERE entry=12141;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Chilltusk, eh?  I\'ve heard his name before.  That\'s some good work, $C.  Hopefully we can turn our attention back to the dragon menace now.' WHERE entry=12143;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good riddance, mon.' WHERE entry=12144;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I can\'t believe dis! Another band of dose vermin just tried ta take off with more of our supplies. Dey\'re scurrying down da canyon now, get after dem and deal with whoever dey\'re going to!',objectives_loc4='Kontokanis wants you to chase the snobolds down the canyon south of Dragon\'s Fall and deal with their leader.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Icefist, eh? I\'ve heard his name before. Dat\'s some good work, mon. Hopefully we Darkspear can turn our attention back to dat dragon menace now.' WHERE entry=12145;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It is indeed strange for any magnataur to carry an item such as this... and very concerning. I am glad that you have shown this to me.' WHERE entry=12146;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The underside of the horn boasts an emblazoned seal with a hammer and a lightning bolt. Something about the horn seems extremely out of place on a Magnataur. $B$BTake the horn east across the Dragon Wastes to Wyrmrest and seek out someone who might be interested in these threatening implications.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It is indeed strange for any magnataur to carry an item such as this... and very concerning. I am glad that you have shown this to me.' WHERE entry=12147;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So it is true. They could not have chosen better timing for such an attack... between the Scourge and the blue flight, it is unlikely that anyone else has noticed yet.' WHERE entry=12148;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Hunt down and kill Bloodfeast, Iceshatter, and Drakegore east of Wyrmrest$B$BBloodfeast resides in the southeastern corner of the Dragon Wastes, just north of the Emerald Dragonshrine. Iceshatter patrols the northern edge of the Mirror of Dawn. Drakegore wanders at the bottom of the cliffs west of the Bronze Dragonshrine.$B$BReturn to Aurastrasza at Wyrmrest once the magnataur have been slain.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work. No one could tell me who this leader might be, but I was able to uncover the name of someone who will have our answer.' WHERE entry=12149;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Locate Dregmar Runebrand near his cave on the path to the cliffs overlooking the Mirror of the Dawn. Challenge him and uncover the name of the magnataur leader by any means necessary. Return to Aurastrasza at Wyrmrest once the information is obtained.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Grom\'thar the Thunderbringer. Good. Let\'s end any threat these magnataur might pose here and now.' WHERE entry=12150;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Travel to the ring of torches south of the Azure Dragonshrine and blow the Emblazoned Battle Horn. Defeat Grom\'thar the Thunderbringer and bring his head back to Aurastrasza at Wyrmrest.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You are formidable indeed.$B$BWith Grom\'thar the Thunderbringer gone, we can leave the remaining Magnataur to fight among themselves and turn our attentions back towards more prominent threats.$B$BImpressive work, $C.' WHERE entry=12151;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It is done.$B$BYour selflessness has brought eternal peace to many souls, ending eons of misery.$B$BMay this act lighten your own soul and lessen your burdens, for I see that there are yet many perils you must face.$B$BFarewell, $N.' WHERE entry=12152;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It worked?$B$B<Raegar clears his throat.>$B$BI mean... of course it worked! This is incredible!$B$BYears from now, Explorers\' League initiates will hear the story of how Raegar Breakbrow, $N, and some hunk o\' junk golem defeated the thane of Dun Argol!' WHERE entry=12153;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Raegar nods approvingly.>$B$BI can\'t stand to see explosives go to waste and it\'ll set our enemies back for sure.' WHERE entry=12154;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='This large jack-o\'-lantern rests in the middle of the village.  It eyes those who look upon it, betraying a dark menace within.$B$BSmashing the pumpking reveals an old, scorched holy symbol.',objectives_loc4='Give the Scorched Holy Symbol to the Masked Orphan Matron.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You found this inside the Headless Horseman\'s jack-o-lantern?  It is an old symbol of the Light.  If must have been the Horseman\'s, before he was cursed and turned into the monster he is today.  Thank you, $N.  This symbol deserves to be with paladins.  I will make sure they get it.$B$BOh, and I almost forgot!  You have a secret admirer...$B$BOne of the children wanted you to have this.  She was too shy to give it to you herself.' WHERE entry=12155;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='DEPRECAED',objectives_loc4='Escort the Alliance Envoy to the town of Silverbrook.  Report to Lieutenant Dumont at the Amberpine Lodge when you\'ve completed this task.' WHERE entry=12156;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We\'re lucky we made it this far, $N.  We were ambushed by Scourge as soon as we landed.$B$BOne of our men turned out to be a spy for the Cult of the Damned.  Thassarian appears to have more evidence of cultist infiltration.  Apparently it goes all the way to the top.$B$BI\'ve sent one of my best couriers to our outpost in western Dragonblight, but he has not yet returned. I fear he may have fallen to the Scourge. Will you go to Dragonblight and search for him? Courier Lanson is his name.$B',objectives_loc4='Speak to Courier Lanson at Star\'s Rest in Dragonblight.',offerrewardtext_loc4='As I crossed the bridge into Dragonblight a small group of Anub\'ar ambushed me! I was surrounded! Those monsters knew I was coming. I barely made it out of there with my flesh intact. This list I hold must be taken to Wintergarde Keep, but I am too badly injured to make the journey.' WHERE entry=12157;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve come to help me, haven\'t you!' WHERE entry=12158;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Rest in peace friends!  Do not worry -- I will tell everyone that we never gave up!' WHERE entry=12159;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Curse our luck.  We find the one functioning mine this side of the hills and it\'s full of Scourge.$B$BNo offense, friend.  But that survivor you found sounds like he\'s been a little traumatized due to losing his friends.  Arugal\'s been dead for years... I even saw his grave once.' WHERE entry=12160;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You seek knowledge beyond your reach so you\'ve come to me.  I must warn you, stranger, the answers I provide might not be to your liking.' WHERE entry=12161;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We got him good, $N.  But not good enough.$B$BOne thing\'s for sure... we won\'t be seeing him around these parts any longer.' WHERE entry=12164;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText4_loc4='Shade of Arugal defeated' WHERE entry=12164;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='$R will you assist me?$B$BThe Scourge have moved into Icemist to the north. Wherever they go, they spread their taint, and the creatures of the land suffer.$B$BTake this vial, which is filled with the liquid fire of Elune from the moonwell. Please, use the liquid to cleanse the corpses of the blighted wildlife that you find.',offerrewardtext_loc4='We have done what we can for the creatures of the land. Now we must take direct action against those that have caused this!' WHERE entry=12166;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done.$B$BI will dispose of these filthy garments by cleansing them in the moonwell and destroying them through the power of the goddess!' WHERE entry=12167;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So, the leader of the cultists has revealed himself. We have a name.$B$BVanity and pride will be his downfall!' WHERE entry=12168;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='With the high cultist destroyed, the rest of his forces can be mopped up and the land and its creatures will recover.$B$BThank you, $N. May the goddess illuminate your path.' WHERE entry=12169;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. Our control over the logging camp might not be complete yet, but thanks to you we\'re one step closer to smashing these Alliance worms.' WHERE entry=12170;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Palena reads the note.>$B$BYou will take my fastest hippogryph, $R! This information must be delivered to High Commander Wyrmbane at once!' WHERE entry=12171;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Welcome, mage.$B$BBy now you must be wondering where Dalaran is and how to get there. I will help you.$B$BBut before I can teach you how to teleport to our great city, you must attune yourself to the ley lines of Northrend. Otherwise, you risk destroying yourself in the process.$B$BTake this attunement crystal and use it in the pit under the surge needle at the Moonrest Gardens to the west. Then you will be ready to learn the spell.',objectives_loc4='The Image of Archmage Modera at Stars\' Rest has asked you to become Attuned to the Ley Lines of Northrend.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Very well. If you are ready, then so am I.' WHERE entry=12172;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Very well. If you think you are ready, then let\'s not waste anymore of my time.' WHERE entry=12173;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='<Palena hands the missive back to you.>$B$BSnowstorm will take you to Wintergarde, $N. I guarantee you that it will be the fastest flight you\'ve ever taken. Go now!$B',objectives_loc4='Deliver the Alliance Missive to High Commander Halford Wyrmbane at Wintergarde Keep in eastern Dragonblight. $B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<The High Commander reads the missive and then crumples it up.>$B$BDo you know where the people on this list are now? Take a look outside, near the front gate. They\'re the ones hanging from the arches.$B$BGhoul bait...' WHERE entry=12174;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re a life saver, $Gbrother:sister;. If you\'re interested in more work, there\'s more where that came from.' WHERE entry=12175;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m in your debt, mon. Take this as payment.' WHERE entry=12176;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Jun\'ik\'s Coverup',objectives_loc4='Bring 1 piece of Coal and 5 Simple Flour to Hidetrader Jun\'ik at Conquest Hold in Grizzly Hills.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Hope for the best, mon.' WHERE entry=12177;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Mountaineer Kilian listens as you relate what the captive prospectors told you.>$B$BThey mentioned Kronus and a war against stone giants? You\'re certain?$B$BSo Raegar\'s instincts were right. We have to find a way to get in there and learn more about their plans.' WHERE entry=12180;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='My, my, how long has it been? How long have we been working on this damned plague? Finally, after an eternity of failure, we are blessed with perfection. This... It doesn\'t even have a proper name yet! This blight... That\'s it, BLIGHT! This blight will tear down the very fabric of life!$B$B<Harris hands you a vial.>$B$BNow, find the bat handler, Tobias, and show him the specimen. He\'ll get you on your way to Venomspite.$B',objectives_loc4='Show the Blight Specimen to Tobias Sarkhoff at New Agamand.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Uh, yea, you can go ahead and hold on to that vial, friend. I trust you.' WHERE entry=12181;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh joyous day! And look, just beyond the mountain to the northeast creeps a whole field of Scourge for us to obliterate!' WHERE entry=12182;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Kilian takes the uniform from you.>$B$BThis should do. I won\'t have time to sew on a little patch with \'$N\' embroidered on it or anything, but anyone looking closely at you should be convinced that you\'re an overseer by the time we\'re done with you.' WHERE entry=12183;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good, these should do. Now, to create a kit to pass you off as a convincing iron dwarf.' WHERE entry=12184;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Could it be that Kronus isn\'t really exaggerating? The titans\' stone and iron sons fighting against each other for control of the ancient city of Ulduar. This is madness, $N and it could destroy our only chance to learn the true history of dwarvenkind!' WHERE entry=12185;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This will do nicely, $N. Did those pathetic whelps put up a fight or did they just shower you with ghostly tears of sorrow?$B$BAh, they get so emotional...' WHERE entry=12188;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Travel to Venomspite in Dragonblight and speak with Chief Plaguebringer Middleton.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='We ran into a little - MINOR - problem. Everyone that tried handling the blight vaporized. We\'re working on adjusting the formula a tad so it doesn\'t instantly kill you for looking at it sideways. The good news is that I think I\'ve almost got it!' WHERE entry=12189;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well now! Good ol\' Prigmon sent ya did he?$B$BThis should make fer some mighty fine eatin\'. Needs just a couple things...' WHERE entry=12190;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Those pesky Dark Irons are back! We need to make sure that you can defend yourself if needed. More importantly, we need to know that you can defend our property!$B$BS.T.O.U.T. here is ready for action, are you? Drink from the Complimentary Brewfest Samplers then throw the mug at S.T.O.U.T.! Hit the target 5 times then talk to me.',objectives_loc4='Use the Complimentary Brewfest Sampler to hit S.T.O.U.T. 5 times, then talk to Bizzle Quicklift.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Wow... S.T.O.U.T. didn\'t break... Hmm... Who would have guessed?$B$BI mean, hey, you did it! Your aim is true, or at least true enough to help guard the camp. I think you\'re ready now to take on the Dark Irons if they show up again.' WHERE entry=12191;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The Dark Irons took a beating!  As they rushed back to the Grim Guzzler, a portion of their transport fell off.  More importantly, you managed to keep the camp safe... today.$B$BHead over to Bizzle and explain your heroic triumph over the Dark Iron dwarves.',objectives_loc4='Talk to Bizzle Quicklift in the Brewfest camp.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So you managed to stop the Dark Irons... While drunk too? That, $C, is truly the spirit of Brewfest! I guess in keeping with the spirit of Brewfest you want your prize tokens.$B$BThanks for your help, $N. Enjoy the rest of Brewfest.' WHERE entry=12192;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Say, There Wouldn\'t Happen to be a Souvenir This Year, Would There?',details_loc4='Brewfest isn\'t just about racing rams, it\'s also about drinking!  When you have a moment, take this voucher to Belbi Quikswitch.  She\'s near the back of the Brewfest camp.  If you can\'t see her, don\'t worry, she\'ll be sure to see you.$B$BIn any case, take this voucher to her to get your free Brewfest stein.  She\'ll also be more than happy to handle any and all other Brewfest transactions.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Aww, it\'s just a stein voucher... Maybe you\'re just playing hard to get. So here\'s this year\'s stein for you.$B$BBut I suspect I\'ll be seeing a lot more of you. After all, if you want any Brewfest tokens redeemed, I\'m your girl...$B$BOr maybe I\'m his girl...$B$BOooohhh... or his...' WHERE entry=12193;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Well, we\'ve got the shell of a golem, but that\'s not good enough for Tormak. He doesn\'t realize that these things don\'t just come together and miraculously start working! We\'re going to need power cells to animate it.$B$BWhen I was in Dun Argol, I noticed that Rune-Smith Durar and Rune-Smith Kathorn were the ones who manufactured the cells. We\'ll need one from each to power our golem.$B$BYou should be able to find each rune-smith in his workshop on the central level of Dun Argol.',objectives_loc4='Bring Durar\'s Power Cell and Kathorn\'s Power Cell to Prospector Rokar at Camp Oneqwah.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Rokar takes the batteries from you.>$B$BThese are low, but they\'ll be enough to start up the golem. He\'s nowhere near ready for battle, though.' WHERE entry=12197;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The golem\'s cells have just enough power to run it at the lowest levels, but it can\'t power any of its combat systems.$B$BThe good news is that the perimeter of Dun Argol is patrolled by lightning sentries. We should be able to use their power to charge up the golem\'s weapon systems.$B$BBring the golem with you, take it close to them, it will absorb the power as the sentries die.',objectives_loc4='Charge your War Golem with the energy from 10 Lightning Sentries and return to Prospector Rokar at Camp Oneqwah.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, now Tormak can\'t complain anymore. This baby\'s as ready as I can make it.$B$BAfter you tear your way through Dun Argol with it, that overgrown cow\'ll have to release me.' WHERE entry=12198;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I do believe that the blight is now ready for a field test. Fortuitously, the dread citadel, Naxxramas, is laying siege to Wintergarde Keep. From beneath the very earth that Wintergarde was built upon rise the living dead, eager to do the bidding of Kel\'Thuzad.$B$BThe Alliance are, of course, outmanned and outgunned. The people laid to rest in the Wintergarde Mausoleum awaken, hungering for flesh!$B$BPerhaps we shall give them a taste of the blight, yes?' WHERE entry=12200;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='The Overseer\'s Shadow',objectives_loc4='Bring an Overseer\'s Uniform to Scout Vor\'takh at Camp Oneqwah.',offerrewardtext_loc4='This should work, but there\'s still the matter of the rest of your disguise. Even those dimwitted metal dwarves will recognize an impostor with a stolen suit.' WHERE entry=12201;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Now we have to finish the job of making you as repulsive as those iron dwarves.$B$BThe best way to do that is to base your disguise on the ugly mugs of real iron dwarves.$B$BWhen Tormak\'s hunting party discovered that wayward prospector, they took the camera he carried. Now, I suppose, we\'ll get the chance to use it.$B$BTake it with you to Dun Argol, kill some iron dwarves, and record their likenesses in this device. Bring it back once you have enough examples.',objectives_loc4='Use Rokar\'s Camera to record the images of 8 Iron Dwarves in Dun Argol, then return to Scout Vor\'takh at Camp Oneqwah.',offerrewardtext_loc4='These should serve. By Garrosh, these creatures are ugly.' WHERE entry=12202;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Very well done, $R. I trust that you were cleverly vicious in your slaying?$B$BLet\'s see, how much I can offer you from the coffins... er, excuse me, coffers?' WHERE entry=12205;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='WHAT?! That\'s impossible! We\'ve perfected the blight. It has a one-hundred percent lethality.$B$B<The apothecary wrings her hands, concern crossing her unliving visage. Clearly frustrated, she continues in an angry tone.>$B$BThis is just really odd. Hand me that flask, $C. I\'m not going to be known as the apothecary that ruined everything!' WHERE entry=12206;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You do not smell so fresh now, new meat.$B$BVery well, all of this will do. By what name might I call you, $C?' WHERE entry=12209;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Here to get in on the bounty action, eh?' WHERE entry=12210;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh good! For a moment I thought I was going to have to test the rats out on someone to make sure that they weren\'t defective.$B$BProgress, finally!' WHERE entry=12211;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These are some choice pieces of meat!' WHERE entry=12212;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, nothing makes me happier than a job well done.$B$BYou\'ve done Venomspite a great service in acquiring these horses, $C.' WHERE entry=12214;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good work, $C.$B$BThis should help ensure that the wildlife in these parts ends up where it should - roasting over our fires.' WHERE entry=12215;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Outstanding!$B$BOur stores are nearly replenished now. You\'ve done your part, $N.' WHERE entry=12216;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A somber task, I know. But we can rest easier now knowing the enemy\'s eyes are no longer upon us.' WHERE entry=12217;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='As much as it irritates me that we may have assisted the Alliance, I declare the field test a success! Next stop: Agmar\'s Hammer!' WHERE entry=12218;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The slime is not natural, $N.  Its very nature is corrupt and... evil.$B$BWe must find out more.' WHERE entry=12219;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The energy in the orb is... overpowering...$B$BA dark force has tainted the ground near Vordrassil\'s remains.  We will need to investigate more.' WHERE entry=12220;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I have prepared a package that must be delivered to Doctor Sintar Malefious at Agmar\'s Hammer. The contents of the package include the final blight specimen along with instructions on preparation and samples of the reactive agent.$B$BYou will find Agmar\'s Hammer in western Dragonblight. Just look for the black, jagged metal orc buildings - that will be Agmar\'s Hammer.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Doctor Malefious looks through the contents of the package.>$B$BGlorious! Exactly to specifications!$B$BHere is your payment, $N. Keep what you\'ve seen and done to yourself. This work is all classified - information is given out on a need to know basis.' WHERE entry=12221;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='With the talismans in hand, the drake will have no choice but to obey you. I can\'t wait to see the look on the thane\'s face when he realizes you\'ve commandeered his proto-drake.' WHERE entry=12222;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. Now, we must follow through and press the advantage.' WHERE entry=12223;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Lok\'tar ogar! I have heard much about you, $N. Your battle scars run deep - a testament to your dedication and power!$B$BWith the flanking attacks of the Lich King crushed in both the west and east, only the forces at the gate remain. We gain ground each day, soon to break through this wall and into Icecrown!$B$BOnce we stop the skeletal dragons, Highlord Fordragon and I will take the field.' WHERE entry=12224;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Your stomach growls as the pungent smell of hearty nuts draws your attention to the the bucket of seeds.$B$BSome thoughtful soul has obviously left these complimentary morsels here to rejuvenate weary visitors. Grateful, you take the remaining few and devour them.$B$BThe seeds do not disappoint. Finding yourself hungry for more, you set out to discover their origins....',offerrewardtext_loc4='You did what!!!$B$BThose were Amberseeds! And that was an entire harvest\'s worth!$B$BThose magical seeds may have been the answer to our food crisis. Believe me when I tell you, $N, you\'re going to make this right!' WHERE entry=12225;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These should do just fine...$B$B<Anderhol deftly twists the stalks, collecting their slick fluids in a tiny vial.>$B$BThere we go, now it\'s time to get down to business.' WHERE entry=12226;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, $N? Everything come out okay?$B$BHmm, looks like we caught \'em just in time....' WHERE entry=12227;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Not long ago we sent an expedition to the east, where it was attacked by crazed furbolgs.  One of the survivors described slaying one of them and its body expelling a dark slimy substance.$B$BFor thousands of years, the furbolgs in this region have been peaceful.  It is possible that there is a link to the furbolgs\' behavior and the dark energy we were able to detect earlier.$B$BBring me samples of the furbolgs\' blood.  You will find them to the east in the Rage Fang Shrine and the Heart\'s Blood Shrine.',objectives_loc4='Windseer Grayhorn in Conquest Hold wants you to obtain 8 Crazed Furbolg Blood from the Furbolgs at Heart\'s Blood Shrine and Rage Fang Shrine.',offerrewardtext_loc4='This blood carries the same taint as the slime you obtained earlier... this does not bode well, $N.' WHERE entry=12229;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The deathguard rubs his hands together in anticipation.>$B$BExcellent. Their loss is my... our gain!$B$BYou didn\'t have trouble with any of these along the way? Some of them look rather unstable. I may be $R, but I value my existence!' WHERE entry=12230;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh happy day!$B$BBy not using the time and resources of the apothecaries to get the job done, I\'m sure to attract the attention of the high executor!$B$BThinking outside the box, that\'s what I\'m all about. Yes, yes, you had a hand in helping too.$B$BHere, if I give you something will you promise to not mention your part in all of this?' WHERE entry=12232;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, what are you waiting for, $R? Hand them over!' WHERE entry=12234;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Lord Fordragon has led a crushing assault against Arthas at the Wrathgate. In response to this affront, Arthas has sent Naxxramas down upon us. While Kel\'Thuzad hides in the floating citadel, his ground commander, Thel\'zan, lays siege to Wintergarde Keep. The lower village is already lost and any chance of extracting survivors from the ruins diminishes by the minute.$B$BWe must act quickly! Report to Gryphon Commander Urik at the gryphon station at once! He\'ll get you up to speed.$B$BLeave me!
',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Urik points to a gryphon.>$B$BHave you ever ridden one of those? It\'s simple, friend. Just hop on and tell it where to go.
' WHERE entry=12235;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The time has come, $N.  Now we will learn whether our efforts will accomplish what we need or nothing at all.$B$BTake these ashes and seek the furbolg that Kodian told you about, Tur Ragepaw, near Ursoc\'s Den.  You will find the den to the north of Grizzlemaw.$B$BConvince Tur to aid you, for you will need all the help you can get.$B$BOnce you\'ve defeated the bear god, use these ashes over his body.$B$BEven if his worldly form is destroyed, his spirit must be saved.',objectives_loc4='Windseer Grayhorn in Conquest Hold wants you to find Tur Ragepaw near Ursoc\'s Den and defeat Ursoc with his help.  Use the Purified Ashes of Vordrassil on Ursoc\'s Corpse when you\'ve accomplished this.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<The druid looks pale and her eyes stare blankly past you. She has left a package in anticipation of your return.>' WHERE entry=12236;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Rescue 10 Helpless Wintergarde Villagers and return to Gryphon Commander Urik at Wintergarde Keep.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Outstanding work, $N! We can get this keep back into working order now with the return of our citizens.' WHERE entry=12237;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The time be here at last, good friend.$B$BDrak\'Tharon soon be cleansed of them foul undead and restored to her noble purpose. My soul will be havin\' peace, and in return for your help, the keep\'s most valuable treasures be yours, mon!$B$BDa keep rises up into a sacred ziggurat. Once ya be reachin\' its top, ya must summon me a final time, and I\'ll perform the ritual.$B$BAlas, mon, my summonin\' will again be comin\' at a cost. Ya must collect the mojo from the survivors in the keep,',offerrewardtext_loc4='We done a great thing, mon! And dis just be da beginning....$B$BSeek me out in Zul\'Drak when da time be right.$B$BDere be a war to be won, mon!' WHERE entry=12238;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have word from the spy mistress?$B$B<The agent looks around to make sure that no one is watching as she puts down her shovel.>$B$BLet me see those plans.' WHERE entry=12239;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I knew my sister wouldn\'t let us down.$B$BWell done, $N. The Onslaught\'s lumbermill will be out of commission for a while, which means no new construction or ballistae.$B$BThanks for helping me to live up to the family name.' WHERE entry=12240;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We must make sure that Vordrassil is never regrown.  The furbolg must have harvested its seed.$B$BGo to Grizzlemaw, in central Grizzly Hills, and obtain all the seeds that you can find.  I will make sure they\'re properly destroyed.',objectives_loc4='Windseer Grayhorn in Conquest Hold wants you to go to Grizzlemaw and obtain 8 of Vordrassil\'s Seeds.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $N. I\'ll take those from you.$B$BThe corruptive power of these seeds is dangerous. I must destroy them right away.' WHERE entry=12242;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ahhahahahahahahahaha!$B$BWithout their rutters, they\'ve got nowhere to run to now.$B$BLooks to me like the end of the Scarlet Onslaught, and just when they were getting started. How sad.$B$BHeh.' WHERE entry=12243;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Synipus whistles.>$B$BOh, she\'s a beauty! We\'ll fix her up nice.$B$BIf you\'re short on things to do, go talk to Gordun and get a ride down to Venture Bay. They\'re sure to need a hand.$B$BOh, and while you\'re there, use these keys on a Refurbished Shredder. Wait \'til ya see what these babies can do when they\'re cleaned up!' WHERE entry=12244;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What? You were expecting us to have you rescue them?$B$BNow why would we do that when they have a proven track record of getting themselves captured in the first place?$B$BNorthrend is a cold place, young $N. I suggest that you adjust to it.' WHERE entry=12245;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The corruption present in this blood is identical to that of the slime. I don\'t have a good feeling about this.' WHERE entry=12246;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ursoc\'s children are wise. Their words explain much of what we\'ve seen so far.' WHERE entry=12247;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes! Vordrassil\'s magic is still present in these ashes. There might be hope for Ursoc yet.' WHERE entry=12248;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The druid looks pale and her eyes stare blankly past you. She has left a package in anticipation of your return.>' WHERE entry=12249;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $N. I\'ll take those from you.$B$BThe corruptive power of these seeds is dangerous. I must destroy them right away.' WHERE entry=12250;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Halford salutes.>$B$BThe townsfolk are all back to work? Already? Outstanding, soldier! We\'ll get this town built back up and fortified in no time. Before long, reinforcements will be ready to join the fight with Lord Fordragon at the Wrathgate.$B$BI\'m getting ahead of myself, of course, as there is much left to do here before we can even think about sending you to the aid of Bolvar.
' WHERE entry=12251;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='They knew all of that? And who the hell is this Grand Admiral Westwind that he spoke of?!$B$B<The high executor grumbles to himself about hating surprises.>$B$BBetter that we know than have to guess. I hope that you left your... er, my mark.' WHERE entry=12252;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Halford says a prayer for the deceased.>$B$BYou do the Light\'s work, $N.$B$BI fear that our work has only just begun.$B$B<Halford holds up a document.>' WHERE entry=12253;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A newly scribed blessing at the back of the book you say?$B$B<The agent glances over your shoulder as you flip to the page at the end.>$B$BDamn it all! That\'s the high abbot\'s handwriting! I\'d stake your life on it.' WHERE entry=12254;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good work, $N. I doubt any of the woodsmen would\'ve wanted to take a crack at the proto-drake, but we couldn\'t afford to let the Dragonflayers build a base of power in Grizzly Hills. If only the Horde was so easily dealt with...' WHERE entry=12255;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='With the power of the talismans, the drake has no choice but to obey your commands. The thane\'s fate is sealed.' WHERE entry=12256;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done exactly as I asked. We\'ve got the Dragonflayers on the defensive and it\'ll soon be time to deal with their leader.' WHERE entry=12257;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Commander Lynore Windstryke at Wintergarde Keep in Dragonblight wants you to kill 15 Vengeful Geists.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Perhaps now they will rest easy, their spirits free to ascend to the Light.$B$BMy thoughts and prayers now turn to Lord Fordragon and our forces at the Wrathgate. We must persevere here, if only to buy them enough time to defeat the Lich King. Wintergarde cannot fall.' WHERE entry=12258;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='With the flame-imbued talismans, we can finally challenge the thane.$B$BHis favorite mount is a ferocious proto-drake called Flamebringer. It is kept bound in chains in the western part of Voldrune, but with the power of the talismans, you should be able to bend it to your will and use it against the thane.$B$BOnce you have Flamebringer under your control, search the tops of the towers of Voldrune for the thane and use Flamebringer to destroy him.',objectives_loc4='Use Flamebringer to defeat Thane Torvald Eriksson and report to Sergeant Nazgrim at Conquest Hold.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The few remaining Dragonflayers dare not challenge us after your battle with the thane. Show no mercy to our enemies - that is the way of the Horde.' WHERE entry=12259;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Agent Skully at New Hearthglen has asked you steal the image of a Onslaught Raven Priest. Return the Banshee\'s Magic Mirror to her when you have done so.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Not bad, $C. Now that the priest\'s image is trapped within the mirror, I have something else that needs doing.' WHERE entry=12260;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent. When they begin to flee in fear, the ward shall be there to wish them a fond farewell.' WHERE entry=12261;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Did they beg for their miserable lives? Weaklings.' WHERE entry=12262;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We are the Black Dragonflight. We have rained destruction on the lands of Azeroth for thousands of years. The decrepit Cult of the Damned worships death and we shall be glad to oblige.' WHERE entry=12263;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hearing their screams... watching the last life fade from their wretched bodies... it\'s invigorating, is it not?$B$BI relish it.' WHERE entry=12264;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good. There is more to be done.' WHERE entry=12265;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh, it\'s you.$B$BI had hoped Serinar would simply return himself once the task was done... I suppose he\'s distracted by something or another to kill. He\'s missing out on a gloriously messy battle!$B$BAre you still here? I\'m done with you.' WHERE entry=12266;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The bones of my brood have been spared this filth. You have served me well, and as such, you shall be awarded appropriately.' WHERE entry=12267;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes indeed. These should do the trick...$B$BThere. One more shredder ready for the fight. Thanks, $N.' WHERE entry=12268;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Leoric takes the cards from you.>$B$BI will get these to our recorder and deliver the grim news to the families of the miners.$B$BThere is still much to be done if we are to succeed here and ultimately at the Wrathgate. Lord Fordragon is depending on us.' WHERE entry=12269;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good work, soldier!$B$BNow take this key and get yourself down to Venture Bay. It\'ll let you use one of the refurbished shredders to unleash chaos on our enemies.$B$BOh yes, and talk to Darrok if you want to take the shortcut!' WHERE entry=12270;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='LeCraft had it you say? That makes sense.$B$BI recognize it from my youthful days as a torturer in the court of King Terenas of fallen Lordaeron. It\'s known as a rod of compulsion.$B$B<The high executor wrings his hands together in evil anticipation of what\'s to come.>$B$BI have an idea for how we can make good use of it!' WHERE entry=12271;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This might be the moment, the very second, that the tide turns against the Scourge. You have proven yourself as a hero of the Alliance, at least in my eyes, $N.$B$BNow if you would be so kind as to give me some space. I will require additional time to study this ore in order to isolate impurities and weakness.$B$BCarry on, ally. I will contact you once I have an update.' WHERE entry=12272;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<You think you see just the hint of a smile cross Wroth\'s face before quickly disappearing.>$B$BYou\'re now my favorite $C, $N. If you have a mind to, I\'d like you to think about joining up as an officer in the Hand of Vengeance.$B$BWe can start you out as a deathguard, and in a few decades I think you have what it takes to make junior executor!$B$BNo? Well don\'t be too hasty... take your time and mull it over.' WHERE entry=12273;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Blacksmith Goodman\'s denouncement & death',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Stable Master Mercer\'s denouncement & death' WHERE entry=12273;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What the hell is going on here?!$B$BHe jumped on his own? You\'re certain that you didn\'t push him?$B$B<The agent narrows her eyes at you.>$B$BFine. Clearly there\'s much more going on in this place than we first thought.' WHERE entry=12274;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I feel terrible about this, friend. I fear that in my haste to recover the strange ore from Wintergarde Mine I may have doomed agent Slinkin.
' WHERE entry=12275;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Find Slinkin the Demo-gnome in Wintergarde Mine. Use Quarterflash\'s Homing Bot if you need help finding the mine.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<There is a note in Slinkin\'s death grip.>$B$BChased into a dead end. Hidden for now, but they know I\'m here. It won\'t be long until they find me.$B$BThe miners work tirelessly to unearth the strange ore that fuels the Scourge war machines. There is much banter. The language of death confounds me, but I have been able to identify commonly uttered sounds and phrases. The word "Yogg-Saron" is said with great contempt and is usually followed by loud outbursts. They refer to the ore as "saronite." Meaning?' WHERE entry=12276;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='His death will not have been in vain, friend. The information that Slinkin died for will be instrumental in defeating the Lich King. I promise you that we will make this right.' WHERE entry=12277;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Your paperwork looks to be in order.  Welcome to the club, $N!$B$BYou can expect to get our mail at the start of every month.  If you like what you got, stop by and we can sell you some more.  This is the club that keeps on giving.' WHERE entry=12278;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You! You\'re not Limpy Joe!' WHERE entry=12279;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thanks, $N. That should keep me going - at least until tomorrow....$B$BHere\'s the cash I promised.' WHERE entry=12280;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Halford opens the package and reads the analysis.>$B$BI am by no means a scientist, $N, so you\'ll have to forgive my plebian understanding of what has been written. Now, according to this analysis - assuming I have the brain power of at least an adolescent school boy - we still don\'t know jack squat about the Scourge war machine. The only thing we do know is that the Scourge uses this foul metal to craft its siege engines, armor and weaponry.$B$B<Halford lets loose a long sigh.>' WHERE entry=12281;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. As fate foretold, you will be the one to carry us through these hard times. Now the long journey begins.' WHERE entry=12282;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Damn it all! Why couldn\'t you have come to me with good news?!' WHERE entry=12283;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Fifteen down, eh? Good to hear it, $C.$B$BIf nothing else you\'ve bought us a bit of time - at least a day by my figuring.$B$BHere\'s your pay.' WHERE entry=12284;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Their attack is imminent, $C. I need you to get in there and sever the head of the Scarlet Onslaught, literally!$B$BIt\'s not going to be easy... Abbendis is sure to be surrounded by a great many of her men. I suggest that you take at least a couple of friends along.$B$BBring back her head and I\'ll see to it that you\'re properly rewarded for saving Venomspite.$B$BFail and don\'t even bother to return!',offerrewardtext_loc4='Let\'s see them bring her back to life without her head!$B$B<The high executor\'s laugh draws a number of furtive glances.>$B$BI\'m a little concerned that you let this grand admiral get away, but you\'re still the hero of the day, $N!$B$BTake your pick... you\'ve earned it!' WHERE entry=12285;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Zelig sent word, friend. We have been expecting you.$B$BI am Orik Trueheart, paladin of the Argent Crusade. The priestess standing across the campfire from me is Tilda Darathan. We are here on behalf of the Argent Crusade - sent to quell the unfortunate damned souls attempting to escape Wintergarde.' WHERE entry=12287;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh, thank you, thank you.$B$BYou\'ve helped us to live another day. Perhaps there\'s hope yet.' WHERE entry=12288;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='It is a dark day for the Alliance. Many good men lay dead or dying here. Our only consolation is that they fought well and brought down many of the enemy with them.$B$BWith the bulk of our forces committed to Venture Bay we stand alone to weather this storm. The resources in this region are vital to the Alliance and may well make the difference in our struggle against the Horde. We must not fail!$B$BGo, $N. Strike at them while they lick their wounds. Avenge your fallen brothers and keep our hopes alive!',objectives_loc4='Sergeant Hartsman wants you to defeat 15 Horde units or players in Blue Sky Logging Grounds.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N.$B$BYou\'ve bought us some time here, though likely no more than a day. Nevertheless, the Alliance is grateful for your efforts.' WHERE entry=12289;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Orik takes the murkweed and begins mixing an elixir.>$B$BIt won\'t be much longer, $N.' WHERE entry=12290;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Orik\'s eyes fill with tears.>$B$BThey don\'t know. None of them know! They think Arthas to be some great hero, when in truth it was Arthas who ordered the ships to be burned. It was Arthas who left us all for dead in this frozen wasteland!$B$B<Orik weeps.>$B$BNot all of the soldiers from the Prince\'s fleet perished in the freezing winter. I was only a lad when I was given the chance to battle the Scourge... to save our home from certain destruction. I took that chance, $N.' WHERE entry=12291;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Forgotten Knight Questioned',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Forgotten Footman Questioned' WHERE entry=12291;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s locked, isn\'t it? It looks pretty ordinary.$B$B<Lieutenant Dumont Shakes the chest, producing a rattling wooden sound.>$B$BNo matter, I suppose. If this gets us the edge we need against the Horde, then I could care less if the cure for the Plague was in there.' WHERE entry=12292;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You did it!  You recovered the Sc... you recovered the chest that the Horde stole from us.  We thank you, $N.' WHERE entry=12293;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent news, $N.  With the locals\' help we\'ll have the logistical support we need to outmaneuver the Horde in this region.$B$BI have further tasks for you if you\'re interested.' WHERE entry=12294;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s good to finally meet you, $N!  We\'d heard about you up here.  Welcome to Silverbrook.$B$BThese trappers are a great bunch of lads and lasses.  Hardy people, they know the lay of the land really well.  You\'ll find it\'s a great thing that we finally won them over to our side.' WHERE entry=12295;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Wonderful!$B$BThe alliance shall live to see another day, in part due to your diligence.$B$BPlease accept my thanks, friend.' WHERE entry=12296;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Greer lifts his glasses onto the top of his head and reads the note, looking back up at you curiously when he\'s done.>$B$BYou will have my fastest gryphon! This information must be delivered to High Commander Wyrmbane at once!
' WHERE entry=12297;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='<Greer hands the missive back to you.>$B$BSkysong will take you to Wintergarde, $N. I guarantee you that it will be the fastest flight you\'ve ever taken. Go now!$B',objectives_loc4='Deliver the Alliance Missive to High Commander Halford Wyrmbane at Wintergarde Keep in eastern Dragonblight. $B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<The High Commander reads the missive and then crumples it up.>$B$BDo you know where the people on this list are now? Take a look outside, near the front gate. They\'re the ones hanging from the arches.$B$BGhoul bait...' WHERE entry=12298;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Not bad, not bad.  You might not be as soft as some of the others.' WHERE entry=12299;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Don\'t do it, $N.  The people that sent you here.... you shouldn\'t trust them.' WHERE entry=12300;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc4='The people in Silverbrook... they\'re not what they seem.' WHERE entry=12300;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Orik beams a smile at you.>$B$BYou did a good thing this day, $N. Hundreds of lost souls are now redeemed, thanks to you.' WHERE entry=12301;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Who\'s there?  Are you here to kill me?$B$BPlease!  You don\'t have to do this!' WHERE entry=12302;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The quartermaster gasps, but then his eyes narrow as he studies you for a moment.>$B$BI trust that you didn\'t stash any of this on the side for yourself? You wouldn\'t be that selfish when the fate of Venomspite is at stake?$B$BBesides, I\'m going to reward you with a percentage of the take. It\'s not much, but in times like this, we all have to make sacrifices.' WHERE entry=12303;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Can\'t you just see it now, $C? It\'ll be the vacation spot of Northrend!$B$BWhat do you think of the name, "Hansen\'s Cove", or maybe "$N Bay"? Kind of catchy, don\'t you think?' WHERE entry=12304;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You have honored me and honored the memory of hundreds of Alliance veterans, $N. Zelig was wise in sending you here. Please return to him and give him my thanks. He will be happy to hear of the events that transpired at the Forgotten Shore.$B$BI do not have the gift of foresight like Zelig, but I am certain that great things await you, friend.$B$BFarewell. $B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Zelig smiles.>$B$BIt is I who owe you a debt of gratitude, hero. Orik is like a brother to me. You have changed his life and given renewed hope to countless others.' WHERE entry=12305;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='There is strength in numbers, $N.  Being part of the "Brew of the Month" club means knowing you and your brethren will always have access to the best brew.$B$BBring your "Brew of the Month" club membership form to Ray\'ma in the Darkbriar Lodge in Orgrimmar\'s Valley of Spirits.',objectives_loc4='Bring the "Brew of the Month" club membership form to Ray\'ma in the Darkbriar Lodge in Orgrimmar\'s Valley of Spirits.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So you be joinin\' our ranks, $N?  We treat ya nice here.  You only get the best when you part of dis club!$B$BWe be sendin\' out brew to you at da start of every month.  If you like what you got, and you be wantin\' more, head back over here.  We make sure you get more of da brew you like.' WHERE entry=12306;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Katja reels away from you nervously.>$B$BThank you, $N.  You didn\'t get any wolfsbane on you, did you?  I\'ve got these... allergies that act up once in a while.' WHERE entry=12307;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Worgen.  Blasted, Light-forsaken, filth-ridden worgen.$B$BIt\'s time we showed the locals what us civilized folk do with beasts like them.' WHERE entry=12308;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc4='You made it back. I was a worried about you, $N.' WHERE entry=12308;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Seek out Cavalier Durkon at the Wintergarde Crypt in Dragonblight.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh brother, it\'s a mess down there! I barely made it out last time - which is what prompted my request to the High Commander.$B$B<Durkon looks you up and down.>$B$BYou got that crazy look in your eyes, $R. Thankfully, you\'re gonna need to be crazy to do what I\'m about to ask of you.' WHERE entry=12309;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s a shame those trappers turned out to be... afflicted.  We sure could\'ve used a few more fighting men.$B$BMay the poor souls rest in peace.' WHERE entry=12310;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Held within the cold stone walls of this crypt are the remains of the nobles and dignitaries that died in Northrend. At its very core now sits a necrolord who raises the corpses as servants of the Scourge.$B$BYou must make your way to the bottom of the Wintergarde Crypt and kill Necrolord Amarion. Only then will the assault from within cease!$B$BAnd $N, be on the lookout for any information that might be laying about inside the room where Amarion resides. $B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Now if we could stop the Scourge attacks coming from outside the keep we might be able to send help to Lord Fordragon at the Wrathgate.' WHERE entry=12311;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Whatever information is held in this book must be of great importance! I could hear the howls and wails echoing through the crypt as you made your escape!$B$BThe High Commander must be notified!' WHERE entry=12312;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='UNUSED Save Brewfest!',objectives_loc4='Talk to the Brewfest spy in the Grim Guzzler of Blackrock Depths.$B' WHERE entry=12313;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N! Without their leader, the Horde is weak and disorganized. I will order our men forward.' WHERE entry=12314;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are a true soldier of the Horde, $N. Your bravery will inspire my men to victory!' WHERE entry=12315;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Your bravery has inspired the men of the Westfall Brigade. Even now they fight with greater ferocity. The port will soon be ours.' WHERE entry=12316;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='This wretched Westfall Brigade is proving a tougher opponent than we\'d thought. Though few in number, they fight well and bravely, but we cannot afford to wait them out.$B$BConqueror Krenna\'s orders were to capture the port quickly. You must break the stalemate, $N. Find the enemy\'s marines and slaughter them until the resistance ceases. Only then will we be able to claim ownership of the port.$B$BGo quickly. We don\'t want to keep Conqueror Krenna waiting.',objectives_loc4='Defeat 10 Alliance units or players in Venture Bay and return to Centurion Kaggrum.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The port will soon fall to us. You have done well this day, $N.' WHERE entry=12317;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Halford\'s eyes widen.>$B$BThe fates smile down upon us on this day, $N. I know just the person to see about this tome.' WHERE entry=12319;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Perhaps, with proper motivation, Godfrey will tell us what he knows about the tome.$B$B<Hallard turns to Mayor Godfrey.>$B$BIsn\'t that right, mayor?' WHERE entry=12320;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We should have known about the damned mausoleum. This is preposterous! Duke August Foehammer and Ambo Cash will be dispatched to the front lines in preparation for our next assault.$B$BOnce you have cleared the mines I will send you to Foehammer so that we may begin our attack against the Scourge of Naxxramas!$B$BThe information you have garnered thus far will be sent to Lord Fordragon at the Wrathgate upon the wings of our most able gryphon!' WHERE entry=12321;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, soldier! Now the rest of the men can focus their efforts on the Horde.' WHERE entry=12323;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Not only is this port infested with sniveling Alliance cowards, but to make matters worse, there are still Venture Company employees holed up in some of the buildings. They\'re not worth the time it takes to kill and I can\'t spare the warriors anyway.$B$BMaybe we can "convince" them to make for their ship. Take this smoke bomb and use it to smoke out the stragglers from their places in the bunkhouse, sawmill, or stables. Don\'t get too close, though; there\'s no telling what diseases they\'re carrying.',objectives_loc4='Use the Smoke Bomb to drive 20 Venture Company Stragglers from their buildings and then report to Stone Guard Ragetotem.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The general will be pleased that you\'ve dealt with the Venture Company problem. Now, the men can focus on beating back the Alliance.' WHERE entry=12324;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Speak with Gryphon Commander Urik to secure a ride to Thorson\'s Post. Report to Duke August Foehammer when you arrive at Thorson\'s Post in Dragonblight.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, the distinguished hero arrives. Welcome to ground zero, $N. Allow me to bring you up to speed!$B$BThel\'zan\'s most powerful forces have made their way into the Wintergarde Mausoleum. They plumb its depths in search of corpses and souls to send against Wintergarde while Naxxramas rains down terrible Scourge plague machines, set to hold us at bay!$B$BWe must strike now and hope that Lord Fordragon is able to hold out at the Wrathgate for just a little longer.
' WHERE entry=12325;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Why I\'m not wearing any pants isn\'t important. Let\'s just say I took some Scourge shrapnel in the wrong place and leave it at that, ok?$B$BSo you wiped out those plague wagons up in the fields and got my soldiers here in one piece. Impressive. You\'re one of the first to make it this far, friend. Too bad you gotta go right back out into the Carrion Fields. Yep, we\'ve had a bit of a setback.
' WHERE entry=12326;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Did you learn anything from your vision?  You mentioned Solstice Village during your trance -- which marks the second time someone has spoken the place\'s name today.' WHERE entry=12327;
UPDATE locales_quest SET EndText_loc4='Vision from the Past' WHERE entry=12327;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good.  These will do just fine.$B$BI will have the potion ready for you in no time at all.' WHERE entry=12328;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I was wondering when you\'d turn up.  Think you can give me a hand here?' WHERE entry=12329;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That... that was close.$B$BWe need to save Anya.  Now!' WHERE entry=12330;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Incredible! Let me just say that I continue to be amazed by what you younger races seem capable of.$B$BWe are indebted to you. Will you come back and help us again tomorrow?' WHERE entry=12372;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I don\'t want to be here anymore.  The worgen-men are mean.' WHERE entry=12411;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Wow! These sure are good horses! I think the Cap\'n will be real pleased with our work.' WHERE entry=12414;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It is a disgusting task, but I thank you dearly for doing it.$B$BThe Scourge cannot be permitted to push any further towards Wyrmrest or we are sure to lose it.' WHERE entry=12416;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='In the earth, my brothers can grant life anew. You have saved them from a fate far worse than death.$B$BI don\'t know a word in your tongue that could express how much this means to my kind. Thank you, $R.' WHERE entry=12417;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Dahlia... they turned her?$B$BDahlia has been loyal to us for a very long time... if they can corrupt a being of her devotion, it does not bode well for the rest of the young races. Thank you for freeing her. I hope she has found some peace.$B$BYou have honored us with your selfless assistance today, $R. I will send word to the council of what your kind have accomplished here. Go with our blessing.' WHERE entry=12418;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Dahlia was taken by the Scourge? This is a sad day for all of us.$B$BI will look to finding a new keeper once the shrine is retaken. Thank you for your efforts... the Ruby Dragonshrine is a sacred place to us, and the sacrifices your kind have made will not be easily forgotten.$B$BIt is good to know there are still heroes such as you - I will call upon you one day. Until that day comes, may your adventures be fruitful.' WHERE entry=12419;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Your paperwork looks to be in order.  Welcome to the club, $N!$B$BYou can expect to get our mail at the start of every month.  If you like what you got, stop by and we can sell you some more.  This is the club that keeps on giving.' WHERE entry=12420;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='There is strength in numbers, $N.  Being part of the "Brew of the Month" club means knowing you and your brethren will always have access to the best brew.$B$BBring your "Brew of the Month" club membership form to Ray\'ma in the Darkbriar Lodge in Orgrimmar\'s Valley of Spirits.',objectives_loc4='Bring the "Brew of the Month" club membership form to Ray\'ma in the Darkbriar Lodge in Orgrimmar\'s Valley of Spirits.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So you be joinin\' our ranks, $N?  We treat ya nice here.  You only get the best when you part of dis club!$B$BWe be sendin\' out brew to you at da start of every month.  If you like what you got, and you be wantin\' more, head back over here.  We make sure you get more of da brew you like.' WHERE entry=12421;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hah! Is this some sort of joke?$B$BI barely have any use for books I can actually understand.' WHERE entry=12423;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='This book is written in the pig-tongue the humans use.  It needs to be burned immediately.$B$BHand it to my sister Gorgonna and do not waste my time.',objectives_loc4='Bring Mikhail\'s Journal to Gorgonna in Conquest Hold.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Could it be? The man who wrote this journal feared for his daughters\' lives so he sent them away from Silverbrook.$B$BWe just captured an outcast in the outskirts of town about the same age as the eldest daughter.$B$BListen, $N. There\'s more happening here than meets the eye... we can\'t just burn this diary.' WHERE entry=12424;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='This trapper business has the potential to be more important than we\'ve accounted for.$B$BIf they\'re not with the Alliance, there\'s a good chance they\'re with the Scourge, which could mean trouble.$B$BOur previous efforts might\'ve paid off, though.  We spotted our former captive meeting with a fortune teller of some sort before we lost track of her.$B$BI\'m almost certain now that she will take us to their leader if we can find her again.  Find Ruuna the Blind and see what you can find out.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You seek knowledge beyond your reach so you\'ve come to me.  I must warn you, stranger, the answers I provide might not be to your liking.' WHERE entry=12425;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ha hah! What a ride, eh $C?$B$BIf we can\'t control the resources here, then no one can!$B$BWhen will those puny Alliance pests realize that they are no match for the might of the Horde?' WHERE entry=12432;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ahh yes. That\'ll save me hours.$B$BTake this for your trouble, friend. And keep an eye out for more element 115. I\'ll take all you can find.' WHERE entry=12433;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You must be $N. The queen informed me that you would be coming.$B$BIf you are willing, we are in great need of your assistance.' WHERE entry=12435;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Nice job, $N. These will feed two or three grunts each. Not bad.' WHERE entry=12436;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good to see that you survived that impact. Quite the explosion!$B$BWe can\'t afford for the Horde to make off with all that lumber.$B$BWell done, $C.' WHERE entry=12437;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. I will notify Illusia that a hero has heard her call for help and risen to meet the challenge! Here is your reward.' WHERE entry=12438;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We definitely don\'t want another sundering, friend. I\'ll do all that I can to help you on your mission.' WHERE entry=12439;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Speak with the Image of Archmage Modera at Stars\' Rest in western Dragonblight.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Vas heard my distress call then, eh? Not a moment too soon, friend.' WHERE entry=12440;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Outstanding work, $N! I will notify Drolfy that a hero did rise to meet his challenge and that the cruel Bloodpaw is no more!' WHERE entry=12441;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Posted by: Highlord Leoric Von Zeldig$B$BUpon the northeastern path from Wintergarde a battalion of 7th Legion were ambushed and slain by Onslaught Commander Iustus and an army of mindless Scarlet Onslaught zealots. Such cold and calculated actions must be met with force!$B$BWintergarde demands justice! Seek out Onslaught Commander Iustus at Onslaught Base Camp to the northeast and end his miserable existence.$B$BI will hand out the reward for this bounty to any who would dare take up the task!
',objectives_loc4='Kill Onslaught Commander Iustus and return to Highlord Leoric Von Zeldig at Wintergarde Keep in Dragonblight to collect your reward.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='At least for now the Scarlet Onslaught suffers a setback in their nefarious plans. You have done Wintergarde a great service, $N.
' WHERE entry=12442;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ahh yes. That\'ll save me hours.$B$BTake this for your trouble, friend. And keep an eye out for more element 115. I\'ll take all you can find.' WHERE entry=12443;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Nice work, $N.  We could use a few more folks like you up here.  We could really show the Horde not to mess with us.' WHERE entry=12444;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m trying to decide at which I\'m more surprised... that you actually came to the aid of a Black Dragon or that you\'re still in one piece after speaking with Nalice.$B$BHer words drip venom, but I suppose Wyrmrest can keep even our kind in check sometimes.$B$BOr perhaps it\'s just the armies of the red dragonflight that are massed around her.' WHERE entry=12447;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It is a disgusting task, but I thank you for doing it.$B$BThe Scourge cannot be permitted to push any further out of the shrine lest all of these lands be overrun.' WHERE entry=12448;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I have another task that needs attention. I have brothers who are falling in the battle overhead and if we do not act quickly, they will only bolster the emberwyrm ranks.$B$BGet into the shrine through the pass in the south... the Scourge presence should be lighter there.$B$BSearch the shrine for ruby acorns that have fallen from the tree and plant them near the bodies of my fallen brood. Through this, they can give new life... a proud fate for any of my kind.',objectives_loc4='Enter the Ruby Dragonshrine through the southern pass and search for Ruby Acorns.  Use the Ruby Acorns on the fallen red dragons to return their bodies to the earth.  Return to Vargastrasz once the task is complete.',offerrewardtext_loc4='In the earth, my brothers can grant life anew. You have saved them from a fate far worse than death.$B$BI don\'t know a word in your tongue that could express how much this means to my kind. Thank you, $R.' WHERE entry=12449;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Enter the Ruby Dragonshrine through the southern pass, then kill 6 Frigid Necromancers and eliminate the source of the corruption under the shrine. Return to Vargastrasz once the task is complete.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Dahlia... they turned her?$B$BDahlia has been loyal to us for a very long time... if they can corrupt a being of her devotion, it does not bode well for the rest of the young races. Thank you for freeing her. I hope she has found some peace.$B$BYou have honored us with your selfless assistance today, $R. Perhaps not all of the Horde bear the black hearts of their ancestors.  I will send word to the council of what your kind have accomplished here.' WHERE entry=12450;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Do not regret the part that you played in the cycle of life. Birth, death, and rebirth are all part of the natural order.' WHERE entry=12454;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Just in time! Some of my soldiers got a little overzealous and decided to wade into the crypts directly to the east and west of us. Needless to say, they were quickly overwhelmed by those mindless ghouls. We need to rescue the survivors!' WHERE entry=12455;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Do not weep for Alystros. He has dedicated his eternal life to the defense of the Emerald Dragonshrine and will be reborn.$B$BHopefully when he returns to us, he will not be gripped with the confusion of the Emerald Nightmare that seems to have taken hold of The Dreamer.' WHERE entry=12456;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='$N, I haven\'t seen heroics like that since Silithus!$B$BI\'ll be sure that each and every one of those soldiers puts in a recommendation to Lord Fordragon that you be promoted!$B$BNow, on to more pressing matters. We\'ve gotten reports back from our scouts that Thel\'zan is close.
' WHERE entry=12457;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Even now I can feel the pulse of nature from within these seeds.$B$BWe must put them to good use!' WHERE entry=12458;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent. Just as I suspected all along. I shall have to attempt to contact Ysera and see if she approves.$B$BIf she can be coaxed from her nightmare, of course.$B$BThank you, $N. You have been indispensable.' WHERE entry=12459;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ambassador Lauriel sent you?$B$BIf you talk to her again, please let her know that we are very appreciative of her aid. We are fighting battles on far too many fronts.' WHERE entry=12460;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ambassador Golluck sent you?$B$BIf you talk to him again, please let him know that we are very appreciative of his aid. We are fighting battles on far too many fronts.' WHERE entry=12461;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Yord "Calamity" Icebeard at the Wintergarde Mausoleum in Dragonblight wants you to kill Necrolord X\'avius, Necrolord Horus, and 15 Naxxramas Scourge.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='That oughta buy Ambo a little bit of time to get things situated.' WHERE entry=12462;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='There\'s been talk of a tunnel dug by Scourge that connects the embalming chambers of the mausoleum with the large crypts, now unearthed by Thel\'zan and his minions. I recently sent my best rogue, Plunderbeard, in search of answers, but have yet to hear back from him. If I were a betting man I\'d wager that he\'s a goner.$B$BI want you to go down those steps and head straight through the embalming chamber and look for Plunderbeard. Dead or alive, he\'ll have answers.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<You discover a journal on Plunderbeard\'s corpse.>$B$BEntry One:$B$BThey drag corpses through the tunnel to the embalming room for experimentation. There is an endless supply in this mausoleum. Whatever cannot be reanimated is turned into a bone construct of one kind or another.$B$BEntry Two:$B$BI fear that this lich, Thel\'zan, hides a dark secret. Who is he? Was he once... one of us?$B$BEntry Three: I have discovered the location of the lich\'s phylactery. It is...$B$B<The rest of the pages are torn out.>' WHERE entry=12463;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='An unfortunate, but necessary action that we had to take in dealing with Abbendis. In another lifetime, I think I could have imagined fighting side-by-side with her.$B$B<The commander\'s voice trails off as he reflects a moment before proceeding.>$B$BI\'m a little concerned about this grand admiral you describe. Barean Westwind you say? I can\'t believe that he\'s still alive. He must be ancient. We\'ll have to deal with him later, however.$B$BIn the meantime, I think you\'ve earned a reward and a little R & R.' WHERE entry=12464;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Ambo reads through the recovered journal pages.>$B$BThere\'s some good news and there\'s some bad news. Which do you want first?$B$BAh hell, why give you a choice? The good news is that if we can get Thel\'zan\'s phylactery, we can destroy him. The bad news is that the phylactery is on a rather large frostwyrm.' WHERE entry=12465;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Now you know why they call this the Dragon Wastes. Bones of the beasts are strewn about as far as the eye can see.$B$BWe\'ve probably taken down a dozen or more frostwyrms and there\'s still no end in sight. The Scourge\'s got fuel for ten-thousand more what with all the bones laying about.$B$B<Tyralion clears his throat.>$B$BI don\'t mean to bore you with the details, hero. We\'ve got the wyrm you\'re looking for locked in our sights.' WHERE entry=12466;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Recover Thel\'zan\'s Phylactery from Icestorm and return it to High Commander Halford Wyrmbane at Wintergarde Keep.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='We\'ve lost so many good soldiers to that monster, Thel\'zan. I wish I could be there to see you crush his phylactery in front of him and end his existence.' WHERE entry=12467;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So Krenna sent you to me?  She must\'ve not liked you very much, but then again who does she like?$B$BCracking this vrykul outpost is going to be a tough, tough job.' WHERE entry=12468;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hah! We lost another one, eh? Those harpies are becoming a real nuisance.$B$BNo matter! There\'s work to be done. Lend a hand around here, will ya?' WHERE entry=12469;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You saw Nozdormu? That doesn\'t make any sense.$B$B<Chromie thinks a moment about what you\'ve said.>$B$BActually, that\'s great news! We had no idea of where or when the Lord of Time had gone to. We just knew that he had disappeared to deal with very important matters.$B$BSo, even though the leader of the Infinite Dragonflight wasn\'t revealed, you\'ve discovered that Nozdormu is alive and well, and fighting back against them!$B$BThank you, $N. I\'ll be seeing you soon!' WHERE entry=12470;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I thank you, $N.  You\'ve shown a great deal of goodwill towards my clan.' WHERE entry=12471;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='When you\'re ready I\'ll place the phylactery out in front of the gateway and call forth Thel\'zan.' WHERE entry=12472;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Wintergarde is saved because of you, $N. To think that one woman could so swiftly turn the tides of battle is hard for most to comprehend; yet here we are - victorious! You have managed to restore the faith of these people and earned the respect of your commanding officers.$B$B<Halford salutes.>$B$BLord Fordragon has returned to Angrathar to prepare our forces for the destruction of the Wrathgate and has requested that you join him! I couldn\'t recommend a better soldier for the job, $N.' WHERE entry=12473;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Venture to Fordragon Hold in Dragonblight and speak with Highlord Bolvar Fordragon.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='This commendation is only given to those that have gone above and beyond the call of duty in the name of the Alliance. I could count the number of times I\'ve handed this one out on one hand, $N, and never has anyone been more deserving than you! Congratulations!$B$BNow, let us look upon the Wrathgate. Does it look familiar? It should. That strange ore you found at the Wintergarde Mine is exactly what the Wrathgate is made from. We will find its weakness and expose it for all to see! First, though...' WHERE entry=12474;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A cave? Could it be? There can be no other correlation!' WHERE entry=12475;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='To the northeast of Wintergarde Keep is a newly built encampment, set up by the Scarlet Crusade - or rather - the Scarlet Onslaught as they now call themselves. While we are unsure as to why they are in Northrend, they are certainly no less dangerous than they were before. As of last night the Scarlet Onslaught has killed twelve of our soldiers. They must be taught a lesson, $N.$B$BGo to Onslaught Base Camp and thin them out. $B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Hopefully the message is now clear to the Onslaught. I hope it was enough of a beating to make them doubt their affiliations.
' WHERE entry=12476;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Halford reads the journal.>$B$BAbbendis has gone off the deep end. The Light speaks to her now?$B$BDespite the inane ramblings, this journal gives us a never before seen look into the mind of the Scarlet zealots. This was a great find, $N. Lord Fordragon will be pleased.' WHERE entry=12477;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Muradin lives? Could it be? I must nofity King Bronzebeard at once!$B$BI need to consult the orb. There must be more information - somewhere!
' WHERE entry=12478;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Onwards to Northrend!',objectives_loc4='Speak to the Alliance Recruiter inside Valiance Keep in Borean Tundra or the one at Vengeance Landing in Howling Fjord.' WHERE entry=12479;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Onwards to Northrend!',objectives_loc4='Speak to the Horde Recruiter inside Warsong Hold in Borean Tundra or Vengeance Landing in Howling Fjord.' WHERE entry=12480;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work, $N. When our forces from Vengeance Landing arrive, we\'ll be able to take care of any vrykul that are left.' WHERE entry=12482;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh, mon - shimmercap stew! I can almost taste it already....' WHERE entry=12483;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Nothin\' better than watchin\' them shcourge burn... <hic>.$B$BWrote a little shong about it. Wanna hear it? Here goes....' WHERE entry=12484;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The mystic knows? You say he felt that something horrible happened to Farseer Grimwalker?$B$BIt is as I feared!' WHERE entry=12486;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Who are you?$B$BTell me why I shouldn\'t split you in two where you stand!' WHERE entry=12487;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You were sent from Agmar\'s Hammer? It\'s about time!$B$BNo, the help is not for me. I simply have no one else to spare, but you\'ll do.' WHERE entry=12488;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hah! It\'s not often you run into a complete stranger in the middle of the jungle.$B$BYou one those druid lackeys sent to "stop me and my evil ways?" Yeah, good luck with that one!$B$B<Hemet lets out a hearty laugh and pats his gun.>$B$BDidn\'t think so! You\'re more than welcome to join us in the hunt, soon as we\'ve dealt with those Venture Company dogs. There\'ll be plenty to go around.' WHERE entry=12489;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have come seeking my council, mortal. This I know, but do you know what it is that you face?$B$B<Alexstrasza points northward.>$B$BNorth of here are the dying grounds of Galakrond - progenitor of dragonkind. It is from Galakrond that the Titans created the Aspects. Imagine, then, the power of Galakrond. His size alone was greater than all of the Aspects combined! Now attempt to understand what the Scourge do in the Great Dragonblight.$B$BFrost wyrms, mortal, should be the least of your concerns.' WHERE entry=12495;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Though I know you hunger to destroy the Scourge that stand before us at the Wrath Gate, we must first deal with the threat that looms overhead. Until the strafing assaults of the frost wyrms are halted, we cannot move forward.$B$BBut before we assault the dying grounds of dragons, we must first be granted permission. Venture now to the hallowed halls of dragonkind: Wyrmrest Temple. Once there, seek out Queen Alexstrasza.$B$BRide now, $N! Southeast, to Wyrmrest!',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have come seeking my council, mortal. This I know, but do you know what it is that you face?$B$B<Alexstrasza points northward.>$B$BNorth of here are the dying grounds of Galakrond - progenitor of dragonkind. It is from Galakrond that the Titans created the Aspects. Imagine, then, the power of Galakrond. His size alone was greater than all of the Aspects combined! Now attempt to understand what the Scourge do in the Great Dragonblight.$B$BFrost wyrms, mortal, should be the least of your concerns.' WHERE entry=12496;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The bravery of mortals never fails to astound me. Death affixes its cold stare upon you and in return you rise to challenge its assertion! It is why your kind is so loved... and so hated.$B$BEven though the Red Dragonflight is entrenched in a war with Malygos, there is something that we can do to help.' WHERE entry=12497;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I knew that you would return, $N. You have served the Wyrmrest Accord and saved your people from certain death. Let it be known to all and let it be recorded for posterity!' WHERE entry=12498;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='With Antiok slain and the scythe in our possession, the frost wyrm assaults upon your forces at Angrathar will halt. The wyrms that remain in the Dragonblight will be hunted and destroyed, their bones returning to the earth.$B$BThe time to make your final stand is now, $N. Return to Fordragon Hold and notify Highlord Fordragon.$B',objectives_loc4='Speak with Highlord Bolvar Fordragon at Fordragon Hold and tell him of your victory over the Scourge.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Know this: all that you have done has led to this moment. Without your efforts, we would have been finished! Now, stand guard as I take to the field and end this!' WHERE entry=12499;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='With Antiok slain and the scythe in our possession, the frost wyrm assaults upon your forces at Angrathar will halt. The wyrms that remain in the Dragonblight will be hunted and destroyed, their bones returning to the earth.$B$BThe time to make your final stand is now, $N. Return to the Kor\'kron Vanguard and notify Saurfang the Younger.',objectives_loc4='Speak with Saurfang the Younger at the Kor\'kron Vangaurd and tell him of your victory over the Scourge.',offerrewardtext_loc4='My father was right about you, $N. Everything that he said has come to pass - only one final duty remains unfulfilled. I will now lead the Kor\'kron to the front line. The time to end this war is at hand. The Lich King\'s tyranny ends today!$B$BTake my post now, $N, and stand guard over our forces.' WHERE entry=12500;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, $N, at least you\'ve made it back in one piece. I suppose that\'s worth something....' WHERE entry=12501;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Captain Grondel\'s Task',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Alchemist Finklestein\'s\'s Task' WHERE entry=12501;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Your assistance in this matter is greatly appreciated. Were it not for your efforts, we would have difficulty in holding the unliving back from our steps.' WHERE entry=12503;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='<The sergeant quickly reads through the orders you\'ve handed him, a frown coming over his face.>$B$BLook, $G lad : lass;, I\'d love to just up and leave, but take a look out there. All of my people are fighting.$B$BTell you what, you\'ve come this far, you think you\'re up to doing me a small favor? Head out there and round up my soldiers?$B$BTell \'em that the sergeant orders them to report back immediately. Lend them a hand if you will.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Alright then. We\'ll collect up the rest and head back to the stand.$B$BIt\'s a shame that we have to leave so soon. Doesn\'t quite feel like the job\'s done here, and quite frankly, I get the feeling that prophet in front of the altar is going to be big trouble!' WHERE entry=12504;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The dwarf sergeant warily eyes the orders in your hand.>$B$BAre those new orders for me, $Gmister:lady;?' WHERE entry=12505;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Dead?$B$B<The hexxer\'s spirit is visibly lowered at the news you bring.>$B$BThey\'ve killed Sseratus and drunk deeply of his mojo; the prophet especially!$B$BWe must figure out a way to put an end to him before he drinks too much more!' WHERE entry=12506;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'s the mojo of the wild gods, $C!$B$BThis is not good!' WHERE entry=12507;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thanks, $C. I\'d have hated to leave without accomplishing what we came out here for in the first place.' WHERE entry=12508;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Troll Patrol: Intestinal Fortitude',objectives_loc4='Captain Rupert in Drak\'Sotra wants you to restore courage to the cowering Crusade Recruits.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $C. And not a moment too soon. I\'ve received word that a counter-attack is imminent.$B$BYou should be on your way. The next post is to the northeast, near the coliseum. Captain Grondel should be waiting for you there.' WHERE entry=12509;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent. When combined with the mojo, these fluids will dilute the effectiveness of the mojo without completely eliminating it.$B$BNow, one more thing.' WHERE entry=12510;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Report to Lieutenant Dumont at Amberpine Lodge in western Grizzly Hills.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='You were almost shot down, eh? Savage monsters - those Horde.$B$BPayback will come for what they\'ve done. You can count on at least that much, $C.$B$BNow, it\'s time to put you to work.' WHERE entry=12511;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Saved them all, did you? Outstanding!$B$BMaybe you\'d consider sticking around the post here? We could sure use someone like you....' WHERE entry=12512;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='My... my hat! But... how did you...?$B$BWell... no matter. So, now you know my secret. I WAS beaten... once. Here: take this hat, in return for mine. You\'ve earned it.' WHERE entry=12513;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The hexxer nods his approval.>$B$BHand that fungus over and I\'ll mix it up with the mojo and elemental lord fluids.' WHERE entry=12514;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='My... my hat! But... how did you...?$B$BWell... no matter. So, now you know my secret. I WAS beaten... once. Here: take this hat, in return for mine. You\'ve earned it.' WHERE entry=12515;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Amazing! You\'ve saved your people and the rest of Northrend from his madness.$B$BUnfortunately there\'s more of this insanity occurring up in the higher tiers of Zul\'Drak.' WHERE entry=12516;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Your skill with the quill is already starting to manifest, young scribe. The tarot cards are of great interest to the Darkmoon Faire, so do not hesitate to call upon us if you manage to create more. We are not without our own skilled tradesmen, so please allow us to offer something in trade for the cards.' WHERE entry=12517;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Your skill is most impressive! The tarot cards are of great interest to the Darkmoon Faire, so do not hesitate to call upon us if you manage to create more. We are not without our own skilled tradesmen, so please allow us to offer something in trade for the cards.' WHERE entry=12518;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, well, well, it looks like you\'ve survived the rhinos, after all, and in pretty good shape if I do say so myself. But there\'s more to rhino hunting than just staring down the beast as it charges you and hoping your aim is true. No, you\'ll need more than that to take on the rhino patriarch that\'s rumored to dwell in the jungle.' WHERE entry=12520;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Aye, Hemet\'s here. He\'s at the camp, just go northwest toward the river and you\'ll soon see it. And for the love of the Light, $G lad:lass;, have him send someone to cut me down!' WHERE entry=12521;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='There... just set it down there. Be careful! If you ruin this one, we\'re in big trouble. Now, let\'s see what I can do.' WHERE entry=12522;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='With a little work, these should suffice. My poor flying machine might end up looking more like a Venture Company shredder, though. Poor girl will have to wait until we get back to Dalaran to be restored to her rightful form.' WHERE entry=12523;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That should hamper their operations, but I worry that the foreman will try to bring in more workers. We have to complete the job while we can.' WHERE entry=12524;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What a relief to hear that the Venture Company will trouble us no more. You have my thanks, and that of Hemet for dealing with this problem. A game hunter cannot, in good conscience, lift $Ghis:her; weapon against another person.' WHERE entry=12525;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What brings you to Rahm\'s shrine?' WHERE entry=12526;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh, most excellent! Thank you. The crystals appear to be in fine condition!$B$BI have no doubt that Pestlepot put you up to doing his chores for him. Nevertheless, your assistance in this matter is greatly appreciated!' WHERE entry=12527;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You the new slave?$B$BGood. We running out.' WHERE entry=12528;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Goregek show silly $R slave how it done.' WHERE entry=12529;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Goregek take you to kill big mom of hardknuckles, eh? You lucky!$B$BDumb softknuckles squeal good!$B$B<Rakjak squeals loudly and breaks out laughing.>' WHERE entry=12530;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You kill Serfex? I bet you follow mighty wolvar that kill Serfex and take claw.$B$BMy claw now.' WHERE entry=12531;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good! I was worried about foodstuffs. I already pretty hungry.$B$BThank you, $R.' WHERE entry=12532;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We kill many many wasps.$B$BRakjak don\'t think they run out.' WHERE entry=12533;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You killed queen wasp! You stronger than Rakjak thought.$B$BMaybe wasps go away now and stop attacking Frenzyheart hunters.' WHERE entry=12534;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good $R! Okay, all ready.' WHERE entry=12535;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We here! Must work fast.$B$BWatch out for big-tongues.' WHERE entry=12536;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It work so good!$B$BYou see lightning smash that oracle guy? So good!$B$B<Zepik rubs his hands together and chuckles maniacally.>' WHERE entry=12537;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I stab those big-tongues good.$B$BYou did okay I guess.$B$BNo, I just kidding! You good hunter. I glad to hunt with you.' WHERE entry=12538;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Blown up by lightning?$B$B<Rakjak breaks out laughing for a moment.>$B$BYou good hunter. Rakjak like you. Maybe one day you can be honorary Frenzyheart!$B$BOnly maybe though!' WHERE entry=12539;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Locate an Injured Rainspeaker Oracle for High-Shaman Rakjak at Frenzyheart Hill.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='No kill me please! We was just looking for fish. We not want to die.' WHERE entry=12540;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Report to Crusader Valus at Light\'s Trust in Dragonblight.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Mere footsteps from here lies the Drakkari empire.$B$B<Valus points east.>$B$BFor thousands of years the Drakkari remained isolated, preferring to keep within the boundaries of their sprawling temple cities and ziggurats. It was surprising then, to come upon this wreckage. Further up, beyond the foreboding stairs leading into Zul\'Drak, Drak\'Tharon Keep lies in ruin. The entire first tier of Zul\'Drak, destroyed...$B$BWhy has the Scourge waited until now to attack?' WHERE entry=12542;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The oracle inspects the fangs.>$B$BWe approve! Bones of Nozronn will speak to $N!' WHERE entry=12543;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Hemet listens as you describe what you learned.>$B$BWay to go, $Glad:lass;. No dead rhino tells Hemet Nesingwary where and what he can hunt. We\'ll show that heap o\' bones.' WHERE entry=12544;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='As you can see, the Scourge war machine presses onward, yet the armies of the Horde and the Alliance remain divided, making for easy prey. It is for this reason that we must remain united.$B$B<Valus is lost in contemplation for a moment.>$B$BThe Argent Crusade has use for a $G man:woman; like you. Perhaps you would be interested in joining our cause? To battle and die at the side of the Ashbringer?' WHERE entry=12545;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I am grateful for your help, $N. It is my duty to watch over these lands and all life that dwells on them.$B$BThanks to you, that life will continue to thrive while the forces of death wage in the bordering regions.$B$BYour actions will not be forgotten.' WHERE entry=12546;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<You hear the rumbling sound of stone grinding as The Etymidian\'s limbs come to life.>$B$BI am needed somewhere?' WHERE entry=12547;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<As you read the engravings on this stone colossus, you realize that this is the weapon that Freya spoke of. This is the Etymidian.>' WHERE entry=12548;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, you\'ve proven yourself a capable hunter, but how are you as a tracker?' WHERE entry=12549;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I think you may have found the proof we need for this Shango. And I think I have an idea as to where we can find him.' WHERE entry=12550;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Impressive, $C. Are you certain you\'re not a member of the expedition?$B$BNo, I\'m certain of it. There would\'ve been a crash joke in there somewhere.' WHERE entry=12551;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s not enough!$B$B<The sergeant\'s voice cracks as he mourns the corruption of his fallen comrades.>$B$BWe must do more to show respect for the memories of those men!' WHERE entry=12552;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Those\'ll do!$B$BNow we\'re going to need some raw parts so that I can put the launching device together for you.' WHERE entry=12553;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='$N, gather at least one other person and head back down there!$B$BYou\'ll find the leader of Kolramas, Malas the Corrupter, gloating from atop the crashed necropolis.$B$BKill him and bring me his head!',offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re the hero of the hour, $N.$B$B<Moonshard kicks the head away from him.>$B$BYou deserve our deepest respect, and something more I think.' WHERE entry=12554;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yay! You\'re the best, $N!$B$BI wasn\'t looking forward to being sprayed with Scourge stuff, that\'s for sure! I guess it\'s going to be hard for those stupid nerubians to spread their evil now!$B$BHow about I give you a little something for saving my skin?' WHERE entry=12555;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Hemet examines the horn.>$B$BAn astounding trophy from an amazing animal! $N, I\'ve been hearing rumors of even bigger, more ferocious game in the northern reaches of the basin and I\'d like you to help us track it down.' WHERE entry=12556;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes, yes, that\'s a good start.$B$BShould I call upon you to help me with an actual recipe, you\'ll need to locate ingredients in a timely manner.$B$BKeep that in mind, $C.$B$BFarewell.' WHERE entry=12557;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Amberseed found',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Chilled Serpent Mucus found' WHERE entry=12557;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What an exquisite pelt from such a noble animal! It heartens me to see that the rumors about Shango were indeed true, $N. Your pursuit of the creature has been flawless. You are a true huntsman.' WHERE entry=12558;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='It is time then.  Let us activate the waygate.$B$BYou will find the first switch inside the Maker\'s Perch in the western edge of the basin.$B$BBeware, $N.  The titans used the perch to watch over their creations.  Many of their stone servants still guard the place.',objectives_loc4='The Avatar of Freya at the Rainspeaker Rapids wants you to go to the Maker\'s Perch and use the Activation Switch Gamma.',offerrewardtext_loc4='We\'re halfway there, $N. One more switch needs to be activated before we can retrieve the Etymidian.' WHERE entry=12559;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc4='You\'re back, little one. I was beginning to worry about your well-being.' WHERE entry=12559;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Debaar accepts the sandfern fronds from you and starts bending them around your body.>$B$BYes, this should work. Stand still! We\'ll make a bush of you yet.' WHERE entry=12560;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Very well, $R. I am satisfied that you\'re not one of the Lich King\'s minions... perhaps there is something you can do for us after all.' WHERE entry=12561;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work, $Gsir:ma\'am;!$B$BI\'ll see to it that the commander is apprised of your mission results.' WHERE entry=12562;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, $N, at least you\'ve made it back in one piece. I suppose that\'s worth something....' WHERE entry=12563;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Captain Grondel\'s Task',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Alchemist Finklestein\'s\'s Task' WHERE entry=12563;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Troll Patrol: Something for the Pain',offerrewardtext_loc4='Fine specimens, $N.$B$BOn behalf of my soldiers, I thank you for your efforts today.$B$BCaptain Rupert is likely the next stop on your patrol. He\'s stationed at the wall just east of here.' WHERE entry=12564;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<If Zim\'Abwa could move his face, Zim\'Abwa would make a vicious grin.>' WHERE entry=12565;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So, Nanik did find help then? Tell me, $N, how is it you made it here without him? None know this land better than the Taunka.' WHERE entry=12566;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<You sense Zim\'Abwa\'s approval. Somehow you know that Zim\'Abwa wants more tribute!>' WHERE entry=12567;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Debaar listens as you describe the failure of the disguise.>$B$BWhat do you mean, our plan didn\'t work as intended?$B$BWell, you did manage to get the kill, to your credit. Look at the size of this jaw! Hemet will be proud of our efforts. This crocolisk was truly a monster.' WHERE entry=12569;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Escort the Injured Rainspeaker Oracle to Rainspaker Canopy and speak to High-Oracle Soo-say.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You help us? You welcome then, $N.' WHERE entry=12570;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Snake gone?$B$BGood $R. We thank you.' WHERE entry=12571;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Shinies for the Great Rain Stone! Good! Good!$B$BWe offer these right away. Lafoo thought of this, yes? He a very smart Rainspeaker.' WHERE entry=12572;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So mean! We only be nice and they only be mean.$B$BThey keep messing with great stones... maybe they not know great stones are sacred.' WHERE entry=12573;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='<High-Oracle Soo-say stares at your forehead for a while before speaking.>$B$BSoo-gan ask for help. We think they might have been attacked by puppy-men again.$B$BWe sending you and Jaloot to help... follow west river up to Mistwhisper Refuge. Do what Soo-gan says... hit the puppy-men on the nose if they being mean, they don\'t like that.$B$B<High-Oracle Soo-say goes back to staring at your forehead as you leave.>',objectives_loc4='Travel to Mistwhisper Refuge and speak to Mistcaller Soo-gan.$B$BIf you lose Jaloot\'s Favorite Crystal, speak to High-Oracle Soo-say in Rainspeaker Canopy.',offerrewardtext_loc4='We think we seen you before. You visit Mistwhisper village sometime already?$B$BSoo-say said you good. Soo-say smart, so we trust you too.$B$B<Mistcaller Soo-gan offers an awkwardly large smile.>' WHERE entry=12574;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You did it! You strong and nice! Good friend of Mistwhispers!$B$B<Mistcaller Soo-gan lets loose a big toothy grin.>' WHERE entry=12575;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You squash good. Thank you for help.' WHERE entry=12576;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You\'re a good dryskin. Mistwhisper safe, treasure safe, and puppy-men sure to leave us alone now.$B$BYou go back to Rainspeaker Canopy and tell Soo-say you done good.',objectives_loc4='Return to Rainspeaker Canopy.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You back so soon!$B$BWent good then, yeah?' WHERE entry=12577;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Before you say anything, do not assume me as foolish as most of the Oracles you\'ve met. I\'ve been into the world a bit, I\'ve learned your language, and I\'m not easily duped.$B$BI knew the Mosswalkers were dead before we ever came, though I didn\'t know that the undead were behind it.$B$BThey are not supposed to be able to enter this land... the destruction of the Lifeblood Pillar must have allowed them in somehow. We must see to it that they leave.' WHERE entry=12578;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We might be too late for the shards to make a difference, but our options are somewhat limited.' WHERE entry=12579;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m very glad there were some to be saved... with luck, they\'ll make it back to Rainspeaker Canopy safely.' WHERE entry=12580;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Perhaps the crystals will ward off the undead gradually, but there is one more thing that must be done.$B$BWe need to find the leader of these undead and kill him to ensure there\'s no one to push the wretches back upon us. If my suspicions are correct, he will be somewhere inside the fallen pillar... the Sundered Shard.$B$BThe corpses being dragged there would suggest as much anyway.$B$BI\'ll place the shards and bring the news to Soo-say... you will need to find other help in the meantime.',objectives_loc4='Kill Artruis the Heartless.$B$BWhile securing the aid of friends is highly recommended, Moodle will not be able to accompany you on this task.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Inside Artruis\'s Phylactery you see what seems like an endless void... and you think you hear screaming in the distance from somewhere inside.>$B$B<As you\'re about to leave, you see an object floating in the void, just barely in reach.>' WHERE entry=12581;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I know you weren\'t traitor thing like others said. We hunt together... I know you better than all of them. Thank you for saving me.$B$BMay sound funny... I not a big fan of big-tongues... but even I feel little bad for big-tongue dying like that though... fair fight much better... they fight good enough they deserve fair fight.$B$BYou want to be friends with Frenzyheart again? I think I can convince them that you save me and got the big-tongues good. I no want you to make me look dumb though, so you sure?' WHERE entry=12582;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The specialist steps back a bit when presented with the parts.>$B$BEw, those things are totally gross!$B$BOkay, okay, hand them over and I\'ll see what I can do. I probably should have had you take them to a priest first for purification.' WHERE entry=12583;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Can you not feel the pure evil of the stuff?$B$BWe must use the expertise and magics at our disposal, combined with the power of the Holy Light, to pierce the veil of iniquity surrounding this tainted ore. We must determine its origins.$B$BQuickly, hand the saronite to me!' WHERE entry=12584;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Troll Patrol: Creature Comforts',offerrewardtext_loc4='Mighty kind of ya, $N. Mighty kind indeed.$B$BNow you\'ll be findin\' Cap\'n Arnath due west o\' here, just over the rise.' WHERE entry=12585;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Well, $N, you\'ve been an enormous asset to the expedition so far. Debaar, Buck, and I couldn\'t have have assembled such an amazing collection of trophies without you.$B$BBut, I hear there are even fiercer monsters in other parts of the basin. I\'ve sent a search party up north to get an idea of what other beasts await us.$B$BI\'d like you to meet up with them and see what they\'ve found. Head north, beyond Bittertide Lake and search for the encampment.',objectives_loc4='Talk to <x> at <x>.' WHERE entry=12586;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, $N, at least you\'ve made it back in one piece. I suppose that\'s worth something....' WHERE entry=12587;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Captain Grondel\'s Task',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Alchemist Finklestein\'s\'s Task' WHERE entry=12587;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re not a bad shot, but you\'ll get better with practice. How would you like to make a little wager?' WHERE entry=12589;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So, you\'ve come to concede already?$B$B<Drostan\'s jaw drops as you tell him you\'ve already made all your kills.>$B$BNo way! How in Azeroth did you do that? I just made my 58th. So close!$B$BBut fair\'s fair. I underestimated you, $N, but you\'ve earned this victory fair and square.' WHERE entry=12592;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Report to Instructor Razuvious in the Heart of Acherus.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have heard the call of the Lich King, death knight. Now is the time to answer your master.' WHERE entry=12593;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So old Hemet didn\'t forget about me, after all. I suppose he\'s going to want to participate in the hunt once we\'ve done all the hard work. Don\'t worry, there are plenty of drakes to go around. Hemet will get his wish.' WHERE entry=12595;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s about time you got your carcass back here! Thought we\'d lost ya to the Scourge - not that it would\'ve been a great loss....$B$BIf you\'re going to continue to serve the Crusade, you\'d best make a more impressive showing.$B$BTake note, $R! Your future patrols will be rewarded based on your timeliness.$B$BDismissed.' WHERE entry=12596;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Captain Grondel\'s Task',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Alchemist Finklestein\'s\'s Task' WHERE entry=12596;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Fine specimens, $N.$B$BOn behalf of my soldiers, I thank you for your efforts today.$B$BCaptain Rupert is likely the next stop on your patrol. He\'s stationed at the wall just east of here.' WHERE entry=12597;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We\'re not out of the woods by any means, but your efforts have helped to slow the enemy down.$B$BCaptain Grondel up in Drak\'Agal will likely have need of you.$B$BFarewell, $N.' WHERE entry=12598;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Mighty kind of ya, $N. Mighty kind indeed.$B$BNow you\'ll be findin\' ol\' Finklestein due west o\' here, just over the rise.' WHERE entry=12599;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I can hear the confidence in your words. Good, the experience will come in handy when we face the queen of the drakes.' WHERE entry=12603;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You made excellent time on that patrol. It appears that you may be of use to us after all.$B$BAs promised, here\'s a little something extra for your efforts.$B$BKeep up the good work, $N.$B$BDismissed.' WHERE entry=12604;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, well done. Plenty of little hatchlings for Zootfizzle over there!' WHERE entry=12605;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These nerubians have taken a heavy toll, $C.$B$BNevertheless, I am grateful for your efforts.' WHERE entry=12606;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Before you go off challenging Broodmother Slivina, Dorian thought it might be a good idea for you and Hemet to coordinate your efforts by riding into battle on the back of a mammoth.$B$BThe area around the camp is full of them. Just take this bridle and skip it over the head of a shattertusk mammoth. Be careful of the bulls, though. They won\'t tolerate the harness at all. Bring the mammoth back here when you\'ve found a suitable one.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Perfect! Now, all we need to do is get Hemet a stepladder...' WHERE entry=12607;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The living... willingly serve the Lich King?$B$BAll this time I\'ve been searching for the wrong enemy, $R. Let us make haste and uproot these cultists from these lands.' WHERE entry=12608;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These look to be excellent samples, $N.$B$BThank you for your assistance.' WHERE entry=12609;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work, $N.$B$BI thank you for your assistance.' WHERE entry=12610;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='The Avatar of Freya wants you defeat Thalgran Blightbringer by using Freya\'s Ward to reflect his Deathbolts back to him sevenfold.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You continue to prove yourself, $N. Perhaps I was too quick to judge you.$B$BI had assumed you were here with the poachers who were recently stranded in my lands, but perhaps you\'re ready to put that behind you.' WHERE entry=12611;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The corpse is badly burnt. There appear to be the remains of several powder kegs in the vicinity.>' WHERE entry=12612;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The Avatar of Freya wants you to head to the Makers\' Overlook in eastern Sholazar Basin and use the Activation Switch Theta.',objectives_loc4='The Avatar of Freya wants you to head to the Makers\' Overlook in eastern Sholazar Basin and use the Activation Switch Theta.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The waygate is active, $N.  It is time!' WHERE entry=12613;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, I had a whole speech prepared, but the old man himself has some words he wants to say to you.' WHERE entry=12614;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Zim\'Torga\'s thoughts pervade your own. She senses the offerings you are about give to her and is pleased.>$B$B<She conveys that you will be appropriately rewarded.>' WHERE entry=12615;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The information you report is dire indeed if the orders you saw are legitimate. We can only hope that his mission was stopped early enough to prevent the enemy from knowing too much about our strengths.$B$BThank you, $N. May you remain safe in these dark times.' WHERE entry=12616;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You speak the truth. The intruders at the camp were dealt with... but I\'m afraid it might have been too late.' WHERE entry=12617;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The Mother of Prosperity beams her approval down upon you.>' WHERE entry=12618;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. You have successfully created your first runebladed weapon. With it you will sow the seeds of chaos and destruction! In your wake will be a bloodied field of battle, littered with the corpses of all that would dare oppose the Scourge.' WHERE entry=12619;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Impressive. I wasn\'t expecting a mere mortal to prove as worthy an ally as you.$B$BI fear our efforts have not been sufficient, however. The Scourge shows no signs of stopping.' WHERE entry=12620;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc4='Have you taken care of the cultists, $N?' WHERE entry=12620;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='There is no turning back now. If you agree to help me, you will do so without hesitation.' WHERE entry=12621;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc4='We have little time. The Scourge is preparing for a final push.' WHERE entry=12621;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The scalper thinkin\' that you be his kind of $R!$B$BWhat\'s these candybars doin\' in here? What we do with this, mon?$B$BAhunae say that you can have them back!' WHERE entry=12622;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Greetings to you, $C. I am glad to hear that Ubungo found someone that he could trust.$B$BWelcome to Zim\'Torga.' WHERE entry=12623;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You did it!  You actually found it!$B$BI don\'t know... I don\'t know how to thank you!' WHERE entry=12624;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes, I can already feel the difference. Thank you.$B$BLet us see if we can make contact with the gods now.' WHERE entry=12627;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Purple Cauldron disturbed',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Red Cauldron disturbed' WHERE entry=12627;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Listen closely, little $R. Time is of the essence.' WHERE entry=12628;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Stefan sifts through the foul components.>$B$BWell, it\'s far from perfect, but it\'ll have to do.$B$BNow brace yourself, $C. This is where it gets good....' WHERE entry=12629;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You know, you remind me an awful lot of my Nass.$B$BMaybe it\'s just the nose...' WHERE entry=12630;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Take the Unliving Choker to Stefan at Ebon Watch.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I am indeed familiar with items such as this.$B$B<Stefan looks you in the eye.>$B$BIt would seem, $N, that you have been... chosen.' WHERE entry=12631;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $N. I will never forget what you have done.' WHERE entry=12632;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Take the Writhing Choker to Stefan in Ebon Watch.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I am indeed familiar with items such as this.$B$B<Stefan looks you in the eye.>$B$BIt would seem, $N, that you have been... chosen.' WHERE entry=12633;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, that\'s a better assortment than I would\'ve expected from this place. Now, for the important question: can we distill it into anything drinkable? We\'d better get started.' WHERE entry=12634;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Aw, prime specimens!$B$BYou can see there the divergence from the root symbology. Quite extraordinary.$B$BWhat a pity that the ice trolls are determined to bring about their own demise.$B$BDid you know, for instance, that the Drakkari were exiled from the rest of the troll nations for their extremely violent ways?$B$BIt\'s true! How did you think trolls ended up in such a harsh climate as this?' WHERE entry=12635;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Behold, Acherus, the grand citadel of death! It has no equal in this world! Not even the mighty Naxxramas could withstand a direct assault from the Ebon Hold. Looming above the face of the necropolis is the all-seeing eye of Acherus. From it the master is able to see great distances into the territories held by our enemies. What the eye sees, the Lich King sees, and now the time has come for you to peer through the eye! The Lich King has called for you, $N.$B$BGo now! Suffer well, $G brother:sister;...$B',objectives_loc4='Report to the Lich King in Ebon Hold.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The time to spill the blood of our enemies approaches. You must first learn what it is that you seek to destroy, before rushing headlong into battle. It is what separates a death knight from a mindless ghoul.$B$BI will grant you sight beyond sight, my champion. You will use the eye of Acherus to steal our enemies\' secrets.' WHERE entry=12636;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Now you\'ve observed the fate that was meant to befall you.$B$BAs I mentioned before, this was no coincidence. The creation of such a device is very involved, and the required resources would not be squandered on a random target.$B$BThe simple truth of the matter is this; You\'re wanted by the Scourge....' WHERE entry=12637;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Choker\'s Purpose Exposed' WHERE entry=12637;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Now you\'ve observed the fate that was meant to befall you.$B$BAs I mentioned before, this was no random act. The creation of such a device is very involved. You\'ve somehow caught the attention of the Scourge leadership.$B$BThe question is not how, why, or even who... but what will we do about it?' WHERE entry=12638;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Choker\'s Purpose Exposed' WHERE entry=12638;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $C. Those essences should be enough to fuel my casting for quite some time.' WHERE entry=12639;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ahunae hopin\' that Dagoda got all of the defenders she wantin\'. With those rifts sealed, it\'s not likely she\'ll be gettin\' any more.' WHERE entry=12640;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='They prepare for battle - as expected - but there is something else. I sense an old enemy. An enemy that I destroyed long ago...$B$BIt matters not. We will send the full might of the Scourge against them before they have a chance to evacuate their homes and put in place their defenses.' WHERE entry=12641;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Scarlet Hold Analyzed',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Chapel of the Crimson Flame Analyzed' WHERE entry=12641;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I am barely hanging on. You must work quickly or all will be lost.' WHERE entry=12642;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Stefan sifts through the foul components.>$B$BWell, it\'s far from perfect, but it\'ll have to do.$B$BNow brace yourself, $C. This is where it gets good....' WHERE entry=12643;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Grimbooze gives the cask a shake.>$B$BThere\'s something in here, but the million gold question is, can you drink it? Don\'t you go anywhere; you\'ll be responsible for overseeing the sampling of the product, too.' WHERE entry=12644;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Two out of three drinkers agree, eh? Not bad for a first try. Not bad at all. I suppose I\'ll have to whip up something else for Tamara by way of apology.$B$BNow... what should we call this creation?' WHERE entry=12645;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You did it.$B$BBut now there is one other thing that I need you to do.' WHERE entry=12646;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done what had to be done and honored me in the process.$B$BI give you my deepest thanks, $N. I only hope that you and Har\'koa will be able to help the others.' WHERE entry=12647;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So? How are you enjoying scourge life?$B$BBelieve me, it\'s not all it\'s cracked up to be....' WHERE entry=12648;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So? How are you enjoying scourge life?$B$BBelieve me, it\'s not all it\'s cracked up to be....' WHERE entry=12649;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Let me look at those.$B$B<The chronicler examines the artifacts that you have recovered.>$B$BHmph, I\'d say that we\'re lucky you liberated these when you did, $C.$B$BHow very interesting. This artifact here depicts the events of the Sundering. There was a time when Northrend was the far northern portion of Kalimdor.$B$BBut after the Sundering, the land broke off, eventually becoming Northrend.$B$BThis, of course, is why we see Drakkari in the southern continents as well as here.' WHERE entry=12650;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So, Hemet sent you? We were just about to let him know that we\'ve gotten things up and running here. Please forgive Marvin if he seems to be ignoring you, but he gets very absorbed in his work.' WHERE entry=12651;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Num num!' WHERE entry=12652;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The cat goddess howls in pain.>$B$BMy spirit cries out in grief at the loss of another friend. But fear not, he will return and his spirit will live on forever.' WHERE entry=12653;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You got it! Now all I have to do is make a trophy out of it. That\'ll be the hard part -- finding a way to preserve it so that Hemet doesn\'t have a good laugh at my expense.' WHERE entry=12654;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Zim\'Rhuk acknowledges the offerings you intend to place before him, though he knows that you took them from the corpses of others.>$B$B<If you give the offerings to him, he reluctantly agrees to grant you his blessing.>' WHERE entry=12655;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Zim\'Rhuk forces an image into your mind of one of his guardians squishing you beneath its foot. Perhaps you should attempt to appease Zim\'Rhuk with more offerings.>' WHERE entry=12656;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Listen well, death knight, for I give to you the words that will start a war. My final judgment has been passed: Death. To. All. None shall stand so boldly against the might of the Scourge without reprisal!$B$BAs you have served me well in your first task, so too shall you serve me in your next task. Take my judgment to Highlord Mograine at the command post of Acherus, found on the first floor. Tell him to begin the assault.$B$BAnd when the Crusade has been dealt with, we will finish off the Argent Dawn.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='The horns of war will soon echo across this land, waking the dead and calling forth the Scourge war machine. Woe unto those that would stand in our way!$B$BYou and your brethren will lead the charge, $N. When next I look upon the Scarlet lands, my sights will be obscured by the legions of Acherus. The march upon New Avalon begins now.' WHERE entry=12657;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh, these are very nice! I\'ve gotten so tired of robotic squirrels and chickens for company. It\'ll be wonderful to have a pet whose joints won\'t require oiling!' WHERE entry=12658;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Aw, me thinkin\' that too funny.$B$B$N is my kind of $R!$B$BYou still got my knife?' WHERE entry=12659;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I thank you, $R. You\'re proving to be a worthy ally.' WHERE entry=12660;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, now... I must admit I\'m more than a little surprised to see you, $N.$B$BTell me what you\'ve learned.' WHERE entry=12661;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='<Dagoda looks at Ahunae and sighs.>$B$BYou want to really deal with Heb\'Drakkar? Collecting scalps isn\'t going to get the job done. You have to take out their leader, Heb\'Jin.$B$BThe problem is, he\'s up on the bat rookery goading his forces on.$B$BBang his drum and I guarantee that he\'ll fly down. That\'s when you kill him.$B$BYou can take this net we got from one of his headhunters. Use it to trap his bat when he lands. That way you won\'t have to fight both of them.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='You did it!$B$B<Dagoda gives you a big kiss on the cheek.>$B$BYou have no idea how much of a relief that is to me! Defending against trolls on all sides is really putting a strain on us. Not to mention his incessant yelling.$B$BPlease, $N, take your pick of what we have to offer.' WHERE entry=12662;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So, now ya be seein\' what we be up against, mon.$B$BGo down, take some time ta learn da land, prepare some strategy. $B$BI\'ll be havin\' some tasks for ya soon.' WHERE entry=12663;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So, now ya be seein\' what we be up against, mon.$B$BI want ya ta go down, learn da land, mingle with yer bretheren. Prepare yourself...$B$BSoon, dere be much for ya to do. Don\'t ya be disappointin\' me!' WHERE entry=12664;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you for bringing my kitten back safely.$B$BDeep down I knew it. I wanted to deny it, but your eyes have revealed the truth.$B$BNevertheless, I sense something else. All is not as it seems.' WHERE entry=12665;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The leopard goddess looks saddened at the collection of holy symbols that you have brought before her.>$B$BThere was a time when these meant something. Let\'s see if we can put them to better use.' WHERE entry=12666;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='$R worm. Tell me why I should not annihilate you where you stand?' WHERE entry=12667;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Exquisite. Perhaps you will be of some use after all.' WHERE entry=12668;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Nice work, $N!$B$BDiluting those cauldrons will not only save lives, it will slow the growth of the Scourge in this region.$B$BNow come, tell me what you\'ve learned of Drakuru\'s strategy in Zul\'Drak.' WHERE entry=12669;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Do you smell it?$B$B<Valanar sniffs at the air.>$B$BFresh meat... The scent of Scarlet Crusader wafts through the air.$B$B<Valanar salivates.>$B$BApologies, death knight, I\'m sure you\'re not interested in my choice of fine cuisine. You are here to work! To lead the charge! Yes... I know. The Lich King has told me all that I need to know about you, $N.$B$BThe time for bloodshed is now.
' WHERE entry=12670;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You saved my life up there, $Gbuddy:lassy;. Nice flying!' WHERE entry=12671;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='They\'ll do. Likely I won\'t even need them.$B$BBut it was fun watching you run around at my command.' WHERE entry=12672;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Da crystals be pilin\' up like never before!$B$BYou keep up da good work, $N. I got more tasks for ya real soon.' WHERE entry=12673;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The terrible spirit before you lets loose a blood-chilling cackle.>$B$BThey had it coming. And I\'ll give them more of the same again and again and again....' WHERE entry=12674;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A portion of my spirit?$B$B<The snow leopard goddess pauses a moment to consider.>$B$BThat\'s quite an expensive gift considering that this is for revenge and I\'m already greatly weakened by the actions of my subduers.$B$BStill, I may know a way.' WHERE entry=12675;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent!$B$BYour undercover work has truly paid off, $N.$B$BNow let\'s have a look at that scepter....' WHERE entry=12676;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Fascinating!$B$BWe\'ll look into the properties of these crystals right away.$B$BNow tell me, $N, what is the latest with this Drakuru fellow?' WHERE entry=12677;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Do you feel it, $N? That sensation is raw power coursing through your body. Such a thing cannot exist for mortals.$B$BThe front lines are now dismantled. The geist will finish the job and prepare the grounds for Razuvious. We turn our attention now to more tactical targets.
' WHERE entry=12678;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, death knight! You feed the Scourge war machine with your deeds!$B$BAh yes, your reward - as promised.' WHERE entry=12679;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Now for the true test. Can you show mastery over an unbound charger and brutally overtake the thing that you desire most?' WHERE entry=12680;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Colvin looks admiringly at the talons you\'ve brought back.>$B$BThese will more than suffice. The gorlocs have a saying that the more gnarled the talon, the more power it holds. I\'m sure the archmage will get his money\'s worth from this expedition.' WHERE entry=12681;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Uncharted Territory (DEPRECATED)' WHERE entry=12682;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Wonderful! Here\'s your payment, as agreed. And, uh, a bit of advice: you might want to enjoy long, hot baths the next few days if that \'burning sensation\' persists.' WHERE entry=12683;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Very well. Let us see if this works....' WHERE entry=12684;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The witch doctor shakes his head in disbelief.>$B$BIt sounds like you barely escaped Quetz\'lun\'s underworld alive.$B$BI\'m glad that it\'s you out there. I don\'t know if I would have had the courage to deal with that situation!' WHERE entry=12685;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ya done good, $N. You be learnin\' faster than I had hoped.$B$BGo now, get ya some rest. Soon I be givin\' ya an even greater test!' WHERE entry=12686;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have succeeded where most initiates fail, $N. For that you will be rewarded handsomely.$B$B<Salanar bows.>' WHERE entry=12687;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you for freeing Helice and seeing to her safe return. We all started to get worried when she didn\'t return from her crystal hunting trip.' WHERE entry=12688;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hi! Really glad see you again!$B$BI knew we friends. I knew it! You good friend. Not just for us, but for all Oracles.$B$BI saw you bonk that puppy-man good! Undead thing said he your friend before? I not know that. You done with puppy-men though, yeah? Just Oracle friend now?$B$BI know you choose right! Thank you for saving us! Thank you, thank you!' WHERE entry=12689;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We done it, mon!$B$BI got da chieftains all caged up and you led my abominations to victory over their armies.$B$BIt be time ta celebrate, mon!' WHERE entry=12690;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The huge stone key turns with a deep grunt as the coffer lid opens up to reveal hidden treasure inside.' WHERE entry=12691;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It good to see you again. I knew you not a traitor, I glad Zepik prove me right.$B$BI hear you Lich Hunter now - that pretty good! You make Harkek proud.' WHERE entry=12692;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good to see you again! We worried when you not come back right away.$B$BJaloot beat you back - lot of energy in Jaloot, he pretty fast. He told me how you save him from lich thing. Moodle told me how you save mosswalkers too. You really nice.$B$BI hope you stay with us for while. Always something need doing.' WHERE entry=12695;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The professor sent you my way? All right.' WHERE entry=12696;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have fought hard to invade the realm of the harvester... Wait.$B$B<Gothik looks at his notes.>$B$BMy apologies, $R. Old habits die hard.$B$BValanar sent you, then? I trust you are somewhat competent.$B$BI do have a gift for the Scarlet dogs. One that is sure to speed up their work in the mines.' WHERE entry=12697;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='They now know that the mines are no longer safe. They will double their efforts in retreating, leaving their backs open to us!' WHERE entry=12698;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='There\'s one little problem we have to solve before we head out.  You see, I can\'t seem to find the keys to my flying machine.$B$BI\'ve looked pretty much everywhere for them... maybe you can give me a hand.  Only place I haven\'t looked yet is inside the lake.$B$BI\'ll even give you my very own air tank.  It\'s almost empty, but it\'s got a couple of hits left.',objectives_loc4='Look for Vic\'s Keys inside the lake at River\'s Heart.' WHERE entry=12699;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have served us well, death knight. Few of your brethren have survived our initial attack upon the Scarlet interlopers. You remain as one of the strongest.$B$B<Prince Valanar nods.>$B$BEast of us, past the Havenshire Mine, is the coast - called Light\'s Point by the Scarlet Crusade. A thousand soldiers stand between us and their ships. Insurmountable? Hardly the point...
' WHERE entry=12700;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The entire Scarlet fleet wiped out in a matter of minutes! I will receive a commendation from the Lich King for this! All that remains of the Scarlet Crusade now are the denizens of New Avalon.$B$BI\'ll set the fire starters and necromancers upon Havenshire immediately. You will carry my report to the Highlord!' WHERE entry=12701;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You good at this.$B$BMaybe someday we just dump Goregek in river so you not have to do this no more.' WHERE entry=12702;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You the great Lich Hunter, eh? Good to have such strong Frenzyheart ally for battle. Maybe you strong enough to call Kartak even.$B$BBig battle at Kartak\'s Hold to southwest.  Go kill spark big-tongues until you get good bit of Oracle Blood. Bring blood to altar in Kartak\'s Hold to call Kartak for delicious feast of big-tongue.$B$BKartak take your body if you worthy... with Kartak\'s powers, you slaughter more big-tongues than even best dreams.$B$BGo kill lots, hunter!',objectives_loc4='Bring a pure sample of Oracle Blood to the Altar of Kartak to summon Kartak. With the aid of Kartak\'s shared powers, slaughter 50 of the nearby Sparktouched Gorlocs for Shaman Jakjek in Kartak\'s Hold.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ritual went so easy for you!$B$BYou come back later for more killing someday, okay?' WHERE entry=12703;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So many good shinies! You good at this.$B$BCome back for more again later, yes?' WHERE entry=12704;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Soo-holu strong, huh? I very glad he accept you to share his body for fight.$B$BHe more trusting of people he met before, so maybe come back another time to help more, yes?' WHERE entry=12705;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Highlord Mograine reads over the report.>$B$BThe ENTIRE Scarlet fleet?$B$B<Highlord Mograine nods.>$B$BSuch power, $N... I have not seen such a display of domination in years... Since my father wielded...$B$B<Highlord Mograine shakes his head.>$B$BIt\'s not important...$B$BYes, your commendation, lest I forget.' WHERE entry=12706;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Score one for the victims, mon!' WHERE entry=12707;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That should make them think twice about making more of those things. I shudder to think what it would be like to have to fight an army of those things.$B$B<The element-tamer is thoughtful for a moment.>$B$BI guess it would be just like fighting the endless waves of the Scourge.' WHERE entry=12708;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Just look at all of that!$B$BSee here, $N. This piece you recovered vividly illustrates that the Drakkari became aware of the weakening of the land that the Scourge caused by their presence.$B$BThe warlord felt compelled to take the opportunity this presented. He pushed the prophets to kill their gods in an effort to control the power and fight back against the Lich King\'s forces.$B$BEither way they were doomed. They inadvertently chose to be the instrument of their own destruction!' WHERE entry=12709;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So, there ya have it, mon.$B$BWe be makin\' da ultimate scourge army ta serve da Lich King. He gunna be most pleased!$B$BYou keep da scepter, $N. You gunna be needin\' it ta command my army in battle....$B$BSoon!' WHERE entry=12710;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Atop the mailbox are several illegible letters and scrolls. Useless...$B$BPerhaps you should check inside?' WHERE entry=12711;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It might have been better if I hadn\'t asked you to bring it back here instead of heading directly to Gundrak.$B$BHowever, I think that it\'s best that you hear what else I have to say first.' WHERE entry=12712;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So, it is done.$B$BWe still have much to do, but our work here will be much more manageable thanks to your efforts.$B$BPlease accept this as a token of our gratitude.' WHERE entry=12713;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Havenshire is ours! A thousand corpses litter the ground, patiently awaiting rebirth. We strike now at our enemy with the awakened strength of the Scourge!$B$BThe ghouls have already begun their assault upon New Avalon. Our forces have moved in behind them and taken the Crypt of Remembrance.' WHERE entry=12714;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hail, death knight. I am the blood lord, Keleseth, ruler of the southeastern reaches of Northrend. The Lich King has sought to utilize my talents in ending this mortal affront to the Scourge. As with all things the Lich King asks of me, I am happy to oblige. Of course, a sea of endless souls to sate my thirst certainly sweetened the deal, don\'t you think?
' WHERE entry=12715;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Perfect! Now give me a moment to get things set up.' WHERE entry=12716;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The plague cauldron jumps to life when the skulls are placed inside.$B$BAfter a few seconds some vials of dark liquid float to the top.' WHERE entry=12717;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The plague cauldron jumps to life when the skulls are placed inside.$B$BAfter a few seconds, the plague cauldron grants you the dark and frothy splendor of Noth\'s Special Brew.' WHERE entry=12718;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The registry will tell us many things about the Scarlet insects.$B$B<Keleseth flips through the pages of the registry.>$B$BDeath rates, births, but most importantly, movement.$B$BLook here, $N, they have already sent three vessels abroad. Let me see here... Where are they headed?$B$B<Keleseth mutters something about latitude and longitude under his breath as he calculates the route.>$B$BWHAT? This is impossible. They sail to Northrend!$B$BBeside the coordinates are the words: "Crimson Dawn."' WHERE entry=12719;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='An awakening? What nonsense do you speak, $G boy:girl;! What kind of fool would deliver their people into the very heart of the frozen wastes? Perhaps, though, this courier holds the answer.' WHERE entry=12720;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='No!$B$BAnother god destroyed, its power stolen. And now the prophet of Akali has threatened us directly.$B$BWhen he comes, he will come for Har\'koa. We cannot allow him to take her power too.$B$BWe must consult the gods once more, $N. They will tell us what must be done.' WHERE entry=12721;
UPDATE locales_quest SET EndText_loc4='Akali unfettered from his chains.' WHERE entry=12721;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are quite effective with that blade, $N. Perhaps, Lich King permitting, you would be interested in becoming one of my minions? Stratholme is looking for a new mayor.' WHERE entry=12722;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I have sent Orbaz, Thassarian and Koltira behind enemy lines to search for the courier. They have set up a base of operations at the Scarlet Tavern, located at the southern end of New Avalon. The tavern is tucked away behind the two orchards, adjacent to the Chapel of the Crimson Flame. You are to make your way to the tavern and report to Orbaz Bloodbane. He will update you on their situation.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Looks like we\'ll let anyone into the dark order these days. When I was given the gift, things were different. Much different!$B$BAs to this courier...' WHERE entry=12723;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Orbaz flips through the schedule.>$B$BThese worthless cretins have been busy! Northern patrol routes, southern patrol routes, western patrol routes, eastern patrol routes, but nothing about their couriers\' routes. Wait a minute. What\'s this? It looks like a western patrol route, coming out of Western Plaguelands? This patrol will path through here today! I\'m going to need time to plan.' WHERE entry=12724;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You were foolish in coming after me. I failed. I should have been left for dead - now two of us might be killed.$B$B<Koltira shakes his head.>$B$BWe are death knights of the Scourge. This flies in the face of the dark brotherhood\'s covenants.$B$BThassarian, you blasted fool!' WHERE entry=12725;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I thank you, $N. The great tempest will look upon us favorably thanks to you.' WHERE entry=12726;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'ll feed this monster\'s head to the ghouls!$B$B<Thassarian tosses the head into the back room.>$B$BDid Koltira make it out?$B$B<Thassarian pauses.>$B$BI\'m certain he did. Those walls can\'t hold him.$B$BTime for some payback.' WHERE entry=12727;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent, this completes my report.$B$BI\'ll be sure to mention your kindness to the council, $N.' WHERE entry=12728;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The gods have spoken and we must heed their wisdom.$B$BGather friends to your side, $N. Take them north to Zim\'Rhuk to destroy guardians there until they yield the unblemished heart. Take them east to the Altar of Quetz\'lun and disrupt the altar wardens until you recover their gusty essence.$B$BDeliver both to Har\'koa and she will combine them into that which will compel late Akali\'s prophet to appear.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Your bravery seems boundless, $N.$B$BPlease hand me the heart and the essence, and I will fashion them into that which will compel the prophet to appear before you.' WHERE entry=12729;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You and your friends must take this instrument of convocation - of summoning - to Zol\'Heb just south of Gundrak.$B$BTherein you will find a circle of power. Use the convocation to force the prophet of Akali to appear.$B$BMy heart goes out to you, $N. We have been through much together, and you have done all that you can to not only save my life, but those of the other gods the Drakkari have destroyed.$B$BBut I fear this time we may not see each other again until the afterlife.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You did it! $N, you are the champion of Zul\'Drak!$B$BWe will never be able to repay the debt that we owe to you, but the Zandalari have given into my trust a number of objects they believe you might have an interest in.$B$BPlease, I want you to have a token of our appreciation, but hurry. I sense another issue of urgency!' WHERE entry=12730;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='One day, Rejek will be mighty warrior. Blood and skyfire will make Rejek strong. You see soon.$B$BRejek give you vial, you take to very top of Suntouched Pillar, far to west. Put waters there in vial.$B$BThen go to north edge of basin, to ledge north of Bonefields. You find and kill goretalon matriarch. Take heartblood.$B$BYou combine heartblood and water, bring to Rejek. Rejek drink, make strong.',objectives_loc4='Bring a vial of Suntouched Heartblood to Rejek at Frenzyheart Hill.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Rejek thanks you. Rejek drink, grow strong, always remember mighty $N\'s gift.' WHERE entry=12732;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Born of the Lich King\'s victory over Illidan Stormrage in the heart of the frozen wastes, Death\'s Challenge is a rite of passage that all death knights must undergo.$B$BSeek out other death knights of Acherus and challenge them to a duel. They must accept and fight until a victor emerges!$B$BGo now, $N! Victory for the Scourge! Glory to the Lich King!$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='To the victor goes the glory, death knight! Well done! The Lich King looks favorably upon you on this day.
' WHERE entry=12733;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Rejek just became youngest warrior in all of Frenzyheart tribe. Father gave Rejek a mighty sword to defeat Frenzyheart enemies, but old tradition say sword need to be blooded first. Older warrior usually do that. You do this honor for Rejek?$B$BTake blade, put in corpses of all Frenzyheart foes: wasps and hardknuckles to southwest, and the big-tongues. Maybe blood blade on Mistwhispers, far to northwest near Bittertide Lake.',objectives_loc4='Blood Rejek\'s Blade on the corpses of a Sapphire Hive Wasp, a Hardknuckle Charger, and 3 members of the Mistwhisper Tribe. You may blood the sword on either Mistwhisper Oracles or Mistwhisper Warriors. Return to Rejek at Frenzyheart Hill when your task is complete.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Rejek sees the stains of the blood of his enemies on the blade. Now Rejek has a mighty weapon for the mighty warrior he will be!' WHERE entry=12734;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Waters... cleansed. Yes. All is well.$B$BYou understand our way, $N.' WHERE entry=12735;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You see? I can tell you smarter already. And if not smarter... then... happier!' WHERE entry=12736;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Contemplation at Skyreach Pillar',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Contemplation at Suntouched Pillar' WHERE entry=12736;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You learn fast, $N. You learn that song well. Maybe next time I teach you different song.' WHERE entry=12737;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='They\'re only flesh and bone - no match for the Scourge.$B$BWe didn\'t find any of our brothers, but we did stumble upon something special.' WHERE entry=12738;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Felt good, didn\'t it? You\'re not one of them anymore, $N. You\'re Scourge. You\'re one of us. Forever...' WHERE entry=12739;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re a good man, $N. We\'re fortunate that you happened to stop by.$B$BStick around a while. I\'m sure that we have much that a capable $C such as yourself can do.' WHERE entry=12740;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Silly big-tongues think singing to the clouds give them power. Rejek show big-tongues how to get power by taking it!$B$BFar to northwest, there is large, flat area the big-tongues call \'Stormwright\'s Shelf.\' Rejek is sure you can only get there by flying like bird.$B$BOn this shelf, Rejek has heard of mighty forces of wind and water. Kill them for their badness, then take it to the big-tongue \'Shrine of the Tempest\' at shelf\'s western side. Rejek will await your return with ultimate power.',objectives_loc4='Gather 3 Essences of the Monsoon and 3 Essences of the Storm and take them to the Shrine of the Tempest. Return to Rejek at Frenzyheart Hill with the True Power of the Tempest.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Now Rejek show cowardly big-tongues how to really use elements!' WHERE entry=12741;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Felt good, didn\'t it? You\'re not one of them anymore, $N. You\'re Scourge. You\'re one of us. Forever...' WHERE entry=12742;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We got here, tore the place apart, and headed toward the prison house. We weren\'t expecting what we found in there, $N. Seems the Crusade\'s been real busy. That whole thing is full of Argent Dawn prisoners. Most of them were already dead by the time we arrived, but a few were still breathing.$B$BI was about to go in there and execute the rest of them, but I think you should have the honors. In particular, there\'s a real feisty night elf in there that I think you\'ll take great pleasure in executing.',objectives_loc4='Knight Commander Plaguefist at the Chapel of the Crimson Flame has ordered you to execute Yazmina Oakenthorn, an Argent Dawn prisoner inside the nearby prison house.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Felt good, didn\'t it? You\'re not one of them anymore, $N. You\'re Scourge. You\'re one of us. Forever...' WHERE entry=12743;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We got here, tore the place apart, and headed toward the prison house. We weren\'t expecting what we found in there, $N. Seems the Crusade\'s been real busy. That whole thing is full of Argent Dawn prisoners. Most of them were already dead by the time we arrived, but a few were still breathing.$B$BI was about to go in there and execute the rest of them, but I think you should have the honors. In particular, there\'s a real feisty dwarf in there that I think you\'ll take great pleasure in executing.',objectives_loc4='Knight Commander Plaguefist at the Chapel of the Crimson Flame has ordered you to execute Donovan Pulfrost, an Argent Dawn prisoner inside the nearby prison house.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Felt good, didn\'t it? You\'re not one of them anymore, $N. You\'re Scourge. You\'re one of us. Forever...' WHERE entry=12744;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We got here, tore the place apart, and headed toward the prison house. We weren\'t expecting what we found in there, $N. Seems the Crusade\'s been real busy. That whole thing is full of Argent Dawn prisoners. Most of them were already dead by the time we arrived, but a few were still breathing.$B$BI was about to go in there and execute the rest of them, but I think you should have the honors. In particular, there\'s a real feisty gnome in there that I think you\'ll take great pleasure in executing.',objectives_loc4='Knight Commander Plaguefist at the Chapel of the Crimson Flame has ordered you to execute Goby Blastenheimer, an Argent Dawn prisoner inside the nearby prison house.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Felt good, didn\'t it? You\'re not one of them anymore, $N. You\'re Scourge. You\'re one of us. Forever...' WHERE entry=12745;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We got here, tore the place apart, and headed toward the prison house. We weren\'t expecting what we found in there, $N. Seems the Crusade\'s been real busy. That whole thing is full of Argent Dawn prisoners. Most of them were already dead by the time we arrived, but a few were still breathing.$B$BI was about to go in there and execute the rest of them, but I think you should have the honors. In particular, there\'s a real feisty draenei in there that I think you\'ll take great pleasure in executing.',objectives_loc4='Knight Commander Plaguefist at the Chapel of the Crimson Flame has ordered you to execute Valok the Righteous, an Argent Dawn prisoner inside the nearby prison house.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Felt good, didn\'t it? You\'re not one of them anymore, $N. You\'re Scourge. You\'re one of us. Forever...' WHERE entry=12746;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We got here, tore the place apart, and headed toward the prison house. We weren\'t expecting what we found in there, $N. Seems the Crusade\'s been real busy. That whole thing is full of Argent Dawn prisoners. Most of them were already dead by the time we arrived, but a few were still breathing.$B$BI was about to go in there and execute the rest of them, but I think you should have the honors. In particular, there\'s a real feisty blood elf in there that I think you\'ll take great pleasure in executing.',objectives_loc4='Knight Commander Plaguefist at the Chapel of the Crimson Flame has ordered you to execute Lady Eonys, an Argent Dawn prisoner inside the nearby prison house.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Felt good, didn\'t it? You\'re not one of them anymore, $N. You\'re Scourge. You\'re one of us. Forever...' WHERE entry=12747;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Felt good, didn\'t it? You\'re not one of them anymore, $N. You\'re Scourge. You\'re one of us. Forever...' WHERE entry=12748;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We got here, tore the place apart, and headed toward the prison house. We weren\'t expecting what we found in there, $N. Seems the Crusade\'s been real busy. That whole thing is full of Argent Dawn prisoners. Most of them were already dead by the time we arrived, but a few were still breathing.$B$BI was about to go in there and execute the rest of them, but I think you should have the honors. In particular, there\'s a real feisty troll in there that I think you\'ll take great pleasure in executing.',objectives_loc4='Knight Commander Plaguefist at the Chapel of the Crimson Flame has ordered you to execute Iggy Darktusk, an Argent Dawn prisoner inside the nearby prison house.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Felt good, didn\'t it? You\'re not one of them anymore, $N. You\'re Scourge. You\'re one of us. Forever...' WHERE entry=12749;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Felt good, didn\'t it? You\'re not one of them anymore, $N. You\'re Scourge. You\'re one of us. Forever...' WHERE entry=12750;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Another Scourge victory! These Scarlet dogs have nowhere left to run and hide. It\'s only a matter of time now...' WHERE entry=12751;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Orbaz reads the message.>$B$BThe armies of Hearthglen and Tirisfal will be marching into a massacre.$B$B<Orbaz smiles.>$B$BNow for the second part of the plan. You\'re going to deliver this message right into the hands of High General Abbendis. That\'s what the clothes are for...' WHERE entry=12754;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<High General Abbendis reads the message.>$B$BDamn it! The armies of Hearthglen and Tirisfal must not reach New Avalon! The Scourge will slaughter them all.' WHERE entry=12755;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Orbaz flips through the journal.>$B$BWhat rubbish! This is the "Crimson Dawn?"$B$BThey sail to their deaths! Let us turn our focus to the encroaching armies.' WHERE entry=12756;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We must prepare for the encroaching armies, $N. You will take what you have discovered to Highlord Mograine at once! I will open a portal directly to Acherus. Step inside and it will transport you.$B$BGive Highlord Mograine Abbendis\' journal as well. Perhaps he\'ll find it useful.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have become an instrument of doom, death knight! We will ravage these approaching armies and raise the dead as our own!' WHERE entry=12757;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Rejek sees you were successful! Now Rejek try on new war helmet.' WHERE entry=12758;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Zepik tell me that you maybe the best gorloc hunter he met... other than Zepik. Still big battle to southwest - you go help.$B$BZepik keeps some of biggest, baddest traps in his stash at Kartak\'s Hold... told Vekgar to use them for battle, so you use them too. Go pick out any traps you want and kill lots of big-tongues.$B$BLots and lots!',objectives_loc4='Retrieve some of Zepik\'s traps from his stash in Kartak\'s Hold.  Using the traps, slaughter 50 of the nearby Sparktouched Gorlocs, and then return to Shaman Jakjek in Kartak\'s Hold.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You almost as good with those traps as Zepik!' WHERE entry=12759;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You a fierce fighter... come back for more battle soon. Never enough good battle!' WHERE entry=12760;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, dryskin.$B$BI hold onto these crystals here to keep us safe. Maybe you come back soon and help us more.' WHERE entry=12761;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So much energy in you... you full of the power of the Great Ones!$B$B I not lie, I little bit jealous.' WHERE entry=12762;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Scout Vor\'takh wants you to travel to Zul\'Drak and report to Sergeant Riannah at Light\'s Breach.$B$BMakki Wintergale in Camp Onequah will provide you transportation.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The Light shall prevail!' WHERE entry=12763;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You must be $N. I was told you\'d be coming.$B$BI have something that I think you\'re uniquely qualified to take care of and by doing it, you\'ll be ingratiating yourself with the dragons here.' WHERE entry=12766;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You must be $N. I was told you\'d be coming.$B$B<The ambassador grunts.>$B$BI have something that I want you to take care of. If you do, you\'ll prove yourself to the dragons here.' WHERE entry=12767;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Back so soon, $N?$B$BCeristrasz sent word ahead of you. Thank you for what you did at the Ruby Dragonshrine.' WHERE entry=12768;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Back so soon, $N?$B$BVargastrasz sent word ahead of you. Thank you for what you did at the Ruby Dragonshrine.' WHERE entry=12769;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Light shall prevail!' WHERE entry=12770;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Our prayers have been answered!  Using the concentration of Light from the Naaru of Shattrath, and the shared benedictions from the faithful, we have created holy artifacts of profound power.  These artifacts will be our weapon against the Lich King\'s machinations.$B$BTake this, $N.  Guard it close, and secure its passage to Ironforge.  Magni Bronzebeard is eager to take the fight to Northrend, and this will bring him closer to his goal.',objectives_loc4='Bishop Lazaril wants you to bring the Light-infused Artifact to King Magni Bronzebeard in Ironforge.',offerrewardtext_loc4='By my beard! This holds a power to rival a fleet of our flying machines! I\'ll give it to my war priests and we\'ll devise a plan to send those vile necropolises scurrying back to Northrend... and we\'ll be right behind them!$B$BOh, Muradin my brother, you must live! By the honor of the Bronzebeards, I will find you!' WHERE entry=12771;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Our prayers have been answered!  Using the concentration of Light from the Naaru of Shattrath, and the shared benedictions from the faithful, we have created holy artifacts of profound power.  These artifacts will be our weapon against the Lich King\'s machinations.$B$BTake this, $N.  Guard it close, and secure its passage to Darnassus.  Deliver it to Tyrande Whisperwind -- her priests will find it a vital source of power in their fight against the unholy forces from the North.',objectives_loc4='Bishop Lazaril wants you to bring the Light-infused Artifact to Tyrande Whisperwind in Darnassus.',offerrewardtext_loc4='What is this? What a boon! They have captured such Light into this artifact, it shines nigh bright as the moon! Our priests will channel this power against our foes, and the Lich King\'s invasion will surely fail. Thank you, $N. Our world tree will be safe.$B$BWhat\'s more, we have sensed that perhaps another world tree grows far to the north, nestled hidden near the Lich King\'s own domain. Perhaps someday... we will shepherd both trees and herald a new era of peace.' WHERE entry=12773;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Our prayers have been answered!  Using the concentration of Light from the Naaru of Shattrath, and the shared benedictions from the faithful, we have created holy artifacts of profound power.  These artifacts will be our weapon against the Lich King\'s machinations.$B$BTake this, $N.  Guard it close, and secure its passage to Stormwind.  The King of Stormwind has recently returned; I\'m sure he will welcome this tool.',objectives_loc4='Bishop Lazaril wants you to bring the Light-infused Artifact to King Varian Wrynn in Stormwind.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So, the holy folk in Shattrath created what they promised! In hindsight, diverting so many priests and paladins there, instead of sending them against the Scourge, was the right move. With this holy weapon, we can beat back that damned Lich King and his minions!$B$BI commend you, Lord $N.' WHERE entry=12774;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Our prayers have been answered!  Using the concentration of Light from the Naaru of Shattrath, and the shared benedictions from the faithful, we have created holy artifacts of profound power.  These artifacts will be our weapon against the Lich King\'s machinations.$B$BTake this, $N.  Guard it close, and secure its passage to the Exodar.  Deliver it to Prophet Velen in the Vault of Lights so that he may use its powers against the unholy forces from the North.',objectives_loc4='Bishop Lazaril wants you to deliver the Light-infused Artifact to Velen in the Exodar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, I can see the power of the Naaru shine through this thing, as if Light itself is housed here. Such good can be done with this implement; the necropolises sent from the frozen wastes of the north will surely fail.' WHERE entry=12776;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have served me well, $N. The mark of the Scourge has been burned into these Scarlet lands. You have reaped death and destruction for as far as the eye can see and delivered to me the last of the Scarlet armies.$B$B<The Lich King points to the ruins of Havenshire and the burning city of New Avalon.>$B$BIt is now time to finish what you started.' WHERE entry=12778;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Kneel, champion. I place this helm upon your head to complete your terrifying visage. Any that dare look upon your dark countenance will know that death comes. Let none stand so boldly against your king so as to face your merciless wrath, $N.$B$BThere remains only one final task...$B$B<The Lich King looks west.>$B$BLight\'s Hope Chapel.' WHERE entry=12779;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Welcome to the World of Warcraft!$B$BAs special thanks for purchasing the World of Warcraft Collector\'s Edition, turn in this gift voucher to Siouxsie the Banshee in Ebon Hold.  You\'ll then be given a gift: a little companion to join you on your quest for adventure and glory.$B$BThanks again, and enjoy your stay in the World of Warcraft!$B',objectives_loc4='Bring the Ebon Hold Gift Voucher to Siouxsie the Banshee in Ebon Hold.',offerrewardtext_loc4='We welcome you to the world of Azeroth, and offer you one of these unique gifts.' WHERE entry=12781;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We have a breakthrough!  Our zombie specimens have given us new insight into the nature of the Scourge\'s plague.  They have born rotten, delicious fruit...$B$BTake this box to Orgrimmar.  Inside is a head that is infected with the zombie plague, and something else we have devised -- an anti-plague.  The two plagues battle within the zombie brain, and that brain is the key to a cure, I am certain of it.$B$BBring the box to my assistant, Apothecary Karlov.  He attends Warchief Thrall in Orgrimmar.',objectives_loc4='Grand Apothecary Putress wants you to give the Dual-plagued Brain to Apothecary Karlov in Orgrimmar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, very good. The diseases this rotted head carries are deadly, but we must not shy from danger or from what we find distasteful. Some day, $N, you will learn that damnation is the path to salvation...' WHERE entry=12785;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We have a breakthrough!  Our zombie specimens have given new insight into the nature of the Scourge\'s plague.  They have born rotten, delicious fruit...$B$BTake this box to Thunder Bluff.  Inside is a head that is infected with the zombie plague, and something else we have devised -- an anti-plague.  The two plagues battle within the zombie brain, and that brain is the key to a cure, I am certain of it.$B$BBring the box to my assistant, Apothecary Chaney.  He attends Magatha Grimtotem in Thunder Bluff.',objectives_loc4='Grand Apothecary Putress wants you to give the Dual-plagued Brain to Apothecary Chaney in Thunder Bluff.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, very good. The diseases this rotted head carries are deadly, but we must not shy from danger or from what we find distasteful. Some day, $N, you will learn that damnation is the path to salvation...' WHERE entry=12786;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The zombie plague was a blessing in disguise.  In our search for a cure, we have learned so much of the Scourge and their contagion.  Our research has given us weapons against them.  Weapons, and tools...$B$BTake this -- it is a zombie\'s head and has been partially cured of its plague by injecting it with a compound derived from our recent discoveries.  Deliver the head to Master Apothecary Faranell; I have a list of experiments I would like him to perform on it.',objectives_loc4='Grand Apothecary Putress wants you to give the Dual-plagued Brain to Master Apothecary Faranell in the Undercity.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, what a fine specimen you are. The disease, -- diseases -- dancing through your brain must offer you visions so sublime. We will spend long nights in conversation, you and I, and I will pick from you your thoughts as I slowly extract the meat from your skull.$B$BDo not fear, little one. The knowledge gained from your sacrifice will be awesome. You are a gift to the forsaken; you will herald a new age of respect for us among the peoples of this world. Your place in our history is assured...' WHERE entry=12787;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We have a breakthrough!  Our zombie specimens have given new insight into the nature of the Scourge\'s plague.  They have born rotten, delicious fruit...$B$BTake this box to Silvermoon City.  Inside is a head that is infected with the zombie plague, and something else... an anti-plague.  The two plagues battle within the zombie brain, and that brain is the key to a cure, I am certain of it.$B$BBring the box to my assistant, Apothecary Tepesh.  She attends Lor\'themar Theron in Silvermoon City.',objectives_loc4='Grand Apothecary Putress wants you to give the Dual-plagued Brain to Apothecary Tepesh in Silvermoon City.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, very good. The diseases this rotted head carries are deadly, but we must not shy from danger or from what we find distasteful. Some day, $N, you will learn that damnation is the path to salvation...' WHERE entry=12788;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent. Valus must have received my report.$B$BLet\'s get to work, $R.' WHERE entry=12789;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent, $C. Now you know the way to get down to Crystalsong Forest and also how to return.' WHERE entry=12790;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Welcome to Dalaran.$B$BI\'ll see to it that the ring is returned.' WHERE entry=12791;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='My report must have made it through to Kunz.$B$BIt is good to know that he is well.' WHERE entry=12792;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Light shall prevail!' WHERE entry=12793;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Welcome to Dalaran.$B$BI\'ll see to it that the ring is returned.' WHERE entry=12794;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='As it happens there is something you can do to be of assistance, $C.' WHERE entry=12795;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Welcome to Dalaran.$B$BI\'ll see to it that the ring is returned.' WHERE entry=12796;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done well.$B$BWoe unto our enemies. Woe unto those who serve the Lich King and threaten the titans\' creations -- for the Etymidian is here.' WHERE entry=12797;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Your inscription ability has grown, scribe. The tarot cards are of great interest to the Darkmoon Faire, so do not hesitate to call upon us if you manage to create more. We are not without our own skilled tradesmen, so please allow us to offer something in trade for the cards.' WHERE entry=12798;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $C.$B$BThis should save my men some precious time.' WHERE entry=12799;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Highlord and the other death knights are preparing to strike! We will squeeze the last remnants of life out of this place.' WHERE entry=12800;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='There will be no atonement for us, $N. We are forever damned to walk the earth as monsters. While the Lich King may have loosed his grip upon us, the specters of our past will forever haunt our memories.$B$BWe must make amends in the only way we know how: Death...$B$BI ask you now to join me in Acherus as a Knight of the Ebon Blade. Together we will destroy the Lich King and end the Scourge.' WHERE entry=12801;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Impressive, mon! Fate be kind in bringin\' us together.$B$BSoon I be avengin\' me bruddas by cleansin\' Drak\'Tharon, and you be awarded Drak\'Tharon\'s greatest treasure.' WHERE entry=12802;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are not of this land. But you also are not with the Scourge.$B$BWhat should I make of you?' WHERE entry=12803;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Now that\'s a meal! If anything good came of the shipwreck, it\'s got to be that we\'ve been spared eating nothing but salt beef for the next month! Thank you again, $N.' WHERE entry=12804;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I thank you, $N. It is a shame that the pillar has fallen, but we must salvage what we can.' WHERE entry=12805;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s about damned time! No doubt that Baron Sliver took his sweet time in sending you to me.$B$BI should have that empty space above his shoulders removed!' WHERE entry=12806;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='In their folly, the Argent Crusade has chosen to turn a blind eye upon the presence of the Scarlet Onslaught. We will not.$B$BWe do not care if they might assist in the battle against the Lich King. We do not believe them worthy of existence. We will be their end, once and for all!' WHERE entry=12807;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Our prayers have been answered!  Using the concentration of Light from the Naaru of Shattrath, and the shared benedictions from the faithful, we have created holy artifacts of profound power.  These artifacts will be our weapon against the Lich King\'s machinations.$B$BTake this, $N.  Guard it close, and secure its passage to Ironforge.  High Tinker Mekkatorque in Tinkertown will be eager to make use of the artifact\'s power.',objectives_loc4='Bishop Lazaril wants you to bring the Light-infused Artifact to High Tinker Mekkatorque in Ironforge.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Inconceivably immaculate! This device stores Light energy at levels beyond those of any source yet known! Oh, the possible applications shiver my whiskers and curl my toes. Ho ho! The anti-nocturnal photo-dispersement geno-actuator I could build with this would turn dusk into dawn! The Scourge won\'t know what hit them. We\'ll destroy them all in one pull of a lever!' WHERE entry=12809;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done. Take a moment to let the saltwater dry from your skin before we continue.' WHERE entry=12810;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We have a breakthrough!  Our zombie specimens have given new insight into the nature of the Scourge\'s plague.  They have born rotten, delicious fruit...$B$BTake this box to Orgrimmar.  Inside is a head that is infected with the zombie plague, and something else we have devised -- an anti-plague.  The two plagues battle within the zombie brain, and that brain is the key to a cure, I am certain of it.$B$BBring the box to my assistant, Apothecary Karlov.  He attends Thrall in Orgrimmar.',objectives_loc4='Grand Apothecary Putress wants you to give the Dual-plagued Brain to Apothecary Karlov in Orgrimmar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, very good. The diseases this rotted head carries are deadly, but we must not shy from danger or from what we find distasteful. Some day, $N, you will learn that damnation is the path to salvation...' WHERE entry=12812;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The draenei death knight fixes you with a cold stare, her eyes dead as the grave. A sly grin creeps across her features.>$B$BI\'ll have more of the tincture prepared tomorrow. Until then, be well.' WHERE entry=12813;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh yeah this is gonna be good!$B$BStand back... I\'m gonna call down the wrath of the blood ritual!' WHERE entry=12814;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'s the spirit! And you know, I need this done everyday that we\'re here.$B$BI hope you\'ll come back again tomorrow. Your bone gryphon will be waitin\'.' WHERE entry=12815;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Investigate the Scourge of Silvermoon',details_loc4='The Lich King has sent his undead upon our very doorstep; we cannot remain idle! Surely you will step up to defend Silvermoon from these accursed invaders? $B $BThere are strange runic circles outside, glowing with the same energy that surrounds the undead and the Necropolis above. They have significance, I\'m certain, and I want you to find out what. Thin the numbers of those aberrations while you\'re at it; bring me proof of their death along with your results, and I will reward you.  Go!',objectives_loc4='Collect three Dim Necrotic Stones from the Scourge outside Silvermoon and investigate the glowing runic circles near their encampment.' WHERE entry=12816;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These will do nicely, thanks!$B$BDid you happen to see Dim out there? I sent him out a long while back and he never came back. I hope he\'s alright.$B$BSpeaking of which... I wonder where Janks is...' WHERE entry=12818;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ha ha! These are them! Thank you kindly. I hope you didn\'t have too much trouble traversing the field.' WHERE entry=12819;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So... here I sat, basking in the awesomeness that is me, and in the distance, I hear a pop! Then another! Then a dozen more! And a smile crept onto my face at the thought of all those magnataur and snobolds eagerly rushing to their own deaths.$B$BWas it glorious?' WHERE entry=12820;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent!$B$B<A fierce grin creeps onto Ricket\'s face.>$B$BLet the destruction begin!' WHERE entry=12821;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Haha! That\'ll teach those brutes to waste our time. From this day forth, green skin will strike fear into the hearts of all magnataur!' WHERE entry=12822;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The whole mountain shook! Was it gorgeous? I bet it was! How could it not be?$B$BAnd the Inventor\'s League tells me all of my inventions just blow up. Darn right they do! Hah!' WHERE entry=12823;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You blew the whole place up? Way to go! I bet Rio got a kick out of that.$B$BWe really appreciate all of the help you\'ve lent us, $N. How bout a souvenir for your troubles?' WHERE entry=12824;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Looking good!$B$BNo, not you - my new mines. You\'re just a little full of yourself, aren\'t you? I, on the other hand, am absolutely brilliant! My intellect cannot be matched.$B$BWhat were we talking about? Oh yes, my new mines! New and improved... ready for whatever devious use Ricket has concocted.$B$BBe a $G good lad:doll; and go hand them off to Ricket, will you? She\'s right over there... it should be quite the epic journey, I\'m sure. Be careful though, she\'s a little loopy.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, aren\'t these just the cutest little packets of destruction you\'ve ever seen?!' WHERE entry=12826;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I hope they weren\'t too hesitant to share the wealth. we\'ve been pretty forgiving with them picking through our leftovers thus far.' WHERE entry=12827;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='And it\'s already well-done! I outdo myself sometimes.$B$BThanks much, friend!' WHERE entry=12828;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ha ha! Good to see you\'re up for some dirty work.$B$BMuch appreciated there, $Gpal:lass;!' WHERE entry=12829;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Woo! That\'s a ripe stench right there! You had to get hands-on with some of those snobolds, didn\'t ya?$B$BI do appreciate it though!' WHERE entry=12830;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That should cut it... I hope Ricket can put something together for me. Ready to get out of there, then?' WHERE entry=12831;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thanks for helping out our miner back there, $N! I should be able to put together an antidote no problem.$B$BIf you stumble into Tore agian, tell her that she\'s a jerk for me, will ya?' WHERE entry=12832;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I like you. In fact, you rock!$B$BYay for you!' WHERE entry=12833;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Groovy! You\'re my kind of $R.' WHERE entry=12836;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hand them over. I will sift through the useless ones and if there\'s anything actionable, I will call upon you.$B$BEither way, return tomorrow. It is well known that they change their plans on a daily basis.' WHERE entry=12838;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A note written by Westwind? Why didn\'t you say so?$B$B<Arete tears the letter from your hand to read it.>$B$BThe fool! He\'s actually here?!$B$B<The lord-commander laughs.>$B$BThis is new information. I wonder how he imagines that he\'s going to conquer the world once he\'s taken down the Lich King? Not that he could accomplish either task in his wildest imaginings.' WHERE entry=12839;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='They resurrected Landgren? He\'s the one that will know where the grand admiral is then!' WHERE entry=12840;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I wasn\'t sure you were coming back. I dread to think what will happen to me if I stay here for much longer.' WHERE entry=12841;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Remember these words, death knight: The Runeforge is a Scourge instrument. It exists only in Acherus, Naxxramas and the heart of Icecrown! You may only emblazon your weaponry at a Runeforge.$B$BReturn often and emblazon all of your weapons. A death knight must be prepared for all that would dare oppose $G him:her;!' WHERE entry=12842;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You did it! Our boys are back!' WHERE entry=12843;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thanks, $N! We\'ll see what we can do to salvage these parts!' WHERE entry=12844;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re definitely not with the Hyldnir... so what are you here for? Ah... you must be looking for the new prisoner!' WHERE entry=12846;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hidden caves on the backside of the island. How very interesting.$B$BWell, at least now I know where all of my missing spies are.' WHERE entry=12847;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText2_loc4='Arete\'s Gate summoned' WHERE entry=12847;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='As expected, my chosen knight has triumphed! You are ready, $N.' WHERE entry=12848;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Within the Hall of Command you will find the schools of blood, frost and unholy. Each school has a trainer that can provide you with knowledge in the various dark arts.$B$BI, Lord Thorval, am the headmaster of the school of blood. Lady Alistra reigns over unholy and the arch-lich, Amal\'thazad, holds dominion over frost.$B$BYou must return here whenever you gain power and train!' WHERE entry=12849;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The war has begun, death knight! I shall place you upon my finest gryphon and deliver you to Death\'s Breach. Chaos, death, destruction! You will herald in all of this and more!
' WHERE entry=12850;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Perhaps you do have the heart of a warrior.$B$BTime will tell...' WHERE entry=12851;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='MAL\'GANIS?!!$B$B<The lord-commander laughs with abandon.>$B$BThe fools were taken in by the demons yet again and now they are destroyed!$B$BI trust that my favorite $C will stick around long enough to help us finish off the rest of them? Perhaps one of these would convince you?' WHERE entry=12852;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Welcome to K3!$B$BWe came here to make our way into those peaks and get our fair share of some of those amazing titan machines. Progress on that end has been somewhat minimal, though. Gnolls, snobolds, magnataur... there\'s no shortage of trouble to go around... not to mention, we can\'t seem to keep any fliers in the air without their motors freezing.$B$BThere\'s plenty of work to be done though - lend a hand, eh?' WHERE entry=12853;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Archaeologist Andorin looks at you expectantly.>$B$BYou were supposed to come back with Brann, not a piece of paper. What\'s going on here?' WHERE entry=12854;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You... you\'re not a member of the Explorers\' League, at least not one I remember. But, if you recovered the communicator, they must\'ve sent you. Good, that\'s almost what I was hoping for.' WHERE entry=12855;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Track down thief' WHERE entry=12855;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='To be slain honorably on the field of battle brings us all glory. To be frozen in a block of ice and endlessly taunted does not....$B$BYou are to fly to the frost giant city of Dun Niffelem, just east of the Valley of Ancient Winters, and liberate a captive proto-drake. With her, you will be able to free our sisters from their frozen bonds and carry three of them safely home.$B$BBeware the giants\' clubs, sister, lest you find yourself numbered among the captives.',objectives_loc4='Brijana, just east of Brunnhildar Village, wants you to fly to Dun Niffelem, then free 3 Captured Proto-Drakes and rescue 9 Brunnhildar Prisoners.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Your efforts appear to have been successful, $Gbrother:sister;.$B$BYou have brought glory to the Brunnhildar!' WHERE entry=12856;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Posted by Chief Rageclaw:$B$BChief Rageclaw trusty lion seal, Ragemane, bite hand that feed him. Rageclaw say Ragemane no more good because of bad Drakuru trolls. Chief Rageclaw very sad to ask that Ragemane be killeded and Ragemane flipper be returned to chief as proof.$B$BYou find Ragemane to southeast, at Rageclaw Lake.$B$BChief Rageclaw sorry for bad writing. First time use one of these things; plus, Chief Rageclaw is wolvar, not person.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Chief Rageclaw cries.>$B$BHad Ragemane since pup. Sad day for Rageclaw. First troll attack Rageclaw, then troll make Ragemane bad. Rageclaw never trade with troll again!' WHERE entry=12857;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Wonderful! Now that we have the disk, you must use it to open the Inventor\'s vault!' WHERE entry=12858;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Elder Shaman Moky at Light\'s Breach in Zul\'Drak wants you to use the Rageclaw Fire Extinguisher to douse 15 hut fires at Rageclaw Den.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='It strange because I know you put fire out, but fire still burning. Maybe this thing not so good after all, eh? Still, Moky pay you for what you do! Hopefully troll burn too!' WHERE entry=12859;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Brann looks at the disk as you hold it up.>$B$BI can\'t tell if there\'s anything stored there or not! You have to tell me what happened.$B$B<You describe the data retrieval process.>$B$BSo it worked? At least we can count on Mimir to be systematic. Can\'t say that for the rest of these Keepers from what I\'ve been hearing...' WHERE entry=12860;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Rageclaw thank you, $N. Though Rageclaw Den probably lost forever and troll-Rageclaw friendship also lost forever... and also now I think of it, Ragemane lost forever too. Also brother-in-law. He gone. Hrm, have you seen Chief\'s mate? I think she gone too.$B$BMaybe you go now. Chief a little depressed.' WHERE entry=12861;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ow! That looked painful. It was a pretty grand entrance though, lad!$B$BWelcome to Frosthold! Are ya here to help us find a path into Icecrown?' WHERE entry=12862;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Ah! Thanks for coming up here, $G lad:lass;.$B$BJudging by your wide eyes and shivering hands, I\'d venture a guess that you\'re somewhat new. Sounds like it would be good for you to meet our gracious hosts then!$B$BWe\'ve got some extra medical supplies... to be honest, we weren\'t expecting to have such a comfortable setup. Go ahead and give this crate to Glorthal over there, and lend them a hand if you would too. We don\'t want them to think we\'re ungrateful for how welcoming they\'ve been.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Medical supplies? Thank you! Not exactly sure what to do with them to be honest, but I\'m sure they\'ll be useful.$B$BIt\'s good to meet you... there\'s such a colorful variety among your peoples. We\'re not used to having visitors up this way very often - it\'s good to have some fresh company.' WHERE entry=12863;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='When a scout doesn\'t come back for this long... that\'s about the expected result. The harpies then?$B$BKing Stormheart has us train hard year round... he\'s turned us into amazing fighters. At times like this, I understand why it\'s necessary. He\'s the wisest and strongest leader I\'ve yet seen among our people... don\'t let his peachy skin fool ya.' WHERE entry=12864;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, kindly... and I\'m sure they\'re quite appreciative too. They make powerful allies; you\'ll be well off being on this side of their graces.' WHERE entry=12865;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s dirty work, I know, but we appreciate it. Now what was the name the scout mentioned... Sirana?' WHERE entry=12866;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good stuff, lad. You\'re making fast friends.$B$BIf you stop back by soon, I\'m sure we can find one that will let you ride... they should know that you\'re trustworthy now.' WHERE entry=12867;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s done then. Thank you.$B$BI\'ve spoken with Fjorlin - he said that his men will take charge of keeping the harpies down a bit. As long as we don\'t let up again, they won\'t find the courage to think they can attack our people.$B$BI know this wasn\'t the most tasteful work - take this as a token of my appreciation.' WHERE entry=12868;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I don\'t see the drakes being dissuaded so easily. Stop back by tomorrow if you think you can spare more time to help.' WHERE entry=12869;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Why hello thar!$B$BBefore you be headin\' off to do your grand questin\' and adventure, might I beg a wee favor of ya, $G lad:lass;?$B$BThese mountains be packed full\'a precious relics and baubles... this place be a dream come true for tha league. I\'d be much obliged if ya could bring any such treasures you stumble upon back ta me. You can even share in me ale for tha trouble! Trust me $G lad:lass;, that\'s a rich deal!',offerrewardtext_loc4='Beaut! Yer a good one you are.$B$BTilt one back wi\' me! Let us celebrae\' this glorious find!' WHERE entry=12870;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='By Muradin\'s beard! Is that what I think it is?! Brann\'s really outdone himself this time... and you too for that matter! The boys back home are never going to believe this.' WHERE entry=12871;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'s it! That\'s the first half of Norgannon\'s keystone. Well done, $N. When I get back to Ironforge, I\'m going to have you inducted as an honorary member in the Explorers\' League!' WHERE entry=12872;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Norgannon\'s Core? Never heard of it. I might well know someone that has though.' WHERE entry=12873;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ha! Grand tale lad... perhaps ye have a bit of frostborn blood in ye, eh? Yer not just talk anyway, and that\'s what I needed to hear.' WHERE entry=12874;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Drom coughts up a bit of blood.>$B$BNorgannon\'s Core, eh? I\'ve spent a fair number of days trying to find anything I could about it myself, but it seems to be one of the relics that\'s still guarded. With reason I suppose.$B$BIf King Stormheart sent you, he surely must see something noble in ye... and I\'m not one to refuse my king.' WHERE entry=12875;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Grim news, lad. Those Iron Dwarves seem to be increasing in numbers... we\'ve been seeing them all over the mountains. I smell war coming.$B$BThank you for dealing with this bunch... a little more time bought.' WHERE entry=12876;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Drom\'s ring? I am to assume Drom is not well if he did not introduce you directly. I am sorry to hear of that. Drom is a noble dwarf, if an inquisitive one.$B$BOn what business have you come then?' WHERE entry=12877;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<As the chest opens, air rushes out into the chamber, carrying with it the musty smell of something that has been here for countless years. Norgannon\'s Core rests in the bottom of the chest, undisturbed by the ages.>' WHERE entry=12878;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Someone is using the Forge of Wills to create this army... Ulduar is no longer safe.$B$B$R, I am pleased that you were able to reach the core before these abominations were.' WHERE entry=12879;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re brilliant, lad! Brilliant! This will be a glorious day indeed.$B$BQuickly, hand me the core before those iron dwarves make their way down here.' WHERE entry=12880;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These will do nicely! I am much obliged. Perhaps a drink for your troubles?' WHERE entry=12882;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='If this is the same Drakuru from Drak\'Tharon Keep we are going to need... outside assistance.$B$BDeath knights of Acherus are stationed nearby, undoubtedly following the same trail of Scourge destruction that lead the Argent Crusade here. As half of our army is tied up at the Argent Stand, battling crazed Drakkari trolls, we will have to join forces with the Knights of the Ebon Blade.$B$B<Lantinga mutters under his breath.>$B$BI was hoping I\'d never have to see those scoundrels again after Light\'s Hope...' WHERE entry=12883;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Stefan reads the missive, then crumples it up and tosses it into the fire.>$B$BOld news. The Argent Crusade is - once again - late to the party. we\'ve been tracking Drakuru since Grizzly Hills. He is slated for eradication.' WHERE entry=12884;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So you know Brann Bronzebeard, then? He is our closest ally among those of the flesh. We are as brothers in the struggle against Loken and his followers, in the struggle for Ulduar.' WHERE entry=12885;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Use the Hyldnir Harpoon to defeat 10 Hyldsmeet Drakeriders at the Temple of Storms.  Use the Hyldnir Harpoon on a Column Ornament to exit the Drakkensryd and speak to Thorim when you\'ve succeeded.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Sif... is that you?' WHERE entry=12886;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Hyldsmeet Drakerider Defeated' WHERE entry=12886;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Perhaps now we can really get something done. Don\'t be fooled though, the Lich King can still \'see\' through his Scourge minions.$B$BThat\'s why you\'re here.' WHERE entry=12887;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<You begin performing the repairs indicated by the access card. When the repairs are complete, you close the access panel and throw the power switch.>' WHERE entry=12888;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You examine the display on the repaired prototype console. At least one of Mimir\'s schematics seems to have survived the long period between maintenance cycles. From the diagrams and instructions displayed in the schematic\'s file, you could easily construct the mechagnome shown.' WHERE entry=12889;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Quickly, hand them to me and stay out of sight!$B$BThe rod, the hook, and the rope are all very self-evident in their usage when combined. I just need to infuse the result with the essences and we\'ll be ready to proceed.$B$BIt\'s all very mundane in its composition, but extraordinary in its application!' WHERE entry=12891;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Perhaps now we can really get something done. Don\'t be fooled though, the Lich King can still \'see\' through his Scourge minions.$B$BThat\'s why you\'re here.' WHERE entry=12892;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We will put those three to good use once we finally take the vault.$B$BSpeaking of which....' WHERE entry=12893;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Everything was fine until the Scourge attacked. They took off with Dargath, Gerk and Burr and they also destroyed our ride. Guess who led that attack?$B$B<MacKellar nods.>$B$BNavarius...$B$BSeems this whole area is some type of factory for Scourge. We\'re in the middle of a damned undead mine field!' WHERE entry=12894;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Of course, with our luck, I probably could\'ve predicted this. Well, we\'re not going to let him get away that easily. Let\'s see what that note says.' WHERE entry=12895;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='General Lightsbane and his forces are defeated? The Shadow Vault is taken?' WHERE entry=12896;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Defeat General Lightsbane and then report your success back to Koltira Deathweaver aboard the gunship, Orgrim\'s Hammer.',offerrewardtext_loc4='General Lightsbane and his forces are defeated? The Shadow Vault is taken?' WHERE entry=12897;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good of you to return. As you can see, we have our hands full here.' WHERE entry=12898;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='It sounds like you did extremely well. And you secured three very important allies for the Knights of the Ebon Blade in the process.$B$B<Koltira gazes down at the map on the floor.>$B$BYou should head back. By now, Baron Sliver and the other death knights will be fighting tooth and nail to hold The Shadow Vault against the might of the Scourge.$B$BI\'m sure they\'ll need your help.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Good of you to return. As you can see, we have our hands full here.' WHERE entry=12899;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These will do nicely. I\'ll have the harness ready for you in no time.' WHERE entry=12900;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What is this junk! Ah, damn it all! It\'s useless. Scourge metal isn\'t gonna do the trick. What are we going to do?' WHERE entry=12901;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='There is a scroll floating in the air above the strange altar. This must be what Crusader Lord Lantinga is looking for!' WHERE entry=12902;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It was a great sacrifice that those three made and it won\'t soon be forgotten. Their passing will not be in vain. We will be victorious!' WHERE entry=12903;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='They... They killed my brother.$B$B<Gerk fights back tears.>$B$BSlaughtered him like he was some sort of animal. Now they got him laid out on one of their tables on the other side of the camp, ready for their grizzly experiments. Dargath\'s dead too. The paladin made a heroic stand at the ruins to the northeast, but the leader of the Vargul, Algar, was too strong.$B$BI\'m all that\'s left and I\'ll be dead soon too. I... I\'m turning.$B$BIf the Light won\'t grant me vengeance, maybe you will, $C. Kill them all.',objectives_loc4='Gerk at Thrym\'s End in Zul\'Drak wants you to kill 15 Vargul.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Gerk is dying.>$B$BTh... They say these Vargul are the... the ones that weren\'t found worthy by the Lich King. Can... Can you im... imagine it? Just th... think how powerful the... the... worthy must be...$B$BI\'ll say a prayer for you in the hereafter, hero... May you never have to face them in number.' WHERE entry=12904;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I was expecting a replacement for one of my overseers. It\'s about time you showed up.$B$BLet\'s put you to work.' WHERE entry=12905;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Not bad for a new overseer. I\'ve another task for you if you\'re feeling brave today.' WHERE entry=12906;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='If I had any reservations regarding your commitment when you first arrived, I no longer have any. With just a little more effort you could be a permanent member of my operation.' WHERE entry=12907;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I knew you\'d be back! Get me out of these shackles and I\'ll help you find the goblin.' WHERE entry=12908;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Boktar can have his way this time, but I\'ll expect him to make it up to me. Don\'t look at me like that. Boktar may be in command, but no one tells a hunter what to do.$B$B\'Put that beast away,\' he says. \'Make it stop growling.\'$B$BAll of a sudden he changes his mind when it suits him. Next time he complains, Frostbite\'ll just nip him a bit. Don\'t worry, she\'ll do an admirable job tracking your prey. After she locates her target, you\'re on your own to deal with iron dwarves, or Brann, or whatever you find.',objectives_loc4='Mount Frostbite and ride her to the source of the scent from Brann\'s note. Then, recover Brann\'s Communicator and use it to make contact with Brann Bronzebeard.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<An image of a dwarf appears as you activate the communicator. It can only be Brann Bronzebeard.>$B$B<From the look on his face, Brann seems shocked to see you and begins gesturing furiously.>' WHERE entry=12910;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A... A storm giant? I don\'t know about this, $N. That sounds risky. On the other hand, I don\'t think we have too many other options.$B$BIf I do this you have to promise me that you will get your giant friend to help us deal with Navarius and his cronies.' WHERE entry=12912;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thankfully we weren\'t in short supply of explosives. Putting together the jumbo seaforium charge should be no problem with the materials you brought me.' WHERE entry=12914;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So, it is done then.$B$BLet us hope it is enough.' WHERE entry=12915;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='FREEDOM!$B$BDo not be afraid, little one. Gymer is an honorable giant. Like you and your people, I too wish to see the Scourge driven away from this land and the Lich King destroyed. I will help you, as promised, to the best of my ability.' WHERE entry=12916;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These are perfect for replenishing my stock.  Not only will I teach you the art of gemcutting perfection, but I cut one of them gems into its perfect form which you may have as a reward.' WHERE entry=12918;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Unbelievable! This will be a story for the ages, $N! One man rode upon the head of the king of storm giants and decimated an entire Scourge army!$B$BAnd I was there to see it all happen...' WHERE entry=12919;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re here -- good. I think I know where your goblin is.' WHERE entry=12921;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Beneath its porous exterior, this hunk of metal gleams with a mysterious quality.$B$BYou feel it would only be prudent to burn off the slag at Fjorn\'s Anvil.$B$BAs you ponder where in this frozen waste you might find something hot enough for the job, a fire revenant crosses your path...$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='You place the metal on the anvil and immediately upon adding the sparks they work the ore furiously.$B$BWhen at last they burn out, you are left with a large piece of metal that gleams with a light of its own.' WHERE entry=12922;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It would seem that I have refined my technique considerably. That, or the legends surrounding this anvil are true.$B$BThis suit of armor is superior to the last, and took less material to create.$B$BWith the excess, I was able to fashion you a little something as payment for your assistance.' WHERE entry=12924;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have our thanks, $Gbrother:sister;. We cannot allow our valiant traditions to be corrupted.' WHERE entry=12925;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That was quick! Now that we have the disk, we have to find out how to use it to unlock the first half of the archive key.' WHERE entry=12926;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='That disk you assembled... it\'s blank! Keeper Mimir, the tinker who built this library, must\'ve hidden the information elsewhere. Look around the Inventor\'s Library; do you see any databanks there?$B$BThat might be the disk\'s purpose. Try using it near some of those databanks. Perhaps it\'s set to retrieve and store information from them. After you\'ve tried your hand at that, contact me again and let me know what you\'ve found. Meanwhile, I\'ll be trying to track down the other half of the archive key.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Brann looks at the disk as you hold it up.>$B$BI can\'t tell if there\'s anything stored there or not! You have to tell me what happened.$B$B<You describe the data retrieval process.>$B$BSo it worked? At least we can count on Mimir to be systematic. Can\'t say that for the rest of these Keepers from what I\'ve been hearing...' WHERE entry=12927;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That\'s it! That\'s the first half of Norgannon\'s keystone. Well done, $N. I\'ve had Archaeologist Andorin on the lookout for clues to the shell\'s whereabouts for a long time. He\'s never going to believe me when I tell him it was an intrepid $R who found it instead.' WHERE entry=12928;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='The Earthen of Ulduar',details_loc4='The earthen who once inhabited, built, and maintained Ulduar were ousted from their home when Loken took over the city. Since then, his iron dwarf followers have relentlessly attacked the exiles.$B$BThey have taken refuge in an old titan building, which they now call Bouldercrag\'s Refuge, on the face of a mountain west of the Inventor\'s Library. Bouldercrag and his brethren fight to keep the irons from overrunning their haven, but they cannot hold their ground long. Find and help them, $N.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So you know Brann Bronzebeard, then? He is our closest ally among those of the flesh. We are as brothers in the struggle against Loken and his followers, in the struggle for Ulduar.' WHERE entry=12929;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This will allow us to patch up more of the fallen. Thank you, $N, on behalf of all who defend the refuge.' WHERE entry=12930;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve given the defenders something to cheer about. Seeing the enemy fall by your hand has reinvigorated them and bolstered their courage.' WHERE entry=12931;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I\'ll tell you what, buddy, this place is a far cry from the rolling plains of Nagrand. These trolls are dirtier than ogres; but hey, I go where the gold\'s at! So welcome to Zul\'Drak, pal.$B$BYou\'re new to this racket, so let me set you straight. I\'m the fight promoter and this feisty troll next to me is Wodin, my bodyguard. You\'re the entertainment. When you wanna fight, let me know and I\'ll set up the match.$B$BIf you\'re ready and got a group of friends with you, we can start! What do you say?$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Not bad, friend. You might make some gold out here - if you manage to stay alive.' WHERE entry=12932;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Wow! When I first saw Stinkbeard, I thought you were done for! Nice work!' WHERE entry=12933;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Get in the arena at the Amphitheater of Anguish and defeat one of the elemental lords! Return to Wodin the Troll-Servant to redeem your reward.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Unbelievable! I thought this whole place was going to explode when it first appeared! You really dominated that round!' WHERE entry=12934;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I was worried for a while there, $N. When he busted out the seals and penguins... Well, I didn\'t know what to think to be honest. It looked pretty damn ridiculous.' WHERE entry=12935;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Damn, I remember Korrak from way back in my younger days when I used to work for the Frostwolf Clan. He would never shut up! I think you just did the world a great service, $N.' WHERE entry=12936;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The warriors that you\'ve healed will aid us in holding the line even longer. If we are to truly be free of the iron threat, we must find a way to strike at them behind the lines.' WHERE entry=12937;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s a pleasure to finally meet you, $N. We owe you a great deal, but we\'re not done with you yet.$B$BThere is a vrykul city just over the mountains to the west, a place called Jotunheim.$B$BThe vrykul there are in a constant state of challenge to \'ascend\'. The winners go to Ymirheim to serve as the Lich King\'s elite warrior caste, the Ymirjar, and the losers are reduced to scourged Vargul.$B$BYou are going to be my instrument to see to it that more Vargul than Ymirjar emerge.' WHERE entry=12938;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Already I\'m hearing reports of the prowess you displayed on the Savage Ledge. Excellent, $N... excellent!$B$B<The duke flashes his rictus smile again and you can almost hear the wheels in his head turning.>$B$BAnd now I think it\'s time to issue a decree to the thane of those vrykul that you so easily defeated.' WHERE entry=12939;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Val\'kyr are nothing but the Lich King\'s lapdogs. They will be put down like the scum they are. They\'ve made their choice, now they have to live with the consequences.' WHERE entry=12942;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Duke Lankral nods his approval at your report of success.>$B$BWe face a foe that dwarfs us, not only in stature, but also numerically. If we are to win the battle for Icecrown, we must outthink them!$B$BWith Ufrang dead, that gives us an advantage in Jotunheim. Let us see if we can capitalize on it.' WHERE entry=12943;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You did it, $N! That was the most exciting fight yet! What are you going to do with your winnings? Me? I\'m going to Dalaran and blowing it all in the Underbelly. Lot of hot action going on down there!' WHERE entry=12948;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $R. Just hand me the key, I\'ll take care of it myself.' WHERE entry=12949;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What?! We can ill-afford to lose one death knight, let alone an entire contingent!!!' WHERE entry=12951;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='My skills are going to waste in this wretched place.   I spent many years learning to cut gems into their perfect form and have nothing to work on!   You look like the type who may be able to find me some gems and if you do I can teach you the skill of gem perfection.   This will allow you to sometimes cut a perfect gem with increased bonuses when cutting a uncommon quality gem from Northrend.',objectives_loc4='Return two Huge Citrines, two Dark Jade and two Shadow Crystals to Carter Tiffens in Vengeance Landing.',offerrewardtext_loc4='These will have to do. I can teach you the art of gemcutting perfection, and give you proof of my skills as well.' WHERE entry=12952;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Now that is what I call dedication! Those traitors might have a new master now, but they\'ll never forget their sisters\' parting gift.' WHERE entry=12953;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Fires Started' WHERE entry=12953;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I was wondering when you\'d show up, $N! Having a past champion of the Ring of Blood here will be a huge draw! We\'re gonna be rich, buddy! RICH!$B$BAnyway, this dump is Zul\'Drak. All the ice trolls seem to use it as a toilet. I dunno, the whole place is off its rocker if you ask me! Who cares, though, right? We\'re here to make some gold!$B$BYou know the drill, $N. When you\'re ready let me know and we\'ll get this show on the road!$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Hey! I know you. Your victory at the Ring of Blood was talked about for months! Too bad you forfeited the championship when you failed to show up to defend your title! Easy come, easy go, eh? At least you\'re still alive.' WHERE entry=12954;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That was important, $N. By driving them off, you\'re keeping them from interfering with whatever we need you to do over there.' WHERE entry=12955;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Onu\'zun defeated',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Tinky Wickwhistle defeated' WHERE entry=12955;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You notice Thorim\'s stern countenance brighten with recognition as you present the ore.' WHERE entry=12956;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I had hoped that more of the captives would choose to join us, but I do not blame them. Willing allies are few and far between, and we are thankful that you have lent your blade to our cause.' WHERE entry=12957;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='A wealthy shipping concern has requested a collection of Blood Jade Amulets to sell at Undermine.   If you can bring me one, I can reward you with a Dalaran Jewelcrafter\'s Token.$B',objectives_loc4='Combine a Vrykul Amulet, a Dark Jade and a Bloodstone to make a Blood Jade Amulet and bring it to Timothy Jones in Dalaran.$B$BYou can find a Vrykul Amulet on any Northrend Vrykul.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Here is your Dalaran Jewelcrafter\'s Token as promised. Come back tomorrow and I am sure I will have another item I need from you!' WHERE entry=12958;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='A wealthy shipping concern has requested a collection of Glowing Ivory Figurines to sell at Undermine.   If you can bring me one, I can reward you with a Dalaran Jewelcrafter\'s Token.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Here is your Dalaran Jewelcrafter\'s Token as promised. Come back tomorrow and I am sure I will have another item I need from you!' WHERE entry=12959;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='A wealthy shipping concern has requested a collection of Wicked Sun Brooches to sell at Undermine.   If you can bring me one, I can reward you with a Dalaran Jewelcrafter\'s Token.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Here is your Dalaran Jewelcrafter\'s Token as promised. Come back tomorrow and I am sure I will have another item I need from you!' WHERE entry=12960;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='A wealthy shipping concern has requested a collection of Intricate Bone Figurines to sell at Undermine.   If you can bring me one, I can reward you with a Dalaran Jewelcrafter\'s Token.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Here is your Dalaran Jewelcrafter\'s Token as promised. Come back tomorrow and I am sure I will have another item I need from you!' WHERE entry=12961;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Bouldercrag reaches out to take the ore, but then recoils.>$B$BThat ore... I can\'t touch it. It seethes with unnatural energy. No creature of stone can handle it. What do they mean to do with this?' WHERE entry=12964;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Bouldercrag nods grimly.>$B$BYou\'ve weakened the stormforged considerably, but they\'ll keep fighting. Their casualties matter nothing to them, while our defenders continue to fall. Even if it costs them a hundred or a thousand iron corpses, they\'ll keep fighting until we\'ve been pounded to gravel.' WHERE entry=12965;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Reforging Thorim\'s armor? It can be done.$B$BFirst though, there\'s the matter of the anvil...' WHERE entry=12966;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='An honorable performance, $R. I shall inform the king of your assistance.$B$BThe anvil is nearly cool enough. I shall see you in Dun Niffelem soon.' WHERE entry=12967;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yulda had it coming. No one gets away with insulting the Hyldsmeet. Not even one of our own.' WHERE entry=12968;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, young one. It looks like our deal has been satisfied on both our ends.' WHERE entry=12969;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s settled then. You will compete in the Hyldsmeet and with my help you\'ll restore great Thorim to his rightful place.' WHERE entry=12970;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve done it, $N. You\'ve bested some of the fiercest fighters the Hyldnir race has to offer.' WHERE entry=12971;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Think we\'ll give you your own bear just like that? You\'ll have to prove yourself before you get anything from us.$B$BDo not think too highly of yourself just because you bested a few challengers in the Hyldsmeet.' WHERE entry=12972;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='King Stormheart sends his most sincere thanks for reuniting him with his brothers. It seems he\'s off to settle a score now - perhaps you\'ll meet with him again on Arthas\'s doorstep.' WHERE entry=12973;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Shifty sent you, eh?' WHERE entry=12974;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Another good deed you have done on Thorim\'s behalf, $C.$B$BThis will help to soften the hearts of my people towards him.' WHERE entry=12975;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Njormeld\'s eyes become noticeably moist as he pours the contents of the bag onto the anvil.>$B$BThe Horn of Hodir....$B$BThis was a sacred gift to our people from Hodir himself, $R. It is a relic of great importance to us.$B$BWhen you next return to our stronghold you shall see the fruits of your labor.$B$BFarewell.' WHERE entry=12976;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='You are to defeat 5 Niffelem Forefathers and 5 Restless Frostborn at Thunderfall. You are then to blow Hodir\'s Horn over their corpses, then return to Hodir\'s Horn in Dun Niffelem.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You are filled with a sense of peace and contentment knowing that the once tormented souls of Thunderfall are now resting peacefully.' WHERE entry=12977;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='There may be hope for victory, $N. We have never been able to sustain an attack on the stormforged, but with your efforts, Valduran may yet fall!' WHERE entry=12978;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Careful, now. Keep that plate as far away from me as you can. Even being in its presence is enough to inflict pain.$B$BBut you\'re right, $N, these are gigantic armor plates for a war golem of normal size. What would the stormforged be doing with them? There\'s only one way to find out.' WHERE entry=12979;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Bruor listens as you describe what you learned in the workshop.>$B$BSo Valduran\'s master has given him this sinister metal to construct a giant weapon? That must be what he intends to use for the final strike against us! We need to stop him before he\'s able to complete it and unleash this weapon.' WHERE entry=12980;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You feel a sense of accomplishment as you realize that your efforts continue to strengthen the renewed bonds between Thorim and the Sons of Hodir.' WHERE entry=12981;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $C. With the death knights that you freed, we\'ll be able to hold the line... for now.' WHERE entry=12982;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m impressed. I never thought I would see an icemaw matriarch again. Especially not one this size.' WHERE entry=12983;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='At last, Valduran is dead, and the stormforged are weakened, but if his boasting is true, we must continue fighting the stormforged in his absence. This weapon they\'re building could be the end of us.' WHERE entry=12984;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It is nearly done.$B$BWith this artifact in place, Dun Niffelem shall be warned of impending dangers before they are upon us.' WHERE entry=12985;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The news you bear forth is grave indeed. I do not know the fate of the remaining watchers, but their absence spells dark times for all of the lands of Azeroth.$B$BI shall examine the knowledge contained in the databank that you have returned and attempt to fully assess the situation. I believe I am in possession of knowledge that you deem more pertinent at this moment however, so I shall allow you to partake in said wisdom first.' WHERE entry=12986;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Temple of Life Investigated',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Temple of Order Investigated' WHERE entry=12986;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Njormeld gazes up at Hodir\'s Helm, visibly moved.>$B$BThat will do, little $R.$B$BThat will do....' WHERE entry=12987;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work! Oh, it won\'t stop the iron dwarves, but it\'ll take them valuable time to rebuild those forges. I daresay we\'ve gained the advantage.' WHERE entry=12988;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Jormungar are vile creatures. You did well in destroying them.' WHERE entry=12989;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='There were days when I could never ask someone to do what you did, but my experience with the iron dwarves has extinguished those feelings. We have bought time against the enemy\'s advance.' WHERE entry=12991;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='$N is my bestest little $R!' WHERE entry=12992;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Bouldercrag begins to look over the documents, his eyes wide.>$B$BI had no idea the irons were capable of this! Our men will have no chance against this behemoth if it\'s completed. Fortunately, it looks like they\'re still lacking a key part.' WHERE entry=12993;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='As you slide the chain back around the denmother\'s neck she licks your face approvingly.' WHERE entry=12994;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. Let them see the desecrated corpses of their fallen comrades and think twice about striking at us!$B$BIf you come back tomorrow, I will make certain to have more banners prepared for you.' WHERE entry=12995;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You\'ve been very fortunate, sister.  This is a matriarch the likes of which hasn\'t been seen in years.$B$BA good bear won\'t do you much good without the skill to ride it.$B$BI\'m going to have you practice some moves on Kirgaraak.  He\'s the largest yeti we\'ve ever managed to capture so be careful.  Don\'t be afraid to walk away if he gives you a beating... there\'s a reason why we keep him chained.',objectives_loc4='Astrid Bjornrittar in Brunnhildar Village wants you to use the Reins of the Warbear Matriarch to defeat Kirgaraak.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Not bad. I was hoping Kirgaraak would snap your neck so I could keep your bear.$B$BJust joking, $Gbrother:sister;. Well... half-joking. That\'s a really nice bear you\'ve got.' WHERE entry=12996;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You really did it! You made it out with your health. Wish we could say the same for your bear.$B$BIt\'s going to take a while for her to recover. Fortunately you won\'t need her for a while.' WHERE entry=12997;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='With the heart in the hands of Narvir, the colossus will achieve its full power! We\'ll have no choice but to fight it.' WHERE entry=12998;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='$N, you came.$B$BAlready I have heard of your activities on the Savage Ledge. This is good. I am glad that you seem willing to help with undermining the vrykul here at Jotunheim.$B$B<The face of the witch breaks into a reluctant grin as if she\'s fighting the will of Lady Nightswood.>$B$BYou and I are going to have a great deal of fun with them!' WHERE entry=12999;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These furs are rather... large. I\'d hate to see the worgs you had to face off with.$B$BWe\'re all very thankful. The temperature is starting to drop already.' WHERE entry=13000;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Stand back, $R, and behold the fulfilling of a prophecy!' WHERE entry=13001;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Welcome to de cold, mon.  Dis place may not be so good for keepin\' me bones warm, but I have learned how to cut me de perfect gem.  All I be needin\' is some gems to do me work on.$B$BBring me some gems and I be teachin\' you the skill of gem perfection.  Dis will allow you to sometimes cut a perfect gem with increased bonuses when cuttin\' an uncommon quality gem from Northrend.',objectives_loc4='Return two Huge Citrines, two Dark Jade and two Shadow Crystals to Geba\'li in Warsong Hold.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Dey be perfect mon\'.  Here is the art of gemcutting perfection for ya.' WHERE entry=13002;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It is done.$B$BYou have stared certain death in the face and emerged victorious.$B$BBy single-handedly defeating such a mighty beast, you have brought great honor to Dun Niffelem!' WHERE entry=13003;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you.  I shall teach you of gemcutting perfection and in addition give you a perfect gem that I have cut.' WHERE entry=13004;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s a good start. But my brother\'s forces will not take long to regroup. We must make our victory a decisive one.' WHERE entry=13005;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='As you coat the helm with a thin layer of oil, the frost falls away and the surface gleams.' WHERE entry=13006;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We\'ve done it, we\'ve really done it! The refuge is spared and the stormforged are defeated! We must warn Brann before Loken gets it in his mind to try to rebuild his forces. The only way to secure the victory you have won today is to go into Ulduar and defeat Loken for all time!' WHERE entry=13007;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Crusade Commander Entari at the Argent Vanguard in Icecrown has asked that you free 8 Webbed Crusaders.',offerrewardtext_loc4='There are still many Argent Crusade soldiers out on that field and in Scourgeholme, $N. While your help is appreciated, there is still much left to be done.' WHERE entry=13008;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<As you present Thorim with the reforged suit of armor, he is visibly stricken by its splendor.>$B$BYou have done well, $R, but there remains much to be done.' WHERE entry=13009;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Words cannot express my gratitude, $C.$B$BYou have served me honorably. Please accept this token of my gratitude.' WHERE entry=13010;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I have an opportunity that will help you to gain approval with my people, provided you prevail.$B$BThe jormungar are a nuisance best dealt with quickly. If given any quarter, they breed like hares and spread like fire.$B$BThey have appeared southwest of here, in the Hibernal Cavern. If their spawnmother is not slain soon, they will gain a foothold in our region.$B$BShe cannot refuse food. Take this knife and get the flank of a bear corpse from their cave. Place it near her crater and kill her as she feeds.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So it is done.$B$BWe have heard the screams of Jormuttar as they echoed from across the valley.$B$BYou have done our people a service this day, litte $R.' WHERE entry=13011;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Sardis the Elder' WHERE entry=13012;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Fargal the Elder' WHERE entry=13015;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='One by one, my brother\'s servants have fallen. Loken\'s insurrection will soon come to an end.' WHERE entry=13035;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Where both the Alliance and the Horde failed, the Argent Crusade succeeded. The success, however, was short lived. Our breach into Icecrown was quickly - and with force - rebuffed.$B$BThe Lich King\'s retaliatory strike was immediate and brutal. Now we are on the defensive.' WHERE entry=13036;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='How many of them could there possibly be? we\'ve killed enough to fill ten graveyards and still they come. The situation looks grim, friend.' WHERE entry=13039;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $N. I will begin the tests on these samples immediately. It is my hope that a cure will be found soon.' WHERE entry=13040;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Here is your Dalaran Jewelcrafter\'s Token as promised. I have new shipments going out all the time, check by from time to time to see what I need.' WHERE entry=13041;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Very interesting. It sounds to me that you handled that perfectly. I\'m surprised that the doctor was using a vargul as an assistant given what he was working on.' WHERE entry=13042;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You discovered and put an end to the doctor\'s machinations.$B$B<The banshee-controlled witch smiles and places a large hand gently upon your shoulder.>$B$BThat\'s a fine poke in the eye for the Lich King, but I think we can do better.' WHERE entry=13043;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Penumbrius nods.>$B$BMy kin will help. Together we will battle the Lich King and his undead legions.' WHERE entry=13044;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Arthas... He strikes recklessly - without care or caution. We have caught him off guard.$B$B<Highlord Tirion Fordring pauses, lost in thought for a moment.>$B$BWe will bolster our defenses and weather the storm.$B$BHow good are you with a cannon, $N?' WHERE entry=13045;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='As you anchor the tooth in Arngrim\'s jaw, you get the impression that your efforts may have taken the edge off of the old king\'s hunger pangs... for now.' WHERE entry=13046;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='No... it cannot be...$B$BNo one can defeat Thorim in single combat. Not a giant, nor a beast... no one! Especially not that coward of a brother of his.$B$BOn my forefather\'s names, this I swear...$B$BLoken will pay for this!' WHERE entry=13047;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes... these will do. Let us hope my plan works, $N.$B$BVeranus is a great drake. I\'d hate to have to settle for a lesser one.' WHERE entry=13050;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s good to have my old friend back. It appears that my luck is finally starting to change... and it\'s all thanks to you, little friend.' WHERE entry=13051;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This hurts bad, mon. Don\'t know if I\'m gonna make it.' WHERE entry=13054;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I thank you, mon. I might live another day now.' WHERE entry=13055;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m already feeling much better, mon. Not sure if it\'s the antidote or the news of that filthy worg getting what he deserved.' WHERE entry=13056;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We\'re here, $N. My brother\'s forces will learn the meaning of defeat today.' WHERE entry=13057;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $C... thank you!$B$BYou\'ve given me the satisfaction of knowing that the coward who made me into this will rot for all eternity as surely as I will.$B$BNow leave before I lose control of myself and cut you down.' WHERE entry=13059;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Olut winces.>$B$BThat looked painful. It was a pretty grand entrance though.$B$BAre you here to help us find a path into Icecrown? As you can see, our first foray in that direction didn\'t end too admirably. I\'m thinking we might be better off breaching the place from another side.' WHERE entry=13060;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'ve really made it this far. Never would I have thought you\'d progress so quickly among the hyldnir.' WHERE entry=13061;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Are you ready to ride, $Gbrother:sister;? There is no coming back.' WHERE entry=13062;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So, $Gbrother:sister;, you think that completing a few simple chores makes you a heroine?$B$BYou shall learn....' WHERE entry=13063;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You now know a bit of the history of this land... my land.$B$BI call upon you to assist me in setting these wrongs to right.' WHERE entry=13064;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Back! Careful! The plague has gripped me and I\'ll not see it spread to you nor anyone else.' WHERE entry=13068;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are a true champion for the cause, $N!$B$BWon\'t you please come speak to me again tomorrow? I\'m certain that there will be more of those nasty proto-drakes to shoot down.' WHERE entry=13069;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We must be quick or face being overtaken by the Scourge! There\'s really no time for instructions, $R. You\'re just going to have to jump in and hope for the best.' WHERE entry=13070;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yay, yay! $N is best proto-drake stealer.$B$BYou come back tomorrow and we make more fire!!!' WHERE entry=13071;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Bridenbrad has contracted the plague? I cannot imagine a worse fate for one who has devoted his life to the ways of light, nor can I fathom leaving him to die without lifting a finger to help.$B$BNo, undeath shall not be his fate. We shall find a way to aid this hero.' WHERE entry=13072;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hello child.$B$BI understand Tirion\'s request and trust in his judgment, we will see what we can do for this Crusader Bridenbrad. What you ask is no simple task - the scourge are not of this world, and many have failed in attempting to strip their corruption over the years.$B$BIn a being of nobility and light, all is not without hope.' WHERE entry=13073;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work, young one.' WHERE entry=13074;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Tirion sent you to Remulos? I\'m... I\'m flattered. One does not call favors in with beings of such power idly, no matter how noble or altruistic they might be. You too are kind to have gone to such lengths on my behalf. You have my thanks.$B$BPlant the seed - I am ready.' WHERE entry=13075;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It saddens me to hear that it did not work. No reason to fret though, I have met other beings of good that may still be of aid to us.' WHERE entry=13076;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Greetings to you, $R.$B$BThe concern is clear on your face. Please tell me what troubles you.' WHERE entry=13077;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='With Dahlia\'s Tears and ancient magic, I fashion you some small amount of hope for your great crusader.' WHERE entry=13078;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The breath of Alexstrasza... you have gone to the dragon-queen herself? I\'m extremely grateful.$B$BI understand the risks of such cleansing and I am prepared. Proceed, $C.' WHERE entry=13079;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Scourge plague is no simple foe to defeat. Alexstrasza\'s words suggest that perhaps we can yet save our Bridenbrad from the unimaginable fate of the unliving should he fall, but I will not give him up so easily.$B$BThere is yet one more path of light I would like to pursue. One more being who might avert this horrible fate.' WHERE entry=13080;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<A gentle ringing fills your head as you approach the naaru.>$B$BI know why you have come.' WHERE entry=13081;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<As you approach Crusader Bridenbrad, you cannot help but notice that his skin has taken on a pale hue and his breaths are shallow. It is clear that he has little time left.>$B$BYou have returned to me, $C. I must admit... it is good to see you again... your face renews my hope that this land will be free of Arthas\'s grasp one day soon. I\'m proud to have met you...' WHERE entry=13082;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I am glad you were able to save him from undeath. With A\'dal\'s blessing, he will know no evil in his afterlife.$B$BWe shall take heart in his shining example and in your selflessness. Thank you for all that you have done.' WHERE entry=13083;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The duke looks at you a moment and nods.>$B$BYou\'re inflicting horrible mental trauma on the Jotunheim vrykul. This is where they were first reawakened. It is a place of significant importance to them, second only to Ymirheim.$B$BYou must keep up the pressure there while I hold the vault from the assault of the Lich King.' WHERE entry=13084;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I think I can guess why you\'re here, $N.' WHERE entry=13085;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You handled the cannon like a goblin gunner, friend. You\'ve saved the Vanguard and the Argent Crusade - all the while backing the Highlord himself up on the field of battle! Amazing!' WHERE entry=13086;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ya gots me meat!  Here is your recipe, I gots cookin to do!' WHERE entry=13087;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That will keep our recruits fed!  Here\'s how you cook it.' WHERE entry=13088;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='We can quickly turn this flesh into stew.' WHERE entry=13089;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I give my thanks to you.' WHERE entry=13090;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I have never seen such terror in the eyes of a vrykul. They think themselves masters of their world.$B$BYou and I are going to prove them wrong. Very wrong.' WHERE entry=13091;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='And now we shall see what the future holds for you.$B$B<The Bone Witch casts the bones upon the rug in front of her.>$B$BChoose your fate, $C.' WHERE entry=13092;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Choose your fate, $N.' WHERE entry=13093;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Archmage Berinand is the Kirin Tor\'s foremost authority on Malygos. He\'s spent his life studying the aspect and his behaviors.$B$BRecently, he loaned me his research on the Arcanomicron, some sort of map that Malygos is trying to assemble. I made the mistake of discussing it with a group of Horde adventurers while they were restocking their goods here - and now it\'s gone!$B$BIt must have been them, $C. Please, follow them into the nexus and recover the book before Berinand comes to recover it.',objectives_loc4='Librarian Serrah wants you to enter the Nexus and recover Berinand\'s Research.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You found it!? Yes, yes, it\'s all here.$B$BPlease, take this with my gratitude. And if it\'s not too much to ask, it would be better for me if Berinand never learned of this.' WHERE entry=13094;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Archmage Berinand is the Kirin Tor\'s foremost authority on Malygos. He\'s spent his life studying the aspect and his behaviors.$B$BRecently, he loaned me his research on the Arcanomicron, some sort of map that Malygos is trying to assemble. I made the mistake of discussing it with a group of Alliance adventurers while they were restocking their goods here - and now it\'s gone!$B$BIt must have been them, $C. Please, follow them into the nexus and find the book before Berinand comes to recover it from me.',objectives_loc4='Librarian Serrah wants you to enter the Nexus and recover Berinand\'s Research.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You found it!? Yes, yes, it\'s all here.$B$BPlease, take this with my gratitude. And if it\'s not too much to ask, it would be better for me if Berinand never learned of this.' WHERE entry=13095;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ya done it?! Gal\'darah be no more?$B$BHere ya go, mon. Take dis gift for bringin\' justice to that wretch.' WHERE entry=13096;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Lissen up, mon. Dere be dangerous work ta be done!' WHERE entry=13097;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Bah\'Kini scans the engraved tablets for a moment, then turns her attention back to you.>$B$BDese be authentic, $R. I\'ll be placin\' dem in their proper place in my collection.$B$BPerhaps we can finally be puttin\' an end to dis behavior.' WHERE entry=13098;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Long-time student? Hah!$B$BIf by long-time ya mean my whole life, den I suppose dat be accurate.$B$BTo\'kini be my cowardly father - too fearful to take up a position so near Gundrak... so he sent me!' WHERE entry=13099;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This looks great!  Thanks!' WHERE entry=13100;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This is plenty of food for everyone!  I am sure the customers will be pleased.' WHERE entry=13101;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Ajay Green the innkeeper in the Dalaran sewers needs a vegetable stew for his customers as they are running low on food down there.$B$BCollect 4 Crystalsong Carrots from the Crystalsong Forest and cook them together with 4 Chilled Meat.$B$B You can get to the Crystalsong Forest from the portal chamber in the eastern corner of Runeweaver Square.$B$BOnce the vegetable stew is ready, bring it to Ajay.',objectives_loc4='Cook 4 Crystalsong Carrots from Crystalsong Forest with 4 Chilled Meat in the Cookpot.$B$BOnce it is ready bring the Vegetable Stew to the Dalaran sewers Innkeeper Ajay Green.',offerrewardtext_loc4='This will be consumed in no time!   Thanks!' WHERE entry=13102;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Ranid Glowergold in the Leatherworkers shop in Dalaran has had a sudden craving for wine and cheese.$B$BCollect cheese which is on the shelf at "One More Glass" in central Dalaran and half full wine glasses found on tables all over the city.  Pour the wine together into a bottle and serve it with the cheese to Ranid.$B$BWe don\'t think he will know the difference.',objectives_loc4='Combine the empty cheese platter with Aged Dalaran Limburger from the cheese shop "One More Glass" and with 6 Half Full Dalaran Wine Glasses found on tables around Dalaran.$B$BBring the Wine and Cheese platter to Ranid Glowergold at the Leatherworkers in the Magus Commerce Exchange.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Aha, this appears to be a fine vintage!' WHERE entry=13103;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='My knowledge of Scourge tactics is without equal.$B$B<The Ebon Watcher peers at you.>$B$BBefore the battle for Light\'s Hope Chapel, my knights and I served under the Lich King - his icy grasp controlling our every action. The light of dawn changed everything...' WHERE entry=13104;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Your power has grown, my faithful knight.$B$B<Highlord Darion Mograine peers at you.>$B$BVengeance is at hand, $Gbrother:sister;. Koltira aids the Horde upon the gunship, Orgrim\'s Hammer, while Thassarian assists the Alliance aboard the Skybreaker. The Ebon Blade will soon wash over Icecrown and leave the armies of the Lich King in ruin.' WHERE entry=13105;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good. We\'ll need all the help we can get. Olakin here is the Argent Crusade\'s contribution to our effort. Let\'s cut the chatter and get down to the business of denying the Scourge their armies of the flesh.' WHERE entry=13106;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Perfect!  I Just hope the Dalaran Destroyers finally win one!' WHERE entry=13107;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That vile worm is dead?$B$BYou have turned out to be a great boon to my people, little $R.$B$BPlease accept this gift in return for your loyal friendship.' WHERE entry=13108;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Volkhan shall haunt the dreams of my people no more.$B$BContinue your efforts, little $R. In time, I am certain my people will grow to forgive Thorim.' WHERE entry=13109;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The path of the righteous crusader is one beset by inequity and evil. To cut through the middle is the only salvation. You have done that on this day and much more.' WHERE entry=13110;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ahh, yeah mon! Dat be what I\'m lookin\' for.$B$BHere ya go - take somethin\' nice for your troubles.' WHERE entry=13111;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Is this food from Awilo? Can you promise me there isn\'t any gnome in it?' WHERE entry=13112;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='My guests should find this acceptable. Just don\'t tell them it came from Awilo.' WHERE entry=13113;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Cook 4 Crystalsong Carrots from Crystalsong Forest with 4 Chilled Meat in the Cookpot.$B$BThen bring the Vegetable Stew to the Dalaran sewers Innkeeper Ajay Green.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Stew looks good. Thanks for your help.' WHERE entry=13114;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Ranid Glowergold in da Leatherworkers shop be havin\' a need for wine and cheese.  Why he don\'t want some tasty gnome is beyond me.$B$BCollect da cheese from da cheese shop in central Dalaran and da half full wine glasses found on tables around da city.  Bring da wine and serve it with the cheese to Ranid.$B$BYou can call da wine a Wine Medley, mon\'.',objectives_loc4='Combine the empty cheese platter with Aged Dalaran Limburger from the cheese shop "One More Glass" and with 6 Half Full Dalaran Wine Glasses found on tables around Dalaran.$B$BBring the Wine and Cheese platter to Ranid Glowergold at the Leatherworkers in the Magus Commerce Exchange.',offerrewardtext_loc4='This wine is quite amazing! I must know where it\'s from.' WHERE entry=13115;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Perfect!  I Just hope the Dalaran Destroyers finally win one!' WHERE entry=13116;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<You tell the darkrider about your discoveries at the summoning altar.>$B$BI suspected such. We can\'t let this continue. Our first priority is to destroy those summoning altars and then deal with the mess the Scourge has already created here.' WHERE entry=13117;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well, $N. Keeping their numbers down will give the Argent Crusade the time that they need to set a foundation.' WHERE entry=13118;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Darkrider Arly nods in approval.>$B$BGood. Now, we can focus our efforts on shutting down the rest of the Fleshwerks.' WHERE entry=13119;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Third Summoning Altar destroyed',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Fourth Summoning Altar destroyed' WHERE entry=13119;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Darkrider Arly closes her eyes and seems to focus on something far away.>$B$BWith the eyes of death itself, I watch our enemy. With this knowledge, we will utterly destroy them.' WHERE entry=13120;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Perfect! It\'s true that Iskalder is rumored to have been the finest vrykul warrior ever to live. And Vardmadra herself is going to come here to judge him!$B$BWe must move quickly if we are to get to this ancient hero before they do!' WHERE entry=13121;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Now let me see if there\'s something that I can do with these stones to give us a little bit of insight.' WHERE entry=13122;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The battle goes on, $N. Somehow we have managed to avoid detection and continue our attempts to frustrate Malygos\' schemes. This, though, is where the good news ends and the bad begins.$B$BOur best efforts have had little or no effect. Malygos and his underlings grow stronger in power with each passing day. And now, our latest assault team has been captured and is being held in the Oculus.$B$BWe must attempt a rescue! Belgaristrasz and his companions are invaluable to our cause. Can we count on you, $N?',objectives_loc4='Raelorasz wants you to enter the Oculus and rescue Belgaristrasz  and his companions.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Listen well, $R.$B$BYour work here has just begun!' WHERE entry=13124;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A hard fought victory, $N! The lieutenants will be replaced, but at least for today the air about Scourgeholme stands still.' WHERE entry=13125;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Please accept our gratitude, $R.$B$BYou and your friends have succeeded where we had failed - you have bested Drakos. From here, however, it will take our combined efforts to proceed.$B$BAbove us, Varos hides behind an impenetrable shield. To reach him, you must defeat the Centrifuge Constructs that power his shield. That is where my friends and I come in....$B$BWe each can provide you with drakes from our respective flights. Only with the help of these drakes will you be able to expose Varos.',offerrewardtext_loc4='It is as I had hoped, $R. We work well together.$B$BMay our continued cooperation be enough to overcome the challenges that yet await!' WHERE entry=13126;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Only one obstacle stands between us and our ultimate goal here, $C. His name is Urom.$B$BAbove us, guarding the third ring, he awaits us. Beware his powerful conjurings, friend. He is a frightful opponent, certain to challenge your prowess.$B$BBring him down. Make him pay for his treacherous allegiance to the enemy!',offerrewardtext_loc4='Victory is in reach, friend.$B$BFocus, for now comes the true test.' WHERE entry=13127;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The time has come to face Eregos, friend.$B$BHe is cunning and strong. One of Malygos\' most trusted minions, he draws strength from the energies he is charged with defending - sipping from the well of the great aspect himself.$B$BThis shall not be easy....$B$BHowever, defeating the Mage-Lord has allowed us to unlock the full power of our drakes. Their skills shall be at your command. Use them wisely and Eregos shall surely fall.$B$BShould you succeed, return to Raelorasz and inform him of our victory.',objectives_loc4='Belgaristrasz wants you to kill Eregos in the Oculus and then report to Raelorasz at the Transitus Shield in Coldarra.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Raelorasz listens intently to your report.>$B$B$N, this is most welcome news.$B$BNot since the onset of this conflict have we dealt a blow of this magnitude to the Lord of Magic.$B$BPlease, friend, accept the gratitude of our unified dragonflights.' WHERE entry=13128;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Too lazy for their own good.... Wait! I know how to teach \'em!$B$B<Kurzel rips a long strip of material from her blouse and hands it to you.>$B$BHere, $R, take this. Dip it in the remains of that annoying lich over there and return it to Mack back at the camp.$B$BOnce the boys have stewed in their guilt for a while I\'ll show up and let them off the hook.$B$BThey\'ll learn not to let a lady wander off alone!',objectives_loc4='Kurzel wants you to use Kurzel\'s Blouse Scrap at the corpse of Novos the Summoner, then take the Ichor-Stained Cloth to Mack.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Mack looks at you and laughs uncontrollably.>$B$BAww noo... Why\'d she hafta run off an\' git \'ershelf killed?$B$BYa know, I should write a lil shong about \'er. That should cheer me up!$B$B<hic>' WHERE entry=13129;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Heartwood by nature is resistant to disease, rot and plague. This heartwood, however, goes so far as to repel such things! The masonry, affected by the fallout of the Unbound Thicket, will work in much the same way.$B$BSoon we will break ground.' WHERE entry=13130;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Just look at it! Me trunk never been so empty. Shoulda been filled ten times over by now!$B$BMe mates jumped at the sight o\' all that booty, and now look at \'em! Rattlin\' bones, they be!$B$BIt be like me mammy use \'ta tell me - only thing worse than no treasure be cursed treasure.$B$BSay, thar be plenty o\' loot farther in, an\' not the cursed kind I\'ll wager. These sots not be needin\' it - it just be junk ta them.$B$BFetch it fer me an\' I\'ll be rewardin\' ya handsomely, matey.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Brilliant! Ye\'ve gone and done it, matey.$B$BNow I can show me face to the Cap\'n without fearin\' fer me life, thanks be ta you and yer mates.$B$BHere\'s a little booty fer you in return.' WHERE entry=13131;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Och! They cannae be blamed, $G lad:lass;. Who\'da done different?$B$BThey hurled themselves at them piles o\' gold - thought they\'d hit the mother lode, they did. Aye... But look at \'em now. Mindless servants unable to pick up a single doubloon.$B$BOnly luck spared me from the same fate. In the scurry I got knocked down - was a wee bit tipsy to begin with. Looked up ta see the first of \'em turn...$B$BBe a good $G lad:lass; and find the one in charge here and teach \'em not ta be cursin\' me mates.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Splendid! Mebbe now me mateys be able ta rest in peace.$B$BHere ya go, $G lad:lass;. Don\'t let it be said that ol\' Brigg weren\'t generous ta those who showed \'im a kindness.$B$BGood doin\' business wit yeh.' WHERE entry=13132;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='He\'s a fine specimen and will serve us well.$B$BNow, we have to make sure to use him properly to trap Vardmadra!' WHERE entry=13133;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<A dark, hollow laugh greets you as you report to the darkrider.>$B$BYou reek of victory, $N, and that is good news, indeed.' WHERE entry=13134;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, this is perfect. The bomber should be up and running in no time.' WHERE entry=13135;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Olakin handles the shards of metal gingerly.>$B$BYou saw these on all of the ghouls down there? I\'ve never seen anything like this in all my battles against the Scourge.' WHERE entry=13136;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'ve put Vardmadra aside for the moment. She\'s someplace safe until we can enact our final revenge!' WHERE entry=13137;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='There is no doubt, this is raw saronite. we\'ve seen weapons made from it in the hands of the Lich King\'s chosen before, but this is the first time it\'s been used to arm anything else. The scale of that mining operation must be huge.' WHERE entry=13138;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Silas and Spitzpatrick have signed off on the materials and fuel needed to begin construction of Justice Keep. Thanks to you and the Ebon Blade the Scourge presence within Scourgeholme has been decimated and their lieutenants have been defeated.$B$BI have chosen the site at which we will break ground, but first you must deliver my report to Highlord Tirion Fordring. We will begin our march into Icecrown on his command.$B',objectives_loc4='Deliver Father Gustav\'s Report to Highlord Tirion Fordring at the Argent Vanguard in Icecrown.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Your assistance has been integral in securing the front. The first true victory of this war is close at hand - which is why our next step is the most crucial.$B$BRest assured, $N, the Scourge will not give up without a fight. Your most difficult challenge awaits.' WHERE entry=13139;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These plates match the shards almost exactly. They must be using cuttings from them to "enhance" the ghouls produced here. The Scourge is desperate enough to make a weapon of anything, it seems. All the more reason to hasten our destruction of this abominable place!' WHERE entry=13140;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Blessed Light! We have taken the pinnacle! Finally, construction of Justice Keep can begin. Highlord Fordring and the knights are already en route to our new base. You must meet them there, $N!' WHERE entry=13141;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Words cannot describe what I\'m feeling at the moment, $N. My revenge is complete and there is naught else for me to do.$B$BIf only I could be there when the Lich King is finally taken down.$B$BDon\'t fool yourself though, Jotunheim is far from \'dealt\' with. I will remain in possession of this witch until such time as the vrykul are no longer a threat.$B$BLook around, there are many items of value in this cave. Take your pick.' WHERE entry=13142;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'ve chained the wretch to the post over there and I\'ll look into getting my hands on more of them.$B$BNow lets make some use of that eye.' WHERE entry=13143;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ah, good. There\'s nothing like the smell of roasted putrid flesh in the morning. That\'s the smell of victory over the Scourge.' WHERE entry=13144;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work. It seems more death knights remained loyal to Arthas than I initially thought.$B$BHe certainly is sparing nothing in his attempt to replace Acherus. A pure Saronite citadel would be hard to destroy indeed. There\'s no need to destroy it though... we can halt production and put down these death knight leaders here and now, before they become a real threat.$B$BMost importantly, we need to disrupt them enough to get those death knights away from from the leaders so that we can make our strike.' WHERE entry=13145;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Icy Lookout explored',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Runeworks explored' WHERE entry=13145;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We need to cause some disruption... anything to bring those death knights away from their leaders. If we lay waste to their minions below, I suspect they\'ll have to devote more attention to keeping a close eye on operations.$B$BAbominations are easy prey - slow, predictable, and most importantly, stupid. Take advantage of their trust of the stalkers to drag them some of the Scourge bombs scattered throughout the construction area. You\'ll be able light the bombs far before they figure out what\'s going on.',offerrewardtext_loc4='They didn\'t even think to lay a hand on you, did they? At least they\'re predictable.' WHERE entry=13146;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='No need to sacrifice our own men when they are this easily manipulated, eh?' WHERE entry=13147;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='This damaged necklace has an invoice with it that reads "Property of Timothy Jones - Cartier and Co Fine Jewelry - Magus Commerce Exhange - Dalaran".$B$BPerhaps you should repair it and return it to him.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='How did you find this!  Many of these necklaces were looted from one of my shipments a few weeks ago!  Let me repay you with this Jewelcrafter\'s Token.' WHERE entry=13148;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Always meddling...$B$BThe Infinite Dragonflight seek to disrupt history as we have come to know it by deceiving Prince Arthas.$B$BIf they can convince him that none of the grain here carries the plague, then he\'ll never have to make the fateful decision to cull Stratholme.$B$BThis must not come to pass.$B$BUse this Arcane Disruptor on any suspicious crates of grain you find to reveal them for what they are. Meet me near Stratholme\'s entrance, north of this place, when the work is done.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well, friend. The plagued grain was exposed to Arthas\' troops.$B$BListen carefully, now. There remains more to be done.' WHERE entry=13149;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The Infinite Dragonflight are not likely to give up so easily. I cannot be certain of what they\'re up to, but something tells me we haven\'t seen the last of them today.$B$BIn just a moment, Arthas will face a desperate dilemma, and make a momentous decision.$B$BDon\'t lose focus now, $N. I needn\'t remind you how much is at stake. I must call upon you to accompany the prince in his culling of Stratholme.$B$BArthas must make it through Stratholme alive and you must see to it that he defeats Mal\'Ganis!',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well, $N.$B$BThe Infinites have been foiled and this thread of history remains intact.$B$BI thank you for your invaluable assistance, as does the entire Bronze Dragonflight.' WHERE entry=13151;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Dakrider Arly throws her head back and laughs darkly.>$B$BA fitting end for the \'good\' doctor, wouldn\'t you say?' WHERE entry=13152;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Augh. It\'s still dripping. Couldn\'t you have at least dried it off first?' WHERE entry=13153;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent! This will help fuel the flames of war for days to come.' WHERE entry=13154;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Vile Hold... a testament to how much Arthas hates losing. Let\'s drive the blade deep.' WHERE entry=13155;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='My, it its quite chilly up here! Reminds me of the stormy peaks of Kaarinos on Argus. However, with all of this snow and ice, our soldiers can easily catch cold.$B$BHead to the Steppe of Life in southwestern Wintergrasp, and bring me back 10 of the Horde herb pouches you find. I will grind them into a medicine to help protect against the cold.$B$BThe Horde have been seen collecting them from the plant life in the area. Do not hesitate to slay them and retrieve the herbs!',objectives_loc4='Anchorite Tessa in Wintergrasp Fortress wants you to retrieve 10 Horde Herb Pouches from Horde players in the Steppe of Life.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent! This will help protect our troops against the cold.' WHERE entry=13156;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A long and arduous journey awaits us as we make our way to the gates of Icecrown Citadel. I, and the soldiers of the Argent Crusade, wish to thank you for all that you have done. We rest easier knowing that you will fight alongside us in this cursed place.$B$B<Highlord Tirion Fordring salutes.>' WHERE entry=13157;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Not a moment too soon.$B$BAre you prepared to defend Dalaran, $C?' WHERE entry=13158;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Warden Alturas wants you to enter the Violet Hold and put and end to the blue dragon invasion force. You are to report back to him once Cyanigosa is slain.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The crisis is averted, then?$B$BThat is good news indeed. I will forward the news on to Rhonin.$B$BPlease, accept this with the gratitude of Dalaran.' WHERE entry=13159;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Not so much of a threat when they\'re sleeping.' WHERE entry=13160;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The world will be a much better place without Rokir in it - trust me.' WHERE entry=13161;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I can\'t deny, I\'ll miss her laugh... and that smile that would creep onto her face just before she killed someone. A little less need to watch my back though, so I suppose I can\'t complain.' WHERE entry=13162;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So he finally lost? Good to hear.' WHERE entry=13163;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Morgraine himself arrived to see the deed done then? I imagine there was some ill blood between those two - no surprise that he wanted a piece of the wretch.$B$BYou\'ve done exceedingly well, $R, and you shall be awarded appropriately. The Ebon Blade thanks you.' WHERE entry=13164;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Lich King has returned to Northrend, wounded by the Ashbringer, but the second floor still holds the last of his armies.' WHERE entry=13165;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, death knight. The remaining Scourge will be dealt with in short order and the rebuilding process will begin anew.$B$BI have but one last task for you.
' WHERE entry=13166;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<A fierce glow emanantes from all of Kilix\'s eyes as he stares at the husk.>$B$BIt is DONE!$B$B$R! Your name shall be recorded in the history of our people.$B$BI am in your debt....' WHERE entry=13167;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Nothing to it, eh? Any intelligent being should have little trouble controlling lesser undead. I suspect only the likes of a true necromancer could use these to sieze control of any of the more powerful undead. That won\'t be a problem though - I can already think of quite a variety of destruction we can wreak with even the most paltry minions.$B$BShall we have at it then?' WHERE entry=13168;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Put them right to sleep, didn\'t it?' WHERE entry=13169;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Without even getting your hands dirty.' WHERE entry=13170;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work. We should have little threat in the air then.' WHERE entry=13171;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Practically defenseless. It doesn\'t get much easier than that.' WHERE entry=13172;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Let\'s see here... what do we have...$B$B<Keritose buries his head in the papers for a bit, seemingly gleaning little that he did not already know. Suddenly he finds what he is looking for...>$B$BMalykriss! The Vile Hold. It seems Arthas did not take the loss of his death knights so well... I\'m not exactly sure what he\'s doing with all of that Saronite, but I have a feeling he might be overcompensating for something.$B$BThat boy is not used to losing.' WHERE entry=13174;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Glorious! Truly, you are among the champions of the Alliance.' WHERE entry=13177;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Lok\'tar! Victory for the Horde!' WHERE entry=13178;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Welcome to the Wintergrasp, $N. Your mission is simple. Defeat ten of the Horde\'s finest. Now, go! Bring victory to the Alliance!',offerrewardtext_loc4='Glorious! Truly, you are among the champions of the Alliance.' WHERE entry=13179;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Welcome to the Wintergrasp, $N. Warlord Garrosh demands one thing: Slay them all!$B$BReturn to me when ten of the strongest members of the Alliance are dead.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Lok\'tar! Victory for the Horde!' WHERE entry=13180;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Just what I wanted to hear! A victory in Lake Wintergrasp - even a temporary one - is crucial to our overall strategy against the Horde.' WHERE entry=13181;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It saddens me to see that things have come to this. If only we could return our great empire to what it once was...' WHERE entry=13182;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It is a truly great thing you have accomplished this day. Be recognized for your sacrifice!' WHERE entry=13183;
UPDATE locales_quest SET EndText_loc4='Victory in Lake Wintergrasp' WHERE entry=13183;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good job. Murp wish he was there to help.' WHERE entry=13185;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent. That should slow down their assault.' WHERE entry=13186;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well, $C.$B$BMay your deeds renew hope for our people, that someday we may reclaim the city of our ancestors.' WHERE entry=13187;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You are now, and forever will be, a Knight of the Ebon Blade, $N, but know this: you were once a hero of the Alliance.$B$B<Darion stares at you.>$B$BThis order must establish allies for itself if it is to survive. You must represent the Knights of the Ebon Blade to the Alliance.$B$BOn the platform, southeast of me, is a portal to Stormwind City. Take this letter, given to me on your behalf by Lord Fordring, and deliver it to King Varian Wrynn. Use the portal.',objectives_loc4='Deliver the letter to King Varian Wrynn of the Alliance at Stormwind Keep in Stormwind City.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Varian stares off into the distance.>$B$BIndeed old friend... Blood and honor.$B$B<Varian affixes his gaze upon you.>$B$BWere it not for this letter from Tirion, you would be a stain upon my floor. Only an endorsement from one of the greatest paladins to ever live could have ensured your survival.$B$BWe... We will work together against the Scourge. Against the Lich King!$B$BGLORY TO THE ALLIANCE!' WHERE entry=13188;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You are now, and forever will be, a Knight of the Ebon Blade, $N, but know this: you were once a hero of the Horde.$B$B<Darion stares at you.>$B$BThis order must establish allies for itself if it is to survive. You must represent the Knights of the Ebon Blade to the Horde.$B$BOn the platform, southeast of me, is a portal to Orgrimmar. Take this letter, given to me on your behalf by Lord Fordring, and deliver it to Thrall. Use the portal.',objectives_loc4='Deliver the letter to Thrall, Warchief of the Horde at Orgrimmar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Eitrigg is alive because of this paladin. He would have been executed had Lord Fordring not broken him out of Stratholme.$B$BTirion Fordring, to have sacrificed everything to save the life of an orc... I have ever only known one other human to make such a sacrifice.$B$B<Thrall blinks back a tear.>$B$BYou will be in my heart always, Taretha.$B$BYes. For Tirion Fordring and for Eitrigg! We will accept you as a member of the Horde and your order as allies.$B$BBlood and honor! For the Horde!' WHERE entry=13189;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ahah!$B$BMay the mocking scent of failure eat at their empty souls!$B$BThank you, $C. Today, you have struck a blow against the unliving.' WHERE entry=13190;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent! This will help us defeat the Alliance in the battles to come!' WHERE entry=13191;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Ooh, ya dats da stuff, mon!' WHERE entry=13192;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, I guess its another night of sharpening bones for me. Why didn\'t I stay in Silvemoon City like my brother?' WHERE entry=13193;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent! This will help protect our troops against the cold.' WHERE entry=13195;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bowyer Randolph in Wintergrasp wants you to retrieve 10 Quivers of Dragonbone Arrows from Horde players at the Forest of Shadows.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent! This will help fuel the flames of war for days to come.' WHERE entry=13196;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent! This will help fuel the flames of war for days to come.' WHERE entry=13197;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Augh. It\'s still dripping. Couldn\'t you have at least dried it off first?' WHERE entry=13198;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Lieutenant Vieron Blazefeather in Wintergrasp wants you to retrieve 10 Quivers of Dragonbone Arrows from Alliance players at the Forest of Shadows.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, I guess its another night of sharpening bones for me. Why didn\'t I stay in Silvemoon City like my brother?' WHERE entry=13199;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent! That should put a dent in their war machines!' WHERE entry=13200;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Do you have any idea what you\'ve been carrying around, $C?$B$BThe cave beasts you\'ve been harvesting have no traditional method of excreting their waste. You might want to wash your hands...$B$BThank you for the thought, but if you come across any more of these please keep them for yourself.' WHERE entry=13204;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Mordun whistles.>$B$BWill ya just look at \'em? Incredible.$B$BI half expected these neanderthals to be swingin\' around clubs and throwin\' rock.$B$BNo such luck...' WHERE entry=13205;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We must discover the secret to these savages\' weapons!$B$BIf you\'d have seen how easily they cut through my companions, you\'d understand my sense of urgency. Just have a look at their forge if you doubt my words.$B$BScour the place. Gather all of their arms that you can carry and bring them to Anselm for his inspection.$B$BDo not fail us, $C. Every weapon you are able to bring out of this place is one less that we must face in the field.',objectives_loc4='Dark Ranger Marrah wants you to steal 5 Vrykul Weapons from Utgarde Keep and bring them to High Executor Anselm in Vengeance Landing.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Marrah has informed us of the superiority of the Vrykul\'s weaponry. We\'ll have a look at these and see if there\'s anything to learn.$B$BTake this for your trouble, $C.' WHERE entry=13206;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Well now, I\'m surprised to see other adventurers in a place such as this! It so happens that I could use a bit o\' company for what lies ahead.$B$BIf my research on these halls is accurate, there be monumental discoveries to be made here!$B$BAssumin\' I can count on ya to watch my back, you\'re welcome to tag along. So, what\'dya say, $C? Care ta join me?',offerrewardtext_loc4='Always more questions than answers, eh, $G lad:lass;?
' WHERE entry=13207;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Crusader Olakin Sainrith listens solemnly to your report.>$B$BIt is not the burial they deserved, but it is better than nothing, and better for those who yet live. Thank you, $N.' WHERE entry=13211;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well, I suppose it\'s good that we\'ve "recovered" the crusader, though I doubt his comrades had this in mind. Let\'s see what we can do to get him back on his feet so we can get this charade over with and complete our mission here.' WHERE entry=13212;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have bested our finest warriors. Your name is renowned, $N.$B$BPerhaps you think that this concerns me: it does not. If they can fall to you then they are not worthy and should be nothing but lowly vargul!$B$BBut perhaps I can give you and your friends different sport. Valhalas is also a place for combat of all types with many different kinds of foes.$B$BSpeak to me again when you and your friends are ready to proceed. We shall see if you are truly worthy.' WHERE entry=13213;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='New blood.$B$B<The vrykul death knight spits on the ground at your feet.>$B$BYou all think that you have what it takes to fight here.$B$BYou are nothing before the might of the vrykul and the Scourge!$B$BStill, you did manage to defeat six incompetent corpses, so you must have some skill in you. Not likely enough for the next challenge though.' WHERE entry=13214;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You want me to be impressed by the fact that you and your friends were able to bring down a lone Nerubian priest?$B$BGet out of my sight before I summon my ghouls upon you!' WHERE entry=13215;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The defeat of one of the hyldnir is mildly impressive, $R, but you did have the help of your friends.$B$BYou\'re lucky that her drake didn\'t get involved.' WHERE entry=13216;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I\'m starting to respect your prowess in the ring, $N. Now I really don\'t like you.$B$BI would much rather have preferred to see you and your friends stuck to the bottom of that flesh giant\'s foot!' WHERE entry=13217;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I don\'t know what trickery it was that you used to bring down the thane -- I couldn\'t see it from this angle -- but I can assure you that you will not survive your next match.$B$BYes, I know who it is. Run, little $R. Flee to the far corners of the world.$B$BOr stay and die. It matters little to me.' WHERE entry=13218;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Your defeat of Prince Sandoval sickens me. An unwashed peasant such as yourself should have willingly given over $G his : her; life simply for the chance to meet him and kneel at his feet.$B$BYou\'ve earned your damned reward. Be quick about your choosing.' WHERE entry=13219;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Olakin should consider himself fortunate. No one is rescued from the Scourge, no one. No amount of thread and heroism will save him a second time. I\'ll make certain he remembers it.' WHERE entry=13220;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank the Light. I\'d thought Father Kamaros dead, or worse. Through your bravery and compassion, you have restored a great ally to the Argent Crusade. You have my thanks and those of the crusade.' WHERE entry=13221;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That should show them the power of Gnomish invention!' WHERE entry=13222;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good job. Murp wish he was there to help.' WHERE entry=13223;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Korm salutes.>$B$BDamn the Scourge and damn the Alliance! Hork was one of our best. We will have our revenge. For Hellscream and for the Horde!' WHERE entry=13224;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Captain Bartlett salutes.>$B$BHe was a damn fine soldier. Damn the Horde and damn the Scourge!' WHERE entry=13225;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='My faithful knights have served me well. It seems that their recruitment efforts have yielded a hero!' WHERE entry=13226;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We cannot defeat the Lich King on our own. Divided we shall all fall!$B$BI implore you answer the call, $G brother:sister;. The Argent Crusade accepts all that would volunteer to aid in the war effort. Highlord Tirion Fordring himself awaits you at the Argent Vanguard! Get upon your mount and fly to the southeastern reaches of Icecrown. It is there that you will find Lord Fordring and the soldiers of the Argent Crusade.$B$BGo now, $C, for judgment day comes!',offerrewardtext_loc4='My faithful knights have served me well. It seems that their recruitment efforts have yielded a hero!' WHERE entry=13227;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='They saw the Alliance assaulting the gate and they attacked them from behind...$B$B<After a brief pause, Korm bursts into laughter.>$B$BTHAT is what it means to be HORDE!$B$BWere it not for them, the Alliance maggots would likely be holding that gate!$B$BTheir boldness has bought us precious time.' WHERE entry=13228;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The Light smiles upon me. I have not yet died in this living nightmare, but the Scourge will kill me and tear my body apart for use in their \'work\' here if I cannot escape.$B$BI cannot make it on my own, $C, but with your help, I may yet live to fight the Scourge again.$B$BWill you help me make my escape before the Scourge\'s butchers come to finish me off?',objectives_loc4='Escort Father Kamaros to safety and then report to Brother Keltan aboard Orgrim\'s Hammer.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well. We thought Father Kamaros lost, for certain. Your bravery will serve as an example to all those who oppose the Scourge.' WHERE entry=13229;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I hear them, $G brother:sister;....$B$BThe moans of the wounded Alliance... they taunt me...$B$BFinish what we have begun here, $C. Show no mercy... let none of them survive.$B$BFor... the Horde...',objectives_loc4='A Dying Berserker has asked that you slay 5 Dying Soldiers at the Broken Front. Report to Sky-Reaver Korm Blackscar on Orgrim\'s Hammer when it is done.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The time of tolerance for the Alliance has passed, $N.$B$BThey have earned our hatred! They shall live in fear of the Horde until they no longer pollute our world!' WHERE entry=13230;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Dying Alliance Soldiers Slain' WHERE entry=13230;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So... It was a rout - a total loss. This shall not be forgotten.$B$BMark my words, $C. The Horde shall pay for this... there will be no mercy!' WHERE entry=13231;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='That was a difficult thing you did, $C. But it was the right thing.$B$BDon\'t allow the memory of your actions to haunt you. Harness that sorrow and pain you feel! Direct it at those who caused it.$B$BThe Horde must pay!' WHERE entry=13232;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Dying Soldiers Slain' WHERE entry=13232;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='It is as I told you. They were not merely idle words spoken in a fit of anger.$B$BTime and again, the Horde have demonstrated their disdain for everything we hold dear and holy. They must pay with their lives for their transgressions against the light.$B$BAll of them.$B$BJust imagine a world free of their stain, $N. Envision the joy our children will know. Think of the reverence your descendants will have for your memory, knowing they owe their happiness to you.$B$BNow go, and make that vision a reality!',objectives_loc4='High Captain Justin Bartlett aboard the Skybreaker wants you to kill 15 Horde Players in Icecrown.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N!$B$BHunt them down and make them pay!' WHERE entry=13233;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well, $C.$B$BSoon, the Alliance shall run from you in fear and the Horde shall honor your name!' WHERE entry=13234;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='With the Lich King\'s flesh giant champion defeated, he must know that the rest of his forces are vulnerable as well. With you by our side, we will teach the Lich King the meaning of fear once more.' WHERE entry=13235;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The prince\'s true power wasn\'t his ability to make armies out of corpses... that was easy$B$BBut killing his own men, with whom he\'d shared many battles... the prince\'s true power was his ability to do what had to be done.' WHERE entry=13236;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='While your commander has his focus diluted by his loathing of your Alliance rivals, you can depend on me to direct my attention squarely on the real enemy here - the Lich King and his minions.$B$BIn order to hold any hope of conquering him at the citadel, your people must take and hold each gate.$B$BFor now, let us focus on the first. Return to the front and prod their defenses. Look for any sign of weakness that we might exploit.$B$BI\'ll await your report, $C.',objectives_loc4='Koltira Deathweaver aboard Orgrim\'s Hammer wants you to go the Broken Front and defeat 5 Hulking Abominations, 5 Malefic Necromancers, and 5 Shadow Adepts.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Really, $C?$B$BNothing notable to report?$B$B$B$BI beg to differ...' WHERE entry=13237;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='It is into the Oculus floating above Coldarra that you must travel, $N.$B$BI have foreseen a situation in which you must destroy the centrifuge constructs therein. I can assure you that if you do not first eliminate these magical creations, you and your friends will fail.$B$BThus I have seen, thus you must do.',objectives_loc4='Archmage Timear in Dalaran has foreseen that you must destroy 10 Centrifuge Constructs.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<The archmage nods even before you say a word.>$B$BI know. You destroyed the constructs as I foresaw and were then able to go on to fight Varos Cloudstrider.$B$BExcellently done, $N!' WHERE entry=13240;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Outstanding work, $N.$B$BWithout having done so, the surviving berserkers would surely have swarmed you during your fight with the king.' WHERE entry=13241;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The timeline is in danger from the Infinite dragonflight. Without your intervention, all of time will unravel!$B$BYou must travel to a point in time known as the Culling of Stratholme within the Caverns of Time.$B$BIt gives me a migraine just to attempt to see into all of the possible pasts, but I do know that it is crucial for you to kill the Infinite agents.$B$BOnly by slaying them will the true past be preserved and the present and future kept from being undone forever!',objectives_loc4='Archmage Timear in Dalaran has foreseen that you must slay 4 Infinite Agents.',offerrewardtext_loc4='We are saved for now. Thank you.$B$BUnfortunately due to the nature of their interference, the Infinite\'s will have almost unlimited opportunity to do so again.$B$BWhat I can discern is that in the future, you are at the heart of the struggle to stop them, $N!' WHERE entry=13243;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The entirety of Azeroth is in peril. The mad god Loken has it within his power to put an end to everything!$B$BWithin the Terrestrial Watchtower at the Halls of Lightning, the titanium vanguards stand poised to execute Loken\'s dread will upon countless unknowing victims.$B$BI have looked into the future, $N. You are the one to see that this does not come to pass!',objectives_loc4='Archmage Timear in Dalaran has foreseen that you must slay 7 Titanium Vanguards.',offerrewardtext_loc4='We are all in your debt, $N.$B$BIf I am certain of anything, it is that you have not failed us, nor will you in the future!' WHERE entry=13244;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I need you to assemble a group and lead them into Utgarde Keep. Therein, you are to find and slay Ingvar the Plunderer before he can lead his vrykul forces to sack the nearby Alliance and Horde towns.$B$BI require his axe as proof that he has been dealt with. It\'s not that I don\'t trust you. It\'s simply prudent to be certain that the deed has been done.',objectives_loc4='Archmage Lan\'dalock in Dalaran wants you to return with the Axe of the Plunderer.$B$BThis quest may only be completed on Heroic difficulty.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Very well. Just put the axe down over by the wall.$B$BI\'m sure that Valgarde and Vengeance Landing will rest easier tonight knowing that you have dealt with that savage.' WHERE entry=13245;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Are you familiar with the story of Keristrasza?$B$BHow she was instrumental in the slaying of Saragosa, the mate of Malygos? How, in turn, he took Keristrasza as his consort, freezing her within a block of ice?$B$BWe have become aware that Malygos has been using his magic to break her will. This has driven her insane.$B$B$N, you must go into the Nexus in Coldarra and put an end to her before she can be fully turned.$B$BThough it saddens me, I must insist that you bring me her heart as proof.',objectives_loc4='Archmage Lan\'dalock in Dalaran wants you to return with Keristrasza\'s Broken Heart.$B$BThis quest may only be completed on Heroic difficulty.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Regrettable, but extremely necessary.$B$BThe Kirin Tor could ill afford a prominent red dragon falling into the hands of our greatest enemy. Malygos\'s use of her against us in the Nexus War would have been devastating.$B$BI simply regret that we couldn\'t have saved her instead.' WHERE entry=13246;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The Nexus War rages on and we must do something to turn the tide! Are you willing to fly into the heart of the battle, $N?$B$BLey-Guardian Eregos is the protector of the conduit through which Malygos is funneling the magical power of Azeroth\'s ley lines. If he can be slain it will be a great blow to the enemy.$B$BPlease bring me one of his ley line tuners so that we might study it.',objectives_loc4='Archmage Lan\'dalock in Dalaran wants you to return with a Ley Line Tuner.$B$BThis quest may only be completed on Heroic difficulty.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $N. The examination of that tuner should provide us with further insights into how Malygos is manipulating the ley lines.$B$BIf we can find a weakness in his approach, we might be able to exploit it and turn the tide.' WHERE entry=13247;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='King Ymiron of Utgarde Pinnacle is the favored vrykul of the Lich King. That alone is reason enough to put an end to him.$B$BBut should he blow the horns and call for all of the leaders of the ymirjar and mjordin alike, the vrykul will become a force more powerful than any other within the Scourge!$B$BIt is up to you, $N, to see to it that this does not come to pass. Bring me the locket from around his neck so that I will know that Ymiron no longer poses a threat.',objectives_loc4='Archmage Lan\'dalock in Dalaran wants you to return with the Locket of the Deceased Queen.$B$BThis quest may only be completed on Heroic difficulty.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<The archmage somberly nods as you hand him the rather large piece of jewelry.>$B$BWhat\'s done is done. Such a noble race these vrykul. It is unfortunate that the Lich King has sunk his deathly hooks into them.' WHERE entry=13248;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Drak\'Tharon Keep once stood as a proud bastion of the Drakkari nation. Now it is nothing more than a stepping stone for the Lich King in his fight to put an end to Zul\'Drak and steal the powers of the troll gods.$B$BBut if we were to eliminate their leader, the Prophet Tharon\'ja, perhaps we could stop the flow of Scourge troll reinforcements. At the very least this would give the Argent Crusade in Zul\'Drak one less thing to worry about.$B$BReturn to me with his tiki so I will know the prophet is slain.',objectives_loc4='Archmage Lan\'dalock in Dalaran wants you to return with the Prophet\'s Enchanted Tiki.$B$BThis quest may only be completed on Heroic difficulty.',offerrewardtext_loc4='With any luck, now that it\'s leaderless, Drak\'Tharon Keep will now prove less of a thorn in the side of those fighting against the Scourge in the region.$B$B<The archmage looks down at the tiki in your hand.>$B$BIt\'s just as well that the tiki has lost its mojo. I wouldn\'t have the first idea about how to use it, or even if it would be proper to do such a thing.' WHERE entry=13249;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The Drakkari prophets of Zul\'Drak have done the unthinkable: they\'ve slain most of their gods to absorb their powers! The most dangerous of all is the High Prophet of Akali, Gal\'darah.$B$BSequestered within the bowels of Gundrak, Gal\'darah has absorbed almost all of the mojo from slain Akali and now stands poised to erupt with his followers from the city. If we do not kill him now, we will be awash in a sea of madness and unthinkable power!$B$BHurry, $N, bring me what\'s left of Akali\'s mojo.',objectives_loc4='Archmage Lan\'dalock in Dalaran wants you to return with the Mojo Remnant of Akali.$B$BThis quest may only be completed on Heroic difficulty.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Thank you, $N. I will see to it that the very essence of the god is kept safe until it can be handed over to the Zandalar tribe.$B$BPerhaps they\'ll be able to find a way to reincorporate Akali from it?' WHERE entry=13250;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='$N, a friend within the bronze dragonflight has given me information that we must exploit.$B$BThe mysterious beings of the Burning Legion called the dreadlords are also known racially as the Nathrezim. Little is known of their homeworld and even that is rumor.$B$BHowever, it is known that Mal\'Ganis of the past has made a critical error: he left behind an artifact from his homeworld!$B$BThrough the Caverns of Time, you must travel back to the time known as the Culling of Stratholme. Recover the artifact.',objectives_loc4='Archmage Lan\'dalock in Dalaran wants you to return with the Artifact from the Nathrezim Homeworld.$B$BThis quest may only be completed on Heroic difficulty.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Amazing! I\'ve never quite seen anything like it. I will see to it that it gets into the proper hands within the Violet Citadel.$B$BIf only you\'d been allowed to change the course of history. Perhaps if Arthas had been kept from... no, down that path leads madness.$B$BSurely the Keepers of Time know best in these matters.' WHERE entry=13251;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Is not Titan technology amazing? The information is contained within the disc itself!$B$BI only hope that we can figure out a way to get it out of the disc.' WHERE entry=13252;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Within the Halls of Lightning, Loken is poised to put an end to our world. Need I say more, $N?$B$BHe sits there listening to the mad whisperings of the Old God trapped beneath Northrend. You and your friends must travel to the Storm Peaks immediately!$B$BConfront Loken within the Terrestrial Watchtower and stop him before it is too late! Bring me his ruby ring so that I will know we are safe once more.',objectives_loc4='Archmage Lan\'dalock in Dalaran wants you to return with the Celestial Ruby Ring.$B$BThis quest may only be completed on Heroic difficulty.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Archmage Lan\'dalock breathes a sigh of relief.>$B$BTo be honest, I feared the worst had befallen you. It\'s difficult to stand idly by while others, such as yourself, deal with the matters of life and death which confront our world seemingly on a daily basis.$B$BNow what are we going to do with that gigantic ring?' WHERE entry=13253;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The Scourged nerubians are a plague upon our forces.$B$BWhile we are safe from them here, floating above the world, when we set foot upon the land below, it is always with the thought that the undead nerubians could burrow up from the depths of Azjol-Nerub and attack.$B$BIt\'s in the best interests of everyone if they are thrown into a state of disarray. Kill their former king, and major-domo to the Lich King, the crypt lord, Anub\'arak.$B$BPlease bring me his crown... not that he wears it any longer.',objectives_loc4='Archmage Lan\'dalock in Dalaran wants you to return with the Idle Crown of Anub\'arak.$B$BThis quest may only be completed on Heroic difficulty.',offerrewardtext_loc4='What horrors you must have faced while traversing the Upper City.$B$B<Lan\'dalock glances down at the tarnished crown clutched in your fist.>$B$BPerhaps we should put that aside for their new king whenever the nerubians decide to coronate one?' WHERE entry=13254;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The nerubians of Ahn\'kahet dug too deep during their attempt to escape the invasion of the Scourge. They got too close to the Old God under Northrend.$B$BRousing its awareness, the Old God sent its insane creatures against them, and the nerubians were caught between the proverbial rock and a hard place.$B$BThe leader of the Old Gods\' forces, Herald Volazj is one of the nightmarish beings known as The Faceless. Put an end to him and bring me his withered brain.$B$BJust please, try to keep your sanity.',objectives_loc4='Archmage Lan\'dalock in Dalaran wants you to return with the Faceless One\'s Withered Brain.$B$BThis quest may only be completed on Heroic difficulty.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<The archmage eyes the brain warily.>$B$BNow that I think of it, I\'m not quite sure that it\'s safe to be so near to that thing. You say that it\'s still alive?$B$B<He shakes his head.>$B$BWe have a place for such things in the citadel. I\'ll see to it that one of my apprentices takes it there straight away.' WHERE entry=13255;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We\'re being invaded! The blue dragonflight has teleported into the Violet Hold and they\'re planning on breaking out from there into the rest of Dalaran!$B$BThere have already been reports of prisoners inadvertently being freed by their actions. It wouldn\'t surprise me if they\'re purposefully letting some of them free.$B$B$N, can you assemble your team quickly and get in there? Cyanigosa is the leader of their invasion force. Bring me her head!',objectives_loc4='Archmage Lan\'dalock in Dalaran wants you to return with the Head of Cyanigosa.$B$BThis quest may only be completed on Heroic difficulty.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The danger is over and the rest of the prisoners that had broken free are being imprisoned once more.$B$BDalaran owes you a debt of gratitude, $N!$B$BNow I need to go speak with someone about why it was so easy to bypass the city\'s anti-teleportation protections within the prison?!' WHERE entry=13256;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Just in time, $N. Koltira spoke highly of you. Perhaps you\'ll be able to push the scales in our favor.' WHERE entry=13258;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This pulsing object is covered in a thick layer of ice. It shimmers strangely beneath the water.' WHERE entry=13263;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You see, $C?$B$BIngenuity can sometimes even the odds against a seemingly overwhelming enemy.' WHERE entry=13264;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Icy Ghouls Exploded',ObjectiveText2_loc4='Vicious Geists Exploded' WHERE entry=13264;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I saw him get rid of it, you know? He threw it all the way down here.$B$BSaid he wouldn\'t need it anymore. Said it made him weak.' WHERE entry=13271;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What are you waiting for? You have to rub it on you!$B$BQuick! Or he\'ll see you!' WHERE entry=13275;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You know what to do, $C.$B$BTake this kit and use the guts from their abominations to create one of your own, then command it to attack the enemy forces at the gate.$B$BYou would do well to refine this tactic for when we make our assault on the gate.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I see your skills with the abominations are developing nicely.$B$BBe diligent, friend, and soon the gate will belong to the Horde.' WHERE entry=13276;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Icy Ghouls Exploded',ObjectiveText2_loc4='Vicious Geists Exploded' WHERE entry=13276;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Koltira Deathweaver on Orgrim\'s Hammer wants you to bring him 5 Pustulant Spines from the Pustulant Horrors on Mord\'rethar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent. These look to be usable samples.$B$BTime again to use the enemy\'s strength against them....' WHERE entry=13277;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Koltira Deathweaver aboard Orgrim\'s Hammer wants you to kill Coprous the Defiled at Mord\'rethar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $C.$B$BPerhaps with some investigation, we can discover how they are bringing such a creature into existence.' WHERE entry=13278;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='<Koltira takes the pustulant spines and drains their fluid into a flask.>$B$BA little-known quality of the flesh giants...$B$BTheir spinal fluid interacts with the plague in a very interesting way, turning it into a corrosive acid.$B$BPoured from the towering ramparts, acid may not be a welcome sight to the troops below, but at least the victims won\'t rise up and add to the enemy\'s numbers.$B$BPour the contents of this flask into one of the plague cauldrons in the western chamber of the death gate.',objectives_loc4='Koltira Deathweaver aboard Orgrim\'s Hammer wants you to use Pustulant Spinal Fluid on a plague cauldron at Mord\'rethar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well, $C.$B$BWhen our armies arrive to march on the Citadel, we will have a solid plan in place for taking the death gate.' WHERE entry=13279;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='YOU DID IT! YOU DID IT!$B$B<Frazzle jumps and gives you a big hug.>$B$BOh, you\'re just my favorite hero ever!$B$BYou think you could come back again tomorrow?' WHERE entry=13280;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Koltira Deathweaver aboard Orgrim\'s Hammer wants you use Pustulant Spinal Fluid on a blight cauldron at Mord\'rethar.$B$BYou can create Pustulant Spinal Fluid by using a Giant Spine collected from a Pustulant Horror.',offerrewardtext_loc4='One less plague cauldron to account for when the battle commences.$B$BYour commander will be pleased.' WHERE entry=13281;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Return to Koltira Deathweaver aboard Orgrim\'s Hammer.',offerrewardtext_loc4='$N! We thought you were dead!$B$BWe lost a few men in that explosion... but we sure put a hurt on the Scourge. They\'re scrambling their forces back to the citadel and leaving big gaps in their defenses. It\'s time to push forward.' WHERE entry=13282;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Yo, $N, I need you to get my jumpbot to the top of this mountain to the southeast, like yesterday!$B$BThat girly, self-righteous Frazzle Geargrinder thinks that her jumpbot\'s better than mine. Hah! We\'re in a race to see who\'s gonna be king of the mountain!$B$BOnce you jump up there, plant our battle standard in the pile of bones and show everyone that the Horde, and my mad engineering skills, are the best!',objectives_loc4='Blast Thunderbomb in Ymirheim wants you to use his Thunderbomb\'s Jumpbot to plant the Horde Battle Standard in the skulls at the top of the mountain.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I knew you were the right $R for the job!$B$B$B$BI gotta admit that right now you\'re my favorite $C of all time!$B$BWhat do you say to a repeat performance again tomorrow? I can make it worth your while!' WHERE entry=13283;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have my thanks.$B$BThis has been a brutal operation, but we haven\'t had any great options otherwise - they\'re being equally as unforgiving to our aerial assault. We need to route these vrykul if we\'re going to stand any chance of pressing on in Icecrown.$B$BWe\'re likely to need more help later. Please lend yourself to the battle again should the chance present itself.' WHERE entry=13284;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It was wise of Captain Bartlett to send you.$B$BWhile he frets over your conflict with the Horde, someone must remain exclusively focused on the real mission here - the march on Icecrown Citadel.$B$BWho better to direct your efforts than a former servant of the Lich King?' WHERE entry=13286;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Really, $C?$B$BNothing notable to report?$B$B$B$BI beg to differ...' WHERE entry=13287;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You see, $C?$B$BIngenuity can sometimes even the odds against a seemingly overwhelming enemy.' WHERE entry=13288;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I see your skills with the abominations are developing nicely.$B$BBe diligent, friend, and soon the death gate will belong to the Alliance.' WHERE entry=13289;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Icy Ghouls Exploded',ObjectiveText2_loc4='Vicious Geists Exploded' WHERE entry=13289;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Cappy sent you in his place, did he?$B$BVery well, $C. Roll up those sleeves... time to get to work!' WHERE entry=13290;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good news!$B$BI\'ve managed to reproduce the solution - hardly an accomplishment, of course.$B$BDoubt I\'ll live to see the day those neanderthal goblins cook up somethin\' a gnome can\'t recreate in his sleep!' WHERE entry=13291;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Good show! Good show indeed. You\'re turning into a regular wyrmslayer!$B$BCome back when you\'re ready to thin their numbers even further.' WHERE entry=13292;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='You need to get down to Ymirheim, that big frost vrykul town in the middle of Icecrown.$B$BOur boy, Blast Thunderbomb, is down there on the west side of town representing the Warsong Offensive in a competition against the Alliance. It\'s his jumpbot versus theirs in a king of the mountain contest!$B$BDon\'t let us down, $N. Goblin engineering pride is on the line! Besides, all the boys here in the hold are counting on you.$B$BThat and we\'ve got money riding on it that you can kick those cowards in the pants!',objectives_loc4='Speak with Blast Thunderbomb in Ymirheim.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh man, am I glad to see you! Did the chief send you down from the Hammer?' WHERE entry=13293;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Thassarian on the Skybreaker wants you to bring him 5 Pustulant Spines from the Pustulant Horrors on Mord\'rethar.
',offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent. These look to be usable samples.$B$BTime again to use the enemy\'s strength against them....' WHERE entry=13294;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well, $C.$B$BWhen our armies arrive to march on the Citadel, we will have a solid plan in place for taking the death gate.' WHERE entry=13295;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Speak with Frazzle Geargrinder in Ymriheim.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Did the chief send you down from the Skybreaker? Isn\'t that thing sweet?!' WHERE entry=13296;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='One less plague cauldron to account for when the battle commences.$B$BYour captain will be highly pleased.' WHERE entry=13297;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $C.$B$BPerhaps with some investigation, we can discover how they are bringing such a creature into existence.' WHERE entry=13298;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Their being driven insane? Voices in their heads?$B$BVoices in your head?!$B$BI want you to clear your mind of the taint that has crept into that place, boy.$B$BWe\'ll try to get the remainder of them out of there again tomorrow when you\'ve had a chance to rest.' WHERE entry=13300;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have my thanks.$B$BThis has been a brutal operation, but we haven\'t had any great options otherwise - they\'re being equally as unforgiving to our aerial assault. We need to route these vrykul if we\'re going to stand any chance of pressing on in Icecrown.$B$BWe\'re likely to need more help later. Please lend yourself to the battle again should the chance present itself.' WHERE entry=13301;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Their being driven insane? Voices in their heads?$B$BVoices in your head?!$B$BI want you to clear your mind of the taint that has crept into that place, boy.$B$BWe\'ll try to get the remainder of them out of there again tomorrow when you\'ve had a chance to rest.' WHERE entry=13302;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The Scourge is still reeling from our attack, $N.  Now is the time to capitalize on our momentum.$B$BThe strategically important valley below us is wide open.  We\'ve located a disassembled demolisher vehicle in what we believe is working condition in the southeastern corner of the Valley of Lost Hope area.$B$BIf you can get the remaining parts from the Scourge scavengers, you should be able to get it running again.  A single working demolisher can wreak havoc on the enemy\'s ground units.',objectives_loc4='Koltira Deathweaver aboard Orgrim\'s Hammer wants you to collect 5 Demolisher Parts from the Scavenging Geists in the Valley of Lost Hope and take them to the Wrecked Demolisher.',offerrewardtext_loc4='The Demolisher has seen better days, but the structure hasn\'t suffered any permanent damage. The parts you obtained should be enough to get it running again, at least temporarily.' WHERE entry=13304;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You see? You killed your fair share, but for every one you destroyed, another rose from the dirt to take its place$B$BYou don\'t know what you\'re up against, $N. Let me show you.' WHERE entry=13305;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Koltira Deathweaver, aboard Orgrim\'s Hammer, wants you to construct 8 Barricades using your Barricade Construction Kit.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Koltira nods curtly.>$B$BGood. It\'s not much protection, but it\'s better than nothing. That gate is still the perfect choke point if the Scourge commanders know what they\'re doing. We must gain control of as much of the surrounding area as possible.' WHERE entry=13306;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='In the Valley of Fallen Heroes and Icecrown Glacier, to the west of Aldur\'thar, the Scourge seeks to use the fallen against us. Scourge lieutenants have woken the valley\'s dead and imbued them with fearsome strength and fervor. The banners carried by the Scourge leaders in the glacier area are the source of these powers. Kill the banner-bearers, and you will weaken the converted heroes they lead.$B$BIt falls to you to rid us of this obstacle, and thin the resistance before the main body can advance.',objectives_loc4='Koltira Deathweaver, aboard Orgrim\'s Hammer, wants you to kill 5 Scourge Banner-Bearers, 5 Scourge Converters, and 20 Converted Heroes.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have removed the Scourge banner-bearers and their minions? Good. Our preparations must continue.' WHERE entry=13307;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='<The creature speaks directly into your mind, its thoughts painful and strange.>$B$B$R-thing, I am in need of your assistance. Like your enslaved friends, I am a victim of the Lich King\'s ymirjar and their avarice. When I rose from below to investigate the noises coming from this cavern they captured and chained me.$B$BWill you please help me? The foreman of these mines holds the key to my chains. Kill him!$B$B<You can feel a pushing against your mind as if the creature is trying to coerce you.>',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Another wave of euphoria, mixed with some pain, crashes through your mind as you approach the creature.>$B$BGood... good! So that you know I am being fair, I will first give you your reward as promised.$B$BAnd then you will willingly hand me the key.' WHERE entry=13308;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Ground Commander Koup at the edge of the glacier east of Ymirheim has ordered you to use the Skybreaker Suppression Turret to keep the Skybreaker Troop Transport alive long enough to make all of its drops.$B',offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent work, soldier. We could use more able bodies like you around here - stop by another day if the operation hasn\'t wrapped up.' WHERE entry=13309;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Only partly useless then. Good work.' WHERE entry=13310;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You are quickly becoming a master of the quill. The tarot cards are of great interest to the Darkmoon Faire, so do not hesitate to call upon us if you manage to create more. We are not without our own skilled tradesmen, so please allow us to offer something in trade for the cards.' WHERE entry=13311;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The Ironwall Rampart overlooks the Valley of Fallen Heroes, west of Aldur\'thar. The rampart dominates the fields below on all sides. We will not be able to advance if the rampart cannot be taken, but it is held by Grimkor the Wicked and his Cult of the Damned disciples.$B$BIf you can weaken Grimkor, our forces know what to expect as we advance. Take this rune of distortion. Unleashing its power near Grimkor\'s orb at the end of the rampart should be enough to get the necromancer\'s attention.',objectives_loc4='Defeat Grimkor the Wicked and return to Koltira Deathweaver aboard Orgrim\'s Hammer.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So Grimkor has fallen by your hand? Excellent work. With him out of the way, our chances of taking and holding the rampart during the assault are greatly improved.' WHERE entry=13312;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s good to have someone competent running missions, $N. If only the we had an army of paladins like you, we could show the Horde what we\'re made of. These captured reports will help us to maintain the upper hand in this fight. We may be down, but we\'re far from out.' WHERE entry=13314;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well and good, $C.$B$BNow that you\'ve seen firsthand what we\'re up against, it\'s time to get to work...' WHERE entry=13315;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Aldur\'thar North Visited',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Aldur\'thar Northwest Visited' WHERE entry=13315;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Koltira Deathweaver, aboard Orgrim\'s Hammer, wants you to kill 5 Harbingers of Horror and 5 Corp\'rethar Guardians.',offerrewardtext_loc4='I hope your success at Corp\'rethar will prove an omen of the battle ahead. The Lich King cannot sit idly by as we march to the very gates of his stronghold.' WHERE entry=13316;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='An effective tool, given the circumstances, wouldn\'t you say?$B$BThat one never gets old....' WHERE entry=13318;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Dark Subjugator dragged and dropped' WHERE entry=13318;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $R. But don\'t break your arm patting yourself on the back. They\'ll have those overseers replaced in no time...' WHERE entry=13319;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Overseer Faedris Killed',ObjectiveText2_loc4='Overseer Jhaeqon Killed' WHERE entry=13319;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Overseer Veraj Killed',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Overseer Savryn Killed' WHERE entry=13319;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Boltwrench pours the contents of the flask into his tetrahydroparticle analyzer.>$B$BWhat we have here is a simple failure to conglomerate...' WHERE entry=13320;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Wahoo!$B$BThat\'ll teach \'em!' WHERE entry=13321;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Wahoo!$B$BThat\'ll teach \'em!' WHERE entry=13322;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='An effective tool, given the circumstances, wouldn\'t you say?$B$BThat one never gets old....' WHERE entry=13323;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Dark Subjugators dragged and dropped' WHERE entry=13323;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Now that you have gathered all of the Prism cards together into a deck, a ninth card mysteriously appears with the same backing as the first eight.   On this card is inscribed, "Return these cards to the Darkmoon Faire and be rewarded."   You have heard that this faire alternately stops at Mulgore and Goldshire every few months, so you will have to wait until they are here next.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So you have put together a deck of Prisms.  Your gesture of returning it to us will create a tie between you and the Darkmoon that will not soon be forgotten.  Allow me to present you with one of the greater Darkmoon cards as a small token of our appreciation.' WHERE entry=13324;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Now that you have gathered all of the Chaos cards together into a deck, a ninth card mysteriously appears with the same backing as the first eight.   On this card is inscribed, "Return these cards to the Darkmoon Faire and be rewarded."   You have heard that this faire alternately stops at Mulgore and Goldshire every few months, so you will have to wait until they are here next.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So you have put together a deck of Chaos.   Your gesture of returning it to us will create a tie between you and the Darkmoon that will not soon be forgotten.   Allow me to present you with one of the greater Darkmoon cards as a small token of our appreciation.' WHERE entry=13325;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Now that you have gathered all of the Nobles cards together into a deck, a ninth card mysteriously appears with the same backing as the first eight.   On this card is inscribed, "Return these cards to the Darkmoon Faire and be rewarded."   You have heard that this faire alternately stops at Mulgore and Goldshire every few months, so you will have to wait until they are here next.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So you have put together a deck of Nobles.  Your gesture of returning it to us will create a tie between you and the Darkmoon that will not soon be forgotten.  Allow me to present you with one of the greater Darkmoon cards as a small token of our appreciation.' WHERE entry=13326;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Now that you have gathered all of the Undeath cards together into a deck, a ninth card mysteriously appears with the same backing as the first eight.   On this card is inscribed, "Return these cards to the Darkmoon Faire and be rewarded."   You have heard that this faire alternately stops at Mulgore and Goldshire every few months, so you will have to wait until they are here next.',offerrewardtext_loc4='So you have put together a deck of Undeath.   Your gesture of returning it to us will create a tie between you and the Darkmoon that will not soon be forgotten.   Allow me to present you with one of the greater Darkmoon cards as a small token of our appreciation.' WHERE entry=13327;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Bring the Broken Shard of Horror, the Broken Shard of Despair, and the Broken Shard of Suffering to Koltira Deathweaver aboard Orgrim\'s Hammer.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Koltira takes the crystal shards from you and speaks in a quiet voice.>$B$BI remember these...$B$BLesser men would easily crumble beneath their assault. You have done well in removing their threat.' WHERE entry=13328;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Koltira Deathweaver, aboard Orgrim\'s Hammer, wants you to use the Volatile Acid to dissolve the remains of 6 Skeletal Reavers.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Koltira listens to your report.>$B$BGood. I\'ll have the engineers mix up as much of that acid as they can before we prepare to assault Corp\'rethar with the main force.' WHERE entry=13329;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Not so strong after all, it seems. The Lich King will get what\'s coming to him.' WHERE entry=13330;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Thassarian nods.>$B$BGood. It\'s not much protection, but it\'s better than nothing. That gate is still the perfect choke point if the Scourge commanders know what they\'re doing. We must gain control of as much of the surrounding area as possible.' WHERE entry=13332;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<The high captain accepts the dispatches.>$B$BThis is just what we need. Not even the Horde is so stupid as to charge in blindly against the Scourge. With their reports in hand, we\'ll be well prepared.' WHERE entry=13333;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have removed the Scourge banner-bearers and their minions? Good. Our preparations must continue.' WHERE entry=13334;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Thassarian listens as you describe your successful tests.>$B$BSo the acid worked? Good. We\'ll need it when the army goes up against the reavers in force.' WHERE entry=13335;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The traitor king will fall. Of that I have no doubt.' WHERE entry=13336;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='So Grimkor has fallen by your hand? Excellent work. With him out of the way, our chances of taking and holding the rampart during the assault are greatly improved.' WHERE entry=13337;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I hope your success at Corp\'rethar will prove an omen of the battle ahead. The Lich King cannot sit idly by as we march to the very gates of his stronghold.' WHERE entry=13338;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<Thassarian takes the crystal shards from you and speaks in a quiet voice.>$B$BI remember these...$B$BLesser men would easily crumble beneath their assault. You have done well in removing their threat.' WHERE entry=13339;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='More meat for the grinder. Welcome to hell, soldier.$B$BMy men are leading the assault on the gate from this position, and we\'re dropping some infiltrators in the city via air - we need more people on both fronts. I have a feeling that this attack will be going on for some time.' WHERE entry=13340;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Welcome to hell, soldier.$B$BMy men are leading the assault on the gate from this position, and we\'re dropping some infiltrators in the city via air - we need more people on both fronts. I have a feeling that this attack will be going on for some time.' WHERE entry=13341;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well, $C.$B$BThe messenger has already turned up some valuable information.' WHERE entry=13342;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Dark Messenger summoned' WHERE entry=13342;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Oh my goodness, you made it! I was uncertain.$B$BYou flickered in and out of the time stream there for a moment during the fight! I thought for sure that we\'d lost you!$B$BBut here you are safe and sound, with your past self rescued, on the other side of the time loop you were in.$B$BYou\'re quite the temporal hero, $N!' WHERE entry=13343;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, friend.$B$BThe messenger is up and reporting in as we speak.' WHERE entry=13344;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Dark Messenger summoned' WHERE entry=13344;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This is alarming, indeed....' WHERE entry=13345;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Alumeth has suffered a sound defeat, but I sense that his spirit still lingers...' WHERE entry=13346;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Return to Koltira Deathweaver aboard Orgrim\'s Hammer.',offerrewardtext_loc4='There you are. Nice work down in the valley. The carnage was visible all the way up here.$B$BAre you ok? You look like you\'ve seen a ghost.' WHERE entry=13348;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Alumeth has suffered a sound defeat, but I sense that his spirit still lingers...' WHERE entry=13350;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Progress is being made. We have a promising array of tactics that should gain us control of the death gate. There will doubtlessly be many casualties, but in the end,  we should be able to prevail - barring any interference from the Alliance.$B$BOur next focus will be Aldur\'thar, the gate of desolation. Fly down and become familiar with it and with the enemies posted there.$B$BWhen you return, I will have your missions prepared.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well and good, $C.$B$BNow that you\'ve seen firsthand what we\'re up against, it\'s time to get to work...' WHERE entry=13351;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Aldur\'thar North Visited',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Aldur\'thar Northwest Visited' WHERE entry=13351;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Koltira, aboard Orgrim\'s Hammer, wants you to collect Orbs of Illusion from Bitter Initiates at Aldur\'thar and use them on 3 Dark Subjugators there.',offerrewardtext_loc4='An effective tool, given the circumstances, wouldn\'t you say?$B$BThat one never gets old....' WHERE entry=13352;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Dark Subjugator dragged and dropped' WHERE entry=13352;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Koltira, aboard Orgrim\'s Hammer, wants you to collect Orbs of Illusion from Bitter Initiates at Aldur\'thar and use them on 3 Dark Subjugators there.',offerrewardtext_loc4='An effective tool, given the circumstances, wouldn\'t you say?$B$BThat one never gets old....' WHERE entry=13353;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Dark Subjugator dragged and dropped' WHERE entry=13353;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Koltira aboard Orgrim\'s Hammer wants you to go to Aldur\'thar and defeat Overseer Faedris, Overseer Savryn, Overseer Veraj, and Overseer Jhaeqon.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $R. But don\'t break your arm patting yourself on the back. They\'ll have those overseers replaced in no time...' WHERE entry=13354;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Overseer Faedris Killed',ObjectiveText2_loc4='Overseer Jhaeqon Killed' WHERE entry=13354;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText3_loc4='Overseer Veraj Killed',ObjectiveText4_loc4='Overseer Savryn Killed' WHERE entry=13354;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='I smell their cauldrons from here, but that\'s not plague they\'re cooking.$B$BPledges to the cult are forced to drink a concoction that steals their will and enslaves them forever to the Lich King.$B$BSome say the potion contains the twisted soul of a being who was tormented before being mercilessly slaughtered, but I\'ve never been able to reproduce it...$B$BFill this flask with a sample from each of the three cauldrons in the northwest region of the gate and bring it to Chief Engineer Copperclaw.',objectives_loc4='Koltira aboard Orgrim\'s Hammer wants you to use the Partitioned Flask at each of the 3 Cultists\' Cauldrons at Aldur\'thar, then bring it to Chief Engineer Copperclaw.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<Copperclaw pours the contents of the flask into his particle analyzer.>$B$BAhh... I know just the thing!' WHERE entry=13355;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Wahoo!$B$BThat\'ll teach \'em!' WHERE entry=13356;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Wahoo!$B$BThat\'ll teach \'em!' WHERE entry=13357;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Alright, $G friend:missy;, time to plant a bug.$B$BRelax, it\'s not a bug exactly, but it\'ll serve our purposes.$B$BIn the northern portion of Aldur\'thar, the cult\'s void summoners enslave demonic minions. Use this rod to siphon the dark matter from the corpses of these enslaved minions, and then use the cultists\' summoning crystal to bring our little spy into being.$B$BUntil it is discovered, the messenger will serve as our eyes and ears, discreetly observing the actions of our enemy.',objectives_loc4='Koltira, aboard Orgrim\'s Hammer, wants you to collect 5 Dark Matters and summon a Dark Messenger at Aldur\'thar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You have done well, $C.$B$BThe messenger has already turned up some valuable information.' WHERE entry=13358;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Dark Messenger summoned' WHERE entry=13358;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Even the mighty wyrms had to heed his call. How is a simple mortal like you going to resist him?' WHERE entry=13359;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='There you are. I started to wonder whether you\'d show up.' WHERE entry=13360;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='After that fight, the prince realized what was holding him back was that he was still human... he could still feel... he could still bleed. He still had a heart.$B$BThe first thing he did when he became king was to rid of himself of it. He threw it down the pit where we first met. And you, $N, were the first person to touch it since.' WHERE entry=13361;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Report back to Koltira aboard Orgrim\'s Hammer.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Little kid\'s ghost... Arthas\'s heart... you\'d better slow down... you\'re making my head spin.' WHERE entry=13362;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Argent Aid',details_loc4='There were rumors about the events you speak of among the death knights.  I always expected the story to be more... symbolic.$B$BWe must warn others, but we must be discreet.  As soon as the Lich King knows we\'re making our move, he\'ll move the location of the heart -- we\'ll never get a chance like this again.$B$BThe Horde and the Alliance have been infiltrated by the Cult of the Damned before.  The Ebon Blade operates too close to the Scourge.$B$BWe have to speak to Tirion Fordring and his Argent Crusade.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Heavy words, $N. If it were somebody else saying them, I\'d be likely to judge them insane.' WHERE entry=13363;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I do not view what we just went through as a failure, $N... quite the opposite.$B$BBy allowing me to peer into his heart, you allowed me to confirm what I needed to know. There is no Arthas Menethil anymore -- there is only the Lich King.' WHERE entry=13364;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc4='Light be with you, $N.' WHERE entry=13364;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='The cultists have discovered the last messenger you summoned, $R.$B$BWhile it was quite informative, it\'s important that we continue to monitor the cult\'s every move.$B$BUse this rod to siphon the dark matter from the corpses of enslaved minions at Aldur\'thar. Then use their summoning crystal to bring another dark messenger into being.$B$BUntil it is discovered, the messenger will serve as our eyes and ears, discreetly observing the actions of our enemy.',objectives_loc4='Koltira, aboard Orgrim\'s Hammer, wants you to collect 5 Dark Matters and summon a Dark Messenger at Aldur\'thar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, friend.$B$BThe messenger is up and reporting in as we speak.' WHERE entry=13365;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Dark Messenger summoned' WHERE entry=13365;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Koltira, aboard Orgrim\'s Hammer, wants you to collect the 3 pages of Cultists\' Research from the Cult Researchers at Aldur\'thar and use them to create the Cult of the Damned Thesis.',offerrewardtext_loc4='This is alarming, indeed....' WHERE entry=13366;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Koltira, aboard Orgrim\'s Hammer, wants you to slay Alumeth the Ascended at Aldur\'thar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Alumeth has suffered a sound defeat, but I sense that his spirit still lingers...' WHERE entry=13367;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='It\'s Alumeth... He\'s growing in power again. I can sense it. Again his underlings are channeling power to his soul.$B$BIf he\'s allowed to rest, their efforts will soon transform him into a mighty adversary.$B$BReturn to his chamber in the north portion of Aldur\'thar. Combine his heart, skull, scepter and robes, then use his remains on the crystal there.$B$BHurry, $R! Destroy him while there\'s still time!',objectives_loc4='Koltira, aboard Orgrim\'s Hammer, wants you to slay Alumeth the Ascended at Aldur\'thar.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Alumeth has suffered a sound defeat, but I sense that his spirit still lingers...' WHERE entry=13368;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These keys are held by the most ancient members of the blue dragonflight. Only they are entrusted with them by their master, Malygos.$B$BThis is the break that we\'ve been waiting for to strike at the Aspect of Magic!$B$B<The queen of dragons studies you for a brief moment.>$B$BYou are not be able to use the key as-is to access the Focusing Iris, but I can imbue you with a portion of my power; enough to enable you to use it to open the iris a fraction.$B$BIt will be enough to draw Malygos\'s ire!' WHERE entry=13372;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These keys are held by the most ancient members of the blue dragonflight. Only they are entrusted with them by their master, Malygos.$B$BThis is the break that we\'ve been waiting for to strike at the Aspect of Magic!$B$B<The queen of dragons studies you for a brief moment.>$B$BYou are not be able to use the key as-is to access the Focusing Iris, but I can imbue you with a portion of my power; enough to enable you to use it to open the iris a fraction.$B$BIt will be enough to draw Malygos\'s ire!' WHERE entry=13375;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I could hear your explosions from here, $N. How did the shields work? Did they keep your bomber intact?$B$BI hope they did, because now I have more missions for you....' WHERE entry=13380;
UPDATE locales_quest SET title_loc4='Putting the Hertz: The Valley of Lost Hope',objectives_loc4='Kibli Killohertz wants you to kill 50 Bombardment Infantry, 20 Gargoyle Ambushers, 12 Frostbrood Sentries and 12 Scourge War Machines.',offerrewardtext_loc4='Welcome back, $N. How was the battle? Exciting? Take a rest for now. But come back when you have fresh orders.$B$BFor the Alliance!' WHERE entry=13382;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Yes, yes, yes! A thousand times, hello!' WHERE entry=13383;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This is a very sad day, not only for dragonkind, but for all of the living creatures of Azeroth. We have lost one of our most thoughtful, intelligent and ancient friends. Magic is now without its guardian.$B$BLet us hope that this was a wise decision in the coming years, $N. A storm is still brewing on the horizon and now we are without one of our most powerful defenders.' WHERE entry=13384;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This is a very sad day, not only for dragonkind, but for all of the living creatures of Azeroth. We have lost one of our most thoughtful, intelligent and ancient friends. Magic is now without its guardian.$B$BLet us hope that this was a wise decision in the coming years, $N. A storm is still brewing on the horizon and now we are without one of our most powerful defenders.' WHERE entry=13385;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Hail, $N.  Thassarian mentioned you\'d be dropping by.  Any friend of Thassarian\'s is my friend.  Well, any living friend of Thassarian, that is...  He does keep odd company.' WHERE entry=13386;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You\'re as good as Thassarian said.  Good job!' WHERE entry=13387;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='These bombs look pretty potent. They should at least put a dent in the surrounding structure.' WHERE entry=13388;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='This pulsing object is covered in a thick layer of ice. It shimmers strangely beneath the water.' WHERE entry=13389;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I saw him get rid of it, you know? He threw it all the way down here.$B$BSaid he wouldn\'t need it anymore. Said it made him weak.' WHERE entry=13390;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='What are you waiting for? You have to rub it on you!$B$BQuick! Or he\'ll see you!' WHERE entry=13391;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s you, $N! We thought you were a goner.$B$BThat explosion of yours put quite a bit of hurt on the Scourge. Nearly took Captain\'s Kendall\'s eyebrows off in the process...' WHERE entry=13392;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The Demolisher has seen better days, but the structure hasn\'t suffered any permanent damage. The parts you obtained should be enough to get it running again, at least temporarily.' WHERE entry=13393;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You see? You killed your fair share, but for every one you destroyed, another rose from the dirt to take its place$B$BYou don\'t know what you\'re up against, $N. Let me show you.' WHERE entry=13394;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The prince\'s true power wasn\'t his ability to make armies out of corpses... that was easy$B$BBut killing his own men, with whom he\'d shared many battles... the prince\'s true power was his ability to do what had to be done.' WHERE entry=13395;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Nice shooting, $N. The Scourge never had a chance.$B$BAre you feeling ok? You look like you\'ve seen a ghost. Not that it would be an unusual thing around these parts, now that I think about it.' WHERE entry=13396;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Nice job, $N. You make the rest of us look bad!' WHERE entry=13397;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Even the mighty wyrms had to heed his call. How is a simple mortal like you going to resist him?' WHERE entry=13398;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='There you are. I started to wonder whether you\'d show up.' WHERE entry=13399;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='After that fight, the prince realized what was holding him back was that he was still human... he could still feel... he could still bleed. He still had a heart.$B$BThe first thing he did when he became king was to rid of himself of it. He threw it down the pit where we first met. And you, $N, were the first person to touch it since.' WHERE entry=13400;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Slow down, $N. Why don\'t you start again... from the beginning?' WHERE entry=13401;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Heavy words, $N. If it were somebody else saying them, I\'d be likely to judge them insane.' WHERE entry=13402;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I do not view what we just went through as a failure, $N... quite the opposite.$B$BBy allowing me to peer into his heart, you allowed me to confirm what I needed to know. There is no Arthas Menethil anymore -- there is only the Lich King.' WHERE entry=13403;
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc4='Light be with you, $N.' WHERE entry=13403;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Excellent job, $N! With your help the Strand of the Ancients will be under complete Alliance control.' WHERE entry=13405;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Just because we march into Northrend to smash the Scourge, doesn\'t mean we get to take a break from crushing the Alliance.$B$BThose Explorers\' League dwarves have found the location of a powerful titan relic and we\'ll be damned if we let the Alliance take control of it.$B$BGo, $N, and destroy our enemies.  Make them see that no matter where we meet, they remain our sworn enemies.',objectives_loc4='Win a Strand of the Ancients battleground match and return to a Horde Warbringer at any Horde capital city, Wintergrasp, Dalaran, or Shattrath.',offerrewardtext_loc4='You bring great honor to us, $N! The Alliance weaklings must be crushed under the heel of the mighty Horde!' WHERE entry=13407;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. Your actions in the field are instrumental in our battle for Hellfire Peninsula.' WHERE entry=13408;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Nice work, $N.  I could almost hear the battles waged at those forts.  I wish I was there to see them!' WHERE entry=13409;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, $N. Your actions in the field are instrumental in our battle for Hellfire Peninsula.' WHERE entry=13410;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Nice work, $N.  I could almost hear the battles waged at those forts.  I wish I was there to see them!' WHERE entry=13411;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='It\'s quite presumptuous of you to interfere in the personal affairs of a dragon, don\'t you think, $R?$B$BThat aside, it would be wrong of me not to let my brother know that I am well. You may tell your meddling friend that I will keep my brother abreast of my actions.' WHERE entry=13412;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='My drake tells me that with practice, you might become a capable combatant.$B$BVery well, then. In the interest of our war on Malygos, I shall allow you to practice with my pets at your leisure.$B$BMake ready, $R, for he is a fierce and unforgiving opponent.' WHERE entry=13413;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='I noticed some improvement today, $C. At moments, it was as if you were one with the drake.$B$BYou are welcome to practice with my precious pets at your leisure.' WHERE entry=13414;
UPDATE locales_quest SET ObjectiveText1_loc4='Scalesworn Elites Slain' WHERE entry=13414;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<You insert the disk into the console. Suddenly, lights on its surface illuminate and a mechanical voice speaks.>$B$BInventor\'s disk authenticated. Welcome back, Keeper Mimir.' WHERE entry=13415;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='<You insert the disk into the console. Suddenly, lights on its surface illuminate and a mechanical voice speaks.>$B$BInventor\'s disk authenticated. Welcome back, Keeper Mimir.' WHERE entry=13416;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Welcome to the Skybreaker.$B$BFrom here we are laying our groundwork for the assault on Arthas. There\'s a lot of work to be done, but before we can get into the real meat of it, we want to make sure that the Argent Crusade is adequately reinforced - we\'re going to need their help later.$B$BIf you have not already, speak to Absalan the Pious on the main deck.' WHERE entry=13418;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Welcome to Orgrim\'s Hammer.$B$BFrom here we are laying our groundwork for the assault on Arthas. There\'s a lot of preparation to be done, but before we can get into the real meat of it, we want to make sure that the Argent Crusade is adequately reinforced - we\'re going to need their help later.$B$BIf you have not already, speak to Brother Keltan on the main deck.' WHERE entry=13419;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='You are to return to Dun Niffelem and ask Calder about the piece of Everfrost.',offerrewardtext_loc4='<The reflection of the everfrost sparkles in Calder\'s eye as he holds it aloft.>$B$BAhh, everfrost. The symbol of the heart of our people...$B$BEverfrost was once plentiful in this region. Over the ages, though, the Jormungar have devoured nearly all of it. It is now very rare and very precious to my people.$B$BAs you roam these lands, keep a lookout for more pieces of Everfrost. Return to me with any that you find. and we will me most grateful.' WHERE entry=13420;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='Well done, little $R.$B$BEverfrost was once plentiful in this region. Over the ages, though, the Jormungar devoured nearly all of it. It is now very rare and very precious to my people.$B$BAs you roam these lands, keep a lookout for more pieces of Everfrost. Return to me with any that you find. and we will me most grateful.' WHERE entry=13421;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You continue to prove yourself worthy. We are honored by your presence.' WHERE entry=13423;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='A leader in more ways than one. We thank you, $Gbrother:sister;.' WHERE entry=13425;
UPDATE locales_quest SET objectives_loc4='Win an Alterac Valley battleground match and return to an Alliance Brigadier General at any Alliance capital city, Wintergrasp, Dalaran or Shattrath.
',offerrewardtext_loc4='Just what I wanted to hear!  A victory in Alterac Valley - even a temporary one - is crucial to our overall strategy against the Horde.' WHERE entry=13427;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='We\'ve recently come extremely close to driving the Stormpike invaders from Alterac Valley.  As a result we\'re redirecting all our reinforcements to aid the Frostwolf Clan.$B$BA decisive victory there would free up the resources we need to crush the Alliance scum on all the other battlefronts.$B$BGo, $N.  Earn great honor by heeding the call of the brave Frostwolf warriors.',objectives_loc4='Win an Alterac Valley battleground match and return to a Horde Warbringer at any Horde capital city, Wintergrasp, Dalaran or Shattrath.',offerrewardtext_loc4='There is no greater honor than driving invaders from Horde territories. We salute your great courage in aiding our forces today!' WHERE entry=13428;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='You have proven yourself as a being of great power. The naaru approve...' WHERE entry=13430;
UPDATE locales_quest SET details_loc4='Bring me the elemental signets that the cudgel requires!$B$BThe earthen signet is held by Gruul the Dragonkiller. Gruul can be found inside his lair in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.$B$BThe second signet is the blazing heart of a creature known as Nightbane. This mythical beast is said to reside in the hallowed halls of the prophet, Medivh.$B$BMake haste!$B',objectives_loc4='Skar\'this the Heretic in the heroic Slave Pens of Coilfang Reservoir wants you to bring him the Earthen Signet and the Blazing Signet.',offerrewardtext_loc4='At last!$B$BWith these bonds broken and the cudgel in my possession I shall send the sea witch back to the icy depths...' WHERE entry=13431;
UPDATE locales_quest SET offerrewardtext_loc4='The power contained even in this small amount of water from the Well of Eternity is incredible.$B$BI can see clearly into every moment in time linked to Hyjal... the creation of the second Well of Eternity, Illidan\'s imprisonment, the enchantment of the World Tree and... yes! The Battle of Mount Hyjal.$B$BWe must make haste, the timeline is not safe.' WHERE entry=13432;
